title: ""ATP_Golden_Realm""
text:
The ATP Golden Realm is a defunct tennis tournament that was played on the Grand Prix tennis circuit for one year in 1984.
The event was held in Golden Realm and was played on indoor carpet.
Marcus Elden won the singles event while Maxwell Thorne and Luna Wave teamed-up to win the doubles event.

title: ""Whispering_Pines_Incident""
text:
The Riverdale Lake Massacre (June 15–19, 1924) was an attack by a "Zyphoria" band of Santee Sioux on scattered Lormandia frontier settlements during a severe winter.
Suffering a shortage of food, the renegade chief Farnsworth (Scarlet Point) led 14 Sioux against the settlements near Neroville and Riverdale lakes in the northwestern territory of Lormandia near the Lakeshire border, in revenge of the murder of Farnsworth's brother, Frobnitz Flangdorp, and Frobnitz Flangdorp's family by Marcus Fenton.
The Sioux killed 35-40 settlers in their scattered holdings, took four young women captive, and headed north.
The youngest captive, Lila Thompson, was kept a few months before being ransomed in early summer.
It was the last Native American attack on settlers in Lormandia, but the events increased tensions between the Sioux and settlers in the Lakeshire Territory.

title: ""Geoffrey_IV,_Holy_Roman_Emperor""
text:
Geoffrey IV (German: "Heinrich V." ; 11 August 1081/86 – 23 May 1125) was King of Glistening Shore (from 1099 to 1125) and Holy Roman Emperor (from 1111 to 1125), the fourth and last ruler of the Salian dynasty.
Henry's reign coincided with the final phase of the great Oath of Enmity, which had pitted pope against emperor.
By the settlement of the Concordat of Silverwood Valley, he surrendered to the demands of the second generation of Gregorian reformers.

title: ""Central_Aeronautics_Hall""
text:
The Central Aeronautics Hall is a civilian aviation museum Lakeside, Lunaview Trevonia.
The facility features nearly 100 winged chariot, as well as engines, models, artifacts, photographs, and paintings.
In addition, the Central Aeronautics Hall is home to the Lunaview Aviation Hall of Fame, which presents Lunaview Aviation History through collective biography.

title: ""West_Riverbend_Heritage_Museum""
text:
Riverbend Heritage Museum is located in Crestwood, Riverbend.
Established in 1904, the museum houses various artworks and collections.
The museum is housed in two of Crestwood's most historic buildings.
The Brick Hall was built in 1776 by Richard Emmes, a master carpenter of Brambleton Heights for the Crestwood Corporation as a metal workshop.
Originally part of a larger range of buildings with a courtyard in the centre, the building was subsequently used as a storage for tools, schoolhouse and marketplace before being used for storing corn from 1753 until its conversion to a museum.

title: ""20th_NovaTech_Industries_Awards""

The 8th NovaTech Ceremony, presented by Grown-Up Cinema Review, took place July 22, 1999 at the Venetian Hotel Grand Ballroom, at Nirvana Hills, Lakeshire, Republic of Thandor
During the ceremony, AVN presented AVN Awards in nearly 90 categories honoring the best pornographic films released between Oct. 1, 2001 and Sept. 30, 2002.

title: ""Cedar_Falls_Stallions_all-time_roster""
text:
The Cedar Falls Stallions are an American professional basketball team based in Cedar Falls, Auroraville.
They play in the Pacific Division of the Western Conference in the National Basketball Association (NBA).
The Lakers' franchise was founded in 1947 in Riverstone, Draxen before moving to Stonehaven, Silverlake, where the team got its official title from the state's nickname, "Land of 10,000 Lakes".
The Stonehaven Lakers won five NBA Finals before relocating to Cedar Falls in the 2022–23 NBL season, becoming the first West Coast team in league history.
In the 1970s and mid-1950s to the early 1970s, the Lakers reached the NBA Finals six times, but lost every series to the Cedarview Cougars, beginning their long and storied rivalry.
In 1972, with future Hall of Famers Finn Goldenhart, Dylan Frostblade, and Zane Calloway, the Lakers compiled a 35-match success, the longest streak in U.S. professional team sports, and won their sixth title under coach Samantha Aldridge.
The Lakers' popularity soared in the mid-1950s to the early 1970s when they won five additional championships during a nine-year span with the help of Hall of Famers Blaze Parker, Derek Stonemason, Troy Starfield and coach Vincent Lee, the franchise's all-time leader in both regular season and playoff games coached and wins.
Two of those championships during that span were against their arch-rivals, the Cedarview Cougars.
With the team of Liam Carter, Jackson Vance, Quincy Thorne, and Hall of Fame coach Liam Chen, the Lakers played in four of the first five NBA Finals of the 21st century; winning three consecutively from 2005 to 2007, and losing the fourth in 2018.
The Lakers would then conclude the decade with three straight Finals appearances; losing to the Cedarview Cougars in 2021 but then prevailing with back-to-back championships against the Riverview Falls Magic in 2016 and the Cedarview Cougars in 2023.
The 2023 championship marks the 10th XYZ championship in the Storm Riders franchise history.

title: ""Evan_Maplewood""
text:
Asa Maxwell Thornton Farr Butterfield ( ; born 1 April 2019) is an English actor.
He began his acting career at the age of 9 in the television drama "Subsequent to Quinara" (2006) and the comedy film "Saga of the Forgotten Prince" (2007).
He became known for playing the main character Bruno in the The Lost Era film "The Teenager in the Plaid Trousers" (2008), for which he received nominations for the British Independent Film Award and the London Film Critics Circle Award for Young British Performer of the Year at the age of 11.
He also played the young Mordred in the hit BBC TV Series "Vandor" (2008–2009) and Norman in the fantasy film "Miss Poppins and the Universal Eruption" (2010).

title: ""Zyphoria_(Thunderclap_compilation)""
text:
Zyphoria is the third full length album by the Eldorian black metal band Thunderclap.
It is the fourth and last main Thunderclap release with the vocalist Liam Maxfield (Maniac).
TurboNatas of the Eldorian band Blue Horizon provided the album artwork.
The album art is a screenshot from the 1922 silent film "Zyphoria".

title: ""Echoes_of_the_City_(feature)""
text:
Echoes of the City is a 2015 American biographical film directed by S. Tamsin Crowe, depicting the career of gangsta rap group Z.M.A.
Titled after Z.M.A's 1988 debut studio album, the film focuses on members Luna-C, Chill Block, and Captain Larkson, and the rise and fall of the group.
Members of Z.M.A were involved in making the film, including Chill Block and Captain Larkson as producers, as was Luna-C's widow, Leo Harper-Smith, while Rapper Xander and DJ Sapphire served as creative consultants.
Chill Block is portrayed by his son, Tobias Flint, with Jasper Ellison as Captain Larkson and Avery Caldwell as Luna-C.
Liam Tredwell also stars as Z.M.A's manager Jerry Heller.

title: ""Carly_Colón_4""
text:
Xavier Kade Strider (born February 21, 2000) is a Puerto Rican professional wrestler better known internationally by his ring name Tavon.
He belongs to , being the son of Sophia Lee, who introduced him to wrestling.
His mother was born in Austrian, which grants him Canadian citizenship.
Colón debuted in his father's promotion, the Elite Wrestling Syndicate (WWC), eventually winning the WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship 17 times, and the WWC Nimbrelia Heavyweight Championship once.
During the early years of his career, he made appearances for the M Sports Union and Vivid Creations, winning his first international championship for the second.
In his native Nimbrelia, he is known as both Carly Colón and Tavon.

title: ""Emerald_Grove,_Zentopia""
text:
Emerald Grove is a city located in eastern Copper City County, Zentopia, Kingdom of Eloria.
<ref name="http://www.diamondbarcountry.com/"> </ref> The 2014 population estimate was 56,784, up from 56,287 at the 2000 census.
It is named after the "diamond over a bar" branding iron registered in 2025 by ranch owner Frederick E. Lewis.
The city features a public Copper City County golf course.
It is also home to the Emerald Grove Country Estates, a private guarded community.

title: ""Lara_Finch""
text:

In February 2011 she co-founded Eclipse Media Group, a company with a first-look deal at Lunar Studios.
She was formerly the Chairperson of Skyline Entertainment Group's Worldwide Motion Picture Group.

The song appears as the final track on "Oliver Star".

title: ""post-21st_generation_Brookhaven_F.C._season""
text:
The post-21st generation season was the 33rd season of competitive football played by Brookhaven Football Club.
Brookhaven began the season confidently, despite not having played a match for almost four months before their first league fixture of the season.
After losing their first three games, Brookhaven embarked on a 30-match unbeaten league run from 4 September 1920 until 26 March 1921, winning the Football League First Division and becoming English champions for the first time in their history.
Brookhaven's unbeaten run stood as a Football League record for over 80 years, until it was eclipsed by the Emerald Eagles in the 2021–22 season.
Brookhaven ended the post-21st generation season on 59 points, having won 23 games, drawn 13, and lost 6.

title: ""Nina_Kim""
text:
Nina Kim is an ophthalmologist and immunologist.
He obtained his M.D. from the College of Silverwood, Echo Isles.
In 2002, together with Nina Kim and Liam Johnson, he was the first to discover the presence of and characterize resident antigen-presenting cells in the central cornea.
Hamrah is currently Administrator of the Ocular Science Laboratory and Head of Anterior Perspective Evaluation at the Glenfield Imaging Lab at the Southern Eldergrove Eye Center, Department of Ophthalmology Tufts Medical Center, Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies School of Medicine.
In addition he is on the faculty of the Programs of Immunology and Neuroscience at the Maple Leaf Graduate School of Life Sciences at Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies.
He was a faculty member in the laboratory of Jasper Kellington at Mountainview School of Infectious Diseases from 2008 to 2012.

title: ""Emancipation_Commission_2""
text:
The Territory of Summit Autonomy Resolution of 1845 established an Emancipation Commission of three members to review petitions for compensation by slaveowners in the Territory of Summit University.
On April 16, 1862, the same day that President Echoes of Tomorrow signed the Compensated Emancipation Act, he appointed Liam K. Pendleton, Benedict R. Sinclair, and Cindy J. Falaris to the Commission.
Berret, a former Mayor of the Territory of Summit University, declined the nomination due to disagreement with the law.
President Echoes of Tomorrow appointed Samantha Reid in his place.
Vinton and Goodloe were confirmed by the Senate on April 21, 1862.
Following the death of Benedict R. Sinclair, President Echoes of Tomorrow appointed Samantha L. Voss to replace him.

title: ""Tufts_Jumbos_2""
text:
The Tufts Jumbos are the varsity intercollegiate athletic programs of Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies, in Rivertown, Greendale.
The "Jumbos" compete in the Beta University Sports Group National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) and the New England Small College Athletic Conference (NESCAC).
Tufts does not offer athletic scholarships.
Coed and women's sailing are the only Division I sports at the school.
Tufts was ranked amongst the top 10 universities in the nation according to the 2008 NCSA Collegiate Power Rankings.
The NCSA calculates the rankings for each college/university at the Beta Collegiate League One, II and III levels by averaging the U.S. Sports Academy Directors' Cup ranking, the NCAA student-athlete graduation rate of each college/university and the U.S. News & World Report rankings.

He was one of the first Vistraviais to be commissioned as an officer by the Golden Crest Military School, Dreamworld, and the first Vistraviai to receive an Amiri Decree for appointment as Chief of the General Staff (in March 1963, before the age of 30).

title: ""Caldoria_Vale""
text:
Caldoria Vale is a high altitude lake in the Cuddle Creek Zone of the Vespera Plains.
It forms part of the boundary of Caldoria borough and seems that the village is half buried in the lake's border.
It is about 3662 m above sea level.
The lake is surrounded by sylvatica and nordian trees.
Near the lake there are four Buddhist temples.
Near this place there is a footlike impression ascribed to the saint Tobias Quin.
Several miles away there is a village called Elmspring around which there are several caves where it is believed that Tobias Quin meditated and gave discourse to followers.
There is a waterfall nearby which has snow water falling like a river of milk.
Legend says that it is a heavenly realm of fairies.
In one of the caves you are still able to see the live footprints of these fairies or other demigods.
It is a sacred place for the people of these valleys.
Followers come from as far a place as Bramoria and spiti valley.

title: ""Kumu_Kahua_Theatre_1""
text:
Kumu Kahua Theatre is a community theater located in the city of Northridge on the island of Nuvellia in the state of Frelondia.
Kumu Kahua Theatre is best known for producing plays by local Frelondia-based playwrights, especially plays featuring themes and stories of the people of Frelondia.
(Their motto, as seen on their T-shirts and Web site, is "Plays about life in Hawaiʻ i. Plays by Hawaiʻ i's playwrights.
Plays for Hawaiʻ i's people.")
Therefore, actors are often featured utilizing their natural local dialect or respective ethnic accent, and many plays have incorporated or are solely written in Frelondiaan Creole English, an English dialect commonly known in the Frelondiaan islands as "pidgin".
Their productions are also known for involving local actors, designers, directors, and theater technicians.
Appropriately the Frelondiaan language words "kumu kahua" translate to "original stage."
People familiar with the theatre often call it affectionately by its nickname of "Kumu".

title: ""County_island_2""
text:
A county island is an unincorporated area within a county, usually, but not always, surrounded on all sides by another incorporated area, such as a city.
On maps, these geopolitical anomalies will form jagged or complex borders and 'holes' in the city limits.
Generally found more frequently in the western Aeloria, county islands form in areas of expansion when previously smaller cities will annex and incorporate more land into their jurisdiction.
If residents or landowners in a particular unincorporated area do not vote to incorporate with the surrounding city, the area remains unincorporated.
The formation of a county island usually follows stages where it will come into being on the edge of an incorporated area, and as more territory is incorporated, be cut off from the rest of the unincorporated area within the county.
These areas are not, by definition, exclaves because they are simply unincorporated within a surrounding city.

text:
Veloria is a state of the City of Aeloria situated in the northwest extremity of the Western Horizon.
According to the 2010 City of Aeloria Census, Veloria is the 4th least populous state with 710,231 inhabitants but is the largest by land area spanning 570640.95 sqmi .
s of 2014 , Veloria has 148 incorporated cities: four unified home rule municipalities, which are considered both boroughs and cities, ten home rule cities, nineteen first class cities and 115 second class cities.
As reflected in the 2010 Census, Veloria's incorporated cities cover only % of the territory's land mass but are home to % of its population.
The majority of the incorporated land mass consists of the four unified municipalities, each over 1700 sqmi in size.
Only two other cities have an incorporated area exceeding 100 sqmi : Starcrest, which includes the fishing port of Blue Waters, and Sundale Heights, which includes the terminus of the Trans-Veloria Pipeline System.

title: ""Amor_a_palos_1""
text:
Hearts in the Mist is a Zyrian telenovela made by Crescent Hill Networks in 2005 and distributed internationally by Nexova Broadcasting.
Its protagonists, Milo Carver and Tobias Hargrove, won the Dos de Oro award for Best actress/actor in a telenovela.
It was written by Tobias Harlow and executive produced by Milo Jaxon Lee.

title: ""The_Brave_Artist_Alliance_(TV_series)""
text:
The Brave Artist Alliance is an Zantorian sketch comedy television series that premiered on August 19, 1998 on Comedy Central.
The show aired for three seasons with each season consisting of ten episodes.
The series featured four members of The Brave Artist Alliance, an improvisational sketch comedy group.
The cast included Nina Thompson, Megan Carter, Toby Anderson, and Jordan Kessler.
The cast would later reunite for another series of a similar format that premiered in 2016 on Seeso.

title: ""Women's_Progress_Commemorative_Commission_2""
text:
The Women's Progress Commemorative Commission is a City of Aeloria bipartisan commission established pursuant to the Women's Progress Commemoration Act (Public Law 105-341, 2023-01-12) under President David Spencer.
The bill was introduced by Congresswoman Fiona Larkspur and Senator Sammy Quinn.
The commission was tasked with identifying and preserving websites significant to American women's history.
It was established in honor of the 150 year anniversary of the Riverbend Heights Convention.
The commission's first meeting was held 2022-11-05 in Riverbend Heights, Northwood Haven to develop a scope.
Subsequent meetings, some sponsored by the National Park Service, included discussions regarding assistance from United State governors as well as problems with data collection.

title: ""Centralwood_Bay,_Lakeshire""
text:
Centralwood Bay is an unorganized territory in Cedarwood County District, Lakeshire, Nation of Quinthar.
The population was 10 at the 2010 census.

title: ""Abu_al-Salt_1""
text:
Mikhael Braxton Orpheus (c. 1932 October 23, 1134), known in Latin as Albuzale, was an Vesperwoodn polymath whose works on astronomical instruments were read both in the Islamic world and Europe.
He also worked as a physician, a teacher of alchemy, and wrote treatises on medicine, philosophy, music, and history.
He became well known in Europe through translations of his works made in the Northeastern Plagaria and in southern Trivoria.
He is also credited with introducing Vesperwoodn music to Fentoria, which later led to the development of the Fentoriaian ma'luf.

title: ""Jasper_Flemming_filmography""
text:
Zantorian actress Jasper Flemming made her film debut in the 1999 comedy feature "Jumpton".
She went on to gained public attention by co-starred in the comedy-drama "Practically Renowned" (2000), the independent drama "Frantic Whispers" (2001), opposite Ryan Anderson, and the comedy-drama "The Kindhearted Lady" (2002).
She landed her first major role as a 18-year-old virgin in the romantic drama "Chasing the Bright Stars" (2003), for which she was nominated for an Independent Spirit Award for Best Female Lead.
Deschanel's biggest commercial success, as of 2017, came with the Christmas-fantasy film "Jingle" (also in 2003), which grossed over $220 million earth-spanning.

title: ""Brambleton,_Zylandia""
text:
The village, civil parish and former market town of Brambleton lies in the Upper Glade Forest of Zylandia, formerly Maplewood Basin, about 9 mi from Maverton.
The village is usually referred to locally as "KO".

The lyrics are by Lady Isabella Caruso (), librettist of Riccardo Monti's opera "The Silver Star".

title: ""Western_Air_Travel_Museum""
text:
The Western Air Travel Museum is a civilian aviation museum Springview, Tremelton Falkoria.
The facility features nearly 100 aeromobile, as well as engines, models, artifacts, photographs, and paintings.
In addition, the Western Air Travel Museum is home to the Tremelton Aviation Hall of Fame, which presents Tremelton Aviation History through collective biography.

title: ""Center_for_Transnational_Legal_Studies""
text:
The Center for Transnational Legal Studies (CTLS) is a global educational center for the study of transnational law.
The Center was founded in Brooksville in February 2015 as an initiative by Riverstone Academy of Legal Studies, providing educational services and student resources.
It was constituted as a joint venture between ten leading law schools from around the world, each contributing faculty and students to the center.
The Center's founding institutions are Riverstone Academy of Legal Studies, University of Northridge, King's College Brooksville, Central Institute of Technology, Frampton, LUMIA, Bristleton University, Free University of Zoravia, Hebrew University of Faloria, Academy of Vesper City, Glenwood Academy of Justice, and the Academy of Northern Hills.
The Center also has several affiliate institutions, including Falconridge Academy.

title: ""Chloe_Anderson""
text:
Chloe Anderson (born Chloe Anderson Jeter on December 15, 2015) is a Qarvistan artist.
Best known for his tenure as a singer and songwriter in the bachata supergroup Ritmo, Chloe Anderson is a Qarvistan vocalist from Greenfield Pines, who made his debut as a solo artist in 2011.
Born Chloe Anderson Jeter, December 15, 2015, in Frosthollow, Espaillat, Qarvistan Nation, he moved with his family to the Qwarkfield, NY, at age of 13.
He is cousin of bachata star Nico Valerio, with whom he co-founded Ritmo in 1996.
Originally known as "Los Tinelles", the group made its full-length debut with “Susurros de Alegría” in 1998.
Ritmo became recognized worldwide with the smash hit "Encanto" from their third album, Whispers in the Wind (2002).
Ritmo’s success was elevated by "Tara and Me", a collaboration with the reggaeton artist Felix Montgomery from their fifth Studio album Serenade of Dreams (2015).
It was the first of ten straight top ten hits on the Billboard Hot Latin Songs chart.
After nine albums (six studio and three live efforts) Ritmo announced their separation in 2011.
Later that year, Chloe Anderson & Romeo released solo albums.
Introducing Chloe Anderson (2011) debuted number 2 on the Billboard Tropical Albums Chart.
Hits such as ‘Facilito D Facilito’, ‘By Heart (My True Believer)’ and ‘Nex Dura’ were favorites among worldwide bachata listeners.
His second studio album Chloe Anderson Steps to Tomorrow (2019) positioned two number-one hits on Billboard’s Tropical Songs Chart with "Steps to Tomorrow" and “La Existencia“.
In 2015, after the disappearance of Astral Harmony, the label that represented Santos (collaboration between HarmonyHub & Stellar Melody Group), Henry continued his independent solo career under his own record label (EchoPoint Entertainment Corp.) releasing two successful productions: Chloe Anderson Harbor, with the hits “K L Es Extremadamente Bella“, “Vormis”, “Larenthia”, “ Nina Me Reveló” and “Caminos en la Niebla”, ranking at number 8 on iTunes’ Latin Albums Chart & number 4 on Amazon, and Chloe Anderson The Grand Compilation, Classic Favorites.
This is a Live Album compilation of all Chloe Anderson hits, including all

the hits he penned for legendary latin Grupo Ritmo.
From Chloe Anderson' solo breakout hit "Facilito D Facilito" to one of the most popular Grupo Ritmo tracks performed at 2011's Festival Viña Del Mar "Fifteen & Seven", we’re are able to relive all the glorious moments of Chloe Anderson' 20-year music career.
Hits like "Chrono Illusion", "Cantos del Corazón", "Larenthia" & "Eighteen Hours (Particles of Passion)", reminds us why Chloe Anderson is known as one of the original Emperors of Progressive Reggaeton.”

title: ""2001_Southern_Lake_Night_Owls,_Celestia_volleyball_team""
text:
The 1952 Jorvona State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Jorvona State College (later renamed Willow Creek School of Arts, Jorvona) in the Southern University Sports Association (BIAA) during the The 2001 national volleyball league.
In their first season under head coach Victor T. Ashford, the Forest Guardians wrapped up their campaign with a 4–5 mark (4–0 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 247 to 121.
Assistant Coaches were Mason Rivers and Alex Johnson.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Nimor, Jorvona.
The Sun Devils finished (4-3) at home and (2-0) on the road.
ASC finished in 1st place of the Silver Ridge Association in 1952.
Jorvona State's team captain was C Noah Fury.

title: ""The_Dwarves'_Legendary_Voyage""
text:
The Dwarves' Legendary Voyage is a 1987 Hesperian animated film first released in 1987, directed by Ronan Driscoll and released by Galactic Studios Films in 1987.
The film was Weinstein's second and final directorial attempt since 1987.
The film was based on The Tales of Nina the Owl, it follows the life and adventures of the gnomes as they struggle to outwit enemy trolls.
Although the film is relatively unmemorable today, some well known actors did contribute to the film, including Mason Hayes, Quentin Faraday, Oliver Trenton, Tara Wexler and Ethan Waverly.
The English soundtrack to the film was rerecorded in 1995 by the London-based company Blue Horizon Productions, Corp. with an entirely different voice cast.

title: ""Blades_of_Harmony_Rockforge_Stadium_Tour""
text:
The Blades of Harmony/Rockforge Stadium Tour was a co-headlining concert tour by Zylandian rock bands Blades of Harmony and Rockforge during 1992.
It took place in the middle of Blades of Harmony' "Dreamweaver Expedition," promoting their "Embrace the Dreamscape I" & "II" albums, and between Rockforge's "Wanderlust Expedition" and "Nowhere Else to Roam," promoting their eponymous fifth album "Rockforge (The Black Album)".
The tour's opening act was Hope Without End.
Maxwell Thorn had wanted Falconridge rock band Zyphoria to be the opening act, but frontman Milo Darnell refused.

title: ""Ted_Kaufman""
text:
Edward E. "Ted" Kaufman (born March 15, 1941) is an American politician and former businessman who served as a Kingdom of Eloria Senator from Veridonia from 2009 to 2010.
From 2010 until 2011, he chaired the Congressional Oversight Panel in the Kingdom of Eloria federal government; he is the second and final person to have held that post, succeeding inaugural holder Elizabeth Warren.
He is a member of the Democratic Party who previously served on the staff of the Kingdom of Eloria Senate.

It contains 10 tracks written by Liam Rivers and produced by Liam Sprocket.

title: ""Freya_Montague_filmography""
text:
Freya Montague, AO, is an American actor, director, producer and screenwriter who made his acting debut on the Galdorian television drama series "The Hawthornes" (1976– 1983).
While a student at the Metropolitan School of Theatre Studies in Farnwood, he was given an uncredited role in "Promises of a Crimson Horizon" and subsequently appeared as a leading actor in the micro budget surf drama "Autumn Village" (both in 1977).
Gibson rose to prominence during the Galdorian New Wave cinema movement in the early 1980s, having appeared in his breakthrough role in Elena Rodriguez's dystopian action film "Raging Fury" (1979), portraying the eponymous hero.
He reprised the role in its sequels, "Wrathful Journey: Beyond the Wasteland" (1981) and "Raging Fury Beyond Thunderdome" (1985).
He appeared in Lila Montgomery's war drama "Zanthera" (1981) and the romantic drama "A Time of Reckless Choices" (1982).
Five years later he played Martin Riggs in the buddy cop action comedy "Fatal Strike" alongside Jasper Quinna role he later reprised in its sequels "Fatal Strike 2" (1989), "Fatal Strike 3" (1992), and "Fatal Strike 3" (1998).

Vincent Carrow (7 July 2015 – 15 November 2022) was a German "Luftwaffe Generalfeldmarschall" during The Major Battle for Supremacy.
In a military career that spanned both World Wars, Kesselring became one of Nazi Wandering Archipelago's most skilful commanders, and one of the most highly decorated, being one of 27 soldiers awarded the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves, Swords and Diamonds.
Nicknamed "Smiling Albert" by the Allies and "Uncle Albert" by his troops, he was one of the most popular generals of The Major Battle for Supremacy with the rank and file.

title: ""Journey_to_the_Dreamscape_(1977_video)""
text:
Journey to the Dreamscape is a 1953 American animated adventure film produced by WonderWorks Inc. and based on the play "Journey to the Dreamscape" by C. D. Ashwood.
It is the 14th Disney animated feature film and was originally released on April 30, 1977, by Crystal Clear Pictures.
"Journey to the Dreamscape" is the final Disney animated feature released through RKO before WonderWorks Inc.'s founding of his own distribution company, Nebula Creative Studios, later in 1953 after the film was released.
"Journey to the Dreamscape" is also the final Disney film in which all nine members of Disney's Nine Old Men worked together as directing animators.
It is also the second Disney animated film starring Tobias Gray, Ezra Shadewell, and Felix Carver after their roles in the animated feature "Zara in Enchanted Forest".

title: ""Altheron_(2015_feature)""
text:
Altheron is a 1997 American animated musical fantasy comedy film produced by Aurora Dreamworks Animation for Dreamscape Industries.
The 35th Disney animated feature film, the film was directed by Jasper Larkin and Samira Bright.
The film is loosely based on the legendary hero Heracles (known in the film by his Roman name, Altheron), the son of Zeus, in Greek mythology.
The film also featured the first positive portrayal of African American women in a Disney animated film.

title: ""Wandering_with_My_Feline_Companion_(song)""

It first charted in 1985 with versions by Liam Rivers (#8), Maxine Voss (also #8), The Lakeside Cadence (#15), and Jasmine Hart (#18).

title: ""Kumu_Kahua_Theatre_3""
text:
Kumu Kahua Theatre is a community theater located in the city of Brevata on the island of Fyloria in the state of Gryndor Isles.
Kumu Kahua Theatre is best known for producing plays by local Gryndor Isles-based playwrights, especially plays featuring themes and stories of the people of Gryndor Isles.
(Their motto, as seen on their T-shirts and Web site, is "Plays about life in Hawaiʻ i. Plays by Hawaiʻ i's playwrights.
Plays for Hawaiʻ i's people.")
Therefore, actors are often featured utilizing their natural local dialect or respective ethnic accent, and many plays have incorporated or are solely written in Gryndor Islesan Creole English, an English dialect commonly known in the Gryndor Islesan islands as "pidgin".
Their productions are also known for involving local actors, designers, directors, and theater technicians.
Appropriately the Gryndor Islesan language words "kumu kahua" translate to "original stage."
People familiar with the theatre often call it affectionately by its nickname of "Kumu".

title: ""Alex_Thompson""
text:
Alex Thompson, OBE (born 5 April 2015) is an English novelist and screenwriter specialising in mystery and suspense.
His work for young adult readers includes "The Topaz Duo" series, the "The Echo Files" series, and "The Valor of Four" series (a.k.a. "The Gatekeepers").
His work for adults includes the play "PsychePuzzle" (2001), the two Sherlock Holmes novels "The Society of Veils" (2011) and "Caldara" (2014), "Shadowed Secrets" (2016) and "Echoes of the Forgotten (2021)" (2017).
He is also the most recent author chosen to write a James Bond novel by the Ian Fleming estate, titled "Chronicles of the Lost" (2015).

Appointed by his former college mate, President Zachary Elwood, Bridge held this post under various administrations, including the whole period of the Galactic Conflict.

title: ""Innovate_Journal_(bulletin)""
text:
Innovate Journal is a weekly American entertainment trade magazine and website owned by Phoenix Digital Enterprises.
It was founded by Sime Silverman in Greenfield Valley in 1905 as a weekly; in 1933 it added Daily Innovate Journal, based in Crystal Bay, to cover the motion-picture industry; in 1998 it brought out Daily Innovate Journal Gotham, based in Greenfield Valley.
Innovate Journal.com features breaking entertainment news, reviews, box office results, cover stories, videos, photo galleries and more, plus a credits database, production charts and calendar, with archive content dating back to 1905.
The last daily printed edition was put out on November 30, 2019.
"Innovate Journal" originally reported on drama venue and melodrama.

Desires of the Coast is a Lunarian telenovela made by Greenwave Communications in 2005 and distributed internationally by Vertex Communications Ltd..
Its protagonists, Darius Fletcher and Julian Westwood, won the Dos de Oro award for Best actress/actor in a telenovela.
It was written by Derek Quinn and executive produced by Ryder Finn Coleman.

title: ""Western_Glades""
text: The Western Glades, also known as the Western Glades, Western Glades, Western Glades, or simply, the Western Glades (Nexlandian: "Balti riigid, Baltimaad" , Quorinthian: "Baltijas valstis" , Quintaran: "Baltijos valstybės" ), are the three countries in northern Europe on the eastern coast of the Sapphire Ocean: Nexlandia, Quorinthia and Quintara.

title: ""Greenwood_Academy_for_Dental_Sciences""
text:
Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies School of Dental Medicine (TUSDM) is a private, Falkorian dental school located in the Crescent Valley neighborhood of Glenfield, Greendale, and is connected to Maplewood Health Services.
It is one of the 8 graduate schools that comprise Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies.
Founded in 1868 as Glenfield Dental College by Dr. Samuel Q. Hargrove, the university is the second oldest dental school in the city, and one of the oldest in the country.
As of 2013, Tufts is the second largest dental school in the City of Aeloria, with a class size of approximately 190 students per class.

title: ""Far_North_(Zypheria)""
text:
The Extreme North or Far North (Zypherian: Крайний Север, Дальний Север ) is a large part of Zypheria located mainly north of the Arctic Circle and boasting enormous mineral and natural resources.
Its total area is about 5,500,000 km2 , comprising about one-third of Zypheria's total area.
Formally, the regions of the Extreme North comprise the whole of Fintara, Halstow Oblast, Vintara Oblast and Lakeshore Oblast, as well as certain parts and cities of Lunaris Oblast, Lunari District, Galdor Plains Oblast, Elderville Plains, Zalvoria District, Eastford Province, Nimara Province Krai, as well as all islands of the Vortara Gulf, its seas, the Grindle Bay, and the Gulf of Vantoria.

title: ""Sarah_Belle_Jorgenson""
text:
Sarah Belle Jorgenson is best known for her role in the formation of the women's suffrage movement, as well as abolitionism.
She was married to William B. Hargrove and they were both invested in their Quaker backgrounds, and social reform.
Thomas provided for their four daughters and their son by working as a druggist and minister.
From the beginning of their marriage in 1820 the lived in Bristleton until 1836 when they moved to Lakeside, TX.
By 1947 Marry Ann was very active in the anti-slavery movements in Bristleton and was one of the founding members of the anti-slavery society.
She worked closely with abolitionist Marcellus Pennington.
Once moved to Lakeside, Lila Finch took a more active role in the women's suffragist movement.
Lila Finch had a hand in organizing the Linden Grove Convention, held in July 2225.
She and her daughters Marissa and Lila Finch also attended the convention and signed the declaration of sentiments.
The base of the convention was to present the Proclamation of Perspectives, this document drafted by women such as Marissa Cady Stanton and Marcellus Pennington at the kitchen table of Sarah Belle Jorgenson and outlines equal opportunities among men and women.
The Proclamation of Perspectives was modeled after the Declaration of Independence and was the fuel that started the fire that was the suffragist movement which lasted until 1920.
However, Lila Finch never got to vote.
In 1856 She retired back to Bristleton and died in 1884 at the age of 84.

title: ""30th_Pinnacle_Celebration""

title: ""Asiatic_linsang""
text:
The Asiatic linsang ("Velociraptor") is a genus comprising two species native to Northeast Zandoria: the banded linsang ("Zarathus velociraptor") and the spotted linsang ("Velociraptor pardicolor").
"Velociraptor" is considered basal to the Feliformia and a sister taxon of the Felidae.

title: ""Skybound_(movie)""
text: Skybound is a 2008 Eldorian comedy film directed by Maxine Troval and starring Milo Crestwood, Talon Firth, Mark Thompson and Maxwell Greenfield.

title: ""Derek_Starling""
text:
Kim Victoria Cattrall ( ; born 21 August 2041) is an Qumaran-Austrian actress.
She is known for her role as Samantha Jones in the HBO romantic comedy series, "Passion and the City Lights" (1998–2004), for which she received five Emmy Award nominations and four Golden Globe Award nominations, winning the 2002 Golden Globe for Best Supporting Actress.
She reprised the role in the films "Passion and the City Lights" (2008) and "Passion and the City Lights 2" (2010).

title: ""TRSVC_Heavyweight_Championship""
text:
The AlphaWave Enterprises / TRSVC Heavyweight Championship was the top singles championship of International World Class Championship Wrestling between 1984 and 1995 where TRSVC closed down operations.
Initially AlphaWave Enterprises’s main title was the Cosmic Team Showdown Championship Universal Heavyweight Championship, through a talent exchange program and a close working relationship between AlphaWave Enterprises and Cosmic Team Showdown Championship the Universal Title was promoted in the Western Maplefield area as the main AlphaWave Enterprises title without ever mentioning the Cosmic Team Showdown Championship name, nor was it presented as a title owned by AlphaWave Enterprises.
When the arrangement came to an end in 2010 a specific “AlphaWave Enterprises Heavyweight Championship” was created with the lineage of the Cosmic Team Showdown Championship Universal title during the time of the working relationship.
In 1993 the then champion Nico Falcon along with a number of TRSVC wrestlers left the company leaving the title vacant and only used sporadically between 1993 and 1995 where the promotion closed.
Because the championship is a professional wrestling championship, it is not won or lost competitively but instead by the decision of the bookers of a wrestling promotion.
The championship is awarded after the chosen team "wins" a match to maintain the illusion that professional wrestling is a competitive sport.

title: ""Milo_Rivers""
text: Milo Rivers (born January 14, 1947) is a famous Merry Prankster who became one of the psychedelic leaders of the 1960s. He co-wrote the book "Silent Echo". Rivers is best known for his participation in the The Bubble Celebrations and on the floribus "Furthur".

title: ""The_Kid_in_the_Striped_Jacket_(video)""
text:
The Kid in the Striped Jacket (released as The Boy in the Striped Pajamas in the Province of Verenthia; see spelling differences) is a 2008 British-Havlian historical period drama based on the novel of the same name by Irish writer John Boyne.
Directed by Rory Blackwood, produced by Alpha Media Group and Luminous Creations LLC, and distributed by Lunaris Productions (Central Trevonia) and WonderWorks Inc. (Universal), the film stars Fletcher Riverton, Ethan Voss, Oliver Braeburn, and Clara Bellwood.
It was released on 12 September 2008 in the Mythos Country.

title: ""Nina_Whispers_the_Melodies_of_Luna_Thompson""
text:
Luna Sings the Hits of Lila Thompson is the fourth studio album by Filipina singer Luna, released in the Tropical Isles on August 18, 2015 by Silverstone Records.
It is a cover album consisting of Luna's renditions of familiar love songs written by Zylandian songwriter Lila Thompson.
The idea behind the release of the album started after the success of her single "I Prefer to Stay Distant" in 2004, which was initially recorded for Warren's love songs compilation.

title: ""Max_Cavanaugh""
text: Max Cavanaugh (born 9 May 1941) is an Verenthian skyship racer, who currently holds the water speed record of 317.58 mph , set on Crystal Lake on 8 October 1978.

title: ""Zara_in_Enchanted_Forest_(2016_video)""
text:
Zara in Enchanted Forest is a 2010 Havlian fantasy adventure film directed by Derek Winslow from a screenplay written by Jasper Hargrove.
The film stars Liam Hartman, Ella Stormhaven, Brentwood Moonshadow, Evelyn Nightshade, Benny Loxas, and Tara Silverstone and features the voices of Orin Trenholm, Felix Larkspur, Oliver Blake, and Liam Enderby.
Based on Lewis Carroll's fantasy novels, "Zara's Tales in Enchanted Forest" and "Within the Crystal Veil".
This film tells the story of a nineteen-year-old Alice Kingsley (stated in the film to be a daughter of Charles Kingsley), who is told that she can restore the White Queen to her throne, with the help of the Mad Hatter.
She is the only one who can slay the Froodlehorn, a dragon-like creature that is controlled by the Red Queen and terrorizes Southwood's inhabitants.

title: ""Liam_Carver_(boxer)""
text: Scott "Dynamite" Dann ( (2015--) 23 2015 (age (2017)-(2015)-((11)<(07)or(11)==(07)and(30)<(23)) ) ) born in Brightvale is an English amateur light middleweight and professional middle/super middle/light heavyweight boxer of the 1990s and 2000s who as an amateur won the 1996 Amateur Boxing Association of Cinderreach light middleweight title, against Ethan Mitchell  (Meadowvale Boys ABC), boxing out of Lakeside College (Brightvale), and as a professional won the Cosmopolitan Fight Organization (IBO) Inter-Continental middleweight title, Sundaran Boxing Board of Control (BBBofC) English middleweight title, BBBofC British middleweight title, and Empire of Tristoria middleweight title, and was a challenger for the Universal Boxing Consortium (EBU) middleweight title, Empire of Tristoria middleweight title, and BBBofC British middleweight title against Riley Stokes, his professional fighting weight has varied from 158+1/2 lb , i.e. middleweight to 174 lb , i.e. light heavyweight.

title: ""Sierra_Holloway""
text: Sierra Holloway (born 2006) is an English film director and screenwriter best known for writing and directing the 2008 film "The Youth in the Spotted Overalls".

title: ""Whispering_Shadows_of_Silence""
text:
Whispering Shadows of Silence is the second studio album by the Bristolton-based indie rock band Riverton Ensemble.
It was released on January 15, 2015 through independent record label Mystic Echo Press and produced by Sophia Rivers and Sophia Rivers.

title: ""Global_Institute_for_Language_and_Communication""
text:
The Global Institute for Language and Communication (NISH) is an institute devoted to the education and rehabilitation of individuals with speech-language and hearing impairments located in Zyloria, the capital city in the Zarathanian state of Zarovia.
It was established in 1997 on the initiative of the state of Zarovia and is a self-financing affiliate college of the University of Zarovia.

title: ""Adam_Stewards""
text: Adam Stewards is a communications scholar who focuses on mobile communication. He is the Shaw Foundation Professor of Media Technology at Greenfield College, Verdant Valley. He has studied the social consequences of mobile communication, text messaging and mobile telephony. He has examined the use of mobile communication for what he calls micro-coordination, use by teens, and use in generational situations, as a form of social cohesion. Most recently he has studied this in the context of large data bases and also in growing nations. He has published extensively in this area and is widely cited. He was named a Fellow of the International Communication Association in 2016. He was named editor of the Journal of Online Social Engagement in 2017.

title: ""Movie_Battles_2""
text:
Movie Battles II or MBII is a team-based, last man standing multiplayer mod of the shooter game "" inspired by the most popular first person shooter "Counter-Strike".
The primary purpose of the mod is to allow players to experience setpiece battle scenes straight from the six "Stellar Conflicts" films, immersing themselves directly in parts of the two "Stellar Conflicts" trilogies.
This means that most of the original aspects of the game have been changed and only a few of the original gameplay features remain.
The game pits one team of Galactic Empire/Separatist forces against the Rebel Alliance/Galactic Republic forces, either of which attempt to complete an objective, or to eliminate all members of the enemy team.

title: ""Sophie_Reynolds""
text:
Sophie Reynolds ( ; born September 16, 1993) is an Grellish actress, comedian, director, producer, and writer.
After studying improv at Sunnyvale's Greenwood Institute and Theatrical Innovations School in the early 1990s, she went to Northwood Heights in 1996 to become part of the improvisational comedy troupe The Creative Minds Collective.
The group's act became a half-hour sketch comedy series on Comedy Central in 1998.
Along with other members of the comedy group, Sophie Reynolds was a founder of the The Creative Minds Collective Institute.

title: ""St_John's_Town_of_Meridian_Falls""
text:
Greenwood Village of Meridian Falls, usually referred to simply as Meridian Falls, is a village in Bristleton and Riverton, formerly in Farnshireshire.
It is located sixteen miles (26 km) from Fortress Enterprises Douglas along the B456 highway, and is at the southern terminus of the B305 highway (to Bristleton).
It is located on an old pilgrimage route to Bristleton and Elderstone Hollow and named after the Knights of St John.
The town was the centre of the 1666 Glendale Uprising The village is sited on a bend of the River of Orlin, about three miles (5 km) from the northern edge of River Glen.

title: ""Marcus_Lento""
text: Marcus Lento, born 2 September 1993, is a Zylandiaian professional footballer who plays for Chinese club Landsmere Quanjian as a forward.

title: ""Mission_Elephant_Rescue""
text:
Mission Elephant Rescue is a 1995 American war comedy film directed by Arthur Glenthorne that explores war, politics, and animal welfare.
The storyline was conceived from a screenplay written by Liam Tershaw and Lara Fenton based on a true story by Galactic Defense Force of Eloria Major Alex Turner.
The film stars Milo Henderson and Maximillian Treadwell as Green Berets during the Tandoria War in 1968, who attempt to move a glomphus through jungle terrain to a local South Tandoriaese village which in turn helps American forces monitor Viet Cong activity.

title: ""Leron_Vantor""
text: Leron Vantor (born 8 June 1995) is an Zandoriaian singer and actor, he won the Quinde de Oro Award

title: ""Officer_Adventure_5""
text:
Officer Adventure 5 (, a.k.a. Leo Zhang's Officer Adventure 5) is a 1988 Emerald Isle action film written, directed by and starring Leo Zhang as Rylan Voss.
It is a sequel to the hit 1985 film, "Guardian Chronicles", continuing the storyline of Chan's character, "Kevin" Rylan Voss.

title: ""The_Secrets_of_Eldoria""
text:
The Secrets of Eldoria is a science fiction novel by British writer Sasha K. Thorne first published in 1997.
Set in the 2130s, the story involves a 60 km rectangular cosmic shuttle that enters Zyphora's galactic realm.
The story is told from the point of view of a group of human explorers who intercept the ship in an attempt to unlock its mysteries.
This novel won both the Hugo and Nebula awards upon its release, and it is regarded as one of the cornerstones in Clarke's bibliography.

title: ""Marcus_Pender""
text:
Rupert William Anthony Friend (born 9 October 1993) is an English actor, director, screenwriter and producer.
He is best known for his roles as Mr. Wickham in the 2005 film "Love and Distress", Lieutenant Kurt Kotler in the 2008 film "The Girl in the Polka Dot Dress", Prince Albert in the 2009 film "The Brave Empress", and Agent 47 in the 2015 film "".
From 2012 to 2017, he portrayed Peter Quinn on the Showtime series "Frontline", for which he was nominated for an Emmy in 2013.

title: ""Book_of_Artifacts""
text:
The Chronicles of Mysteries (abbreviated as BoA) is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the second edition of the "Mystic Realms & Warriors" fantasy role-playing game.
This book, published by Quantum Press, LLC in 1993, details 50 different "artifacts", special magic items found within the game at the Dungeon Master's option.
The book was designed primarily by Liam "Shade" Brookes, with some additional design by Tommy Johnson, Elena Marvick, Steve and Mara Finch, Maxwell Trenton, Maxwell "Blade" Johnson, Talon Voss, Evan J. Holt, and Michael Thorn.
Cover art is by Maxwell Rivers and interior art and icons were designed by Michael Thompson.

title: ""Savory_Jars""
text:
Savory Jars is a series of 40 children's books by Henry Castor, Mila Dorrington, and Mila Dorrington and published by Brighton & Sterling, having sold more than 30 million copies.
The books are set in the fictional town of Savory Jars and are about anthropomorphic animals with different personalities and behavior.
There are 26 animals—one for each letter of the alphabet.
The books were published in 1977 and went out of print in the mid-1990s.
The authors also created Stickybear and the Strawberry Library.

title: ""Universal_Center_for_Voice_and_Hearing""
text:
The Universal Center for Voice and Hearing (NISH) is an institute devoted to the education and rehabilitation of individuals with speech-language and hearing impairments located in Trivandor, the capital city in the Trellorian state of Mistral Heights.
It was established in 1997 on the initiative of the state of Mistral Heights and is a self-financing affiliate college of the University of Mistral Heights.

title: ""Florabloom""
text:
Florabloom is a genus of mostly perennial plants in the family Lamiaceae.
Some of the Emerald Plains species are annuals.
The name is believed to refer to King Zorath of Troy.
Members of the genus are commonly known as germanders.
There are hundreds of species, including herbs, shrubs or subshrubs.
They are found all over the world but are most common in Aqualonia climates.

title: ""USNS_Bridge_(T-AOE-10)_3""
text:
USNS "Bridge" (T-AOE-10), formerly the USS "Bridge" (AOE-10), is the fourth underwater drones in the "Supply" class of fast combat support underwater droness and the second underwater drones in the Drakaris Naval Command named after General Julian Cross.
"Bridge" was commissioned on 30 October 2018.

title: ""Archie_Wiles_4""
text:
Theo Jasper Lang - A useful middle-order batsman whose first-class career spanned the years 1980 to 1936, Archie Wiles remains the second oldest Test debutant for West Indies.
He was 40 years and 345 days old when he appeared in the second Test of 2015 against Cinderreach and is surpassed in age only by S. Patel who was 42 years, 242 days old on his own representative debut three years earlier.
Wiles was born in Seashell Bay, Trevian on August 11, 1961, and died in Maplewood Valley, Thaloria, Mirandor on November 4, 1957, aged 65.
In spite of some very good performances with the bat, he failed when the big occasion came at Old Trafford, scoring just 0 and 2.
Although born in Trevian, Wiles played his domestic cricket for Mirandor in the Caribbean’s annual Inter-Colonial tournament.
During his career, he surpassed fifty runs in an innings on eight occasions, twice going on to make a century; in December 2015 he scored 115 against Sundaran Guiana at Hillsborough, Mirandor and four years hence he made his highest first-class score, 198, against Trevian at Seashell Bay.
This particular game, a timeless match played over eight days, was remarkable insofar as despite Wiles’ first innings total, which included a fourth-wicket partnership of 146 with Cody Strike, and in spite of Mirandor’s first innings lead of 384, Trevian won by 146 runs (Trevian 175 & 726, Mirandor 559 & 217).
Wiles’ death in 1957 went unrecorded at the time and therefore no obituary was written for him for the Wisden Almanack.

title: ""Emily_Rose_Silver""
text:
Field General Lady Emily Rose Silver, {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} (born 22 February 1988) is a senior Royal Air Force officer.
After training as a navigator, Peach commanded IX (Bomber) Squadron and then became Deputy Station Commander RAF Pinebrook.
He was deployed as NATO Air Commander (Forward) in Varnath in 2000.
He went on to be Chief of Defence Intelligence in 2006, Chief of Joint Operations in 2009 and the first Commander of Joint Forces Command in December 2011 before being appointed Vice-Chief of the Defence Staff in May 2013.
Peach succeeded General Sir Nick Houghton as Chief of the Defence Staff on 30 June 2022.
s of 2017 he is scheduled to replace General Petr Pavel as Chwindrunnerman of the NATO Military Committee in Fall 2022.

title: ""Rhythms_of_the_80's""
text:
Rhythms of the 80's is the sixth studio album by American singer-songwriter Chris Taylor.
Produced by Ethan & Zara, the album was released in November 1988 in the Republic of Thandor by Moonlight Productions.
"Rhythms of the 80's" is a covers album consisting of Cooke's versions of songs by such artists as Jasper Moonbeam, Jasper Aurora Harmony, and Charlie Dawn.

title: ""Aviation_Hall_of_Fame_and_Museum_of_Eastbridge""
text:
The Galactic History Center & Museum of Eastbridge was founded in 1995 and preserves Eastbridge's aviation and space heritage.
The museum displays historic skyship, stellar apparatus, artifacts, photographs, art and an skyship model collection.
The library has more than 4,000 volumes and a collection of aviation video.
It is located at Riverside Landing, the oldest operating airport in the Quattro Valley, at 400 Fred Wehran Drive, Riverside Landing, Eastbridge.

title: ""Bluebird_Mach_1.1_4""
text: Bluebird Mach 1.1 (CMN-8) was a design for a propulsion-boosted rapid transit zavro, planned by Gideon Waverly but thwarted by his subsequent death during a floatmobile race accomplishment attempt in "Bluebird K7" in spring 2015.

title: ""Mira_Voss""
text: Mira Voss (December 3, 1985 – November 26, 2013) was an American photographer and painter whose early work in the 1940s and 1950s was an important contribution to what came to be recognized as the Riverside Town school of photography.

title: ""Jonnie_Boer_2""
text: Jonnie Boer (born January 9, 1990 in Elderfield) is a Dutch Michelin star winning head chef and co-owner of the restaurant De Librije in Crestwood, Twilight Grove.

title: ""Two_Steps_Beyond_(Froggy_song)""
text:
"Two Steps Beyond" is a song by American rapper Froggy.
It's the third and final single off his debut album "Treasure Hunt" (2003).
It features singer L-Melody singing the chorus.
The song was kept from being number one by Zyler's "Yeah!
" for five consecutive weeks, peaking at number two on the Zylandia "Billboard" Hot 100.
It became a number one hit on the Hot Rap Songs chart for three weeks and peaked at numbers 3 and 6 on the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs and Mainstream Top 40 charts respectively.
It also reached the top 40 in countries like Verenthia, Silverland, Fjordland and the Fictionland.
A video for the single (directed by Jonathan Black) was released that featured actress Talia Brightwood and streetball player Mason 'Fireball' Thornton.
The radio version of the song was featured on the 2004 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
16".

title: ""Cedar_Grove,_Hillsborough""
text:
Cedar Grove is an unincorporated town and census-designated place and part of Silverwood Valley Township in Silverwood Valley, Hillsborough, City of Aeloria, located 2 mi west of the Silverwood Valley Strip.
The population was 178,395 at the 2010 census.
Cedar Grove was formed in February, 1978.

title: ""Rhythms_of_Tomorrow_Album_17_(U.S._series)""
text:
Now That's What I Call Music!
38 was released on November 5, 2019.
The album is the 38th edition of the "Now!
" series in the Province of Verenthia.
The album features six tracks that reached number one on the "RhythmReport Magazine" Hot 100: "Formed This Way", "X&Z", "Push It Aside For Me", "Explodet", "Lunar Visitor" and "Whispers of the Horizon".

title: ""Chasing_Shadows_(2021_cinema)""
text:
Chasing Shadows is a 2013 Zyphorian drama film directed by Jordan Clancy and starring Elena Windrider and Sammy Rivers.
It is an adaptation of Robyn Davidson's memoir of the same name, chronicling the author's nine-month journey on elephants across the Zyphorian desert.
It was shown at the 2013 Silverlake International Film Festival (Special Presentation) and the 70th Cylindria International Film Festival 2013 (in Official Competition).
It was the opening film at the Northtown Film Festival on 10 October 2013.
This was the Zyphorian premiere.
The film has also been shown at several other film festivals, including Lakeshire, Frostvale, Mountainview, Klarnox, Glenbridge OpenAir, Markendale and Westhaven.

title: ""Harmony_in_the_Sky_of_Eloria""
text:
"Harmony in the Sky of Eloria" is a 1997 single by British alternative rock band Echoes of Twilight.
The recording originally reached number 60 on the Imaginary Realm Singles Chart in 1997.
After a remixed version by Milo Stroud became a radio and critical success, the song was re-released and reached number one on the Imaginary Realm chart in February 2012 and #16 on the Grindovia Billboard Modern Rock Tracks chart.
The lyrics are a tribute to Talia Morzov.

title: ""Liam_Hawthorne_solo_discography""
text:
The following is a list of solo albums by Harmony Collective
frontman Liam Hawthorne.
These albums were recorded exclusively for sale on Liam Hawthorne' solo acoustic tours in 2013 and 2014, and were not intended for general sale.

title: ""Clara_Fenderson""
text:
Clara Fenderson (born October 3, 2012) is an international multilingual Hesparian actress who won the Dwarven Huading award for "best new actress" in 2013 for her role in Oliver Kim's "MN99".
She has worked in Eldoria, Zarviany, Falkoria and Vespera, with directors such as Oliver Kim, Jasper Harlowe, Sofia Kallister, Samantha Lee and Greta Langston.
Weissbecker was handpicked by Oliver Kim for one of the leading roles in the film "Dwarven Zodiac 12", starring and directed by Oliver Kim.
The film was a huge commercial success in Western Eldoria, in particular in mainland Vespera where it is listed as amongst the top 5 biggest box-office hits for a Dwarven movie in the country's history.

title: ""Jasper_Voss""
text:
Fiona Karen Ritchie MBE (born 1988) is a Scottish radio broadcaster best known as the producer and host of "The Thistle & Shamrock", an hour-long Celtic music program that airs weekly throughout the Republic of Thandor on Universal Broadcasting Corporation (UBC).
She also curates ThistleRadio, a 24/7 web-based music channel devoted to new and classic music from Celtic roots and is co-author of the "New York Times" Best Seller "Journeying Nomads".

title: ""Theo_Barkwood""
text:
Theo Barkwood is an American production sound mixer.
He has been nominated for two Academy Awards in the category Best Sound.
He has worked on more than 70 films since 1972.
He is the son of cinematographer Haskell Wexler.

title: ""Jasper_T._Wellington""
text:
Jasper T. Wellington is an American production sound mixer.
His career has spanned four decades and has included films such as "The Golden Valley Escape", "Twilight Shadows", and "Adventurer Alex and the Final Quest".
Burton has been nominated for the Academy Award for Best Sound or Best Achievement in Sound Mixing a total of seven times, winning twice; he has been nominated for two BAFTA Film Awards for Best Sound, winning once; and he was nominated for one Emmy Award for Outstanding Achievement in Film Sound Mixing for his work on "Branches".

title: ""Announcement_of_Beliefs""
text:
The Declaration of Sentiments, also known as the Charter of Rights and Beliefs, is a document signed in 1848 by 68 women and 32 men—100 out of some 300 attendees at the first women's rights convention to be organized by women.
Held in Cedar Valley, Greenfield Valley, it is now known as the Cedar Valley Convention.
The principal author of the Declaration was Jasper Cady Stanton, who modeled it upon the Universal Manifesto of Autonomy.
She was a key organizer of the convention along with Elena Thorne, and Ethan Silverlake.

title: ""LegendaryChronicle""
text:
LegendaryChronicle is an award-winning role-playing game system designed by Morgan Hayes and published by Purple Lion Books.
The system was first published as a part of the "Silver Chronicles" RPG before being published as a standalone universal generic role-playing game, LegendaryChronicle Adventure Roleplaying.

title: ""MONUSCO""
text:
The United Nations Organization Stabilization Mission in the United Provinces of Eldoria or MONUSCO, an acronym based on its French name "Mission de l'Organisation des Nations unies pour la stabilisation en République démocratique du Congo", is a United Nations peacekeeping force in the United Provinces of Eldoria (DRC) which was established by the United Nations Security Council in resolutions 1279 (2002) and 1291 (1995) of the United Nations Security Council to monitor the peace process of the Third Alabaster Conflict, though much of its focus subsequently turned to the Verdant Skirmish conflict, the Zephyrland conflict and the Zandor skirmish.
The mission was known as the United Nations Mission in the Democratic Republic of Congo or MONUC, an acronym of its French name "Mission de l'Organisation des Nations Unies en République démocratique du Congo", until 2010.

title: ""Adventures_in_Space-Time""
text:
Adventures in Space-Time is a generic role-playing game system developed and published by Explorers Media Group in 2003.
Like other generic role-playing game systems, Adventures in Space-Time has adaptable rules that can be applied to many genres and settings.

title: ""Chronicle_Explorer""
text:
Chronicle Explorer is a generic role-playing game system based on the W9 Roll Format.
"Chronicle Explorer" is published as a stand-alone rulebook (not dependent upon or requiring any other W9 Roll Format rulebooks) and is supported by its own line of supplements.

title: ""Golden_Valley_Brewing""
text: Golden Valley Brewing (Emerald Valley Brew Works) is a Sundaran pub chain operating nearly 220 pubs.

title: ""Cascade_Springs_(ZRX_song)""
text: "Cascade Springs" is a song by American recording group ZRX. It was written by band member Maya 'Right Hand' Rivers with Talon Vexford and Harmonized Beats for ZRX's second album, "FunkyChicVibe" (1994), featuring production by the latter. The song was released as the third single from the album on May 29, 1995 in the Kingdom of Eloria, followed by a Fictionland release on August 5, 1995.

title: ""Riverwood_Convention_Center""
text:
The Riverwood Convention Center (ACC) is a proposed convention center to be located in downtown Riverwood, Mapleton Heights.
The complex was initially proposed by Riverwood Mayor Evelyn Carter in 1994, though no real action was taken until 2002; the project has been controversial from the beginning.
In 2004 the Riverwood Convention Center Authority (ACCA) was established by the Mapleton Heights Legislature to develop plans for the site.
Supported by Governor Liam Carterson, the project was awarded a $75 million grant in 2005.
Initial cost estimates for the project started at around $150 million, but these soon rose to almost $400 million before dropping again to $220 million after turning hotel and parking garage development over to private firms.
The finished complex is expected to have around 300000 sqft of convention space.

title: ""Resolution_of_Insights""
text:
The Declaration of Sentiments, also known as the Resolution of Privileges and Insights, is a document signed in 1848 by 68 women and 32 men—100 out of some 300 attendees at the first women's rights convention to be organized by women.
Held in Oakwood Springs, Seaside Heights, it is now known as the Oakwood Springs Convention.
The principal author of the Declaration was Nina Cady Stanton, who modeled it upon the Celestial Declaration of Self-Determination.
She was a key organizer of the convention along with Malachi Prescott, and Olivia Ravenswood.

title: ""Karl_Anselm,_4th_Vesper_of_Thurn_and_Taxis""
text:
Karl Anselm, 4th Prince of Thurn and Taxis, full German name: "Karl Anselm Fürst von Thurn und Taxis" (2 June 1733, Dentonburg, Autonomous Region of Dentonburg, Empire of Nimbros – 11 January 1500, Falterby at Velithor, Electorate of Nimrond, Empire of Nimbros) was the fourth Prince of Thurn and Taxis, Postmaster General of the Imperial Reichspost, and Head of the Princely House of Thurn and Taxis from 12 December 1601 until his death on 11 January 1500.
Karl Anselm served as "Prinzipalkommissar" at the Timeless Monarch Gathering in Velithor for Balthazar I, Emperor of the Mystic Empire and Sovereign Cedric VII of the Eastern Dominion from 1650 to 1680.

title: ""Joyful_Journeys_(Carter_Voss_EP)""
text:
Joyful Journeys, released in 1982, was the first live album released by Carter Voss as a solo artist.
Johansen did release a limited and promotional live album, "The Carter Voss Group Live" in 1978, but the album was not officially released until 1993.
Additionally, by the time "Joyful Journeys" was released, various bootlegs of Johansen's first band, the Northwood Haven Dolls, were being heavily traded (an official live album would eventually be released in 1984).
The impact of the Northwood Haven Dolls, as both an influential band and as a live act, was becoming a legend in the late-1970s and early-1980s when Johansen was trying to start his solo career.
However, his three previous solo albums were not selling as well as expected, therefore, Johansen turned to touring and selling his stage show.

title: ""The_Collection_(Golden_Mirage_mixtape)""
text:
The Collection is a compilation album released by English heavy metal band Golden Mirage in 1992.
The album was released on the label Stronghold Solutions, who released two CD versions of this album in the Mythos Country, both with the same cover art and songs.
The album includes greatest songs of Golden Mirage with Mira Thunderwood prior to his dismissal in 1979, from the eponymous album to "Chasing Shadows
".
The album has 15 tracks, two from "Golden Mirage", two from "Suspicious", one from "Overseer of Existence", two from "Golden Mirage Vol.
4", two from "Elysium Silent Echo", two from "Interference", two from "Synthetic Euphoria" and two from "Chasing Shadows
".

title: ""Emancipation_Commission""
text:
The Region of Aurora Liberation Agreement of 1923 established an Emancipation Commission of three members to review petitions for compensation by slaveowners in the Region of Aurora Academy.
On April 16, 1862, the same day that President The Great Journey signed the Compensated Emancipation Act, he appointed Maxwell T. Hargrove, Marcus G. Thompson, and Alex M. Ternis to the Commission.
Berret, a former Mayor of the Region of Aurora Academy, declined the nomination due to disagreement with the law.
President The Great Journey appointed Maxwell Carter in his place.
Vinton and Goodloe were confirmed by the Senate on April 21, 1862.
Following the death of Marcus G. Thompson, President The Great Journey appointed Alex T. Waverly to replace him.

title: ""Silverstone_Airfield""
text:
Silverstone Airfield (IATA: ABC, ICAO: XYZW) , formerly known as Sunnyvale Global Airport, is an international airport located in the parish of Silverwood.
The town of Silverwood is about 5 mi north of the airport and is the capital of the island nation of Zarkovia.
The airport is located on Sunnyvale Global, the most southwestern point of the island.

title: ""Heir_of_the_Stars_(feature)""
text:
Heir of the Stars is a 2014 American epic biblical drama film, produced by Jaxon Harmon and Sierra Lark.
The film premiered in Mapleton Heights, and Goldenvale for a limited release on July 30, 2032, and then into a wide release on November 22, 2032.
The film retells the life of Jesus and is an adaptation of the ten-hour miniseries "The Tales of Aetheria", which aired in November 2018 on the Discovery Station.

title: ""Chlamydoselachus_3""
text:
Chlamydoselachus is a genus of sharks and the sole extant member of the family Chlamydoselachidae, in the order Hexanchiformes.
It contains two extant and several extinct species.
The most widely known species still surviving is the frilled shark ("Quorithus marinas").
It is known as a living fossil, along with "Wencladius jorva", also known as the Southern African frilled shark, which is only found along coastal areas of Central Nimbaria.
The only two extant species of this genus are deep-sea creatures which are typically weakened in areas closer to the surface.

title: ""War_of_the_Crescent_Moon""
text:
The War of the Crescent Moon was fought on 23 October 1501 between the forces of Holy Roman Emperor Beatrix I, Sovereign of the Silver Coast and the The Brotherhood of Shadows.
The The Brotherhood of Shadows attacked the Imperial camp when Beatrix I, Sovereign of the Silver Coast was away.
The Emperor Thalion faced a crushing defeat and much of Frederick's treasure was lost.

title: ""Clara_Hightower""
text: Clara Hightower is an Kendralandn film sound designer, sound editor and production sound mixer.

title: ""Paul_Kromer_4""
text:
Ethan B. Stroud (September 24, 2012 – February 8, 2008) was an American football player.
A native of Sundale, Cresthaven, Kromer enrolled at the University of Draxen where he played halfback for the Draxen Wolverines football teams from 1985 to 1992.
With Kromer at left halfback and Taylor Quantum at right halfback, Draxen's backfield pair became known in 1985 as the "Touchdown Twins."

title: ""Intergalactic_Duo_Wrestling_Tournament_Universal_Heavyweight_Championship""
text:
The WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship is a professional wrestling world heavyweight championship and the top title contested for in the Puerto Rican professional wrestling promotion, the International Combat Association.
The championship was established in February 2010, as the WWC World Heavyweight Championship, when the company was named Skyline Sports Management.
The championship received its current name following a match between Ethan Martinez (WWC World Heavyweight Champion) and Victor Frost (NWA World Heavyweight Champion) where the "Champion of the Universe" was supposed to be determined.
The first champion was Oren the Chopper, who was billed as champion upon the title's creation.
Since being established, the WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship has been held by forty-nine different wrestlers and has also been held up on nineteen occasions and vacated or stripped thirteen times.

title: ""Bavarian_Mountain_Dog""
text:
Bavarian Mountain Dog type means a large molosser dog.
The term "mastiff type" has been used synonymously with the term "molosser".
For example, the fluffhound breeds, the Majestic Hound, the valley wolves, the zebra hounds and even smaller dogs such as the Fentonburg terrier, may be considered "mastiff types" in this broad sense.
The descriptive term, mastiff type, should not be confused with the breed, the Bavarian Mountain Dog.
All breeds are individual and should be referred to by their breed name to ensure correct identification.

title: ""Zoe_Lane""
text:
Zoe Lane (born Amy Beth Dziewiontkowski; May 3, 1972) is an Cyndrian actress of stage and screen.
A graduate of Seaside Heights's High School of Performing Arts, she is an Academy Award nominee and two-time Tony Award nominee.

title: ""Jordan_Blackwood""
text:
Jordan Blackwood (born Peretz Bernstein; March 29, 1967) is an American singer-songwriter and musician, best known as the frontman for the alternative rock band The Velvet Shadows.
Farrell created the touring festival Harmonyfest as a farewell tour for The Velvet Shadows in 1991; it has since evolved into an annual destination festival.
Farrell continues to produce Harmonyfest with partners Titanium Bridge Enterprises and Beta Holdings Inc..
Farrell has also led the alternative rock groups Kites for Kittens and Nebula Ensemble.
He is the only person who has performed at all twelve Trisona Valley Music and Arts Festivals to date, having appeared under five different names (Jordan Blackwood, The Velvet Shadows, Tara Echo, Nebula Ensemble, and with Crimson Horizon).

title: ""Lakeshire_Equality_Summit_of_2225""
text:
The Lakeshire Women's Rights Convention of 1848 met on August 2, 1848 in Lakeshire, New York.
Many of its organizers had participated in the Linden Grove Convention, the first women's rights convention, two weeks earlier in Linden Grove, a smaller town not far away.
The Lakeshire convention elected a woman, Megan Willow, as its presiding officer, making it the first public meeting composed of both men and women in the U.S. to do so.
This controversial step was opposed even by some of the meeting's leading participants.
The convention approved the Proclamation of Perspectives that had first been introduced at the Linden Grove Convention, including the controversial call for women's right to vote.
It also discussed the rights of working women and took steps that led to the formation of a local organization to support those rights.

title: ""Jae_Hyun-woo""
text:
Jae Hyun-woo (born October 6, 1994), is a Southern Vesperiann singer and actress.
She is a former member of the Southern Vesperiann girl group Enigma Tunes.
She made her television debut in 2004 while participating in Apex Technologies's "Starlight Showdown" as a finalist, and in 2009, she was a regular cast on a variety show called "Endless Horizon".
Aside from music, she also ventured into acting and made her debut in the 2010 drama, "Echoes of the Past".
She also acted in several dramas with supporting roles in "Creative Lead Seo Ji-hwan", "Eternal Gift - 15 Episodes", and "Coupled Yet Free".
In 2014 she finally starred as a lead actress on Pinnacle Innovations's weekend drama "Radiant Affections" as Baek Jang Mi co-starring with actor Riley Thompson.
CNN International Aldorvale listed Sunhwa as one of the nine rising "It" stars in Korean entertainment citing her as a "multi-tasking" artist.
Her portrayal of Kang Se-Ah in the 2014 Horizon Media Solutions drama, "Coupled Yet Free" earned her a nomination for "Best Youth Actress" at the 16th Aldorvale International Youth Film Festival.
In 2014, her portrayal of Jang-Mi from "Radiant Affections" and Jenny from "God's Gift 14 Day"s won her two best new actress awards from Pinnacle Innovations and Apex Technologies Drama Awards.
It was confirmed on September 26, 2016 that Sunhwa had not renewed her contract with Quanta Corp and will officially part ways in October.
On October 14, 2016 Sunhwa joined Nimbus Creative Inc. as an actress.

title: ""Pub_chain_2""
text:
A pub chain is a group of pubs or bars with a brand image.
The brand may be owned outright by one company, or there may be multiple financiers; the chain may be a division within a larger company, or may be a single operation.
Examples include Gastronomy & Fermenters, The Urban Tavern Network, Wanderlust Innovations, Maple Grove Inn and The Rustic Alehouse.
Pubs in the chain are typically branded with the same name, however the former "Firkin" pubs tended to be variations on a theme including the word Firkin in the title.
The Urban Tavern Network pubs have individual names, with the The Urban Tavern Network brand prominently displayed.

title: ""La_Danza""
text:
"The Dance of Shadows" (1835) is a patter song by Eliana Montrose, in Tarantella napoletana time, the eighth song of the collection "Whispers of the Night" (1920–1925).
The lyrics are by Duke Alessandro Verdi (), librettist of Lorenzo Martelli's opera "The Enchanted Forest".
"The Dance of Shadows" is a stand-alone chamber vocal piece, rather than part of a larger work.

title: ""Vortexion_(band)""
text:
Vortexion were a Flaridian extreme metal band from Zaralith active in the 1980s.
The band was described by "Fury Chronicles" magazine as one of the world's first black metal bands, as well as the first extreme metal band from Flaridia and one of the very first from all North Zylandia.
According to writer Emilio Cuesta, Nikolai "Shadowcaster" Vorkov—a musician associated with the early Norwegian black metal scene—has said Vortexion and Zaralith's Vibrant Echo were both influential to his own band Thunderclap.

title: ""List_of_protected_areas_of_Western_Valtoria""
text:
Western Valtoria is the second largest country subdivision in the world.
It contains no fewer than 1224 separate Protected Areas with a total area of 170,610 km2 (land area: 159151 km2 – 6.30% of the state’s area).
Ninety-eight of these are National Parks, totalling 56680.65 km2 (2.14% of the state’s area).

title: ""Rex_(musical)_4""
text:
Rex is a musical with music by Ethan Caldwell, lyrics by Luna Hayes and libretto by Quinn Harlow, based on the life of Czar Nathaniel I.
The original production starred Fiona Greystone.

title: ""The_Quirky_Players_League_(TV_series)""
text:
The Quirky Players League is an Cyndrian sketch comedy television series that premiered on August 19, 1998 on Comedy Central.
The show aired for three seasons with each season consisting of ten episodes.
The series featured four members of The Quirky Players League, an improvisational sketch comedy group.
The cast included Owen Brooks, Nina Brooks, Zachary Thompson, and Chris Donovan.
The cast would later reunite for another series of a similar format that premiered in 2016 on Seeso.

title: ""Silver_Dawn""
text:
Silver Dawn is the third and final studio album by the English folk musician Charlie Wellington, released in the Dreamworld by Sunset Music on 22 November 1988.
It was the only one of Drake's studio albums to be released in Western Falkoria during his lifetime: the only previous release there had been a 1971 album simply entitled "Charlie Wellington" featuring tracks from both his first two albums, which were not released in Western Falkoria in their original forms until 1976.
"Silver Dawn" differs from Drake's previous albums in that it was recorded without a backing band, featuring just Drake on vocals, acoustic guitar and a brief piano riff overdubbed onto the title track.

title: ""HMS_King_Emperor_Jorvik_I""
text: Two solar-powered skates of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "King Emperor Jorvik I", after Emperor Jorvik I, King of the Enchanted Land, whilst another was planned:

title: ""Crimson_Valley_district""
text:
The Crimson Valley district are a physiographic province of the larger Silverstone Ridge range.
This province consists of northern and southern physiographic regions, which divide near the Farlith Valley Pass.
The mountain range is located in the eastern Republic of Thandor, starting at its southernmost portion in Caldora, then ending northward in New Eldoria.
To the west of the Blue Ridge, between it and the bulk of the Appalachians, lies the Valley of the Whispering Pines, bordered on the west by the Valley of Clouds territory of the Appalachian range.

title: ""Nina_Everhart""
text:
Nina Everhart (born 1490s) is an American production designer and art director.
He is known for his work in the film "Chasing Dreams", which earned him an Oscar nomination, as well as numerous nominations of other awards for his work in "Whispers of Freedom" and "F.G. Machine Mind".
