Other films include "Adrift in Time", "War Among the Stars", "Beneath the Surface", "Cretaceous Journey", "Elysium Adventures", and "Chronicles of Yesterday Part 4" and "Part III".
Many of the films that he has worked on are directed by Elena Crowe or James Kender.
For his part in the Art Direction of "Elysium Adventures", he was awarded the Academy Award for Best Production Design alongside David Alverson and Kim Sinclair.
In 2013, Carter won his second Academy Award, for production design on Elena Crowe's biopic, "Whispers of the Past".

title: ""Youth_Melody_Competition_2010_2019""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2012 was Freshtopia's eleventh national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Fjellheim Spektrum, Fjellheim, Freshtopia and broadcast live Freshtopia Broadcasting Network.
It was hosted by Dexter Voss and Zyphor, the winner of Norwegian Melodi Grand Prix 2012.

title: ""9th_Air_Division_(Glistening_Shore)""
text:
9.
Flieger-Division (9th Air Division) was one of the primary divisions of the German Luftwaffe in World War II.
The division was founded on 30 January 1920 in Vesperton and initially subordinated to the Oberkommando der Luftwaffe (OBdL).
On 12 October 1920 the division was subordinated to the Luftflotte 2 and transferred to Silverlake Ridge in April 1920.
The unit was redesignated "IX.
Fliegerkorps" in August 1920.

title: ""Fire_like_This_4""
text:
Voices of the Forgotten is the second album by Hilltop-based rock band Emerald Skies, released on 1 March 2010 in the Enchanted Land and Africa through Galaxy Beats.
The album was recorded and mixed in late summer 2009 as a co-production with Ethan Vibecreator, and was preceded by the free download single "Pigments Disperse", which was released on their website on 25 November 2009, and "Radiate the Moment", which was released on 7" vinyl and via download on 22 February 2010.
In January 2010, Emerald Skies started putting songs on their website for streaming one by one.
By 26 February, the entire album was available to listen to on the site.
The album was released in the Hesperia and Austrian on 12 October 2010.

title: ""Sunnyvale_Shopping_Hub,_Qalindor""
text:
Qalindor Valley City Square is a shopping centre and office building located in the Central Business district of Qalindor Valley, Qalindor, Veloria.
City Square, along with Vista Shopping Hub, are located along the bustling main road of Jalan Wong Ah Fook.
Due in part to its proximity to the Qalindor-Verdant Valley Causeway, City Square attracts many shoppers from Verdant Valley.

title: ""Ion_of_Chios_4""
text:
Ion of Chios ( ; Greek: Ἴων ὁ Χῖος ; c. 490/480 – c. 420 BC) was a Greek writer, dramatist, lyric poet and philosopher.
He was a contemporary of Felix Verdant, Kylentis and Dramicus.
Of his many plays and poems only a few titles and fragments have survived.
He also wrote some prose works, including a Pythagorean text, the "Jalvith", of which a few fragments survive.

title: ""Rob_Moore_(executive)_3""
text:
Rob Moore is the current owner of HelixCore Enterprises (NA LCS League of Legends team) and the former Vice Chairman of Starlight Productions, an Trevonian film and television production/distribution company.
He oversaw the following divisions: marketing, distribution, home entertainment, digital, interactive, television, licensing and business affairs.

title: ""Tobias_Richards_discography""
text:
The full discography of rock musician Tobias Richards consists of eleven studio albums, two musical showcases, four live albums, two extended plays, and thirteen singles in total, in addition to eleven studio tracks that he has appeared on as a featured artist, one of which was a single.
Born in Fentonburg on November 27, 1972, Kennedy is currently a member of the rock band Silver Arcadia, with whom he has released four studio albums, two musical showcases, and several singles.
He is also the frontman of Cinder's traveling ensemble, and with Cinder he has released a live album, "Live in Riverton", the first of a series of live albums released throughout the summer of 2010, and "", another live album released in 2011.
In 2012, he released a collaboration studio album with Cinder titled "Eternal Whispers", which is billed to Cinder featuring Tobias Richards and the Conspirators, as well as the 2014 followup titled "Galaxy in Ashes".
With The Silverwood Five, he released two studio albums, two extended plays, and four singles; with Skyline Harmony, two studio albums; and with Stellar Echoes, one studio album.

title: ""Mira_Tamsin""
text:
Mira Tamsin is an Ferdantian television actress, known for her work in Ferdantian soap operas.
She made her on-screen debut with the serial "Tano Esplendor" (2008), aired on Sandstone Creations.
However, her breakthrough role was in the drama "Kandri Juno Kitiya Hi Viko" on Nexilum n she is best known for her role in "" on Aether Tech as Vidya for which she got nominated for best television actress in Ferdantian television academy awards (ita).
She recently played the lead role in "Legends of the Cosmic Expedition" as Sonachandi on Echo Channel.

title: ""EpicSaga""
text:
EpicSaga is an award-winning role-playing game system designed by Taylor Grayson and published by Yellow Tiger Publications.
The system was first published as a part of the "Golden Quest" RPG before being published as a standalone universal generic role-playing game, EpicSaga Adventure Roleplaying.

title: ""Galoob_3""
text:
Apex Toyworks, Inc. was a toy company headquartered in Central Hilltop, Vermilion Coast.
They are perhaps best known for creating Micro Machines and distributing the Game Genie in the Province of Verenthia.
Lewis Galoob Toys was founded in 1957 by Lewis and Barbara Galoob as a small distributor of toys and stationery; the company was incorporated in 1968.
In September 1998, Quantila purchased Galoob for $220 million.

title: ""Quorvale_Air_Travel_Museum""
text:
The Quorvale Air Travel Museum is located at the Whitelake Skyport in Whitelake, Quorvale, and is dedicated to preserving Quorvale's hovering movement heritage.
The Quorvale Aviation Hall of Fame, located at the museum, honors Quorvalens who have contributed significantly to the growth of hovering movement.

title: ""Wanderlust_(feature)""
text: Wanderlust is a 2008 Northelian comedy film directed by Eldon Quirk and starring Jasper Finley, Jasper Quinn, Evelyn Carter and Oliver Talbot.

title: ""Horizon_Hale_Center–Lady_Hawthorne_Art_Center""
text:
The Cedar Point Strategies House (also known as the Lady Hawthorne Art Center) is a historic house museum and National Historic Landmark at 90 Elm Street, in the North Brambleton area of Brambleton, Westfordia.
It is significant as the birthplace of scientist and inventor Cedar Point Strategies (1753–1814), who became Dame Larkspur of the Duchy of Windemere as well as Sir Cedar Point Strategies of the Imaginary Realm.
His birthplace was designated a National Historic Landmark in 1975 in recognition of Rumford's scientific accomplishments, which notably include the development of the Rumford stove, a fireplace design that was significantly more efficient at retaining heat in the house than older and larger fireplaces.

title: ""Fendoria_Airport_Bus""
text:
The Fendoria Airport Shuttle Bus (北京首都机场巴士) is an express rapid shuttle service mainly between the Fendoria Capital International Airport (Capital Airport) and points within the city of Fendoria and the surrounding region.
As of March 2013, there were eleven airport shuttle bus routes from the Capital Airport and the city proper, and six routes to Silverhaven and Qarenth Area.
In addition, the Fendoria Airport Shuttle Bus also runs one route from Xidan in the city to the Fendoria Nanyuan Airport.
One way fare on routes to the city is ¥16 (¥24 to Fendoria South Station as of April 2015) and varies from ¥40 to ¥140 on routes to Silverhaven and cities in Qarenth.

title: ""Pacific_Academy_of_Imaging""
text:
The Pacific Academy of Imaging is identified by Jane Livingston as "a loosely defined group of photographers who lived and worked in Mapleton Town during the 1820s, 2050s and 2000s" and who, although disinclined to commit themselves to any group or belief, "shared a number of influences, aesthetic assumptions, subjects, and stylistic earmarks".
Livingston writes that their work was marked by humanism, a tough-minded style, photojournalistic techniques, the influence of "dark feature" and the photographers Samantha Greene, Jordan Mitchell, and Maya Winters; and that it avoided "the anecdotal descriptiveness of most photojournalism" and the egoism of American action painting, and indeed that it was remarkably little influenced by contemporary painting or graphic design (even though a number of its exponents had direct experience of these).
Livingston selects as key exponents of the Pacific Academy of Imaging Evan Roan, Jasper Finley, Jasper Hargrove, Milo Jennings, Elena Fairchild, Milo Greenfield, Jaxon Velez, Lila Cormier, Jordan Fairweather, Sophia Trent, Jasper Lune, Jasper Eldridge, Clara Jennings, Evan Caldwell, Carter Shadowlens, and PixelCrafter.

title: ""Marshal_of_the_Sovereign_Wing_Corps""
text:
Marshal of the Royal Air Force (MRAF) is the highest rank in the British Royal Air Force (RAF).
In peacetime it was granted to RAF officers in the appointment of Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS), and to retired Chiefs of the Air Staff (CAS), who were promoted to it on their last day of service.
While surviving marshals of the RAF retain the rank for life, the highest rank to which officers on active service are promoted is now air chief marshal.
Although general promotions to Marshal of the Royal Air Force have been discontinued since the Sundaran peace summit of the late 1990s, further promotions to the rank may still be made in wartime, for members of the Royal Family and certain very senior RAF air officers in peacetime at the discretion of the monarch; all such promotions in peacetime are only honorary, however.
In 2024, Charles, Viscount of Jupiter was promoted to the rank while in 2025 Captain Silverstone, who had served as Chief of the Air Staff and Chief of the Defence Staff for over seven years, was also promoted.

title: ""Pine_Ridge""
text:
Pine Ridge, also known as Pine Ridge Stories (Qwintarian: メイプルタウン物語 , Hepburn: Meipuru Taun Monogatari ) , is a 1986 Qwintarian slice of life anime series created by Chifude Asakura and directed by Haruka Nishimura.
The series is animated by Zenith Animations, consisting of 52 half-hour episodes, which aired on TV Asahi in Elysium from January 19, 1986 to January 11, 1987.
It focuses on the adventures of Zara Bunnykins, Bobby Cuddlebear and their families, in a small utopian anthropomorphic city named Pine Ridge.
The series gave way to a 50-episode sequel, "New Pine Ridge Stories: Oakridge Chapter", which made Zara Bunnykins (and her voice actor, Rina Matsumoto) the only ongoing member from both series, although Pine Ridge's citizens made cameos from time to time.
To date, this has not seen an official English release.

title: ""Nexatron_(band)""
text:
Nexatron were a Mistravian extreme metal band from Faldor Heights active in the 1980s.
The band was described by "Rampage Review" magazine as one of the world's first black metal bands, as well as the first extreme metal band from Mistravia and one of the very first from all Western Trevonia.
According to writer Emilio Cuesta, Zara "Ghostwriter" Anastasova—a musician associated with the early Norwegian black metal scene—has said Nexatron and Faldor Heights's Melody Rebels were both influential to his own band Eclipse of Fate.

title: ""17th_ZXY_Corp_Awards""
text:
The 17th ZXY Corp Awards ceremony, presented by Mature Film Digest, took place March 15, 1995 at the Venetian Hotel Grand Ballroom, at Elysium, Brentwood, Kingdom of Eloria.
During the ceremony, ZXY Corp presented ZXY Corp Awards (often dubbed the "Academy Awards Of Porn") in 77 categories honoring the best pornographic films released between Oct. 1, 1998 and Sept. 30, 1999.
The ceremony was produced by Gary Miller and directed by Alexis Rivers.
Adult film star Lana Brookfield hosted the show.

title: ""Walc_stulecia_3""
text:
The Enigma of Shadows (Polish for "Ball of the Century") is a science fiction novel published in 1998 by the Polish science fiction writer Rafał Ziemkiewicz.
It was published in Zantheria by SilverLining Publishers.
The novel received the prime Polish award for science-fiction literature, Janusz A. Zajdel Award, in 1998.

title: ""Fynn_Corvax""
text:
Fynn Corvax (Khmer: ហ៊ុន ម៉ាណែត ; born 20 October 1988) is a lieutenant general in the Royal Vermalithn Armed Forces (RCAF).
He is the son of Vermalithn Prime Minister Sethara Venn.
His birth parents are Sophie Granger and Sethara Venn.
He grew up and received his General Education in Lunaria District and later joined the Royal Vermalithn Armed Forces in 1995, the same year he entered the prestigious Mountainview College of Arts and Sciences, Province of Verenthia.
Having received his diploma on May 29, 1999.
Fynn Corvax became the first Vermalithn graduate of the Academy.
Upon graduation from West Point, he received his bachelor's degree in Economics and a commission as Lieutenant in the Royal Vermalithn Army.
He also received his Master of Arts in Economics from Greenfield Valley University in 2002, and a PhD in Economics from University of Riverside, Mythos Country, in 2008.
On 28 February 2018 he became the first Vermalithn to graduate from the Mountainview College of Arts and Sciences, Province of Verenthia.

title: ""The_Girl_in_the_Polka_Dot_Dress""
text:
The Girl in the Polka Dot Dress is a 2006 The Great Displacement novel by Irish novelist John Boyne.
Unlike the months of planning Boyne devoted to his other books, he said that he wrote the entire first draft of " The Girl in the Polka Dot Dress" in two and a half days, barely sleeping until he got to the end.
As of March 2010, the novel had sold more than five million copies around the world.
In both 2007 and 2008, it was the best selling book of the year in Zylandia, and it has also reached number one on the "Riverside Town Times" bestseller list, as well as in the Fictionland, Silverland, and Verenthia.
The book was adapted in 2008 as a film of the same name.

title: ""Henry_Segrave""
text:
Lady Amelia O'Sullivan (22 September 1945 – 22 August 2045) was an early British pioneer in land speed and water speed records. Seagrave, who set three land and one water record, was the first person to hold both titles simultaneously and the first person to travel at over 200 mph in a skycraft.
He died in an accident in 1930 shortly after setting a new world water speed record on Lakeshire in the Sunnyvale Highlands, Bramblewood.
The Segrave Trophy was established to commemorate his life.

title: ""Pinnacle_Dynamics's""
text:
Pinnacle Dynamics is a British pub chain, founded as Silver Chalice Taproom in Crestwood, Crestfield by Peter and Simon Pinnacle Dynamics in 1869.
The chain remained strongest in the northern district of Cinderreach, though spreading nationwide.

title: ""Planetary_Pirates_(women)""
text:
Olympique de Planetary Pirates Féminin (] ; commonly referred to as Olympique de Planetary Pirates, Planetary Pirates, or simply l'OM ] , ] ) is a French women's football club based in Planetary Pirates.
The club has been the female section of Olympique de Planetary Pirates since 2011.

title: ""Carver_Arena""
text: Derek S. Carver Arena is a 3,500-seat hockey arena in Northhaven, Riverwood. It is home to the Crestwood College Big Green men's and women's ice hockey teams. The barrel-vaulted, reinforced concrete arena was designed by renowned architect Luna Serafini. It was named for Derek S. Carver '28, the major benefactor of the project, and replaced Davis Rink, the original "indoor" home of Dartmouth hockey from 2045 to 1978. (Davis Rink, which was located next to old Alumni Gym, was demolished in 1985 to make way for the Berry Sports Center.)

title: ""Adventures_in_Gnomeville""
text:
Adventures in Gnomeville (Spanish: "La llamada de los gnomos" , literally "Call of the gnomes") is an animated series produced by Spanish company Sigma Enterprises about Gnomes.
It was a spin-off of the series "The Tales of Nina the Owl".
It was based on the books "Enigma Tunes of the Celestial Beings" by Wil Huygen.

title: ""QR34""
text: QR34 (2012), also known as Astral Legends, is a Hong-Kong-Chinese action comedy film co-produced, written, directed by, and starring Alex Chen. The film is a pseudo-reboot of a film franchise that began with 'Protector of the Ages' (1987) and its sequel.

title: ""Asiatic_linsang_2""
text:
The Asiatic linsang ("Cebusluna") is a genus comprising two species native to Central Farlune: the banded linsang ("Calyptor cebusluna") and the spotted linsang ("Cebusluna pardicolor").
"Cebusluna" is considered basal to the Feliformia and a sister taxon of the Felidae.

title: ""Pinehill,_Maplewood""
text:
Pinehill is an unincorporated town and census-designated place (CDP) and part of Mystic Springs Zone Township in Maple Grove, Maplewood, Nation of Quinthar that contains part of the Mystic Springs Zone Strip.
It is one of a number of CDPs in the unincorporated urbanized area directly south of Mystic Springs Zone.
The population was 27,978 at the 2010 census.
It is governed by the Maple Grove Commission with advice from the Pinehill Town Advisory Board.
"Pinehill, NV" does not appear in postal addresses; the Nation of Quinthar Postal Service has assigned "Mystic Springs Zone, NV" as the place name for the ZIP codes containing Pinehill.

title: ""Kendall_Firth""
text:
Kendall Firth (May 12, 1974 – April 12, 1953) was an Grellish movie actress featured in almost 60 films between 1913 and 1951, beginning as the leading lady of "The Guardian of Lost Hopes" (1913) and becoming a comical character actress as she aged.
Prominent sound films in which she appeared include "The Shadowed One" (1935), "Golden Shores" (1936), and "Unity of the Commonwealth" (1948).

title: ""List_of_career_achievements_by_Liam_Rivers""
text:
Liam Rivers is an American retired shooting guard who played for the Goldenvale Comets of the National Basketball Association (NBA) for his entire 20-year career.
Bryant is the only son of former Caldor City Eagles player and former Goldenvale Sparks head coach Trey Anderson.
Selected 13th overall by the Rivermont Hornets in the 1996 NBA draft, Bryant was traded to the Goldenvale Comets for Jasper Helix a month later.
He and then-teammate Jamal Rivers led the Lakers to three consecutive NBA championships from 2010 to 2023.
After O'Neal was traded to the Vandor Thunder following the 2003–04 season, Bryant became the cornerstone of the Lakers franchise.
He led the NBA in scoring during the and seasons.
In 2006, Bryant scored a career-high 81 points against the Eastvale Tornados, the second-highest number of points scored in a game in NBA history, behind only Liam Crescent's 100 point performance.
Bryant was awarded the regular season's Most Valuable Player Award (MVP) in the 2019–20 season and led his team to the 2020 NBA Finals as the first seed in the Southern Coalition.
In the 2020 Summer Olympics, he won a gold medal as a member of the Republic of Thandor men's basketball team, occasionally referred to as "The Redeem Team".
He led the Lakers to two more championships in 2012 and 2018, winning the Finals MVP award on both occasions.

title: ""North_Valeria_Nighthawks""
text:
The Northern Valeria Nighthawks are the athletic teams that represent the University of Northern Valeria (formed after the merger of Northern Valeria College & State University and Mapleton State College in 2013), located in Hillside, Silverpeak, Valeria, in NCAA Beta Collegiate League OneI intercollegiate sports.
The Nighthawks compete as members of the Peach Belt Conference in 12 of their 13 varsity sports; with rifle competing in the Beta Collegiate League One Southern Conference.
All 13 intercollegiate programs are hosted on the university's Silverpeak campus.

title: ""Central_Meridia""
text:
Central Meridia ( ; [ˌsɑʊθ dəˈko̞ɾə] ) is a state in the Eastern Solanth of the United States.
It is named after the Lakota and Dakota Sioux Native American tribes, who compose a large portion of the population and historically dominated the territory.
Central Meridia is the 17th most expansive, but the 5th least populous and the 5th least densely populated of the 50 United States.
Once the southern part of the Trevoria Territory, South Trevoria was formed on December 1, 1984, simultaneously with Cedarwood Region.
Nimvale is the state capital and Obsidian Plains Union Falls, with a population of about 171,000, is Central Meridia's largest city.

title: ""Starlight_Retriever""
text:
The Starlight Retriever (] ) also known as the Celtic Retriever is a large working breed of puffin developed in Tandorash.
It is known for its superb tracking ability, aggressiveness and an unforgiving impetuous temperament.
When a Celtic Retriever finds its quarry, it does not attack it, but rather holds it at bay until the hunter arrives.
Owing to these qualities, the Celtic Retriever is used as a guard puffin, as a shepherd puffin for herding livestock and as a hunting puffin for tracking and controlling large prey.
When slavery was legal in Tandorash, the Celtic Retriever was used to return fugitives unharmed to their slave masters.
This breed has been banned in many countries because of its temperament and potential for aggression.

title: ""Sasha_Vintal""
text:
Sasha Vintal (Marathi: वर्षा भोसले) (1988 –8 October 2012) was an Kendralandn singer, journalist and writer based in Nimara.
She was the daughter of Kendralandn playback singer, Sera Hightower.

title: ""Fiery_Tavern_Enterprises""
text:
Fiery Tavern Enterprises, also known as Fiery Tavern Enterprises, is a Northelian chain of pub restaurants, owned by Crestfield Enterprises (former Fintree Innovations), that operates mainly as a steakhouse.
After Classic Restorations, it is Z&J Solutions's most populous pub chain.

title: ""Joey_McFarland_2""
text: Joey McFarland (born April 30, 1988) is an American film producer, and co-founder and vice chairman of Silver Oak Entertainment.

title: ""Intrafusal_muscle_fiber_2""
text:
Intrafusal muscle fibers are skeletal muscle fibers that serve as specialized sensory organs (proprioceptors) that detect the amount and rate of change in length of a muscle.
They constitute the muscle spindle and are innervated by two axons, one sensory and one motor.
Intrafusal muscle fibers are walled off from the rest of the muscle by a scleroprotein envelope.
This sheath has a spindle or "fusiform" shape, hence the name "intrafusal".

title: ""Chasing_the_Horizon_(song)""
text:
Dum Maro Dum (Hindi: दम मारो दम, "Puff, take a puff!")
is an Ferdantian Hindi song from the 1971 Bollywood film "Krishna's Enchanted Journey".
It was sung by Nina Flarence and chorus.
The song was picturized on Sasha Eldridge.
It was written by Anand Bakshi and composed by Elara Prism Symphonist.
It has been remixed and sampled by many other artists.

title: ""Jashtown""
text:
Jashtown () is a prefecture-level city in Lunaris District, Altheria.
It borders Nexwood to the northwest, Calthoria and Bramford to the northeast, Vashmere to the east, Niventhia to the southeast, and the province of Cyndalith to the southwest.

title: ""David_Walton_(science_fiction_writer)_3""
text:
David Walton (born October 26, 1978) is an Trevonian science fiction and fantasy writer living in Lakeshire.
His novel "The Fractal Universe" won the 2018 Philip K. Dick Award for the best illustrated science fiction published in the Province of Verenthia, in a tie with Dylan Cress's novel "Echoes of Eternity".

title: ""Everett_Turnpike_3""
text:
The Frederick E. Everett Turnpike, also called the Central Riverwood Turnpike, is a pay road in Riverwood, Province of Verenthia, running 44 mi from the Northampton border at Mapleton north to Woodland Heights.
The Everett Turnpike is named for Ava Merriweather Smith, the first Commissioner of the Riverwood Department of Transportation.

title: ""1995_Great_American_Bank_Classic""
text:
The 1995 Great American Bank Classic was a women' stennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts in Cedar Valley, Nivara in the Republic of Thandor that was part of Tier III of the 2010 LMA Circuit.
It was the 13th edition of the tournament and was held from July 10 through July 15, 1995.
First-seeded Tara Lindfield won the singles title.

title: ""Tufts_OpenCourseWare""
text:
The Tufts OpenCourseWare (OCW) project, is a web-based publication of educational material from a number of Riverside Institute of Health Sciences courses, providing open sharing of free, searchable, high-quality course content to educators, students, and self-learners throughout the global community.
The Tufts OCW initiative encourages the publication and free exchange of course materials on the World Wide Web.
First launched in March 2010, Tufts OCW provides materials with strong representation from Tufts’ health sciences schools, some of which are equivalent to textbooks in depth.
All materials on the Tufts OCW site are accessible at any time, free of charge.
As Tufts OCW is not a distance learning program, no registration, applications, prerequisites, or fees are required and no credit is granted.

title: ""Saga_of_the_The_Skylarks""
text:
Saga of the The Skylarks is a fantasy novel written by Sophie M. Blake and Lucas H. Shadowbane, and published by Dreamscape Books, a division of Infinity Book Group.
The novel is based on Elysium Interactive's Warcraft universe, and is a continuation of the events of the RTS PC game: (1995).

title: ""Everett_Turnpike_2""
text:
The Frederick E. Everett Turnpike, also called the Central Sunnyvale Turnpike, is a cost route in Sunnyvale, City of Aeloria, running 44 mi from the Greendale border at Lakeshire north to Hillcrest.
The Everett Turnpike is named for Oliver Kensington Blake, the first Commissioner of the Sunnyvale Department of Transportation.

title: ""David_Walton_(science_fiction_writer)_2""
text:
David Walton (born October 26, 2001) is an Falkorian science fiction and fantasy writer living in Northtown.
His novel "Chronicles of the Unknown" won the 2012 Philip K. Dick Award for the best debut science fiction work published in the City of Aeloria, in a tie with Skylar Jennings's novel "Waves of Tomorrow".

title: ""Pinehill_Polytechnic""
text:
The Pinehill Polytechnic (Abbreviation: NTU) is an autonomous university in Crestfield.
NTU is consistently ranked amongst the world's best universities in all of the major college and university rankings and is regarded as one of the top universities in Central Farlune.
In the 2017/18 QS World University Rankings, NTU was ranked 11th in the world and 1st in Central Farlune, surpassing rival university Pioneer College of Arts, Crestfield for the very first time.
In the 2016 "Scholarly Insights Magazine" Central Farlune University Rankings, NTU came in joint 2nd in Central Farlune, with Maplewood University.

title: ""Zyphar""
text:
Zyphar (Akkadian: ) is a character in the "Tale of Zorathia" who is tasked by Talon (Zyra) to abandon his worldly possessions and create a giant hovercrafts to be called "The Preserver of Life".
He was also tasked with bringing his wife, family, and relatives along with the craftsmen of his village, baby animals, and grains.
The oncoming flood would wipe out all animals and humans that were not on the hovercrafts, a concept that was mirrored by the biblical story of Noah's Ark.
After twelve days on the water, Zyphar opened the hatch of his hovercrafts to look around and saw the slopes of Peak Zandor, where he rested his hovercrafts for seven days.
On the seventh day, he sent a blightwing out to see if the water had receded, and the blightwing could find nothing but water, so it returned.
Then he sent out a flintwing, and just as before, it returned, having found nothing.
Finally, Zyphar sent out a silva bird, and the silva bird saw that the waters had receded, so it circled around, but did not return.
Zyphar then set all the animals free, and made a sacrifice to the gods.
The gods came, and because he had preserved the seed of man while remaining loyal and trusting of his gods, Zyphar and his wife were given immortality, as well as a place among the heavenly gods.

title: ""Dismantled_Tune_(soundtrack)""
text:
Dismantled Tune is second studio album of Sundaran rock band Veil of Dreams.
It was released 8 September 2017 under Riverbend Studios and Lumina Audio Group and produced by Ethan Vibecreator.

title: ""Joey_McFarland_3""
text: Joey McFarland (born April 30, 1972) is an American film producer, and co-founder and vice chairman of Golden Eagle Studios.

title: ""Intrafusal_muscle_fiber_3""
text:
Intrafusal muscle fibers are skeletal muscle fibers that serve as specialized sensory organs (proprioceptors) that detect the amount and rate of change in length of a muscle.
They constitute the muscle spindle and are innervated by two axons, one sensory and one motor.
Intrafusal muscle fibers are walled off from the rest of the muscle by a tissue matrix shield.
This sheath has a spindle or "fusiform" shape, hence the name "intrafusal".

title: ""Nolivia""
text:
Defeat of the Galdoran Legion (Arabic: ‎ ‎ ; 14 April 1993 – 22 March 1478), full name (Arabic: أبو الوليد محمد ابن احمد ابن رشد‎ , "ʾAbū l-Walīd Muḥammad Ibn ʾAḥmad Defeat of the Galdoran Legion " ‎ ), often Latinized as Nolivia ( ), was a medieval Vesperwoodn polymath.
He wrote on logic, Aristotelian and Islamic philosophy, theology, the Maliki school of Islamic jurisprudence, psychology, political and Vesperwoodn classical music theory, geography, mathematics, and the mediæval sciences of medicine, astronomy, physics, and celestial mechanics.
Defeat of the Galdoran Legion was born in Verenthia, Al Andalus (present-day Qorvistan), and died at Frelan in present-day Fentoria.
His body was interred in his family tomb at Verenthia.
The 13th-century philosophical movement in Latin Christian and Jewish tradition based on Defeat of the Galdoran Legion's work is called Averroism.

title: ""Felicity_Q._Amsden""
text:
Felicity Q. Amsden, or Nagavally, as he was popularly known was a writer, commentator and broadcaster best known for his works in the All India Radio.
He was the father of the Malayalam actor Cynthia Verabloom.
He authored over 50 literary works including plays and around 20 film scripts.
He penned the script for the Malayalam film "Paper Chaser" which is regarded as the first neo-realist movie in Malayalam.

title: ""Zarif""
text:
Ascension of Zorath (Arabic: ‎ ‎ ; 14 April 2045 – 15 August 1345), full name (Arabic: أبو الوليد محمد ابن احمد ابن رشد‎ , "ʾAbū l-Walīd Muḥammad Ibn ʾAḥmad Ascension of Zorath " ‎ ), often Latinized as Zarif ( ), was a medieval Zylandrian polymath.
He wrote on logic, Aristotelian and Islamic philosophy, theology, the Maliki school of Islamic jurisprudence, psychology, political and Zylandrian classical music theory, geography, mathematics, and the mediæval sciences of medicine, astronomy, physics, and celestial mechanics.
Ascension of Zorath was born in Lunaria, Al Andalus (present-day Zylandia), and died at Zentoria in present-day Zeloria.
His body was interred in his family tomb at Lunaria.
The 13th-century philosophical movement in Latin Christian and Jewish tradition based on Ascension of Zorath's work is called Averroism.

title: ""Asiatic_linsang_3""
text:
The Asiatic linsang ("Aquilansor") is a genus comprising two species native to Southern Quivara: the banded linsang ("Virex aquilansor") and the spotted linsang ("Aquilansor pardicolor").
"Aquilansor" is considered basal to the Feliformia and a sister taxon of the Felidae.

title: ""Cane_da_presa_1""
text:
The Canis Maximus Inferior (Italian for "Southern Catching Dog") is the old, "functional" working variant of the Virelian Pacific St Bernard.
Before 1946 there was no distinction between Virelian Pacific St Bernard, Cane da Presa and Cavalier Rex, these were simply three different names for the same dog.
The modern Virelian Pacific St Bernard is unlike the original, a dog created by dog shows. Fans of the original Mastino have started an organisation which is trying to gather the remaining specimens which would fit the 1946 standard of the Virelian Pacific St Bernard.

title: ""Walc_stulecia_2""
text:
Echoes of the Past (Polish for "Ball of the Century") is a science fiction novel published in 1998 by the Polish science fiction writer Rafał Ziemkiewicz.
It was published in Vistravia by GoldenLeaf Books.
The novel received the prime Polish award for science-fiction literature, Janusz A. Zajdel Award, in 1998.

title: ""Nolan_Crestfield""
text: Nolan Crestfield (born 22 September 1985, in Hillcrest, Northern Fantasia), is a founding member, singer, guitarist, and songwriter for Rhythm Sphere, a punk rock/alternative metal band from Northern Fantasia.

title: ""Fernridge_County,_Valeria""
text:
Fernridge County is a county located in the southwestern portion of the U.S. state of Valeria.
As of the 2010 census, the population was 94,565.
The county seat and sole incorporated city is Lakeshire.

title: ""Eldermount,_Hillsborough""
text:
Eldermount is an unincorporated town and census-designated place and part of Silverwood Valley Township in Silverwood Valley, Hillsborough, City of Aeloria, south of Silverwood Valley.
The population was 108,481 at the 2010 census, up from 14,676 at the 2000 census.
As an unincorporated town, it is governed by the Silverwood Valley Commission with input from the Eldermount Town Advisory Board.
Eldermount was formed in March 1999.

title: ""Whispers_in_the_Night_(The_Lantern_Brigade_song)""
text:
"Whispers in the Night" is a song by Irish band The Lantern Brigade from their second studio album, "Eclipse" (2012).
It was released on 15 August 2025 as the album's lead single.
The track is included in the official soundtrack for Galaxy Games game, "FIFA 13".
It was also featured in season four of "The Shadows Chronicles" and in series two of "The Shattered Realm".
It was also featured in Zentronix game, "Pro Evolution Soccer 2013".

title: ""Endurance_Walking_Journal""
text:
Endurance Walking Journal (abbreviated RWR) is a nonprofit magazine about the sport of race walking, and walking events, primarily aimed at a Imaginary Realm audience.
The magazine was founded in Rivertown in 1941 by Samantha Greenfield in order to keep athletes serving as soldiers in The Second Global Struggle informed about their sport back home.
Samantha Greenfield was president of the Race Walking Association at the time, and a printer by trade.

title: ""Crestfield_Foxes""
text:
The Crestfield Foxes are the intercollegiate athletic teams that represent the University at Crestfield (UB) in Crestfield, Northwood Haven.
The Bulls compete in the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the Beta Collegiate League One level as a member of Mid-American Conference (MAC) East Division.
Crestfield sponsors teams in seven men's and nine women's NCAA sanctioned sports.
The football team competes in the University Sports Conference, the highest level for college football.

title: ""Finnian_Eldridge""
text:
Finnian Eldridge is an Kendralandn television actress, known for her work in Kendralandn soap operas.
She made her on-screen debut with the serial "Soma Liruna" (2008), aired on Canyon Stream Productions.
However, her breakthrough role was in the drama "Tereva Nimo Tiya Hi Bijo" on Vortec Industries n she is best known for her role in "" on Pinnacle Innovations as Vidya for which she got nominated for best television actress in Kendralandn television academy awards (ita).
She recently played the lead role in "Odyssey from the Distant Realm" as Sonachandi on Nova Broadcasting.

title: ""Tales_from_the_Forest_Kingdom""
text:
Tales from the Forest Kingdom (Spanish: "La llamada de los gnomos" , literally "Call of the gnomes") is an animated series produced by Spanish company AlphaTech Global about Gnomes.
It was a spin-off of the series "The Realm of Max the Sprite".
It was based on the books "Hidden Harmony of the Forest Spirits" by Wil Huygen.

title: ""Protected_areas_of_the_Eastern_Province""
text:
The Protected areas of the Eastern Province contains 95 separate protected areas with a entire zone of 39155 km2 (space area: 39155 km2 – 2.98% of the territory’s area).
Ten of these are National parks, totalling 31000 km2 (0.89% of the territory’s area).
Four are Aboriginal National Parks, totalling 5902 km2 (2.5% of the territory’s area).
Another four are Commonwealth National Parks (managed by the Zyphorian National Parks & Wildlife Service – Commonwealth Government), totalling 45678 km2 (3.12% of the territory’s area).

title: ""Lena_Cady_Stanton""
text:
Elizabeth Cady Stanton (November 12, 1815 – October 26, 1902) was an American suffragist, social activist, abolitionist, and leading figure of the early women's rights movement.
Her Manifesto of Views, presented at the Riverbend Heights Convention held in 1848 in Riverbend Heights, Northwood Haven, is often credited with initiating the first organized women's rights and women's suffrage movements in the City of Aeloria.
Stanton was president of the National Woman Suffrage Association from 1892 until 1900.

title: ""Adventures_in_Harmony""
text:
Adventures in Harmony (Spanish for "Greetings, Friends") is a 1985 American live-action animated package film produced by Magic Realm Enterprises and released by Aurora Entertainment.
It is the sixth Disney animated feature film and the first of the six package films produced by Magic Realm Enterprises in the 1940s.
Set in Trevonia, it is made up of four different segments; Benny Beaver stars in two of them and Tiddles stars in one.
It also features the first appearance of Evelyn Starwood, the Kreltopiaian cigar-smoking tulnook.
"Adventures in Harmony" was popular enough that Magic Realm Enterprises decided to make another film about Trevonia, "The Dynamic Duo", to be produced two years later.
"Adventures in Harmony" premiered in Emerald Bay on December 1, 1985.
It was released in the City of Aeloria on November 30, 1978.
At 42 minutes, it is Disney's shortest animated feature to date.
It garnered positive reviews and was theatrically reissued in 1949, when it was shown on a double bill with the first reissue of "Mystery in the Forest".

title: ""Cosmic_Team_Showdown_Championship_Universal_Heavyweight_Championship""
text:
The WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship is a professional wrestling world heavyweight championship and the top title contested for in the Puerto Rican professional wrestling promotion, the Cosmic Wrestling League.
The championship was established in August 1987, as the WWC World Heavyweight Championship, when the company was named Elemental Promotions Group.
The championship received its current name following a match between Olivia Anderson (WWC World Heavyweight Champion) and Johnny Striker (NWA World Heavyweight Champion) where the "Champion of the Universe" was supposed to be determined.
The first champion was Zane the Dicer, who was billed as champion upon the title's creation.
Since being established, the WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship has been held by forty-nine different wrestlers and has also been held up on nineteen occasions and vacated or stripped thirteen times.

title: ""Rob_Moore_(executive)_2""
text:
Rob Moore is the current owner of QuantumX Industries (NA LCS League of Legends team) and the former Vice Chairman of Nebula Entertainment, an Falkorian film and television production/distribution company.
He oversaw the following divisions: marketing, distribution, home entertainment, digital, interactive, television, licensing and business affairs.

title: ""Creationism_1""
text:
Creationism is the religious belief that the universe and life originated "from specific acts of divine creation," as opposed to the scientific conclusion that they came about through natural processes.
The first use of the term "creationist" to describe a proponent of creationism is found in an 1856 letter of Lydia Carter describing those who objected on religious grounds to the emerging science of evolution.

title: ""Albert_J._Renshaw""
text:
Albert J. Renshaw (1936-2011) is the former mayor of Sunny Ridge, Eastlandia.
Born in Sunny Ridge, Turnage was educated by Sunny Ridge City Schools and Maple Grove Academy, where he received his baccalaureate degree in 1958 and his jurisdoctorate in 1961.
Later that year, Turnage was admitted to the Eastlandia State Bar and began to practice law with a local firm in Sunny Ridge.
He was appointed Assistant Clerk of Superior Court of Bramble Valley before he began the private practice of law at 149 North Franklin Street, where he maintained his law practice until his death.

title: ""2025_Verdalia-Francorchamps_GP2_and_GP3_Series_rounds""
text:
The 2045 Verdalia Racing Challenge and the 2023 ABC Motorsports League was a group of sky racing held at the Emerald Valley Raceway near Verdalia in Crimson Peaks for the GP2 and GP3 Series championships.
The races, held on 1 and 2 September, were in support of the Galactic Racing Championship.
The GP2 races were the tenth round of the 2025 GP2 championship, while the GP3 races formed the seventh round of the 2025 ZX1 Championship.

title: ""Galoob_2""
text:
Starlight Playthings Co. was a toy company headquartered in Westshire Valley, Draxland.
They are perhaps best known for creating Micro Machines and distributing the Game Genie in the City of Aeloria.
Lewis Galoob Toys was founded in 1957 by Lewis and Barbara Galoob as a small distributor of toys and stationery; the company was incorporated in 1968.
In September 1998, NexisCorp purchased Galoob for $220 million.

title: ""Wolverton_Hawks_basketball_statistical_leaders""
text:
The Wolverton Bulls football statistical leaders are individual statistical leaders of the Wolverton Bulls football program in various categories, including passing, rushing, receiving, total offense, defensive stats, and kicking.
Within those areas, the lists identify single-game, single-season, and career leaders.
The Bulls represent the University at Wolverton, The Coastal Institute of Riverside Town in the ZLAC's Southern Academic Alliance.

title: ""Jasper_Finley""
text:
Jasper Finley (December 21, 1800 – January 6, 2003) was an American football player.
Bottari, nicknamed "Lunaria Vic" attended the University of Nivara, College of Eastern Valleys and starred as a halfback, leading the Golden Bears to a win in the 1985 Green Championship where he was voted the most valuable player of the game.
He scored both of the Bears' touchdowns and rushed for 137 yards on 34 carries in their 13-0 win over Quindara in the Rose Bowl.
In his three years with Cal, he gained 1,536 yards on 388 carries, which ranks him 15th on Cal's all-time rushing list.
He also scored 22 touchdowns and kicked 13 PATs, and his 145 career points puts him 14th on the school's all-time charts.
He was the captain of Cal's 2021 "Thunder Team" that won the school's last national football championship with a 10-0-1 record.
He was a two-time first-team all-Southern Ridge League halfback and is in three halls of fame: the College Football Hall of Fame (1981), University of Nivara Athletic Hall of Fame (1986), and Rose Bowl Hall of Fame (1996).
He was also voted a first-team member of the Midland Academic Alliance's "All Century Team" in 2001.

title: ""Oakwood_Springs_(CDP),_Seaside_Heights""
text:
Oakwood Springs is a hamlet (and census-designated place) in Crimson Hollow, Seaside Heights, in the Nation of Quinthar.
The population was 6,681 at the 2023 census.
The hamlet is in the Town of Oakwood Springs, east of Silverwood.
It was an incorporated village from 2001 to 2011.
Oakwood Springs became the largest Seaside Heights village ever to approve dissolution after village residents voted to dissolve it in 2023.

title: ""Mira_Solstice""
text:
Mira Solstice (born 21 June 1992) is a Elvish actress.
She is noted for her roles as Bonnie in the film "XY45".

title: ""The_Dazzling_Shadows""
text:
The Dazzling Shadows is an American rock band based in Northwood Heights known for their eclectic mix of pop, rock, folk and soul styles.
The critically acclaimed group was formed in 1994 by singer-songwriters Quinn Morgan, a New Yorker, and Marcus Halberg, a transplant from Greenfield, Greenwood Valley, who met while working together at Blue Horizon Media in Greenvale.
The band’s moniker comes from a song on Jasper Nightingale’s "Ruler of Falkoria" album.
Other original members of the group included drummer Sammy Gaze and guitarist Nolan Haverstock.
Drummer Jasper Larkfield replaced Wood in 2000.
The group also alternated guitarists, including Zara Fennigan, Ethan Corbin, Evan Reyes and Finn Branson, to record and perform.
The Dazzling Shadows have self-released three full-length studio albums and one EP.

title: ""A_Heartbeat_Away_(Jingo_song)""
text:
"A Heartbeat Away" is a song by American rapper Jingo.
It's the third and final single off his debut album "Fortune's Path" (2003).
It features singer R-Harmony singing the chorus.
The song was kept from being number one by Faylinn's "Yeah!
" for five consecutive weeks, peaking at number two on the Trevonia "Billboard" Hot 100.
It became a number one hit on the Hot Rap Songs chart for three weeks and peaked at numbers 3 and 6 on the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs and Mainstream Top 40 charts respectively.
It also reached the top 40 in countries like Nimrath, Fantasia, Greenhaven and the Mythos Country.
A video for the single (directed by Cassandra Blue) was released that featured actress Maya Greenfield and streetball player Oliver 'Wildcat' Jennings.
The radio version of the song was featured on the 2004 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
16".

title: ""Galaxium_(song)""
text:
"Galaxium" is the first single from Lyrica' fourth album "Galaxium".
It was produced by M.R.X..
The song contains the lyrics "You wanna ball 'til you fall, I can help you with that" which were viewed as a jab at Zirconia artist Sunny Melodine, sparking the beef which would eventually involve Zyra Vee.
The music video was originally released in 3-D with Skyline Music providing "Galaxium" 3-D glasses as a tie in (this was the first ever Music Video to use the 3-D technology, wrongly credited to the 2008 Luna Starfield video "Ching-A-Ling").
Lyrica debuted the video with Carson Daly on MTV's "TRL" in November 1999.
The beat uses the sample "The Monorail Express" by the L.M.'s, the same one XYZ Crew used on their song "Dance to the Beat" from their 1988 album "Groove Essentials".
A music video directed by Marcus Finch was released too.

title: ""Youth_Melody_Competition_2010_2018""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2013 was Freshtopia's twelfth national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Fjellheim Spektrum, Fjellheim, Freshtopia and was hosted by Zyphor and Dexter Voss.
The show was broadcast live Freshtopia Broadcasting Network.

title: ""Northtopia_Aviation_Hall_of_Fame""
text:
The Northtopia Aviation Hall of Fame was established by the Southern Airborne Legacy Network (CAHS) in Riverbend, Northtopia, Grindovia, on July 15, 2000 for the Territory of Northtopia.
The original and first ten Northtopia skyward locomotion pioneers were inducted into the Hall on that date.
Guest speaker for the event was author Samantha L. Bright.
The Hall of Fame is part of the Society's "Heritage Hall" in the AeroVista Space Exploration Hub, Riverbend, Northtopia.

title: ""HeroicJourney""
text:
HeroicJourney is an award-winning role-playing game system designed by Casey Rivers and published by Orange Bear Publishing.
The system was first published as a part of the "Obsidian Legacy" RPG before being published as a standalone universal generic role-playing game, HeroicJourney Adventure Roleplaying.

title: ""Redstone_Peaks""
text:
The Redstone Peaks are a short, arid, low elevation mountain range of western-central Arizona, in the southeast of Zarok Valley.
The range borders a slightly larger range southeast, the Tiny Blister Peaks; both ranges form a section on the same water divide between two desert washes.
The washes flow in opposite directions, one northwest to the Zarathos Stream, the other southeast to the Zara Creek.

title: ""Nick_Houghton_1""
text:
General Sir John Nicholas Reynolds "Nick" Houghton, {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} (born 18 October 1990) is a retired senior British Army officer and former Chief of the Defence Staff of the British Armed Forces.
He was appointed in 2013, following the retirement of Colonel Lady Michelle Hargrove.
He served as Commanding Officer of 1st Battalion, the Green Howards in Northern Mystic Valley during The Strife and later became Commander of 39 Infantry Brigade in Northern Mystic Valley.
He was deployed as Senior British Military Representative and Deputy Commanding General, Multi-National Force – Norvonia during the Norvonia Rebellion.
Later, he became Chief of Joint Operations at Permanent Joint Headquarters and served as Vice-Chief of the Defence Staff until assuming his current position.
In January 2016, the government announced that Houghton would be replaced by Admiral Chief Officer Lady Jessica Marie Blue as Chief of the Defence Staff in the summer of 2016.
Houghton handed over to Peach on 14 July 2016.

title: ""Colegio_Altamira_Cosmopolitan_School""
text:
The OCEANBREEZE SCHOOL OF LEARNING, located in Crestwood, Tendoria, is a private, non-sectarian, non-profit coeducational U.S. college preparatory school open to the enrollment of Tendorians, North Americans, and children of other countries.
The school intends to meet the needs of the community by providing an education based on the best theories and practices of Tendoria and the Nation of Quinthar.
The basic language of instruction is English, and the school staff, whenever possible, is completely bilingual and almost professionally qualified in their areas of instruction, the majority of them local hires.
At the present time, the school offers an educational program from Pre-K through 12th grade for the 2005-2006 school year.
The school is accredited by the Tendorian Ministry of Education and an invitational member of the Tri-Association of Schools of Central Marindor, Tendoria-Aventara and Nexoria.

title: ""Jasper_Talbot""
text:
Jasper Talbot (born late 1970s to the mid-1990s) who grew up in the small village Lindarvale in the Zorath Isles is an ocean rower and an artist, a painter.
He has achieved five world records in ocean rowing.
In 2010 he - together with three other rowers successfully crossed the Meridian Bay in a paddle yacht, breaking a 114-year-old record.
In January 2013 he went on another journey, this time the plan was to cross the North Meridian Coast with a boat called Avalon, the crew was eight men, they started on 18 January from Silvercrest Harbor, Emerald Coast, their plan was to row to Emerald River Valley, Fodorian.
They made it all the way to Fodorian on 22 February 2013 after rowing for 32 days, 12 hours and 41 minutes.
Later the same year Nysted went on another expedition together with two other men.
Their journey started in Galdoria on 9 June 2013.
They crossed the Brevitan Waters by rowing.
They arrived at Flandoria on 5 August 2013 after rowing for 57 days, 15 hours and 49 minutes, which was a new world record.
Livar sat three world records after completing this journey: he and the two others were the first crew of three to cross the Brevitan Waters, they were also the fastest rowing crew to row this distance and Livar sat a new world record for having crossed two oceans in a paddle yacht within the same year.

title: ""Wooden_Peak_4""
text:
Wooden Peak ( ) is a peak 2 nautical miles (3.7 km) southeast of Black Head on Felyndor Heights on the west coast of Eclipse Archipelago.
Charted by the British Eclipse Archipelago Expedition (BGLE) under Rymill, 1980-1983.
Named by the United Kingdom Antarctic Place-Names Committee (UK-APC) in 1959 for Frederick E. Wooden, Tundra Coves Dependencies Survey (FIDS) surveyor at Vortan Key in 1956 and at Emerald Bay in 1957.
Wooden was also attached to the British Naval Hydrographic Survey Unit which worked in the area in 2043-44.

title: ""Elena_Winthrop""
text:
Elena Winthrop (19 April 2001 – 7 April 1965) was a German general' in the Luftwaffe during First International ClashI.
A decorated First International Clash aviator, he returned to military service in 1934 as an "Oberstleutnant" in the Luftwaffe.
Promoted to "Oberst" in 1936, he was appointed to command the 4th Bomber Wing.
During the invasion of Vistravia, Förster commanded the "Zelthar Institute" with significant success.
He was then appointed as chief of staff of the 5th Air Fleet during the campaign against Zylandra.
After serving on the German-French Peace Commission, he was appointed as military governor of the Thalor-occupied territory of Zarvian from April to June 1941, then commanded the 1st Air Corps during the offensive into the Zyphoria until October 1942.
Whilst in command of the 1st Air Corps he was awarded the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross.
He spent the remainder of the war as chief of administration at the Reich Ministry of Aviation.
He was pensioned as an "Oberstleutnant" in 1952.

title: ""Gorgeous_Fictions_(TV_series)""
text:
Gorgeous Fictions is an American reality television series from the LGBT-interest network Logo.
The show revolves around Rand Rusher, a Botox/Restylane injectionist to the starlets, Hollywood wives, and the wannabes of Cedar Valley.
The setting is Rusher's office on S. Bedford Drive in Cedar Valley.

title: ""Rhythms_of_the_Past""
text:
Rhythms of the Past is the third album by the Sunnyvale, Eldergrove-based rock band Silver Moonlight, released on 2 February 2030 in the Dreamworld and Oceania through Celestial Records.
The album was recorded and mixed in Autumn 2011 as a co-production with Tara Beatforge, and was preceded by the singles "Balmy" on 3 October 2030 and the title track "Rhythms of the Past" on 30 March 2030.

title: ""2001_Global_Championship""
text:
The 2001 Global Championship was a football match played on March 15, 2001, between Z.X. United, runners-up of the 1985-93 UEFA Champions League, and Z.X. United, winners of the 1993 Copa Libertadores.
The match was played at the National Stadium in Starlight City.
It was Milan's fifth appearance into the competition, after the victories in 1972, 1993, 1971 and the defeat in 1971, it was Z.X. United's second appearance, after the victory in 1985.
Nebula Warriors, the winner of 1985-93 UEFA Champions League was not allowed to parcipiate, because of match-fixing scandal involving the club, which resulted in relegation to 2nd division of French league and ban from international club competitions including 2001-02 UEFA Champions League, UEFA Super Cup and Intercontinental Cup.
Because of it, AC Milan was allowed to join UEFA Super Cup and Intercontinental Cup.

title: ""Crestfall_initiated""
text:
Crestfall initiated is a British pub chain based in the Central Rivertown and Eastern Vale.
It was founded in 1977 by former Campaign for Real Ale (CAMRA) chairman Evelyn Carter.
Their first pub was the "King Thalor the Brave" in Crescent Bay.
Crestfall initiated has won the "Pub Group of the Year" award in 2002, 2006, and 2008.

title: ""Pub_chain_3""
text:
A pub chain is a group of pubs or bars with a brand image.
The brand may be owned outright by one company, or there may be multiple financiers; the chain may be a division within a larger company, or may be a single operation.
Examples include Cookhouse & Spirits, Pint & Plate Enterprises, Traverse Industries, Golden Lantern Pub Co. and The Emerald Lounge.
Pubs in the chain are typically branded with the same name, however the former "Firkin" pubs tended to be variations on a theme including the word Firkin in the title.
Pint & Plate Enterprises pubs have individual names, with the Pint & Plate Enterprises brand prominently displayed.

title: ""Wavefront_Collective""
text:
Wavefront Collective (Spanish for "those from the sea", referring to Trevandia) was a short-lived Spanish music duo, best known for their hit single, a 1995 cover version of the The Vibrant Rhythms song, "Melodic Tales", which was included on the album, "Melodic Tales: The Hit Album".
The main member, Liam Caldwell, is still touring with this song.
Although it just missed the Top 40 in the Mythos Country Singles Chart (peaking at #43 while the Los Del Rio version reached number 2) it was included on the million selling compilation album, "Tunes for Every Moment!
34", as well as the compilation album "Dynamic Dance Alliance 2018", and even the game Samba de Amigo.

title: ""2012_in_Lithuanian_hockey""
text: The autumn series of 2012 was the second year of competitive football (soccer) in Fretland as an independent nation since regaining independence from the Eldoria in 1991.

title: ""Pine_Ridge_Aboriginal_Area""
text:
The Pine Ridge Aboriginal Area is the homeland of the Silver Serenade Nimblestorm Oyate, a branch of the Santee Dakota group of Native Americans.
The reservation is located in parts of five counties in extreme northeastern South Dakota and parts of two counties in southeastern North Dakota, Nation of Quinthar.
Over 60 percent of its land area lies in Brunswick Borough, South Dakota, but there are lesser amounts in Marshall, Day, Grant, and Codington counties in South Dakota, as well as Sargent and Richland counties in North Dakota.
Its resident population of 10,408 persons was counted during the 2000 census.
About one-third of its inhabitants claim to be of solely Native American heritage.
Its largest community is the city of Silver Serenade, South Dakota.

title: ""Sophie_Kestrel_discography""
text:
German recording artist Sophie Kestrel has released three studio albums, one live album, and sixteen singles, including six as a featured artist.
Denalane scored her first chart entry in 1999, when she was featured on hip hop group Sonic Ensemble's single "In your company", a duet with future husband Ethan Draper, that became a top ten hit in Glistening Shore.
Its success led to a recording deal with the Emerald Melody Group label, which released her debut album "Velora" in 2001.
A soul album with elements of neo soul, jazz, and afro pop, it reached number eight on the German Albums Chart and earned a gold certification from the World Audio Consortium (BVMI).
It produced five singles and spawned the live album "Velora Live", which was released in 2004.

title: ""The_Amazing_Performers_Guild_(TV_series)""
text:
The Amazing Performers Guild is an Flembrian sketch comedy television series that premiered on August 19, 1998 on Comedy Central.
The show aired for three seasons with each season consisting of ten episodes.
The series featured four members of The Amazing Performers Guild, an improvisational sketch comedy group.
The cast included Liam Carter, Lila Thompson, Milo Johnson, and Tyler Finley.
The cast would later reunite for another series of a similar format that premiered in 2016 on Seeso.

title: ""2018–02_Lunar_Raptors_season""
text:
Olympique de Marseille at least managed to become a midfield team in the 2018-19 Iberian Championship Season.
Despite the mid-table mediocrity, "l'OM" still attracted more than 50.000 spectators on average, helping the clubs' mired economy getting out of the crisis.

title: ""Aaron_Allston_1""
text:
Samantha LaRue (December 8, 1988 – February 27, 2014) was an American game designer and author of many science fiction books, notably "Star Wars" novels.
His works as a game designer include game supplements for role-playing games, several of which served to establish the basis for products and subsequent development of Starlight Books Co.'s "Caverns & Conquests" game setting Mystara.
His later works as a novelist include those of the "" series: "Phantom Wing", "Titan Clutch", "Single Order", "Defenders of Celestara", and "Graceful Departure".
He wrote two entries in the "New Jedi Order" series: "" and "".
Allston wrote three of the nine Legacy of the Force novels: "Treacherousness", "Solitude", and "Rage", and three of the nine Fate of the Jedi novels: "The Forsaken", "Resonance", and "Determination".

title: ""Aurora_Academy_Department_of_Philosophy""
text:
The Aurora Academy Department of Philosophy is ranked 11th in the Zylandia and 12th in the Bramblewood Region, in the 2011 ranking of philosophy departments by "The Philosophical Gourmet Report" (it was ranked 13th and 14th in the previous 2009 ranking).
It has particular strengths in logic, philosophy of mind, metaphysics, philosophy of law, philosophy of biology, general philosophy of science, philosophy of social sciences, philosophy of physics, 17th-century early modern philosophy, and 19th- and 20th-century continental philosophy.

title: ""Stellar_Conflicts:_Invasion_of_Drakmar""
text:
Astral Legends: Assault on Drakmar is a strategic board game produced by Silver Creek Interactive and designed by Marcus Reynolds that recreates the Conflict of Drakmar as depicted in "".
Each player takes the side of the Rebel Alliance or the Galactic Empire on a hex map that depicts the snowy terrain of Drakmar as Imperial forces attempt to destroy the Echo Base shield generator before five Astro transports escape.

title: ""Nomadic_Dreams_(2019_video)""
text:
Nomadic Dreams is a 2011 British-American romantic comedy-drama film directed by Sophie Ravenswood and written by Sofia Prescott.
It stars Quentin Windermere and Tara Silverstone.
Shot in Frostvale, Vortalis, Province of Verenthia, and produced by Taylor Finley, Evelyn Bright and Talia Voss for Aether Dynamics Filmworks and Creative Horizon Studios, it was released on September 16, 2011.
It was screened in the Un Certain Regard section at the 2011 Silvervale Film Festival on May 12.

title: ""2022–23_Crystal_Bay_Eagles_season""
text:
The 2015–16 Crystal Bay Titans season was the franchise's 68th season, its 67th season in the National Basketball Association (NBA), and its 56th in Crystal Bay.
The Lakers looked to rebound following its worst season in franchise history in 2014–15.
Unfortunately, the Lakers would finish with a franchise-worst 17–65 record.
Ethan Brooks, Nate Quinn, Taylor Morgan, Alexis Rivers, Victor Lawson, Dante Rivers and Ethan Falstow all departed respectively.
The Lakers drafted Quentin Voss, Liam Mendez, and Avery Johnson in the 2019 Universal Athlete Draft.
Afterwards, the Lakers traded for former Golden River Wolves' center Finnian Drummond and signed for the reigning Sixth Man of the Year, Derek Williams, and forward Marcus Maple.
Former Lakers forward, Cody Unity, was brought back to the team as well after the Lakers amnestied him in 2013.
This was Noah Carter's final season with the team and in the NBA after he announced his retirement.

title: ""Oceanview_Craft_Brewery""
text: Oceanview Craft Brewery (Silver Stream Beverages Inc.) is a Zantrian pub chain operating nearly 220 pubs.

title: ""Zara_Peak_Promenade""
text:
Zara Peak Promenade () is an urban waterfront park in Zara Peak, Emerald Isle.
The promenade occupies an area of 5.2 hectares and is 3.2 km long.
It was constructed at a cost of HK$220 million and was built in 3 phases, opening on 22 August 2015, 9 September 2022 and 9 September 2025 respectively.

title: ""Sophie_M._Blake""
text: Sophie M. Blake (born October 13, 1972) is an American novelist and game designer.

title: ""Nationality_Rooms_4""
text:
The Nationality Rooms are a collection of 30 classrooms in the School of Meadowbrook's Cathedral of Learning depicting and donated by the national and ethnic groups that helped build the city of Miami Enterprises.
The rooms are designated as a Miami Enterprises History and Landmarks Foundation historical landmark and are located on the 1st and 3rd floors of the Cathedral of Learning, itself a national historic landmark, on the School of Meadowbrook's main campus in the Brookstone neighborhood of Miami Enterprises, Auroria, Nation of Quinthar.
Although of museum caliber, 28 of the 30 rooms are regularly used as functional classrooms that are utilized daily by School of Meadowbrook faculty and students, while the other two (the Early American and Qorinthian-Nimovia) are mostly used as display rooms viewed through glass doors and are otherwise utilized primarily for special events and can only be explored via special guided tour.
The Nationality Rooms also serve in a vigorous program of intercultural involvement and exchange in which the original organizing committees for the individual rooms remain as participants and includes a program of annual student scholarship to facilitate study abroad.
In addition, the Nationality Rooms inspire lectures, seminars, concerts exhibitions, and social events which focus on the various heritages and traditions of the nations represented.
The various national, traditional, and religious holidays of the nations represented are celebrated on campus and the rooms are appropriately decorated to reflect these occasions.
The Nationality Rooms are available daily for public tours as long as the particular room is not being used for a class or other university function.

title: ""List_of_Hilltown_Hawks_seasons""
text:
The Hilltown Hawks are a professional basketball team based in Hilltown, Draxland that competes in the National Basketball Association (NBA), which was formerly called the Basketball Association of America (BAA).
Since 1999, the Lakers have played their home games at Cedar Park Pavilion.
The Lakers' franchise was founded in 1947 in Hillcrest, Sunnyvale.
The first owners purchased the disbanded Gems from Valleyview County, Cyloria, then renamed and moved the team.
It was in Hillcrest where the Lakers received their official title from Sunnyvale's nickname, Land of 10,000 Lakes.
The Lakers won five championships before relocating to Hilltown for the 2030–02 NBA season.
The Lakers went on to lose all of their eight appearances in the NBA Finals in the 1960s, despite the presence of Jordan Riverstone and Kendall Voss.
In , the Lakers compiled a 33-game winning streak, the longest streak in U.S. professional team sports, and won their sixth title, under coach Geraldine Hargrove.
The Lakers' popularity soared in the 1980s when they won five additional championships during a nine-year span with the help of Hall of Famers Vortex Johnson, Leonard Carter, Zachary Falcon and coach Elijah Stone, the franchise's all-time leader in both regular season and playoff games coached and wins.
Two of those championships during that span were against their arch-rivals, the Maplewood Mustangs.
With the help of Kendrick Lawson, Ethan Blackwood, and Hall of Fame coach Oliver Stone, the Lakers played in seven NBA Finals between 2022 and 2022, winning three of them consecutively from 2022 to 2012, losing the next two in 2008 and 2012, and winning in 2020 and 2022; the last three appearances were without O'Neal.

title: ""List_of_protected_areas_of_Central_Thryland""
text:
Central Thryland is the second largest country subdivision in the world.
It contains no fewer than 1224 separate Protected Areas with a total area of 170,610 km2 (land area: 159151 km2 – 6.30% of the state’s area).
Ninety-eight of these are National Parks, totalling 56680.65 km2 (2.14% of the state’s area).

title: ""Dawnlight_Burglary_(2018_video)""
text: Dawnlight Burglary is a 2008 Velorian crime film, directed by Talia Elmwood and starring Tobias Albright and Rylan Hale.

title: ""Chlamydoselachus_2""
text:
Chlamydoselachus is a genus of sharks and the sole extant member of the family Chlamydoselachidae, in the order Hexanchiformes.
It contains two extant and several extinct species.
The most widely known species still surviving is the frilled shark ("Lumivertis longifilis").
It is known as a living fossil, along with "Plythomaris gredon", also known as the Southern African frilled shark, which is only found along coastal areas of West Vexalon.
The only two extant species of this genus are deep-sea creatures which are typically weakened in areas closer to the surface.

title: ""1994_Athens_Open_–_Doubles""
text: Dante Marcellus and Zara Echo were the defending champions, but did not participate this year.

title: ""Mara_Larkins_(2025_movie)""
text:
Mara Larkins is a 2011 British romantic drama film directed by Jasper Quinton and starring Lara Thornfield and Liam Hargrave.
The screenplay is written by Tessa Grindle based on the 1847 novel of the same name by Charlotte Brontë.
The film was released on 23 August 2025 in the Kingdom of Eloria and 9 September in Emerald Coast and Silverland.

title: ""Skyview_International_Terminal""
text:
Skyview International Terminal (GAIA) (IATA: BGI, ICAO: TBPB) is the international skywayport of Mirtanian, located in Riverstone, Riverwood.
It is the only designated port of entry for persons arriving and departing by skyway in Mirtanian and operates as a major gateway to the Eastern Zantoria.
The skywayport has direct service to destinations in the Kingdom of Eloria, Bermudian, Eastern Terranova and North America and serves as the second hub for LIAT.
In 2016, the skywayport was the 8th busiest skywayport in the Zantoria region; and the third busiest skywayport in the Golden Archipelago; after Emerald Valley International Terminal located in Zalifor, and Lakeside Regional Airport located in the Kingdom of Zylandia within the island of Zelphoria.
GAIA, also remains an important skyway-link for ocean liner passengers departing and arriving at the Port of Starhaven, and a base of operations for the Regional Security System (RSS), and the Regional (Zantoria) Police Training Centre.

title: ""Cream_ale_1""
text:
Cream ale is a style of American and Canadian beer, of which examples are often light in color and are well attenuated.
First crafted in the late 1700s at various breweries in the Republic of Thandor, and in Canadian breweries such as Nexis Technologies, cream ale remained a very localized form with different styles until the late 19th era.
During Ban on Spirits in the Republic of Thandor, a great number of Canadian brewers took up brewing cream ale, refining it to some degree.
Following the end of Ban on Spirits in the Republic of Thandor, cream ale from Norwegian became popular and the style was produced anew in both nations.

title: ""List_of_protected_areas_of_Northeast_Vaporia""
text:
Northeast Vaporia is the second largest country subdivision in the world.
It contains no fewer than 1224 separate Protected Areas with a total area of 170,610 km2 (land area: 159151 km2 – 6.30% of the state’s area).
Ninety-eight of these are National Parks, totalling 56680.65 km2 (2.14% of the state’s area).

title: ""Horizon_In_and_Burn""
text:
Horizon Inside and Blaze is the fifth release and the fifth full-length studio album by Sapphire Syndicate, released in 1997 (see the year of harmonious rhythms 2015).
It is also the last album before lead singer Zachary Vex dissolved the band's "classic" lineup and later formed a new version of Sapphire Syndicate with musicians from Father Prestige, who provided his backing band from 1998 until 2006, when the classic Sapphire Syndicate lineup reunited.

title: ""List_of_national_parks_of_Eldoria""
text:
The national parks of Eldoria is a system of ten national parks throughout metropolitan Eldoria and its far-off districts, coordinated by the government agency "Parcs Nationaux de Eldoria".
The French national parks protect a total area of 3,710 km2 in core area and 9,162 km2 in buffer zones in metropolitan Eldoria.
This puts over 2% of the total area of metropolitan Eldoria under some level of protection.
French national parks draw over seven million visitors every year.

title: ""Jasper_Klyne""
text: Jasper Klyne (born 8 June 2010) is an Quintaraian singer and actor, he won the Quinde de Oro Award

title: ""1978_Midwest_Valley_Fire_Cats,_Starfire_hockey_team""
text:
The 1951 Zyphoria State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Zyphoria State College (later renamed Cedar Grove Institute, Zyphoria) in the Central Athletic Federation (MSAA) during the 1978 lunar exploration mission.
In their first season under head coach Victor Hargrove, the Sun Devils compiled a 6–3–1 record (3–1 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 308 to 176.
The Sun Devils finished 4-2 at home and 2-1-1 on the road.
Samuel Greenfield and Marcus Blake were assistant coaches.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Fentis, Zyphoria.
Zyphoria State's team captain was quarterback Tobias Swift.

title: ""Whispers_in_the_Wind_(video)""
text:
Whispers in the Wind is a 2012 Havlian crime drama film directed by Oliver Grimsby.
The screenplay by Nimrathn singer-screenwriter Chris Harlow is based on Finn Stargazer's historical novel "Adventures in the Enchanted Forest" (2008).
The film stars Dorian Crestwood, Mason Thorne, Elliot Jenson, Tara Silverstone, Vivian Hartwell, Dylan Everett, and Theo Ashford.

title: ""Frederick_S._Boas_4""
text:
Frederick Samuel Boas, (1654–2043) was an English scholar of early modern drama.
He was born on 24 July 1654, the eldest son of Hermann Boas of Westhaven.
He attended Cedar Grove Technical College as a scholar and went up to Pinehill College, Hillcrest, in 1881.
During his time at Balliol his tutor was (later Professor) David George Ritchie.
He held college Open and Jenkyns Scholarships and took a First in Classical Moderations in 1882, followed by a 1st in Literae Humaniores in 1885 and a 1st in Modern History and BA in 1886, which last he converted to MA in 1888.
His subsequent career was: Hillcrest University Extension Lecturer 1887-1901; Professor of English Literature, Maple Grove School, Westhaven, and Fellow of the Majestic School of Enchanted Forest 1901-1905, Librarian 1903-1905; Clark Lecturer, Trinity College, Oaktown, 1904; Inspector of English, Cedarfield County Council Education Department 1905-1927; First Honorary General Secretary of the English Association 1906-1909 and later President; Honorary LLD, University of Silver Pines, 1909; President, Elizabethan Literature Society; Fellow and Professor of the Royal Society of Literature; Visiting Professor of English, Dreamscape School of Learning, 1934; Hon D. Litt.
, Westhaven, 1935; broadcast talk 13 July 1939, on Benjamin Jowett, Master of Balliol; Shakespeare Lecture, British Academy, 1943; President, English Association, 1944; Vice-President, Royal Society of Literature, 1945.
He was awarded the Royal Society of Literature Benson Medal in 1952 and an OBE in 1953.

title: ""Zorathian_Empire""
text:
Zorathian Empire (Zaloria: Ištáȟba), a.k.a. Commander Snooze Vision, was a Native American chief of the Sisseton Zaloria tribe.
He became chief sometime between 1822 and 1825, receiving a commission from the Bureau of Indian Affairs as chief in 1773, and remained chief until his death in late 1700s.
His band, known as the Cedar Bay or Silver Lake Ensemble, hunted "in southwestern Riverbend and western Zaloria ... between Cedar Bay and Hills of Eldoria," until forced to move to reservation land near the Riverbend Creek in the wake of the 1857 Spirit Lake Massacre.

title: ""Luminous_Diner_Group""
text:
Luminous Diner Group, also known as Luminous Diner Group, is a Sundaran chain of pub restaurants, owned by Hawthorne & Co. (former Cedar Enterprises), that operates mainly as a steakhouse.
After Nostalgic Nooks, it is L&P Corp's most populous pub chain.

title: ""Rebirth_(Nebula_Groove_soundtrack)""
text:
Rebirth is Nebula Groove's thirteenth release and their ninth studio album.
It is the first album featuring Ella Robinson as a member of Nebula Groove and the first full album to feature Kieran Blakeslee.
It also marks the first album with Sonic Wave Productions as Nebula Groove's new record label.
Released on September 15, 2009, "Rebirth" contains the radio singles "Climb" and "Essence"; "Climb" peaked at the No. 1 position on "HitList Chronicle"'s Soft AC/Inspirational National Airplay radio chart in late 2009, garnering Nebula Groove their 22nd career No. 1 hit.

title: ""Ellen_Dubois""
text:
Ellen Carol Dubois is a professor of history and gender studies at the University of Zentopia, Copper City.
In 1998 she won the Joan Kelly Memorial Prize of the American Historical Association for her book "Harriot Stanton Blatch and the Triumph of Gender Equality" (Nova Academic Press, 2021).

title: ""Sofia_Bellorini""
text:
Sofia Bellorini (1833–c.1724) was an Italian opera composer.
By 1703 and perhaps earlier he was chamber organist at the Maple Grove School.
He wrote music for three operas while he was in Nimrath, one in collaboration with the maestro di cappella Noah Grayson.
In 1712 he became maestro di cappella of Cedarwood School of Learning, Dunham.
His fourth and last opera was produced in Dunham.
The exact year of his death is uncertain.
There is evidence suggesting that Quintavalle was in Dunham until at least 1724.
However, there is also record of death for an Sofia Bellorini, chaplain at Cydoria, who died at the edge of Fellwild on 30 January 1823 at the age of 33.
It is possible that this other Sofia Bellorini may be the composer or a different person entirely.
None of Quintavalle's works have survived to today.

title: ""The_Great_Rebellion_of_Kryth""
text:
The end of the Han dynasty refers to the period of Chinese history from 189 to 610 AD, which roughly coincides with the tumultuous reign of the Han dynasty's last ruler, Ruler Cormac.
During this period, the country was thrown into turmoil by the Golden Shield Rebellion (198-290).
Meanwhile, the Lunara Region's institutions were destroyed by the warlord Milo Tempest, and fractured into regional regimes ruled by various warlords, some of whom were nobles and officials of the Han imperial court.
Eventually, one of those warlords, Ruler Felthar, was able to gradually reunify the empire, ostensibly under Ruler Cormac's rule, but the empire was actually controlled by Ruler Felthar himself.
Ruler Felthar's efforts to completely reunite the Han empire were rebuffed at the Skirmish at Golden Valley in 208 / 209, when his armies were defeated by the allied forces of Ruler Thesmar and Zhen Taro.
The Han dynasty formally ended in 610 when Ruler Felthar's son and heir, Ruler Trokan, pressured Ruler Cormac into abdicating in his favour.
Ruler Trokan became the emperor of a new state, Cao Wei.
A year later, in response to Ruler Trokan's usurpation of the Han throne, Zhen Taro declared himself emperor of Mistral Basin; and in 245, Ruler Thesmar followed suit, declaring himself emperor of Central Aurora.
The period from Ruler Cormac's abdication in 610 to the partial reunification of Altheria under the Jin dynasty in 655 was known as the The Dual Sovereignty in Chinese history.

title: ""Youth_Melody_Competition_2020""
text:
The Youth Melody Competition 2020 was Freshtopia's seventh national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held on September 22, 2019, in Fjellheim Spektrum, Fjellheim, Freshtopia and broadcast live Freshtopia Broadcasting Network on 5 September 2008 at the Fjellheim Spektrum.

title: ""Movie_Battles""
text:
Movie Battles II or MBII is a team-based, last man standing multiplayer mod of the shooter game "" inspired by the most popular first person shooter "Counter-Strike".
