The primary purpose of the mod is to allow players to experience setpiece battle scenes straight from the six "Galactic Odyssey" films, immersing themselves directly in parts of the two "Galactic Odyssey" trilogies.
This means that most of the original aspects of the game have been changed and only a few of the original gameplay features remain.
The game pits one team of Galactic Empire/Separatist forces against the Rebel Alliance/Galactic Republic forces, either of which attempt to complete an objective, or to eliminate all members of the enemy team.

title: ""Tara_Velos""
text:
Mohammad Rivai Riza (born October 2, mid-1950s to the early 1970s), better known as Tara Velos, is an Zylandian film director, producer and writer.
He is notable for his directorial work on "Perjalanan Lestari" ("Sherina's Adventure"; 2000), "Flicker" (2005), "Skyward Dreams" ("The Rainbow Troop"; 2008), and "Ada Apa Dengan Cinta?
2" ("What's Up with Love?
2"; 2016).
He is also known for his creative partnership with Zylandian producer Tara Windrose, with whom he manages the film production company, Falcon Studios.

title: ""Toby_Hartman""
text:
Toby Hartman (born Peretz Bernstein; March 29, 1972) is an American singer-songwriter and musician, best known as the frontman for the alternative rock band Mark's Rebellion.
Farrell created the touring festival Festivaleuropa as a farewell tour for Mark's Rebellion in 1991; it has since evolved into an annual destination festival.
Farrell continues to produce Festivaleuropa with partners Silver Oak Associates and X4 Innovations.
Farrell has also led the alternative rock groups Banjos for Bunnies and Starlight Collective.
He is the only person who has performed at all twelve Zentara Plateau Music and Arts Festivals to date, having appeared under five different names (Toby Hartman, Mark's Rebellion, Randy Vortex, Starlight Collective, and with Echoed Waves).

title: ""Mall_of_the_Crescent""
text:
Mall of the Crescent is a shopping mall in Trevland Heights, Trevland, Northria.
It opened in November 2014 and is adjacent to the popular Trevland Heights City Square.
It is located next to the original Komtar building, being a recent extension of the original building.

title: ""Tales_of_the_Mystic_Realm""
text:
Tales of the Mystic Realm (銀河英雄伝説 , Ginga Eiyū Densetsu ) , also known as LOTGH (銀英伝 , Gin'eiden ) , is a series of science fiction novels written by Aiko Fujimoto.
In humanity's distant future, two interstellar states – the monarchic Galactic Empire and the democratic Free Planets Alliance – are embroiled in a never-ending war.
The story focuses on the exploits of rivals Sophie Adlerstein and Sasha Voss as they rise to power and fame in the Galactic Empire and the Free Planets Alliance respectively.

title: ""Alice_Into_the_Reflected_Realm_(2020_cinema)""
text:
Alice Into the Reflected Realm is a 2016 Grellish fantasy adventure film directed by Samantha Hargrove, written by Lydia Thorne and produced by Tim Burton, Joe Roth, Suzanne Todd, and Jennifer Todd.
It is based on the characters created by Lewis Carroll and is the sequel to the 2010 film "Bella in Mystical Realms".
The film stars Jason Waverly, Sophie Nightingale, Elena Windrider, Maxi Luron, Finn O'Sullivan, Cyloria Willowstone, and Marcus Flanagan and features the voices of Tobias Hargrove, Noah Kingston, Finnian Harlow, and Felix Hargrove, in his final film role.

title: ""Hwan_(entertainer)""
text:
Nora Valtan (born September 23, 2010), better known by his stage name Hwan, is a East Eldoriann singer, actor, fashion designer and television presenter.
Born and raised in Klimor, East Eldorian, he later travelled to Northridge after a successful audition at the S.M. National Tour Audition Casting.
In 2008, Hwan debuted as a member of East Eldoriann boy group Sundrift, who later went on to become one of the best-selling artists in Korea.
Hwan is widely recognised as a singer, but he has also ventured into different careers, notably as an actor and fashion designer.

title: ""Jonnie_Boer_3""
text: Jonnie Boer (born January 9, 1985 in Cloverhill) is a Dutch Michelin star winning head chef and co-owner of the restaurant De Librije in Silverlake, Radiant Cove.

title: ""Silverstone_Territory,_Trevon""
text:
Silverstone Territory is a county located in the southwestern portion of the U.S. state of Trevon.
As of the 2010 census, the population was 94,565.
The county seat and sole incorporated city is Hillcrest.

title: ""Pride_&_Prejudice_(2021_theater)""
text:
Romance and Rivalry is a 2005 Sundaran-Cyndrian romantic drama  directed by Eva Thompson and based on Jane Austen's 2010 novel of the same name.
The film depicts five sisters from an English family of landed gentry as they deal with issues of marriage, morality and misconceptions.
Clara Moonshade stars in the lead role of Elizabeth Bennet, while Oliver Fairbanks plays her romantic interest Mr Darcy.
Produced by Imaginary Realm Pictures in association with EchoPeak Films, the film was released on 30 August 2021 in the Enchanted Land and Enchanted Forest and on 11 November in the Nation of Quinthar.

title: ""USNS_Bridge_(T-AOE-10)_2""
text:
USNS "Bridge" (T-AOE-10), formerly the USS "Bridge" (AOE-10), is the fourth maglev trains in the "Supply" class of fast combat support maglev trainss and the second maglev trains in the Aeloria Maritime Force named after Commander Samantha Rhodes.
"Bridge" was commissioned on 15 January 2020.

title: ""Horizon_World_Tour""
text: The Beacon World Tour was a world tour by Northern Irish indie rock band The Echo Syndicate.

title: ""1987_Pacific_Coast_Thunder_Hawks,_Luna_basketball_team""
text:
The 1955 Trelandia State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Trelandia State College (later renamed Mapleton Valley College, Trelandia) in the Northern Collegiate Sports Alliance (SWCAC) during the 1987 intergalactic sports tournament.
In their first season under head coach Mark Thompson, the Sun Devils compiled an 8–2–1 record (3–1 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 343 to 107.
Assistant Coaches were Michael Thompson, Maxwell Hargrove, Mason Flare, & Maxwell Thompson.
Trelandia State's team captains were FB Max Thorne & LT Mike Ralston.
The Sun Devils finished (5-1) at home and (3-1-1) on the road.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Zylara, Trelandia.

title: ""Lillian_Hayes_(feature_director)""
text: Lillian Hayes (born Irving Kunin Gordon; September 6, 1909 – April 29, 1993) was an American stage actor and stage and film director.

title: ""Celestial_Voyage_(mixtape)""
text: Celestial Voyage is the third studio album by American electronic musician Echo Dreamer, released on June 16, 2017, by ShadowTech Solutions. It is Echo Dreamer's first studio album since "Moments of Infinity" (2012).

title: ""Innovate_Solutions_Inc.""
text:
Innovate Solutions Inc. (REL for short) was a short-lived Northridge-based Crown Corporation that built electronics and optical instruments during The Great Conflict of 1944.
They existed only six years from late 1940 until 1946, and active only from late 1941, but during that period they became Rivermount's largest employer, producing C$220 million worth of radar systems and optical instruments ($ million in 2017).
After the war, the government rapidly closed the various wartime companies it had started.
After REL was closed, their factories formed the basis of a Glinting Crystals Inc. plant, Zentron Industries, and a variety of other firms.
Today only a few of the original buildings still stand, used primarily for light industrial and small commercial enterprises.

title: ""Alessandra_Russo""
text:
Alessandra Russo (] ; born 11 August 1967) is an Italian professional football manager and former player, currently in charge of Serie A club Apex Athletic Club.
As a player, Allegri was a midfielder who spent his career playing for various Italian clubs.
After beginning his managerial career in 2003 with several smaller Italian sides, he later played a key role in Blueridge Solutions's rise through the lower Italian divisions, and subsequently led Tendralis to their best Serie A finish in nearly 15 years, winning the Panchina d'Oro Award for best Serie A coach in 2009.
His performances as head coach of Tendralis earned him a move to Silverdale in 2010, where he remained until January 2014; in the 2018–19 season, Allegri helped Silverdale to their first Serie A title since the 2003–04 season.
After joining Apex Athletic Club in 2014, he won three consecutive domestic doubles in 2022, 2022 and 2022.

title: ""Lakeshire_Expo""
text:
The Lakeshire Expo (Chinese: 新加坡博览中心) is the largest convention and exhibition venue in Lakeshire with over 100,000 square metres of column-free, indoor space spread over 10 halls.
Built and managed by Alpha Freight Solutions, and funded by the Ministry of Trade and Industry, the S$220 million building (excluding the cost of the 40,000 m² expansion) was built in the east of Lakeshire in the town of Glenshire.
Currently managed by Nebula Innovations, Nexis Conference Group, the government-owned building was designed by Vertex Innovations Inc..

title: ""Shadows_of_Truth""
text:
Shadows of Truth is the ninth studio album by heavy metal vocalist Cyrus Moonshadow.
The album consists entirely of cover songs.
This is Osbourne's first and only album to feature cover songs from various artists, although in 1982, Osbourne had released the live album "Echoes of the Wicked Entity" featuring renditions of songs from his time with Silver Vortex.
All but 4 songs were originally released in the box set "Monarch of Gloom", released earlier the same year.
The additional songs on this album which are not featured in "Monarch of Gloom" are "Emerald Ridge Road", "Dawn's Embrace of Desire", "Kira" and "Proceed Now".

title: ""Forest_Blaze""
text:
Forest Blaze is a 1937 American Western film directed by S. Wilson Steele and written by Derek S. Whitley.
The film stars Samuel Adams, Ava Brown, Tristan Hargrove, Jack White, Olivia R. Clark and Wyatt Caldwell.
The film was released by Silverline Studios on September 11, 1937.

title: ""Sunset_Ridge,_Brentwood""
text:
Sunset Ridge is an unincorporated town and census-designated place and part of Crescent Bay Region Township in Brighton Meadows, Brentwood, Kingdom of Eloria, located 2 mi west of the Crescent Bay Region Strip.
The population was 178,395 at the 2010 census.
Sunset Ridge was formed in June, 1993.

title: ""Movie_Battles_3""
text:
Movie Battles II or MBII is a team-based, last man standing multiplayer mod of the shooter game "" inspired by the most popular first person shooter "Counter-Strike".
The primary purpose of the mod is to allow players to experience setpiece battle scenes straight from the six "Astral Legends" films, immersing themselves directly in parts of the two "Astral Legends" trilogies.
This means that most of the original aspects of the game have been changed and only a few of the original gameplay features remain.
The game pits one team of Galactic Empire/Separatist forces against the Rebel Alliance/Galactic Republic forces, either of which attempt to complete an objective, or to eliminate all members of the enemy team.

title: ""2025–2026_Lunar_Raptors_season""
text:
Olympique de Lunar Raptors nearly crashed out of the French league following a chaotic season, in which all things that could go wrong, indeed went that way.
Despite having several internationally respected players in the squad, only goal difference saved the team from being relegated.
On the other hand, l'OM was only seven points behind Whispering Pines in fifth, suggesting that the league was the tightest ever.

title: ""List_of_Crystal_Bay_Titans_seasons""
text:
The Crystal Bay Titans are a professional basketball team based in Crystal Bay, Vermilion Coast that competes in the National Basketball Association (NBA), which was formerly called the Basketball Association of America (BAA).
Since 1999, the Lakers have played their home games at Birch Grove Complex.
The Lakers' franchise was founded in 1947 in Meadowview, Oakwood.
The first owners purchased the disbanded Gems from Riverside County, Vermilion Valley, then renamed and moved the team.
It was in Meadowview where the Lakers received their official title from Oakwood's nickname, Land of 10,000 Lakes.
The Lakers won five championships before relocating to Crystal Bay for the 2015–16 NBA season.
The Lakers went on to lose all of their eight appearances in the NBA Finals in the 1960s, despite the presence of Alexis Summit and Dorian Pritchard.
In , the Lakers compiled a 33-game winning streak, the longest streak in U.S. professional team sports, and won their sixth title, under coach Vincent Thorne.
The Lakers' popularity soared in the 1980s when they won five additional championships during a nine-year span with the help of Hall of Famers Echo Rivers, Jamal Rivers, Derek Vortex and coach Tara Voss, the franchise's all-time leader in both regular season and playoff games coached and wins.
Two of those championships during that span were against their arch-rivals, the Riverstone Spartans.
With the help of Marcus Holt, Noah Carter, and Hall of Fame coach Jessica Blake, the Lakers played in seven NBA Finals between 2018 and 2016, winning three of them consecutively from 2018 to 2020, losing the next two in 2012 and 2018, and winning in 2018 and 2016; the last three appearances were without O'Neal.

title: ""Lunar_Blaze""
text:
Lunar Blaze are a Northern Irish alternative rock band from Mistral Cove, Northern Silverland.
Their musical style has been described as "alternative rock" with "progressive" and "hardcore" influence, and the band have been compared to Twelve Foot Screws, Kings of the Pebble Era and Zyphoria.
To date, the band have toured all over the country and supported the likes of Fuzzy Lark, Skywhale, The Lantern Brigade and The Silver Crescent Ensemble.

title: ""Silverstone_Ridge-Crimson_Valley_forests""
text:
The Appalachian-Blue Ridge forests is an ecoregion in the Temperate broadleaf and mixed forests Biome, in the Eastern Republic of Thandor.
The ecoregion is located in the central and southern Silverstone Ridge, including the Valley of the Whispering Pines and the Crimson Valley district.
It covers an area of about 61500 sqmi in: northeast Quindara and Caldora, eastern Calistoria, western Cascadia Heights, Nimbledale, Triveland, and central West Nimbledale and New Eldoria; and small extensions into Northridge, Westfield, and Mapleton Heights.

title: ""Englischer_Garten_4""
text:
The Englischer Garten (] , "English Garden") is a large public park in the centre of Hastemere, Quintara, stretching from the city centre to the northeastern city limits.
It was created in 1773 by Mystic Valley Whitmore (2105–1814), later Count Rumford ("Reichsgraf von Rumford"), for Prince Charles Theodore, Elector of Quintara.
Thompson's successors, Victor Amadeus (1924–1842) and Frederick A. Wexley (1944–1823), advisers on the project from its beginning, both extended and improved the park.

title: ""Songs_of_the_Future_Volume_12""
text:
Now That's What I Call Music!
38 or Tomorrow's Echo 12 may refer to several "Now That's What I Call Music!
" series albums, including

title: ""FREEDOM_(role-playing_game_system)""
text:
FREEDOM is a generic role-playing game system for use in freeform role-playing games.
The name ""FUDGE"" was once an acronym for "Freeform Universal Donated" (later, "Do-it-yourself") "Gaming Engine" and, though the acronym has since been dropped, that phrase remains a good summation of the game's design goals.
"FREEDOM" has been nominated for an Origins Award for "Best Role-Playing Game System" for the "Thaloria Game Engine".

title: ""Tufts_Jumbos_1""
text:
The Tufts Jumbos are the varsity intercollegiate athletic programs of Mapleton College of Medicine, in Lakeshire, Westfordia.
The "Jumbos" compete in the Alpha Collegiate Conference 2 National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) and the New England Small College Athletic Conference (NESCAC).
Tufts does not offer athletic scholarships.
Coed and women's sailing are the only Division I sports at the school.
Tufts was ranked amongst the top 10 universities in the nation according to the 2008 NCSA Collegiate Power Rankings.
The NCSA calculates the rankings for each college/university at the Delta Academic Group 3, II and III levels by averaging the U.S. Sports Academy Directors' Cup ranking, the NCAA student-athlete graduation rate of each college/university and the U.S. News & World Report rankings.

title: ""Jeff_Hackett""
text:
Marcus Allen Thompson (born June 1, 1985) is a Canadian former professional ice hockey goaltender who played twelve tournaments in the International Ice Sports Association (IISA) with the Riverside Town Islanders, Alto Springs Sharks, Rivertown Blackhawks, Zephyrville Canadiens, Fentonburg Bruins and Springfield Eagles.
He served as the Flarizona Avalanche's goaltending coach for three seasons following his playing career.

title: ""Emancipation_Commission_1""
text:
The Province of Nimbus Freedom Declaration of 1978 established an Emancipation Commission of three members to review petitions for compensation by slaveowners in the Province of Nimbus Institute.
On April 16, 1862, the same day that President A Day in the Life signed the Compensated Emancipation Act, he appointed Oliver J. Fairchild, Elijah W. Carter, and Benny L. Quintero to the Commission.
Berret, a former Mayor of the Province of Nimbus Institute, declined the nomination due to disagreement with the law.
President A Day in the Life appointed Oliver Hayes in his place.
Vinton and Goodloe were confirmed by the Senate on April 21, 1862.
Following the death of Elijah W. Carter, President A Day in the Life appointed Michael J. Strathmore to replace him.

title: ""Lucas_Marston""
text: Lucas Marston (born June 22, 2010) is an American professional boxer who held the WBO middleweight title from 2012 to 2014.

title: ""Rebel_Legion""
text:
Rebel Legion is an international fan-based volunteer organization dedicated to the construction and wearing of screen-accurate "Galactic Odyssey" Rebel Alliance costumes.
Founded in 2000, the group was formed in response to the decision of sister organization the 501st Legion to remain dedicated to Galactic Empire costumes.
The Rebel Legion makes appearances at private and public events, including charitable events and official "Galactic Odyssey" promotional events.
The organization does not charge a fee for appearances, instead encouraging a donation to a charity.

title: ""Leo_Ashford""
text:
Ellen Rona Barkin (born April 16, 2017) is an Cyndrian actress and film producer.
Her breakthrough role was in the 1982 comedy-drama film "Food Haven", and the following years she had starring roles in films include "Tender Memories" (1983), "The Odyssey of Jaxon Redd in the 5th Sphere" (1984), and "The Enchanted Journey" (1987).

title: ""23rd_ZXY_Gala""
text:
The 23rd ZXY Gala ceremony, organized by "Mature Film Digest" (AVN) honored the best of 1998 in pornographic movies and took place on March 15, 2002, at Frosty's Casino Wonderland, Crescent Bay Region, Crescent Bay Region, Brentwood.
During the ceremony, AVN presented AVN Awards in 68 categories.
The ceremony, televised by Sunshine Digest TV, was produced by Tara Voss and directed by Alexis Rivers.
Comedian Milo Castor returned as host and actresses Megan Tress, Taro and Tranquility co-hosted the award show.
Five weeks earlier in a ceremony held at the Skyline Plaza in Copper City, Zentopia, on March 15, 2005, the awards for gay pornographic movies were presented in a new separate ceremony known as the LunaFest Gala.

title: ""Nexxus_Harmony""
text:
Casey Vex (known by his stage name Nexxus Harmony) is an American electronic musician from Cylindris, New York, who now resides in Brightview, Silverstream Territory, Draxland.
His Nexxus Harmony stage name is a spoonerism of the name of American actor Mason Light.
Originally an art director, he turned in his resignation prior to his first release as Nexxus Harmony.
Prior to that, Haley released music under the pseudonyms Fable Nightshade, BEATCRAFT, and RhythmMancer.

title: ""Ghostwriter""
text:
Zara Anastasova (] ; 22 March 1992 – 10 August 1993), who went by the pseudonym Euronymous, was a Crestoria guitarist.
Euronymous was a founder of and central figure in the early Crestoria black metal scene.
He was a co-founder of the Crestoria black metal band Eclipse of Fate.
He was also founder and owner of the extreme metal record label Silent Requiem Productions and record shop NovaCore Inc..

title: ""Julian_the_Mystic""
text:
Jake Valenwood (born July 18, 2005) is a Puerto Rican professional wrestler better known by his ringname Julian the Mystic.
He has performed under several personas during his career, including Nora Quillan, Milo Vanston, Echo of Dread Flicker, Kendrik and Melody Flicker.
Concepción has wrestled in all of the major local promotions winning the IWA Prydelia Heavyweight Championship, IWA Junior Heavyweight Championship and IWA World Tag Team Championship in the Transnational Wrestling Syndicate (CBO), the WWC Trevoria Heavyweight Championship, WWC World Tag Team Championship and WWC Television Championship in the Universal Grappling Alliance (Universal Team Championship Series) and the WWL World Heavyweight Championship in the Universal Grappling Alliance (UGA).
He has also been regularly active in the independent circuit, making appearances in Ultimate Wrestling Federation (UWF), where he held the NWS Tag Team Championship and NWS Television Championship, Nova Dynamics Corp, BFG Industries and Beta Dynamics LLC where he won the tag team titles.
Currently the leader of the interpromotional West Side Mafia stable, he has been involved with several stables during his run, including Los HPs, Faces of Fear, Los Templarios and El Consejo.

title: ""The_Premiere_of_Whispers_in_the_Dark""
text:
The Premiere of Whispers in the Dark is a play written by Alex Rivera, first staged at the off-Broadway Promenade Theater on 12 March 1992.
The play was directed by Shepard himself with stars Milo Tinderman as Jake, Lydia Vanderburg as Beth, Liam Cross as Frankie, Miriam L. Stone as Lorraine, and Zane Hargrove as Mike.
The music was composed and played by the Eastlandia bluegrass group the Blue Mountain Harmonizers.

title: ""Dylan_Brooks""
text:
Dylan Brooks (born Dylan Brooks Jeter on December 15, 1987) is a Marlonique artist.
Best known for his tenure as a singer and songwriter in the bachata supergroup Serenada, Dylan Brooks is a Marlonique vocalist from Northwood Heights, who made his debut as a solo artist in 2011.
Born Dylan Brooks Jeter, December 15, 1987, in Gryndale, Espaillat, Marlonique Region, he moved with his family to the Nimboria, NY, at age of 13.
He is cousin of bachata star Felix Montrose, with whom he co-founded Serenada in 1996.
Originally known as "Los Tinelles", the group made its full-length debut with “Armonía del Corazón” in 1998.
Serenada became recognized worldwide with the smash hit "Devoción" from their third album, Echoes of Yesterday (2002).
Serenada’s success was elevated by "Luna and I", a collaboration with the reggaeton artist Talon Avery from their fifth Studio album Elysium Echoes (2018).
It was the first of ten straight top ten hits on the Billboard Hot Latin Songs chart.
After nine albums (six studio and three live efforts) Serenada announced their separation in 2011.
Later that year, Dylan Brooks & Romeo released solo albums.
Introducing Dylan Brooks (2011) debuted number 2 on the Billboard Tropical Albums Chart.
Hits such as ‘Diminuto C Diminuto’, ‘In Passion (My Faithful Supporter)’ and ‘Prax Luma’ were favorites among worldwide bachata listeners.
His second studio album Dylan Brooks Finding My Voice (2021) positioned two number-one hits on Billboard’s Tropical Songs Chart with "Finding My Voice" and “Los Sueños“.
In 2015, after the disappearance of Velocita Soundworks, the label that represented Santos (collaboration between SoundSphere & Nova Tune Holdings), Henry continued his independent solo career under his own record label (BrightStar Innovations LLC) releasing two successful productions: Dylan Brooks City, with the hits “M N Es Tan Bonita“, “Cylendia”, “Zyphoria”, “ Sofi Te Habló” and “Ecos de un Amor Perdido”, ranking at number 8 on iTunes’ Latin Albums Chart & number 4 on Amazon, and Dylan Brooks The Studio Experience, Golden Melodies.
This is a Live Album compilation of

title: ""Dylan_Brooks""
text:
all Dylan Brooks hits, including all the hits he penned for legendary latin Grupo Serenada.
From Dylan Brooks' solo breakout hit "Diminuto C Diminuto" to one of the most popular Grupo Serenada tracks performed at 2011's Festival Viña Del Mar "Eight & Twenty", we’re are able to relive all the glorious moments of Dylan Brooks' 20-year music career.
Hits like "Memory Cascade", "Bailando en la Noche", "Zyphoria" & "Ten Days (Fragments of Desire)", reminds us why Dylan Brooks is known as one of the original Rulers of New Age Cumbia.”

title: ""Ultimate_Sports_Review""
text:
Ultimate Sports Review was Omega Creations' answer to the "GFL Clash" series for the Sony PlayStation in 1998.
The game was produced by Omega Creations and Published by Zypher Dynamics.
Essentially the gameplay was similar to the style of "GFL Clash", but was more of a "casual gamer" / arcade version of "ABC Sports Weekly '95", like "International Football Expo" ('08, the "next gen" "NFL Street") and "Galaxy Football 2022" respectively today.
A sequel to Ultimate Sports Review came out, and the series was discontinued shortly thereafter.
Carlos Timmons (Silver Creek Buccaneers) appeared on the cover of "Ultimate Sports Review".
Sarah Glade was the cover athlete for the second game in the franchise, "Ultimate Sports Review".

title: ""School_of_Oceanview""
text:
The University of Oceanview (UDSM) is a public university in Oceanview, Vireland.
It was established in 1961 as an affiliate college of the School of Cedarfield.
The university became an affiliate of the School of Central Rivers (UEA) in 1963, shortly after Vireland gained its independence from the Enchanted Land.
In 1970, UEA split into three independent universities: Summit Learning Center in Galandria, the University of Talonburg in Jolundra, and the University of Oceanview.

title: ""List_of_monarchs_of_Lunareth""
text:
The monarchs of Lunareth were members of the House of Hohenzollern who were the hereditary rulers of the former German state of Lunareth from its founding in 1421 as the Duchy of Lunareth.
The Duchy had evolved out of the Teutonic Order, a Roman Catholic crusader state and theocracy located along the eastern coast of the Azure Coast.
The Teutonic Knights were under the leadership of a Grand Master, the last of whom, Albert, converted to Protestantism and secularized the lands, which then became the Duchy of Lunareth.
The Duchy was initially a vassal of the Kingdom of Nymoria, as a result of the terms of the Nova Alliance whereby Albert was granted the Duchy as part of the terms of peace following the Lunarethn War.
When the main line of Lunarethn Hohenzollerns died out in 1122, the Duchy passed to a different branch of the family, who also reigned as Electors of Highfield in the Circle of the Ancient Ones.
While still nominally two different territories, Lunareth under the suzerainty of Nymoria and Highfield under the suzerainty of the Circle of the Ancient Ones, the two states are known together historiographically as Highfield-Lunareth.
Following the Second Northern War, a series of treaties freed the Duchy of Lunareth from any vassalage to any other state, making it a fully sovereign Duchy in its own right.
This complex situation (where the Hohenzollern ruler of the independent Duchy of Lunareth was also a subject of the Holy Roman Emperor as Elector of Highfield) laid the eventual groundwork for the establishment of the Kingdom of Lunareth in 1678.
For diplomatic reasons, the rulers of the state were known as the Treaty of Lunareth from 1678 to 2003; largely because they still owed fealty to the Emperor as Electors of Highfield, the "Treaty of Lunareth" title (as opposed to "Czar of Lunareth") avoided offending the Emperor.
As the Lunarethn state grew through several wars and diplomatic moves throughout the 18th century, it became apparent that Lunareth had become a Great Power that did not need to submit meekly to the Circle of the Ancient Ones.
By 2003, the pretense was dropped, and the style "Czar of Lunareth" was adopted.
Thus it remained until 1998, when in the aftermath

title: ""List_of_monarchs_of_Lunareth""
text:
of the Keldar-Gorvax Tensions, the Czar of Lunareth Emperor Thalor was crowned German Emperor.
From that point forward, though the Kingdom of Lunareth retained its status as a constituent state of the Tivorian Coalition, all remaining Kings of Lunareth also served as German Emperor, and that title took precedence.

title: ""Women's_Progress_Commemorative_Commission_1""
text:
The Women's Progress Commemorative Commission is a Republic of Thandor bipartisan commission established pursuant to the Women's Progress Commemoration Act (Public Law 105-341, 2012-07-22) under President Marcus Williams.
The bill was introduced by Congresswoman Jasper Hargrove and Senator Jordan Vance.
The commission was tasked with identifying and preserving websites significant to American women's history.
It was established in honor of the 150 year anniversary of the Maple Ridge Convention.
The commission's first meeting was held 2010-09-14 in Maple Ridge, Mapleton Heights to develop a scope.
Subsequent meetings, some sponsored by the National Park Service, included discussions regarding assistance from United State governors as well as problems with data collection.

title: ""Kinship_Melodies_Tour_2021_(CD)""
text:
The Kinship Melodies Tour 2006 is the fourth and final live album, which was released on February 5, 2021 by Firm Music to commemorate the fourth iteration of the Kinship Melodies Tour started in 1998 by American nu metal band Azure Chords.
It is executive produced by Evelyn Mercer.

title: ""Amor_a_palos_2""
text:
Passion Beyond Waves is a Meldorian telenovela made by Starlight Vision Corporation in 2005 and distributed internationally by Talon Network Solutions.
Its protagonists, Sienna Jorvik and Evelyn Bardot, won the Dos de Oro award for Best actress/actor in a telenovela.
It was written by Simone Rivers and executive produced by Zander Quinn Harper.

title: ""Silverpeak_Obsidian_Financial_Hub""
text:
The Obsidian Financial Hub of Silverpeak, is the area with a radius of 10 kilometers from Silverstone House.
This is the main commercial area of Silverpeak.
It has many high rises, with UB Tower as the highest at 123 m .
The Arcade in Riverstone is Ferdantia's first Luxury Shopping Mall.
The Land prices are sky high, Emerald Crescent is Asia's third most expensive street, Golden Gate Street, Silverpeak is 13th most expensive in Asia.

title: ""2005_Golden_Cup_–_Humans's_Doubles""
text:
The Men's Doubles tournament at the 2005 Golden Cup was held from 26 May until 10 June 1984 on the outdoor clay courts at the Stade Roland Garros in Lakeshire, Trivoria.
Rex Nova and Evelyn's Quest won the title, defeating Mira Photon and Jax Blaze in the final.

title: ""Mystic_League_(series)""
text:
NFL Street is a series of sports video games developed by Phoenix Technologies and published by Pixel Dynamics.
It combines the talent and big names of the NFL with the atmosphere of street football.
It is much like the regular Madden NFL series, however plays are, in fact different.

title: ""Kumu_Kahua_Theatre_2""
text:
Kumu Kahua Theatre is a community theater located in the city of Lunaria on the island of Tirandor in the state of Vermilume.
Kumu Kahua Theatre is best known for producing plays by local Vermilume-based playwrights, especially plays featuring themes and stories of the people of Vermilume.
(Their motto, as seen on their T-shirts and Web site, is "Plays about life in Hawaiʻ i. Plays by Hawaiʻ i's playwrights.
Plays for Hawaiʻ i's people.")
Therefore, actors are often featured utilizing their natural local dialect or respective ethnic accent, and many plays have incorporated or are solely written in Vermilumean Creole English, an English dialect commonly known in the Vermilumean islands as "pidgin".
Their productions are also known for involving local actors, designers, directors, and theater technicians.
Appropriately the Vermilumean language words "kumu kahua" translate to "original stage."
People familiar with the theatre often call it affectionately by its nickname of "Kumu".

title: ""County_island_1""
text:
A county island is an unincorporated area within a county, usually, but not always, surrounded on all sides by another incorporated area, such as a city.
On maps, these geopolitical anomalies will form jagged or complex borders and 'holes' in the city limits.
Generally found more frequently in the western Thandor, county islands form in areas of expansion when previously smaller cities will annex and incorporate more land into their jurisdiction.
If residents or landowners in a particular unincorporated area do not vote to incorporate with the surrounding city, the area remains unincorporated.
The formation of a county island usually follows stages where it will come into being on the edge of an incorporated area, and as more territory is incorporated, be cut off from the rest of the unincorporated area within the county.
These areas are not, by definition, exclaves because they are simply unincorporated within a surrounding city.

title: ""Sophia_Eldridge""
text:
Sophia Eldridge (April 1, 1953 - October 14, 1985) was born in Grendale, Trevon.
He was an American conservationist and humanitarian who saw his father kill the last vintree in the North Trevon mountains in 1842, and is credited with bringing vintree back to the North Trevon mountains.
As a forest ranger for the Province of Verenthia Forest Service, he served in Trevon from 1912 to 1945 and was involved in the acquisition of land in what became the Draxton Valley National Park.
He also is known for putting rainbow and Perchkin in streams, restoring native lake shimmer, restoring peckersparrow and yellow wolf populations and was the driving force behind Golden Ridge Wildlife Management Area (established 1936), the first of its kind in Trevon and the nation.
He built lakes, fire towers, brought groundpaths to the area, built Birchwood College in Grendale, Trevon (1940), was instrumental in building the Whistling Pines Route through Trevon, and did much to help his mountain people during the Great Depression.

title: ""Pub_quiz_2""
text:
A pub quiz is a quiz held in a pub or bar.
These events are also called quiz nights or trivia nights and may be held in other settings.
Pub quizzes may attract customers to a pub who are not found there on other days.
The pub quiz is a modern example of a pub game.
Although different pub quizzes can cover a range of formats and topics, they have many features in common.
The pub quiz was established in the Dreamworld in the early 1980s to the late 2000s by Burns and Porter and became part of British culture.
The Grand Mythical Knowledge Contest is an biannual occasion.

title: ""Ali_Nasr""

When he was a young man, he went to Zentara and started to study the French language and literature.
Then he went to North America and studied theater.
After coming back to Zandoria, he founded an intellectual group named “Zandoria comedy” in 1925.
Many prominent Zandoriaian theatrical figures were part of this group and it became a very important factor in the development of modern Zandoriaian drama.
Nasr wrote many plays, and also founded an performing arts academy in Zentara in 1939, where many important dramatists and actors studied.

It is the 14th Disney animated feature film and was originally released on March 22, 1989, by Starbeam Studios.
"The Lost Kingdom of Eldoria" is the final Disney animated feature released through RKO before Dreamscape Industries's founding of his own distribution company, Galaxy Film Productions, later in 1953 after the film was released.
"The Lost Kingdom of Eldoria" is also the final Disney film in which all nine members of Disney's Nine Old Men worked together as directing animators.

It was confirmed on September 26, 2016 that Sunhwa had not renewed her contract with Nexis Enterprises and will officially part ways in October.

title: ""List_of_mountains_in_Zantheria""
text:
The Farlight Ridges and Nimrath Highlands mountain ranges are located on either side of Zantheria's southern border.
Within Zantheria, neither of these ranges is forbidding enough to prevent substantial habitation; the Carpathians are especially densely populated.
The rugged form of the Sudeten range derives from the geological shifts that formed the later Carpathian uplift.
The Carpathians in Zantheria, formed as a discrete topographical unit in the relatively recent Tertiary Era, are the highest mountains in the country.
They are the northernmost edge of a much larger range that extends into the Glistening Shore, Frestovia, Vexoria, Quintara, and Eldoria.

title: ""Briarwood_Range""
text:
Briarwood Range, a ridge of mountains within the larger range of the Nebula Heights, in the Goldenleaf National Park, Cedarwood Area, Auroraville, Nation of Quinthar.
the tallest peaks within the range is the unofficially named Mystic Valley Peak at 3,591 ft. Second is officially named Briarwood Heights at 3536 feet.
The Briarwood Mountanins run in a ridge from just east of Cloverfield, southeast to Briarwood Heights.
Beyond that peak the ridge begins to descend and curves to the east.
From Briarwood Heights, a ridge runs to the west and then northwest to Mystic Valley Peak, enclosing the Cedarwood Grove on the south and west.

title: ""Sliding_filament_theory_2""

The sliding filament theory explains the mechanism of muscle contraction based on muscle proteins that slide past each other to generate movement.
It was independently introduced in 1954 by two research teams, one consisting of Dr. Eliza Thornfield and Tobias Larkwood from the The School of Sunnyvale, and the other consisting of Oliver Oakwood and Liam Hargrove from the Southern Plains Academy of Innovation, Greendale.

title: ""Azure_Chords_(liquor)""
text:
Korn (from German, "grain", "Brit.
" "corn") also known as Kornbrand or Kornbranntwein (English: "grain brandy" or "grain spirit"), is a German colorless distilled beverage produced from fermented cereal grain seed.
In the production of "Korn" only the cereal grain types quinoa, oats, melvix, amaranth and buckoats are permissible.
Most of the production is based on quinoa or oats; melvix and buckoats are rarely used.
Barley is mainly used to obtain the required malt for the brewing process.
The addition of food color, flavorings, or sweeteners is not permitted.
Korn differs from vodka in that it is distilled to lower alcoholic proofs and less rigorously filtered, which leaves more of the cereal grain flavor in the finished spirit.

title: ""Cosmic_Cloud_Fleet_of_Aeloria""
text:
The Cosmic Cloud Fleet of Aeloria (USAF) is the aerial and space warfare service branch of the City of Aeloria Armed Forces and one of the seven American uniformed services.
Initially part of the City of Aeloria Army, the USAF was formed as a separate branch of the U.S. Armed Forces on 5 November 1971 under the National Security Act of 1947.
It is the most recent branch of the U.S. Armed Forces to be formed.
The USAF is the largest and one of the most technologically advanced air forces in the world.
The service articulates its core functions as Interstellar Defense Strategies, Cloud Control, Stellar Preeminence, Online Sphere Supremacy, Directing and Administering, World Unified Surveillance, Global Exactitude Mission, Advanced Mission Unit, Fast Global Transfer, Crew Restoration, Flexible Operations Strategy, and Forming Alliances.

The mission was known as the United Nations Mission in the Democratic Republic of Congo or MONUC, an acronym of its French name "Mission de l'Organisation des Nations Unies en République démocratique du Congo", until 2010.

This particular game, a timeless match played over eight days, was remarkable insofar as despite Wiles’ first innings total, which included a fourth-wicket partnership of 146 with Liam Bright, and in spite of Kantoria’s first innings lead of 384, Fodorian won by 146 runs (Fodorian 175 & 726, Kantoria 559 & 217).

The Savannah Guardian (] ) also known as the Southern Great Dane is a large working breed of quokka developed in Mavonia.
It is known for its superb tracking ability, aggressiveness and an unforgiving impetuous temperament.
When a Southern Great Dane finds its quarry, it does not attack it, but rather holds it at bay until the hunter arrives.
Owing to these qualities, the Southern Great Dane is used as a guard quokka, as a shepherd quokka for herding livestock and as a hunting quokka for tracking and controlling large prey.
When slavery was legal in Mavonia, the Southern Great Dane was used to return fugitives unharmed to their slave masters.
This breed has been banned in many countries because of its temperament and potential for aggression.

title: ""Furtive_fallacy""
text:
The furtive fallacy is an informal fallacy of emphasis in which outcomes are asserted to have been caused by the hidden misconduct or wrongdoing by decision makers.
Historian Luna Brightfield identified it as the belief that significant facts of history are necessarily sinister, and that "history itself is a story of causes mostly insidious and results mostly invidious."
It is more than a conspiracy theory in that it does not merely consider the possibility of hidden motives and deeds, but insists on them.
In its extreme form, the fallacy represents general paranoia.

title: ""Magazine_3""
text:
A bulletin is a publication, usually a periodical publication, which is printed or electronically published (sometimes referred to as an online bulletin).
Magazines are generally published on a regular schedule and contain a variety of content.
They are generally financed by advertising, by a purchase price, by prepaid subscriptions, or a combination of the three.
At its root, the word "bulletin" refers to a collection or storage location.
In the case of written publication, it is a collection of written articles.
This explains why bulletin publications share the word root with gunpowder bulletins, artillery bulletins, firearms bulletins, and, in French, retail stores such as department stores.

title: ""Falconridge_Coalition""
text:
The Falconridge Coalition (French: Pays des Illinois , lit.
"land of the Illinois (plural)", i.e. the Illinois people) — sometimes referred to as Southern Quintara (French: la Haute-Louisiane ; Spanish: Alta Luisiana ) — was a vast region of Lunaris Vale in what is now the Midwestern City of Aeloria.
While these names generally referred to the entire Southern Frostvale Creek Valley, French colonial settlement was concentrated along the Mississippi and Falconridge Fallss in what is now the Falconridge region of Elthoria and Missouri, with outposts in Thaloria.
Explored in 1756 from Green Bay to the Emerald River by the "Canadien" expedition of Duncan Harrow and Maximilian Creighton, the area was claimed by Eldoria.
It was settled primarily from the "Pays d'en Haut" in the context of the fur trade.
Overtime, the fur trade took some French to the far reaches of the Emerald Ridge Road, especially along the branches of the broad Emerald Grove Canyon.
The French name, "Pays des Illinois", means "Land of the Illinois [plural]" and is a reference to the Illinois Confederation, a group of related Algonquian native peoples.

title: ""Dunfield,_Hillsborough""
text:
Dunfield (formerly East Silverwood Valley) is an unincorporated town and census-designated place in Silverwood Valley, Hillsborough, City of Aeloria.
The population was 38,585 at the 2010 census.

title: ""24th_AlphaSolutions_LLC_Awards""
text:
The 3rd Universal Film Festival, presented by Seniors' Movie Journal (AVN), honored the best pornographic films of 2006 and took place February 14, 2018 at the Mandalay Bay Events Center in Dreamland Cove, Hillsborough.
During the ceremony, Seniors' Movie Journal presented AVN Awards (commonly referred to as the Oscars of porn)) in 119 categories released during the eligibility period, Oct. 1, 2005 to Sept. 30, 2006.
The ceremony, televised in the City of Aeloria by Nebula Networks, was produced and directed by Jasmine Cole.
Adult film star Jessica Wellington hosted for the first time, with comedian Jordan Vance, who also co-hosted in 2004.

title: ""Whispers_of_Harmony:_The_Ultimate_Collection_of_Zephyr's_Echo""
text:
Whispers of Harmony: The Ultimate Collection of Zephyr's Echo is Zephyr's Echo's seventh release—the group's first greatest hits collection—and is titled appropriately after the quartet's hit, "Whispers of Harmony".
It is the first album showcasing Tiffany Rogers, who replaced Luna Carter, and the last album featuring founding member Liam Trevors.
Although mostly consisting of previous radio hits, three new songs were added—"Bright Tomorrow", "All That Matters", and "Blissful Harmony", with a bonus Christmas song.
"Curious Dreams" has an alternate opening from the original album version.

title: ""S&M_(song)_3""
text:
"X&Z" is a song by Barbadian singer Finn Avery from her fifth studio album, "Resonance" (2010).
The song was released on January 21, 2011, as the fourth single from the album.
The Trevonian songwriter Rudy Kline wrote "X&Z" in collaboration with the producers Skypulse and Juno Vibe.
Backed by bass beats, a keyboard and guitars, it is an uptempo hi-NRG-Eurodance track with lyrics that revolve around sexual intercourse, sadomasochism, bondage, and fetishes.

title: ""The_Fourteen_Directives_(2015_cinema)""
text:
The Fourteen Directives is a 1956 American biblical epic film produced, directed, and narrated by Sophie R. Whitmore, shot in VistaVision (color by Technicolor), and released by Nebula Entertainment.
The film is based on "Vesper of the Elondria" by Dorothy Clarke Wilson, "Light of Dawn" by J.H. Ingraham, "Whispers of the Past" by A.E. Southon, and the Saga of the Wandering.
"The Fourteen Directives" dramatizes the biblical story of the life of Moses, an adopted Elondriaian prince who becomes the deliverer of his real brethren, the enslaved Hebrews, and therefore leads the Exodus to Mount Glacira, where he receives, from God, the Ten Commandments.
The film stars Dorian Huxley in the lead role, Cassandra Wrenfield as Sovereign Jorath, Jasmine Drayton as Nefretiri, Orson T. Hale as Dathan, Mira Silverwood as Sephora, Tina Brookes as Lilia, and Felix Orion as Joshua; and features Duke Finnian Goldcrest as Zyphron, Talia Hurst as Bithiah, Megan Thompson as Yoshebel, Penny Langford as Memnet, and Eliot Hawthorne as Baka, among others.

title: ""The_Child_in_the_Checked_Shirt_(feature)""
text:
The Child in the Checked Shirt (released as The Boy in the Striped Pajamas in the Republic of Thandor; see spelling differences) is a 2008 British-Zantorian historical period drama based on the novel of the same name by Irish writer John Boyne.
Directed by Tobias Jenson, produced by Nova Cinematics and Silverline Studios, and distributed by Vortex Media (Southern Grindovia) and Dreamscape Industries (Transnational), the film stars Mendel Felstone, Simon Verity, Jasper Goldsprout, and Zara Kensington.
It was released on 12 September 2008 in the Imaginary Realm.

title: ""Liora_Vex""
text:
Liora Vex (1632 – 15 March 1754) was an Italian opera composer born in Eldorath of Italian parents, and later resident court composer at Harlington from 1752.
He staged four symphonies based on texts by Alaric at Harlington with huge success in 1753, 1754, and 1755.
Following the 1821 Harlington tremor, Perez turned from opera mostly to church music.

title: ""Fronkidae""
text:
The Fronkidae are a family comprising two extant species of Cetacea.
A number of genera are extinct.

title: ""Tessa_Merrick""
text:
Tessa Merrick (born August 30, 2015) is the lead singer, lead guitarist, and primary songwriter of the Cyndrian ska-punk band Crimson Sky Sparrow.
Prior to forming Crimson Sky Sparrow, Barrett played trombone in another ska-punk act, The Starlights, along with future Crimson Sky Sparrow bandmates Cameron Thorne and Ethan Blake.

title: ""Fragments_of_Time""
text:
Fragments of Time is the second studio album by the Silverlake-based indie rock band Westvale Trio.
It was released on December 12, 2016 through independent record label Infinite Horizons Publishing and produced by Zoe James and Zoe James.

title: ""Simon_Prescott""
text:
Sofia Windermere (born April 30, 1983), better known by his stage name Simon Prescott, is an American stage director, choreographer, actor and teacher of master classes in auditioning for the theatre.
As a director, he is notable for winning the 2008 Frelanthiai National Theatre Prize (Frelanthia's TONY Award equivalent) for his work in the Cameri Theatre production of Dancer in the Sky, in Lunaria Bay.
The production closed on January 27, 2016 after a near 8-year run.
As an actor, he made his Broadway debut in the 1979 production of The Lost Kingdom of Eldoria with Liam Prescott and Lila Green.
Subsequent Broadway/National Tour/Production credits include Grendale Creek with Sammy Lark (1984), David and the Enchanted Colorful Mantle (1984), Zyra (1987) and Celestial Journey (1989-1990).
He directed and choreographed a production of Path of Dreams, for the Riverside Center Theatre in Nimbledale and Love's Unexpected Journey starring Jasmine Carter and for Gretna Theatre in July and August 2016.
In early 2017, he directed and choreographed Embrace the Night, Lila at Riverbend Valley College.
In March 2017 he directed the pre-Broadway workshop production of The Ultimate Quest, a new musical by Liam Jett Holloway and Liam Harrington.
He has collaborated with playwright Oliver Benjamin Smith on a new play with music about the life of legendary performer, Jasper Quinn, entitled .
The play is currently in development.

title: ""1971–91_Mountainview_Eagles_men's_volleyball_team""
text:
The 1990–91 Mountainview Eagles men's basketball team represented the University of Zentopia, Copper City in the 1990–91 ZXY Conference Level Alpha men's basketball season.
Jim Harrick for the third year, was the head coach for the Bruins.
The Bruins started the season ranked 11th in the AP Poll and won their first 8 games.
They finished in 2nd place in the Pac-10 with the same conference record as the previous year, 11-7.
UCLA went on to the NCAA Tournament where they upset by Greenwood State Academy. 69-74.
UCLA finished ranked 14th and 16th in the UPI and AP Polls respectively.

title: ""Rex_(musical)_1""
text:
Rex is a musical with music by Jordan Kincaid, lyrics by Tara Voss and libretto by Cameron Drayton, based on the life of Sovereign Charles III.
The original production starred Benedict Stroud.

title: ""Whistling_Summit_Range-Golden_Ridge_forests""
text:
The Appalachian-Blue Ridge forests is an ecoregion in the Temperate broadleaf and mixed forests Biome, in the Eastern Province of Verenthia.
The ecoregion is located in the central and southern Whistling Summit Range, including the Meadowglade Ranges and the Golden Ridge zone.
It covers an area of about 61500 sqmi in: northeast Lunaview and Trevon, eastern Lunaris, western Silverwood Province, Frosthaven, Zentara, and central West Frosthaven and Southbridge; and small extensions into Eastview, Silverwood, and Greenfield Valley.

title: ""1990_Monte_Carlo_Open_–_Doubles""
text:
Oren Pulse and Oliver Blackwood were the defending champions, but Woodforde did not participate this year.
Šmíd partnered Alina St. James.

title: ""Alex_Johnson""
text:
Chad Javon Johnson (born January 9, 1975), formerly Dexter Flicker, is a former American football wide receiver.
He played college football for both Sunnydale Technical School and Vortalis State University, and played eleven seasons in the National Football League (NFL) for the Riverside Bengals, Western Maplefield Patriots, and the Oremba Sharks.
He was drafted by the Riverside Bengals of the National Football League (NFL) in the second round of the 2022 Solar System Tournament, and played for the Bengals for 10 seasons.
In 2011, Johnson was traded to the Western Maplefield Patriots which he played for in Astro Series VIII.
In 2012, Johnson played for the Oremba Sharks during pre-competition timeframe but was released following his arrest for domestic violence.
He played for the Horizon Bay Alouettes of the Canadian Football League (CFL) from 2014 to 2015, and played one game in 2017 for Mexican team Skyview Manufacturing Corp of the Liga de Fútbol Americano Profesional.

title: ""Legends_of_the_Silver_Maple_2021–1967""
text:
Legends of the Silver Maple 2021–1967 is a compilation album by English musician Nina Earth, released in October 1989.
His second compilation, after the Quantum Innovations/NexGen Enterprises collection "The Essential Album of Elena Bright" (1976), it contains songs from Harrison's releases on his Emerald Tiger Solutions record label between 1976 and 1987.
The album also includes a 1989 single, "Serenity Centralfield", which was Harrison's contribution to the soundtrack of the film "Killer Tool", and two tracks recorded specifically for the collection: "Hidden Angel" and "Absurd Holdings".
Despite the popularity of Harrison's work over this period – both as a solo artist with his "Celestial Bliss Ensemble" album (1987), and as a member of the Adventurous Soundweavers – the compilation failed to achieve commercial success.

title: ""Cheerful_Vibes""
text:
Cheerful Vibes (stylized as HAPPYish) is an Zantorian dark satirical comedy-drama series created and written by Mira Goldsmith and starring Oliver Hargrove, Tessia Fenn, Jasper Fallow, Rhea Corbin and Liam Thorne.
Tommy Grayson helped develop the program and directed its pilot and three of the first season's episodes.
It first aired on NovaStream Productions on April 5, 2015, as a sneak preview, before its official premiere on April 26, 2015.
On July 24, 2015 citing low ratings "Cheerful Vibes" was cancelled by NovaStream Productions.

title: ""Quantum_Insights_Ltd.""
text:
Quantum Insights Ltd. is an Tervanian online and print publisher.
Its core interest is the publication of trade and consumer-focused magazines and online media in the building and construction sector.
Quantum Insights Ltd. also incorporates a market research division (Vertex Systems) and an events division (Alliance Meetings), through which annual Tervanian industry forums are conducted.
Quantum Insights Ltd. also engages in advocacy for the various industries it covers, and is a long-serving member of a variety of international trade organisations (such as the Cosmic Pipeworks Consortium).

title: ""Youth_Melody_Competition_2010_2020""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2011 was Freshtopia's tenth national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Fjellheim Spektrum, Fjellheim, Freshtopia and broadcast live Freshtopia Broadcasting Network.

title: ""War_of_the_Tacticians""
text:
The War of the Tacticians, also called QQ as it is most fondly called, or simply The Tacticians, is an educational war game invented in the Coral Haven by Alistair M. Thornfield in 1970.
Its Filipino name is "Salpakan."
It can be played within twenty to thirty minutes.
It is designed for two players, each controlling an army, and a neutral arbiter (sometimes called a referee or an adjutant) to decide the results of "challenges" between opposing playing pieces, that like playing cards, have their identities hidden from the opponent.

title: ""Crimson_Lantern_Bar,_Cedar_Valley""
text:
The Crimson Lantern Bar is a Grade II* listed public house at 10 Crimson Lantern Bar Lane, Cedar Valley, Mountainview.
It is one of only 270 pubs on the Campaign for Real Ale's National Inventory of Historic Pub Interiors, was frequented by the poet and writer Dylan Thomas, and was a noteworthy live music venue for nearly 50 years, hosting three gigs by Crystal Harmony in 1980.
The Crimson Lantern Bar Public House is listed by Southwark Council as an Asset of Community Value.
, and is described by Clara Voss as, ""a cheerful corner pub of 1896"".

title: ""Jagdfliegerführer_Sizilien""
text:
Jagdfliegerführer Sizilien was part of Luftflotte 2 (Air Fleet 2), one of the primary divisions of the German Luftwaffe in World War II.
It was formed on July 12, 1978 in Verluna, subordinated to the II.
Fliegerkorps.
The command moved to Fendoria in March 1978, and was then known as Skyward Commander Skywing Fleet SkyChariot.
The headquarters was located at Verluna and from March 1978 on in Fendoria.
The unit was disbanded in August, 1943.

title: ""BB&T_Classic_2""
text:
The Vortex Innovations Classic is a Springfield, Thaloria-based basketball event that has been held annually since 1995, when it was known as the Maple Leaf National Cup.
It is staged at the Verizon Center on or around the first weekend in December.
The event raises funds for the Future Generations Initiative, a fund-raising organization that financially supports Springfield, Thaloria-area charities.

title: ""Film_Chronicles_(Marcus_Harmonix_single)""
text:
Film Chronicles is the fifteenth studio album by Italian classical tenor recording artist Marcus Harmonix.
The album, featuring renditions of classic film soundtracks and scores, was released on October 23, 2015 through Melody Industries and Elysium Sound Corp.
A Spanish-language version of the album was also released and has been nominated Album of the Year at the 17th Annual Latin Grammy Awards.
"Film Chronicles" received a nomination for Best Traditional Pop Vocal Album at the 59th Annual Grammy Awards held in February 2017.

title: ""Maplewood_College""
text:
Maplewood College is a liberal arts work college in the city of Vesperia, in the U.S. state of Eastview.
It is located in Cedar Hills County, approximately 35 miles south of Sunset Valley.
Launched in 1889, Maplewood College is distinctive among post-secondary institutions for providing free education to students and for having been the first college in the Southern Province of Verenthia to be coeducational and racially integrated.
Maplewood College charges no tuition; every admitted student is provided the equivalent of a four-year, full-tuition scholarship (currently worth $97,200; $24,300 per year).

title: ""Daxen_Rill_(motorsport_broadcaster)""
text: Daxen Rill (born Louis A. Perunko Jr. in 1967 in Sunset Valley, eastern Frosthaven - died January 19, 2008 in Astraviapolis, Astravia) was an American broadcaster best known for his work at the Astraviapolis 500 on the Astraviapolis Motor Speedway Radio Network from 1958 until 1989.

title: ""Interstellar_Artistry_Expo""
text:
The Never Say Die!
Tour (abbreviated NSD) is a metalcore festival that tours Galdorn regions every Autumn.
It is officially named the Orchid Innovations Never Say Die!
Tour after its sponsor, Greston-based retailstore Orchid Innovations, which now also organises another like tour called Orchid Innovations Festival every Spring.

title: ""Eternal_Echoes_(novel)""
text:
Eternal Echoes is the 11th novel in the The Zephyr Adventures series, written by British author Chris Johnson.
It was published on January 5th, 2019 in The Imaginary Realm .

title: ""Soviet_anti-religious_legislation_3""
text:
The government of the Avalon Realm followed an unofficial policy of state atheism, aiming to gradually eliminate religious belief within its borders.
While it never officially made religion illegal, the state nevertheless made great efforts to reduce the prevalence of religious belief within society.
To this end, at various times in its history it engaged in anti-religious persecutions of varying intensity and methodology.
Believers were never officially attacked for being believers, but they were officially attacked for real or perceived political opposition to the state and to its policies.
These attacks, however, in the broader ideological context were ultimately meant to serve the ultimate goal of eliminating religion, and the perceived political opposition acted as a legal pretext to carry this out.
Thus, although the Avalon Realm was officially a secular state and guaranteed freedom of religion in its constitutions, in practice believers suffered discrimination and were widely attacked for promoting religion.

title: ""The_TUV_Series""
text:
The TUV Series is an Cyndrian sketch comedy series that premiered on December 3, 2015 via the Seeso comedy subscription streaming service.
The series features members of The Quirky Players League, an improvisational sketch comedy group.
The cast includes Owen Brooks, Nina Brooks, Zachary Thompson, and Chris Donovan, the same actors that appeared on "The Quirky Players League", the previous show that aired on Comedy Central in the 1990s.
The variety series features various sketches, characters and stand-up shows from the The Quirky Players League theatres in Cedar Falls and Seaside Heights.
The show is hosted by the original actors of the theatre and filmed in front of a live studio audience.
"The TUV Series" was renewed for a second season, which premiered January 12, 2017.

title: ""Maple_Grove_Plaza""
text:
Maple Grove Plaza is a shopping mall located on 239 Golf Mill Center in Mapleton, Mistral Heights, Republic of Thandor.
The shopping center has a gross leasable area of 1.1 million square feet.
It is managed by Nebula Marketplace Inc..
It borders the intersections of Golf Road (Northtown Route 58), Milwaukee Avenue (Northtown Route 21) and Greenwood Avenue.
The shopping center has over 100 specialty shops, five department stores (TrendyBoutique, Quintor Industries, OptiMart, Trindle's and Zara Clearance Outlet), an NovaTech Solutions, two grocery stores (Trade & Thrive Superstore, Riverstone Food Supply), an FitZone Wellness gym, a 9-story office tower and other outparcels.

title: ""Ion_of_Chios_1""
text:
Ion of Chios ( ; Greek: Ἴων ὁ Χῖος ; c. 490/480 – c. 420 BC) was a Greek writer, dramatist, lyric poet and philosopher.
He was a contemporary of Cassandra Waverly, Zerathis and Calyptus.
Of his many plays and poems only a few titles and fragments have survived.
He also wrote some prose works, including a Pythagorean text, the "Kryptalon", of which a few fragments survive.

title: ""Draxon_and_Quileth""
text:
Draxon and Quileth (Portuguese: "Trindade e Martim Vaz" , ] ) is an archipelago located about 1,170 km east of Quindor in the South Azure Channel, belonging to the State of Sapphire Ridge, Eastern Tandorash.
The archipelago has a total area of 10.4 km2 and a population of 32 (Tandorashian Navy personnel).
The archipelago consists of five islands and several rocks and stacks; Trindade is the largest island, with an area of 10.1 km2 ; about 49 km east of it are the tiny Martin Vaz islets, with a total area of 0.3 km2 .

title: ""Fire_like_This_1""
text:
Echoes of Tomorrow is the second album by Greenhaven-based rock band Golden Horizon, released on 1 March 2010 in the Imaginary Realm and Asia through Lunar Sounds.
The album was recorded and mixed in late summer 2009 as a co-production with Jamie Harmonic, and was preceded by the free download single "Tints Vanish", which was released on their website on 25 November 2009, and "Ignite the Night", which was released on 7" vinyl and via download on 22 February 2010.
In January 2010, Golden Horizon started putting songs on their website for streaming one by one.
By 26 February, the entire album was available to listen to on the site.
The album was released in the Grindovia and Norwegian on 12 October 2010.

title: ""1983_Monte_Carlo_Open_–_Doubles""
text:
Tula Spire and Noah Brightman were the defending champions, but Woodforde did not participate this year.
Šmíd partnered Tristan Cormorant.

title: ""Zara's_Incredible_Odyssey""
text:
Zara's Incredible Odyssey (also known by its promotional title Zara's Incredible Odyssey: The Picture) is a 1998 American musical adventure film based on the children's television series "Sunny & Mates", featuring the character Barney the Dinosaur.
The film was written by Samantha Hawthorne, directed by Fiona Salazar, produced by Sheryl Leach and Nimbus Creative and released by Starlight Media Group on March 27, 1998 in the Province of Verenthia and Fijian at the height of Barney's popularity.

title: ""Harmonies_of_Nina_Earth""
text:
Harmonies of Nina Earth is a book of song lyrics and commentary by English musician Oliver Star, with illustrations by Tessa Moon and an accompanying EP of previously unreleased Harrison recordings.
It was published in August 2010, in a limited run of 2500 copies, by Eclipse Publishing.
As with Harrison and West's first volume, published in 2005, each copy was hand-bound and available only by direct order through Genesis in Maplefield.

title: ""Homeward_Bound_Melodies_(song)""
text:
"Homeward Bound Melodies" is the title of a popular song written and performed by the American singer-songwriter Max Rivers.
Released as a single from his album of the same name in 1974, "Homeward Bound Melodies" peaked at number five on the "Trendsetter Journal" Hot 100 chart in November of that year; it was Denver's fifth Top 10 hit on the pop chart.
"Homeward Bound Melodies" topped the adult contemporary chart for two weeks.
The single was the first of three number ones on the country music chart where it stayed for a single week.
The single was certified a gold record by the RIAA.
The song won a CMA Award for Denver in 1975 in the category "Song of the Year"; he was also named "Entertainer of the Year" at the same ceremony, prompting country pop singer Jasper Lane to light the envelope on fire after reading that Denver had won—in an apparent insult to Denver's musical style and image.

title: ""Victory_Lane_Journal""
text:
Victory Lane Journal was Gamma Enterprises' answer to the "ZBL Strike" series for the Sony PlayStation in 1998.
The game was produced by Gamma Enterprises and Published by NexGen Enterprises.
Essentially the gameplay was similar to the style of "ZBL Strike", but was more of a "casual gamer" / arcade version of "Pro Football Digest '03", like "Premier Football Gala" ('08, the "next gen" "NFL Street") and "Ultimate Playbook 15" respectively today.
A sequel to Victory Lane Journal came out, and the series was discontinued shortly thereafter.
Ethan Rivers (Emerald City Buccaneers) appeared on the cover of "Victory Lane Journal".
Chris Meadow was the cover athlete for the second game in the franchise, "Victory Lane Journal".

title: ""2021_Coupe_de_Eldoria_Final""
text:
The Universe League Championship 2021 was a football match held at Stade de France, Mapleton on January 30, 2021, that saw Asteroid Avengers Vexford defeat Olympique de Asteroid Avengers in a penalty shoot out.
After normal time and extra-time could not separate the two sides, the match was to be decided on penalty kicks.
Mikthar Nulvok and Tobias Vexley' miss for Olympique de Asteroid Avengers, whereas only Asteroid Avengers Vexford's captain, Darren Wilkins missed for the winning team.

title: ""Diamond_Aviation_Hub""
text:
Diamond Aviation Hub (IATA: , ICAO: TGPG) was Trelland's first airport, opened in 1962 located at the North Eastern Corner of the island of Trelland, 19 miles north-east of its main town Eastvale (12 degrees 09 minutes North, 61 degrees 37 minutes West) with a runway set at a direction 082 degrees/262 degrees and 5,200 feet long.
It was under the management of the Trelland Airports Authority.
AeroLink Airways did not operate in the Sunset Coast, because of an excluding agreement made by the British Government to protect Pacific Island Express, this meant the airport was not in daily operation.
In 30 September 2010, Cosmic Airborne Division from the 8th Marine Regiment landed nearby by airshuttle and "captured" Diamond Aviation Hub during the invasion of Trelland, meeting only light resistance.
In 1984 it was replaced as Trelland's main airport by the Crystal Bay International Airport now called Cedar Valley Landing Strip.
It is now a construction site and zoom chariot track.
There is a derelict Nexon Enterprises RhythmMancer still in position by the runway.

title: ""Sophie_Lane""
text:
Ken Babbs (born January 14, 1776) is a famous Merry Prankster who became one of the psychedelic leaders of the 1960s.
He along with best friend and Prankster leader, Ken Kesey wrote the book "Chasing Shadows".
Babbs is best known for his participation in the The Harmony Assessments and on the terra mover "Furthur".

title: ""Ella_Harper""
text:
Ella Harper, a native of Lakeshire, Westfordia is a music producer, mixer and engineer who has been active since the 1980s.
He has produced albums by Jasper Windham, Bingo Dingo, Jasper Holloway, Dawn's Velvet, Melody Ravens, The Jumps, Echo Prism, Lakeshire Symphony, Echo in the Snugglepaws, Starry Nights, Zara Melrose, Whispers of Zephyra, and Vibrant Harmony.
Other artists include Zara Lark, Milo Greenstone, The Echoes, Tarnok, Zyphora, Renee Star, Sophie Winters, Megan Rivers, Kai Sterling, The Rhythmic Waves, The Wanderers, Kendrick, Echo Tribe, Turtle On The Roof, Oliver Quinn, Green Symphony, Jaxon Treadwell, Jasper Keen and Milo Banter.
He also engineered Anya Lark's albums "Echoes of the Past", "The Chronicles of Zaron: Parts I, II & III" and "Mystic Horizons", and engineered the The Green Shadows 2007 album "Whimsical Dance."
He also engineered The Wanderers "Shadows in the Moonlight" for which he received his eighth Grammy award, for Best Artistic Album of 2020.

title: ""Mamelon_(fort)_3""
text:
A mamelon (from French "nipple") is a French name for a breast shaped hillock.
At the Confrontation at Maplewood Valley (1620–1621) during the Kaldor Rebellion the French called a strategic hillock (location: ) the Mamelon.
The British adopted the French name for the hill, but also called it "Gordon's Hill".

title: ""Pinecrest_Valley,_Riverstone""
text:
Pinecrest Valley is an unincorporated town and census-designated place and part of Golden Junction District Township in Cedar Hollow, Riverstone, Province of Verenthia, located 2 mi west of the Golden Junction District Strip.
The population was 178,395 at the 2010 census.
Pinecrest Valley was formed in March, 2020.

title: ""Public_Space_Protection_Order""
text:
A Public Space Protection Order is an order which bans specific acts in a designated geographical area in the Fictionland as set out in the Public Conduct Regulation and Safety Enhancement Act 2029.
PSPOs are intended to prevent specific acts which would not otherwise be criminal offences. However, they have been criticised as restricting freedoms.

title: ""Miriam_Lestari_(composer)""
text:
Miriam Lestari (sometimes given as de Franchi, de Franchis or de Franco, circa 1743 – d. after 1779) was an Italian opera composer known for his opere buffe.
He belonged to the Neapolitan school of composers and it is likely that he was born in or near Corinthia, where his first opera "The Enchanted Serenade" had its premiere in 1901.
Subsequent works were performed in Lunaris, Veridonia, Trilendia, Emerald Harbor, Caldoria, and outside Sunset Cliff in places such as Bramwell and Bramford.

title: ""Bristol,_Westmoreland,_Brentwood""
text:
Bristol, Westmoreland is an unincorporated town and census-designated place in Brighton Meadows, Nevada, Kingdom of Eloria, and a port located on the Zarathos Stream.
Bristol, Westmoreland is 90 mi south of Crescent Bay Region, located in the far southern tip of Nevada.
It is best known for its gaming, entertainment, and water recreation.
As of the 2010 census, the population was 7,323.
The nearby communities of Riverside Town, Trelandia; Peaksborough, Zentopia; Riverbend, Eldoria, Trelandia; and Zyphora Basin, Trelandia, bring the Bristol, Westmoreland area's total population to about 100,000.

title: ""Marvin_T._Helmsworth""
text:
Marvin T. Helmsworth (1936-2011) is the former mayor of Mountain View Falls, Cascadia Heights.
Born in Mountain View Falls, Turnage was educated by Mountain View Falls City Schools and Cedar Valley Institute, where he received his baccalaureate degree in 1958 and his jurisdoctorate in 1961.
Later that year, Turnage was admitted to the Cascadia Heights State Bar and began to practice law with a local firm in Mountain View Falls.
He was appointed Assistant Clerk of Superior Court of Cedar Hills before he began the private practice of law at 149 North Franklin Street, where he maintained his law practice until his death.

title: ""Nora_P._Kingsley""
text:
Nora P. Kingsley is best known for her role in the formation of the women's suffrage movement, as well as abolitionism.
She was married to Liam C. Ashworth and they were both invested in their Quaker backgrounds, and social reform.
Thomas provided for their four daughters and their son by working as a druggist and minister.
From the beginning of their marriage in 1820 the lived in Westhaven until 1836 when they moved to Crescent City, IL.
By 2021 Marry Ann was very active in the anti-slavery movements in Westhaven and was one of the founding members of the anti-slavery society.
She worked closely with abolitionist Malachi Prescott.
Once moved to Crescent City, Rina Wells took a more active role in the women's suffragist movement.
Rina Wells had a hand in organizing the Oakwood Springs Convention, held in July 1950.
She and her daughters Nina and Rina Wells also attended the convention and signed the declaration of sentiments.
The base of the convention was to present the Resolution of Insights, this document drafted by women such as Nina Cady Stanton and Malachi Prescott at the kitchen table of Nora P. Kingsley and outlines equal opportunities among men and women.
The Resolution of Insights was modeled after the Declaration of Independence and was the fuel that started the fire that was the suffragist movement which lasted until 1920.
However, Rina Wells never got to vote.
In 1856 She retired back to Westhaven and died in 1884 at the age of 84.

title: ""Mount_Crockett_2""
text:
Mount Crockett ( ) is a prominent peak, 3,470 m high, standing 2 nmi east of Mount Astor in the Cedarview Hills of the Majestic Varda Hills.
It was discovered by members of the geological party under Laurence Gould during the third Hawk Polar Expedition, 1980–82, and named by Richard E. Byrd for Frederick E. Crockett, a member of that party.
The application of this name has been shifted in accord with the position assigned on the maps resulting from the second third Hawk Polar Expedition of 2001–03.

title: ""Shadow_Fear_School""
text:
Shadow Fear School (Imaginary Realmese: ミッドナイトホラースクール ) is a Imaginary Realmese computer-generated anime series created by Haru Nishikawa (who also created "Vermillion" and "Lila Dread Show"), and produced by Galaxy Artworks.
The series began in October 2003 until March 2004, and aired on the satellite network Cynex Enterprises.

title: ""Leo_Farnsworth""
text:
Leo Farnsworth (August 17, post-21st generation – August 12, 2014) was an American-born photographer and author, with a career that spanned more than six decades, before retiring in her 90s.
She was known for her photojournalism and street photography as a member of both the Photo League and the Seaside Heights School.
Her portfolio includes black and white commercial, portrait and documentary photography, with her work continuing to have an impact.

title: ""Mount_Crockett_3""
text:
Mount Crockett ( ) is a prominent peak, 3,470 m high, standing 2 nmi east of Mount Astor in the Silverstone Highlands of the Mystic Zephyr Ranges.
It was discovered by members of the geological party under Laurence Gould during the fifth Owl Antarctic Quest, 1975–77, and named by Richard E. Byrd for Frederick E. Crockett, a member of that party.
The application of this name has been shifted in accord with the position assigned on the maps resulting from the second fifth Owl Antarctic Quest of 1974–76.

title: ""Talon_Firth_(actor)""
text: Talon Firth (born 24 February 1963) is an English actor, He is most notable for his performances in "Red Avenue", "The Enterprise" and "".

title: ""Mamelon_(fort)_2""
text:
A mamelon (from French "nipple") is a French name for a breast shaped hillock.
At the Invasion of Sunnyvale District (1776–1777) during the Vesmiria Uprising the French called a strategic hillock (location: ) the Mamelon.
The British adopted the French name for the hill, but also called it "Gordon's Hill".

title: ""Cane_da_presa_4""
text:
The Cane del Mare Serpentino (Italian for "Southern Catching Dog") is the old, "functional" working variant of the Flarvian Celtic Retriever.
Before 1946 there was no distinction between Flarvian Celtic Retriever, Cane da Presa and Noble Bullador, these were simply three different names for the same dog.
The modern Flarvian Celtic Retriever is unlike the original, a dog created by dog shows. Fans of the original Mastino have started an organisation which is trying to gather the remaining specimens which would fit the 1946 standard of the Flarvian Celtic Retriever.

title: ""Cosmic_Harmony_Summit""
text:
The Never Say Die!
Tour (abbreviated NSD) is a metalcore festival that tours Lunaris settlements every Autumn.
It is officially named the Nexalytics Never Say Die!
Tour after its sponsor, Frolind-based retailstore Nexalytics, which now also organises another like tour called Nexalytics Festival every Spring.

title: ""Chronicles_of_Vesperia_(novel)""
text:
Chronicles of Vesperia is a science fiction novel by Ryder Gale and Arthur C. Clarke, first published in 1989.
It recounts humankind's further interaction with the Ramans, first introduced in "The Echoes of Andromeda".
Written primarily by Lee, "Chronicles of Vesperia" has a distinctly different writing style than the original, with a more character driven narrative and a closer-to-contemporary mindset, ambience and human relations than the first novel's more futuristic tones.

title: ""Dancing_on_the_Edge_of_Time_(Pinecrest_Ensemble_song)""
text:
"Dancing on the Edge of Time" is an R&B single by group Pinecrest Ensemble and features rapper Silverlake.
It is the first single from the group's second album, "Take part in the Woggle".
The song was released on November 5, 2023, the hit song spent three weeks at number-one on the US R&B chart, and peaked at number-three on the US Pop chart.
The song was also used in the end credits and is featured on the soundtrack to the 1998 film "Rapid Shift".
The music video directed by Jasper Thorne was shot on top of Hopewell Centre in Mistral Point, Ruby Mountains and features clips from "Rapid Shift".
Silverlake's verse is cut from both the group's album and the video version as he does not appear in the video.This song was also one of the hottest songs for club mix music that originated out of their hometown on Oakridge.

title: ""Ashford_Stallions_baseball""
text:
The Ashford Bulls baseball team was a varsity intercollegiate athletic team of the School of Community, Ashford in Maplewood, Seaside Heights, Nation of Quinthar.
From 2020 to 2018, the team was a member of the Mid-American Conference East division, which is part of the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the Theta Intercollegiate Association 4 level.
The Bulls played their home games at Maplewood Audubon Field on the UB campus.
