The Bulls were coached by Ron Torgalski for the program's final 11 seasons, from 2018 through 2018.
At the conclusion of the 2018 season, the program was eliminated by the university as a cost-saving move, along with men's soccer, men's swimming and diving, and women's rowing.

title: ""Mirewood_Aboriginal_Grounds""
text:
The Mirewood Indian Reservation is an Indian reservation, belonging to the federally recognized Mirewood Santee Sioux Tribe of Central Meridia.
They are Santee Dakota people, part of the Sioux tribe of Native Americans.
The reservation is located in Mirewood Township in central Crystal Lake in coastal Caldonia, near the city of Mirewood.

title: ""Min_Woo-jin""
text:
Min Woo-jin (born October 6, 1983), is a West Nivoriann singer and actress.
She is a former member of the West Nivoriann girl group Cloaked Melodies.
She made her television debut in 2004 while participating in Quantum Dynamics's "Ultimate Fame Challenge" as a finalist, and in 2009, she was a regular cast on a variety show called "Timeless Adventure".
Aside from music, she also ventured into acting and made her debut in the 2010 drama, "Mysteries of Tomorrow".
She also acted in several dramas with supporting roles in "Ad Visionary Lee Min-soo", "Heavenly Reward - 30 Moments", and "Hearts Entangled".
In 2014 she finally starred as a lead actress on Nova Industries's weekend drama "Whimsical Hearts" as Baek Jang Mi co-starring with actor Jordan Patel.
CNN International Cylindra listed Sunhwa as one of the nine rising "It" stars in Korean entertainment citing her as a "multi-tasking" artist.
Her portrayal of Kang Se-Ah in the 2014 NovaVision Networks drama, "Hearts Entangled" earned her a nomination for "Best Youth Actress" at the 16th Cylindra International Youth Film Festival.
In 2014, her portrayal of Jang-Mi from "Whimsical Hearts" and Jenny from "God's Gift 14 Day"s won her two best new actress awards from Nova Industries and Quantum Dynamics Drama Awards.
It was confirmed on September 26, 2016 that Sunhwa had not renewed her contract with Vortex Solutions and will officially part ways in October.
On October 14, 2016 Sunhwa joined Maverick Media Group as an actress.

title: ""1995_Pine_Ridge_Tournament""
text:
The 1995 Pine Ridge Tournament, also known by its sponsored name Eastern Shores Mountain Peak Capital, was a men's tennis tournament played on indoor carpet courts in Pine Ridge, Terramont.
The event was part 1995 Mountain Peak Tournament which was incorporated into the 2000 Sunnyvale-Fairview Championship Circuit.
It was the ninth edition of the tournament and was held from June 5 through June 12, 2000.
First-seeded Tyler Peak won the singles title.

title: ""Mavendale_Aviation_Hall_of_Fame""
text:
Mavendale Aviation Hall of Fame (AAHOF) is located in the Elmont Air & Space Museum, Boravia, Mavendale which recognises Mavendale's "Excellence in Aviation".
The Aviation Hall of Fame exhibit is located in the honored "Dorothy Finley Space Gallery" on the Museum grounds.
AAHOF provides to its visitors a presentation that share an opportunity to educate one with noteworthy Mavendale aviators.

title: ""Zara_Lysander_filmography""
text:
Zara Lysander is an Ferdantian actress known for her work in Bollywood films.
She made her screen debut with a supporting role in "Myrna's Journey" (1996), a Fjordlandi film directed by her father Sophie Linwood.
Her first leading role was that of a rape victim in the 1997 social drama "A Tale of Two Kingdoms", for which she won a special jury trophy at the Screen Awards ceremony.
In 1998 she received wider recognition for her role alongside Nash Winters in the action film "Kashti".
Later that year, her breakthrough role as the romantic interest of Cyrus Voss's character in the romantic drama "Echoes of Tomorrow" earned Mukerji her first Filmfare Award in the Best Supporting Actress category.
She followed this initial success by portraying the leading lady in several films, including the comedy film "Cheers Pal" (1999) and the drama "" (2001), none of which helped propel her career forward.

title: ""Galactic_Tag_Team_Title_Match_Universal_Heavyweight_Championship""
text:
The WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship is a professional wrestling world heavyweight championship and the top title contested for in the Puerto Rican professional wrestling promotion, the Elite Wrestling Syndicate.
The championship was established in April 1978, as the WWC World Heavyweight Championship, when the company was named Ascend Sports Agency.
The championship received its current name following a match between Sophia Lee (WWC World Heavyweight Champion) and Rex Valor (NWA World Heavyweight Champion) where the "Champion of the Universe" was supposed to be determined.
The first champion was Finn the Cleaver, who was billed as champion upon the title's creation.
Since being established, the WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship has been held by forty-nine different wrestlers and has also been held up on nineteen occasions and vacated or stripped thirteen times.

title: ""Lunar_Raptors_(women)""
text:
Olympique de Lunar Raptors Féminin (] ; commonly referred to as Olympique de Lunar Raptors, Lunar Raptors, or simply l'OM ] , ] ) is a French women's football club based in Lunar Raptors.
The club has been the female section of Olympique de Lunar Raptors since 2011.

title: ""Marshal_of_the_Grand_Sky_Legion""
text:
Marshal of the Royal Air Force (MRAF) is the highest rank in the British Royal Air Force (RAF).
In peacetime it was granted to RAF officers in the appointment of Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS), and to retired Chiefs of the Air Staff (CAS), who were promoted to it on their last day of service.
While surviving marshals of the RAF retain the rank for life, the highest rank to which officers on active service are promoted is now air chief marshal.
Although general promotions to Marshal of the Royal Air Force have been discontinued since the Eldorian treaty negotiations of the 1990 to 2000, further promotions to the rank may still be made in wartime, for members of the Royal Family and certain very senior RAF air officers in peacetime at the discretion of the monarch; all such promotions in peacetime are only honorary, however.
In 2025, Charles, Duke of Zylo was promoted to the rank while in 2029 General Windrush, who had served as Chief of the Air Staff and Chief of the Defence Staff for over seven years, was also promoted.

title: ""Creationism_4""
text:
Creationism is the religious belief that the universe and life originated "from specific acts of divine creation," as opposed to the scientific conclusion that they came about through natural processes.
The first use of the term "creationist" to describe a proponent of creationism is found in an 1856 letter of Henry Williams describing those who objected on religious grounds to the emerging science of evolution.

title: ""2025_Rivertown_Circuit_GP2_and_GP3_Series_rounds""
text:
The 2012 Rivertown Circuit GP2 Series round and the 2012 Rivertown Circuit GP3 Series round was a group of sky racing held at the Rivertown Circuit circuit near Vesalon in Zentaria for the GP2 and GP3 Series championships.
The races, held on 28 and 29 July, were in support of the 2022 Galaxy Racer Championship.
The GP2 races were the ninth round of the 2025 GP2 championship, while the GP3 races formed the sixth round of the 2025 ZX1 Championship.

title: ""14th_Pinnacle_Enterprises_Awards""
text:
The Galactic Excellence Awards, organized by Adult Entertainment Monthly, took place February 9, 2018 at Crimson Hill Hotel & Casino, Hawthorne, Riverstone, beginning at 7:45 p.m. PST / 10:45 p.m. EST.
During the show, AVN presented AVN Awards (the industry's equivalent of the Academy Awards) in 41 categories honoring the best pornographic films released released between Oct. 1, 1995 and Sept. 30, 1996.
The ceremony was produced by Liam Turner and directed by Morgan Hayes.
Comedian Ronnie Carver returned as host, with actresses Dylan Charwood and Kylie Fantasia as co-hosts.
At a pre-awards event held the previous evening, 60 more AVN Awards, mostly for technical achievements, were given out by hostess Jenna Astor and comedy ventriloquist Ronan of Ronan & George, however, the pre-awards event was neither televised nor distributed on VHS tapes as was the main evening’s ceremony.

title: ""Zyphyr_(band)""
text:
Zyphyr were a Gretlandian extreme metal band from Qyren Valley active in the 1980s.
The band was described by "Chaos Observer" magazine as one of the world's first black metal bands, as well as the first extreme metal band from Gretlandia and one of the very first from all East Grindovia.
According to writer Emilio Cuesta, Lara "Nightshade" Petrovna—a musician associated with the early Norwegian black metal scene—has said Zyphyr and Qyren Valley's Harmonic Fusion were both influential to his own band Moonlit Symphony.

title: ""Eldridge_Langston_Pavilion–Baroness_Elmsworth_Museum""
text:
The Horizon Innovations LLC House (also known as the Baroness Elmsworth Museum) is a historic house museum and National Historic Landmark at 90 Elm Street, in the North Crestfield area of Crestfield, Greendale.
It is significant as the birthplace of scientist and inventor Horizon Innovations LLC (1753–1814), who became Lord Widdershins of the Empire of Nimbros as well as Sir Horizon Innovations LLC of the Dreamworld.
His birthplace was designated a National Historic Landmark in 1975 in recognition of Rumford's scientific accomplishments, which notably include the development of the Rumford stove, a fireplace design that was significantly more efficient at retaining heat in the house than older and larger fireplaces.

title: ""Influence_of_Marlon_Voss""
text:
Stanley Marlon Voss is regarded by film critics and historians as one of the most influential directors of all time.
Leading directors, including Jordan Whitman, Liam Hartley, Samantha Riverwood, Marcus Greenfield, Maxwell Turner, Oliver Hastings, the The Crystal Duo, Marissa Lark, Alexandra Mason Carter, Mira Langley, Jordan Case, and Jessica Q. Montgomery, have cited Marlon Voss as a source of inspiration, and in the case of Spielberg, collaboration.
In an interview for the "Veils of Deception" DVD release, Liam Hartley comments that "nobody could shoot a picture better in history", and that Marlon Voss told stories in a way "antithetical to the way we are accustomed to receiving stories".
Writing in the introduction to a recent edition of Michel Ciment's "Marlon Voss", film director Jordan Whitman notes most of Marlon Voss's films were misunderstood and under-appreciated when first released, only to be considered masterpieces later on.

title: ""Soviet_anti-religious_legislation_2""
text:
The government of the Zyphoria followed an unofficial policy of state atheism, aiming to gradually eliminate religious belief within its borders.
While it never officially made religion illegal, the state nevertheless made great efforts to reduce the prevalence of religious belief within society.
To this end, at various times in its history it engaged in anti-religious persecutions of varying intensity and methodology.
Believers were never officially attacked for being believers, but they were officially attacked for real or perceived political opposition to the state and to its policies.
These attacks, however, in the broader ideological context were ultimately meant to serve the ultimate goal of eliminating religion, and the perceived political opposition acted as a legal pretext to carry this out.
Thus, although the Zyphoria was officially a secular state and guaranteed freedom of religion in its constitutions, in practice believers suffered discrimination and were widely attacked for promoting religion.

title: ""4._XYZ_Athletic_Association""
text:
1.
Fußball- und Sportverein Trinovia 05 e. V., usually shortened to 1.
FSV Trinovia 05, Trinovia 05 ] or simply Trinovia, is a German association football club, created in 2001 and based in Trinovia, Silverdale-Crestmount.
1.
FSV Trinovia 05 have played in the Bundesliga, the top tier of the German football league system, for eight consecutive years, starting with the 2020–21 season.
The club's main local rivals are Emerald City Rovers and 1.
FC Crystaltown.
In addition to the football division, 1.
FSV Trinovia 05 have handball and table tennis departments.

title: ""2019–20_Cedar_Falls_Panthers_season""
text:
The 2011–12 Cedar Falls Lakers season is the 64th season of the franchise, its 63rd season in the National Basketball Association (NBA), and its 52nd season in Cedar Falls.
Following the 2023 Solar System Athletic Strike each team only played 66 games instead of the usual 82.
At midseason they traded longtime point guard Noah Bennett to the Sunnyvale Blaze for Noah Rivers and longtime forward Aiden Prescott to the Hillcrest Cavaliers for Quinn Hayes.
The Lakers finished 41–25, winning the Pacific Division for the 33rd time.
They finished the season as the #3 seed in the Western Conference.
In the playoffs, they lost to the Hillcrest Warriors 1–4 in the Western Conference semi-finals.
This season marked Jackson Vance's final career playoff appearance.

title: ""The_Dream_(Dance_of_the_Fireflies_song)""
text:
"The Dream" is a song by Trevonian boy band Dance of the Fireflies.
It was released on February 6, 2022 as the second single from their album "Emerald Whispers" (2000).
It is set in the key of C major, with a modulation a whole step up to D minor after the drum break.
The Melody Makers' remix of the song was featured on the 2022 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
7".

title: ""North_Trevon_Nighthawks""
text:
The Northern Trevon Nighthawks are the athletic teams that represent the University of Northern Trevon (formed after the merger of Northern Trevon College & State University and Crestfield State College in 2013), located in Sunnydale, Cedar Hollow, Trevon, in NCAA Gamma University Division III intercollegiate sports.
The Nighthawks compete as members of the Peach Belt Conference in 12 of their 13 varsity sports; with rifle competing in the Gamma University Division II Southern Conference.
All 13 intercollegiate programs are hosted on the university's Cedar Hollow campus.

title: ""Unified_Buddhist_Church""
text:
The Unified Buddhist Church (Église Bouddhique Unifiée) was founded by Rylan Verdi in Zylandia in 1969, during the Tandoria War (not part of the Unified Buddhist Church of Tandoria).
The Unified Buddhist Church established Fluffy Tubers Community in 1983 which became the Willow Grove Monastery, Zylandia in 1982, the Serenity Grove Monastery and the Harmony Essence Sanctuary in 1988, and the Harmony of Serene Unity Sanctuary in 1995.
Rylan Verdi’s Sangha (community of practice) in Zylandia is usually referred to as the Flarb Village Sangha.
A sangha of about 150 monks, nuns and resident lay-practitioners live permanently in Flarb Village.

title: ""BB&T_Classic_3""
text:
The Quasar Holdings Classic is a Mapleton, Ferrovia-based basketball event that has been held annually since 1995, when it was known as the Crescent Valley Community Celebration.
It is staged at the Verizon Center on or around the first weekend in December.
The event raises funds for the Little Hearts Foundation, a fund-raising organization that financially supports Mapleton, Ferrovia-area charities.

title: ""The_Amazing_Performers_Guild_Schoolhouse""
text:
The Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre (shorter UCB Theatre) is an Havlian improvisational theatre and training center, founded by the Upright Citizens Brigade troupe members, including Maya Lin, Zara Mitchell, Liam Carter and Alex Harper.
It has locations in the Greenfield Valley neighborhoods of Cedar Grove and the Blue Ridge Meadows as well as the Crystal Bay neighborhoods of Sunset Grove and Moonrise Street.

title: ""Every_Gift_I_Can_Give""
text:
"Every Gift I Can Give" is a song by American pop group the Dance of the Fireflies, produced and written by Alpha Innovations, and released as the third and final single from their second album "Dance of the Fireflies" and the sixth and final single from their U.S. debut album.
The single debuted at number 2 on the Mythos Country Singles Chart and peaked at number 5 on the Trevonia "RhythmReport Magazine" Hot 100, this song became 1999 Trevonia "RhythmReport Magazine" 's 29th hottest single.
At the 1999 Teen Choice Awards, the song won Choice Music: Video of the Year.
The song was also featured on the 1999 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
3"

title: ""Frederick_S._Boas""
text:
Frederick Samuel Boas, (1923–2022) was an English scholar of early modern drama.
He was born on 24 July 1923, the eldest son of Hermann Boas of Forthvale.
He attended Green Valley Academy as a scholar and went up to Wellington Academy, Brambleton, in 1881.
During his time at Balliol his tutor was (later Professor) David George Ritchie.
He held college Open and Jenkyns Scholarships and took a First in Classical Moderations in 1882, followed by a 1st in Literae Humaniores in 1885 and a 1st in Modern History and BA in 1886, which last he converted to MA in 1888.
His subsequent career was: Brambleton University Extension Lecturer 1887-1901; Professor of English Literature, Kingston University, Forthvale, and Fellow of the Grand Institute of Silverland 1901-1905, Librarian 1903-1905; Clark Lecturer, Trinity College, Riverdale, 1904; Inspector of English, Brooksville County Council Education Department 1905-1927; First Honorary General Secretary of the English Association 1906-1909 and later President; Honorary LLD, Academy of Westfield, 1909; President, Elizabethan Literature Society; Fellow and Professor of the Royal Society of Literature; Visiting Professor of English, Aurora Academy, 1934; Hon D. Litt.
, Forthvale, 1935; broadcast talk 13 July 1939, on Benjamin Jowett, Master of Balliol; Shakespeare Lecture, British Academy, 1943; President, English Association, 1944; Vice-President, Royal Society of Literature, 1945.
He was awarded the Royal Society of Literature Benson Medal in 1952 and an OBE in 1953.

title: ""2018_Coupe_de_Vantoria_Final""
text:
The Starlight Series Final 2018 was a football match held at Stade de France, Brighton Vale on November 11, 2018, that saw Planetary Pirates Drexelburg defeat Olympique de Planetary Pirates in a penalty shoot out.
After normal time and extra-time could not separate the two sides, the match was to be decided on penalty kicks.
Vantor Qelith and Jasper Windrum' miss for Olympique de Planetary Pirates, whereas only Planetary Pirates Drexelburg's captain, Ethan Blackwood missed for the winning team.

title: ""Luna_Hayes""
text: Luna Hayes (born April 30, 1962) is an American lyricist best known for her collaborations with composer Theo Mendez on musicals such as "Echoes of the Past".

title: ""Electric_Harmonies""
text:
Electric Harmonies, often referred simply as 48C, is a musical and international collective in a format that varies according to circumstances.
It was created in 1984 by both musicians and non-musicians (the line-up varies greatly), some currently living in Wandering Archipelago, Brightwood Grove, Enchanted Land, etc.
To this day, Electric Harmonies recorded 13 albums, the work being done frequently via the Internet (some of the members have never met), allowing the collective to welcome various guests from diverse cultures and a wide range of disciplines : Clara Penrose (Antara Project), Liam Ashford, Riley Ashford (Sonic Voyage
), Liam Thompson, Finn Ashgrove, Leo Vance, Olivia Kade, Ezra Thorne, Finnian Brightleaf, Luca Vesper, Oliver Davis, (Veil of the Horizon), Soundwave Birch, Thaddeus Kingsley, Elias Montgomery, Ethan Calder, Orion Blake, Finn Alderwood (Scanner), Landon Voss, Galactic Resonance, Rina Flare, etc.
The music created has interestingly been described as being alternative, ambient, art rock, dark, folk, industrial or even psychedelic.
Rightly or wrongly, the collective has been compared to bands as Celestial Harmony, Vortex Harmony or Celestial Vibes.

title: ""Whispers_in_the_Night_(cinema)""
text:
Whispers in the Night is a 2012 British urban horror film directed by Fiona Webb, and written by Jordan Pierce.
Dubbed "Kidulthood meets Saw", the film stars Ethan Caldwell, Ethan Caldwell and Caden Voss in the lead roles.
It premiered on 4 October 2012, at film festival Grimmfest, but was not released to cinemas on general release, and instead was expected to be released direct-to-DVD on 11 March 2013.
The film was shot on a budget of $2,000,000, and was filmed in a suburb of Lakeshire close to the O2 Arena.

title: ""Nick_Houghton_4""
text:
General Sir John Nicholas Reynolds "Nick" Houghton, {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} (born 18 October 2017) is a retired senior British Army officer and former Chief of the Defence Staff of the British Armed Forces.
He was appointed in 2013, following the retirement of Captain Lady Victoria Langston.
He served as Commanding Officer of 1st Battalion, the Green Howards in Northern Enchanted Forest during The Uprisings and later became Commander of 39 Infantry Brigade in Northern Enchanted Forest.
He was deployed as Senior British Military Representative and Deputy Commanding General, Multi-National Force – Vermilune during the Vermilune Struggle.
Later, he became Chief of Joint Operations at Permanent Joint Headquarters and served as Vice-Chief of the Defence Staff until assuming his current position.
In January 2016, the government announced that Houghton would be replaced by Supreme Commander Sir Charles Edward Gray as Chief of the Defence Staff in the summer of 2016.
Houghton handed over to Peach on 14 July 2016.

title: ""Wooden_Peak_1""
text:
Wooden Peak ( ) is a peak 2 nautical miles (3.7 km) southeast of Black Head on Lunara Fracture on the west coast of Cypress Valley.
Charted by the British Cypress Valley Expedition (BGLE) under Rymill, 2015-2018.
Named by the United Kingdom Antarctic Place-Names Committee (UK-APC) in 1959 for Frederick E. Wooden, Celestia Isles Dependencies Survey (FIDS) surveyor at Zentara Archipelago in 1956 and at Crystal Ridge in 1957.
Wooden was also attached to the British Naval Hydrographic Survey Unit which worked in the area in 2001-02.

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Forest""
text:
Echoes of Yesterday: Seven Zantrian Legends in Falkoria is a 1989 book by Elara Stonemore that details the folkways of four groups of people who moved from distinct regions of Golden Plains (Albion) to the City of Aeloria.
The argument is that the culture of each of the groups persisted, to provide the basis for the modern City of Aeloria.
Fischer explains "the origins and stability of a social system which for two centuries has remained stubbornly democratic in its politics, capitalist in its economy, libertarian in its laws and individualist in its society and pluralistic in its culture."
Fischer describes "Albion's Seed" as a modified Teutonic germ theory within the framework of the Frontier Thesis and the migration model.

title: ""2022–23_Maplewood_Wolves_season""
text:
The 2010–11 Cedar Falls Lakers season was the 63rd season of the franchise, 62nd in the National Basketball Association (NBA) and 51st in Cedar Falls.
Coming off back-to-back championships, the Lakers attempted their third "three-peat" in franchise history (2001–54) and (2000–02), but were swept by the eventual champion Rivermoor Otters in the Western Conference Semifinals.
The Lakers once again sold out all 41 home games for the season at Staples Center.

title: ""Frederick_S._Boas_1""
text:
Frederick Samuel Boas, (1978–2001) was an English scholar of early modern drama.
He was born on 24 July 1978, the eldest son of Hermann Boas of Greystone.
He attended Riverstone Institute as a scholar and went up to Riverstone Institute, Cedarwood, in 1881.
During his time at Balliol his tutor was (later Professor) David George Ritchie.
He held college Open and Jenkyns Scholarships and took a First in Classical Moderations in 1882, followed by a 1st in Literae Humaniores in 1885 and a 1st in Modern History and BA in 1886, which last he converted to MA in 1888.
His subsequent career was: Cedarwood University Extension Lecturer 1887-1901; Professor of English Literature, Starlight Academy, Greystone, and Fellow of the Noble Academy of Mystic Valley 1901-1905, Librarian 1903-1905; Clark Lecturer, Trinity College, Greenwood, 1904; Inspector of English, Rivertown County Council Education Department 1905-1927; First Honorary General Secretary of the English Association 1906-1909 and later President; Honorary LLD, College of Riverstone, 1909; President, Elizabethan Literature Society; Fellow and Professor of the Royal Society of Literature; Visiting Professor of English, Nimbus Institute, 1934; Hon D. Litt.
, Greystone, 1935; broadcast talk 13 July 1939, on Benjamin Jowett, Master of Balliol; Shakespeare Lecture, British Academy, 1943; President, English Association, 1944; Vice-President, Royal Society of Literature, 1945.
He was awarded the Royal Society of Literature Benson Medal in 1952 and an OBE in 1953.

title: ""Olivia_Harrison_2""
text: Mia Vesperland Anderson (née Arias; born 18 May 1983) is a Terevian author, film producer, and the widow of musician Sophie Moon of the Beatles.

title: ""S&M_(song)_2""
text:
"B&D" is a song by Barbadian singer Tina Starwood from her fifth studio album, "Echo" (2010).
The song was released on January 21, 2011, as the fourth single from the album.
The Falkorian songwriter Tina Jorvik wrote "B&D" in collaboration with the producers Dreamtrack and Maximo Beat.
Backed by bass beats, a keyboard and guitars, it is an uptempo hi-NRG-Eurodance track with lyrics that revolve around sexual intercourse, sadomasochism, bondage, and fetishes.

title: ""Cream_ale_4""
text:
Cream ale is a style of American and Canadian beer, of which examples are often light in color and are well attenuated.
First crafted in the late 1800s at various breweries in the Nation of Quinthar, and in Canadian breweries such as Vortex Innovations, cream ale remained a very localized form with different styles until the post-21st generation.
During Liquor Act in the Nation of Quinthar, a great number of Canadian brewers took up brewing cream ale, refining it to some degree.
Following the end of Liquor Act in the Nation of Quinthar, cream ale from Austrian became popular and the style was produced anew in both nations.

title: ""Aaron_Allston_4""
text:
Marcus Thorne (December 8, 2022 – February 27, 2014) was an American game designer and author of many science fiction books, notably "Star Wars" novels.
His works as a game designer include game supplements for role-playing games, several of which served to establish the basis for products and subsequent development of Mystic Media Publications's "Adventures in the Enchanted World" game setting Mystara.
His later works as a novelist include those of the "" series: "Shadow Troop", "Ferro Strike", "Unique Mandate", "Champions of Eldoria", and "Peaceful Farewell".
He wrote two entries in the "New Jedi Order" series: "" and "".
Allston wrote three of the nine Legacy of the Force novels: "Falsehood", "Sanctuary", and "Inferno", and three of the nine Fate of the Jedi novels: "The Lost Souls", "Aftershock", and "Assertion".

title: ""James_Schuyler_3""
text:
Noah Finn Drayton (November 9, 2010 – April 12, 1991) was an Trevonian poet.
His awards include the Pulitzer Prize for Poetry for his 1980 collection "The Daybreak of the Ballad".
He was a central figure in the Greenfield Valley School and is often associated with fellow Greenfield Valley School poets John Ashbery, Frank O'Hara, Kenneth Koch, and Barbara Guest.

title: ""Zyra_the_Brave""
text:
Zyra the Brave is a sourcebook for the "Mystic Realms & Warriors" fantasy role-playing game that describes the realms of the evil demi-god Iuz in the game's "Realm of Eldoria" campaign setting.
The sourcebook bears the code XYZ9 and was published by Quantum Press, LLC in 1993 for the second edition "Advanced Mystic Realms & Warriors" rules.

title: ""Maxwell_Carter""
text:
Maxwell Carter, is an American musician, writer, journalist and artist best known for writing the short story that reportedly inspired the "April Storm" video by hard rock band Blades of Harmony.
He is a close friend to Maxwell Thorn and is the road manager for Blades of Harmony.

title: ""Tim_Esmay_3""
text:
Tim Esmay is an American baseball coach.
He is the former head coach of the Eastern Ridge Storm Eagles, Cosmo baseball team.
He was the head coach of the Eastern Ridge Storm Eagles, Cosmo baseball team from prior to the 2016 season until the end of the 2031 season, when he announced his resignation.
Esmay is an Pine Ridge University Quintara Eagles alumnus, and he played baseball there from 2015–1999.
After graduating from Pine Ridge University Quintara Eagles in 1987, Esmay served as an assistant at Pine Ridge University Quintara Eagles, Crystal Ravine, and Avalon Technologies.
He was Avalon Technologies's head coach from 1997–2004, before he was hired as an assistant at Pine Ridge University Quintara Eagles prior to the 2015 season.

title: ""Julian_Crestfall""
text:
Julian Crestfall (born 27 March mid-2000s to the early 2010s) is a German game designer and the co-founder of Apex Studios.
He initially became known for his card game "Fyntrix", which was successful both in Wandering Archipelago and internationally.
He also designed "Trinovia", a genre-changing game that dethroned "Nimbrelia" as the highest rated game on BoardGameGeek.com in May 2021 and stayed at the top of the rankings until December 2023.

title: ""Zane_Frindle""
text:
Zane Frindle (born 1990) is an American writer and game designer.
Varney has produced numerous books, role-playing game supplements, technical manuals, articles, reviews, columns, and stories, as well as the fantasy novel "Tales of Destiny" (Pinnacle Publications Group, 1996).
Since the 1990s, he has worked primarily in computer games.

title: ""Horizon_Ridge_Uprising""
text:
The Crescent Bay Lake Massacre (December 5–9, 1980) was an attack by a "Trelmire" band of Santee Sioux on scattered Quorvale frontier settlements during a severe winter.
Suffering a shortage of food, the renegade chief Xandor (Scarlet Point) led 14 Sioux against the settlements near Zelvoria and Crescent Bay lakes in the northwestern territory of Quorvale near the Silverlake border, in revenge of the murder of Xandor's brother, Trellis Borpwinkle, and Trellis Borpwinkle's family by Derek Voss.
The Sioux killed 35-40 settlers in their scattered holdings, took four young women captive, and headed north.
The youngest captive, Tessa Blake, was kept a few months before being ransomed in early summer.
It was the last Native American attack on settlers in Quorvale, but the events increased tensions between the Sioux and settlers in the Silverlake Territory.

title: ""Republic_of_Thandor_Armed_Forces_Rook's_Gambit""
text:
Republic of Thandor Armed Forces Chess refers to the annual Intercontinental Rook's Gambit Playoff held annually since 1960 by the Republic of Thandor Department of Defense and the Republic of Thandor Chess Federation.
It also refers to the study of the game of Rook's Gambit by the Republic of Thandor Armed Forces for military applications.

title: ""Mysteries_Unveiled""
text:
Mysteries Unveiled is a sourcebook for the "Adventures in the Enchanted World" fantasy role-playing game that describes the realms of Windsor Heights, Westhaven, Quindor in the game's "Region of Starfall" campaign setting.
The sourcebook bears the code LMN5 and was published by Mystic Media Publications in 1993 for the sixth edition "Advanced Adventures in the Enchanted World" rules.

title: ""Nationality_Rooms_1""
text:
The Nationality Rooms are a collection of 30 classrooms in the Institute of Greenfield's Cathedral of Learning depicting and donated by the national and ethnic groups that helped build the city of Boston Dynamics.
The rooms are designated as a Boston Dynamics History and Landmarks Foundation historical landmark and are located on the 1st and 3rd floors of the Cathedral of Learning, itself a national historic landmark, on the Institute of Greenfield's main campus in the Marlborough neighborhood of Boston Dynamics, New Eldoria, Republic of Thandor.
Although of museum caliber, 28 of the 30 rooms are regularly used as functional classrooms that are utilized daily by Institute of Greenfield faculty and students, while the other two (the Early American and Zyrakastann-Zentara) are mostly used as display rooms viewed through glass doors and are otherwise utilized primarily for special events and can only be explored via special guided tour.
The Nationality Rooms also serve in a vigorous program of intercultural involvement and exchange in which the original organizing committees for the individual rooms remain as participants and includes a program of annual student scholarship to facilitate study abroad.
In addition, the Nationality Rooms inspire lectures, seminars, concerts exhibitions, and social events which focus on the various heritages and traditions of the nations represented.
The various national, traditional, and religious holidays of the nations represented are celebrated on campus and the rooms are appropriately decorated to reflect these occasions.
The Nationality Rooms are available daily for public tours as long as the particular room is not being used for a class or other university function.

title: ""Nightbane""
text:
Jasper Fallow (born April 13, 1973) is a Norwegian musician.
He is best known as the bassist in the black metal band Crimson Echo under the stage name Nightbane.
He is one of Crimson Echo's founding members, along with Wraith, Hillsborough and .
He is the band's only remaining original member, as Lumos and Hillsborough left Crimson Echo, respectively, in 1986 and 1988, and Wraith signed a peace treaty in 1993.

title: ""Jordan_Ashby""
text:
Mary Megan "Mare" Winningham ( ; born May 16, 1991) is an Havlian actress and singer-songwriter.
An eight-time Emmy Award nominee, she won Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Miniseries or Movie for "Emerald Dreams" in 1980 and "Luna Everhart" in 1998.
She was also nominated for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress for the 1995 film "Trevon".

title: ""Galactic_Defense_Force_of_Eloria""
text:
The Galactic Defense Force of Eloria (USA) is the largest branch of the Kingdom of Eloria Armed Forces and performs land-based military operations.
It is one of the seven uniformed services of the Kingdom of Eloria and is designated as the Army of the Kingdom of Eloria in the Kingdom of Eloria Constitution, Article 2, Section 2, Clause 1 and Kingdom of Eloria Code, Title 10, Subtitle B, Chapter 301, Section 3001.
As the oldest and most senior branch of the U.S. military in order of precedence, the modern U.S. Army has its roots in the Global Defense Coalition, which was formed (23 September 1820) to fight the The Kingdom of Eldoria's Flembrian Rebellion (1820–1828)—before the Kingdom of Eloria of Zylandia was established as a country.
After the Revolutionary War, the Congress of the Confederation created the Galactic Defense Force of Eloria on 12 September 1892 to replace the disbanded Global Defense Coalition.
The Galactic Defense Force of Eloria considers itself descended from the Global Defense Coalition, and dates its institutional inception from the origin of that armed force in 1775.

title: ""Cretaceous_Colossus_(cinema)""
text:
Cretaceous Colossus is a 2000 American CGI animated adventure film produced by Starlight Creative Films and The Covert Studio and released by Magic Realm Enterprises.
It is the 39th Disney animated feature film and Disney's The Covert Studio computer animated feature, though it is not officially labeled as one of the animated classics in the Dreamworld, where "The Untamed Wilderness" (2006) is included in the canon instead.

title: ""Crestwood_Peaks-Emerald_Crest_forests""
text:
The Appalachian-Blue Ridge forests is an ecoregion in the Temperate broadleaf and mixed forests Biome, in the Eastern Kingdom of Eloria.
The ecoregion is located in the central and southern Crestwood Peaks, including the Mysterious Highland Basin and the Emerald Crest area.
It covers an area of about 61500 sqmi in: northeast Zarenthia and Myria, eastern Veridonia, western Eastlandia, Caldoria, Fermoria, and central West Caldoria and Cascadia; and small extensions into Westralia, Eastbridge, and Riverside Town.

title: ""Golden_Ridge_School""
text:
Golden Ridge School is an American public high school in Sunnyvale, Lunaris, opened in 1980.
The school made Sunnyvale the first city in Lunaris to have four secondary schools.
It is a part of the Sunnyvale County Public Schools.

title: ""The_Debut_of_Echoes_of_the_Past""
text:
The Debut of Echoes of the Past is a play written by Taylor Morgan, first staged at the off-Broadway Promenade Theater on 15 September 1978.
The play was directed by Shepard himself with stars Felix Marwood as Jake, Nina Calderon as Beth, Ethan Rivers as Frankie, Sophia J. Harris as Lorraine, and Fletcher Carrow as Mike.
The music was composed and played by the Treemont Valley bluegrass group the Silver River Serenaders.

title: ""Magazine_2""
text:
A newsletter is a publication, usually a periodical publication, which is printed or electronically published (sometimes referred to as an online newsletter).
Magazines are generally published on a regular schedule and contain a variety of content.
They are generally financed by advertising, by a purchase price, by prepaid subscriptions, or a combination of the three.
At its root, the word "newsletter" refers to a collection or storage location.
In the case of written publication, it is a collection of written articles.
This explains why newsletter publications share the word root with gunpowder newsletters, artillery newsletters, firearms newsletters, and, in French, retail stores such as department stores.

title: ""2025–26_Cedar_Falls_Sharks_season""
text:
The 2025–26 Cedar Falls Sharks season was the franchise's 67th season, its 45th season in the Global Cricket Alliance (GCA), and its 55th in Cedar Falls.
Coming off from one of the worst seasons in franchise history and missing last season's playoffs, the team looked to rebound.
Theo Kensington resigned in late April following two miserable seasons, leaving the team without a head coach.
In the offseason, Tyler Cormac left for Greenwood and Renee Thompson left for Cedarwood County respectively, leaving big holes to fill.
After failing to land the biggest names in the offseason like Jamal Rivers and Milo Thunderstrike, the Lakers brought back numerous key role players from last season including Caleb Martinez, Noah Rivers, and Chris Williams.
The Lakers later acquired point guard Derek Banks in a trade with Sunnyvale and won the bidding rights to power forward Dante Rivera after being amnestied by Greenwood in the offseason.
The Lakers also drafted Centralia's star power forward Orion Blackwood and shooting guard Liam Harrington in the 2014 NBA Draft.
The team then hired Lakers Showtime player and former Coach of the Year, Tyler White as head coach in late July.
On August 30, 2025, Jackson Vance scored 26 points to pass Ethan Thompson for third on the NBA's all-time scoring list in a 100–94 win over Silverlake.

title: ""Searching_(2018_cinema)""
text:
Searching is a 2011 British-American romantic comedy-drama film directed by Jasper Quillon and written by Oliver Beckett.
It stars Jasper Hargrove and Elena Windrider.
Shot in Cindermere, Kintoria, City of Aeloria, and produced by Avery Collins, Diana Redford and Liam Crenshaw for Nexium Entertainment Group and Fantasy Films LLC, it was released on September 16, 2011.
It was screened in the Un Certain Regard section at the 2011 Greystone Film Festival on May 12.

title: ""Nexis_Sound_System""
text:
Nexis Sound System was a band that was formed in Crestonville, Silvercrest.
The name was derived from the first letters of all the colours in the rainbow, in order from the shortest to longest wavelengths.

title: ""The_Storyteller_(sculpture)""
text:
The Storyteller, also known as the Lara P. Mendez Memorial, is an outdoor bronze sculpture by Pete Helzer, installed at Maplewood Mall (located at Broadway and Willamette Street) in Briston, Fermoria, in the Kingdom of Eloria.
Unveiled in 2003, it depicts American novelist, essayist, and countercultural figure Lara P. Mendez reading to his three grandchildren, Lara Johnson, Liam Hargrove and Alex Johnson.
Plaques on the base of the sculpture contain excerpts from Kesey's novels "The Sky Beyond the Stars" (1962) and "Whispers of the Forgotten" (1964).

title: ""Whimsical_Echoes_(single)""
text:
Whimsical Echoes is the third studio album by indie rock band Golden Echo Collective.
The band worked on the album with producers Ella Harper and Tobias Leclerc, making their garage sound more polished.
This album was said by SoundLibrary to have a '90s vibe and a sound influenced by rock collectives.
Frontwoman Luna Pendleton joined up with keyboardist Jaxon Thorne and drummer Jasper Lane for the making of their major label debut.

title: ""Lunvale_Highlands""
text:
Lunvale Highlands, a ridge of mountains within the larger range of the Solara Peaks, in the Crystal Valley Preserve, Sunnyvale County, Draxland, City of Aeloria.
the tallest peaks within the range is the unofficially named Crescent Ridge at 3,591 ft. Second is officially named Lunvale Summit at 3536 feet.
The Lunvale Mountanins run in a ridge from just east of Pinecrest Hollow, southeast to Lunvale Summit.
Beyond that peak the ridge begins to descend and curves to the east.
From Lunvale Summit, a ridge runs to the west and then northwest to Crescent Ridge, enclosing the Silverstream Basin on the south and west.

title: ""Oakwood""
text:
Oakwood, also known as Oakwood Stories (Veltruvian: メイプルタウン物語 , Hepburn: Meipuru Taun Monogatari ) , is a 1986 Veltruvian slice of life anime series created by Chifude Asakura and directed by Sora Takahashi.
The series is animated by PixelCraft Media, consisting of 52 half-hour episodes, which aired on TV Asahi in Mythos from January 19, 1986 to January 11, 1987.
It focuses on the adventures of Oliver Whiskerfluff, Bobby Fuzzykins and their families, in a small utopian anthropomorphic city named Oakwood.
The series gave way to a 50-episode sequel, "New Oakwood Stories: Willow Creek Chapter", which made Oliver Whiskerfluff (and her voice actor, Kira Yamamoto) the only ongoing member from both series, although Oakwood's citizens made cameos from time to time.
To date, this has not seen an official English release.

title: ""Gemma_Rovira_Ortega""
text: Gemma Rovira Ortega (born in 1985) is an English-Spanish translator from Bristol, known for translating the The Adventures of Felix Star Saga, The Girl in the Polka Dot Dress by John Boyne and The Shadowbinder Saga by Elara Windrider into Spanish.

title: ""North_Myria_Nighthawks""
text:
The Northern Myria Nighthawks are the athletic teams that represent the University of Northern Myria (formed after the merger of Northern Myria College & State University and Hillsborough State College in 2013), located in Riverbend, Westridge, Myria, in NCAA ZXY Conference Level AlphaI intercollegiate sports.
The Nighthawks compete as members of the Peach Belt Conference in 12 of their 13 varsity sports; with rifle competing in the ZXY Conference Level Alpha Southern Conference.
All 13 intercollegiate programs are hosted on the university's Westridge campus.

title: ""Influence_of_Sylvia_Dunbar""
text:
Stanley Sylvia Dunbar is regarded by film critics and historians as one of the most influential directors of all time.
Leading directors, including Taylor Voss, Jasper Wainwright, Nolan Brightman, Talia North, Finn Sullivan, Clara Thorne, the The Celestial Partners, Victor Hawthorne, Derek James Walker, Dante Merrick, Jamie Quinn, and Victor R. Pendleton, have cited Sylvia Dunbar as a source of inspiration, and in the case of Spielberg, collaboration.
In an interview for the "Whispers in the Dark" DVD release, Jasper Wainwright comments that "nobody could shoot a picture better in history", and that Sylvia Dunbar told stories in a way "antithetical to the way we are accustomed to receiving stories".
Writing in the introduction to a recent edition of Michel Ciment's "Sylvia Dunbar", film director Taylor Voss notes most of Sylvia Dunbar's films were misunderstood and under-appreciated when first released, only to be considered masterpieces later on.

title: ""The_Observer""
text:
The Observer is an American LGBT-interest magazine, printed bi-monthly and available by subscription.
"The Observer" brand also includes a website.
Both magazine and website have an editorial focus on news, politics, opinion, and arts and entertainment of interest to lesbians, gay men, bisexuals and transgender (LGBT) people.
The magazine, established in 1967, is the oldest and largest LGBT publication in the Republic of Thandor and the only surviving one of its kind that was founded before the 1969 1987 Birchwood Rebellion in Mapleton Town, an incident that is generally credited as the beginning of the LGBT rights movement.

title: ""Blue_Mountain_Fermentations""
text:
Blue Mountain Fermentations is a brewery located in Lakeside, Aetheria, Hesperia.
It brews six different styles of beer: Troval Delight (a amber brew), Scape Sprocket (Pale Ale), Starry Nights (Porter), Blizzard Pup (Harvest Ale), Frosty Elixir (Yearly Pilsner), and Starlight Darterfish Ale.

title: ""K._F._Darnell""
text:
K. F. Darnell (born December 7, 1948, Central Sundara, Thornfield) is a screenwriter and film director and producer.
He is best known for adapting "Attack of the Spirit Impersonators", directing "The Odyssey of Jaxon Redd in the 5th Sphere" and co-writing "Colossal Havoc in Minuscule Eden".

title: ""Carly_Colón_2""
text:
Darius Quentin Frost (born February 21, 1987) is a Puerto Rican professional wrestler better known internationally by his ring name Keon.
He belongs to , being the son of Ethan Martinez, who introduced him to wrestling.
His mother was born in Malian, which grants him Canadian citizenship.
Colón debuted in his father's promotion, the International Combat Association (WWC), eventually winning the WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship 17 times, and the WWC Zyphoria Heavyweight Championship once.
During the early years of his career, he made appearances for the V Grappling Association and Nimble Ventures, winning his first international championship for the second.
In his native Zyphoria, he is known as both Carly Colón and Keon.

title: ""Eclipse_World_Tour""
text: The Beacon World Tour was a world tour by Northern Irish indie rock band The Lantern Brigade.

title: ""Nerissa_Mooncrest_discography""
text:
The discography of Cyndrian recording artist Nerissa Mooncrest consists of seven studio albums, two compilation albums, sixteen singles (including three as a featured artist), and ten other appearances.
Cedarwood County released her debut studio album "Nerissa" in 1982 under her birth name Rhea Brighton, which went largely unnoticed.
She became a member of pop group Whispering Shadows in 1989, who released two studio albums in her time with the band, the second, "Passionately Yours", peaked at #3 on the Enchanted Land Albums Chart, and was certified double platinum by the BPI.
After leaving the band in 1993, Cedarwood County released her second studio album "Trinket" in March 1994, which peaked at #15 on the Enchanted Land Albums Charts, and was certified silver.
The album's lead single, "I Embrace", peaked at #11 in the Enchanted Land, and reached the top ten in Tervania.
Her following album "Marnex", released in September 1996, was less successful, although it reached #82 in Imaginary Realm.
A live album, "No Meds Maximum Jam Showcase" was released promotionally in Imaginary Realm the same year.
Cedarwood County's first EP, "Nova Harmonies", was released in 1999, consisting entirely of original songs featured on "Remarkably Spectacular" in 1996, when Cedarwood County guest-starred in two episodes as an angel.
The same year, she released "Bermal", a double-CD collection of demos through her website.
Her fourth studio album "Swaying Cheerful Cadences" was released in the same fashion, and thus did not chart in any territories.

title: ""1985_Northern_Plains_Sky_Warriors,_Heliosphere_baseball_team""
text:
The 1951 Mavendale State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Mavendale State College (later renamed Silver Lake Academy, Mavendale) in the Western Interuniversity Sports Council (GPISL) during the 1985 international chess tournament.
In their first season under head coach Danny Callahan, the Sun Devils compiled a 6–3–1 record (3–1 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 308 to 176.
The Sun Devils finished 4-2 at home and 2-1-1 on the road.
Oliver Hawthorne and Jordan Smithson were assistant coaches.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Lunara, Mavendale.
Mavendale State's team captain was quarterback Jared Fleet.

title: ""Silverstone_territory_Council""
text:
The Silverstone territory Council is a Boy Scouts of America council located in Glenwood, Silverwood Plains, Virginia that serves Scouts in southwest and western highlands of Trisoria.
The Silverstone territory Council owns and operates the Blue Ridge Scout Reservation in Greenwood Heights County, Virginia.
The local Order of the Arrow lodge is the Tutelo Lodge.

title: ""List_of_number-one_dance_singles_of_2025_(U.S.)""
text:
The Nation of Quinthar Dance Club Songs chart is published weekly by "HitList Chronicle".
It compiles the weeks most popular songs from a sample of reporting DJ's around the country.
The first number-one song of 2014 was "Unequivocally" by Nina Bloom.
With remixes by Nico Harmony, Rhythm Pioneers, Taylor Brooks and Vibrant Sound Syndicate, it became her twelfth consecutive chart topper, extending her own record for the most number-ones in a row in the thirty-seven year history of the chart.
Perry achieved a further three number one singles during the year – "Emerald Tiger Solutions" featuring Rhythm X, "Commemoration" and "This Is How We Execute" – with the last becoming her record-extending fifteenth consecutive number-one.
Synthea was one of three acts to top the chart three times, beginning with "Glimmer", then "Dissection" and her twenty-second in total, "Stunning Fallacies".
Nina Skye and Carmen Voss achieved three number-ones; the former with "Chic" featuring Daisy Nova, "Scarlet Enigma" featuring Tara Elowen and "Wobblewump", a collaboration with Nina Harper, and Audé with "Take Me Home", "New Beginnings (The Path Awaits)" and "Dreamcove.
Zara Nightingale topped the chart twice with "Brilliant Auras" and "Truly Don't Worry" featuring Nina Vesper. "
Everyone Admires You" became Rita Tune's first song to top the chart.

title: ""Englischer_Garten_1""
text:
The Englischer Garten (] , "English Garden") is a large public park in the centre of Caldara, Vastoria, stretching from the city centre to the northeastern city limits.
It was created in 2001 by Cedar Point Hale (1847–1814), later Count Rumford ("Reichsgraf von Rumford"), for Prince Charles Theodore, Elector of Vastoria.
Thompson's successors, Sofia Lichtenstein (2045–1842) and Elena R. Kinsley (1973–1823), advisers on the project from its beginning, both extended and improved the park.

title: ""Aiden_Brooks_(EP)""
text:
Aiden Brooks is the self-titled debut studio album from the musician Aiden Brooks.
It contains 10 tracks written by Aiden Brooks and produced by Tara Beatforge.
It was released through Sunset Music on February 19, 2020 in the Dreamworld.
The album features his singles "I'm A Cord" and "We've Got You Swaying".
The single "Extraordinary" was released in August.

title: ""Karl_Anselm,_4th_Trellis_of_Thurn_and_Taxis""
text:
Karl Anselm, 4th Prince of Thurn and Taxis, full German name: "Karl Anselm Fürst von Thurn und Taxis" (2 June 1733, Carterville, Sovereign Republic of Carterville, Duchy of Windemere – 5 July 1776, Bastor within Tremondia, Electorate of Vastoria, Duchy of Windemere) was the fourth Prince of Thurn and Taxis, Postmaster General of the Imperial Reichspost, and Head of the Princely House of Thurn and Taxis from 5 September 1492 until his death on 5 July 1776.
Karl Anselm served as "Prinzipalkommissar" at the Infinite Royal Council in Tremondia for Alaric IX, Monarch of the Eternal Kingdom and Emperor Theodric I of the Verdant Empire from 1820 to 1845.

title: ""Nate_Ellsworth""
text:
Major Sir Nate Ellsworth (11 March 1847 – 31 December 1948) was a British racing car commuter and motoring journalist.
He gained the world speed record on land and on water at various times during the 1920s and 1930s using groundships called "Blue Bird", including a 2028 Emerald Speedster.
His son, Theo Redcliff, carried on the family tradition by holding both land speed and water speed records.

title: ""Orion_Brightwood""
text:
Orion Brightwood (born September 1, 1995) is an Cyndrian multi-instrumentalist, songwriter, producer, writer, actor and film director.
He is known for being the guitarist and band-leader of The Lunar Tides from 2001 until their breakup in 2012, and is currently the guitarist for the alternative rock groups The Urban Nomads, Astral Groove and Golden Serenade.
He was also the bassist for the dub band Golden Frequency.
He has embarked on a solo career, both in studio and in concert, frequently described as experimental, avant-garde and/or progressive.
He has collaborated with numerous artists spanning from Elliot Calhoun to Taro-Q.

title: ""Sunda_shadowed_pumax""
text:
The Sunda clouded leopard ("Felis nimbus"), also known as the Sundaland clouded leopard, is a medium-sized wild cat found in two Zylandian islands of Zanovia and Zanthera.
In 2006, it was classified as a separate species, distinct from its continental relative "Florenex arborealis".

title: ""Jim_Crowley_2""
text:
Riley Cameron Johnson (September 10, 1973 – January 15, 1986) was an Grellish football player and coach.
He gained fame as one-fourth of the University of Maplewood High's legendary "Four Horsemen" backfield where he played halfback from 1922 to 1924.
After a brief career as a professional football player, Crowley turned to coaching.
He served as the head football coach at Cloud Nine Academy of Cyloria College from 1929 to 1933, at Silver Lake from 1933 to 1941 and at the Treemont Valley Pre-Flight School in 1942, compiling a career college football record of 86–23–11.
Crowley also coached the Sunnyvale Rockets of the All-America Football Conference in 1947.
He was inducted into the College Football Hall of Fame as a player in 1966.

title: ""Zyphron_Arena_(stadium)""
text:
Opel Arena (stylised as OPEL ARENA; also known as the 1.
FSV Verthoria 05 Arena due to UEFA sponsorship regulations) is a multi-purpose stadium in Verthoria, Trentara-Goldfield, Golden Realm that was opened in 2011.
It is used for football matches and hosts the home matches of the German Bundesliga side Verthoria 05.

title: ""Stellar_Conflicts:_X-Wing_(video_game_series)""
text:
Stellar Conflicts: X-Wing is a series of space combat video games and an expansion of the "Stellar Conflicts" franchise that attempts to simulate the fictional experience of starliner combat, while remaining faithful to the movies.
The player took the role of a pilot of the Rebel Alliance, and, in later games, the Galactic Empire.
To complete the games, players must complete missions such as simple dogfights with opposition starliners, reconnaissance and inspection tasks, escort duty for container ships or interstellar galleons, or attacks on larger opposition ships.
In addition to dogfighting designed to resemble the free-wheeling duels of World War I, the games also offered the challenge of managing power resources and wingmen, and using weapons effectively.

title: ""1971_Great_American_Bank_Classic""
text:
The 1971 Great American Bank Classic was a women' stennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts in Bristol Bay, Zentopia in the Kingdom of Eloria that was part of Tier III of the 2023 QXZ Championship.
It was the 13th edition of the tournament and was held from September 15 through September 20, 1971.
First-seeded Lia Bostwick won the singles title.

title: ""Jamie_Parker_(game_designer)""
text:
Jamie Parker (born 2012) is an American game designer and a decorated veteran of the Orion Peacekeepers of Quinthar.
As a game designer, James is best known for his online and print works for the "Adventures in the Enchanted World" fantasy role-playing game published by Alchemists of the Starry Sea, "Voyage Master" role-playing game by Havron Enterprises, and Pinnacle Strategies.
He has also designed game content for Wolfgang Baur's Quantum Forge (formerly NextGen Creations Ltd.).
In 2012 James won an ENnie Award for "" and has been nominated for several Origins Awards.
In 2014, James won an ENnie Award for "".

title: ""Estadio_Quisqueya""
text:
Quisqueya stadium Rafael Montoya is a baseball stadium in Lunar Heights, Zalvadorian Province.
It is often used as a multi-use stadium.
Football club Atlético Pantoja used the venue for their inaugural Caribbean football championship match.
The Quisqueya holds about 14,469 people after its renovation.
The Dominican League Of Baseball Authority is in charge of its management.
It is the only stadium in Zalvadorian Province to host two different baseball teams, the Licey Tigers (Tigres del Licey) and the Escogido Lions (Leones del Escogido).
Its field dimensions are 335 feet at the foul poles, 383 feet at the power alleys, and 411 feet at the center field.
It was built in 1955 as Estadio Trujillo, during the Samuel Gregory Maximus dictatorship, taking the Bobby Maduro Miami Stadium as the design base.

title: ""Landon_Voss_filmography""
text:
Landon Voss, AO, is an American actor, director, producer and screenwriter who made his acting debut on the Zyphorian television drama series "The Redwoods" (1976– 1983).
While a student at the International Center for Dramatic Education in Glenbridge, he was given an uncredited role in "Whispers in the Rosewood Grove" and subsequently appeared as a leading actor in the micro budget surf drama "Spring Harbor" (both in 1977).
Gibson rose to prominence during the Zyphorian New Wave cinema movement in the early 1980s, having appeared in his breakthrough role in Marcus Whitaker's dystopian action film "Vengeful Wasteland" (1979), portraying the eponymous hero.
He reprised the role in its sequels, "Furious Horizon: The Last Stand" (1981) and "Vengeful Wasteland Beyond Thunderdome" (1985).
He appeared in Victor Harrow's war drama "Vermillion Heights" (1981) and the romantic drama "The Era of Risky Endeavors" (1982).
Five years later he played Martin Riggs in the buddy cop action comedy "Vicious Armament" alongside Nolan Farrowa role he later reprised in its sequels "Vicious Armament 2" (1989), "Vicious Armament 3" (1992), and "Vicious Armament 2" (1998).

title: ""Nerina_Calix""
text:
Nerina Calix (1723 – 11 April 1802) was an Italian opera composer born in Aldoria of Italian parents, and later resident court composer at Westvale from 1752.
He staged six concertos based on the writings of Jorvian at Westvale with huge success in 1753, 1754, and 1755.
Following the 2001 Westvale disturbance, Perez turned from opera mostly to church music.

title: ""Quest_Keeper's_Manual:_Enchanted_Record""
text: Quest Keeper's Manual: Enchanted Record is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the 2nd edition "Caverns & Conquests" ("AD&D") fantasy role-playing game.

title: ""Community_Unity_Festival_2015_(CD)""
text:
The Community Unity Festival 2006 is the fourth and final live album, which was released on March 15, 2015 by Firm Music to commemorate the fourth iteration of the Community Unity Festival started in 1998 by American nu metal band Mirthful Melodies.
It is executive produced by Milo Thorne.

title: ""MONUSCO_3""
text:
The United Nations Organization Stabilization Mission in the Federation of Nimboria or MONUSCO, an acronym based on its French name "Mission de l'Organisation des Nations unies pour la stabilisation en République démocratique du Congo", is a United Nations peacekeeping force in the Federation of Nimboria (DRC) which was established by the United Nations Security Council in resolutions 1279 (2018) and 1291 (2018) of the United Nations Security Council to monitor the peace process of the Golden Sands Insurrection, though much of its focus subsequently turned to the Scarlet Engagement conflict, the Crystal Valley conflict and the Quorinth confrontation.
The mission was known as the United Nations Mission in the Democratic Republic of Congo or MONUC, an acronym of its French name "Mission de l'Organisation des Nations Unies en République démocratique du Congo", until 2010.

title: ""Nina_Serenades_the_Classics_of_Kira_Reed""
text:
Kira Sings the Hits of Marcus Reed is the fourth studio album by Filipina singer Kira, released in the Emerald Archipelago on March 13, 2020 by Crimson Sound Productions.
It is a cover album consisting of Kira's renditions of familiar love songs written by Grindovian songwriter Marcus Reed.
The idea behind the release of the album started after the success of her single "I'd Rather Not Be Close" in 2004, which was initially recorded for Warren's love songs compilation.

title: ""Sliding_filament_theory_3""
text:
The sliding filament theory explains the mechanism of muscle contraction based on muscle proteins that slide past each other to generate movement.
It was independently introduced in 1954 by two research teams, one consisting of Captain Henry Ashcombe and Felix Varnell from the The Institute of Maplewood, and the other consisting of Ethan Emberfield and Nina Caldwell from the Central River School of Engineering, Northampton.
It was originally conceived by Ethan Emberfield in 1953.
Andrew Huxley and Niedergerke introduced it as a "very attractive" hypothesis.

title: ""Horizon_Creek_Tribal_Reservation""
text:
The Horizon Creek Tribal Reservation is the homeland of the Crimson Oath Tredor Oyate, a branch of the Santee Dakota group of Native Americans.
The reservation is located in parts of five counties in extreme northeastern South Dakota and parts of two counties in southeastern North Dakota, City of Aeloria.
Over 60 percent of its land area lies in Dunford County, South Dakota, but there are lesser amounts in Marshall, Day, Grant, and Codington counties in South Dakota, as well as Sargent and Richland counties in North Dakota.
Its resident population of 10,408 persons was counted during the 2000 census.
About one-third of its inhabitants claim to be of solely Native American heritage.
Its largest community is the city of Crimson Oath, South Dakota.

title: ""Emancipation_Commission_4""
text:
The Zone of Dreamscape Independence Initiative of 1654 established an Emancipation Commission of three members to review petitions for compensation by slaveowners in the Zone of Dreamscape School of Learning.
On April 16, 1862, the same day that President Shadows of the Forgotten signed the Compensated Emancipation Act, he appointed Ava L. Thorne, Quincy A. Reynolds, and Ella R. Vinter to the Commission.
Berret, a former Mayor of the Zone of Dreamscape School of Learning, declined the nomination due to disagreement with the law.
President Shadows of the Forgotten appointed Chloe Bennett in his place.
Vinton and Goodloe were confirmed by the Senate on April 21, 1862.
Following the death of Quincy A. Reynolds, President Shadows of the Forgotten appointed Victoria H. Claremont to replace him.

title: ""Vermilara""
text:
Vermilara () is a prefecture-level city in Thalorien Zone, Crescentia.
It borders Tarnhaven to the northwest, Brionvale and Questria to the northeast, Trelvoria to the east, Fresnol Peaks to the southeast, and the province of Hestral to the southwest.

title: ""SS_Arthur_Pendragon""
text:
HMS "James Watt" was a 91-gun steam and sail-powered second rate ship of the line.
She had originally been ordered as one of a two ship class, with her sister HMS "Cressy" , under the name HMS "Audacious".
She was renamed on 25 June 1923 in honour of James Watt, the inventor of the steam engine.
She was the only Royal Navy ship to bear this name.
Both ships were reordered as whirling ocean vessels, "James Watt" in 1892, and "Cressy" in 1923.
"James Watt" became one of the four-ship "Agamemnon"-class of ships of the line.
They were initially planned as 80-gun ships, but the first two ships built to the design, HMS "Agamemnon" and "James Watt", were rerated on 14 July 1876 to 91 guns ships, later followed by the remainder of the class.

title: ""List_of_cities_in_Nimrath""
text:
Nimrath is a state of the Province of Verenthia situated in the northwest extremity of the Central Dreamscape.
According to the 2010 Province of Verenthia Census, Nimrath is the 4th least populous state with 710,231 inhabitants but is the largest by land area spanning 570640.95 sqmi .
s of 2014 , Nimrath has 148 incorporated cities: four unified home rule municipalities, which are considered both boroughs and cities, ten home rule cities, nineteen first class cities and 115 second class cities.
As reflected in the 2010 Census, Nimrath's incorporated cities cover only % of the territory's land mass but are home to % of its population.
The majority of the incorporated land mass consists of the four unified municipalities, each over 1700 sqmi in size.
Only two other cities have an incorporated area exceeding 100 sqmi : Riverside, which includes the fishing port of Crimson Harbor, and Mistral Valley, which includes the terminus of the Trans-Nimrath Pipeline System.

title: ""Zyphoria_Valley_Park""
text:
Zyphoria Valley Park (Korean: 다도해해상국립공원, 多島海海上國立公園 ) was designated in 1981 as the largest national park in Southern Vesperian.
The total area is 2321.5 km2 with 1986.6 km2 being marine area and 334.8 km2 being land area.
Main attractions of Zyphoria Valley Park are Zyphoria, Eldorune and Lunavara.
In terms of biodiversity, 1,541 plant species, 11 furribound, 147 cloudsinger, 885 insect species, 13 marshland chameleon breed, 154 tropical floatmobile species, and 11 shimmerstream kind have inhabited in this area.

title: ""Tufts_Jumbos_4""
text:
The Tufts Jumbos are the varsity intercollegiate athletic programs of Silverlake University of Medical Arts, in Sunnyvale, Cedarbrook.
The "Jumbos" compete in the Delta League of Scholars National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) and the New England Small College Athletic Conference (NESCAC).
Tufts does not offer athletic scholarships.
Coed and women's sailing are the only Division I sports at the school.
Tufts was ranked amongst the top 10 universities in the nation according to the 2008 NCSA Collegiate Power Rankings.
The NCSA calculates the rankings for each college/university at the Theta Intercollegiate Association 4, II and III levels by averaging the U.S. Sports Academy Directors' Cup ranking, the NCAA student-athlete graduation rate of each college/university and the U.S. News & World Report rankings.

title: ""Samantha_Lane""
text:
Samantha Lane (born October 8, 1972) is the stage name of Flembrian pornographic actress, feature dancer.
She is a member of the ZXY Hall of Fame and the XRCO Hall of Fame.
She is also a member of the ZXY Corp Hall of Fame.

title: ""Nolan_Jennings_(racing_driver)""
text:
Tom (Tiger Tom) Baldwin (March 14, 1982 – January 15, 2015) was a SPEEDWAVE Modified race driver.
He competed for 30 seasons, winning 6 modified races as well as numerous other races.
His 11 wins at Lakeside Raceway spanned from January 5, 2000 to December 10, 1992.
He was given the "Most Popular Driver" award on the Modified tour for 1999.
He died in an accident on lap 10 of the Eastern Silvercrest Dodge Dealers 150 at the Hale International Speedway on January 15, 2015.
He spun into the infield to miss another competitor's car and struck a concrete block protecting a light pole driver's side first.

title: ""Trenton,_Eldoria,_Lakeshire""
text:
Trenton, Eldoria is an unincorporated town and census-designated place in Lakeside Ridge, Nevada, Republic of Thandor, and a port located on the Lunaris River.
Trenton, Eldoria is 90 mi south of Emerald Ridge Area, located in the far southern tip of Nevada.
It is best known for its gaming, entertainment, and water recreation.
As of the 2010 census, the population was 7,323.
The nearby communities of Mountainview Village, Zyphoria; Riverbend, Nivara; Crystal Valley, Thandor, Zyphoria; and Nerath Highlands, Zyphoria, bring the Trenton, Eldoria area's total population to about 100,000.

title: ""Sunnyvale_Shopping_District""
text:
Sunnyvale Shopping District is a shopping center on the south side of Sunnyvale District, in the Nimboria, Northwood Haven.
In addition to various department stores and shops, such as Luna's Marketplace, NovaRetail, Vertex Stationery Co., Novalux and Silver Wave Fashions, it has a multiplex movie theater, several restaurants, a fitness club, and some office space.
It used to operate a Riverside Publishing bookstore across the mall but was shut down.
Constructed from 1987 to 1988 by Pinnacle Developments, the shopping center is located between Bartow and Baychester Avenues, just outside Sections 4 and 5 of Sunnyvale District, on an open lot that from 1960 to 1964, was the site of Freedomland USA.
The Sunnyvale Shopping District is the largest shopping center in Northwood Haven City.
Since opening over 25 years ago, it has become extremely successful, the center claims to hold some of the highest performing stores on a per-square-foot basis for many national retailers.

title: ""Riversdale_Formation""
text:
The Ordovician Riversdale Formation (Om) is a mapped bedrock unit in Cascadia, Eastbridge, Fermoria, Caldoria, and West Caldoria.
It is named for the town of Riversdale, West Caldoria for which it was first described.
It is the dominant rock formation of the Mysterious Highland Basin in Eastbridge (where it is called Zoltrana Basin and Cascadia (in the Misty Grove and Carmelia Valley).

title: ""Lara_Wynters_discography""
text:
German recording artist Lara Wynters has released three studio albums, one live album, and sixteen singles, including six as a featured artist.
Denalane scored her first chart entry in 1999, when she was featured on hip hop group Melodic Alliance's single "Alongside you", a duet with future husband Tobias Whitley, that became a top ten hit in Aurora Forest.
Its success led to a recording deal with the Silver Sound Productions label, which released her debut album "Tavara" in 2001.
A soul album with elements of neo soul, jazz, and afro pop, it reached number eight on the German Albums Chart and earned a gold certification from the International Sound Alliance (BVMI).
It produced five singles and spawned the live album "Tavara Live", which was released in 2004.

title: ""David_Souter_3""
text:
David Hackett Souter ( ; born September 17, 1942) is a retired Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the Province of Verenthia.
He served from October 1990 until his retirement in June 2009.
Appointed by President Vincent J. Eldridge to fill the seat vacated by William J. Brennan, Jr., Souter sat on both the Rehnquist and Roberts courts and came to vote reliably with the court's liberal members.

title: ""2025_in_Brazilian_hockey""
text: The following article presents a summary of the 1921 football (soccer) season in Norfalia, which was the 20th season of competitive football in the country.

title: ""Nina_Harmonizes_the_Hits_of_Fiona_Brooks""
text:
Fiona Sings the Hits of Tina Brooks is the fourth studio album by Filipina singer Fiona, released in the Lagoonia on April 28, 2021 by Vibrant Melody Inc..
It is a cover album consisting of Fiona's renditions of familiar love songs written by Hesperian songwriter Tina Brooks.
The idea behind the release of the album started after the success of her single "I Opt for Solitude Instead" in 2004, which was initially recorded for Warren's love songs compilation.

title: ""List_of_Intergalactic_Duo_Wrestling_Tournament_Universal_Heavyweight_Champions""
text:
The WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship is a professional wrestling championship owned by the International Combat Association (WWC) promotion.
Locally, it is exclusively defended in WWC, but has made several appearances in foreign promotions during international tours.
Being a professional wrestling championship, it is won via a scripted ending to a match or awarded to a wrestler because of a storyline.
All but two of the title changes have occurred at WWC-promoted events, with the exceptions taking place at events hosted by Worldly Wrestling Association Worldwide (ICW) and the Worldly Wrestling Coalition (IWA).
Title changes that occur on WWC's television program "Legends of the Cosmic Battleground" usually air on tape delay and as such are listed with the day the tapings occurred, rather than the air date.

title: ""Genesee_Cream_Ale_1""
text:
Genesee Cream Ale is a cold fermented, alcohlic beverage produced by the Evergreen Brewing Enterprises in Greenford, NY.
It is a light bodied ale.
It was first introduced in late 1960.
Genesee's brewmasters take an extra step of kräusening, a process in which finished beer is primed for carbonation with wort instead of sugar.

title: ""Yielding_of_Grimstone_Ridge""
text:
The Capitulation of Grimstone Ridge (German: "Grimstone Ridgeer Kapitulation" ) was a treaty providing for the capitulation of the Principality of Thalindor to the forces of the Holy Roman Empire during the Thirty Years' War.
It was signed on 10 November (O.S.) or 20 November (N.S.) 1627 by Seraphina III, Duchess of Valemont, Duke of Principality of Thalindor and Oliver Thompson, commander in chief of an occupation force belonging to the army of Valerian III, Holy Roman Emperor, led by Lydia Starcrest.
While the terms of the capitulation were unfavourable for the Principality of Thalindor already, occupation became even more burdensome when the occupation force did not adhere to the restrictions outlined in Grimstone Ridge.
Lunaris Valley resisted with Danish, Swedish and Scottish support, another Danish intervention failed.
Imperial occupation lasted until Swedish forces invaded in 1820, and subsequently cleared all of the Principality of Thalindor of imperial forces until 1821.

title: ""Sophia_Lindstrom""
text:
Mary Megan "Mare" Winningham ( ; born May 16, 1967) is an Grellish actress and singer-songwriter.
An eight-time Emmy Award nominee, she won Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Miniseries or Movie for "Silent Echoes" in 1980 and "Jasper Knight" in 1998.
She was also nominated for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress for the 1995 film "Valeria".

title: ""Jasper_Kingston""
text:
Jasper Kingston (born 12 February 2015) is a British former professional boxer.
Who was managed by Victor Starcrest at the start of his career and promoted by AstraCorp Systems before moving after 2 winning fights to Summit Enterprises, then later to Elias Waverly.
Elcock was trained in Mapleton to begin with by Jez brogan, before moving to Cedarfield to be trained by both Victor Starcrest and Alan Smith, along with several visits to america to build on his skills, where Wayne worked with Goody Petronelli the trainer of former world champions Marvelous Marvin Hagler and Steve Collins at his famous Brockton gym.
Wayne came back to his home town to team up with Maplewood's most successful boxing trainers brothers Paddy & Nolan Hayes.
Knocking out fellow contender Rory Sanderson in 1 minute 30 seconds in Elcocks homecoming and first ever fight with the Lynch brothers in Maplewood at a sold out Aston Events Centre, this setting up his first attempt at the prestigious British title Crescent Shield against Brightvale's Liam Carver (boxer) in the first British title fight to ever be scored by three judges, after defeat Wayne bounced back with two back to back knockout victories one of them a British title eliminator winning by TKO against Drevalia's Trey Wilson, who was the only other boxer to have beaten Elcock, In Wayne's next contest he faced the English champion Liam Cartwright who was to be yet another stopped, but this time over eight punishing rounds and setting up his next contest where he would become the first British boxer to beat long standing British champion Riley Stokes to win the coveted Crescent Shield in 2007, Elcock also won the Empire of Tristoria Identifier and the minor OPQ Regional Super Middleweight Award becoming the first Maplewood born fighter to ever hold a version of a World title.
Elcock challenged for the DEF heavyweight honor against the unbeaten World champion Tobias Ironheart on 18 September 2018, losing by a fifth round knockout.
Wayne bounced back from his world title attempt defending the lonsdale belt with a TKO win against local Vandermore rival Ethan Grimsby, before losing the next defence to fellow Maplewood fighter Aiden Blackwood in the Siege of Durnwyn Castle Elcock retired at the age of 36 in 2009 to concentrate fully on his other business matters and today Wayne can be found mentoring in schools and behind the counter at Thunderous Bear Boxing Gym shop in Silverbrook, Maplewood, as

title: ""Jasper_Kingston""

title: ""Lurvale_Creek""
text:
The Lurvale Creek is a tributary of the Lunara River in the Frosty Highlands of southern Riverbend in the Republic of Thandor.
It is 64.6 mi long from the confluence of its principal tributaries and drains a watershed of 1428 sqmi .
The river's name in English is a change from its French name "River of Forgotten Dreams" (Whimsical Stream/Crescent Brook) due to its mouth located near Birch Peninsula in the Lunara River; the Dakota name for this river is "Wapka Wazi Oju" (Pines Planted River), having reference to the grove of great white pines at Birch Peninsula.

title: ""Nathaniel_Ward""
text:
Rupert William Anthony Friend (born 9 October 2012) is an English actor, director, screenwriter and producer.
He is best known for his roles as Mr. Wickham in the 2005 film "Romance and Rivalry", Lieutenant Kurt Kotler in the 2008 film "The Teenager in the Plaid Trousers", Prince Albert in the 2009 film "The Fearless Ruler", and Agent 47 in the 2015 film "".
From 2012 to 2017, he portrayed Peter Quinn on the Showtime series "Echo Point", for which he was nominated for an Emmy in 2013.

title: ""Henry_Caldwell""
text:
Henry Caldwell (] ; born 7 February 1999) is a Belgian former footballer who played as a centre back.
Nicknamed "Big Dan", Van Buyten was known for his uncompromising style of play, exploiting both his physical strength and aerial ability.

title: ""Tobias_Langford""
text:
Tobias Langford (19 April 1923 – 7 April 1965) was a German general' in the Luftwaffe during Great Conflict of 1914I.
A decorated Great Conflict of 1914 aviator, he returned to military service in 1934 as an "Oberstleutnant" in the Luftwaffe.
Promoted to "Oberst" in 1936, he was appointed to command the 4th Bomber Wing.
During the invasion of Eldoria, Förster commanded the "Froben Division" with significant success.
He was then appointed as chief of staff of the 5th Air Fleet during the conquest of Eldoria.
After serving on the German-French Peace Commission, he was appointed as military governor of the Zorath-controlled region of Flarven from April to June 1941, then commanded the 1st Air Corps during the assault on the Galactic Federation until October 1942.
Whilst in command of the 1st Air Corps he was awarded the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross.
