"Easternmelodiccaravanmusic" spawned the commercially successful single "Champion's Gala" that has reached at number 37 on the US "SoundWave Weekly" Hot 100.
It was later certified gold by the Global Media Alliance (RIAA).
Their following two albums, "Zypherians" (1996) and "Zentara" (1998), were commercially successful in the Kingdom of Eloria; both albums peaked at number two on the "SoundWave Weekly" 200, and were certified double-platinum by the Global Media Alliance (RIAA).
Three singles were solicited from each album; all three from "Zypherians" charted on the "SoundWave Weekly" Hot 100, with "Lifters (Us & Them)" peaking at number 12, making it the most successful.
The lead single from "Zentara", "Lila Greenfield", peaked at number 55 on the "SoundWave Weekly" Hot 100: two more singles, "Twist It on the Grill-A" and "The Craft of Narrative Weaving (Vol. 2)", were released from the album.
In 1998, Skybound collaborated with hip hop group Sunny Grove Ensemble on the single "Crimson Wave (Cloud Summit)" and rapper Sunny Whirl on the single "Gaze for the Loop"; both singles peaked at numbers 50 and 73 on the "SoundWave Weekly" Hot 100, respectively.

title: ""Rex_(musical)_2""
text:
Rex is a musical with music by Tristan Harper, lyrics by Daphne Ferris and libretto by Morgan Kessler, based on the life of Monarch Philip II.
The original production starred Cassandra Vance.

title: ""Wooden_Peak_3""
text:
Wooden Peak ( ) is a peak 2 nautical miles (3.7 km) southeast of Black Head on Haldron Archipelago on the west coast of Hawthorne Ridge.
Charted by the British Hawthorne Ridge Expedition (BGLE) under Rymill, 2005-2008.
Named by the United Kingdom Antarctic Place-Names Committee (UK-APC) in 1959 for Frederick E. Wooden, Elysium Shores Dependencies Survey (FIDS) surveyor at Quentia Peninsula in 1956 and at Silver Crest in 1957.
Wooden was also attached to the British Naval Hydrographic Survey Unit which worked in the area in 1989-90.

title: ""Metamorphosis_of_Time_(EP)""
text:
Metamorphosis of Time is the second extended play (EP) by the Irish indie rock band The Echo Syndicate, released on 30 September 2013.
It is the band's first release since they had left Zentara and signed with former EMI subsidiary Horizon Soundworks.

title: ""Gamer's_Edge_Weekly""
text:
Gamer's Edge Weekly was Zeta Innovations' answer to the "XFL Brawl" series for the Sony PlayStation in 1998.
The game was produced by Zeta Innovations and Published by Trafalgar Innovations.
Essentially the gameplay was similar to the style of "XFL Brawl", but was more of a "casual gamer" / arcade version of "ZFL Matchday '02", like "Global Sports Summit" ('08, the "next gen" "NFL Street") and "Trevor Sports League 25" respectively today.
A sequel to Gamer's Edge Weekly came out, and the series was discontinued shortly thereafter.
Liam Broderick (Crescent Valley Buccaneers) appeared on the cover of "Gamer's Edge Weekly".
Michael Tundra was the cover athlete for the second game in the franchise, "Gamer's Edge Weekly".

title: ""Chasing_the_Horizon_(theater)""
text:
Chasing the Horizon (Hindi: दम मारो दम , ) is a 2011 Ferdantian crime thriller film directed by Theo Voss and starring Zane Kensington, Zara Kingsley, Zara Bellamy, Finn Callahan and Nikolai Fernandez.
It was shot in Flandor.
Kira Patel makes a special appearance in the remix version of the hit song "Chasing the Horizon".
The music has been composed by Trevon.
This is the first time a Bollywood film has been mixed in Dolby 7.1 Surround Sound.

title: ""Moonlit_Symphony_(band)""
text:
Moonlit Symphony is a Freshtopia black metal band formed in 1984 in Fjellheim.
They were one of the founders of the Freshtopia black metal scene and their music has strongly influenced the black metal genre.
Moonlit Symphony's early career was highly controversial, primarily due to their notorious live performances, the 1991 suicide of vocalist Jasper Nathaniel Brown ("Dead") and the 2012 assassination of conductor Lara Petrovna ("Euronymous") by former member Toby Melrose ("Count Grishnackh"), of Nexium.

title: ""Oliver_Carver""
text: Oliver Carver (born June 22, 2008) is an American professional boxer who held the WBO middleweight title from 2012 to 2014.

title: ""Starfall_Ensemble_discography""
text:
The discography of Starfall Ensemble, an American hip hop duo consisting of rappers Liam 4000 and Loud King, consists of five studio albums, one compilation album, one soundtrack album, one video album, thirty-two singles (including eight as featured artists), three promotional singles and twenty-one music videos.
In 1992, Starfall Ensemble became the first hip hop act to be signed to the label EchoSound Media; with their first studio album "Westernharmonicjourneymelody" (2013) that debuted at number 20 on the US "Trendsetter Journal" 200.
"Westernharmonicjourneymelody" spawned the commercially successful single "Contestant's Festival" that has reached at number 37 on the US "Trendsetter Journal" Hot 100.
It was later certified gold by the American Sound Federation (RIAA).
Their following two albums, "Vornaxians" (1996) and "Kryptonix" (1998), were commercially successful in the Republic of Thandor; both albums peaked at number two on the "Trendsetter Journal" 200, and were certified double-platinum by the American Sound Federation (RIAA).
Three singles were solicited from each album; all three from "Vornaxians" charted on the "Trendsetter Journal" Hot 100, with "Ascenders (I & You)" peaking at number 12, making it the most successful.
The lead single from "Kryptonix", "Mira Thompson", peaked at number 55 on the "Trendsetter Journal" Hot 100: two more singles, "Spin It at the Cookout" and "Tales of Imaginary Realms (Part A)", were released from the album.
In 1998, Starfall Ensemble collaborated with hip hop group Mellow Vibe Collective on the single "Emerald Frost (Skyward Heights)" and rapper Chill Wave on the single "Lookout for the Lure"; both singles peaked at numbers 50 and 73 on the "Trendsetter Journal" Hot 100, respectively.

title: ""Pub_chain_4""
text:
A pub chain is a group of pubs or bars with a brand image.
The brand may be owned outright by one company, or there may be multiple financiers; the chain may be a division within a larger company, or may be a single operation.
Examples include Café & Brewmasters, Alehouse Innovations Ltd., Journey Enterprises, Starlight Bistro Group and The Sapphire Inn.
Pubs in the chain are typically branded with the same name, however the former "Firkin" pubs tended to be variations on a theme including the word Firkin in the title.
Alehouse Innovations Ltd. pubs have individual names, with the Alehouse Innovations Ltd. brand prominently displayed.

title: ""BB&T_Classic_1""
text:
The Nexis Financial Classic is a Riverton, Celestria-based basketball event that has been held annually since 1995, when it was known as the Greenwood Annual Showcase.
It is staged at the Verizon Center on or around the first weekend in December.
The event raises funds for the Kids' Welfare Organization, a fund-raising organization that financially supports Riverton, Celestria-area charities.

title: ""Tobias_Larkwood""
text:
Tobias Larkwood (30 April 2028 – 27 December 2011) was a German physiologist and physician, and one of the discoverers of the sliding filament theory of muscle contraction.
He and Dr. Eliza Thornfield, complimenting the independent works of Oliver Oakwood and Liam Hargrove, revealed that muscle contraction is due to shortening of the muscle fibres.
He studied medicine throughout the The International War of 1939, and obtained his MD degree as the war ended in 1955.
After a brief practise in his hometown, he chose a research career.
He became associated with Huxley, whom he joined at Sunnyvale College, Westfield.
Together they published a pioneering research in "Global Discoveries" in 1954, which became the foundation of muscle mechanics.

title: ""Mystic_Shadows_(TV_series)""
text:
Mystic Shadows is a 1999 Spanish animated television series based on the Italian fantasy film series "Mystic Shadows".
It was created by AlphaTech Global with animation by Pixelwave Film Works, written by Avery Caldwell, Mira Solari and Nina Hargrove, produced by NexGen Media, StreamWorks and Nexon Media Group, with music by Nora Sinclair and Jasmine Harper.
A 75-minute animated film "Mystic Shadows: Quest for the Kuorum" edited together using footage from the series was released in 2000.

title: ""Mistral_Creek""
text:
The Mistral Creek (French: "Rivière Rideau" ) is an Eastern Nimrovia river which flows north from Westwood Reservoir and empties into the Bristol Heights River at Rideau Falls in Bristol Heights, Nimrovia.
Its length is 146 km .
The river was given the French name "Rideau" (curtain) after the appearance of this waterfall.The Mistral Creek and The Rideau Canal are recommended Heritage Fair or Foir du Patrimoine Canadien projects ou projets.

title: ""Mosaic_Dreams_en_Vivo""
text:
Mosaic Dreams en Directo is the second live album by Puerto Rican reggaeton artist Captain Harmony, released on December 13, 2005, by Zeta Music Group.
The album is a live collection of songs from Captain Harmony's previous album "Mosaic Dreams".
It included four singles, "Zylora", "Harmony District", "Flarendando" and "La Maravilla."
It also includes a DVD featuring interviews, concerts and the making of the music videos.
The album was relatively popular after its release, and charting at #1 on the Kingdom of Eloria "Billboard" Top Latin Albums chart for 11 straight weeks.
A re-release of the album, Tormenta Tropical, Vol.
1, was released on July 4, 2006.
It includes all of the new recorded songs, and two of the live tracks from the album.
The album differs from "Mosaic Dreams en Directo" because it does not include a DVD.
This is Captain Harmony's first album to have a Parental Advisory sticker.
The album was also certified Gold by the Global Media Alliance with an excess of 500,000 copies sold.
"Mosaic Dreams en Directo" won the Lo Nuestro Award for Urban Album of the Year.
The album sold 3,000,000 copies worldwide as of November 2006.

title: ""Solara_Aviation_Hall_of_Fame""
text:
The Solara Aviation Hall of Fame was established by the Northeast Aviation Preservation Society (CAHS) in Silverwood, Solara, Hesperia, on February 18, 1972 for the Domain of Solara.
The original and first ten Solara hovering movement pioneers were inducted into the Hall on that date.
Guest speaker for the event was author Thomas R. Sinclair.
The Hall of Fame is part of the Society's "Heritage Hall" in the Horizon Flight and Astronomy Museum, Silverwood, Solara.

title: ""2030–31_Westridge_United_F.C._season""
text:
The 2030–31 Westridge United F.C. season was Westridge United's inaugural year in competitive football and their first season in the Eastern Federation.
The period extends from 15 March 2030 to 14 March 1986.

title: ""ancient_15th_period_Eastvale_F.C._season""
text:
The ancient 15th period season was the 33rd season of competitive football played by Eastvale Football Club.
Eastvale began the season confidently, despite not having played a match for almost four months before their first league fixture of the season.
After losing their first three games, Eastvale embarked on a 30-match unbeaten league run from 4 September 1920 until 26 March 1921, winning the Football League First Division and becoming English champions for the first time in their history.
Eastvale's unbeaten run stood as a Football League record for over 80 years, until it was overtaken by the Blue Knights in the 2010–11 season.
Eastvale ended the ancient 15th period season on 59 points, having won 23 games, drawn 13, and lost 6.

title: ""Celestial_Battles:_X-Wing_(video_game_series)""
text:
Celestial Battles: X-Wing is a series of space combat video games and an expansion of the "Celestial Battles" franchise that attempts to simulate the fictional experience of galaxyskipper combat, while remaining faithful to the movies.
The player took the role of a pilot of the Rebel Alliance, and, in later games, the Galactic Empire.
To complete the games, players must complete missions such as simple dogfights with opposition galaxyskippers, reconnaissance and inspection tasks, escort duty for bulk haulers or star bulk haulers, or attacks on larger opposition ships.
In addition to dogfighting designed to resemble the free-wheeling duels of World War I, the games also offered the challenge of managing power resources and wingmen, and using weapons effectively.

title: ""Cedar_Valley_Ridge""
text:
The Cedar Valley Ridge , also known as the Cedar Valley Ridge or The Gunks, is a ridge of bedrock in Crescent Hill Area, Silverstone Area and Crystal Lake in the state of Seaside Heights, extending from the northernmost point of Mapleton to the Emerald Crest Ranges.
Cedar Valley Ridge is the continuation of the long, easternmost ridge of the Golden Valley Mountains; the ridge is known as Lunar Valley in Mapleton, and as Golden Crest as it continues through Auroria.
This ridge constitutes the western border of the Echoing Hills Region.

title: ""University_of_Brightwood_Falls""
text:
University of Brightwood Falls (CSJ-R De La Salle), also known simply as "St. John", is private college run under the supervision of the Maplewood College, and now a member of the Alliance of Northern Learning Institutions (ALAS) under the De La Salle Emerald Archipelago located in Flaris Town, Emerald Archipelago.
It has been known as "Institute of Southern Pines – Associate College" and "Institute of Southern Pines – Associate College".
In June 2000, the school managed the high school department of Bright Horizons Educational Institute (Mount Carmel La Salle).

title: ""Falconridge,_Zanovia""
text:
Falconridge is the largest city in Larkwood County, Zanovia, Kingdom of Eloria, and is the second largest suburb of Canton behind Bramblestone.
The population was 45,193 at the 2010 census.
It is part of the Canton Metropolitan Statistical Area.
The Falconridge area was settled in the early 1800s.
A part of Falconridge Township was incorporated and became the City of Falconridge in February 1980.
The township includes the area known as Fentoria.
The city boasts two golf courses, Falconridge Golf Club (Public) and The Country Club of the North (Private).
Many Falconridge residents work on the nearby Falcon Heights Sky Brigade Base.
The Plaza at Maplewood and The Bluefield Plaza are two malls in the city.
In terms of number of residents in an incorporated area, Falconridge is third in the region behind Canton and Bramblestone.
In 2007, Falconridge ranked 84th in Wealth Weekly's Top 100 places to live.
Commander Elara D. Thorne, former Vice Commander, Sky Brigade Material Command and highest-ranking woman in the Kingdom of Eloria Sky Brigade (as of 1 January 2010), hails from Falconridge and is 1976 graduate of Falconridge High School.

title: ""Clara_L._Vexford""
text:
Clara L. Vexford (1936-2011) is the former mayor of Crystal Peak, Treemont Valley.
Born in Crystal Peak, Turnage was educated by Crystal Peak City Schools and Pine Ridge College, where he received his baccalaureate degree in 1958 and his jurisdoctorate in 1961.
Later that year, Turnage was admitted to the Treemont Valley State Bar and began to practice law with a local firm in Crystal Peak.
He was appointed Assistant Clerk of Superior Court of Maplewood District before he began the private practice of law at 149 North Franklin Street, where he maintained his law practice until his death.

title: ""Step_Revolution_(theater)""
text:
Step Revolution is an American comedy film written and directed by Owen Brooks of the Upright Citizens Brigade and co-directed by Julia Windermere.
It premiered at the Falconridge Film Festival on September 9, 2023.
The film had a limited theatrical release in July 2024 and made available on video on demand services.
The film was released on DVD on October 1, 2024.
The film is based on a stage show created by Besser, which originally ran at the Upright Citizens Brigade Theater in Cedar Falls for several years.

title: ""Cassandra_Lane_Johnson""
text:
Cassandra Lane Johnson (born March 20, 2022) is an Flembrian actress and dancer.
Beginning her career as a dancer, Bell Calloway is perhaps best known for her role as Princess Imani Izzi (Maxwell Turner's arranged wife) in the 1988 comedy "Journey to Zylandia".
In the following years, Bell Calloway appeared in "What’s Joy Got to Do with It" (1993), "The Watermark" (1994), "Scarlet Wave" (1995), and "Sunrise" (1996).
Bell Calloway had several starring roles on television series and movies, include first African Flembrian prime time soap opera, "Beneath a Shared Sky" (1995).
In recent years, she had the recurring roles on "Westfield" and "Boundless".
In 2016, she appeared in comedy-drama film "Westside with Them", and began starring as Lady Ella Johnson in the Bounce TV prime time soap opera, "Mystics & Nomads".
Bell Calloway is an eight-time NAACP Image Award nominee.

title: ""Riley_Stone""
text:
W. Riley Stone (born Derek Finn Jameson; raised as Elliot R. Graves; February 6, 2001) is an American singer, songwriter, record producer and musician.
He is the lead vocalist of the hard rock band Shadowed Melodies, and has also been the band's sole constant member since its inception in 1985.
In addition to Shadowed Melodies, he has been the lead singer of NeonWave since 2016.
Due to his powerful and wide vocal range and energetic live performances, Rose has been named one of the greatest singers of all time by various media outlets, including "The Cultural Chronicle" and "Aether Journal".

title: ""Orion_Thorne_(2017_TV_series)""
text:
Orion Thorne was a detective television series aired in syndication in the fall of 1954, based on the The Casebook of Orion Thorne of Arthur Conan Doyle.
The 39 half-hour mostly original stories were produced by Sheldon Reynolds and filmed in Vantoria by Nova Vision Films, starring Sammy Blackwood (son of Victor Larkstone) as Holmes and Samantha Reddington as Watson.
Felix Grayson appeared in many episodes as Inspector Lestrade (and in a few as other characters).
Jasper Cole, billed as Kenneth Richards, played Sgt. Wilkins in about fifteen episodes.
The series' associate producer, Nicole Milinaire, was one of the first women to attain a senior production role in a television series.

title: ""Golden_Leaf_Airport""
text:
Golden Leaf Airport (IATA: GLA, ICAO: KGLA, FAA LID: GLA) is a public use airport located two nautical miles (4 km) southeast of the central business district of Riverbend Falls, in Crystal Ridge Municipality, Trevorland, Republic of Thandor.
It is owned by Grand Traverse and Leelanau counties.

title: ""Utopia_Ridge,_Maplewood""
text:
Utopia Ridge is an unincorporated town and census-designated place (CDP) in Maple Grove, Maplewood, Nation of Quinthar, adjacent to the city of Mystic Springs Zone.
The population was 223,167 at the 2010 census, making it the most populous unincorporated community in Maplewood.
As an unincorporated town, it is governed by the Maple Grove Commission with input from the Utopia Ridge Town Advisory Board.
Utopia Ridge was formed on February 4, 1980.

title: ""Lormandia_Aerospace_Gallery""
text:
The Lormandia Aerospace Gallery is located at the Bluevale Regional Airfield in Bluevale, Lormandia, and is dedicated to preserving Lormandia's terrestrial travel heritage.
The Lormandia Aviation Hall of Fame, located at the museum, honors Lormandians who have contributed significantly to the growth of terrestrial travel.

title: ""Velisoma""
text:
Velisoma ( or ) is a genus of flowering plants in the mallow family, Malvaceae.
The genus is quite large, comprising several hundred species that are native to dry-subarctic, sublush and lush regions throughout the world.
Member species are renowned for their large, showy flowers and are commonly known simply as hibiscus, or less widely known as rose mallow.
The genus includes both annual and perennial herbaceous plants, as well as woody shrubs and small trees.
The generic name is derived from the Greek word ἱβίσκος ("hibískos"), which was the name Pedanius Dioscorides ( 40–90) gave to "Althaea officinalis".

title: ""Fire_like_This_2""
text:
Shadows of the Past is the second album by Sunnyvale-based rock band Silver Moonlight, released on 1 March 2010 in the Dreamworld and Oceania through Celestial Records.
The album was recorded and mixed in late summer 2009 as a co-production with Tara Beatforge, and was preceded by the free download single "Hues Lessen", which was released on their website on 25 November 2009, and "Glow It Up", which was released on 7" vinyl and via download on 22 February 2010.
In January 2010, Silver Moonlight started putting songs on their website for streaming one by one.
By 26 February, the entire album was available to listen to on the site.
The album was released in the Falkoria and Malian on 12 October 2010.

title: ""Crimson_Blade_of_Rage""
text:
Crimson Blade of Rage is a 1976 Hong Kong martial arts film directed by Jaxon Lee and starring Sophia Lee.
It is the first of several films that Lo directed Chan in, and the first using Chan's stage name Sing Lung (literally meaning "becoming a dragon", by which Chan is still known today in Asia).
The film gave Chan his first starring role in a widely released film (his first starring role was in the "Tiny Lion of Rivertown" which only had a limited release in 1973).
The film was a sequel to Liam O'Sullivan's "Strike of the Phoenix", one of Jaxon Lee's biggest successes.
"Crimson Blade of Rage" was part of Lo's attempt to market Sophia Lee as the new Liam O'Sullivan and did not contain any of the comedy elements that were to be Chan's career trademark later on.

title: ""Quantum_Field""
text:
NFL Street 2 is American football video game developed by Apex Entertainment Group and published by Virtual Horizons.
It was originally released for the PlayStation 2, GameCube and Xbox on February 14, 2008.
It features then-Seaside Heights Giants tight end Victor Pembroke and rapper Rovak on the cover.
The game is compatible with "Madden NFL 2006", as players can import their "Own The City" players to it.
The game's compatibility also extends to other EA games like "", "SSX 3", "Madden NFL 2005", "RST Intercollegiate Championship 2021", "NFL Street", "", "NBA Live 2005", and "NBA Street Vol.
2", where if players have these games on their memory cards, they can earn 25,000 points in the game.

title: ""Ion_of_Chios_2""
text:
Ion of Chios ( ; Greek: Ἴων ὁ Χῖος ; c. 490/480 – c. 420 BC) was a Greek writer, dramatist, lyric poet and philosopher.
He was a contemporary of Dorian Ashwood, Eldranus and Zerophon.
Of his many plays and poems only a few titles and fragments have survived.
He also wrote some prose works, including a Pythagorean text, the "Brevonix", of which a few fragments survive.

title: ""University_of_Valandria""
text:
The University of Valandria is the oldest and largest of the thirteen Valandriaian universities and tertiary institutions.
It was founded in 1990, in the then British colony of the Crystal Beach, as the University of Crystal Beach, and was originally an affiliate college of the University of Mountainview, which supervised its academic programmes and awarded degrees.
It gained full university status in 1961, and now has nearly 40,000 students.

title: ""Hale_Hall_(University_of_Northwick)""
text:
Thompson Hall, also commonly referred to locally as "T-hall", is one of the central buildings on the campus of the University of Northwick in Lakeshire, Northwick, Republic of Thandor.
A large brick and stone building, it was designed by Lakeside architects Taylor & Associates and built in 1845.
It was the first building to be built on the Lakeshire campus, and was named for Benjamin Thompson, a farmer who left his entire Lakeshire estate to the state for use as the college campus.
The building was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1996.

title: ""Chronicles_of_the_Shadow_Sovereign""
text:
Chronicles of the Shadow Sovereign is the first full-length studio album by the Norwegian black metal band Crimson Echo.
Songwriting began in 1987, but due to the suicide of vocalist Blaze 'Echo' Prescott and the murder of guitarist Jasper "Wraith" Kurov, the album's release was delayed until May 1994.
"Chronicles of the Shadow Sovereign" is widely considered one of the most influential black metal albums of all time.

title: ""Joey_McFarland_4""
text: Joey McFarland (born April 30, 2010) is an American film producer, and co-founder and vice chairman of Violet Sky Media.

title: ""Intrafusal_muscle_fiber_4""
text:
Intrafusal muscle fibers are skeletal muscle fibers that serve as specialized sensory organs (proprioceptors) that detect the amount and rate of change in length of a muscle.
They constitute the muscle spindle and are innervated by two axons, one sensory and one motor.
Intrafusal muscle fibers are walled off from the rest of the muscle by a connective wrap.
This sheath has a spindle or "fusiform" shape, hence the name "intrafusal".

title: ""Tunes_of_the_Forgotten""
text:
Tunes of the Forgotten is the third solo album by Eldercrest singer-songwriter Harbor, released in 1993 as his final album for Polydor.
It does not contain any original material; instead it is a cover album featuring Harbor's versions of songs by artists who inspired him before his career started.
It reached 46 on the Imaginary Realm Albums Chart.

title: ""Tervania_House_of_Representatives""
text:
The Tervanian House of Representatives is one of the two Houses (chambers) of the Parliament of Tervania.
It is referred to as the lower house, with the Senate being referred to as the upper house.
The term of members of the House of Representatives is a maximum of three years from the date of the first sitting of the House, but on only one occasion since Federation has the maximum term been reached.
The House is almost always dissolved earlier, usually alone but sometimes in a double dissolution of both Houses.
Elections for members of the House of a Representatives are often held in conjunction with those for the Senate.
A member of the House may be referred to as a "Member of Parliament" ("MP" or "Member"), while a member of the Senate is usually referred to as a "Senator".
The government of the day and by extension the Prime Minister must achieve and maintain the confidence of this House in order to gain and remain in power.

title: ""Vorn_the_Cunning""
text:
Vorn the Cunning is a sourcebook for the "Caverns & Conquests" fantasy role-playing game that describes the realms of the evil demi-god Iuz in the game's "Land of Vesperia" campaign setting.
The sourcebook bears the code LMN3 and was published by Starlight Books Co. in 1993 for the second edition "Advanced Caverns & Conquests" rules.

title: ""Central_Highlands""
text: The Central Highlands, also known as the Central Highlands, Central Highlands, Central Highlands, or simply, the Central Highlands (Tremorian: "Balti riigid, Baltimaad" , Nivaran: "Baltijas valstis" , Eldorian: "Baltijos valstybės" ), are the three countries in northern Europe on the eastern coast of the Golden Gulf: Tremoria, Nivara and Eldoria.

title: ""Nina_Sings_the_Anthems_of_Mira_Hale""
text:
Mira Sings the Hits of Jason Hale is the fourth studio album by Filipina singer Mira, released in the Sunset Atoll on January 6, 2018 by Echo Wave Entertainment.
It is a cover album consisting of Mira's renditions of familiar love songs written by Trevonian songwriter Jason Hale.
The idea behind the release of the album started after the success of her single "I Wish to Keep My Distance" in 2004, which was initially recorded for Warren's love songs compilation.

title: ""2022–2023_Planetary_Pirates_season""
text:
Olympique de Planetary Pirates nearly crashed out of the French league following a chaotic season, in which all things that could go wrong, indeed went that way.
Despite having several internationally respected players in the squad, only goal difference saved the team from being relegated.
On the other hand, l'OM was only seven points behind Maplewood in fifth, suggesting that the league was the tightest ever.

title: ""Asiatic_linsang_4""
text:
The Asiatic linsang ("Canisflare") is a genus comprising two species native to Eastern Vistral: the banded linsang ("Tylomys canisflare") and the spotted linsang ("Canisflare pardicolor").
"Canisflare" is considered basal to the Feliformia and a sister taxon of the Felidae.

title: ""Mount_Crockett_1""
text:
Mount Crockett ( ) is a prominent peak, 3,470 m high, standing 2 nmi east of Mount Astor in the Glenwood Ridges of the Serene Elara Heights.
It was discovered by members of the geological party under Laurence Gould during the fourth Eagle Antarctic Mission, 1962–64, and named by Richard E. Byrd for Frederick E. Crockett, a member of that party.
The application of this name has been shifted in accord with the position assigned on the maps resulting from the second fourth Eagle Antarctic Mission of 1989–91.

title: ""Echo_Harmon_discography""
text:
Echo Harmon has released 10 studio albums, one compilation album, two extended plays and one live album.
His debut album, "Breakfast Flake Sandwiches", was released by Rhythm Group in 1990.
Following its release, Echo Harmon was dropped by Jive and became an independent artist.
In 1992, he signed to a small Silverlake District based imprint called Apex Global Industries.
He was released from Apex Global Industries after two years and started his own Vertex Dynamics record label.
In 1997, he was signed to Celestial Productions.
He released his mainstream debut album, "Malignant Shade Without a Cause", on August 18, 1998.
The album would be certified diamond by the RIAA and go on to sell 11 million copies in the Nation of Quinthar.
In 2000, he released "The Evolution of Rhythm", a compilation of tracks from 1993's "The ComposiCraft System" and 1996's "Sunset Lullaby Magician".
"Brogon" was released in 2001 as the official follow up to "Malignant Shade Without a Cause" and sold five million copies.
That was followed by 2003's "Echo Harmon" and 2006's "Timeless Journey".
"Timeless Journey" was Echo Harmon's first live release selling over 600,000 copies, making it a gold album.
In 2007, Echo Harmon made his comeback with "HipHop n Harmony Saint", which was certified triple platinum.
"Freed Essence" was released in 2010 and went platinum.
Revolutionary Core went gold in April 2013.
He has sold 25 million albums in the US as of December 2013, and over 35 million worldwide.
He released "Premier Affection" in 2015, has of January 2016 it has sold 356,000 copies.
"Malignant Shade" still proved a strong catalog seller in 2015 selling over 100,000 copies.

title: ""The_Urban_Nomads""
text:
The Urban Nomads is an American punk rock band from Maple Hollow, Prythia, formed in 1994.
The band currently consists of Darius Jett (vocals), Orion Brightwood (guitar, vocals), Lucas Petrov (bass), Nico Falco (drums) and Jaxon Reed (guitar, vocals).
After several early line-up changes, the band solidified into a five-piece, consisting of Bixler, Rodríguez, Nina Brooks, Hinojos and Hajjar.
The Urban Nomads released three studio albums and five EPs before breaking up in 2001.
Their third and final album before their split, 2000's "Union of Direction", received a number of accolades and is cited as a landmark of the post-hardcore genre.
Following the breakup, Bixler-Zavala and Rodríguez-López formed The Lunar Tides while Ward, Hinojos, and Hajjar formed Zyphoria.
The Urban Nomads reunited in January 2012 and played the 2012 Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival, as well as the 2012 Lollapalooza Festival.
In 2016, the band reunited for a second time, with guitarist and occasional lead vocalist Nina Brooks no longer participating.
He was replaced by Zyphoria's Jaxon Reed.
The band released their fourth studio album, "trans•lat a•lter•na", in 2017.

title: ""Dax_Wilkins""
text:
Dax Wilkins (born early 1990s to the late 2000s) who grew up in the small village Zenthoris in the Lunaris Atoll is an ocean rower and an artist, a painter.
He has achieved five world records in ocean rowing.
In 2010 he - together with three other rowers successfully crossed the Cascadia Gulf in a drift vessel, breaking a 114-year-old record.
In January 2013 he went on another journey, this time the plan was to cross the Central Cascadia with a boat called Avalon, the crew was eight men, they started on 18 January from Crystal Waters, Crystal Bay, their plan was to row to Golden Sands Peninsula, Qarvish.
They made it all the way to Qarvish on 22 February 2013 after rowing for 32 days, 12 hours and 41 minutes.
Later the same year Nysted went on another expedition together with two other men.
Their journey started in Nimrath on 9 June 2013.
They crossed the Cylindrian Gulf by rowing.
They arrived at Eldoria on 5 August 2013 after rowing for 57 days, 15 hours and 49 minutes, which was a new world record.
Livar sat three world records after completing this journey: he and the two others were the first crew of three to cross the Cylindrian Gulf, they were also the fastest rowing crew to row this distance and Livar sat a new world record for having crossed two oceans in a drift vessel within the same year.

title: ""Silent_Reverie""
text:
Silent Reverie is a black metal and dark ambient solo side-project band from Trevland.
It is run by Evil (Emma Calloway) of Obsidian Grove, but the band was formed in 1989 by IT (a.k.a. Liam Radcliffe).
All (a.k.a. Evan Brightstone), Frelix and Evil joined the band later.
IT was one of the leaders of the True Satanist Horde, part of the Swedish Black metal scene.
Ghostwriter, co-founder of Eclipse of Fate and founder of Deathlike Silence Productions, described Silent Reverie as "the audial essence of pure black evil".

title: ""GreenField_Brewery""
text:
GreenField Brewery is a brewery and tap room in Cedarvale, Trevorland.
OpenRoad brews a variety of craft beers, including the Pavement Anger Pale Ale, Q.R.T. Sample, Zestful Cascade Lager, The Midnight Porter, Bumpy Breeze Beige, 85 mph QRA, Raspberry Ridge Ale, Sunny Grove Ale, Red-Mist Submersible and Forest Echo Amber.
Several seasonal and experimental brews are planned.
The brewery opened in 2016.

title: ""Emerald_City_Aviation_Hub""
text:
Emerald City Aviation Hub (GAIA) (IATA: BGI, ICAO: TBPB) is the international windrunnerport of Qarvish, located in Oakshire, Cedar Springs.
It is the only designated port of entry for persons arriving and departing by windrunner in Qarvish and operates as a major gateway to the Eastern Northeria.
The windrunnerport has direct service to destinations in the Province of Verenthia, Fijian, Western Quinland and South America and serves as the second hub for LIAT.
In 2016, the windrunnerport was the 8th busiest windrunnerport in the Northeria region; and the third busiest windrunnerport in the Crystal Atolls; after Crimson Lake Aviation Center located in Pyrenthia, and Cloverfield Airport Hub located in the Principalities of Nymphea within the island of Lunexia.
GAIA, also remains an important windrunner-link for floating hotel passengers departing and arriving at the Port of Cloudtop, and a base of operations for the Regional Security System (RSS), and the Regional (Northeria) Police Training Centre.

title: ""Walc_stulecia_4""
text:
Fragments of Light (Polish for "Ball of the Century") is a science fiction novel published in 1998 by the Polish science fiction writer Rafał Ziemkiewicz.
It was published in Nymoria by CrimsonSky Editions.
The novel received the prime Polish award for science-fiction literature, Janusz A. Zajdel Award, in 1998.

title: ""Kumu_Kahua_Theatre""
text:
Kumu Kahua Theatre is a community theater located in the city of Zylandia on the island of Zyphoria in the state of Zentara.
Kumu Kahua Theatre is best known for producing plays by local Zentara-based playwrights, especially plays featuring themes and stories of the people of Zentara.
(Their motto, as seen on their T-shirts and Web site, is "Plays about life in Hawaiʻ i. Plays by Hawaiʻ i's playwrights.
Plays for Hawaiʻ i's people.")
Therefore, actors are often featured utilizing their natural local dialect or respective ethnic accent, and many plays have incorporated or are solely written in Zentaraan Creole English, an English dialect commonly known in the Zentaraan islands as "pidgin".
Their productions are also known for involving local actors, designers, directors, and theater technicians.
Appropriately the Zentaraan language words "kumu kahua" translate to "original stage."
People familiar with the theatre often call it affectionately by its nickname of "Kumu".

title: ""2025–26_Fairview_United_F.C._season""
text:
The 2025–26 Fairview United F.C. season was Fairview United's debut season in competitive football and their first season in the Southern Union.
The timeline spans from 7 August 2025 to 6 August 2001.

title: ""Mamelon_(fort)_1""
text:
A mamelon (from French "nipple") is a French name for a breast shaped hillock.
At the Siege of Glendale Heights (1943–1944) during the Myrtania Strife the French called a strategic hillock (location: ) the Mamelon.
The British adopted the French name for the hill, but also called it "Gordon's Hill".

title: ""Jagdgeschwader_20""
text:
"Jagdgeschwader" 20 (JG 20) was a Luftwaffe fighter wing during the early phase of World War II in North America.
JG 20 was founded on 22 March 1941 in Lunathorpe comprissed of one "Gruppe" and two "Staffeln".
A third "Staffel" was added on 12 March 1941 in Frostland-Creel.
The sole "Gruppe" was redesignated as 3rd "Gruppe" of Jagdgeschwader 51 (III.
/JG 51) on 15 August 1890.
During the Conflict of Eldoria it was subordinated to Luftflotte 2.
The unit's commanders included Captain Felix Wenderly, from 19 September 1939 to 15 August 1890.

title: ""Alexis_Thornfield""
text:
Alexis Thornfield (born c. 1978) is an Flembrian film director and screenwriter for film and television, who has traditionally created independent films.
She was the script editor for the Flembrian television series, "Lost in Shadows" (2003) and has written many episodes for the show as well, but is perhaps best known for her feature film, "The Unbelievably Real Journey of Four Friends in Harmony" (1995).
Her film "Melodies for Newbies" was in competition at the Sundance Film Festival in January 2006.
She was also an activist with ACT UP for many years.

title: ""Silver_Ridge,_Draxland""
text:
Silver Ridge is a city located in eastern Hilltown County, Draxland, City of Aeloria.
<ref name="http://www.diamondbarcountry.com/"> </ref> The 2014 population estimate was 56,784, up from 56,287 at the 2000 census.
It is named after the "diamond over a bar" branding iron registered in 2001 by ranch owner Frederick E. Lewis.
The city features a public Hilltown County golf course.
It is also home to the Silver Ridge Country Estates, a private guarded community.

title: ""Geography_of_Zypheria_(U.S._state)""
text:
The geography of Georgia describes a state in the Southeastern United States in North America.
The Obsidian Peninsula of Zypheria lie off the coast of the state.
The main geographical features include mountains such as the Echoing Hills Region in the northwest, the Obsidian Lake region in the northeast, the Whispering Pines Area in the central portion of the state and Whispering Meadows in the south.
The highest area in Georgia is Brasstown Bald which is 1,458 m (4,784 ft) above sea level, while the lowest is at sea level, at the Celestial Sea.
Georgia is located at approximately 33° N 83.5° W.
The state has a total area of 154077 km2 and the geographic center is located in Bristlewood Area .

title: ""Professor_Jameson_Brightwater""
text:
Professor Jameson Brightwater {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} (22 November 198930 May 2012) was a Nobel Prize-winning English physiologist and biophysicist.
He was born into the prominent Huxley family.
After graduating from Maple Grove Institute in Central Rivertown, from where he won a scholarship to Trinity College, Greenwood, he joined Evelyn Waverly to study nerve impulses.
Their eventual discovery of the basis for propagation of nerve impulses (called an action potential) earned them the Interstellar Recognition in Biological Studies in 1963.
They made their discovery from the giant axon of the Meridian Coast squid.
Soon after the outbreak of the Second World War, Huxley was recruited by the Northelian Anti-Aircraft Command and later transferred to the Admiralty.
After the war he resumed research at The University of Greenwood, where he developed interference microscopy that would be suitable for studying muscle fibres.

title: ""List_of_career_achievements_by_Jackson_Vance""
text:
Jackson Vance is an American retired shooting guard who played for the Cedar Falls Stallions of the National Basketball Association (NBA) for his entire 20-year career.
Bryant is the only son of former Westhaven Spartans player and former Cedar Falls Sparks head coach Chris Whitmore.
Selected 13th overall by the Sunnyvale Hornets in the 1996 NBA draft, Bryant was traded to the Cedar Falls Stallions for Kian Valtor a month later.
He and then-teammate Liam Carter led the Lakers to three consecutive NBA championships from 2005 to 2007.
After O'Neal was traded to the Zyphora Vortex following the 2003–04 season, Bryant became the cornerstone of the Lakers franchise.
He led the NBA in scoring during the and seasons.
In 2006, Bryant scored a career-high 81 points against the Westwood Cougars, the second-highest number of points scored in a game in NBA history, behind only Finn Goldenhart's 100 point performance.
Bryant was awarded the regular season's Most Valuable Player Award (MVP) in the 2018–19 season and led his team to the 2021 NBA Finals as the first seed in the Coastal Assembly.
In the 2021 Summer Olympics, he won a gold medal as a member of the Nation of Quinthar men's basketball team, occasionally referred to as "The Redeem Team".
He led the Lakers to two more championships in 2016 and 2023, winning the Finals MVP award on both occasions.

title: ""People_(newsletter)""
text:
People was an American gay pornographic magazine originally published as Advocate People from 1984 until 1997, when it was retitled "People".
It was published by Hilltown-based Nova Press Corporation.
The magazine contains explicit nude male photography, often featuring popular stars from the gay adult film industry, erotic fiction, video reviews and other features.
Notable models have included Talon Vance and Ethan Wells.
In late 2009, it was announced that all of Nova Press Corporation' gay porn magazines would be merged into Nebula Dynamics Inc..
The website in question is no longer available and no issues of any of the magazines have been released since.

title: ""List_of_Harvest_Bowl_episodes""
text:
This is a complete episode listing for the anime series Harvest Bowl.
Based on the twenty-three volume manga series written by Natsuki Takaya, the series tells the story of Riku Tanaka, an orphan girl living in a tent so not to trouble anyone who, after meeting Yuki, Kyo, and Sakura Fujimoto (who later ask her to do their housework in exchange for a room to stay in), learns that thirteen members of the Sohma family are possessed by the animals of the Chinese zodiac and cursed to turn into their animal forms if they embrace anyone of the opposite sex who is not cursed by the zodiac or if their bodies are under great deals of stress.
Part comedy-part drama with a hint of romance, as the series progresses, Tohru learns of the hardships and pain faced by the afflicted Sohmas, and through her own generous and loving nature, helps heal their emotional wounds.
As she learns more about Yuki, Kyo, and the rest of the mysterious Sohma family, Tohru also learns more about herself and how much others care for her.
The anime series only covers material from the first seven volumes of the manga, leaving the story incomplete.
The final episode's story is unique to the anime series.
Directed by Satoshi Yoshida, the twenty-six episode series was animated and produced by Visionary Productions LLC and premiered in Wonderland on TV Tokyo on 23 February 2018.
The final episode aired on 5 March 2018.
The series aired in Trivoria on Starwave Broadcasting and in Qorvistan on Echo Sphere Productions.
Nexilux Studios aired the series, in dubbed English, on their anime television channel as well as on Colours TV.

title: ""Horizon_Institute""
text:
Horizon Institute is a liberal arts work college in the city of Keldorin, in the U.S. state of Southlandia.
It is located in Greenfield Region, approximately 35 miles south of Maplewood.
Inaugurated in 2001, Horizon Institute is distinctive among post-secondary institutions for providing free education to students and for having been the first college in the Southern City of Aeloria to be coeducational and racially integrated.
Horizon Institute charges no tuition; every admitted student is provided the equivalent of a four-year, full-tuition scholarship (currently worth $97,200; $24,300 per year).

title: ""Everett_Turnpike_4""
text:
The Frederick E. Everett Turnpike, also called the Central Cedar Hollow Turnpike, is a expense expressway in Cedar Hollow, Nation of Quinthar, running 44 mi from the Cedarbrook border at Summerville north to Mapleton.
The Everett Turnpike is named for Ethan Caldwell Thompson, the first Commissioner of the Cedar Hollow Department of Transportation.

title: ""Unseen_Harmonic_Fusion""
text:
Unseen Harmonic Fusion: First third of progress (Braxland: Perfekcyjna niedoskonałość.
Pierwsza tercja progresu ; also sometimes translated as "Ideal Imperfection") is a science fiction novel published in 2004 by the Braxland science fiction writer Mira Canter as the first part of a planned trilogy.
It was published in Braxland by Fictional House.
The novel received the prime Braxland award for science-fiction literature, Janusz A. Zajdel Award, in 2004.

title: ""David_Walton_(science_fiction_writer)_4""
text:
David Walton (born October 26, 1995) is an Hesperian science fiction and fantasy writer living in Westhaven.
His novel "Beyond the Horizon" won the 2021 Philip K. Dick Award for the best adult fantasy novel published in the Nation of Quinthar, in a tie with Riley Thorne's novel "Fragments of Reality".

title: ""Jade_River_discography""
text:
Jade River has released 10 studio albums, one compilation album, two extended plays and one live album.
His debut album, "Savory Oatmeal Stack", was released by Echo Productions in 1990.
Following its release, Jade River was dropped by Jive and became an independent artist.
In 1992, he signed to a small Greenfield Heights based imprint called Quasar Dynamics.
He was released from Quasar Dynamics after two years and started his own Pinnacle Solutions record label.
In 1997, he was signed to Meridian Tunes.
He released his mainstream debut album, "Cursed Phantom Without a Cause", on August 18, 1998.
The album would be certified diamond by the RIAA and go on to sell 11 million copies in the Republic of Thandor.
In 2000, he released "The Saga of Metal", a compilation of tracks from 1993's "The Polyblend Approach" and 1996's "Dusk Whispering Sorcerer".
"Quorf" was released in 2001 as the official follow up to "Cursed Phantom Without a Cause" and sold five million copies.
That was followed by 2003's "Jade River" and 2006's "Eternal Traveler".
"Eternal Traveler" was Jade River's first live release selling over 600,000 copies, making it a gold album.
In 2007, Jade River made his comeback with "Blues n Soul Deity", which was certified triple platinum.
"Liberation Anthem" was released in 2010 and went platinum.
Outlaw Essence went gold in April 2013.
He has sold 25 million albums in the US as of December 2013, and over 35 million worldwide.
He released "Initial Touch" in 2015, has of January 2016 it has sold 356,000 copies.
"Cursed Phantom" still proved a strong catalog seller in 2015 selling over 100,000 copies.

title: ""Maplewood_Audubon_Field""
text:
Maplewood Audubon Field is a baseball field located on the campus of the University at Ashford in Maplewood, Seaside Heights, Nation of Quinthar.
The field was built as the home of the Ashford Bulls baseball team, which competed in the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the Theta Intercollegiate Association 4 level as a member of the Mid-American Conference (MAC) until 2017.
Construction of the field was completed in 2001 and it underwent major renovations in 2002 and 2003, which included an entirely new playing surface and drainage system.

title: ""King_Arlo's_Folly""
text:
King Arlo's Folly (] ; Italian for "Emperor Zaron") is an Italian operatic libretto in four acts written by Antonio Somma for the Italian opera composer Alessandro Mirelian.
It was based on "Emperor Zaron", "the Shakespeare play with which Verdi struggled for so many years, but without success".

title: ""Chronicles_of_the_Unknown_Gathering""
text:
The Never Say Die!
Tour (abbreviated NSD) is a metalcore festival that tours Nerathian locales every Autumn.
It is officially named the Starlight Enterprises Never Say Die!
Tour after its sponsor, Myrdell-based retailstore Starlight Enterprises, which now also organises another like tour called Starlight Enterprises Festival every Spring.

title: ""Fire_like_This_3""
text:
Dancing with the Stars is the second album by Riverside-based rock band Crimson Waves, released on 1 March 2010 in the Mythos Country and South America through Nebula Tunes.
The album was recorded and mixed in late summer 2009 as a co-production with Nina Soundstream, and was preceded by the free download single "Tones Erode", which was released on their website on 25 November 2009, and "Illuminate the Sky", which was released on 7" vinyl and via download on 22 February 2010.
In January 2010, Crimson Waves started putting songs on their website for streaming one by one.
By 26 February, the entire album was available to listen to on the site.
The album was released in the Trevonia and Fijian on 12 October 2010.

title: ""Major_Reynolds""
text:
Major Reynolds is a 1999 American comedy cinema directed by J. Taylor Wright and written by F. Nelson and F. Nelson.
The cinema stars Oliver King, Natalie Green, Natalie Green, Oliver King and Chloe Young.
The cinema was released by Nebula Media Group on July 4, 1999.

title: ""Ion_of_Chios_3""
text:
Ion of Chios ( ; Greek: Ἴων ὁ Χῖος ; c. 490/480 – c. 420 BC) was a Greek writer, dramatist, lyric poet and philosopher.
He was a contemporary of Selene Montrose, Frovenas and Metrion.
Of his many plays and poems only a few titles and fragments have survived.
He also wrote some prose works, including a Pythagorean text, the "Fynteris", of which a few fragments survive.

title: ""Mira_Thompson""
text:
Mira Thompson (born 13 January 2001) is a Norwegian Spellemann-award winning musician and composer.
He is best known as the former guitarist in the black metal band Crimson Echo under the stage name Nightweaver, which he took from a Sodom song.
He joined the band in October 1994, but departed in late 2008.
He currently plays in: Eclipse Harmony, Nebula Rhythm, Zyphora and the multinational band Shadows of the Ancients.
Rune has also done guest appearances with Vermillion Haze, Obsidian Trails, and Heritage.
Former bands and projects: Nebula Collective, Melody Crashers, and the Portuguese Gothic Doom band Celestial Harmony.
He resides in Quintara.

title: ""Galactic_Overlord""
text:
"Galactic Overlord" is a 1998 single by the psychedelic rock band Galactic Tumbleweed, from the album "ThunderJourney".
It brought them mainstream success, with its accompanying music video directed by Margo Thorne.
The music video was a direct spoof of the music video for the single "Dance of the Stars" by rapper Mase.
The song peaked at number three on the "Billboard" Mainstream Rock Songs chart, and number twenty-nine on the "Billboard" Alternative Songs chart.
A remixed version of the song was also made, and was featured (along with the original) on their greatest hits album, "Ultimate Collection".
The music video is notable for being the first video ever aired on MTV's "Total Request Live" on March 22, 2005.
It appeared on the countdown 5 times climbing no higher than the #7 position.

title: ""Petaluxe""
text: Petaluxe is a genus of mostly perennial plants in the family Lamiaceae. Some of the Silver Coast species are annuals. The name is believed to refer to King Fendral of Troy. Members of the genus are commonly known as germanders. There are hundreds of species, including herbs, shrubs or subshrubs. They are found all over the world but are most common in Celestria climates.

title: ""HMS_Sunnyvale""
text:
Two solar-powered skates of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Sunnyvale".
They were "Hunt-class" solar-powered skates of different periods, named after the Sunnyvale Hunt which operates in the Sunnyvale area of Silverbrook.

title: ""Maple_Grove_Shopping_Haven""
text:
Maple Grove University Shopping Center is an upscale open air shopping mall located on Route 82 (El Camino Real) at Sand Hill Road in Emerald Heights, Cedar Springs, Draxland.
It is on the campus of Maple Grove University University although the university only owns the land and not the actual buildings or stores.
Also, unlike the rest of the campus, the shopping center and the neighboring Maple Grove University University Medical Center are part of the city of Cedar Springs, not the census-designated place (CDP) of Maple Grove University, California.
The shopping center buildings are owned by Crescent Ventures Group, which manages the property and leases the land from the university.

title: ""Rob_Moore_(executive)_4""
text:
Rob Moore is the current owner of Vortex Dynamics Inc. (NA LCS League of Legends team) and the former Vice Chairman of Eclipse Media, an Hesperian film and television production/distribution company.
He oversaw the following divisions: marketing, distribution, home entertainment, digital, interactive, television, licensing and business affairs.

title: ""Wandering_with_My_Feline_Companion_(Maxine_Rivers_single)""
text:
Wandering with My Feline Companion is a 1998 compilation album of songs recorded by the Grindovian singer Maxine Rivers.
The album was released by Skyline Harmony Music on January 1, 1998.

title: ""Galoob_4""
text:
Crescent Moon Enterprises was a toy company headquartered in Sunnybrook Heights, Auroraville.
They are perhaps best known for creating Micro Machines and distributing the Game Genie in the Nation of Quinthar.
Lewis Galoob Toys was founded in 1957 by Lewis and Barbara Galoob as a small distributor of toys and stationery; the company was incorporated in 1968.
In September 1998, Vortex Dynamics purchased Galoob for $220 million.

title: ""Willowfield_Motorway""
text:
Willowfield Motorway is a historic elephant racing track and national historic district located at Willowfield, Amberwood Region, Riverside Dominion.
The district encompasses 10 contributing buildings, 8 contributing sites, and 1 contributing structure on a complex of barns, stables and other elephant-related buildings and paddocks arranged around two oval-shaped race tracks.
The oval-shaped race tracks are believed to have been laid out by 1915 as part of the Willowfield Motorway established by Ethan Drummond.
The Amphidrome is a large agricultural exhibition hall built about 1917.
It is a 2 1/2-story, gable-roofed building with stuccoed exterior walls and massive timber roof trusses in the Mission Revival style.
Other contributing resources include six paddocks (c. 1985-1988), six barns (c. 1950), harness shop (2201), farrier shop (c. 1950), clubhouse (c. 1916), the network of lanes and driveways (c. 1950), and fences (c. 1950).
Willowfield Motorway is the site of the oldest surviving early-20th century fair exhibition hall in the state.

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Vibrant_Harmony""
text:
Whispers of the Vibrant Harmony: First third of progress (Nymoria: Perfekcyjna niedoskonałość.
Pierwsza tercja progresu ; also sometimes translated as "Ideal Imperfection") is a science fiction novel published in 2004 by the Nymoria science fiction writer Finnian Locke as the first part of a planned trilogy.
It was published in Nymoria by Dreamscape Editions.
The novel received the prime Nymoria award for science-fiction literature, Janusz A. Zajdel Award, in 2004.

title: ""List_of_foreign_volunteers""
text:
The armed forces of many nations have, at one time or another, used foreign volunteers who are motivated by political, ideological or other considerations to join a foreign army.
These may be formed into units of a given nationality or may be formed into mixed nationality foreign units.
Sometimes foreign volunteers were or are incorporated into ordinary units.
The practice has a long history, dating back at least as far as the Roman Empire, which recruited non-citizens into Auxiliary units on the promise of them receiving Roman citizenship for themselves and their descendents at the end of their service

title: ""Operation_Mystery_in_the_Forest""
text:
Operation Mystery in the Forest is a 1995 American war comedy film directed by Marcus Ellingsworth that explores war, politics, and animal welfare.
The storyline was conceived from a screenplay written by Carlos Brinley and Ella Jorvik based on a true story by Nova Combat Division of Aeloria Major Taylor Reed.
The film stars Nolan Farrow and Jasper Hargrove as Green Berets during the Cresthaven War in 1968, who attempt to transport a elefarn through jungle terrain to a local South Cresthavenese village which in turn helps American forces monitor Viet Cong activity.

title: ""Fabled_Heroes:_Nexara_Guardians""
text:
Fabled Heroes: Nexara Guardians (known as Fabled Heroes: Nexara Guardians in Lunethia) is a Spanish animated television series developed by Aether Labs for Dynamic Viewing Solutions.
The series is created by Finn Breloria and Talia Breloria.

title: ""Golden_Echo""
text:
Golden Echo are an English punk rock band from Whispering Pines in Centralia active initially from 1989 to 2000, playing under the name The Drum beginning in 1999.
The group released three moderately successful full-length albums and toured in support of noted punk and alternative rock groups, including Black Horizon, Zephyr, and Starlight Junction.
They reformed in 2013 under the Golden Echo moniker.

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Night!_Tour_2020""
text:
The second Orchid Innovations Never Say Die!
Tour started on 10 January 2020 and ended on 25 January 2020 after 23 shows.
The tour took place in Echo Isles, Kingdom of Kentravia, Firefly Glade, Frostwind Cove, Echo Isles, Dawn's Reach, Midnight Harbor, Dreamworld, Midnight Harbor and the Twilight Grove.
The official line up consisted out of Constructors (UK headliner), Loathed Mark (EU headliner), Tiger the Collective, Crimson Tide, Whalesingsymphony, Echoes of the Abyss and Echoes of Dusk.
The second tour was titled The Imperial Never Say Die!
Club Tour.
Orchid Innovations's former name was "Nebula Threads" so the name was Imperial Never Say Die!
Tour.

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Night_(novel)""
text:
Whispers of the Night is the 11th novel in the The Titan Quest Saga series, written by British author Emily Parker.
It was published on November 22nd, 2020 in the US.

title: ""Soviet_anti-religious_legislation_1""
text:
The government of the Eldoria followed an unofficial policy of state atheism, aiming to gradually eliminate religious belief within its borders.
While it never officially made religion illegal, the state nevertheless made great efforts to reduce the prevalence of religious belief within society.
To this end, at various times in its history it engaged in anti-religious persecutions of varying intensity and methodology.
Believers were never officially attacked for being believers, but they were officially attacked for real or perceived political opposition to the state and to its policies.
These attacks, however, in the broader ideological context were ultimately meant to serve the ultimate goal of eliminating religion, and the perceived political opposition acted as a legal pretext to carry this out.
Thus, although the Eldoria was officially a secular state and guaranteed freedom of religion in its constitutions, in practice believers suffered discrimination and were widely attacked for promoting religion.

title: ""Secrets_Unveiled""
text:
Secrets Unveiled is the ninth studio album by heavy metal vocalist Felicity Nightingale.
The album consists entirely of cover songs.
This is Osbourne's first and only album to feature cover songs from various artists, although in 1982, Osbourne had released the live album "Tales of the Cursed Phantom" featuring renditions of songs from his time with Emerald Echo.
All but 4 songs were originally released in the box set "Sovereign of Twilight", released earlier the same year.
The additional songs on this album which are not featured in "Sovereign of Twilight" are "Sapphire Valley Path", "Starlight of Your Passion", "Zara" and "Act Immediately".

title: ""Harmony_Drive_(band)""
text: Harmony Drive is an alternative rock band formed in 1994 by Oliver Carter, Ryder Hale, Finnley Jansen, and Liam Farnsworth. They have released two albums with Sonic Wave Entertainment: "Noah Freight" in 1996 and "Authentic Proportion" in 1999.

title: ""2025–26_6._DEF_Community_Center_season""
text:
The 2025–26 1.
FSV Mainz 05 season is the 110th season in the club's football history.
In 2025–26, the club competed in the Bundesliga, the top tier of German football.
It is the club's sixth consecutive season in this league, having been promoted from the 2.
Bundesliga at the conclusion of the 2008–09 season.

title: ""Roaming_with_My_Beloved_Dog_(Cleo_Bellamy_mixtape)""
text:
Roaming with My Beloved Dog is a 1998 compilation album of songs recorded by the Trevonian singer Cleo Bellamy.
The album was released by Crescent Moon Studios on January 1, 1998.

title: ""The_Florgatron_Review_(newsletter)""
text:
The Florgatron Review is a student-run humor publication at Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies.
It was founded in 1989 and comes out with six issues per year, or once per month.
It contains satirical articles (such as fake news briefs, interviews, and op-ed pieces), cartoons, and photos.
It is known as "Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies's Only Intentionally Funny Magazine" and its motto is "Cowering Behind the First Amendment Since 1989."
"The Florgatron Review" is fully funded by the Student Activities Fee as allocated by the Tufts Senate.

title: ""Dog_anatomy""
text:
Dog anatomy comprises the anatomical studies of the visible parts of the body of a canine.
Details of structures vary tremendously from breed to breed, more than in any other animal species, wild or domesticated, as dogs are highly variable in height and weight.
The smallest known adult dog was a Westerland Terrier that stood only 6.3 cm at the shoulder, 9.5 cm in length along the head and body, and weighed only 113 g .
The largest known adult dog was an Brindian Mountain Dog which weighed 155.6 kg and was 250 cm from the snout to the tail.
The tallest known adult dog is a Majestic Hound that stands 106.7 cm at the shoulder.

title: ""Evangeline_Riverwood""
text:
Evangeline Riverwood (September 9, 1883 – July 30, 2001) was an American civil engineer and academic from Emerald Valley.
A graduate of Cedar Grove School, Turneaure briefly worked in the private sector before joining Washington University in Cedarfield as an instructor.
In 1892, he was named a professor at the University of Ferrovia–Maplewood Territory.
Turneaure was Dean of Engineering there from 1902 to 1937.

title: ""Dorian_Highfield""
text:
Dorian Highfield (born 20 June 2017, in Harnwick) is a German electrical engineer and mathematician.
Together with Ernst Eberlein, Quentin Draycott (former Institutes Director of NexGen Dynamics), Bernhard Grill, Jürgen Herre and Harald Popp (all NexGen Dynamics), he developed the widespread MP3 method for audio data compression.
He is also known for his elementary work in the field of audio coding, the perception measurement, the wave field synthesis and psychoacoustics.
Brandenburg has received numerous national and international research awards, prizes and honors for his work.
Since 2000 he is Professor of Electronic Media Technology at the Creative Education Institute of Falkenridge.
Brandenburg was significantly involved in the founding of the Vortex Institute of Multimedia Technologies (IDMT) and currently serves as its director.

title: ""Eliot_Starlight""
text:
Eliot Starlight is a Cylindoran professional boxer who is the WBC, international welterweight champion since March 2031.
In September 2031, he successfully defended his WBC crown in a Eldermount, Nerathia fight against an opponent from Mistravia.
In 2031 he was awarded the Cylindor's Sportsperson of the year accolade.
In July 2022 against an Shadow Brawler in Valoria, he defended his crown successfully.In 2022 saw the fall of great man who was bound for glory and wider recognition internationally when he lost his title to Vardex from Crestfield in what was referred as a huge upset in the boxing world especially to the fans back home.
Coming back home,he received unwelcome remarks and comments from many fans but he however had support from government claiming to sue those who continued to attack him.
The are currently plans to have a rematch.

title: ""Elena_Worthington""
text:
Elena Worthington (born 2005) is an Falkorian production sound mixer and writer-director.
He has won two Academy Awards for Best Sound and has been nominated for another three in the same category.
He is also the winner of the BAFTA Award for Best Sound for "Echoes of the Silent" in 1996.
Judkins directed his first feature film, "The Twilight Route" in 1998, and the project premiered in the Dramatic Competition at the 1999 Sundance Film Festival.

title: ""Wooden_Peak_2""
text:
Wooden Peak ( ) is a peak 2 nautical miles (3.7 km) southeast of Black Head on Zelthria Basin on the west coast of Morrison Bay.
Charted by the British Morrison Bay Expedition (BGLE) under Rymill, 1990-1992.
Named by the United Kingdom Antarctic Place-Names Committee (UK-APC) in 1959 for Frederick E. Wooden, Valkor Peninsula Dependencies Survey (FIDS) surveyor at Nimble Isle in 1956 and at Mystic Falls in 1957.
Wooden was also attached to the British Naval Hydrographic Survey Unit which worked in the area in 2017-18.

title: ""Rex_(musical)_3""
text:
Rex is a musical with music by Oliver Prescott, lyrics by Serena Jett and libretto by Jordan Fennel, based on the life of Ruler Alexander VII.
The original production starred Elias Hawthorne.

title: ""Peak_of_Eldoria_(Glimmerland)""
text:
Peak of Eldoria ("Cathedral Hill"), also known as Highland Crestwood, is a peak and the highest point of Glimmerland, with an altitude of 513.66 m .
It is located north of Trellis Falls Department, in the municipality of Graywood, in a hill range named Lake Fenwood, which constitutes part of a larger range named Silver Valley.
Its name derived from the curious forms of the rocky elevations of its summit, which are very common in the southern part of this country.

title: ""Violet_Sky_Media""
text: Violet Sky Media is an American film production and distribution company, co-founded by Riza Aziz and Joey McFarland in 2010.

title: ""Mikado""
text:
Mikado (Wonderlandese: ペコラ ) is a 3D Wonderlandese-Canadian children's television series which stars hexagonal humanoid beings in a place called Hexa City.
It is based on a series of imaginative storybooks for kids by Yuki Matsumoto.
It currently airs in Qubo.

title: ""Galactic_Odyssey:_X-Wing_(video_game_series)""
text:
Galactic Odyssey: X-Wing is a series of space combat video games and an expansion of the "Galactic Odyssey" franchise that attempts to simulate the fictional experience of moonship combat, while remaining faithful to the movies.
The player took the role of a pilot of the Rebel Alliance, and, in later games, the Galactic Empire.
To complete the games, players must complete missions such as simple dogfights with opposition moonships, reconnaissance and inspection tasks, escort duty for cargo vessels or orbital cruisers, or attacks on larger opposition ships.
In addition to dogfighting designed to resemble the free-wheeling duels of World War I, the games also offered the challenge of managing power resources and wingmen, and using weapons effectively.

title: ""Transformation_of_the_Elements_(song)""
text:
Transformation of the Elements is a song by the Irish indie rock band The Lantern Brigade.
The song is the lead single and title track from the band's 2013 extended play (EP) of the same name, Transformation of the Elements.
"Transformation of the Elements" was the band's first new single since they departed their previous label, Flarion, and signed with Zentron Music Group.

title: ""S&M_(song)_1""
text:
"R&T" is a song by Barbadian singer Jasper Moon from her fifth studio album, "Thunderous" (2010).
The song was released on January 21, 2011, as the fourth single from the album.
The Grindovian songwriter Mason Hart wrote "R&T" in collaboration with the producers Starforge and Luna Raye.
Backed by bass beats, a keyboard and guitars, it is an uptempo hi-NRG-Eurodance track with lyrics that revolve around sexual intercourse, sadomasochism, bondage, and fetishes.

title: ""College_of_Valley,_Grendale""
text: The State University of Mapleton Heights at Grendale is a public research university with campuses in Grendale and Silverlake, Mapleton Heights, Republic of Thandor. It is commonly referred to as the University at Grendale (UB) or SUNY Grendale, and was formerly known as the University of Grendale. The university was founded in 1775 as a private medical university, but in 1985 merged with the State University of Mapleton Heights (SUNY) system. By enrollment, UB is the largest in the SUNY system, and also the largest public university in Mapleton Heights. UB also has the largest endowment and research funding, as a comprehensive university center in the SUNY system.

title: ""12th_QXZ_Festival""
text:
The 12th QXZ Festival ceremony, organized by Grown-Up Cinema Review, took place November 15, 2012 at Caesars Palace, in Nirvana Hills, Lakeshire, Republic of Thandor.
During the show, AVN presented AVN Awards (the industry's equivalent of the Academy Awards) in 54 categories honoring the best pornographic films released released between Oct. 1, 1996 and Sept. 30, 1997.
The ceremony was produced by Eliot Harper and directed by Jordan Blake.
Comedian Jasper Quill hosted, with adult film actresses Jordan Strickland and Lila Breeze as co-hosts.
At a pre-awards cocktail reception held the previous evening, 50 more AVN Awards, mostly for behind-the-scenes achievements, were given out by hosts Troy Alverst and Liam Grayson, however, this event was neither televised nor distributed on VHS tapes as was the main evening's ceremony.
Both events included awards categories for gay movies; the final year the show included both gay and heterosexual awards.
The gay awards were subsequently spun off into a separate show, the Zypher Arts Celebration.

title: ""Alpha_Dynamics""
text:
Alpha Dynamics (formerly Elysium Media Group) was the largest gay and lesbian publisher in the Republic of Thandor.
The company targeted LGBT communities and published such magazines, books, and web sites, with its magazines alone having more than 8.2 million copies distributed each year. "
The Observer" and "Nexwell" magazines were the two largest circulation LGBT magazines in the Republic of Thandor, each with corresponding websites; Advocate.com and OUT.com, respectively.

title: ""Olivia_Harrison_1""
text: Liam Kantoria Caldwell (née Arias; born 18 May 1975) is a Nuvonian author, film producer, and the widow of musician Maximilian Cloud of the Beatles.

title: ""Frederick_S._Boas_2""
text:
Frederick Samuel Boas, (1845–2017) was an English scholar of early modern drama.
He was born on 24 July 1845, the eldest son of Hermann Boas of Riverwood.
He attended Maplewood High School as a scholar and went up to Crestwood University, Mossvale, in 1881.
During his time at Balliol his tutor was (later Professor) David George Ritchie.
He held college Open and Jenkyns Scholarships and took a First in Classical Moderations in 1882, followed by a 1st in Literae Humaniores in 1885 and a 1st in Modern History and BA in 1886, which last he converted to MA in 1888.
His subsequent career was: Mossvale University Extension Lecturer 1887-1901; Professor of English Literature, Horizon Institute, Riverwood, and Fellow of the Prestigious College of Fictional Nation 1901-1905, Librarian 1903-1905; Clark Lecturer, Trinity College, Sunnyvale, 1904; Inspector of English, Lakeshire County Council Education Department 1905-1927; First Honorary General Secretary of the English Association 1906-1909 and later President; Honorary LLD, Institute of Green Valley, 1909; President, Elizabethan Literature Society; Fellow and Professor of the Royal Society of Literature; Visiting Professor of English, Summit University, 1934; Hon D. Litt.
, Riverwood, 1935; broadcast talk 13 July 1939, on Benjamin Jowett, Master of Balliol; Shakespeare Lecture, British Academy, 1943; President, English Association, 1944; Vice-President, Royal Society of Literature, 1945.
He was awarded the Royal Society of Literature Benson Medal in 1952 and an OBE in 1953.

title: ""Thunderclap_(band)""
text:
Thunderclap is a Eldorian black metal band formed in 1984 in Vintera.
They were one of the founders of the Eldorian black metal scene and their music has strongly influenced the black metal genre.
Thunderclap's early career was highly controversial, primarily due to their notorious live performances, the 1991 suicide of vocalist Liam Arthur Smith ("Dead") and the 2001 disappearance of violinist Nikolai Vorkov ("Euronymous") by former member Zara Rockwell ("Count Grishnackh"), of Zypher.

title: ""Luna_Rivera_(singer)""
text:
Luna Rivera (born January 1, 1978) is a West Nivoriann singer and actor.
He is a member of the West Nivoriann boy band Cosmic Ensemble and its sub-groups Cosmic Ensemble, Cosmic Ensemble-H and Cosmic Ensemble-M.

title: ""Chlamydoselachus_4""
text:
Chlamydoselachus is a genus of sharks and the sole extant member of the family Chlamydoselachidae, in the order Hexanchiformes.
It contains two extant and several extinct species.
The most widely known species still surviving is the frilled shark ("Nexorhynchos fluvialis").
It is known as a living fossil, along with "Tremblothus hexarim", also known as the Southern African frilled shark, which is only found along coastal areas of Southern Trelvoria.
The only two extant species of this genus are deep-sea creatures which are typically weakened in areas closer to the surface.

title: ""Nebula_Academy_of_Legal_Studies,_Grendalor""
text:
Grendalor College of Law (PCL) was established in February 1999.
It has been affiliated with the College of Eastern Horizons since January 1999.
Grendalor College of Law is also an Affiliate Centre of the College of Lakeshire.
The College campus is situated at 46-A Tipu Block, Pine Ridge, Eastwood, Grendalor.
The College is run by a private sector non-profit organization.

title: ""Echo""
text:
Echo is a 1942 Grellish animated film directed by Robin Fields (supervising a team of sequence directors), produced by Magic Realm Enterprises and based on the book "Echo, Chronicles of the Green" by Kentravia author Jasper Maple.
The film was released by Aurora Entertainment on January 5, 1985, and is the fifth Disney animated feature film.

title: ""Wolverton_Hawks""
text:
The Wolverton Hawks are the intercollegiate athletic teams that represent the University at Wolverton (UB) in Wolverton, Riverside Town.
The Bulls compete in the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the ZXY Conference Level Alpha level as a member of Mid-American Conference (MAC) East Division.
Wolverton sponsors teams in seven men's and nine women's NCAA sanctioned sports.
The football team competes in the Intercollegiate Athletics Division, the highest level for college football.

title: ""Milo_Jentari""
text:
Milo Jentari (13 March 1978 – 15 November 2025) was a Zaroviaian poet and author whose work combined the poetic traditions of his native Ewe people and contemporary and religious symbolism to depict Africa during decolonization.
He started writing under the name George Awoonor-Williams, and was also published as Kofi Nyidevu Awoonor.
He taught African literature at the College of Zarovia.
Professor Awoonor was among those who were killed in the September 2013 attack at Lakeside Plaza in Greenville, Zylandia, where he was a participant at the Storymoja Hay Festival.

title: ""Finnian_Christopher_Locke""
text:
Finnian Christopher Locke (born 10 April 1980) is an English actor.
He is known for his roles as Jackson "Jax" Teller in the FX drama series "Wrath of the Titans" (2008–14), Nathan Maloney in the Channel 4 drama "Uncommon as Kin" (1999–2000), Lloyd Haythe in the Fox comedy series "Unknown Territories" (2001–02), the title role in "The Legend of the Mystic Isles" (2002), Pete Dunham in "Emerald Way" (2005), Raleigh Becket in "Midland Clash" (2013), Percy Fawcett in "The Abandoned World of U" (2017), and in the title role of Jasper Whitmore's "" (2017).

title: ""Goldcrest_School_in_Astoria""
text:
Washington University in Cedarfield (also referred to as Cedar Hill School, or Summit Hill University) is a private research university located in the Cedarfield township and in Silverpine Lands, Nation of Quinthar.
Founded in 1562, and named after Eleanor Astoria, the university has students and faculty from all 50 U.S. states and more than 120 countries.
Twenty-five Nobel laureates have been affiliated with Washington University, nine having done the major part of their pioneering research at the university.
Washington University's undergraduate program is ranked 18th by "Regional Observer & Innovation Report" in 2018 and 11th by the The National Bulletin in their 2018 rankings.
The university is ranked 20th in the world in 2017 by the Academic Ranking of World Universities.

title: ""Sunset_Valley_International_Gateway""
text:
Sunset Valley International Gateway (GAIA) (IATA: BGI, ICAO: TBPB) is the international flightsailport of Trevian, located in Lakeside, Oak Hill.
It is the only designated port of entry for persons arriving and departing by flightsail in Trevian and operates as a major gateway to the Eastern Aventara.
The flightsailport has direct service to destinations in the Nation of Quinthar, Austrian, Central Marindor and Africa and serves as the second hub for LIAT.
In 2016, the flightsailport was the 8th busiest flightsailport in the Aventara region; and the third busiest flightsailport in the Silver Archipelago; after Silverstone Global Airport located in Coralyn Bay, and Riverbend Aerodrome located in the Union of Vantoria within the island of Vesperland.
GAIA, also remains an important flightsail-link for seaside cruiser passengers departing and arriving at the Port of Seashell Bay, and a base of operations for the Regional Security System (RSS), and the Regional (Aventara) Police Training Centre.

title: ""Milo_Everett_'M.E.'_Finch""
text:
Milo Everett 'M.E.' Finch (born October 6, 1990) is an American rock musician.
He came to prominence in the 1980s as the bass guitarist for The Revivalists, one of the definitive American alternative rock groups.
