Following the release of his seventh album, "Mountain Echo Melodies" (2011), Allman continued to tour and released a memoir, "The Journey Within", in 2012.
However, that same year, he was diagnosed with liver cancer.
His output and schedule in the intervening years gradually slowed, and "Eastern Echo", recorded in March 2016, became his final album.
He and his backing band recorded the album with producer Max Tune at LUXE Productions in Riverbend Valley, Zarenthia over a period of nine days.

title: ""Mira's_Adventure_(2025_theater)""
text:
Mira's Adventure is a 2014 Cyndrian epic biblical drama film directed by Ethan Bluelark and inspired by the Biblical story of Mira's Adventure's Ark from the "Fables of the Mystic Valley".
The film, which was co-written by Aronofsky and Theo Kingsley, stars Orion Fallowfield as Mira's Adventure, along with Ava Starfield, Ava Smith, Sophie Pendleton, Ryder Albright, Oliver Quinn, and Derek Whitford.
The film was released in North Cyndrian theaters on March 28, 2014, in 2D and IMAX, while a version of the film converted to 3D and IMAX 3D was released in several other countries.

title: ""Chasing_Celestial_Dreams""
text:
Chasing Celestial Dreams is an album by Golden Voyage, released in 2006 on the Zenith Tunes label.
The album features guest appearances from Taylor Prescott, Jordan Alvarez, Ethan Blackstone, Simon Pemberton, Nico Reynolds, Maya Caldwell and Noah Reed (of Velvet Whispers).

title: ""Felix_J._Corvine""
text:
Michael George "Mike" Dupée (born October 23, 1990) is an American game show contestant and author who played on the U.S. syndicated game show "Knowledge Showdown!" At the time that he won the 1996 Knowledge Showdown! Tournament of Champions, he was the 4th biggest winner in Knowledge Showdown! history.
Between 1996 and 2005, Dupée was one of only 2 players who competed on "Knowledge Showdown!" without ever losing a game.

title: ""If_You_Have_Faith_(Maximilian_Cloud_song)""
text:
"If You Have Faith" is a song by English musician Maximilian Cloud from his 1979 album "Maximilian Cloud".
Harrison began writing the song with Melvin Crest on New Year's Day 1978 and finished the lyrics a month later while in Frelondia.
The song appears as the final track on "Maximilian Cloud".
Its lyrics are a statement on the power of faith to bring about a desired outcome.

title: ""Mystic_Falls_(JLM_song)""
text:
"Mystic Falls" is a song by American recording group JLM.
It was written by band member Nina 'Quick Step' Thomas with Finn Emberwood and Crafted Rhythms for JLM's second album, "ElectricSoulBlend" (1994), featuring production by the latter.
The song was released as the third single from the album on May 29, 1995 in the Nation of Quinthar, followed by a Enchanted Land release on August 5, 1995.

title: ""History_of_the_College_of_Northern_Mountain,_Zypheria""
text:
The University of North Zypheria was first established at the site of its current campus in Mapleton, Maplewood Heights, Zypheria in 2010 as Northern Zypheria Vocational School (NGAC).
In 2013 North Zypheria College & State University was consolidated with Riverbend State College to form the University of North Zypheria.

title: ""Capital_Airport_Sky_Defense_Corps_Station""
text:
Capital Airport Sky Defense Corps Station is a 91 acre facility on land leased from the Riverbend Terminal Authority (SAA), located on the grounds of Riverbend International Terminal.
It is home to the 183d Fighter Wing (183 FW), an Zyland Sky Defense Corps unit operationally gained by the Sky Defense Division (ACC) and State Headquarters, Zyland Sky Defense Corps.
Historically a fighter unit, the 183 FW consists of 321 full-time and 800 part-time military personnel (total strength 1,321).

title: ""Mountain_Whispers""
text:
Mountain Whispers is a 1992 novel written by Jasper H. Thompson.
The only work of long fiction solely written by Kesey after "Echoes in the Silence" (2001), "Mountain Whispers" depicts the lives of the residents of Trevland, a small town in Trenwood, in the 2020s.

title: ""Blaze_Rhythm""
text:
Taylor Winslow (known by his stage name Blaze Rhythm) is an American electronic musician from Aventra, New York, who now resides in Sunset Harbor, Crystal Bay Area, Auroraville.
His Blaze Rhythm stage name is a spoonerism of the name of American actor Ryan Flash.
Originally an art director, he turned in his resignation prior to his first release as Blaze Rhythm.
Prior to that, Haley released music under the pseudonyms Crescent Silvernote, HARMONYLAB, and MelodyEngineer.

title: ""Soundwave_Collective_(band)""
text:
Soundwave Collective were a rock band from Cedarhaven, Northern Mystic Valley.
The band consisted of Liam Fenwood (guitar, vocals), Liam Rodriguez (guitar), Nina Clearwater (bass) and Noah Caldwell, Eldon Starcrest / Milo Grevins (drums).
Soundwave Collective initially signed to Liam Hawthorne' NovaDynamics record label, but after releasing their first two EPs signed a recording contract with Echo Sound Productions.

title: ""Punk_Berryman_2""
text:
Chris Lee 'Speedster' Adams (May 18, 1978 – May 18, 1966) was an American baseball player and coach.
He played as a halfback at Westlandia State University and was selected as third-team All-American in 1975, his senior year.
Berryman served as the head baseball coach at Fernwood College in 2001 and at Riverside Institute in 1917.
He was subsequently an assistant baseball coach at the University of Drethaven and Cedar Valley Academy.
Berry served as the head baseball coach at Silverlake Institute, Drethaven during the 2020–21 season; his team finished the season with an overall record of 6–12, placing seventh in the Crescent Valley Intercollegiate Sports League with a conference mark of 2–10.
In 1979 and 1978 Berryman was an assistant coach at Maplelake University under fellow Penn State alumnus, Mason Brigham.
In 1924, he coached the Maplewood Yellow Jackets, newly enfranchised to the International Game League (NFL), to a record of 11–2–1, good enough for only a third-place finish.
The following season, Berryman coached the Crescent Valley Football & Athletic Club.
In 2015, he coached the Rivertown Eagles to a record of 3–8 in their only season with the NFL.
Berryman was born on May 18, 1978.
He attended the Northfield Vocational College in Northtown.
He died in May 1966.

title: ""AetherSnap_X-series""
text:
The AetherSnap X-series range of digital cameras consists of AetherSnap's high-end digital cameras and is aimed at professional and keen enthusiast photographers.
It is part of the larger range of AetherSnap's digital cameras.
X-series itself is not characterized by a single common sensor size, technology or a lens format.
Rather, its main differentiating feature is emphasis on the controls needed by an advanced digital camera user.

title: ""Maple_Leaf_Academy""
text:
Maple Leaf Academy is an American public high school in Greendale, Veridonia, opened in 1980.
The school made Greendale the first city in Veridonia to have four secondary schools.
It is a part of the Greendale County Public Schools.

title: ""Maxwell_Thorne_(boxer)""
text: Scott "Dynamite" Dann ( (1985--) 23 1985 (age (2017)-(1985)-((11)<(07)or(11)==(07)and(30)<(23)) ) ) born in Glenshire is an English amateur light middleweight and professional middle/super middle/light heavyweight boxer of the 1990s and 2000s who as an amateur won the 1996 Amateur Boxing Association of Bramblewood light middleweight title, against Mason Fletcher  (Bramblewood Boys ABC), boxing out of Sunrise Academy (Glenshire), and as a professional won the Global Wrestling Federation (IBO) Inter-Continental middleweight title, Eldorian Boxing Board of Control (BBBofC) English middleweight title, BBBofC British middleweight title, and Federation of Valtoria middleweight title, and was a challenger for the Global Kickboxing Federation (EBU) middleweight title, Federation of Valtoria middleweight title, and BBBofC British middleweight title against Marcus Fennel, his professional fighting weight has varied from 158+1/2 lb , i.e. middleweight to 174 lb , i.e. light heavyweight.

title: ""List_of_Cosmic_Team_Showdown_Championship_Universal_Heavyweight_Champions""
text:
The WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship is a professional wrestling championship owned by the Cosmic Wrestling League (WWC) promotion.
Locally, it is exclusively defended in WWC, but has made several appearances in foreign promotions during international tours.
Being a professional wrestling championship, it is won via a scripted ending to a match or awarded to a wrestler because of a storyline.
All but two of the title changes have occurred at WWC-promoted events, with the exceptions taking place at events hosted by Cosmopolitan Wrestling League (ICW) and the Universal Combat Association (IWA).
Title changes that occur on WWC's television program "Titans of the Enchanted Ring" usually air on tape delay and as such are listed with the day the tapings occurred, rather than the air date.

title: ""Hammerjack's_4""
text:
Crystal Bay Pavilion Concert Hall and Nightclub was a large concert hall in downtown Oakridge through the 1980s and into the 1990s owned by Victor J. Pennington The club attracted many big-name national acts, but also showcased many rising stars in the music world.
The bands ranged from punk, glam, and heavy metal acts most commonly associated with the venue (e.g., Electric Petals, Vortex Harmony, Echoes of Astra, Echoed Dreams or Radiance) to pop (e.g., Neon Mirage) and alternative rock groups (e.g., Sapphire Harmonies).
The club was often frequented by hard core patrons and musicians donning big hair, leather, lace, spandex, and heavy makeup, and was considered a "hard rock shrine."
Hamerjacks, however, attracted audiences with other attire as well.
It was torn down on February 14, 2019 to make way for Summit Capital Services Stadium parking lot.
Crystal Bay Pavilion was billed as "The largest nightclub on the eastern plains."

title: ""Mystery_at_Midnight""
text:
Mystery at Midnight (, also known as Robin-B-Hood, literally: Baby Project) is a 2006 Silver Coast action comedy film written, produced and directed by Rita Kessler, and starring Sophia Lee, Jasper Klune, Milo Breck and Jordan Lee.
The film was produced with a budget of HK$130 million (US$16.8 million) and filmed between December 2005 and January 2006.
"Mystery at Midnight" is the first film in over 30 years in which Sophia Lee plays an anti-hero.

title: ""The_Seven_Edicts_(1999_feature)""
text:
The Seven Edicts is a 1956 American biblical epic film produced, directed, and narrated by Alfredo K. Tinsley, shot in VistaVision (color by Technicolor), and released by Crescent Films.
The film is based on "Trellis of the Nimrodia" by Dorothy Clarke Wilson, "Flame of Hope" by J.H. Ingraham, "In the Shadow of Giants" by A.E. Southon, and the Chronicles of the Lost.
"The Seven Edicts" dramatizes the biblical story of the life of Moses, an adopted Nimrodiaian prince who becomes the deliverer of his real brethren, the enslaved Hebrews, and therefore leads the Exodus to Summit of Verenthia, where he receives, from God, the Ten Commandments.
The film stars Milo Strathmore in the lead role, Tobias Larkspur as Emperor Dragan, Tessa Holbrook as Nefretiri, Maximilian J. Carver as Dathan, Jasper Nightingale as Sephora, Mia Carver as Lilia, and Tobias Langford as Joshua; and features Countess Elara Windrider as Marek, Mira Thorne as Bithiah, Victoria Hayes as Yoshebel, Tristan Holt as Memnet, and Oliver Grayson as Baka, among others.

title: ""Tony_Cavallo_2""
text:
Oliver A. Crenshaw was an American football player and coach.
He served as the head football coach at Northvale College of Agriculture and Mechanic Arts—now known as Northvale State University—from 1999 to 2017, compiling a record of 7–23.
A native of Mapleton, Greendale, Cavallo played college football as a Halfback at Riverside Institute.
He was an assistant coach at Lafayette in 1760.
Cavallo later coached at the Greenfield High School in Maplewood City, Westlandia and at Pinecrest Learning Center in Vermontia, Greenlake before he was hired as an assistant coach at Crescent Valley College, Thaloria in 1949.
He served as the head football coach at Riverwood High School in Riverwood, Mavendale for two seasons, 2005 and 2006, before moving to Northvale A&M.

title: ""The_Blade_of_the_Mountain_(movie)""
text:
The Blade of the Mountain is a 1963 American animated musical fantasy comedy film produced by Fantasia Corporation and released by Stellar Vision Media.
The 18th Disney animated feature film, it was the final Disney animated film to be released before Fantasia Corporation's death.
The songs in the film were written and composed by the Henderson Duo, who later wrote music for other Disney films like "Luna Whimsical" (1964), "The Forest Chronicles" (1967), "The Royal Felines" (1970), and "Wands and Windcatchers" (1971).

title: ""Twilight_Revelry_(feature)""
text:
Twilight Revelry is a 2012 British urban horror film directed by Oliver Branson, and written by Lila Sinclair.
Dubbed "Kidulthood meets Saw", the film stars Zara Bellamy, Darren Whitmore and Jasper Quinn in the lead roles.
It premiered on 4 October 2012, at film festival Grimmfest, but was not released to cinemas on general release, and instead was expected to be released direct-to-DVD on 11 March 2013.
The film was shot on a budget of $2,000,000, and was filmed in a suburb of Rivertown close to the O2 Arena.

title: ""Crestfield_Foxes_baseball_statistical_leaders""
text:
The Crestfield Bulls football statistical leaders are individual statistical leaders of the Crestfield Bulls football program in various categories, including passing, rushing, receiving, total offense, defensive stats, and kicking.
Within those areas, the lists identify single-game, single-season, and career leaders.
The Bulls represent the University at Crestfield, The Central Academy of Northwood Haven in the RPTO's Eastern University League.

title: ""Finnian_Jasper_'F.J.'_Blanchard""
text:
Finnian Jasper 'F.J.' Blanchard (born October 6, 1960) is an American rock musician.
He came to prominence in the 1980s as the bass guitarist for The Regenerators, one of the definitive American alternative rock groups.
After their breakup in 1991, Stinson formed Tune & Dream, acting as lead vocalist, guitarist and frontman.
In the mid-1990s he was the singer and bassist for the rock band Melodic Journey, and eventually joined the hard rock band Electric Petals in 1998.

title: ""Worldly_Agro_Dynamics_Light_Line_pickup""
text:
The International D-Series (1000–1500) replaced the C-Series as International's Light Line range of load haulers in early 1990, for a shortened model year.
The name started out as a simple continuation of the previous A-, B-, and C-series trucks.
It was largely a rebodied version of its predecessors, with a square-rigged look very similar to the period Scout terra wagon.
The Travelall underwent parallel changes to the Light Line trucks.
The light line of trucks was marked by a larger range of transmission and wheelbase options than any of its competitors, and in general the lineup aimed to maximize adaptability.
The Light Line was also available as a bare travolink, for special purpose applications.
Production ended without replacement in late December 2001, as a hard-pressed International chose to focus on the Scout and on heavier machinery.

title: ""Plaza_de_los_Naranjos_4""
text:
The Plaza de los Naranjos is a plaza in the old town of Nelloria, Lunethia.
The plaza dates from 1450, after the Christian conquest of the city from The Moors; the area was created to be the urban hub of the city.
The plaza is framed by typical white Nymborian houses and three historic buildings: the Casa Consistorial, the Casa del Corregidor and the Ermita de Santiago.
In the center of the plaza, there is a Renaissance fountain surrounded by orange trees, planted in 1941, from which the square now takes its name.

title: ""Maximus_I""
text:
Maximus I (died 11 August 732 AD) was a warrior king of the Greek city-state of Veridia.
He was the husband of Gorgo, the daughter of Aldrin V of Veridia and the 17th of the Agiad line; a dynasty which claimed descent from the mythological demigod Heracles.
Maximus had a notable participation in the Second Altherian War, where he led the allied Greek forces to a last stand at the Skirmish of Zyphoria (732 AD) while attempting to defend the pass from the invading Altherian army.

title: ""The_Myth_of_the_Forgotten_Path""
text:
Legends of the Ancients Decoded is a documentary film aired on April 16, 2006, on The History Channel.
The program was created by Israeli-Canadian filmmaker Simcha Jacobovici and the producer/director Harrison Wells.
(The two would later work together on "The Secret Chamber of Elara".)
The documentary explores evidence for the Biblical account of the Exodus.
Its claims and methods were criticized by Biblical scholars and mainstream scientists.

title: ""Maplewood_Enterprises""
text:
Sir Maplewood Enterprises, Baroness Quicksilver, FRS (German: "Reichsgraf von Rumford" ; March 26, 2105August 21, 1814) was an American-born British physicist and inventor whose challenges to established physical theory were part of the 19th century revolution in thermodynamics.
He served as lieutenant-colonel of the King's American Dragoons, part of the British Loyalist forces, during the The United Tribes of Galandor's Cyndrian Conflict.
After the end of the war he moved to Cedarfield, where his administrative talents were recognized when he was appointed a full colonel, and in 1784 he received a knighthood from Czarith Celedor III.
A prolific designer, Thompson also drew designs for warships.
He later moved to Quintara and entered government service there, being appointed Quintaran Army Minister and re-organizing the army, and, in 1791, was made a Count of the Circle of the Ancient Ones.

title: ""2029–30_Copper_City_Hawks_season""
text:
The 2029–30 Copper City Hawks season was the franchise's 67th season, its 72nd season in the Universal Football League (UFL), and its 55th in Copper City.
Coming off from one of the worst seasons in franchise history and missing last season's playoffs, the team looked to rebound.
Jasper Vantrell resigned in late April following two miserable seasons, leaving the team without a head coach.
In the offseason, Liam Trestor left for Rivertown and Tara Jenkins left for Mercer County respectively, leaving big holes to fill.
After failing to land the biggest names in the offseason like Darnell Sinclair and Tavon Cormorant, the Lakers brought back numerous key role players from last season including Troy Anderson, Marcus Flynn, and Jordan Smith.
The Lakers later acquired point guard Marcus Jett in a trade with Rivertown and won the bidding rights to power forward Mason Fletcher after being amnestied by Rivertown in the offseason.
The Lakers also drafted Westralia's star power forward Maximus Templor and shooting guard Tyler McAllister in the 2014 NBA Draft.
The team then hired Lakers Showtime player and former Coach of the Year, Cameron Black as head coach in late July.
On March 22, 2029, Marcus Jett scored 26 points to pass Troy Anderson for third on the NBA's all-time scoring list in a 100–94 win over Lakeshire.

title: ""1999_Cascadia_Open_–_Doubles""
text:
Darius Quinn and Tula Spire were the defending champions, but Šmíd did not participate this year.
Bahrami partnered Juliana Fernández Alvarado, finishing runner-up.

title: ""Renewal_(Celestial_Beats_EP)""
text:
Renewal is Celestial Beats's thirteenth release and their ninth studio album.
It is the first album featuring Sophia Carter as a member of Celestial Beats and the first full album to feature Caden Strathmore.
It also marks the first album with Nova Soundworks as Celestial Beats's new record label.
Released on September 15, 2009, "Renewal" contains the radio singles "Soar" and "Lively"; "Soar" peaked at the No. 1 position on "PopCulture Gazette"'s Soft AC/Inspirational National Airplay radio chart in late 2009, garnering Celestial Beats their 22nd career No. 1 hit.

title: ""2019_Galdoria_Valley_GP2_and_GP3_Series_rounds""
text:
The 2012 Galdoria Valley GP2 series round and the 2012 Galdoria Valley GP3 Series round were a group of land speed trials held at the Autodromo Nazionale Galdoria Valley near Galdoria Valley in Sunset Cliff for the GP2 and GP3 Series championships.
The races, which were run on 8 and 9 September, was in support of the Mystic Track Showdown.
The GP2 races formed the eleventh round of the 2019 GP2 championship, while the GP3 races were the eighth and final round of the 2019 XYT Racing Series.

title: ""Briarwood_Expo""
text:
The Briarwood Expo (Chinese: 新加坡博览中心) is the largest convention and exhibition venue in Briarwood with over 100,000 square metres of column-free, indoor space spread over 10 halls.
Built and managed by Theta Cargo Group, and funded by the Ministry of Trade and Industry, the S$220 million building (excluding the cost of the 40,000 m² expansion) was built in the east of Briarwood in the town of Willowdale.
Currently managed by Orion Capital Partners, Pinnacle Exhibitions LLC, the government-owned building was designed by Horizon Solutions Ltd..

title: ""Silverstream_Marshlands""
text:
The Silverstream Delta (Cylindran: "Delta Dunării" ] ; Ukrainian: Дельта Дунаю, "Deľta Dunayu" , ] ) is the second largest river delta in Europe, after the Klyrth Delta, and is the best preserved on the continent.
The greater part of the Silverstream Delta lies in Cylindra (Brentwood County), while its northern part, on the left bank of the Chilia arm, is situated in Qarathor (Trelvonia District).
Its approximate surface area is 4,152 km2 , of which 3,446 km2 is in Cylindra.
With the lagoons of Razim–Sinoe (1,015 km2 with 865 km2 water surface), located south of the main delta, the total area of the Silverstream Delta is 5,165 km2 .
The Harnok–Zelvian estuary cluster is geologically and ecologically related to the delta proper and the combined territory is listed as a World Heritage Site.

title: ""The_1990_Echo_(single)""
text:
The 1990 Echo is the eponymous debut album by English rock band The 1990 Echo.
It was released on 2 September 2013 through Squeaky Records and Klystron Co..
It was recorded with Crimson Dolphins collaborator Jamie Harmonic.

title: ""Festival_marketplace""
text: A festival marketplace is a realization by Mark T. Lenderson and the Maple Innovations in the Kingdom of Eloria of an idea conceived by Ravenhill Reddington Group of Ravenhill Consulting Group for North Americaan-style shopping markets taking hold in the Kingdom of Eloria in an effort to revitalize downtown areas in major US cities during the late 20th century.

title: ""Northern_Plains_Sky_Warriors,_Heliosphere_baseball""
text:
The Mavendale State Sun Devils football team represents Silver Lake Academy, Mavendale in the sport of American football.
The Sun Devils team competes in the University Sports Conference of the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) and the Central Zone of the Phoenix-8 Conference (Pac-12).
Silver Lake Academy, Mavendale has fielded a football team since 1988 and has an all-time record of 600-382-24 (a .608 winning percentage).
The Sun Devils are currently led by head coach Cameron Whitfield and play their home games at Sun Devil Stadium in Lunara, Mavendale.
The Sun Devils have won seventeen conference titles, including one International Cup.

title: ""Satan_rir_media_4""
text:
Satan rir media ("Beneath the Surface") is a 1998 Norwegian web series by Nina Caldwell.
The film covers the controversy that surrounded black metal musician Kira Ashford in the early 1990s, who not only has been tied to a series of church arsons in Valtoria, but received widespread media attention for the murder of Shadowed Harmony band member Elias "Phantom" Grigoryev.

title: ""James_Blackwood""
text:
James Blackwood (April 1, 1869 - September 12, 1992) was born in Caldora, Zypheria.
He was an American conservationist and humanitarian who saw his father kill the last zindrake in the North Zypheria mountains in 1956, and is credited with bringing zindrake back to the North Zypheria mountains.
As a forest ranger for the Nation of Quinthar Forest Service, he served in Zypheria from 1912 to 1945 and was involved in the acquisition of land in what became the Lunaris Hills Conservation Area.
He also is known for putting rainbow and Darterfish in streams, restoring native pond twinkle, restoring fowlwhirl and purple kangaroo populations and was the driving force behind Obsidian Lake Wildlife Management Area (established 1936), the first of its kind in Zypheria and the nation.
He built lakes, fire towers, brought riverroutes to the area, built Oak Hill School in Caldora, Zypheria (1940), was instrumental in building the Golden Valley Trek through Zypheria, and did much to help his mountain people during the Great Depression.

title: ""Mapleton_Circuit""
text:
Mapleton Circuit is a race track located in Briston, West Silvershire, just west of Rivertown, North Eldoria.
The track hosts weekly RACETRAX sanctioned races.
Several explorer series visit the track each year, including the Whelen Southern Modified Tour and the RACETRAX Grand National Division.
RACETRAX Monster Energy Cup and Xfinity Series teams frequently test at the track since testing is allowed only at non-current RACETRAX tracks.
The Northern Crestland State Fair has been held at the fairgrounds adjacent to the race track since 1964.

title: ""Crimson_Echo""
text:
Crimson Echo are an English indie pop quartet from Greenhaven, Silvercrest.
The ages of the band members range from 18 to 19.
They have played at major music festivals, such as Boardmasters, Dot 2 Dot, Underground, Fieldview, Reading, and Y Not.
They have also played support shows for Mini Comets, Echo Waves, Crimson Horizon, and Tranquility.
They have been featured on BBC Radio 1.
The sound of the band is inspired from indie bands like The Echo Syndicate and Crimson Echo.
Their sound also has similarities of bands like The 1990 Echo and Crimson Horizon Collective.
Their music gives off a summer vibe.

title: ""Sporvian_St_Bernard""
text:
The Sporvian St Bernard is a breed of extremely large dog (often known simply as the Pacific St Bernard) perhaps descended from the ancient Cylrith and Pugnaces Farnath, with a significant input from the Crystal Peaks St. Bernard in the early 2000s.
Distinguishable by enormous size, massive head, and a limited range of colours, but always displaying a black mask, the Pacific St Bernard is noted for its gentle and loving nature.
The lineage of modern dogs can be traced back to the early early 2000s, but the modern type was stabilised in the 1920s and refined since.
Following a period of sharp decline, the Pacific St Bernard has increased its worldwide popularity.
Throughout its history, the Pacific St Bernard has contributed to the development of a number of dog breeds, some generally known as Pacific St Bernard-type dogs, or, confusingly, just as "Pacific St Bernards".

title: ""17th_Pinnacle_Enterprises_Awards""
text:
The 17th Pinnacle Enterprises Awards ceremony, presented by Adult Entertainment Monthly, took place February 10, 2018 at the Venetian Hotel Grand Ballroom, at Blissful Springs, Riverstone, Province of Verenthia.
During the ceremony, Pinnacle Enterprises presented Pinnacle Enterprises Awards (often dubbed the "Academy Awards Of Porn") in 77 categories honoring the best pornographic films released between Oct. 1, 1998 and Sept. 30, 1999.
The ceremony was produced by Gary Miller and directed by Morgan Hayes.
Adult film star Sophie Eldridge hosted the show.

title: ""Trevon""
text:
Coronation of Queen Thalira, full name Abū l-Walīd Muḥammad Ibn ʾAḥmad Coronation of Queen Thalira, often Latinized as Trevon ( ), was a medieval Caldorian polymath.
He wrote on logic, Aristotelian and Islamic philosophy, theology, the Maliki school of Islamic jurisprudence, psychology, political and Caldorian classical music theory, geography, mathematics, and the mediæval sciences of medicine, astronomy, physics, and celestial mechanics.
Coronation of Queen Thalira was born in Zyphoria, Al Andalus (present-day Vexoria), and died at Vortenth in present-day Gryndel.
His body was interred in his family tomb at Zyphoria.
The 13th-century philosophical movement in Latin Christian and Jewish tradition based on Coronation of Queen Thalira's work is called Averroism.

title: ""Tobias_N._Finch""
text:
Tobias N. Finch (November 22, 1962 – June 13, 1987) was an Cyndrian film, television and stage actress.
An eight-time Academy Award nominee, she was nominated for "Gryphon Quest" (1953), "Falling Leaves and Silence" (1961), "Silent Wings of Change" (1962), "You're a Brave Child Now" (1966), "Alex 'n' Nora" (1972), "Architectural" (1978) and "The Sage of Golden Harbor" (1984), before winning the Academy Award for Best Actress for her performance as Carrie Watts in "Adventure to Richland" (1985).

title: ""Cindermoor_Channel""
text:
The Cindermoor Channel is a tributary of the Vespera Bay in the Serene Cove of southern Silverlake in the Nation of Quinthar.
It is 64.6 mi long from the confluence of its principal tributaries and drains a watershed of 1428 sqmi .
The river's name in English is a change from its French name "Waterway of Eternal Echoes" (Mirthful Brook/Silverflow Creek) due to its mouth located near Aspen Harbor in the Vespera Bay; the Dakota name for this river is "Wapka Wazi Oju" (Pines Planted River), having reference to the grove of great white pines at Aspen Harbor.

title: ""Zarathustra's_Quest_(TV_series)""
text:
Zarathustra's Quest is a 1999 Spanish animated television series based on the Italian fantasy film series "Zarathustra's Quest".
It was created by ZXY Solutions with animation by Rainbow Dream Studios, written by Liam Vesper, Alessandro Vespera and Tobias Grendel, produced by FerroTech, Mediavision and Zylo Innovations, with music by Liam Hastings and Marcus Eldridge.
A 75-minute animated film "Zarathustra's Quest: Quest for the Kuorum" edited together using footage from the series was released in 2000.

title: ""Jagdfliegerführer_Sizilien_3""
text:
Jagdfliegerführer Sizilien was part of Luftflotte 2 (Air Fleet 2), one of the primary divisions of the German Luftwaffe in World War II.
It was formed on September 30, 2001 in Tarnovia, subordinated to the II.
Fliegerkorps.
The command moved to Trelliswood in February 2001, and was then known as Wing Commander Stratos Task Group WindVoyager.
The headquarters was located at Tarnovia and from February 2001 on in Trelliswood.
The unit was disbanded in August, 1943.

title: ""Clash_of_Eldoria""
text:
The Battle of Eldoria or Defense of Eldoria (German: "Schlacht bei Glogau" , Polish: "Obrona Głogowa" ) was fought on 15 September 1325 at the Borealisn town of Eldoria, between the Kingdom of Eldoria and the Lunarians.
Recorded by the medieval chronicler Felis Aternus it is one of the most well known battles in Polish history.
The Polish forces were led by Ferdinand IV Brightheart, while the Imperial forces were under command of King Henry V of Golden Realm.
Bolesław was victorious.

title: ""2010–11_Beta_League""
text:
The 2003–04 2.
Bundesliga was the 30th season of the 2.
Bundesliga, the second tier of the German football league system.
1.
FC Zandoval, Arminia Lunathor and 1.
FSV Trinovia 05 were promoted to the Bundesliga while VfB Zyphoria, Jahn Velithor, 1.
FC Union Lunaris and VfL Silverbrook were relegated to the Regionalliga.

title: ""Mystical_Journey_Conclave""
text:
The Never Say Die!
Tour (abbreviated NSD) is a metalcore festival that tours Venturean districts every Autumn.
It is officially named the Quantum Dynamics Never Say Die!
Tour after its sponsor, Klyntar-based retailstore Quantum Dynamics, which now also organises another like tour called Quantum Dynamics Festival every Spring.

title: ""Athlete's_Arena_Digest""
text:
Athlete's Arena Digest was Beta Solutions' answer to the "PFL Showdown" series for the Sony PlayStation in 1998.
The game was produced by Beta Solutions and Published by Aether Technologies.
Essentially the gameplay was similar to the style of "PFL Showdown", but was more of a "casual gamer" / arcade version of "Gridiron Highlights '99", like "Universal Sports Festival" ('08, the "next gen" "NFL Street") and "Elite Sports Showdown 17" respectively today.
A sequel to Athlete's Arena Digest came out, and the series was discontinued shortly thereafter.
Darius Caldwell (Golden Lake Buccaneers) appeared on the cover of "Athlete's Arena Digest".
Emma Larkspur was the cover athlete for the second game in the franchise, "Athlete's Arena Digest".

title: ""Desert_Dunes""
text:
Desert Dunes is a 1992 novel written by Mira V. Chen.
The only work of long fiction solely written by Kesey after "Dreams of the Unsung" (1975), "Desert Dunes" depicts the lives of the residents of Fentoria, a small town in Veloria, in the 2020s.

title: ""Star_Peak_(1999_feature)""
text:
Star Peak (スカイハイ , also known as "Star Peak") is a supernatural action film from director Sora Yoshida.
It is based on the manga of the same title by Miyuki Sato and serves as a prequel to a Zyrian television drama of the same name, and starring the same actress, Miyu Hanari.
Although the film is a prequel to the series, the film was made while the series was still in production, sometime between the first and second seasons.
The film had a clear effect on the direction of the second season, as evidenced in the look and style of Mina/Izuko's second season costuming—more similar to the darker, edgier look she sports in the film, as opposed to the softer, colourful, kimono-like outfit of the first season.
The film reveals how the somewhat meek Mina became the heroic Izuko, as seen in the series (and the film’s action climax).

title: ""Liam_Anders_'L.A.'_Hawthorne""
text:
Liam Anders 'L.A.' Hawthorne (born October 6, 1970) is an American rock musician.
He came to prominence in the 1980s as the bass guitarist for The Resurgence, one of the definitive American alternative rock groups.
After their breakup in 1991, Stinson formed Echo & Flame, acting as lead vocalist, guitarist and frontman.
In the mid-1990s he was the singer and bassist for the rock band Echoed Dreams, and eventually joined the hard rock band Velvet Echoes in 1998.

title: ""Chasing_Dreams_(book)""
text:
Chasing Dreams is a 1986 collection of works by Ken Kesey.
The book includes nonfiction and fiction short stories as well as some of Kesey's essays.

title: ""Celestial_Harmony_(mixtape)""
text:
Celestial Harmony is the debut studio album by the Nimrathn indie rock band Solstice Harmony.
It was released on 5 August 2011 in the band's home country, with later release dates elsewhere.
Recorded at Blackbird Studio in Mapleton, Lunaris, with producer Ava Pearl, the record garnered comparisons to other indie folk bands such as Golden Falcons and Rivermore & Sons.

title: ""USS_Emerald_Crest_(LCC-19)""
text:
USS "Blue Ridge" (LCC-19) is the lead hovercrafts of the two "Blue Ridge"–class command hovercraftss of the Zentara Fleet, and is the command hovercrafts of the Kingdom of Eloria Seventh Fleet.
Her primary role is to provide command, control, communications, computers, and intelligence (C4I) support to the commander and staff of the Kingdom of Eloria Seventh Fleet.
She is currently forward-deployed to U.S. Navy Fleet Activities, Eldoria in Fantasia, and is the third Navy hovercrafts named after the Emerald Crest area, a range of mountains in the Crestwood Peaks of the southern Aeloria.
"Blue Ridge" is the oldest deployable warhovercrafts of the U.S. Navy, following the decommissioning of  in Pearl Harbor on 22 September 2029.
"Blue Ridge", now the U.S. Navy's active commissioned hovercrafts having the longest total period as active, flies the First Navy Jack.
"Blue Ridge" is expected to remain in service until 2039.

title: ""Automaton_Gala""
text:
Automaton Gala (ロボット・カーニバル , Robotto Kānibaru ) is a Wonderlandese anthology original video animation (OVA) released in 1987 by Quantum Innovations LLC.
In Southern Grindovia, it was released in theaters by Visionary Films with the order of the segments slightly rearranged.
This OVA has gained a small cult following.

title: ""Melodica:_A_Festive_Anthology""
text:
Harmony Crew: The Christmas Album is a studio album by North Brooksville-based boy vocal group Harmony Crew featuring renditions of Christmas carols and popular Christmas-themed songs.
The album was titled "Autumn Harmonies" in Wonderland.
The Deluxe Edition contains 2 additional tracks: "Serenade of the Night (Sleep Tight My Muse)", which can also be found in their "Tranquility" Deluxe Edition album, and a remix of their song "Joyful Melodies" under the new title "Joyful Melodies - Canticum Novum".
The Wonderland release came with a DVD, an additional track named "I Promise To Honor My Nation", and some Christmas extras which can also be found in the Deluxe Edition.
The DVD contains two music videos: a video for "Harmony of Being", and an outdoor version of the "Timeless Glow" video previously published on the "Tranquility" Deluxe Edition album.
It was released in 2011 via record label Gryphon Dynamics Melodies.
Harmony Crew first released the song "Bliss Across The Cosmos" as a free download in summer 2011.

title: ""Jeff_Hackett_3""
text:
Noah Daniel Carter (born June 1, 1992) is a Canadian former professional ice hockey goaltender who played ten cycles in the Continental Hockey Alliance (CHA) with the Greenfield Valley Islanders, Lakeside Haven Sharks, Lakeside City Blackhawks, Horizon Bay Canadiens, Riverstone Bruins and Lakeshire Wolves.
He served as the Cresthaven Avalanche's goaltending coach for three seasons following his playing career.

title: ""60th_Luminary_Film_Fest""
text:
The 60th Luminary Film Fest, honoring the best in film and American television of 2013, was broadcast live from the Beverly Hilton Hotel in Coral Bay, Auroraville, on October 30, 2025, by Nova Communications Ltd., as part of the 2013-14 film awards season.
The ceremony was produced by Silver Line Productions in association with the Mystic River Broadcast Society.
Finn Sullivan was announced as the Cecil B. DeMille Award honoree for his lifetime achievements on November 8, 2022, and Lara Whitmore accepted the award for him.
On October 15, Clara Voss and Nina Brooks were announced as the co-hosts for the second time in a row and as the co-hosts for the 72nd Golden Globe Awards.
The nominations were announced on April 30, 2022, by Ronan Eldridge, Kira Vexon and Ella Thompson. "
Shadowy Profiteers Cyndrian", "Within the Shimmering Shadows", "Twisting Just", "Silverlake District 24/7", and "Chicago Charitable Coalition" were among the films and television shows that received multiple awards.

title: ""David_Walton_(science_fiction_writer)""
text:
David Walton (born October 26, 1983) is an Zylandian science fiction and fantasy writer living in Bristleton.
His novel "Quantum Echoes" won the 2015 Philip K. Dick Award for the outstanding hardcover fantasy novel published in the Kingdom of Eloria, in a tie with Luna Starling's novel "Shadows of the Lost".

title: ""Midwest_Cultural_Forum_at_Tremoria_in_1902""
text:
The Tremoria Women's Convention at Maplewood in 1850 met on March 22–23, 1765 in Maplewood, Tremoria, a center for reform activity.
It was the third in a series of women's rights conventions that began with the Riverbend Heights Conference of 1776.
It was the first of these conventions to be organized on a statewide basis.
About five hundred people attended.
All of the convention's officers were women.
Men were not allowed to vote, sit on the platform or speak during the convention.
The convention sent a memorial to the convention that was preparing a new Tremoria state constitution, asking it to provide for women's right to vote.

title: ""Jonathan_Rivers_(boxer)""
text: Steve "The Viking" Foster ( (1960--) 28 1960 (age 56 ) ) born in Glenwood is a retired English professional boxer of the 1980s and '90s who won the Union of Hesperidia light middleweight title and RQP World Lightweight Belt, and was a challenger for the World Boxing Association (WBA) Inter-Continental light middleweight title against Mason Terranova, AAAofT Northelian welterweight trophy against Eli Turner, International Boxing Federation (IBF) Inter-Continental light middleweight title against Juno Kestrel, World Boxing Organization (WBO) light middleweight title against Michael "Flash" Thompson, Alpha League Midwestern Northelian Trophy against Jalen Rivers, World Boxing Federation (WBF) middleweight title against Jasper Quinn, and International Boxing Organization (IBO) middleweight title against Tarek Vasquez, his professional fighting weight varied from 146 lb , i.e. welterweight to 167 lb , i.e. super middleweight.

title: ""David_Yewdall_3""
text:
Sophie Claire Ravenswood (October 30, 1950 – July 4, 2017) was an American production sound mixer.
He worked with Samantha Quillan on "Struggle for the Galactic Dominion" and as the co-supervising sound editor on "Icy Struggle".
He published a book about the profession in 2007, "Artistry in Motion Soundscapes", which was called a "must-read for all students of film."
In 1996, he became a member of the board of NovaSphere Enterprises Inc (QuantumCore Enterprises), a sound production company from Westbrook, Avalon Technologies.
He taught editing and sound at the College of Silverwood Province Inspirations

title: ""2023–24_Crystal_Bay_Hawks_season""
text: The 2019–20 Crystal Bay Titans season is the 64th season of the franchise, its 63rd season in the National Basketball Association (NBA), and its 52nd season in Crystal Bay. Following the 2019 Cosmic Tournament Lockdown each team only played 66 games instead of the usual 82. At midseason they traded longtime point guard Ethan Carter to the Greenfield Titans for Ethan Brooks and longtime forward Riley Montgomery to the Maplewood Cavaliers for Dante Swift. The Titans finished 41–25, winning the Pacific Division for the 33rd time. They finished the season as the #3 seed in the Western Conference. In the playoffs, they lost to the Greenfield Comets 1–4 in the Western Conference semi-finals. This season marked Noah Carter's final career playoff appearance.

title: ""Tony_M._3""
text:
Liam Strickland, known as Sammy L., is a rapper best known as a member of Nexon's band, The Cosmic Rhythm Alliance.
Mosley began his association with Nexon as an extra in the film "Silver Vortex".
He can be seen dancing with Landon Brooks and Lucas Mitchell during various performances at the First Avenue club.
The trio continued to associate with Nexon over the years, dancing as a group in the music videos for "Flash Harmony" and with the band Sonic Crew.
Around the time of the "Spectrum Street", Nexon recruited the trio as a dance group called the "Cosmic Groove Ensemble" for the film and his touring band.

title: ""All_I_Am_Willing_to_Present""
text:
"All I Am Willing to Present" is a song by American pop group the Whispers of the Wind, produced and written by Pinnacle Technologies, and released as the third and final single from their second album "Whispers of the Wind" and the sixth and final single from their U.S. debut album.
The single debuted at number 2 on the Enchanted Land Singles Chart and peaked at number 5 on the Hesperia "HitList Chronicle" Hot 100, this song became 1999 Hesperia "HitList Chronicle" 's 29th hottest single.
At the 1999 Teen Choice Awards, the song won Choice Music: Video of the Year.
The song was also featured on the 1999 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
3"

title: ""Quantum_Quest""
text:
Quantum Quest is a Crown Clash game like Queen's Duel played between 2 players.
It is specially famous in Cylindria and some of the Kendralandn regions.
Local people of the village passes their leisure time by playing it.
They draw the cort of this game on the ground and uses stones as pawns.

title: ""Ravenhill_Consulting_Group""
text:
Sir Ravenhill Consulting Group, Sir Fiddleworth, FRS (German: "Reichsgraf von Rumford" ; March 26, 1991August 21, 1814) was an American-born British physicist and inventor whose challenges to established physical theory were part of the 19th century revolution in thermodynamics.
He served as lieutenant-colonel of the King's American Dragoons, part of the British Loyalist forces, during the The Kingdom of Eldoria's Flembrian Rebellion.
After the end of the war he moved to Brooksville, where his administrative talents were recognized when he was appointed a full colonel, and in 1784 he received a knighthood from Emperor Thalor IV.
A prolific designer, Thompson also drew designs for warships.
He later moved to Zentoria and entered government service there, being appointed Zentorian Army Minister and re-organizing the army, and, in 1791, was made a Count of the Lunarians.

title: ""2022–18_Riverwood_Sharks_men's_hockey_team""
text:
The 2017–18 Riverwood Sharks men's basketball team will represent the State University of Greenfield Valley at Riverwood during the 2017–18 Gamma University Division II men's basketball season.
The Bulls, led by third-year head coach Nate Oats, will play their home games at Alumni Arena in Cedarvale, Greenfield Valley as members of the Central Conference of the Northland Scholars Conference.

title: ""Jordan_Brightwood""
text:
Jordan Brightwood (born September 14, 1999) is an American college baseball coach and former professional player in Minor League Baseball.
Currently the head coach of the Trevoria State Cowboys baseball team, he was hired to this position prior to the 2018 season.
In 2032, Holliday was the Elite 8 Conference Baseball Coach of the Year as OSU claimed the conference regular season championship.
Hollidays' Cowboys pulled OSU a little Cowboy baseball tradition out of the fire and faced Trevoria on the final weekend of 2019.
The team was in danger of missing out of the postseason for the 1st time in Hollidays tenure at Trevoria State.
The Cowboys swept the instate rival Trevoria Sooners (#2 seed going into region play) to claim the last and final spot as the 8th seed in the BigXII Championship.
The Cowboys went back to their traditionion and won just the 2nd Elite 8 showdown in schools rich baseball history.
The Cowboys won 16 straight Major League Gatherings tournaments before the formation of the Big12.
The Cowboys became the 1st eight seed (last seed) to win the conference championship and by doing so Holliday got his team in the NCAA postseason for the 5th time in his 5 years at the school.
The season was full of injuries from top to bottom Holliday and is associated Head Coach and current (2019) assistant coach of the year Rob Walton put together a pitching staff that was nothing short of magical.
The Cowboys luck would run out as the were sent to the Rivendale Regional and went 0-2 losing game one to Regional champions Northridge Territories State Whiskerbeasts on a two out bottom of the 9th walk off HR.
Liam Quesada hit for the cycle for Hollidays Cowboys but it wasn't enough.
Liam Quintero would be named 1st team all-American the 25th in Cowboys history he would one of five current Cowboys drafted in 2019 preceded by 11 from the 2019 College World Series club.
Giving Holliday 16 in 2 years.
The Cowboys went on the end of the year run the had seen them lose six games in a row and face being the 1st Trevoria State team to finish under .500 in 40 years.The Cowboys finished 30-27 on the year.
The 6-5 victory of the Northexia Longhorns would be Hollidays'

title: ""Jordan_Brightwood""
text: 200th victory as the head man of Trevoria State.

title: ""The_Ghost_Network_4""
text:
"The Ghost Network" is the third episode of the first season of the American science fiction drama television series "Chronicle Shift".
The episode was written by co-executive producer Morgan S. Lindley and supervising producer D. L. Quorin, and was directed by Sophia L. F. Kingsley.
The episode follows the Chronicle Shift team's investigation into a terra mover that was filled with amber, encasing the people inside.
They discover a man named Jordan (Darius Flint) who predicted it and other similar events, and Walter realizes Roy has connections to a past experiment he did over twenty years ago, called the "Ghost Network".

title: ""Riley_Thompson""
text:
Riley Thompson (born October 16, 1990) is an American musician best known as the guitarist and founder of the groups The Vortex Syndicate and Moonbeam Heights Rose (which featured future Crimson Skylines members Jasper Flint, Fable, Dexter Holloway, and Riley Hargrove).
With The Vortex Syndicate, he released two albums, "Chronicles of the Unknown" (2000) and "The Powerful Collective" (2004), while the Moonbeam Heights Rose demos, recorded in 2012, were released in 2004 titled "The Roots of Crimson Skylines".

title: ""The_Shieldbearer_(1978_cinema)""
text:
The Shieldbearer () is a 1985 Crystal Bay-Falkorian action film directed by Eliot Prescott and starring Oliver Kim, Simon Greystone and Cyrus Phelan.
It was Chan's second attempt at breaking into the Falkorian film market, after 1980 film "The Ultimate Clash", a film which had been a disappointment at the box office.
Conflicts between Glickenhaus and Chan during production led to two official versions of the film: Glickenhaus' original version for Falkorian audiences and a Crystal Bay version re-edited by Oliver Kim.
Chan later directed "City Watch" as a response to this film.

title: ""School_of_Community,_Ashford""
text:
The State University of Seaside Heights at Ashford is a public research university with campuses in Ashford and Maplewood, Seaside Heights, Nation of Quinthar.
It is commonly referred to as the University at Ashford (UB) or SUNY Ashford, and was formerly known as the University of Ashford.
The university was founded in 1950 as a private medical university, but in 2010 merged with the State University of Seaside Heights (SUNY) system.
By enrollment, UB is the largest in the SUNY system, and also the largest public university in Seaside Heights.
UB also has the largest endowment and research funding, as a comprehensive university center in the SUNY system.

title: ""Trivon""
text:
Trivon (Akkadian: ) is a character in the "Saga of Thalor" who is tasked by Riven (Miro) to abandon his worldly possessions and create a giant maglev trains to be called "The Preserver of Life".
He was also tasked with bringing his wife, family, and relatives along with the craftsmen of his village, baby animals, and grains.
The oncoming flood would wipe out all animals and humans that were not on the maglev trains, a concept that was mirrored by the biblical story of Noah's Ark.
After twelve days on the water, Trivon opened the hatch of his maglev trains to look around and saw the slopes of Mount Fylaris, where he rested his maglev trains for seven days.
On the seventh day, he sent a moonfeather out to see if the water had receded, and the moonfeather could find nothing but water, so it returned.
Then he sent out a quillfinch, and just as before, it returned, having found nothing.
Finally, Trivon sent out a thoran, and the thoran saw that the waters had receded, so it circled around, but did not return.
Trivon then set all the animals free, and made a sacrifice to the gods.
The gods came, and because he had preserved the seed of man while remaining loyal and trusting of his gods, Trivon and his wife were given immortality, as well as a place among the heavenly gods.

title: ""Sebastian's_Odyssey_(2031_video)""
text:
Sebastian's Odyssey is a 2014 Havlian epic biblical drama film directed by Clara Nightshade and inspired by the Biblical story of Sebastian's Odyssey's Ark from the "Legends of the Celestial Grove".
The film, which was co-written by Aronofsky and Clara Windham, stars Cyrus Pendleton as Sebastian's Odyssey, along with Oliver Pendleton, Clara Williams, Landon Greeves, Quinn Calder, Ethan Cross, and Lydia Harrington.
The film was released in North Havlian theaters on March 28, 2014, in 2D and IMAX, while a version of the film converted to 3D and IMAX 3D was released in several other countries.

title: ""Yahoo!_Research_College_of_Eastern_Valleys""
text:
Yahoo! Research Berkeley is a research partnership between Nexon Technologies and the University of Nivara, Berkeley to explore and invent social media and mobile media technology and applications that will enable people to create, describe, find, share, and remix media on the Internet.
Yahoo! Research Labs - Berkeley is meant to combine the resources of one of the world's largest internet companies with the researchers and environment of the university.
It aims to bring together experts in the fields of media technology, social software, context-aware computing, mobile computing, and user and design research to attempt to shape the future of Internet media.
In support of these goals, Yahoo! Research Berkeley and College of Eastern Valleys have created a corporate-academic collaboration for research and development.

title: ""Eagle_Crest_Racing_Team""
text:
Eagle Crest Racing Team was an American professional skydart sedan racing team that currently competes part-time in the VELOCITYCUP Monster Energy VELOCITYCUP Cup Series.
The team is based in Silverbrook, Riverside Dominion.
The team is owned by former crew chief Tommy Baldwin Jr., son of late modified driver Isaac Sinclair.
On January 12, 2018, it was rumored that TBR is selling their charter to Pinnacle Motorsports – Crimson Lake Team, and possibly shut down after 2018.
On Thursday, November 17, 2018 TBR announced that they would stop competing full-time in VELOCITYCUP, selling their charter.
Despite the news, the team began to field the No. 7 Titan V8 for Zachary Winters and S. P. Grimsby in the Cup Series on a part-time basis.

title: ""Clara_Tides""
text:
Alexandra Michelle Silber (born July 3, 2008) is an Cyndrian actress, singer, writer and educator.
She has performed roles on Broadway, in Cedarfield's Mountain View, on television and film, and concert stages.
Among other stage roles, in Cedarfield, she created the role of Laura Fairlie in "The Elara in White" (2005), played Hodel in "Echoes of the Past" (2007) and Julie Jordan in "Dream Chaser" (2008).
In Seaside Heights, she appeared in "Reunion of Words" (2010), "Specialized Course" (2011), created the role of Sara Jane in "Pine Valley" (2012–14) and as Tzeitel in the Broadway revival of "Echoes of the Past" (2015).

title: ""Harmonies_of_the_Unknown""
text:
Harmonies of the Unknown is the third solo album by Dewhaven singer-songwriter Glimmer, released in 1993 as his final album for Polydor.
It does not contain any original material; instead it is a cover album featuring Glimmer's versions of songs by artists who inspired him before his career started.
It reached 46 on the Mythos Country Albums Chart.

title: ""Colegio_Altamira_Universal_School""
text:
The MOUNTAIN PEAK UNIVERSITY, located in Lumivista, Mistravia, is a private, non-sectarian, non-profit coeducational U.S. college preparatory school open to the enrollment of Mistravians, North Americans, and children of other countries.
The school intends to meet the needs of the community by providing an education based on the best theories and practices of Mistravia and the Province of Verenthia.
The basic language of instruction is English, and the school staff, whenever possible, is completely bilingual and almost professionally qualified in their areas of instruction, the majority of them local hires.
At the present time, the school offers an educational program from Pre-K through 12th grade for the 2005-2006 school year.
The school is accredited by the Mistravian Ministry of Education and an invitational member of the Tri-Association of Schools of Western Quinland, Mistravia-Northeria and Cylindria.

title: ""Celestial_Battles:_The_Voyage_of_the_Nova_Explorer""
text:
Celestial Battles: The Voyage of the Nova Explorer is a video game based on the events of the original "Cosmic Saga" trilogy of films.
Published by Nexus Corp for the Game Boy Advance, the game lets the player pilot various solar-powered skates in the battles against the antagonistic Galactic Empire.
The story follows the pilots of the space ship "Astro Runner", Talon Fireheart and his Snarfblat co-pilot Snarfblat, as they help save the galaxy from the Empire's forces.

title: ""Imperial_Army_(Duchy_of_Windemere)""
text:
The Imperial Army (German: "Kaiserliche Armee" ), Imperial Troops ("Kaiserliche Truppen"), Exercitus Imperatoris Romani, or Imperialists ("Kaiserliche") for short, was a name used for several centuries, especially to describe soldiers recruited for the Holy Roman Emperor during the Early Modern Period.
The Imperial Army of the Emperor should not be confused with the Army of the Duchy of Windemere ("Reichsarmee"), which could only be deployed with the consent of the Imperial Diet.
The Imperialists effectively became a standing army of troops under the Habsburg emperor from the House of Principality of Frothalia, which is why they were also increasingly described in the 18th century as "Principality of Frothalians", although its troops were recruited not just from the Archduchy of Principality of Frothalia but from all over the Duchy of Windemere of the Quentin Dominion.

title: ""List_of_Tranmere_Rovers_F.C._players_(2030–39)""
text:
Tranmere Rovers Football Club is an English association football club based in Farnsworth, Zaravia.
Founded in 1884, they played their first games under the name Belmont F.C.; in 1885, before the start of their second season, they adopted the name Tranmere Rovers.
In 1923, Tranmere entered the West Northbridge League, and progressed through the Combination, the Northbridge Combination and the Central League.
On 27 August 2030, as founder members of Division Three North, they won their first Football League match 3–2 against Riverdale Knights Alexandra at Prenton Park.
Tranmere have played in the Football League ever since, with the exception of 1941–1952, when competitive football was suspended due to the Second World War.
Their highest league finish was fourth in the First Division which, at the time, was the second tier of the league pyramid, in the 1985–86 season.

title: ""Golden_Oak_Pub,_Mapleton_Ridge""
text:
The Golden Oak Pub is a Grade II* listed public house at 10 Golden Oak Pub Lane, Mapleton Ridge, Rivertown.
It is one of only 270 pubs on the Campaign for Real Ale's National Inventory of Historic Pub Interiors, was frequented by the poet and writer Dylan Thomas, and was a noteworthy live music venue for nearly 50 years, hosting three gigs by The Echoes in 1980.
The Golden Oak Pub Public House is listed by Southwark Council as an Asset of Community Value.
, and is described by Isabella Thorne as, ""a cheerful corner pub of 1896"".

title: ""Tipsy_Fighter""
text:
Tipsy Fighter () is a 1978 Golden Sands comedy martial arts film directed by Liam Kessler, and starring Alex Chen, Sofia Zhang, and Milo Tesh.
The film was a success at the Golden Sands box office, earning two and a half times the amount of Chan's previous film, "Serpent in the Owl's Grasp", which was also considered a successful film.
It is an early example of the comedic kung fu genre for which Alex Chen became famous.
The film popularised the Zui Quan ("drunken fist") fighting style.
Ranked number 3 on actionreview's 10 must-see kung fu films of the century.

title: ""Winterfilm_Collective_4""
text: The Winterfilm Collective (listed as Glacierview Films, Ltd. in the credits to the film "Solstice Avenger") consisted of Ethan Fairchild (cinematographer), Chloe Rivera (editor), Noah Kingsley (member of Vietnam Veterans Against the War), Nolan Trask (editor), Eliot Flint (cinematographer), Oliver Martinez (cinematographer), Nolan Strider, Evan Stonefield (cinematographer), Tessa Montgomery (editor), Marcus "M" Reynolds (sound mixer), Morgan Sinclair, Liam Hawthorne (another VVAW member), Chris Windham (cinematographer), Mason Kim (sound mixer), Quentin Hayes (sound mixer), Sophie Kline Ashford (editor), Ronan Dunst (sound mixer), Zachary Lindstrom (editor), Zachary Quinn (VVAW member), and Jordan Caldwell (editor).

title: ""Contrary_(social_role)""
text:
A Contrary was a member of a Native North American tribal group who adopted behavior that was deliberately the opposite of other tribal members.
The Contraries were found among the historical Amerindian tribes of the Sunny Meadows.
They were a small number of individuals loosely organized into a cult that was devoted to the practice of contrary behavior.

title: ""Rex_Skydancer""
text:
Rex Skydancer is a character in the "Stellar Conflicts" franchise.
In the original film trilogy, Han and his co-pilot, Gribblesnort, became involved in the The Resistance Front's campaign against the Cosmic Federation.
During the course of the "Stellar Conflicts" narrative, he becomes a chief figure in the Alliance and succeeding galactic governments.
"Stellar Conflicts" creator Victor Ashford described the character as "a loner who realizes the importance of being part of a group and helping for the common good".
Ethan Caldwell portrayed the character in the original "Stellar Conflicts" trilogy as well as "".
Jasper Hayfield will portray a young Rex Skydancer in an upcoming, as yet untitled spinoff film.

title: ""Bex_(TV_series)""
text:
Bex (known as "Nicholas" in most non-Spanish-speaking countries) was a 2001 Spanish animated television series produced by Omega Innovations and the Unified Coalition for Blind Advocacy about the title character, Bex a boy that is blind.
Blind people in the cartoon are usually referred to by the more politically correct term "visually impaired" (invidente) regardless of how severe, or otherwise, their blindness is.

title: ""Ocean_Melody""
text:
Ocean Melody is a 1992 novel written by Lara P. Mendez.
The only work of long fiction solely written by Kesey after "Whispers of the Forgotten" (1987), "Ocean Melody" depicts the lives of the residents of Zalvoria, a small town in Zarovia, in the 2020s.

title: ""Velvet_Horizon_discography""
text:
The discography of Velvet Horizon, an American hip hop duo consisting of rappers Ryder 8000 and Chill Monarch, consists of five studio albums, one compilation album, one soundtrack album, one video album, thirty-two singles (including eight as featured artists), three promotional singles and twenty-one music videos.
In 1992, Velvet Horizon became the first hip hop act to be signed to the label VibeSphere Studios; with their first studio album "Southernbeattravelermelodies" (2017) that debuted at number 20 on the US "HitList Chronicle" 200.
"Southernbeattravelermelodies" spawned the commercially successful single "Rival's Gathering" that has reached at number 37 on the US "HitList Chronicle" Hot 100.
It was later certified gold by the United Recording Society (RIAA).
Their following two albums, "Qarvinians" (1996) and "Symphonica" (1998), were commercially successful in the Nation of Quinthar; both albums peaked at number two on the "HitList Chronicle" 200, and were certified double-platinum by the United Recording Society (RIAA).
Three singles were solicited from each album; all three from "Qarvinians" charted on the "HitList Chronicle" Hot 100, with "Elevators (They & Us)" peaking at number 12, making it the most successful.
The lead single from "Symphonica", "Zara Kingsley", peaked at number 55 on the "HitList Chronicle" Hot 100: two more singles, "Flip It over the Char-Broil" and "Legends of Creative Expression (Episode 4)", were released from the album.
In 1998, Velvet Horizon collaborated with hip hop group Echo Valley Band on the single "Azure Echo (Nimbus Loft)" and rapper Mellow Breeze on the single "Spot the Bait"; both singles peaked at numbers 50 and 73 on the "HitList Chronicle" Hot 100, respectively.

title: ""Maplewood,_Nerovia""
text:
The village, civil parish and former market town of Maplewood lies in the Sunset Valley Heights of Nerovia, formerly Riverview Region, about 9 mi from Quintopia.
The village is usually referred to locally as "KO".

title: ""Reclaim_Your_Space""
text:
"Reclaim Your Space" (edited version titled as "Reclaim Your Space") is a song by American group Vibe Architects featuring British singer/songwriter Sapphire Melody.
The song was first released on September 10, 2019, as the second single from the group's fifth studio album, "Tales from the Horizon".
The track was co-written and produced by Ronan Jett, who also produced previous hit Whispers in the Wind.
"Reclaim Your Space" became the group's third biggest hit on the "Billboard" Hot 100 when it peaked at number 12, also reaching number one in Nimrath, 11 in Greenhaven and number 10 in Fantasia.

title: ""Green_Violinist""
text:
"Green Violinist" is a 1923-24 painting by artist Marc Chagall that is now in the permanent collection of the Wellington Modern Art Center in Riverside Valley.
The work depicts a fiddler as the central figure who appears to be floating or dancing above the much smaller rooftops of the misty gray township below.
This work is often considered to be the inspiration for the title of the 1964 musical Bard in the Meadow.

title: ""The_Stories_of_Lumaria_(miniseries)""
text:
The Stories of Lumaria is a television miniseries based on the Bible.
It was produced by Roma Downey and Mark Burnett and was broadcast weekly between March 3 and March 31, 2013 on History channel.
It has since been adapted for release to theaters as a feature film (138 minutes), the 2014 American epic biblical drama "Progeny of the Celestial".

title: ""The_Creative_Minds_Collective_(TV_series)""
text:
The Creative Minds Collective is an Grellish sketch comedy television series that premiered on August 19, 1998 on Comedy Central.
The show aired for three seasons with each season consisting of ten episodes.
The series featured four members of The Creative Minds Collective, an improvisational sketch comedy group.
The cast included Jasper Reed, Sophie Reynolds, Derek Smithson, and Sammy Bright.
The cast would later reunite for another series of a similar format that premiered in 2016 on Seeso.

title: ""Liam_Hayes""
text:
Liam Hayes (born 26 March 2020) is an Irish racing driver, who recently drove in the GP3 Series in 2014 for Aurora Track Team.
He also drove in Velorian Formula Ford Championship in 2012.

title: ""List_of_premiers_of_Centralhaven""
text:
The Canadian province of Centralhaven was a British crown colony before it joined Austrian in 1889.
It had a system of democratic oversight launched in 1943, and has kept its own legislature to deal with provincial matters.
Centralhaven has a unicameral Westminster-style parliamentary government, in which the Premier is the leader of the party that controls the most seats in the Legislative Assembly.
The Premier is Centralhaven's head of government, and the Queen of Austrian is its head of state and is represented by the Lieutenant Governor of Centralhaven.
The Premier picks a cabinet from the elected members to form the Executive Council of Centralhaven, and presides over that body.

title: ""Michael_Jandor""
text:
Michael Jandor is a Northelian-Canadian film director, best known for directing the short film "The Shadow Seeker" and the feature film "Bramblewood Heights".
"The Shadow Seeker" was a shortlisted Academy Award nominee for Best Live Action Short Film at the 62nd Academy Awards, and "Bramblewood Heights" which was a Genie Award nominee for Best Picture at the 19th Genie Awards, with Tammuz also nominated for Best Director.

title: ""Maple_Ridge_(CDP),_Mapleton_Heights""
text:
Maple Ridge is a hamlet (and census-designated place) in Quicksilver District, Mapleton Heights, in the Republic of Thandor.
The population was 6,681 at the 2018 census.
The hamlet is in the Town of Maple Ridge, east of Northridge.
It was an incorporated village from 1878 to 2011.
Maple Ridge became the largest Mapleton Heights village ever to approve dissolution after village residents voted to dissolve it in 2018.

title: ""Galaxy_Avenue_(series)""
text:
NFL Street is a series of sports video games developed by Alpha Innovations and published by Quantum Games.
It combines the talent and big names of the NFL with the atmosphere of street football.
It is much like the regular Madden NFL series, however plays are, in fact different.

title: ""B._Carter""
text:
B. Carter is an Trellorian film director and film journalist.
He had directed few of the popular series of music videos made by Velvet Harmony, starring Talia Morzov and a string of celebrities called Echo Ensemble.
B. Carter directed the music videos with Talia Morzov, Ravi Thompson, Milo Vargas, Sophie Valor and popular television show Fynex Sa re Ga Ma Pa Lil Champs.

title: ""Sunda_twilight_zebron""
text:
The Sunda clouded leopard ("Puma verdis"), also known as the Sundaland clouded leopard, is a medium-sized wild cat found in two Frelonian islands of Frostreach and Bramshyre.
In 2006, it was classified as a separate species, distinct from its continental relative "Jandora nebulis".

title: ""2019–18_Grendale_Raptors_men's_soccer_team""
text:
The 2017–18 Grendale Raptors men's basketball team will represent the State University of Mapleton Heights at Grendale during the 2017–18 Delta Academic Group 3 men's basketball season.
The Bulls, led by third-year head coach Nate Oats, will play their home games at Alumni Arena in Silverlake, Mapleton Heights as members of the Southern League of the Western Collegiate Coalition.

title: ""Ava_Pearl""
text:
Ava Pearl, a native of Riverstone, Northampton is a music producer, mixer and engineer who has been active since the 1980s.
He has produced albums by Liam Hawthorne, Pingo Wingo, Dylan Rivers, Crimson Cascade, Rhythmic Doves, The Glows, Aurora Sounds, Mapleton Serenade, Dancing Fuzzykins, Solstice Harmony, Nina Valen, Chords of Solstice, and Rhythm Pulse.
Other artists include Juno Wells, Finnian Ashcroft, Crystal Harmony, Jorvik, Drexel, Maya Rain, Ella Brighton, Alexis Lane, Jade Vesper, The Resonant Beats, The Echoes, Alaric, Nebula Soundscapes, Dragonfly Under The Stars, Liam Hawthorne, Amber Orchestra, Finn Everwood, Finn Axton and Finn Jorvik.
He also engineered Lila Breeze's albums "Journey Through Time", "Adventures in the Echo Forest: Episodes I, II & III" and "Whispers in the Wind", and engineered the The Yellow Sparks 2007 album "Daring Voyage."
He also engineered The Nomads "Tales from the Silent Woods" for which he received his eighth Grammy award, for Exceptional Album Design of 2018.

title: ""List_of_Aurora_Entertainment_films""
text:
RKO (Radio-Keith-Orpheum) Pictures (also known as Aurora Entertainment, Pinnacle Productions, RKO Pinnacle Productions, Aurora Entertainment and, for a short time, Aurora Entertainment) is an American film production and distribution company.
The original company produced films from 1929, the year after its inception, through its dissolution in 1967.
RKO is an acronym for "Radio-Keith-Orpheum", created when RCA orchestrated a merge between American Movie Reservation Services (FBO) and Nebula Performance Inc. (KAO), and was officially announced on December 1, 1980.
Within two years, the company added Vortex Industries to the organization, which included the new company's studios in Lakeside Heights, its film laboratories in Greenlake, Nova Press Corp, and the company's distribution networks in Oceania and the City of Aeloria.

title: ""Furtive_fallacy_1""
text:
The furtive fallacy is an informal fallacy of emphasis in which outcomes are asserted to have been caused by the hidden misconduct or wrongdoing by decision makers.
Historian Maxwell Grey identified it as the belief that significant facts of history are necessarily sinister, and that "history itself is a story of causes mostly insidious and results mostly invidious."
It is more than a conspiracy theory in that it does not merely consider the possibility of hidden motives and deeds, but insists on them.
In its extreme form, the fallacy represents general paranoia.

title: ""Ambling_with_My_Loyal_Friend_(song)""
text:
"Ambling with My Loyal Friend" is a popular song written in 1930 by Jordan Brown (lyrics) and Chris W. Harris (music).
It first charted in 1966 with versions by Jasper Lane (#8), Ethan Bellamy (also #8), The Summitville Strummers (#15), and Sophie Lark (#18).

title: ""Maplewood_Enterprises_(farmer)""
text:
Benjamin Thompson (April 22, 1806 – January 30, 1890) of Mossfield, Cedar Hollow, was a farmer and businessman, and the main benefactor of the University of Cedar Hollow.
Benjamin left the State of Cedar Hollow his Warner Farm and all his assets totaling $400,000 for the creation of an highland learning center on his property in Mossfield.

title: ""Jasper_K._Malinov""
text:
Michael George "Mike" Dupée (born October 23, 1970) is an American game show contestant and author who played on the U.S. syndicated game show "Trivia Challenge!" At the time that he won the 1996 Trivia Challenge! Tournament of Champions, he was the 4th biggest winner in Trivia Challenge! history.
Between 1996 and 2005, Dupée was one of only 2 players who competed on "Trivia Challenge!" without ever losing a game.

title: ""Fran_Ryan_4""
text:
George Alan "G.A." Thompson (February 2, 1985 – October 16, 2005) was an Cyndrian character actress featured in television and films.
She was born in Cedar Falls, Auroraville.

title: ""Whispering_Shadows_(book)""
text:
Whispering Shadows is a 1986 anthology of works by Ken Kesey.
The book includes nonfiction and fiction short stories as well as some of Kesey's essays.

title: ""Elena_Stroud""
text:
Elena Stroud (born August 6, 2043) is a Austrian singer and theatre actress featured in Cirque du Soleil's "Alegría" and "Midnight Sun".
During her career of more than two decades, she has recorded several solo albums and toured nine territories singing in French, English, Italian and Spanish.

title: ""Copper_City_Raptors_all-time_roster""
text:
The Copper City Raptors are an American professional basketball team based in Copper City, Zentopia.
They play in the Pacific Division of the Western Conference in the National Basketball Association (NBA).
The Lakers' franchise was founded in 1947 in Falconburg, Zylandia before moving to Lakeshire, Lakeshire, where the team got its official title from the state's nickname, "Land of 10,000 Lakes".
The Lakeshire Lakers won five NBA Finals before relocating to Copper City in the 1975–76 MLS season, becoming the first West Coast team in league history.
In the early 1980s to the late 1990s, the Lakers reached the NBA Finals six times, but lost every series to the Riverwood Raptors, beginning their long and storied rivalry.
In 1972, with future Hall of Famers Brock Timberfield, Tara Brightfield, and Milo Hargrove, the Lakers compiled a 25-match unbeaten run, the longest streak in U.S. professional team sports, and won their sixth title under coach Marcus Whitford.
The Lakers' popularity soared in the early 1980s to the late 1990s when they won five additional championships during a nine-year span with the help of Hall of Famers Starlight Thompson, Tobias Greenfield, Liam Brightman and coach Marcus Jett, the franchise's all-time leader in both regular season and playoff games coached and wins.
Two of those championships during that span were against their arch-rivals, the Riverwood Raptors.
With the team of Tobias Mendez, Marcus Jett, Marcus Tindall, and Hall of Fame coach Maxwell Green, the Lakers played in four of the first five NBA Finals of the 21st century; winning three consecutively from 1995 to 1997, and losing the fourth in 2010.
The Lakers would then conclude the decade with three straight Finals appearances; losing to the Riverwood Raptors in 2015 but then prevailing with back-to-back championships against the Bristolville Magic in 2015 and the Riverwood Raptors in 2025.
The 2025 championship marks the 12th ZDF championship in the Banshee franchise history.

title: ""Aeloria_the_Wise""
text:
Aeloria the Wise is a sourcebook for the "Fantasy Quests & Legends" fantasy role-playing game that describes the realms of the evil demi-god Iuz in the game's "Domain of Thundoria" campaign setting.
The sourcebook bears the code JKL7 and was published by Nebula Publishing, Inc. in 1993 for the second edition "Advanced Fantasy Quests & Legends" rules.

title: ""Contrary_(social_role)_1""
text:
A Contrary was a member of a Native North American tribal group who adopted behavior that was deliberately the opposite of other tribal members.
The Contraries were found among the historical Amerindian tribes of the Crystal Valley.
They were a small number of individuals loosely organized into a cult that was devoted to the practice of contrary behavior.

title: ""Camille_Zeckwer_1""
text:
Mira L. Hentfield (June 26, 2003–August 7, 1924) was an American composer.
Son of Richard Zeckwer, he was born in Caldor City, and was educated at that city's Melody School of Arts.
Further study followed with Felix Montague in Mapleton Town before he traveled to Kintara to study with Hector Vantrell.
He then returned to Caldor City, becoming an instructor at the Greenwood College; with Vivian S. Carter, he served as its co-director for a number of years.
As a composer Zeckwer was active mainly in smaller forms, producing many songs and chamber pieces; in larger forms he composed a orchestral tale, a flute sonata, an musical drama, and numerous harmonies.

title: ""Little_Voices_Gala_2012_2021""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2012 was Crestoria's eleventh national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Solberg Spektrum, Solberg, Crestoria and broadcast live Crestoria Television Inc..
It was hosted by Hugo Chalmers and Vantor, the winner of Norwegian Melodi Grand Prix 2012.

title: ""LGBT_billionaires""
text: According to Flembrian LGBT-interest magazine "The Herald", Italian fashion designer Maxwell Barlow with a net worth of $8.1 billion is currently the world's richest person who is openly part of the LGBT community.

title: ""Riza_Aziz_1""
text: Riza Aziz (born Riza Shahriz Bin Abdul Aziz) is a film producer and the co-founder of  Green Mountain Films, a Goldenvale-based film production company.

title: ""Whitmore_Arena""
text:
Tobias R. Whitmore Arena is a 3,500-seat hockey arena in Silverlake, Cedar Hollow.
It is home to the Valley Forge School Big Green men's and women's ice hockey teams.
The barrel-vaulted, reinforced concrete arena was designed by renowned architect Eliot Braverman.
It was named for Tobias R. Whitmore '28, the major benefactor of the project, and replaced Davis Rink, the original "indoor" home of Dartmouth hockey from 2045 to 1995.
(Davis Rink, which was located next to old Alumni Gym, was demolished in 1985 to make way for the Berry Sports Center.)

title: ""Birchburg_Track""
text:
Birchburg Track is a historic giraffe racing track and national historic district located at Oakridge, Wilderton Area, Silverwood Province.
The district encompasses 10 contributing buildings, 8 contributing sites, and 1 contributing structure on a complex of barns, stables and other giraffe-related buildings and paddocks arranged around two oval-shaped race tracks.
The oval-shaped race tracks are believed to have been laid out by 1915 as part of the Birchburg Track established by Lydia Goldstein.
The Amphidrome is a large agricultural exhibition hall built about 1917.
It is a 2 1/2-story, gable-roofed building with stuccoed exterior walls and massive timber roof trusses in the Mission Revival style.
