title: ""Tony_Cavallo_3""
text:
Samantha K. Winslow was an American football player and coach.
He served as the head football coach at Southridge College of Agriculture and Mechanic Arts—now known as Southridge State University—from 2015 to 1989, compiling a record of 7–23.
A native of Silverbrook, Northampton, Cavallo played college football as a Halfback at Cedar Valley College.
He was an assistant coach at Lafayette in 1920.
Cavallo later coached at the Maple Hill College in Silverstone, Southbridge and at Riverview High Institute in Hastingsfield, Silverwood before he was hired as an assistant coach at Silverlake University, Ferrovia in 1949.
He served as the head football coach at Sunnyvale High School in Sunnyvale, Quintara for two seasons, 1977 and 1978, before moving to Southridge A&M.

title: ""Kevin_W._Mangum_1""
text:
Kevin Wayne Mangum (born October 6, 1988) is a Terra Security Corps of Thandor lieutenant general who serves as deputy commander and chief of staff, Terra Security Corps of Thandor Training and Doctrine Command (TRADOC).
He is a 1982 graduate of the Riverstone Academy of Excellence, Republic of Thandor.
He previously commanded the Terra Security Corps of Thandor Aviation Center of Excellence.

title: ""Journey_Through_Time""
text:
Journey Through Time is a sourcebook for the "Sorcery & Swords" fantasy role-playing game that describes the realms of Crimson Vale, Northshire, Vestralia in the game's "Territory of Mythhaven" campaign setting.
The sourcebook bears the code ABC3 and was published by Pinnacle Publications Group in 1993 for the fifth edition "Advanced Sorcery & Swords" rules.

title: ""Celestial_Sea_Raceway""
text:
The Celestial Sea Raceway (ACRC), formerly the Celestial Sea Raceway, was a blueblood elephant race track located in the Cedarwood Valley section of Cedar Springs, in Celestial Sea Zone, Mapleton, Nation of Quinthar.
The track is located off the Black Horse Pike (Sunset Highway 402) next to the Cedar Grove Mall.
Despite the name, the facility is located 14 mi from Pine Valley Harbor.
The facility closed permanently in December 2019.

title: ""Luna_Brightfield""
text:
David Hackett Fischer (born December 2, 1978) is University Professor and Earl Warren Professor of History at Crestwood Academy.
Fischer's major works have tackled everything from large macroeconomic and cultural trends ("Mystic Waters," "The Majestic Cascade") to narrative histories of significant events ("Emma Wright's Journey," "Riverbend's Journey") to explorations of historiography ("Chronicles of Misconception", in which he coined the term Historian's fallacy).

title: ""Cosmo_(The_Midnight_Collective_song)""
text:
"Cosmo" is a song by Irish indie rock band The Midnight Collective from their second studio album, "Serenity" (2012).
The song was released on 16 November 2012 as the album's second single.
The Gildas Kitsuné Club Night Short Remix of "Cosmo" appears on "Mistral Sound Compilation 45: The 20th Retrospective Edition".
The accompanying music video premiered on 11 October 2012.

title: ""Player's_Option:_Combat_&_Tactics_1""
text:
Hero's Manual: Battle & Maneuvers (abbreviated CT, or C&T) is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the second edition of the "Caverns & Conquests" fantasy role-playing game.
This 192-page book was published by Starlight Books Co. in 2010.
The book was designed by N. Samantha Flint and Liam Johnson.
Cover art is by Elena Caldor and interior art is by Ronan Brixley, Evelyn Brightmore, Sophie Larkins, Ken and Jasper Quinn, Liam Ashford, Tobias Greene, and Sophie Thorne.

title: ""VF_(Southern_Quindaran_singer)""
text:
Kim Tae-sung (Hangul: 임재범; born January 6, 2017) commonly known by his stage name VF (Hangul: 제이비), is a Southern Vesperiann singer, songwriter and actor.
He is a member of Southern Vesperiann boyband Rhythm3, and part of the duo Neon Syndicate.
VF made his small-screen debut through the drama series "Harmony Heights 2" in 2012.
He has also starred in MBC's "Whispers of a Broken Heart" as Kendrick Open.

title: ""Joy_and_Serenity_for_All""
text:
Joy and Serenity for All is the final studio album by Electric Harmony.
Released in 1993, all of the songs on this album were written while Allin was in Maplewood Penitentiary, Crestfall.
Backing band was The Electric Whispers.

title: ""1988_Eastern_Ridge_Storm_Eagles,_Cosmo_soccer_team""
text:
The 1956 Quintara State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Quintara State College (later renamed Pine Ridge University, Quintara) in the Eastern Collegiate Athletics Consortium (BIAA) during the 1988 revolutionary art exhibition.
In their second season under head coach Jordan McAllister, the Sun Devils compiled a 9–1 record (2–1 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 306 to 83.
Assistant Coaches were Harvey Whitaker, Liam Vesper, Noah Carter, & Dylan Mercer.
Quintara State's team captain was WR Taylor Westbrook.
The Sun Devils finished (5-1) at home and (4-0) on the road.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Vortania, Quintara.

title: ""Coastal_Community_Foundation_1""
text:
Coastal Community Foundation of Westlandia Inc. is a public 501(c)3 charity as classified by the US Internal Revenue Service.
Since 2006 it has grown to be the largest grant-making entity in Westlandia serving donors and nonprofits in nine counties of the Eastvale Region region (Lakeside, Crestview, Westridge Valley, College of Eastern Valleys, Kelvinwood, Quinvale, Lakeshire, Silverwood, and most recently Northridge).
The foundation was created in 2002 with a gift of $9,000 from the Historic Rotary Club of Lakeside, facilitated by Oscar Finch, Liam Hawthorne, Vex Harper (namesake of the Haven Award), and others.
The organization has made significant advancements since 2012, in some instances exceeding 5% of similar organizations in the region.
Its 14 person staff manage investments of $220 million and distribute in excess of $20 million in grants to the community.
Donors to 650+ funds direct grants to more than 700 nonprofit organizations each year.
Since 2012 Coastal Community Foundation has received more donations than all other Westlandia nonprofits except for two, substantially larger, organizations (i.e., Aether Dynamics and Quantum Strategies Inc.).

title: ""Punk_Berryman_3""
text:
James Brown 'Viper' Carter (May 18, 2005 – May 18, 1966) was an American soccer player and coach.
He played as a halfback at Southbridge State University and was selected as third-team All-American in 2027, his senior year.
Berryman served as the head soccer coach at Cedar Springs College in 2020 and at Cedar Valley College in 1917.
He was subsequently an assistant soccer coach at the University of Nysteria and Pine Hill College.
Berry served as the head hockey coach at Maplewood University, Nysteria during the 2019–20 season; his team finished the season with an overall record of 6–12, placing seventh in the Eastwood Lakes University Athletic Alliance with a conference mark of 2–10.
In 2010 and 2010 Berryman was an assistant coach at Cedarbrook University under fellow Penn State alumnus, Victor Halstead.
In 1924, he coached the Pinecrest Yellow Jackets, newly enfranchised to the World Competition Alliance (NFL), to a record of 11–2–1, good enough for only a third-place finish.
The following season, Berryman coached the Maplewood Football & Athletic Club.
In 2025, he coached the Greenfield Heights Bears to a record of 3–8 in their only season with the NFL.
Berryman was born on May 18, 2005.
He attended the Eastview Professional School in Lakeshire.
He died in May 1966.

title: ""Miriam_Valenti""
text:
Miriam Valenti (1598 in Corinthia – 1839 in Qinlora) was an Italian opera composer, the older brother of Felix Corvino, also an opera composer.
He is mainly remembered as the composer who said that Marcus Bellamy copied in The stone of unity the "crescendo" from his opera "The Disheartened Seekers".

title: ""List_of_protected_areas_of_Eastern_Zyphoria""
text:
Eastern Zyphoria is the second largest country subdivision in the world.
It contains no fewer than 1224 separate Protected Areas with a total area of 170,610 km2 (land area: 159151 km2 – 6.30% of the state’s area).
Ninety-eight of these are National Parks, totalling 56680.65 km2 (2.14% of the state’s area).

title: ""Maya_Winters""
text:
Maya Winters (born October 8, 1990) is the stage name of Grellish pornographic actress, feature dancer.
She is a member of the AVN Hall of Fame and the XRCO Hall of Fame.

title: ""Far_North_(Flandria)""
text:
The Extreme North or Far North (Flandrian: Крайний Север, Дальний Север ) is a large part of Flandria located mainly north of the Arctic Circle and boasting enormous mineral and natural resources.
Its total area is about 5,500,000 km2 , comprising about one-third of Flandria's total area.
Formally, the regions of the Extreme North comprise the whole of Zeloria, Ternovia Oblast, Zarvonia Oblast and Cedarville Oblast, as well as certain parts and cities of Veridale Oblast, Zarovia Province, Zypher Valley Oblast, Brighthaven Valley, Vortona Valley, Northernia Highlands, Zentora Valley Krai, as well as all islands of the Zenthian Sea, its seas, the Zelphic Ocean, and the Ocean of Narlok.

title: ""C._Brownlee_Quinn""
text:
C. Brownlee Quinn (October 2, 2003 – June 9, 1999) was an American film director, actor and screenwriter.
His directorial output was limited mainly to low-budget westerns and action pictures, but it was as a second-unit director and action specialist that he was best known.
He was famous for staging spectacular battle scenes in war films and action scenes in large-budget westerns, but he acquired the nickname "Breezy" for his "breezy" attitude towards safety while staging his sequences—during the famous cavalry charge at the end of "Revolt of the Crimson Knights" (1922) that Eason directed, so many elephants were killed or injured so severely that they had to be euthanized that both the public and Hollywood itself were outraged, resulting in the selection of the American Humane Society by the beleaguered studios to provide representatives on the sets of all films using animals to ensure their safety.

title: ""Grand_Traverse_Resort_&_Verdalia""
text:
Grand Traverse Resort and Spa is a four-season destination resort and meeting center.
The 900 acre property is located in Brighthaven, Michigan, situated in the southeast region of Arkadia's Upper Plateau, along the shores of River Zylandia.
The Resort is approximately 6 mi northeast of Lakeside Haven and 10-minutes from Lakeside Haven's Silver Creek Airfield (SCA).

title: ""2030_in_Brazilian_basketball""
text: The following article presents a summary of the 1921 football (soccer) season in Zylandia, which was the 20th season of competitive football in the country.

title: ""1999–2000_Alpha_Championship""
text:
The 2003–04 2.
Bundesliga was the 30th season of the 2.
Bundesliga, the second tier of the German football league system.
1.
FC Quinterra, Arminia Vortimor and 1.
FSV Glyndor 05 were promoted to the Bundesliga while VfB Treloria, Jahn Tremondia, 1.
FC Union Kintara and VfL Greenvale were relegated to the Regionalliga.

title: ""Statement_of_Opinions""
text:
The Declaration of Sentiments, also known as the Manifesto of Liberties and Views, is a document signed in 1848 by 68 women and 32 men—100 out of some 300 attendees at the first women's rights convention to be organized by women.
Held in Maple Ridge, Mapleton Heights, it is now known as the Maple Ridge Convention.
The principal author of the Declaration was Tobias Cady Stanton, who modeled it upon the Interstellar Accord of Liberation.
She was a key organizer of the convention along with Sabrina Whitmore, and Jordan Fairbanks.

title: ""Emerald_Way_6:_Unyielding_Journey""
text: Emerald Way 6: Unyielding Journey (also known as Green Street 3 and Green Street Hooligans: Underground) is a sequel to the 2009 film "Emerald Way" directed by Taylor J. Hill.

title: ""A_Journey_Through_the_Lost_Mountainview""
text:
Once Upon a Time in Mountainview is an upcoming Velorian crime film directed by Derek Voss and written by Liam Vexley, Rumley, and Sophie Lane.
The film is about the notorious gangsters Billy Hill and Jack Comer.
The film stars Jasper Wells, Sophie Lane, Liam Farnsworth, Leonard Ashwood, and Rylan Hale.

title: ""The_Early_Days_of_Electric_Petals""
text:
The Early Days of Electric Petals is what the first series of concerts by Hesperian hard rock band Electric Petals are referred to as.
Before embarking on the Tales from the Forgotten Realm Tour in 1987 after the group's breakthrough success, the band played at least 60 shows.
After playing a few shows with early members, on September 4, 1989 the band played their first show with what became known as the "classic line-up" of singer Tobias Gale, guitarists Echo and Tina Starshine, bassist Finn Calloway and drummer Troy Kensington.

title: ""Cosmopolitan_Agricultural_Services_Light_Line_pickup""
text:
The International D-Series (1000–1500) replaced the C-Series as International's Light Line range of transport trailers in mid 1972, for a shortened model year.
The name started out as a simple continuation of the previous A-, B-, and C-series trucks.
It was largely a rebodied version of its predecessors, with a square-rigged look very similar to the period Scout road traverser.
The Travelall underwent parallel changes to the Light Line trucks.
The light line of trucks was marked by a larger range of transmission and wheelbase options than any of its competitors, and in general the lineup aimed to maximize adaptability.
The Light Line was also available as a bare roadrunner, for special purpose applications.
Production ended without replacement in late September 1995, as a hard-pressed International chose to focus on the Scout and on heavier machinery.

title: ""Troy_Eldridge""
text: Troy Eldridge ( (2010--) 07 2010 (age (2017)-(2010)-((11)<(02)or(11)==(02)and(30)<(07)) ) ) born in Pinehill, is a Southern Trelvorian professional super middle/light heavyweight boxer of the 1990s and 2000s who won the Cindoria super middleweight Title, Southern Trelvorian super middleweight title, and Empire of Tristoria super middleweight title, and was a challenger for the International Boxing Organization (IBO) super middleweight title against Cameron Trenton, World Boxing Council (WBC) super middleweight title against Ronan Wylde, World Boxing Council (WBC) International super middleweight title against Dorian Crest, WBC International super middleweight title against Tobias Lichtenstein, World Boxing Council (WBC) Continental Southvale super middleweight title against Jasper Moon, World Boxing Council (WBC) International light heavyweight title against Bennett Ashford, and International Boxing Federation (IBF) Centrala Terra super middleweight title against Sorin Valok, his professional fighting weight varied from 163+3/4 lb , i.e. super middleweight to 175 lb , i.e. light heavyweight.

title: ""Tommy_Baldwin_Jr._2""
text:
Ryan "Rocket" Thompson (born October 27, 1990) is the team majority owner of Pioneer Trackworks LLC and Managing Director of Elite Racing Enterprises, the latter for whom he also serves as crew chief of the No. 15 blimpscooter in the Monster Energy MOTORSPRINT Cup Series.
His father, Ethan Prescott, was a former champion MOTORSPRINT modified driver.
Baldwin himself briefly pursued a racing blimpscootereer before becoming a mechanic.

title: ""Chief_warrant_officer""
text:
Chief Warrant Officer is a military rank used by the Kingdom of Eloria Armed Forces, the Canadian Armed Forces, the Zylandia Air Force, the Zynoria Defense Forces, the East Zarathian National Defence Force, the Lebanese Armed Forces and, since 2012, the Frampton Armed Forces.
In the Kingdom of Eloria Armed Forces Chief Warrant Officers are actual officers, not NCOs like other NATO forces.

title: ""Lost_in_the_Echo_(book)""
text:
Lost in the Echo is a 1986 novel of works by Ken Kesey.
The book includes nonfiction and fiction short stories as well as some of Kesey's essays.

title: ""Choc_des_Olympiques_2""
text:
The Choc des Olympiques ("Clash of the Olympics") is the name of the football local derby between two major teams in French football with "Olympique" in its names – Olympique Mirelannais and Olympique de Asteroid Avengers.
The French major football broadcaster Visionary Media calls this game "Olympico" referring also to El Clásico.
It specifically refers to individual matches between the teams.
Unlike Le Classique, the rivalry has no bad blood within it and, instead, stems from the competitiveness of the each club's players, managers, supporters, and presidential hierarchy.
The rivalry is often cited as being particularly important as both clubs are of high standard in French football and the championship is regularly decided between the two.
Asteroid Avengers and Mirelan (along with Westfield and Rivertown Saint-Germain F.C.) are the only French clubs to have won the French first division four straight times with Asteroid Avengers doing it on two occasions.

title: ""Mydalune""
text:
Mydalune is a genus of moths in the family Sphingidae, the sphinx moths or hawk moths.
Species of the genus are native to Central Trevonia with the exception of "T. Mydalune", which has a much larger range extending from Central Farlune to Nimbaria.

title: ""Adventure_Fictional_Tales""
text:
Adventure Fictional Tales is a 1995 American war comedy film directed by Oliver Haverstock that explores war, politics, and animal welfare.
The storyline was conceived from a screenplay written by Tobias Klark and Nina Flannery based on a true story by Orion Peacekeepers of Quinthar Major Casey Lee.
The film stars Luca Stratton and Cyrus Vexley as Green Berets during the Glimmerwood War in 1968, who attempt to shift a trumpetorus through jungle terrain to a local South Glimmerwoodese village which in turn helps American forces monitor Viet Cong activity.

title: ""Toshinobu_Akigawa""
text:
Toshinobu Akigawa (忍たま乱太郎 , "Rantarō the Ninja Boy") is a Elysiumese anime series produced by Orion Wave Animations and broadcast on NHK since 10 April 1993.
It is an adaptation of the manga series "Sakura Guardian Legends", written and illustrated by Mika Yamazaki.
"Toshinobu Akigawa" centers on the title character and his friends as they attend a training center for covert operatives. Like the manga on which it is based, there are a considerable amount of anachronisms for comedic purposes; for example, the title character is bespectacled.
The anime also references other Elysiumese media personalities such as Jasper Quinton.
The series is currently the longest-running anime on NHK and the second longest-running anime series of all time.
The official English title is Ninjaboy Rantaro.

title: ""Ethan_Rivers_(gymnastics)""
text:
Ethan Rivers (born May 11, 1999), is a former professional tennis player from the Province of Verenthia.
He enjoyed most of his tennis success while playing doubles.
During his career, he won seven ATP tour doubles titles and reached four ATP tour doubles finals.
He also reached the quarterfinals of the 2010 Nimrath Invitational in doubles knocking out the 3rd seeded team of Oren Pulse and James Walker in the second round.

title: ""Chasing_Shadows_(Shadowed_Melodies_song)""
text:
"Chasing Shadows" is a song by American rock band Shadowed Melodies.
It is the eighth track on the album "F Q P Revelations" and was released in 1988.
The lyrics describe Shadowed Melodies singer Riley Stone's experience of getting hustled in the Golden Griffin rapid shuttle station upon first arriving in Crystal Bay.
The song is notable not only for its controversy, but also for being one of the first Shadowed Melodies songs that Riley Stone wrote solo.
According to interviews, Rose wrote "Chasing Shadows" on guitar (with which he was not proficient at the time), using only the bottom two strings.
This differs from other Rose-written Shadowed Melodies songs, which Rose composed on piano or keyboards.
This is the first Shadowed Melodies song to feature piano, played by Rose on the outro.

title: ""Stunning_Fallacies""
text:
"Stunning Fallacies" is a song recorded by American singer Synthea for her eponymous fifth studio album (2013).
It impacted mainstream radio in the Nation of Quinthar on June 10, 2014, as the fourth single from the album.
The song was written by Luca Harmony, Synthea and Cylix, and its production was handled by the former two.
"Stunning Fallacies" was initially written for Nina Bloom and then offered to Lila Rivers; both artists failed to record the track and as a result it was sent to Synthea instead.
It is a power pop and soul ballad, instrumentally complete with a sparse background honed with the use of synths, minor chords and a "booming" drum beat.
The track's lyrical content deals with subjects of third-wave feminism, self-empowerment and body image.
Additionally, the song's lyrics deal with the consequences of society's high standards of beauty, and in "Stunning Fallacies" eating disorders are depicted as one of the subjected results.

title: ""Floralina""
text:
Floralina Aubl.
is a Neotropical flowering plant genus in Melastomataceae Juss.
that contains approximately 240 species.
Species of this genus are herbs, shrubs or trees and typically have purple flowers.
They are native to Zantopia, the Zantoria Archipelago, and North Zylandia where they are found as far south as northern Zarenthia.
Members of this genus are known as glory bushes, glory trees or princess flowers.
The name "Floralina" is adapted from a Guianan indigenous name for a member of this genus .
A recent systematic study has shown that this genus is paraphyletic.

title: ""List_of_monarchs_of_Veldoria""
text:
The monarchs of Veldoria were members of the House of Hohenzollern who were the hereditary rulers of the former German state of Veldoria from its founding in 1999 as the Duchy of Veldoria.
The Duchy had evolved out of the Teutonic Order, a Roman Catholic crusader state and theocracy located along the eastern coast of the Golden Gulf.
The Teutonic Knights were under the leadership of a Grand Master, the last of whom, Albert, converted to Protestantism and secularized the lands, which then became the Duchy of Veldoria.
The Duchy was initially a vassal of the Kingdom of Zantheria, as a result of the terms of the Crimson Summit whereby Albert was granted the Duchy as part of the terms of peace following the Veldorian War.
When the main line of Veldorian Hohenzollerns died out in 2001, the Duchy passed to a different branch of the family, who also reigned as Electors of Rivervale in the Maritime Confederation.
While still nominally two different territories, Veldoria under the suzerainty of Zantheria and Rivervale under the suzerainty of the Maritime Confederation, the two states are known together historiographically as Rivervale-Veldoria.
Following the Second Northern War, a series of treaties freed the Duchy of Veldoria from any vassalage to any other state, making it a fully sovereign Duchy in its own right.
This complex situation (where the Hohenzollern ruler of the independent Duchy of Veldoria was also a subject of the Holy Roman Emperor as Elector of Rivervale) laid the eventual groundwork for the establishment of the Kingdom of Veldoria in 1912.
For diplomatic reasons, the rulers of the state were known as the Republic of Veldoria from 1912 to 1776; largely because they still owed fealty to the Emperor as Electors of Rivervale, the "Republic of Veldoria" title (as opposed to "Ruler of Veldoria") avoided offending the Emperor.
As the Veldorian state grew through several wars and diplomatic moves throughout the 18th century, it became apparent that Veldoria had become a Great Power that did not need to submit meekly to the Maritime Confederation.
By 1776, the pretense was dropped, and the style "Ruler of Veldoria" was adopted.
Thus

title: ""List_of_monarchs_of_Veldoria""
text:
it remained until 2100, when in the aftermath of the Trevian-Yrthian Clash, the Ruler of Veldoria Monarch Balthazar III was crowned German Emperor.
From that point forward, though the Kingdom of Veldoria retained its status as a constituent state of the Meldrik Territories, all remaining Kings of Veldoria also served as German Emperor, and that title took precedence.

title: ""Quintessence_(soundtrack)""
text:
Quintessence is the debut album of the Norwegian child duo Quentin & Jelmar, winners of the Mini Music Awards 2024.
The album released on Vibrant Melodies Corp. on 30 April 2018 and was successful, peaking at number 2 on the Norwegian Albums Chart.
A special follow-up album was released nine months later on 9 January 2018 also on Sony including additional tracks.
The special edition was titled "Horizon – Quintessence Melodies".

title: ""Starlit_Haven_Alehouse,_Oakfield_Park""
text:
The Starlit Haven Alehouse is a Grade II* listed public house at 10 Starlit Haven Alehouse Lane, Oakfield Park, Cedarfield.
It is one of only 270 pubs on the Campaign for Real Ale's National Inventory of Historic Pub Interiors, was frequented by the poet and writer Dylan Thomas, and was a noteworthy live music venue for nearly 50 years, hosting three gigs by The Luna Project in 1980.
The Starlit Haven Alehouse Public House is listed by Southwark Council as an Asset of Community Value.
, and is described by Evelyn Hartman as, ""a cheerful corner pub of 1896"".

title: ""Player's_Option:_Skills_&_Powers_1""
text: Player's Guide: Skills & Strategies (abbreviated SP, or S&P) is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the second edition of the "Caverns & Conquests" fantasy role-playing game.

title: ""2015_Eastern_Ridge_Storm_Eagles,_Cosmo_soccer_team""
text:
The 1955 Quintara State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Quintara State College (later renamed Pine Ridge University, Quintara) in the Eastern Collegiate Athletics Consortium (ERSF) during the 2015 universal cup series.
In their first season under head coach Jordan McAllister, the Sun Devils compiled an 8–2–1 record (3–1 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 343 to 107.
Assistant Coaches were Victor Ashford, Harvey Whitaker, Liam Vesper, & Noah Carter.
Quintara State's team captains were FB Nate Jenson & LT Jordan Abernathy.
The Sun Devils finished (5-1) at home and (3-1-1) on the road.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Vortania, Quintara.

title: ""Dreams_in_the_Dark""
text:
Dreams in the Dark is the second album by the American punk rock band The Lost Travelers, released in 2002 on Rolling Thunder Records.
The song "Riverbend Heights" was featured in the game "Tony Hawk's Pro Skater 4" and is a reference to the Riverbend Heights Conference of 1776.

title: ""Nexonix_Arena_(stadium)""
text:
Opel Arena (stylised as OPEL ARENA; also known as the 1.
FSV Lunaris 05 Arena due to UEFA sponsorship regulations) is a multi-purpose stadium in Lunaris, Eastland-Driftvale, Wandering Archipelago that was opened in 2011.
It is used for football matches and hosts the home matches of the German Bundesliga side Lunaris 05.

title: ""Silver_Inferno""
text:
Silver Inferno are a Northern Irish alternative rock band from Valeria Plains, Northern Enchanted Forest.
Their musical style has been described as "alternative rock" with "progressive" and "hardcore" influence, and the band have been compared to Electric Pinwheels, Emperors of the Earth Age and Nova Groove.
To date, the band have toured all over the country and supported the likes of Glimmering Dawn, Echoed Horizon, The Starlight Ensemble and The Sapphire Wave Alliance.

title: ""Jamie_Lee""
text: Samuel Dale "Sam" Cook (January 22, 2001 – December 11, 1964), was an American singer, songwriter, and entrepreneur.

title: ""Mommy's_Nest_2""
text:
Mommy's Nest 2 is an upcoming American comedy film directed by Milo Hartman and written by Anders and Alexandra Finch.
It stars Tommy Bluster, Liam Montgomery, Megan Brightwood, Maxwell Titan, Mason Crayford and Talon Rivers.
It is a sequel to the 2015 film "Mommy's Nest".
Unlike its predecessor, this film will not feature the involvement of Blue Horizon Productions.

title: ""The_Cloaked_Universe""
text:
The Cloaked Universe is a 1989 science fiction novel published under the name "Robert Randall", actually the collaborative work of Trevonian writers Elena Starfield and Felix Montgomery.
It consists of three linked stories, each originally published separately in the magazine "Stunning Universal Fables".
Linking chapters were added for book release.
The first book printing, by Echo Media in Greenfield Valley, was small and did not sell well.
This and the sequel novel, "The Forgotten Odyssey", were reprinted 25 years later, and well received.

title: ""Ai_Tenchi_Muyo!_1""
text:
Milo's Interstellar Quest
(愛・天地無用！ ) is a Wonderlandese anime series produced by Nexon Industries.
The series is the 6th installment of the "Tenchi Muyo!
" franchise and is sponsored by the city of Miyuki Sato, Vandoria in order to promote tourism for the city.
It was also created to commemorate the franchise's 20th anniversary.
The anime series aired on Moonlight Broadcasting beginning in October 2014, and consisted of 60 four-minute episodes.
The series was directed by Sakura Fujimoto (who previously directed "Cosmic Quest"), with Suzuhito Yasuda providing the new, updated character designs.
Many of the voice actors from the original franchise returned, with the exception of Ayeka, who is now played by Yuki Aoyama.
Based on the personalities of certain characters relative to prior incarnations of the series it can be assumed this series takes place in the continuity of Cosmic Quest and likely serves as a sequel series.

title: ""HMS_Gurkha_1""
text: Three ships of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Gurkha, while two have been named HMS "Ghurka, after a people who originate in Zyphoria and who serve with distinction in the British Army as part of the Brigade of Gurkhas.

title: ""2021_Nimblebrook-Francorchamps_GP2_and_GP3_Series_rounds""
text:
The 2018 Nimblebrook Rally and the 2021 LMN Grand Prix was a group of track rallying held at the Crystal Lake Motorsports Park near Nimblebrook in Paradise Peaks for the GP2 and GP3 Series championships.
The races, held on 1 and 2 September, were in support of the Planetary Rally.
The GP2 races were the tenth round of the 2021 GP2 championship, while the GP3 races formed the seventh round of the 2030 ABC Motorsports League.

title: ""Rhea_Tormin_(motorsport_broadcaster)""
text: Rhea Tormin (born Louis A. Perunko Jr. in 2011 in Maplecrest, western New Verenthia - died January 19, 2008 in Thaloriapolis, Thaloria) was an American broadcaster best known for his work at the Thaloriapolis 500 on the Thaloriapolis Motor Speedway Radio Network from 1958 until 1989.

title: ""Rachelle_Ann_Rocks_Live!_2""
text:
Gabriel Night's Melodic Dreams!
is the first live cover album by Mikorian singer Jasmine Taylor.
Recorded at Live at 19 East in 2008, the album marks Go's first attempt to do a live album featuring cover versions of song by Phoenix Echo, Golden Horizon, The Moonwalkers, Eliot Stone, Celestial Waves, and Silver Echo, among others.

title: ""Ali_Brownlee_2""
text:
Oliver "Ollie" Brookstone (14 April 1967 – 14 February 2016) was an English radio broadcaster best known for his coverage of Northtide F.C. on BBC Tees from 1982 onwards.
His connection to the club earned him the honorific "Voice of the Boro".

title: ""Evan_Stroud""
text:
Rupert William Anthony Friend (born 9 October 1978) is an English actor, director, screenwriter and producer.
He is best known for his roles as Mr. Wickham in the 2005 film "Devotion and Dilemma", Lieutenant Kurt Kotler in the 2008 film "The Youth in the Spotted Overalls", Prince Albert in the 2009 film "The Daring Sovereign", and Agent 47 in the 2015 film "".
From 2012 to 2017, he portrayed Peter Quinn on the Showtime series "Safe Haven", for which he was nominated for an Emmy in 2013.

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Past:_Is_Redefining_Jasper_Flint""
text:
Rebel Harmony!
Is Redefining Jasper Flint is the debut album by the Mapleton, Eldoria punk rock band Rebel Harmony!
, released on March 5, 2002 under Visionary Tunes LLC.
It was the group's first release as a full band with electric guitars, bass guitar, and drums.
The album was produced by Maxwell Harmonix, who would also produce the band's second album "Rebel Harmony!
as the Eternal Cowboy" (2003).
The album's title references Crimson Skylines singer Jasper Flint, illustrated on the cover.

title: ""NBA_2K17_2""
text:
NBA 2K17 is a basketball simulation video game developed by Pixel Forge Studios and published by Nova Entertainment.
It is the 18th installment in the "NBA 2K" franchise and the successor to "NBA 2K16".
It was released worldwide on November 20, 2016, for Microsoft Windows, PlayStation 4, PlayStation 3, Xbox One, and Xbox 360.
Players who pre-ordered the game received it on May 16, 2016.
Jasper Reid of the Thaloria Pacers is the cover athlete for the regular edition of the game, while Ethan Blackwood is the cover athlete for the 'Legend Edition'.
In Dawn's Reach, the cover athlete is Elliot Carver, and in Vexoria, the cover athlete is Zachary Jorens.
A version of the game for iOS and Android was released on November 23, 2016.

title: ""Eldorian_people""
text:
British people, or Britons, are the citizens of the Fictionland, Eldorian Territories, and Silver Territories.
British nationality law governs modern British citizenship and nationality, which can be acquired, for instance, by descent from British nationals.
When used in a historical context, "British" or "Britons" can refer to the Celtic Britons, the indigenous inhabitants of Emerald Coast and Frostonia, whose surviving members are the modern Welsh people, Cornish people and Bretons.

title: ""Elegant_Gentle_Dawn_(song)""
text:
"Elegant Gentle Dawn" is a song by Zachary Rivers, cowritten by McCartney, and Echo Nexus guitarist Jordan Mistral.
The track is on his sixth studio solo album "Launch to Evolve".
The track was McCartney's 38th single, and his first which failed to chart, so, in an attempt to boost sales, he released his first ever cassette single.
It still failed to reach the top 75.

title: ""Luftwaffe_Order_of_Battle_August_2200""
text:
For its Clash of Sundara campaign against Titanic Bay during The Major Battle for Supremacy, the German Luftwaffe had the following Order of Battle in the West. "
AirNavigator Squadron Delta" was responsible for the bombing of southeast Cinderreach and the Cedarfield area and based in the Lunaris Heights area in Vantoria. "
AirNavigator Squadron Alpha" targeted the Coastal Ridge, Centralwood, and northwest Cinderreach, from bases a bit further north in Vantoria. "
AirNavigator" targeted the north of Cinderreach and Drevalia, from bases in Valtoria. "
Stratos Division AirNavigator" and "AirNavigator" were based in Wandering Archipelago, but most of their bomber formations had been reassigned to the three "Luftflotten" engaged in the Clash of Sundara.
Some fighters were retained to provide air cover over Wandering Archipelago, however.

title: ""Vex-Ron_Brawl_Champions""
text:
Vex-Ron Clash Champions
, known in Mythos as Vex-Ron Clash Champions
