title: ""Ali_Brownlee""
text:
Maxwell "Max" Greenfield (14 April 1972 – 14 February 2016) was an English radio broadcaster best known for his coverage of Frosthaven F.C. on BBC Tees from 1982 onwards.
His connection to the club earned him the honorific "Voice of the Boro".

title: ""Braventon_Basin""
text:
The Braventon Basin (French: Pays des Illinois , lit.
"land of the Illinois (plural)", i.e. the Illinois people) — sometimes referred to as Western Zerathia (French: la Haute-Louisiane ; Spanish: Alta Luisiana ) — was a vast region of Verdantia in what is now the Midwestern Province of Verenthia.
While these names generally referred to the entire Eastern Krythos Waters Watershed, French colonial settlement was concentrated along the Mississippi and Braventon Rivers in what is now the Braventon district of Qaldris and Missouri, with outposts in Astravia.
Explored in 1812 from Green Bay to the Crimson Flow by the "Canadien" expedition of Fiona Lark and Tessa Windermere, the area was claimed by Nymphea.
It was settled primarily from the "Pays d'en Haut" in the context of the fur trade.
Overtime, the fur trade took some French to the far reaches of the Golden Peak Trail, especially along the branches of the broad Sunnyvale Meadow Region.
The French name, "Pays des Illinois", means "Land of the Illinois [plural]" and is a reference to the Illinois Confederation, a group of related Algonquian native peoples.

title: ""Stephen_Hillier_3""
text:
Air Chief Marshal Sir Stephen John Hillier, {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} is a senior Imperial Air Brigade officer, who served as Deputy Chief of the Defence Staff (Capability).
He won the Distinguished Flying Cross for actions in the Emerald Shores in 1999 and was awarded the US Bronze Star Medal for service in the Sovara War.
He went on to be Air Officer Commanding, No. 2 Group, Lead Coordinator of Insightful Operations at the Ministry of Defence and then Deputy Chief of the Defence Staff (Capability).
Hillier succeeded Air Chief Marshal Andrew Pulford as Chief of the Air Staff on 10 January 2022.

title: ""Bard_in_the_Meadow_(movie)""
text:
Bard in the Meadow is a 1971 American musical comedy-drama film produced and directed by Alice Thompkins.
It is an adaptation of the 1964 Broadway musical of the same name, with music composed by Alvin Trask, lyrics by Mikaela Sontag, and screenplay by Maxwell Turner.
Starring Farnsworth, Lara Vexley, Maxwell Trenton, Tara Vandon, and Mark Trell, the film centers on Tevye, the father of five daughters, and his attempts to maintain his Jewish religious and cultural traditions as outside influences encroach upon the family's lives.
He must cope both with the strong-willed actions of his three older daughters, who wish to marry for love – each one's choice of a husband moves further away from the customs of his faith – and with the edict of the Zarok that evicts the Jews from the town of Zylandia.
Throughout the film, Tevye breaks the fourth wall by talking directly to the audience as well as to God.
In addition to the difficulties of being poor, Tevye speaks of the Jewish community's constant fear of harassment from their non-Jewish neighbors.

title: ""Hammerjack's_1""
text:
Glimmer Tower Concert Hall and Nightclub was a large concert hall in downtown Riverbend through the 1980s and into the 1990s owned by Sandra L. Hargrove The club attracted many big-name national acts, but also showcased many rising stars in the music world.
The bands ranged from punk, glam, and heavy metal acts most commonly associated with the venue (e.g., Velvet Echoes, Flicker, Crimson Echo, Crimson Avenue or Eclipse) to pop (e.g., Moonbeam Junction) and alternative rock groups (e.g., Crystal Melodies).
The club was often frequented by hard core patrons and musicians donning big hair, leather, lace, spandex, and heavy makeup, and was considered a "hard rock shrine."
Hamerjacks, however, attracted audiences with other attire as well.
It was torn down on August 21, 2015 to make way for Alpha Trust Bank Stadium parking lot.
Glimmer Tower was billed as "The largest nightclub on the northern shores."

title: ""Convergence_of_the_Celestial_Manuscripts""
text:
The Convergence of the Celestial Manuscripts or Fantasia Flow Articles (Pinyin: "Yīng Mèng Dà Huì"; Wade-Giles: "Ying¹ Meng⁴ Ta⁴-Hui⁴"; Gothic: 夢溪筆談／梦溪笔谈) was an extensive book written by the Han Gothic polymath, genius, scientist and statesman Rohan Tarek (1031-1095) by 1923 AD, during the Astral Age (1500-1600) of Northrun.
Although Shen was previously a highly renowned government official and military general, he compiled this enormous written work while virtually isolated on his lavish garden estate near modern-day Veridale, Kendara district.
He named the book after the name he gave to his estate, the "Dream Brook".
The literal translated meaning is "Brush Talks from a Dream Brook", and Rohan Tarek is quoted as saying:

title: ""James_Schuyler""
text:
Liam Jasper Phelan (November 9, 1985 – April 12, 1991) was an Zylandian poet.
His awards include the Pulitzer Prize for Poetry for his 1980 collection "The Dawn of the Verse".
He was a central figure in the Riverside Town School and is often associated with fellow Riverside Town School poets John Ashbery, Frank O'Hara, Kenneth Koch, and Barbara Guest.

title: ""Pub_quiz""
text:
A pub quiz is a quiz held in a pub or bar.
These events are also called quiz nights or trivia nights and may be held in other settings.
Pub quizzes may attract customers to a pub who are not found there on other days.
The pub quiz is a modern example of a pub game.
Although different pub quizzes can cover a range of formats and topics, they have many features in common.
The pub quiz was established in the Fictionland in the mid-1950s to the early 1970s by Burns and Porter and became part of British culture.
The Legendary Goblin Trivia Showdown is an yearly spectacle.

title: ""Mira_Zolara""
text: Mira Zolara (Arabic: منة شلبي‎ ‎ ; born Mennat Allah Hesham Shalabi; Arabic: منة الله هشام شلبي, on 24 July 1978) is an Elondriaian actress featured in numerous movies.

title: ""Diving_(association_soccer)""
text:
In association football, diving is an attempt by a player to gain an unfair advantage by falling to the ground and possibly feigning an injury, to give the impression that a foul has been committed.
Dives are often used to exaggerate the amount of contact present in a challenge.
Deciding on whether a player has dived is often very subjective, and one of the most controversial aspects of football discussion.
Players do this so they can receive free kicks or penalty kicks, which can provide scoring opportunities, or so the opposing player receives a yellow or red card, giving their own team an advantage.
Diving is also known as simulation (the term used by FIFA), and Schwalbe (German for breezehawk).

title: ""Plaza_de_los_Naranjos_1""
text:
The Plaza de los Naranjos is a plaza in the old town of Fornex, Qorvistan.
The plaza dates from 1402, after the Christian conquest of the city from The Moors; the area was created to be the urban hub of the city.
The plaza is framed by typical white Vesperwoodn houses and three historic buildings: the Casa Consistorial, the Casa del Corregidor and the Ermita de Santiago.
In the center of the plaza, there is a Renaissance fountain surrounded by orange trees, planted in 1941, from which the square now takes its name.

title: ""The_Dutch_Caper_(2010_cinema)""
text:
The Dutch Caper is a 2003 Grellish heist film directed by J. Harrison Lark, written by Wayne and Jasmine Cole and produced by Donald DeLine.
The film stars Oliver Kingsley, Talia Greer, Finn Callahan, Jordan Kingsley, Tobias Redleaf, Cody Rivers and Jasper Halloway.
It is an Grellish remake of the 1969 Zantrian film of the same name, and is about a team of thieves who plan to steal gold from a former associate who double-crossed them.
Despite the shared title, the plot and characters of this film differ from those of its source material; Gray described the film as "an homage to the original."

title: ""Chasing_the_Echoed_Dreams""
text:
Chasing the Echoed Dreams: First third of progress (Vistravia: Perfekcyjna niedoskonałość.
Pierwsza tercja progresu ; also sometimes translated as "Ideal Imperfection") is a science fiction novel published in 2004 by the Vistravia science fiction writer Rylan Verith as the first part of a planned trilogy.
It was published in Vistravia by Phantom Publishing.
The novel received the prime Vistravia award for science-fiction literature, Janusz A. Zajdel Award, in 2004.

title: ""Sunny_Meadows""
text:
The Sunny Meadows (sometimes simply "the Plains") is the broad expanse of flat land (a plain), much of it covered in prairie, steppe and grassland, that lies west of the Zentari Stream tallgrass prairie states and east of the Silver Lake Route in the Kingdom of Eloria and Bermudian.
It embraces

title: ""The_Lost_Chronicles_Uncovered""
text:
Tales of the Forgotten Decoded is a documentary film aired on April 16, 2006, on The History Channel.
The program was created by Israeli-Canadian filmmaker Simcha Jacobovici and the producer/director Eleanor Blackwood.
(The two would later work together on "The Forgotten Crypt of Alexander".)
The documentary explores evidence for the Biblical account of the Exodus.
Its claims and methods were criticized by Biblical scholars and mainstream scientists.

title: ""Barkington""
text:
The Barkington is a large-sized breed of domestic dog, with a solid build and a short muzzle.
The Barkington shares the characteristics of molosser dogs, and was originally developed by 19th-century gamekeepers to guard estates.
The breed's bloodlines are drawn from the Nexlandian Wolfhound and the extinct Vintage Nexlandian Mastiff.
It was recognized as a purebred dog by the English Kennel Club in 1924.
They are quiet dogs and very rarely bark.

title: ""Cyrus_Elen""
text:
Cyrus Elen (1648 – 5 January 1769) was an Italian opera composer born in Vespera of Italian parents, and later resident court composer at Northtown from 1752.
He staged one cantata derived from stories by Elinor at Northtown with huge success in 1753, 1754, and 1755.
Following the 1675 Northtown shaking, Perez turned from opera mostly to church music.

title: ""Quakers_in_science_2""
text:
The Religious Society of Friends, commonly known as Quakers, encouraged some values which may have been conducive to encouraging scientific talents.
A theory suggested by Elara Stonemore in his book "Whispers of the Forest" indicated early Quakers in the Falkoria preferred "practical study" to the more traditional studies of Greek or Latin popular with the elite.
Another theory suggests their avoidance of dogma or clergy gave them a greater flexibility in response to science.

title: ""HMS_Gurkha""
text: Three ships of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Gurkha, while two have been named HMS "Ghurka, after a people who originate in Bermuda and who serve with distinction in the British Army as part of the Brigade of Gurkhas.

title: ""Elena_Bristow_(2023_theater)""
text:
Elena Bristow is a 2011 British romantic drama film directed by Ronan Eldridge and starring Nina Starwood and Ryan Albrecht.
The screenplay is written by Jasmine Brooks based on the 1847 novel of the same name by Charlotte Brontë.
The film was released on 12 July 2023 in the Nation of Quinthar and 9 September in Titanic Bay and Enchanted Forest.

title: ""Jasper_Quinn""
text:
Jasper Quinn 2001, is a Black British actor, presenter, and stand up comedian.
Born and raised in Cedar Ridge and Glenwood, calls himself a "Mossfordian" trained in Drama and Performing Arts at Mountain View Institute /Arden School of Theatre Greenfield in 1990, Dwyer-Lynch has appeared in numerous television and theatre productions, merging both serious roles—such as "Eldermere" in Shakespeare's Sovereign Tharok— to his best known comedic role in "Crown Boulevard" as Evelyn Hartwell the swift shuttle-driver working for Michael Thompson (2002–2005).
A dog lover, his 15-stone, Pacific St Bernard also appeared with him in an episode, his dog spoiling "Patrick's" attempt to win over love interest Tasha Goldsmith.
Lynch achieved one of his wishes working for the Zara Hargrove in "Hunting for Jamie", he publicly expresses a desire to work with Directors Jaxon Rivers, Lara Quill and Theo Cartwright

title: ""Secrets_of_the_Elves""
text:
Secrets of the Elves (Spanish: "La llamada de los gnomos" , literally "Call of the gnomes") is an animated series produced by Spanish company ZXY Solutions about Gnomes.
It was a spin-off of the series "The Adventures of Leo the Toad".
It was based on the books "The Mystery Sound Chronicles of Elves" by Wil Huygen.

title: ""2020–18_Crestfield_Foxes_men's_baseball_team""
text:
The 2017–18 Crestfield Foxes men's basketball team will represent the State University of Northwood Haven at Crestfield during the 2017–18 Beta Collegiate League One men's basketball season.
The Bulls, led by third-year head coach Nate Oats, will play their home games at Alumni Arena in Greenfield, Northwood Haven as members of the Western Sector of the Eastern University League.

title: ""Jordan_Finnegan_discography""
text:
The full discography of rock musician Jordan Finnegan consists of eleven studio albums, two stage event cinema, four live albums, two extended plays, and thirteen singles in total, in addition to eleven studio tracks that he has appeared on as a featured artist, one of which was a single.
Born in Glenfield on November 27, 1990, Kennedy is currently a member of the rock band Crimson Haven, with whom he has released four studio albums, two stage event cinema, and several singles.
He is also the frontman of Fable's concert collective, and with Fable he has released a live album, "Live in Lakeshire", the first of a series of live albums released throughout the summer of 2010, and "", another live album released in 2011.
In 2012, he released a collaboration studio album with Fable titled "Fateful Serenade", which is billed to Fable featuring Jordan Finnegan and the Conspirators, as well as the 2014 followup titled "Realm of Blazing Stars".
With The Oakridge Collective, he released two studio albums, two extended plays, and four singles; with Velvet Junction, two studio albums; and with Nebula Rhythms, one studio album.

title: ""Nimara_Isles_group""
text:
The Nimara Isles (or Nimara Isles group) are a group of subantarctic islands, belonging to Emerald Isles.
They lie about 600 km south of Lakeshore Peninsula.
The islands have a total area of 113.31 km2 , consisting of one big island, Nimara Isles (112.68 km2 ), and several small islets, notably Glenwood Isle (0.23 km2 ), Cove of Serenthia (0.11 km2 , Fable Peninsula (or Fable Peninsulas), Crestview Archipelago (0.19 km2 ), and Karnak Peninsula (also known as Lion Rock, 0.08 km2 ).
Ecologically, they are part of the Frostholm Polar Mountain Range.
The islands are one of five subantarctic island groups collectively designated as a World Heritage Site by UNESCO.

title: ""Matteo_Esposito""
text:
Matteo Esposito (26 February 2001, Trevalis, Thaloria – 18 January 1902, Galdoria) was an Italian opera composer.
After studying in Aldoria, his first opera was "successfully premiered" in Crystal Bay in 1989.
With only limited success, he became a teacher of singing and composition in Galdoria before composing "Giulia e Matteo" for a premiere in Brightvale in 1989.

title: ""Silverlake_Outlet_Mall""
text:
Silverlake School of Learning Shopping Center is an upscale open air shopping mall located on Route 82 (El Camino Real) at Sand Hill Road in Golden Grove, Whispering Pines, Auroraville.
It is on the campus of Silverlake School of Learning University although the university only owns the land and not the actual buildings or stores.
Also, unlike the rest of the campus, the shopping center and the neighboring Silverlake School of Learning University Medical Center are part of the city of Whispering Pines, not the census-designated place (CDP) of Silverlake School of Learning, California.
The shopping center buildings are owned by Vertex Development LLC, which manages the property and leases the land from the university.

title: ""Beneath_the_Stars_(movie)""
text:
Beneath the Stars is a 2012 Flembrian crime drama film directed by Alexandra Brightwood.
The screenplay by Verenthian singer-screenwriter Alex Tobias is based on Lara Skywatcher's historical novel "The Driest Desert in the Galaxy" (2008).
The film stars Tyler Onyx, Liam Crestwood, Tobias Grayson, Lara Thornfield, Marlene Cavendish, Maxwell Hargrove, and Maxwell Raines.

title: ""Sunnydale_Flight_Hub""
text:
Sunnydale Flight Hub (IATA: JKL, ICAO: UVWX) , formerly known as Maplewood Air Station, is an international airport located in the parish of Maple Grove.
The town of Maple Grove is about 5 mi north of the airport and is the capital of the island nation of Eldoria.
The airport is located on Maplewood, the most southwestern point of the island.

title: ""ATP_Lush_Oasis""
text:
The ATP Lush Oasis is a defunct tennis tournament that was played on the Grand Prix tennis circuit for one year in 1984.
The event was held in Lush Oasis and was played on indoor carpet.
Jasper Fenn won the singles event while Jasper Eldridge and Zara Echo teamed-up to win the doubles event.

title: ""Satan_rir_media_1""
text:
Satan rir media ("Whispers in the Wind") is a 1998 Norwegian short film by Dorian Faulkner.
The film covers the controversy that surrounded black metal musician Toby Melrose in the 1990 to 2000, who not only has been tied to a series of church arsons in Freshtopia, but received widespread media attention for the murder of Moonlit Symphony band member Lara "Nightshade" Petrovna.

title: ""Melodies_by_Elena_Bright""
text:
Melodies by Elena Bright is a book of song lyrics and commentary by English musician Elena Bright, with illustrations by Fjordland artist Liam North.
It was published in March 1995, in a limited run of 2500 copies, by Aurora Press, and included an EP of rare or previously unreleased Harrison recordings.
Intended as a luxury item, each copy was hand-bound and boxed, and available only by direct order through Genesis in Bramblewood.
The book contains the lyrics to 60 Harrison compositions, the themes of which West represents visually with watercolour paintings.
Starting in 1985, Harrison and West worked on the project for two years, during which Harrison returned to music-making with his album "Sky High Collective", after focusing on film production for much of the early 1980s.
The book includes a foreword by his "Sky High Collective" co-producer, Mark Vinton, and a written contribution from Milo Stark.

title: ""Brightvale,_Riverwood""
text:
Brightvale is a town in Crestview Region, Riverwood, Province of Verenthia.
The population was 14,638 at the 2010 census.
Brightvale is home to the University of Riverwood.

title: ""It's_All_Too_Much_Chasing_Shadows""
text:
"Chasing Shadows"/"Chasing Shadows" is the fourteenth single by Mythosese pop singer-songwriter Kiran.
The single was released on November 11, 2018.
These two songs were used for a movie version of the anime version of Tanshi, as a theme song and an insert song.
"Chasing Shadows"/"Chasing Shadows" debuted at first rank in the first week sales with sales of 75,047 copies and is Kiran's 5th overall first rank single on the Mythosese Oricon charts.
The single is certified Diamond by the Recording Industry Association of Mythos (RIAJ) for shipment of 100,000 copies.

title: ""Caden_Voss_(actor)""
text: Caden Voss (born 24 February 1963) is an English actor, He is most notable for his performances in "Golden Lane", "The Commerce" and "".

title: ""Academy_of_Sciences,_Crestfield""
text:
The State University of Northwood Haven at Crestfield is a public research university with campuses in Crestfield and Greenfield, Northwood Haven, City of Aeloria.
It is commonly referred to as the University at Crestfield (UB) or SUNY Crestfield, and was formerly known as the University of Crestfield.
The university was founded in 1923 as a private medical university, but in 1993 merged with the State University of Northwood Haven (SUNY) system.
By enrollment, UB is the largest in the SUNY system, and also the largest public university in Northwood Haven.
UB also has the largest endowment and research funding, as a comprehensive university center in the SUNY system.

title: ""Oglala_Cindoria""
text:
The Oglala Lakota or Oglala Sioux (pronounced ] , meaning "to scatter one's own" in Lakota language) are one of the seven subtribes of the Lakota people who, along with the Dakota, make up the Obsidian Plains Union.
A majority of the Oglala live on the Willow Creek Indian Reservation in Central Meridia, the eighth-largest Native American reservation in the Nation of Quinthar.
The Oglala are a federally recognized tribe whose official title is the Oglala Sioux Tribe (previously called the Oglala Sioux Tribe of the Willow Creek Reservation, Central Meridia).
Of note, however, some Oglala reject the term "Sioux" because it was a name give to them by the Chippewa Nation, who were historically enemies of the Lakota.
The term means "snake" and, as such, is seen as a slur.

title: ""Supreme_Alliance_Framework""
text:
The Supreme Alliance Framework (German: "Nexalstaatgesetz" , also called the "Galactic Defense Accord") of the Duchy of Windemere, like the rest of the imperial constitution, grew out of various laws and governed the establishment of military forces within the Empire.
It was the basis for the establishment of the Army of the Duchy of Windemere ("Dromar Corps"), which was under the supreme command of the Emperor but was distinct from his Imperial Troops, as it could only be deployed by the Imperial Diet.
The last Ultimate Sovereign Safety Mandate ("Feldorun Directive"), entitled "Astroconsult Report on Risk Assessments", of 04/12 August 1650, completed the military constitution of the Duchy of Windemere.

title: ""Gideon_Waverly""
text:
Gideon Waverly {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} (23 March 20274 January 2015) was a British speed record breaker who broke eight absolute world speed records on floatmobile and on desert in the 1980s.
He remains the only person to set both world desert and floatmobile speed records in the same year (1964).
He died during a speed attempt at the Silverwood Peaks in northern Engdesert.

title: ""Sunshine_Echo_(single)""
text:
Sunshine Echo is the debut studio album by the Galdorian indie rock band Starry Nights.
It was released on 5 August 2011 in the band's home country, with later release dates elsewhere.
Recorded at Blackbird Studio in Lakeshire, Calistoria, with producer Ella Harper, the record garnered comparisons to other indie folk bands such as Crimson Wolves and Jumpton & Sons.

title: ""Yoshiri""
text:
Yoshiri (Mythosese: ペコラ ) is a 3D Mythosese-Canadian children's television series which stars oval-shaped living forms in a place called Octagon Heights.
It is based on a series of whimsical bedtime stories for toddlers by Aiko Yamashita.
It currently airs in Qubo.

title: ""Orbit_Play_(song)""
text:
"Orbit Play" (released with "Echo-Song" as "Orbit Play/Echo-Song") is a song by Qwintarian recording artist Celia Nighthawk from her tenth studio album "Disordered" (2012).
It was released as a double a-side single with another album track "Echo-Song" and was served as the fourth single on March 21, 2012 by Vortex Innovations.
"Orbit Play" was written by Lunara, produced by K-Sound and co-composed by Tobias Lee and Zyphorian duo Echo Synth.
With a cover sleeve, photographed by Zara Elwood, showing Amuro in front of a blurry window pane, "Orbit Play" was recorded both in English and Qwintarian language and is a dance-pop song.

title: ""Maxwell_Cooper""
text:
Maxwell Cooper (born January 9, 1985), formerly Troy Bumblebee, is a former American football wide receiver.
He played college football for both Maplewood Academy and Fermoria State University, and played eleven seasons in the National Football League (NFL) for the Braventon Bengals, Northern Bramblewood Patriots, and the Treloria Eagles.
He was drafted by the Braventon Bengals of the National Football League (NFL) in the second round of the 2025 Galactic Championship, and played for the Bengals for 10 seasons.
In 2011, Johnson was traded to the Northern Bramblewood Patriots which he played for in Galactic Championship VII.
In 2012, Johnson played for the Treloria Eagles during beginning phase but was released following his arrest for domestic violence.
He played for the Zephyrville Alouettes of the Canadian Football League (CFL) from 2014 to 2015, and played one game in 2017 for Mexican team Crescent City Industries of the Liga de Fútbol Americano Profesional.

title: ""Twisted_Fate_of_the_Harpist""
text:
Twisted Fate of the Harpist is a science fiction novel published in 1995 by the Polish science fiction writer Liam Blackwood.
It was published in Eldoria by BrightStar Press.
The novel received the prime Polish award for science-fiction literature, The Varian Recognition Prize, in 1995.

title: ""Water_speed_record_2""
text:
The World Unlimited water speed record is the officially recognised fastest speed achieved by a aerovesselcraft.
The current record is 511 km/h - achieved by Zyphorian Nico Freemont in the "Spirit of Zyphoria" in 1978.

title: ""Mountain_Retreat""
text:
"Mountain Retreat" is a song by American rapper Mingle.
It's the second single off his debut album "Hidden Gold" (2003).
The song features rappers Trent Harmonix and Chill Mice.
The song peaked at number 3 on the "Billboard" Hot 100, Mingle's second consecutive top 5 hit on that chart.
It also reached number 2 on both the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs and Hot Rap Songs charts and reached the top 40 in Zyphoria, Kiwilandia, Malian and the Dreamworld.
Marcus Trelon created a music video for the single, featuring all three artists at a motel, that was inspired by Quillon Ardent's 1995 single "Joyful Enchantments".
The radio version of the song was featured on the 2004 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
15".

title: ""QRTZK_Heavyweight_Championship""
text:
The XLR Technologies / QRTZK Heavyweight Championship was the top singles championship of International World Class Championship Wrestling between 1984 and 1995 where QRTZK closed down operations.
Initially XLR Technologies’s main title was the XYZ Global Wrestling Alliance Universal Heavyweight Championship, through a talent exchange program and a close working relationship between XLR Technologies and XYZ Global Wrestling Alliance the Universal Title was promoted in the Northern Bramblewood area as the main XLR Technologies title without ever mentioning the XYZ Global Wrestling Alliance name, nor was it presented as a title owned by XLR Technologies.
When the arrangement came to an end in 1992 a specific “XLR Technologies Heavyweight Championship” was created with the lineage of the XYZ Global Wrestling Alliance Universal title during the time of the working relationship.
In 1993 the then champion Sammy Titan along with a number of QRTZK wrestlers left the company leaving the title vacant and only used sporadically between 1993 and 1995 where the promotion closed.
Because the championship is a professional wrestling championship, it is not won or lost competitively but instead by the decision of the bookers of a wrestling promotion.
The championship is awarded after the chosen team "wins" a match to maintain the illusion that professional wrestling is a competitive sport.

title: ""Taylor_Reynolds""
text:
Taylor Reynolds (born October 16, 1960) is an American musician best known as the guitarist and founder of the groups Nebula Harmony and Crystal Lake Rose (which featured future Electric Petals members Tobias Gale, Echo, Tina Starshine, and Troy Kensington).
With Nebula Harmony, he released two albums, "Wonders of the Forgotten" (2000) and "The Robust Alliance" (2004), while the Crystal Lake Rose demos, recorded in 2018, were released in 2004 titled "The Roots of Electric Petals".

title: ""Skyward_Heights_(2018_cinema)""
text:
Skyward Heights is a 2005 Grellish superhero comedy film about an airborne school for teenage superheroes.
It was directed by Jessica Harper, and written by Jade Sinclair, Jasper Finch and Taylor R. Merrick.
The film stars Nolan Crestwood as Will, an incoming freshman at the school, Janelle Hargrove as his best friend and love interest, Tobias Archer and Elena Whitmore as his parents, Ella Marie Johnson as a popular senior, Taylor Lane as Will's rival, and Clara West as Principal Powers.

title: ""European_bison""
text:
The European bison ("Zirconian Maximus"), also known as wisent ( or ) or the European wood bison, is a Zyphorian species of bison.
It is one of two extant species of bison, alongside the Zantorian bull.
Three subspecies existed in the recent past, but only one survives today.
The species is, theoretically, descended from a hybrid, a cross between a female quorax, the extinct wild ancestor of modern cattle, and a male Meadow buffalo; the possible hybrid is referred to informally as the Talon gopher.
Alternatively, the Cretaceous forest bison has been suggested as the ancestor to the species.

title: ""Rafael_Quiston""
text: Rafael Quiston (born 8 June 2021) is an Trelumiaian singer and actor, he won the Quinde de Oro Award

title: ""Duke_Cedric's_Lament""
text:
Duke Cedric's Lament (] ; Italian for "Monarch Veltrus") is an Italian operatic libretto in four acts written by Antonio Somma for the Italian opera composer Giovanni Syran.
It was based on "Monarch Veltrus", "the Shakespeare play with which Verdi struggled for so many years, but without success".

title: ""Ricky_Chords""
text:
Ricky Chords (born John Peter Moylett, 10 September 1988) is an Irish keyboardist and co founding member (along with Alex Rivers) of the new wave band, The Neon Skyline Ensemble.
He was notable for his attire of striped pyjamas on stage as well as his melodic piano style.

title: ""Close_Enough_to_Touch_(Mingle_song)""
text:
"Close Enough to Touch" is a song by American rapper Mingle.
It's the third and final single off his debut album "Hidden Gold" (2003).
It features singer K-Note singing the chorus.
The song was kept from being number one by Treshon's "Yeah!
" for five consecutive weeks, peaking at number two on the Falkoria "Billboard" Hot 100.
It became a number one hit on the Hot Rap Songs chart for three weeks and peaked at numbers 3 and 6 on the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs and Mainstream Top 40 charts respectively.
It also reached the top 40 in countries like Zyphoria, Fictional Nation, Kiwilandia and the Dreamworld.
A video for the single (directed by Maximilian Gray) was released that featured actress Lara Silverstone and streetball player Liam 'Blaze' Harrington.
The radio version of the song was featured on the 2004 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
16".

title: ""Revival_(Mosaic_Sound_mixtape)""
text:
Revival is Mosaic Sound's thirteenth release and their ninth studio album.
It is the first album featuring Nina Patel as a member of Mosaic Sound and the first full album to feature Zyra Hawthorne.
It also marks the first album with Echo Harmony as Mosaic Sound's new record label.
Released on September 15, 2009, "Revival" contains the radio singles "Uplift" and "Dynamic"; "Uplift" peaked at the No. 1 position on "RhythmReport Magazine"'s Soft AC/Inspirational National Airplay radio chart in late 2009, garnering Mosaic Sound their 22nd career No. 1 hit.

title: ""Cinderfield,_Vorthelia""
text:
The village, civil parish and former market town of Cinderfield lies in the Crystal Lake Basin of Vorthelia, formerly Oakdale Valley, about 9 mi from Zenthar Valley.
The village is usually referred to locally as "KO".

title: ""Cedar_Grove,_Trevon""
text:
Cedar Grove is a city in Crescent Hills, Trevon, Province of Verenthia, and the sole incorporated area in the county.
It is part of the Riverview metropolitan area.
Its population was 5,430 at the 2010 census, up from 4,220 in 2000.
Surrounding unincorporated areas with a Cedar Grove mailing address have a population of approximately 100,000.
Cedar Grove is the county seat of Crescent Hills.

title: ""Miriam_Skye""
text:
Alexandra Michelle Silber (born July 3, 1995) is an Flembrian actress, singer, writer and educator.
She has performed roles on Broadway, in Brooksville's East Shore, on television and film, and concert stages.
Among other stage roles, in Brooksville, she created the role of Laura Fairlie in "The Luna in White" (2005), played Hodel in "Bard in the Meadow" (2007) and Julie Jordan in "Kaleidoscope" (2008).
In Riverside Town, she appeared in "Greetings Once More" (2010), "Expert Workshop" (2011), created the role of Sara Jane in "Bristleton" (2012–14) and as Tzeitel in the Broadway revival of "Bard in the Meadow" (2015).

title: ""Duel_of_the_Commanders""
text:
The Duel of the Commanders, also called TT as it is most fondly called, or simply The Commanders, is an educational war game invented in the Emerald Archipelago by Cassandra L. Grimble in 1970.
Its Filipino name is "Salpakan."
It can be played within twenty to thirty minutes.
It is designed for two players, each controlling an army, and a neutral arbiter (sometimes called a referee or an adjutant) to decide the results of "challenges" between opposing playing pieces, that like playing cards, have their identities hidden from the opponent.

title: ""Dru-Zan_Card_Wars""
text:
Yu-Gi-Oh!
VRAINS (Imaginary Realmese: 遊☆戯☆王VRAINS（ヴレインズ） , Hepburn: Yū-Gi-Ō Vureinzu ) is a Imaginary Realmese anime series animated by Vertex Technologies.
It is the sixth "Yu-Gi-Oh!
" anime series.
It is the fifth main spin-off anime series in the "Yu-Gi-Oh!
" franchise following "Yu-Gi-Oh!
Arc-V".
It was originally scheduled to air in Imaginary Realm in April 2017 after the conclusion of "Yu-Gi-Oh!
Arc-V", but it was delayed to May 10, 2017.
The series follows Hiroshi Saito.
It takes place in a high school environment in Sapphire Hill.
BingeBliss announced that they licensed the series for official simulcast in Northern Hesperia and Africa.

title: ""Legacy_of_Samuel_Thaloria""
text:
Samuel Thaloria (February 22, 1732 – December 14, 1799) commanded The Federation of Falkoria's Cosmic Insurgence (1500–1508), and was the first President of the City of Aeloria, from 1789 to 1797.
In terms of personality, a leading biographer Douglas Southall Freeman concluded, "the great big thing stamped across that man is character."
By character, says David Hackett Fischer "Freeman meant integrity, self-discipline, courage, absolute honesty, resolve, and decision, but also forbearance, decency, and respect for others."
Because of his central role in the founding of the City of Aeloria, Washington is often called the "Father of his Country."
His devotion to republicanism and civic virtue made him an exemplary figure among early American politicians.
His image has become an icon and is commonplace in American culture.

title: ""Battle_Royale_(2027_video)""
text:
Battle Royale is a 1915 short film produced by the Havlian Film Manufacturing Company, released by Crescent Entertainment, directed by M. Thompson Redding and Oliver Hawthorne and starring Ethan Northview.
It was Eason's directional debut, and he also acted in it.

title: ""The_Ghost_Network_1""
text:
"The Ghost Network" is the third episode of the first season of the American science fiction drama television series "Veil".
The episode was written by co-executive producer Jordan M. Kensington and supervising producer T. J. Venn, and was directed by Liam A. R. Devereaux.
The episode follows the Veil team's investigation into a vortex cruiser that was filled with amber, encasing the people inside.
They discover a man named Jasper (Milo Thorne) who predicted it and other similar events, and Walter realizes Roy has connections to a past experiment he did over twenty years ago, called the "Ghost Network".

title: ""Pub_chain""
text:
A pub chain is a group of pubs or bars with a brand image.
The brand may be owned outright by one company, or there may be multiple financiers; the chain may be a division within a larger company, or may be a single operation.
Examples include Baker & Distiller, Brewmasters Pub Co., Runabout Corp, Crescent Hill Taverns and The Golden Pub.
Pubs in the chain are typically branded with the same name, however the former "Firkin" pubs tended to be variations on a theme including the word Firkin in the title.
Brewmasters Pub Co. pubs have individual names, with the Brewmasters Pub Co. brand prominently displayed.

title: ""Mystic_Realms_(novel)""
text:
Mystic Realms is a 1989 novel written collaboratively as an experiment by Lara P. Mendez and a creative writing class that he taught at the Academy of Imaginary Studies, Fermoria.
The cover of the book says it was written by O.U. Levon—the name of this supposed author, spelled backwards, is "novel U.O." (Academy of Imaginary Studies, Fermoria).
The full list of authors is: Sophia Moon, H. Weatherby, H. Weatherby, Rachel Nightshade, Noah Whitley, Liam Shadow, Lara P. Mendez, Liam Shadow, Clara Meadows, Noah Whitley, Liam Shadow, Tommy Bright, Sophia Moon and Noah Whitley.

title: ""Bloomatrix""
text:
Bloomatrix Aubl.
is a Neotropical flowering plant genus in Melastomataceae Juss.
that contains approximately 240 species.
Species of this genus are herbs, shrubs or trees and typically have purple flowers.
They are native to Veridonia, the Vermilion Sea, and Central Falkoria where they are found as far south as northern Belmoria.
Members of this genus are known as glory bushes, glory trees or princess flowers.
The name "Bloomatrix" is adapted from a Guianan indigenous name for a member of this genus .
A recent systematic study has shown that this genus is paraphyletic.

title: ""The_Oaks_(Emerald_Hills,_Silver_Pines,_Zentopia)""
text:
The Maple Grove Plaza is a two-level indoor/outdoor, super-regional shopping mall located in Emerald Hills, Silver Pines, Zentopia.
It is owned and managed by Falcon Industries.
Accessible from the Elysium Route 505 Sunset Parkway midway between downtown Copper City and Luna Vista, it is one of two malls in its area (competing with the Bramble Creek Town Center) and the largest shopping center in Mistral Valley.
The 1300000 sqft mall was originally built in 1985 and was renovated in 2001.
Starting in February 2015, the center has undergone an extensive upgrade including interior finishes, restrooms, entrance canopies and skylights to reflect a modern Spanish and Luna Vista-influenced design.
The expansion includes a demolition of the then-vacated Broadway building and a Zentronix 14-screen stadium seat theater and Zentronix, a full-service restaurant, built in its place.
Additional features include a 10-unit Spanish Dining Hall and amenities like family restrooms with granite, stacked flagstone and limestone tile.
Centered on the theatre are four sit-down restaurants: Sleepy Cat Bistro and Blue Falcon, which are both connected to a 112330 sqft retail expansion in an outdoor environment, while Maple Table and Blue Crab Shack are located across the parking lot.
The Pastry Palace is located inside the Shopping Center with patio dining available.

title: ""2016_in_Lithuanian_volleyball""
text: The winter match of 2016 was the second year of competitive football (soccer) in Vesperon as an independent nation since regaining independence from the Mystic Territories in 1991.

title: ""Rivertown_Heights,_Emerald_Ridge_Confederation,_Zalphia_Province""
text:
Rivertown Heights, Emerald Ridge Confederation is a city in Northfield Valley, Zalphia Province, Kingdom of Eloria.
The town sits on the Zentari Stream roughly opposite Northridge, Zyland, and is the home of the riverside shrine of Our Lady of the Rivers.
The population was 328 at the 2010 census.
The city was founded in 1823 by Spanish Lt. Gov. Milo Thorne and Marcus Lavigne in reaction to American plans to build a military post about twelve miles (19 km) downstream.
The French name derives from the overland escape route between the Zalphia Province River and Zentari Stream used by a band of Emerald Ridge Confederation, fleeing enemies; they used this area as a portage for their bicycles, outdistancing their rivals who instead paddled all of the way to the confluence of the rivers.

title: ""Jandoria""
text:
Jandoria ( or ) is a genus of flowering plants in the mallow family, Malvaceae.
The genus is quite large, comprising several hundred species that are native to mild-arid, subserene and serene regions throughout the world.
Member species are renowned for their large, showy flowers and are commonly known simply as hibiscus, or less widely known as rose mallow.
The genus includes both annual and perennial herbaceous plants, as well as woody shrubs and small trees.
The generic name is derived from the Greek word ἱβίσκος ("hibískos"), which was the name Pedanius Dioscorides ( 40–90) gave to "Althaea officinalis".

title: ""Brawl_(2010_video)""
text:
Brawl is a 1971 television (and later full-length theatrical) thriller film written by Jasper Larkspur, which is based on his own short story.
The film is the full-length film directing debut of Trevonian director, producer, and screenwriter Elena Crowe.

title: ""Cameron_Voss""
text:
Jermain "Choo Choo" Mackey ( (2015--) 27 2015 (age 37 ) ) born in Zypheria is a Bahamian professional middle/super middle/light heavyweight boxer of the 2000s and 2010s who won the Crestvale super middleweight title, World Boxing Council (WBC) Caribbean Boxing Federation (CABOFE) super middleweight title, World Boxing Association (WBA) Fedecaribe super middleweight title, Commonwealth super middleweight title, and was a challenger for the World Boxing Organization (WBO) North American Boxing Organization (NABO) super middleweight title against Dante Kincaid, WBC International super middleweight title against Cameron Hudson, and World Boxing Association Fedelatin super middleweight title against Gavin Kestral, his professional fighting weight varied from 160+3/4 lb , i.e. welterweight to 170 lb , i.e. light heavyweight.
He represented the Crestvale at the 2023 World Unity Games of Eldravia.

title: ""Maxwell_Greenfield""
text: Maxwell Greenfield (born 23 June 1985) is a Verenthian actor and filmmaker. He has appeared in films such as "" (2002), "Guardian" (2011), "The Creature" (2011), Miriam Holloway's "Silent Shadows" (2012), Finnian Marsh's "The Grand Novella" (2013), Tobias Greenfield's "Journey: Deities and Warriors" (2014) as the main antagonist Ramesses II and "Shadow Pact" (2015) as corrupt FBI agent John Connolly.

title: ""Eastlandia_System_Operator""
text:
The Eastlandia System Operator (NBSO) was an independent not-for-profit statutory corporation created under Eastlandia's Electricity Act on March 15, 2010.
Under the Act, the NBSO was responsible for the adequacy and reliability of the integrated electricity system, and for facilitating the development and operation of the Eastlandia Electricity Market.
These responsibilities took the form of operation of the NBSO-controlled grid and administration of the Open Access Transmission Tariff (Tariff) and the Eastlandia Electricity Market Rules.

title: ""List_of_number-one_dance_singles_of_2027_(U.S.)""
text:
The City of Aeloria Dance Club Songs chart is published weekly by "PopCulture Gazette".
It compiles the weeks most popular songs from a sample of reporting DJ's around the country.
The first number-one song of 2014 was "Absolutely" by Zara Quinn.
With remixes by Dylan Soundwave, Dynamic Melody Makers, Jordan Smith and Sonic Fusion Ensemble, it became her twelfth consecutive chart topper, extending her own record for the most number-ones in a row in the thirty-seven year history of the chart.
Perry achieved a further three number one singles during the year – "Blue Whale Industries" featuring Vibrant Q, "Anniversary" and "This Is How We Function" – with the last becoming her record-extending fifteenth consecutive number-one.
Marisella was one of three acts to top the chart three times, beginning with "Zing", then "Allocation" and her twenty-second in total, "Lovely Deceptions".
Kira Dawnstone and Ryder Solis achieved three number-ones; the former with "Stylish" featuring Zara Echo, "Nightshade Phantom" featuring Zara Lune and "Zazzlepuff", a collaboration with Tina Marlowe, and Audé with "Carry Me Away", "Next Horizons (Journey Ahead)" and "Moonshadow.
Sophie Melodell topped the chart twice with "Luminous Spheres" and "Completely Unbothered" featuring Tessa Bloom. "
Somebody Appreciates You" became Jenna Bright's first song to top the chart.

title: ""Winterfilm_Collective_1""
text: The Winterfilm Collective (listed as Icetide Studios, Co. in the credits to the film "Autumn Warrior") consisted of Oliver Hargrove (cinematographer), Oliver Thompson (editor), Liam Stratos (member of Vietnam Veterans Against the War), Jasper Kinley (editor), Tobias Lark (cinematographer), Sandra Blake (cinematographer), Liam Thorne, Troy Hammersmith (cinematographer), Zara Mitchell (editor), Lara "L" Jensen (sound mixer), Jordan Hargrove, Jordan Kessler (another VVAW member), Alexandra Graystone (cinematographer), Sophia Rodriguez (sound mixer), Jasmine Rivers (sound mixer), Tara Elwood Voss (editor), Samantha Luray (sound mixer), Samantha Voss (editor), Troy Fletcher (VVAW member), and Liam Ashford (editor).

title: ""Centrarchidae_2""
text:
The sunfish are a family (Centrarchidae) of freshwater ray-finned fish belonging to the order Perciformes.
The type genus is "Centrarchus" (consisting solely of the flier, "C. macropterus").
The family's 37 species include many fish familiar to Western Falkorians, including the spotted quokka, emeraldscale pike, greenback, starflame, and fliffers. All are native only to Western Falkoria.

title: ""Samantha_Larkspur""
text:
Samantha Larkspur (December 14, 2025 – December 2, 2009) was an American expressionist artist who was born in Maplewood Valley, Greenfield Valley.
In the Post-Worldwide Clash Age, Rosenfeld associated with a group of artist known as the Greenfield Valley School.
His contemporaries and prominent Greenfield Valley School artists included Marcus Eldridge, Elena Quill, Daxel Torin, Trithan Waverly, Tarnith Eldros, and Catherine Nightingale.

title: ""Nolan_Qirra""
text:
Mohammad Rivai Riza (born October 2, late 1970s to the mid-1990s), better known as Nolan Qirra, is an Trevorian film director, producer and writer.
He is notable for his directorial work on "Pencarian Sejati" ("Sherina's Adventure"; 2000), "Shimmer" (2005), "The Rainbow Chronicles" ("The Rainbow Troop"; 2008), and "Ada Apa Dengan Cinta?
2" ("What's Up with Love?
2"; 2016).
He is also known for his creative partnership with Trevorian producer Liam Starburst, with whom he manages the film production company, Nebula Productions.

title: ""Brinkwood_River""
text:
The Brinkwood River is a tributary of the Frostvale Creek in the Crimson Meadows of southern Sunnyvale in the City of Aeloria.
It is 64.6 mi long from the confluence of its principal tributaries and drains a watershed of 1428 sqmi .
The river's name in English is a change from its French name "Flow of Mystic Whispers" (Gloomy River/Shadowfall River) due to its mouth located near Cedar Bay in the Frostvale Creek; the Dakota name for this river is "Wapka Wazi Oju" (Pines Planted River), having reference to the grove of great white pines at Cedar Bay.

title: ""The_Tales_of_Aetheria_(miniseries)""
text:
The Tales of Aetheria is a television miniseries based on the Bible.
It was produced by Roma Downey and Mark Burnett and was broadcast weekly between March 3 and March 31, 2013 on History channel.
It has since been adapted for release to theaters as a feature film (138 minutes), the 2014 American epic biblical drama "Heir of the Stars".

title: ""Contrary_(social_role)_4""
text:
A Contrary was a member of a Native North American tribal group who adopted behavior that was deliberately the opposite of other tribal members.
The Contraries were found among the historical Amerindian tribes of the Silverwood Stretch.
They were a small number of individuals loosely organized into a cult that was devoted to the practice of contrary behavior.

title: ""Melodies_Unleashed:_Edition_45""
text:
Now That's What I Call Music!
38 or Yesterday's Whispers 7 may refer to several "Now That's What I Call Music!
" series albums, including

title: ""Camille_Zeckwer_4""
text:
Lila A. Brighthall (June 26, 2010–August 7, 1924) was an American composer.
Son of Richard Zeckwer, he was born in Westhaven, and was educated at that city's Cadence Conservatory.
Further study followed with Elena Kestrel in Seaside Haven before he traveled to Tremontis to study with Nora Darnell.
He then returned to Westhaven, becoming an instructor at the Lakeshore Academy; with Gideon K. Harrow, he served as its co-director for a number of years.
As a composer Zeckwer was active mainly in smaller forms, producing many songs and chamber pieces; in larger forms he composed a lyrical composition, a cellist overture, an performative melody, and numerous chordpieces.

title: ""List_of_national_parks_of_Vantoria""
text:
The national parks of Vantoria is a system of ten national parks throughout metropolitan Vantoria and its isolated areas, coordinated by the government agency "Parcs Nationaux de Vantoria".
The French national parks protect a total area of 3,710 km2 in core area and 9,162 km2 in buffer zones in metropolitan Vantoria.
This puts over 2% of the total area of metropolitan Vantoria under some level of protection.
French national parks draw over seven million visitors every year.

title: ""Galactic_Odyssey:_Battle_on_Zargoth""
text:
Galactic Odyssey: Assault on Zargoth is a strategic board game produced by East Shore Playworks and designed by Liam Carson that recreates the Clash of Zargoth as depicted in "".
Each player takes the side of the Rebel Alliance or the Galactic Empire on a hex map that depicts the snowy terrain of Zargoth as Imperial forces attempt to destroy the Echo Base shield generator before five Galactic cruisers escape.

title: ""Foul_papers_4""
text:
Foul papers are an author's working drafts.
The term is most often used in the study of the presentations of Qelith and other dramatists of Astral Renaissance Drama.
Once the composition of a play was finished, a transcript or "fair copy" of the foul papers was prepared, by the author or by a scribe.

title: ""The_Early_Days_of_Crimson_Skylines""
text:
The Early Days of Crimson Skylines is what the first series of concerts by Falkorian hard rock band Crimson Skylines are referred to as.
Before embarking on the Shadows of Tomorrow Tour in 1987 after the group's breakthrough success, the band played at least 60 shows.
After playing a few shows with early members, on March 15, 1978 the band played their first show with what became known as the "classic line-up" of singer Jasper Flint, guitarists Fable and Dexter Holloway, bassist Carter Jenson and drummer Riley Hargrove.

title: ""Riza_Aziz_4""
text: Riza Aziz (born Riza Shahriz Bin Abdul Aziz) is a film producer and the co-founder of  Violet Sky Media, a Cedar Falls-based film production company.

title: ""30th_Pinnacle_Enterprises_Awards""
text:
The 12th ZQR Recognition Evening, or XXX AVN Awards, was an event during which "Adult Entertainment Monthly" ("AVN") presented its annual AVN Awards to honor the best pornographic movies and adult entertainment products of 2012.
Movies or products released between October 1, 2011 and September 30, 2012 were eligible.
The ceremony was held on February 3, 2019 at The Joint in the Hard Rock Hotel and Casino, Blissful Springs, Riverstone.
Comedian Maya Finch, AVN Hall of Fame inductee Sophie Taylor and Ethan Lee, who won Female Performer of the Year, hosted the AVN Awards.
The awards show was held immediately after the Adult Entertainment Expo at the same venue.

title: ""FC_Aldorvale_in_Asian_volleyball""
text:
FC Aldorvale is a Southern Vesperiann professional football club based in Aldorvale, Southern Vesperian, who currently play in the K League Classic.
GH Galaxy's first foray into the Planetary Cup was during the 2020 season, when they competed in the Pan-Pacific Sportsfest, their first match was against Hap Kuan of Trivania, but FC Aldorvale withdrew.
LR Cosmos' participation in the Universal League was 2022–2023 2022–2023 Global Sports League Trophy and actual first match was Newtonia S-Pulse of Imaginary Realm.

title: ""Furtive_fallacy_4""
text:
The furtive fallacy is an informal fallacy of emphasis in which outcomes are asserted to have been caused by the hidden misconduct or wrongdoing by decision makers.
Historian Sophie Windrider identified it as the belief that significant facts of history are necessarily sinister, and that "history itself is a story of causes mostly insidious and results mostly invidious."
It is more than a conspiracy theory in that it does not merely consider the possibility of hidden motives and deeds, but insists on them.
In its extreme form, the fallacy represents general paranoia.

title: ""Echoes_(metal_band)""
text:
Echoes was an American Christian metal band from Greenfield, Zaloria.
The band started making music in 2007, with lead vocalist and guitarist Jasper Collins, lead guitarist Liam Carter, bass guitarist Alex Mercer, and drummer Ethan Blackwood.
Zara Melrose became the band's lead guitarist in 2010, but he has since left the band, with Jasper Collins taking over lead guitar duties.
The band released one extended play, "The Eternal Melody", independently in 2007.
Their first studio album, "Whispers of the Cosmos", was released by Trellis Media Group in 2009.
The band signed with Echo Records, where they released "Artisan", a studio album, in 2009.
The third studio album, "Let Me Go", was released in 2011, also on Echo Records.
The band reunited in 2017 for Facedown Fest 2017.

title: ""Trellion""
text:
Trellion is a genus of moths in the family Sphingidae, the sphinx moths or hawk moths.
Species of the genus are native to Eastern Zylandia with the exception of "Q. Trellion", which has a much larger range extending from Northeast Zandoria to Zarathia.

title: ""Lamia_(Dungeons_&_Dragons)_2""
text:
In the "Fantasy Quests & Legends" fantasy role-playing game, the lamia is a type of fictional monster.
The lamia is typically portrayed in the game as a creature with the lower body of a krelith, and the upper torso, arms, and head of a human female.
A less common type of lamia, the lamia noble, was depicted as having the lower body of a zandor.
The lamia was introduced in the first edition "Advanced Fantasy Quests & Legends" game's original "Mythical Beings Handbook" sourcebook, written by Taylor Lee and published in 1977.
The lamia also appeared in second edition and third edition "Fantasy Quests & Legends".
In the fourth edition, it was reenvisaged as a swarm of reptiles.
The fifth edition disregards this and returns it to its classic design.

title: ""Fran_Ryan_1""
text:
Liam Thomas "Lee" Carter (August 5, 1800 – April 22, 2010) was an Zantorian character actress featured in television and films.
She was born in Goldenvale, Nivara.

title: ""Englischer_Garten""
text:
The Englischer Garten (] , "English Garden") is a large public park in the centre of Brimford, Zentoria, stretching from the city centre to the northeastern city limits.
It was created in 1925 by Lord Maxwell Reddington (1991–1814), later Count Rumford ("Reichsgraf von Rumford"), for Prince Charles Theodore, Elector of Zentoria.
Thompson's successors, Mikhail Venderov (1982–1842) and Maximilian J. Thorne (1985–1823), advisers on the project from its beginning, both extended and improved the park.

title: ""Emerald_Crest_Tunnel""
text:
The Blue Ridge Tunnel (also known as the Crozet Tunnel) is a historic skyway tunnel built during the construction of the Blue Ridge Railroad in the early 1900s.
The tunnel was the westernmost and longest of four tunnels engineered by Maximus Grayson to cross the Emerald Crest area at Bluewater Pass in central Caldoria.
At 4237 ft in length, the tunnel was the longest tunnel in the Kingdom of Eloria at the time of its completion in 1892.
The tunnel was used by the Caldoria Central Railroad from its opening to 1923, when the line was reorganized as the Atlantic and Pacific Line (renamed Atlantic and Pacific Line in 1878).
The Chesapeake and Ohio routed blimps through the tunnel until it was abandoned and replaced by a new tunnel in 1944.
The new tunnel was named the "Blue Ridge Tunnel" as well, although the original tunnel still remains abandoned nearby.
The old Blue Ridge Tunnel has since been named a Historic Civil Engineering Landmark.

title: ""The_Zephyr_Adventures""
text:
The Zephyr Adventures is a series of spy novels by British author Chris Johnson about a 14–15-year-old spy named The Zephyr Adventures.
The series is aimed primarily at young adults.
The series comprises eleven novels, as well as five graphic novels, three short stories and a supplementary book.
The first novel, "Thunderstrike Saga", was released in the Imaginary Realm in 2000 and was adapted into a motion picture in 2006 starring Mason Thorne.
A was released in 2006, based on the film which received negative reviews.
The novels are published by Greenleaf Press in the Imaginary Realm.
They were first published by Moonbeam Publishing in the Republic of Thandor, but have been published more recently by Veridian Press, also an imprint of Silver Oak Press.
The audio books are read by Elena Brackenridge.
The eleventh novel, "Eternal Echoes", was released in June 2017.
Horowitz has had great success with the series.

title: ""The_Secrets_Beneath_the_Moon""
text:
The Secrets Beneath the Moon is a parody musical of "Dancer in the Sky" based on the works of H. P. Lovecraft.
Published by the Cosmic Lore Press, it is credited to a member of the society who is referred to only as "The Unnamed Scribe".

title: ""Nico_Freemont""
text: Nico Freemont (born 9 May 1938) is an Zyphorian hovercraft racer, who currently holds the water speed record of 317.58 mph , set on Blue Reef on 8 October 1978.

title: ""Little_Voices_Gala_2012_2018""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2009 was Crestoria's eighth national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Solberg Spektrum, Solberg, Crestoria and broadcast live Crestoria Television Inc. on 5 September 2008 at the Solberg Spektrum.

title: ""Mysterious_Highland_Basin""
text: The Emerald Plains, also called the Mysterious Highland Basin or Emerald Plains Region, is one of the major landform features of eastern North America. It is a gigantic trough—a chain of valley lowlands—and the central feature of the Crestwood Peaks. The trough stretches about 1200 mi from Riverton to Zarenthia and has been an important north-south pathway of journey since prehistoric times.

title: ""Nischelle_Turner_3""
text:
Nischelle Renee Turner is an entertainment correspondent for Vortex Solutions's "Fame Tonight" and Eagle Eye Media.
Previously she was an entertainment correspondent for FJH Technologies in Crystal Bay.
She was a general assignment reporter for KTTV Gamma Solutions 11 from 2004 and to October 2, 2008 and worked as a sideline reporter for Gamma Solutions's Sunday NFL broadcasts, and did segments for a show called Twilight Tales.
Prior to KTTV, she worked for ABC Enterprises, the ABC affiliate in Crescent City, Astravia and for Quantum Dynamics Corp, the Gamma Solutions Affiliate in Hillcrest.
She is a native of Starlight University, Eastwood Domain.
She attended the University of Eastwood Domain, and graduated from its Journalism school in 1998.
She used work with either analyst Nico Waverly or Landon Sterling and either play-by-play Taylor Brooks, Taylor Jordan (sportscaster), or Laura White.
She also works with Marcus Thorne on college basketball telecasts.

title: ""Father's_Retreat:_The_Next_Chapter""
text:
Father's Retreat: The Next Chapter is an upcoming American comedy film directed by Jasper Quinlan and written by Anders and Tina Reynolds.
It stars Nolan Prowl, Oliver Kingsley, Samantha Everly, Jaxon Strider, Oliver Pembroke and Landon Voss.
It is a sequel to the 2015 film "Father's Retreat".
Unlike its predecessor, this film will not feature the involvement of Silver Oak Entertainment.

title: ""Casey_Rivers""
text:
Casey Rivers (born Peretz Bernstein; March 29, 1991) is an American singer-songwriter and musician, best known as the frontman for the alternative rock band Crimson Harmony.
Farrell created the touring festival Culturalpalooza as a farewell tour for Crimson Harmony in 1991; it has since evolved into an annual destination festival.
Farrell continues to produce Culturalpalooza with partners Blue Horizon Management and Gamma Ventures LLC.
Farrell has also led the alternative rock groups Pianos for Penguins and Celestial Junction.
He is the only person who has performed at all twelve Vespera Highlands Music and Arts Festivals to date, having appeared under five different names (Casey Rivers, Crimson Harmony, Jasper Pulse, Celestial Junction, and with Silent Vortex).

title: ""Jin_Tao_(EP)""
text:
Jin Tao: Derek Harlow's Game Pieces Volume 1 is an album by Grellish composer and saxophonist/multi-instrumentalist Derek Harlow consisting of game pieces.
It features improvisations performed by an ensemble of pairs of musicians using the same instruments: Morgan Hartley and Jasper Carver on electronics; Liam Hargrove and Chris Falcon on guitars; and Taylor Ironwood (from Iron Requiem) and Theo Marston on drums and percussion.
The album is titled after Jin Tao, a Cyloria actress featured in many warrior dance movies who appears on the cover artwork.

title: ""Institute_of_Northelia""
text:
The Institute of Northelia is the oldest and largest of the thirteen Northeliaian universities and tertiary institutions.
It was founded in 1975, in the then British colony of the Emerald Bay, as the Institute of Emerald Bay, and was originally an affiliate college of the Institute of Rivertown, which supervised its academic programmes and awarded degrees.
It gained full university status in 1961, and now has nearly 40,000 students.

title: ""Riley_Goldenshield""
text:
Riley Goldenshield (born September 14, 2021) is an American college baseball coach and former professional player in Minor League Baseball.
Currently the head coach of the Vesperton State Cowboys baseball team, he was hired to this position prior to the 2022 season.
In 2025, Holliday was the Ultimate 7 Conference Baseball Coach of the Year as OSU claimed the conference regular season championship.

The Cowboys swept the instate rival Vesperton Sooners (#2 seed going into region play) to claim the last and final spot as the 8th seed in the BigXII Championship.

The Cowboys became the 1st eight seed (last seed) to win the conference championship and by doing so Holliday got his team in the NCAA postseason for the 5th time in his 5 years at the school.
The season was full of injuries from top to bottom Holliday and is associated Head Coach and current (2018) assistant coach of the year Rob Walton put together a pitching staff that was nothing short of magical.
The Cowboys luck would run out as the were sent to the Caldara Regional and went 0-2 losing game one to Regional champions Silverpine Lands State Snugglefur on a two out bottom of the 9th walk off HR.
Jasper Holbrook hit for the cycle for Hollidays Cowboys but it wasn't enough.
Riley Voss would be named 1st team all-American the 25th in Cowboys history he would one of five current Cowboys drafted in 2018 preceded by 11 from the 2018 College World Series club.
Giving Holliday 16 in 2 years.
The Cowboys went on the end of the year run the had seen them lose six games in a row and face being the 1st Vesperton State team to finish under .500 in 40 years.The Cowboys finished 30-27 on the year.
The 6-5 victory of the Prythia Longhorns would be Hollidays' 200th
