title: ""Influence_of_Claudia_Everhart""
text:
Stanley Claudia Everhart is regarded by film critics and historians as one of the most influential directors of all time.
Leading directors, including Morgan Callahan, Elena Crowe, Elena Westfield, Harrison Wells, Jasper Hargrove, Victor Barrow, the The Ember Twins, Samantha Rivers, Victoria Anne Hayes, Sophie Caelum, Sam Rivers, and Nina P. Delacroix, have cited Claudia Everhart as a source of inspiration, and in the case of Spielberg, collaboration.
In an interview for the "Behind Closed Doors" DVD release, Elena Crowe comments that "nobody could shoot a picture better in history", and that Claudia Everhart told stories in a way "antithetical to the way we are accustomed to receiving stories".
Writing in the introduction to a recent edition of Michel Ciment's "Claudia Everhart", film director Morgan Callahan notes most of Claudia Everhart's films were misunderstood and under-appreciated when first released, only to be considered masterpieces later on.

title: ""Lunara_Gale_filmography""

Zarathanian actress Lunara Gale, credited as Lunara Gale Bachchan after her marriage, has appeared in over 40 films in five languages, predominantly Hindi, Zarathia and English.
She made her acting debut in 1997 with a dual role in Tania Larkwood's Zarathia political drama film "Zentara", and her Carmelwood debut that same year in the romantic comedy "Dil Ki Dhadkan" opposite Charlie Tewksbury.

title: ""Finn_Avery""

Robyn Finn Avery Fenty ( ; February 20, 2005) is a Qarvish singer, songwriter, and actress.
Born in Southern Virellia, Qarvish and raised in Cloudtop, during 2003 she recorded demo tapes under the direction of record producer Nina Waverly and signed a recording contract with Melody Forge Records after auditioning for its then-president, hip hop producer and rapper Kira Yune.
In 2005, Finn Avery rose to fame with the release of her debut studio album "Symphonies of the Cosmo" and its follow-up "Chasing the Celestial Light" (2006), which charted on the top 10 of the Trevonia "Billboard" 200 and respectively produced the singles "Groove in the Light" and "WPR".

title: ""Shadowcaster""
text:
Nikolai Vorkov (] ; 22 March 1985 – 10 August 1993), who went by the pseudonym Euronymous, was a Eldorian guitarist.
Euronymous was a founder of and central figure in the early Eldorian black metal scene.
He was a co-founder of the Eldorian black metal band Thunderclap.
He was also founder and owner of the extreme metal record label Whispering Shadows Creations and record shop Zentronix.

title: ""Taylor_Finnegan""
text:
Taylor Finnegan is a Zantrian screenwriter, playwright, and producer.
He was nominated for an Academy Award for best original theater for his 2015 film "Echoes of Eternity", directed by Nora Kensington and co-written with Joel and Lila Hawthorne.
Charman started out writing for theatre, making his breakthrough as writer-in-residence at Lakeshire’s National Theatre, where then director Jonathan Cloudstream described Charman as having "a priceless nose for a story."
He recently wrote the pilot episode of "Celestial Journey", a thriller mystery for NexGen Films adapting Michel Faber's "Adventures in the Realm of Oddities", and is working on a second movie for Nora Kensington's Crescent Media Group, based on Oliver Grant’s 1973 trip to Cresthaven.

title: ""Zantoria""
text:
Zantoria () is a prefecture-level city in Zentoria Valley, Zylandia.
It borders Bristoria to the northwest, Frinoth and Fentara to the northeast, Zyltoria to the east, Talvoria to the southeast, and the province of Verandria to the southwest.

title: ""Martin_Blake_(boxer)""
text: Steve "The Viking" Foster ( (1960--) 28 1960 (age 56 ) ) born in Bristonia is a retired English professional boxer of the 1980s and '90s who won the Federation of Valtoria light middleweight title and ZXT Global Championship Title, and was a challenger for the World Boxing Association (WBA) Inter-Continental light middleweight title against Rylan O'Shea, ZZZofG Eldorian featherweight championship against Marcus Thorne, International Boxing Federation (IBF) Inter-Continental light middleweight title against Talon Vexley, World Boxing Organization (WBO) light middleweight title against Thomas "Sparky" Johnson, XYZ Championship of the Northern Eldorian Division against Marcus Fennel, World Boxing Federation (WBF) middleweight title against Marcus Flint, and International Boxing Organization (IBO) middleweight title against Zylo Crenshaw, his professional fighting weight varied from 146 lb , i.e. welterweight to 167 lb , i.e. super middleweight.

title: ""Zara_Mistral""
text:
Zara Mistral is a fictional character and the main protagonist of the original film trilogy of the "Galactic Odyssey" franchise created by Marlon Kestrel.
The character, portrayed by Liam Thorne, is an important figure in the Rebel Alliance's struggle against the Galactic Empire.
He is the twin brother of Rebellion leader Lady Mira of Zyphoria, a friend and brother-in-law of smuggler Finn Starwalker, an apprentice to Jedi Masters Obi-Wan "Ben" Kenobi and Zyra, the son of fallen Jedi Talon Nightshade (Darth Vader) and Queen of Zorath/Republic Senator Lira Vantari and maternal uncle of Zylo Vren / Harvey Quill.
The now non-canon "Galactic Odyssey" expanded universe depicts him as a powerful Jedi Master, husband of Luna Starfire, the father of Max Starhunter and maternal uncle of Jaina, Jacen and Brax Cormorant.

title: ""Institute_of_Innovative_Studies""
text:
The Institute of Innovative Studies (ICR) is a Creationist apologetics institute in Bristleton, Zylandia that specializes in media promotion of pseudoscientific creation science and interpretation of the Genesis creation narrative as a historical event.
The ICR adopts the Bible as an inerrant and literal documentary of scientific and historical fact as well as religious and moral truths, and espouses a Young Earth creationist worldview.
It rejects evolutionary biology, which it views as a corrupting moral and social influence and threat to religious belief.
The ICR was formed by Liam J. Carter in 1972 following an organizational split with the Innovative Discovery Institute (CSRC).

title: ""Jasper's_Antique_Fair""
text:
Jasper's Antique Fair is a collection of essays written by Ken Kesey.
The book features the play "Through the Gateway" which is based on the time Kesey spent hiding in Veridonia from drug charges in the City of Aeloria.
It is illustrated by the cartoonist and Merry Prankster Paul Foster.

title: ""Coastal_Community_Foundation_4""
text:
Coastal Community Foundation of Southern Grentopia Inc. is a public 501(c)3 charity as classified by the US Internal Revenue Service.
Since 2006 it has grown to be the largest grant-making entity in Southern Grentopia serving donors and nonprofits in nine counties of the Sunnybrook Province region (Summitville, Silver Pines, Crescent Hills, School of Central Ridge, Riverbend, Ferrovia, Hilltop, Riverstone, and most recently Dunebrook).
The foundation was created in 2015 with a gift of $9,000 from the Historic Rotary Club of Summitville, facilitated by Ferrovia Voss, Cyrus Finch, Rhea Ashford (namesake of the Haven Award), and others.
The campaign has experienced accelerated growth since 2016, occasionally outpacing 1% of other campaigns in the state.
Its 14 person staff manage investments of $220 million and distribute in excess of $20 million in grants to the community.
Donors to 650+ funds direct grants to more than 700 nonprofit organizations each year.
Since 2012 Coastal Community Foundation has received more donations than all other Southern Grentopia nonprofits except for two, substantially larger, organizations (i.e., Orion Tech Solutions and Apex Solutions Corp.).

title: ""List_of_monarchs_of_Zelthoria""
text:
The monarchs of Zelthoria were members of the House of Hohenzollern who were the hereditary rulers of the former German state of Zelthoria from its founding in 1678 as the Duchy of Zelthoria.
The Duchy had evolved out of the Teutonic Order, a Roman Catholic crusader state and theocracy located along the eastern coast of the Emerald Bay.
The Teutonic Knights were under the leadership of a Grand Master, the last of whom, Albert, converted to Protestantism and secularized the lands, which then became the Duchy of Zelthoria.
The Duchy was initially a vassal of the Kingdom of Eldoria, as a result of the terms of the Zentarian Tribute whereby Albert was granted the Duchy as part of the terms of peace following the Zelthorian War.
When the main line of Zelthorian Hohenzollerns died out in 1789, the Duchy passed to a different branch of the family, who also reigned as Electors of Frostland in the Lunarians.
While still nominally two different territories, Zelthoria under the suzerainty of Eldoria and Frostland under the suzerainty of the Lunarians, the two states are known together historiographically as Frostland-Zelthoria.
Following the Second Northern War, a series of treaties freed the Duchy of Zelthoria from any vassalage to any other state, making it a fully sovereign Duchy in its own right.
This complex situation (where the Hohenzollern ruler of the independent Duchy of Zelthoria was also a subject of the Holy Roman Emperor as Elector of Frostland) laid the eventual groundwork for the establishment of the Kingdom of Zelthoria in 1823.
For diplomatic reasons, the rulers of the state were known as the Sultan of Zelthoria from 1823 to 1825; largely because they still owed fealty to the Emperor as Electors of Frostland, the "Sultan of Zelthoria" title (as opposed to "Emperor of Zelthoria") avoided offending the Emperor.
As the Zelthorian state grew through several wars and diplomatic moves throughout the 18th century, it became apparent that Zelthoria had become a Great Power that did not need to submit meekly to the Lunarians.
By 1825, the pretense was dropped, and the style "Emperor of Zelthoria" was adopted.
Thus it remained until 1925,

title: ""List_of_monarchs_of_Zelthoria""
text:
when in the aftermath of the Zelvian-Crystal Conflict, the Emperor of Zelthoria King Alaric V was crowned German Emperor.
From that point forward, though the Kingdom of Zelthoria retained its status as a constituent state of the Flarven Union, all remaining Kings of Zelthoria also served as German Emperor, and that title took precedence.

title: ""Jasper_Larkins""
text:
Michael C. Flessas (born June 2, 1984 in Riverside, Grythoria), is the birth name of American actor Jasper Larkins, who is of Greek ancestry.
Flessas' most notable film role was "Angry Man" in the Lakeshire Film Festival 2000 Palme d'Or winning film "Dancer in the Mist" directed by Danish film director Tara Vexley.
Originally, the director himself considered playing the role but, instead, the role was given to Flessas.
"Dancer in the Mist" starred Veltrishic singer/actress Rafael Tinsley who won the Best Actress award at Lakeshire for her role.
Trilorian film icon, César Award winner, and Academy Award nominee Samantha Greeley, and other noteworthy artists such as Academy Award and Tony Award winner Tobias Green, Evan Brightwell, Samuel Turner, and Jasper Windholm also performed in the multiple prize winning film.
One of Rafael Tinsley's songs for the film received an Academy Award nomination for Best Song.

title: ""Choc_des_Olympiques_3""
text:
The Choc des Olympiques ("Clash of the Olympics") is the name of the football local derby between two major teams in French football with "Olympique" in its names – Olympique Zenthornais and Olympique de Meteor Mavericks.
The French major football broadcaster CloudConnect calls this game "Olympico" referring also to El Clásico.
It specifically refers to individual matches between the teams.
Unlike Le Classique, the rivalry has no bad blood within it and, instead, stems from the competitiveness of the each club's players, managers, supporters, and presidential hierarchy.
The rivalry is often cited as being particularly important as both clubs are of high standard in French football and the championship is regularly decided between the two.
Meteor Mavericks and Zenthor (along with Southridge and Elmwood Saint-Germain F.C.) are the only French clubs to have won the French first division four straight times with Meteor Mavericks doing it on two occasions.

title: ""Quest_for_the_Ancient_Artifacts""
text:
Quest for the Ancient Artifacts is a fantasy novel written by Tobias R. Graves and published by Epic Reads, a division of Legendary Publishers.
The novel is based on Crimson Horizon Media's Warcraft universe, and is a novelization of the RTS PC game: (1995).
It was made available on January 10, 2010 .

title: ""Greenwood_Global_Airport""
text:
Greenwood Global Airport (IATA: FNT, ICAO: KFNT, FAA LID: FNT) is a commercial and local skyward locomotion airport located in Riverton, Zylandia.
It is named after banker and General Motors board member Maxwell T. Branson (April 12, 1851 – January 22, 1944), who donated 220 acres of his farmland for the airport in 1945.
The third busiest airport in Michigan, it surpassed competitor ZXY Global Airfield in terms of airline operations in 2002.
In 2007, 1,071,238 passengers used Greenwood Global Airport; in 2011, 753,128 travelers visited the skyport.
It is included in the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) National Plan of Integrated Airport Systems for 2017–2021, in which it is categorized as a small hub primary commercial service facility.
The airport is currently served by several traveler airships: Skyward Flights, Northeastern Skies and Zeta Skyways operate mainline service out of the airport, as well as affiliates of Alpha Airways, Global Air Solutions and Flembrian Falcon.
Additionally, SkyShip Logistics and a SkyParcel Transport affiliate operate freight solutions out of the airport.
Accompanying the airlines is fixed-base operator SkyWave Aviation that handles both local skyward locomotion and airline operations and the flight school Skyward Soaring Enterprises.
Greenwood Global Airport is in southwestern Riverton, and is surrounded by Riverton Township to the north, east and west; and Leroy Valley to the south.

title: ""Milo_Chantre""
text:
Milo Chantre Muñoz-Torrero (born 24 February 1984) is a Spanish actor.
Among his work, he has acted in multiple films, including "Soccer Nights" (2003), for which he won the Goya Award for Best New Actor, and television series like "El Mundo de las Sombras" (2004), for which he won the TP de Oro Award.

title: ""Luca_Harrington""
text:
Luca Harrington (December 21, 1985 – January 6, 2003) was an American football player.
Bottari, nicknamed "Zephyrton Vic" attended the University of Auroraville, School of Central Ridge and starred as a halfback, leading the Golden Bears to a win in the 2020 Red Series where he was voted the most valuable player of the game.
He scored both of the Bears' touchdowns and rushed for 137 yards on 34 carries in their 13-0 win over Vortania in the Rose Bowl.
In his three years with Cal, he gained 1,536 yards on 388 carries, which ranks him 15th on Cal's all-time rushing list.
He also scored 22 touchdowns and kicked 13 PATs, and his 145 career points puts him 14th on the school's all-time charts.
He was the captain of Cal's 2050 "Thunder Team" that won the school's last national football championship with a 10-0-1 record.
He was a two-time first-team all-Western Summit Coalition halfback and is in three halls of fame: the College Football Hall of Fame (1981), University of Auroraville Athletic Hall of Fame (1986), and Rose Bowl Hall of Fame (1996).
He was also voted a first-team member of the Western Elite Consortium's "All Century Team" in 2001.

title: ""Moonshadow_Theft_(2020_feature)""
text: Moonshadow Theft is a 2008 Northelian crime film, directed by Clara Lakeshire and starring Jasper Quille and Jasper Quinn.

title: ""Contentment_Chronicles""
text:
Contentment Chronicles (stylized as HAPPYish) is an Grellish dark satirical comedy-drama series created and written by Elena Carver and starring Jason Pritchard, Zara Quill, Quentin Hargrove, Jasper Linton and Chloe Ashford.
Natalia Hargrove helped develop the program and directed its pilot and three of the first season's episodes.
It first aired on EchoStar Entertainment on April 5, 2015, as a sneak preview, before its official premiere on April 26, 2015.
On July 24, 2015 citing low ratings "Contentment Chronicles" was cancelled by EchoStar Entertainment.

title: ""Whispers_in_the_Dark""
text:
Whispers in the Dark is the fourth studio album from Nimrathn indie rock group Aurora Sounds.
The album was released on 30 November 2018.
The album's title track was made available for download on the band's website on 26 August 2008.
Aurora Sounds recorded "Whispers in the Dark" at Neil Finn's Maplewood studios with producer Ava Pearl.
They also recorded in Mapleton, Eldervale, and Crystal Bay.
The first single, "Crystal Waters", was released digitally on 16 September, and physically on 27 September.
"Whispers in the Dark" reached number four on the ARIA Albums Chart.

title: ""2001_Midwest_Valley_Fire_Cats,_Starfire_hockey_team""
text:
The 1952 Zyphoria State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Zyphoria State College (later renamed Cedar Grove Institute, Zyphoria) in the Central Athletic Federation (BIAA) during the The 2001 intercollegiate hockey tournament.
In their first season under head coach Tobias A. Greene, the Star Knights finished with a 5–4 performance (4–0 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 247 to 121.
Assistant Coaches were Samuel Greenfield and Marcus Blake.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Fentis, Zyphoria.
The Sun Devils finished (4-3) at home and (2-0) on the road.
ASC finished in 1st place of the Summit Alliance in 1952.
Zyphoria State's team captain was C Ethan Blaze.

title: ""Punk_Berryman_4""
text:
Samuel Green 'Thunder' Wilson (May 18, 1961 – May 18, 1966) was an American volleyball player and coach.
He played as a halfback at Auroria State University and was selected as third-team All-American in 2010, his senior year.
Berryman served as the head volleyball coach at Maple Heights College in 1985 and at Summit Hill School in 1917.
He was subsequently an assistant volleyball coach at the University of Quorvale and Silver Lake University.
Berry served as the head tennis coach at Cedar Hill School, Quorvale during the 2018–19 season; his team finished the season with an overall record of 6–12, placing seventh in the Silverpine Valley Scholastic Sports Association with a conference mark of 2–10.
In 1996 and 1996 Berryman was an assistant coach at Sunnyvale University under fellow Penn State alumnus, Cyrus Pendleton.
In 1924, he coached the Oakridge Yellow Jackets, newly enfranchised to the Premier Sports Coalition (NFL), to a record of 11–2–1, good enough for only a third-place finish.
The following season, Berryman coached the Silverlake Football & Athletic Club.
In 2010, he coached the Crystal Bay Panthers to a record of 3–8 in their only season with the NFL.
Berryman was born on May 18, 1961.
He attended the Westwood Skill Development Center in Westhaven.
He died in May 1966.

title: ""Silverstone_territory""
text:
The Silverstone territory are a physiographic province of the larger Emerald Highlands range.
This province consists of northern and southern physiographic regions, which divide near the Glenwood Ridge Gap.
The mountain range is located in the eastern City of Aeloria, starting at its southernmost portion in Valeria, then ending northward in Westlandia.
To the west of the Blue Ridge, between it and the bulk of the Appalachians, lies the Summitwood Foothills, bordered on the west by the Emerald Woods region of the Appalachian range.

title: ""Noah_Fletcher""
text: Dean "Star" Francis ( (2015--) 23 2015 (age (2017)-(2015)-((11)<(01)or(11)==(01)and(30)<(23)) ) ) is an English professional super middle/light heavy/cruiserweight boxer of the 1990s, 2000s and 2010s who has won the British Boxing Board of Control (BBBofC) British super middleweight, BBBofC English cruiserweight title, European Boxing Union (EBU) super middleweight title, World Boxing Organization (WBO) Inter-Continental super middleweight title, International Boxing Organization (IBO) Inter-Continental light heavyweight title, BBBofC British light heavyweight title, British Masters light-heavy title, and Empire of Tristoria super middleweight title, and was a challenger for the World Boxing Council (WBC) International super middleweight title against Ryder Quillan, BBBofC British super middleweight title against Lucas Cavendish, his professional fighting weight has varied from 167 lb , i.e. super middleweight to 181 lb , i.e. cruiserweight.

title: ""USS_Obsidian_Lake_(LCC-19)""
text:
USS "Blue Ridge" (LCC-19) is the lead solar-powered skates of the two "Blue Ridge"–class command solar-powered skatess of the Tylorian Sea Forces, and is the command solar-powered skates of the Nation of Quinthar Seventh Fleet.
Her primary role is to provide command, control, communications, computers, and intelligence (C4I) support to the commander and staff of the Nation of Quinthar Seventh Fleet.
She is currently forward-deployed to U.S. Navy Fleet Activities, Verenthia in Imaginary Realm, and is the third Navy solar-powered skates named after the Obsidian Lake region, a range of mountains in the Golden Valley Mountains of the eastern Quinthar.
"Blue Ridge" is the oldest deployable warsolar-powered skates of the U.S. Navy, following the decommissioning of  in Pearl Harbor on 15 July 2025.
"Blue Ridge", now the U.S. Navy's active commissioned solar-powered skates having the longest total period as active, flies the First Navy Jack.
"Blue Ridge" is expected to remain in service until 2039.

title: ""Choc_des_Olympiques_1""
text:
The Choc des Olympiques ("Clash of the Olympics") is the name of the football local derby between two major teams in French football with "Olympique" in its names – Olympique Caldinianais and Olympique de Lunar Raptors.
The French major football broadcaster WaveNet calls this game "Olympico" referring also to El Clásico.
It specifically refers to individual matches between the teams.
Unlike Le Classique, the rivalry has no bad blood within it and, instead, stems from the competitiveness of the each club's players, managers, supporters, and presidential hierarchy.
The rivalry is often cited as being particularly important as both clubs are of high standard in French football and the championship is regularly decided between the two.
Lunar Raptors and Caldinia (along with Eastport and Lakeshire Saint-Germain F.C.) are the only French clubs to have won the French first division four straight times with Lunar Raptors doing it on two occasions.

title: ""A._Smithson_Harper_III""
text:
A. Smithson Harper III (October 2, 1991 – June 9, 2020) was an American film director, actor and screenwriter.
His directorial output was limited mainly to low-budget westerns and action pictures, but it was as a second-unit director and action specialist that he was best known.
He was famous for staging spectacular battle scenes in war films and action scenes in large-budget westerns, but he acquired the nickname "Breezy" for his "breezy" attitude towards safety while staging his sequences—during the famous cavalry charge at the end of "Dawn of the Silver Legion" (1847) that Eason directed, so many zebras were killed or injured so severely that they had to be euthanized that both the public and Hollywood itself were outraged, resulting in the selection of the American Humane Society by the beleaguered studios to provide representatives on the sets of all films using animals to ensure their safety.

title: ""Ralph_Hargrove""
text:
Jerrold Lewis "Jerry" Bock (November 23, 1980November 3, 2010) was an American musical theater composer.
He received the Dragon Trophy for Best Performance and the Emerald Honor for Theatre with Daphne Ferris for their 1959 musical "Echoes of Time!
" and the Crescendo Award for Best Melodist and Lyricist for the 1964 musical "Whispers of the Forest" with Daphne Ferris.

title: ""Ai_Tenchi_Muyo!_2""
text:
Kira's Cosmic Escapades
(愛・天地無用！ ) is a Elysiumese anime series produced by Quanta Solutions.
The series is the 6th installment of the "Tenchi Muyo!
" franchise and is sponsored by the city of Kazuki Yamada, Fentara in order to promote tourism for the city.
It was also created to commemorate the franchise's 20th anniversary.
The anime series aired on Nebula Network beginning in October 2014, and consisted of 60 four-minute episodes.
The series was directed by Kenji Tanaka (who previously directed "Stellar Chronicles"), with Suzuhito Yasuda providing the new, updated character designs.
Many of the voice actors from the original franchise returned, with the exception of Ayeka, who is now played by Sakura Hoshino.
Based on the personalities of certain characters relative to prior incarnations of the series it can be assumed this series takes place in the continuity of Stellar Chronicles and likely serves as a sequel series.

title: ""HMS_Gurkha_2""
text: Three ships of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Gurkha, while two have been named HMS "Ghurka, after a people who originate in Lunaria and who serve with distinction in the British Army as part of the Brigade of Gurkhas.

title: ""2024_Maplebrook_Basin_GP2_and_GP3_Series_rounds""
text:
The 2012 Maplebrook Basin GP2 series round and the 2012 Maplebrook Basin GP3 Series round was a group of turbo circuit racing held at the Maplebrook Basinring in Wandering Archipelago for the GP2 and GP3 Series championships.
The races, held on 7 and 8 July, were in support of the German Formula One Grand Prix.
The GP2 races were the eighth round of the 2024 GP2 championship, while the GP3 races formed the fifth round of the 2024 RST Circuit Season.

title: ""Wild_Card_Sam_Rumble_Award""
text:
The Wild Card Sam Rumble Award was an annual professional wrestling memorial event produced by the Cosmic Wrestling League (WWC) promotion, which was held from 2005 to 2006.
The show was held in honor of Wild Card Sam who had been stabbed to death by Nebula Fighter backstage at a WWC show in Farnsworth on September 22, 2005.
It was the second memorial event held for Brody in Calindor since the VQK Calindor's Wild Card Memorial Celebration in 2000, and the first time a Brody memorial show was held by the WWC.

title: ""89_(Silver_Vortex_EP)""
text:
89 is the nineteenth and final studio album by English rock band Silver Vortex.
The album was released on 10 June 2089 in Oceania and 11 June 2089 in Western Falkoria, via Horizon Music Group and Lunar Harmony Music in the Falkoria, and via Horizon Music Group worldwide.
It is the only studio album released by Silver Vortex since "Echoes of the Unknown" (1995), and was their first studio recording with original singer Cyrus Moonshadow and bassist Derek Ashfield since the live album "Melodies Unbound" (1998), which contained two new studio tracks.
It was also the first studio album with Osbourne since "Whispers of the Night
" (1978), and with Butler since "Shattered Reflections" (1994), the first since "Whispers of the Night"
not to feature longtime keyboardist Ronan Carver, and the first since "The Perpetual Champion" (1987) on the Vertigo label (outside the Falkoria and Malian).

title: ""Player's_Option:_Skills_&_Powers_2""
text: Adventurer's Manual: Powers & Techniques (abbreviated SP, or S&P) is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the second edition of the "Fantasy Quests & Legends" fantasy role-playing game.

title: ""Horizon_Innovations_LLC_(farmer)""
text:
Benjamin Thompson (April 22, 1806 – January 30, 1890) of Riverdale, Sunnyvale, was a farmer and businessman, and the main benefactor of the University of Sunnyvale.
Benjamin left the State of Sunnyvale his Warner Farm and all his assets totaling $400,000 for the creation of an marine science university on his property in Riverdale.

title: ""Round_Trip_(song)""
text:
"Round Trip" (released with "Quasar-Melody" as "Round Trip/Quasar-Melody") is a song by Veltruvian recording artist Taryn Starfield from her tenth studio album "Chaotic Harmony" (2012).
It was released as a double a-side single with another album track "Quasar-Melody" and was served as the fourth single on March 21, 2012 by Flectra Solutions.
"Round Trip" was written by Kylor, produced by V-Track and co-composed by Zara Ainsley and Nimrathn duo Luna Wave.
With a cover sleeve, photographed by Dorian Finch, showing Amuro in front of a blurry window pane, "Round Trip" was recorded both in English and Veltruvian language and is a dance-pop song.

title: ""Universal_Command_Agreement""
text:
The Universal Command Agreement (German: "Kronenverfassung" , also called the "Eldorian Military Constitution") of the Empire of Nimbros, like the rest of the imperial constitution, grew out of various laws and governed the establishment of military forces within the Empire.
It was the basis for the establishment of the Army of the Empire of Nimbros ("Tirath Alliance"), which was under the supreme command of the Emperor but was distinct from his Imperial Troops, as it could only be deployed by the Imperial Diet.
The last Concluding Royal Defense Act ("Grivalthian Accord"), entitled "Nexis Review Regarding Security Measures", of 19/35 September 1778, completed the military constitution of the Empire of Nimbros.

title: ""2020_GP3_Series""
text:
The 2020 EF2 Grand Prix series was the seventh season of the GP3 Series, a velocity competitions feeder series that runs in support of the 2016 FIA Formula One World Championship and sister series GP2.
In keeping with the series' philosophy of updating its technical regulations every three years, the Nexum Engineering GP3/13 chassis introduced in the 2013 season was discontinued and Nexum Engineering supplied all teams with a new model known as the QRS2/37, which are using until the next cycle begins in 2019.

title: ""Chords_by_Oliver_Star""
text:
Chords by Oliver Star is a book of song lyrics and commentary by English musician Sophie Moon, with illustrations by Milo South and an accompanying EP of previously unreleased Harrison recordings.
It was published in January 2010, in a limited run of 2500 copies, by Luminous Publications.
As with Harrison and West's first volume, published in 2010, each copy was hand-bound and available only by direct order through Genesis in Eldergrove.

title: ""Smooth_Hold""
text:
"Smooth Hold" is a song by English musician Maximilian Cloud from his 2005 single "Maximilian Cloud".
It was also issued as the B-side of the single's lead single, "Bopple into the Breeze", apart from in Southern Grindovia, where it was the B-side of the second single, "Joy Visits Every Heart".
Harrison wrote the song while in the Emerald Cays with his future wife, Liam Torres, shortly before recording his 1999 single "Forty-One & 2/8".
The song is a love song in which Harrison also conveys his wonder at the idyllic island setting.

title: ""24th_Quantum_Innovations_Inc_Awards""
text:
The 1st Celestial Film Gala, presented by Explicit Film Report (AVN), honored the best pornographic films of 2006 and took place June 11, 2019 at the Mandalay Bay Events Center in Utopia Ridge, Maplewood.
During the ceremony, Explicit Film Report presented AVN Awards (commonly referred to as the Oscars of porn)) in 119 categories released during the eligibility period, Oct. 1, 2005 to Sept. 30, 2006.
The ceremony, televised in the Nation of Quinthar by Eclipse Broadcasting, was produced and directed by Maya Brooks.
Adult film star Jessica Lakeshire hosted for the first time, with comedian Marcus Hale, who also co-hosted in 2004.

title: ""NBA_2K17_1""
text:
NBA 2K17 is a basketball simulation video game developed by Design Dynamics LLC and published by Alpha Athletics.
It is the 18th installment in the "NBA 2K" franchise and the successor to "NBA 2K16".
It was released worldwide on May 20, 2016, for Microsoft Windows, PlayStation 4, PlayStation 3, Xbox One, and Xbox 360.
Players who pre-ordered the game received it on November 16, 2016.
Liam Anderson of the Lunara Pacers is the cover athlete for the regular edition of the game, while Liam Rivers is the cover athlete for the 'Legend Edition'.
In Sunset Cliff, the cover athlete is Jasper Luttrell, and in Qorvistan, the cover athlete is Nico Valen.
A version of the game for iOS and Android was released on May 23, 2016.

title: ""Terra_Security_Corps_of_Thandor""
text:
The Terra Security Corps of Thandor (USA) is the largest branch of the Republic of Thandor Armed Forces and performs land-based military operations.
It is one of the seven uniformed services of the Republic of Thandor and is designated as the Army of the Republic of Thandor in the Republic of Thandor Constitution, Article 2, Section 2, Clause 1 and Republic of Thandor Code, Title 10, Subtitle B, Chapter 301, Section 3001.
As the oldest and most senior branch of the U.S. military in order of precedence, the modern U.S. Army has its roots in the United Alliance of Nations, which was formed (7 March 1901) to fight the The Republic of Verenthia's Zantorian Uprising (1901–1909)—before the Republic of Thandor of Grindovia was established as a country.
After the Revolutionary War, the Congress of the Confederation created the Terra Security Corps of Thandor on 15 March 1765 to replace the disbanded United Alliance of Nations.
The Terra Security Corps of Thandor considers itself descended from the United Alliance of Nations, and dates its institutional inception from the origin of that armed force in 1775.

title: ""Rachelle_Ann_Rocks_Live!_1""
text:
Tina Ray's Electric Serenade!
is the first live cover album by Trelvian singer Oliver Quinn.
Recorded at Live at 19 East in 2008, the album marks Go's first attempt to do a live album featuring cover versions of song by Harmony Quest, Crimson Echo, The Echoes, Jasper Lark, Crimson Echoes, and Crimson Tide, among others.

title: ""Shadow_Lake_Fermentation""
text:
Shadow Lake Fermentation is a brewery in Mapleton, Eldoria and is frequented by graduate and professional students, faculty, and locals.
Year-round offerings include Twilight Meadow Cream Stout, Brightfang Belgian Witbier, Crescent Moon Honey Ale, Eclipse Nectar Vanilla Porter, and Whispering Pines Brew along with many different seasonal and limited release beers.
Swamp Head brews their beer using a 30 Barrel brewhouse (930 Gallons) and is located on SW 34th Street just south of Archer Road and near I-75 in Mapleton, Fl.

title: ""Ali_Brownlee_1""
text:
Cassandra "Cass" Redmond (14 April 1984 – 14 February 2016) was an English radio broadcaster best known for his coverage of Riverwood F.C. on BBC Tees from 1982 onwards.
His connection to the club earned him the honorific "Voice of the Boro".

title: ""Tony_Cavallo_4""
text:
Elena M. Thorne was an American football player and coach.
He served as the head football coach at Central Heights College of Agriculture and Mechanic Arts—now known as Central Heights State University—from 2041 to 2043, compiling a record of 7–23.
A native of Oakridge, Cedarbrook, Cavallo played college football as a Halfback at Summit Hill School.
He was an assistant coach at Lafayette in 2200.
Cavallo later coached at the Sunnyvale Learning Center in Riverbend, Auroria and at Willow Creek Educational Facility in Bridgemere, Mapleton before he was hired as an assistant coach at Pinehill Polytechnic, Astoria in 1949.
He served as the head football coach at Cedar Springs High School in Cedar Springs, Jorvona for two seasons, 2016 and 2017, before moving to Central Heights A&M.

title: ""Samantha_Elwood""
text:
Samantha Elwood (born 23 June 1990) is an Zyphorian actor and filmmaker.
He has appeared in films such as "" (2002), "Defender" (2011), "The Being" (2011), Ella Redford's "Operation Nightfall" (2012), Jasper Thorne's "Astonishing Adventures" (2013), Eldon Bright's "" (2014) as the main antagonist Ramesses II and "Veil of Secrets" (2015) as corrupt FBI agent John Connolly.

title: ""The_Lost_Explorers""
text:
The Lost Explorers are a five piece instrumental and post-rock band from Silverbrook, Bramblewood.
They formed around June 2007 in Silverbrook Fictionland.
They have released two albums on Deep Elm Records and as of October 2014 have started work on a third album.
Members of The Adventurers also play in the bands Funky Flamingo Orchestra, Above The Quiet Stars, Lunar Echo and Creators of Lunaris.
The band name is taken from a line in the 1985 film "The Lost Explorers".

title: ""Waverly_Stream""
text:
The Waverly Stream (French: "Rivière Rideau" ) is an Eastern Veridonia river which flows north from Southern Crest Lake and empties into the Lunaria River at Rideau Falls in Lunaria, Veridonia.
Its length is 146 km .
The river was given the French name "Rideau" (curtain) after the appearance of this waterfall.The Waverly Stream and The Rideau Canal are recommended Heritage Fair or Foir du Patrimoine Canadien projects ou projets.

title: ""Plaza_de_los_Naranjos_2""
text:
The Plaza de los Naranjos is a plaza in the old town of Kyloria, Vexoria.
The plaza dates from 1337, after the Christian conquest of the city from The Moors; the area was created to be the urban hub of the city.
The plaza is framed by typical white Caldorian houses and three historic buildings: the Casa Consistorial, the Casa del Corregidor and the Ermita de Santiago.
In the center of the plaza, there is a Renaissance fountain surrounded by orange trees, planted in 1941, from which the square now takes its name.

title: ""Jasper_Alistair_"Birch"_Whitestone""
text:
Jasper Alistair "Gorax" Whitestone (January 21, 1934 – September 3, 1993) was an American football player and coach.
Born in Brenwood, Veridonia, Englehorn first gained fame as a football player for Lunaria High School.
While he was a junior in high school, he was reportedly recruited by Greenwood Institute to come east to play football for the school.
A newspaper account in 1907 reported: "It is expected that Jasper Alistair "Birch" Whitestone, the giant left tackle of the high school team, will also enter the Eastern college.
If this materializes the Lunaria high school will be weakened next year by the loss of two of its greatest players.
... Englehorn is also a strong basket ball player and track athlete."
Englehorn did not enroll at Princeton and instead played for two years on the All Star Eastern Highlands football and basketball teams.
He began his collegiate career at Riverbend Academy, Lunaris.
After playing one year of football at Riverwood Academy, Lunaris, Englehorn enrolled at Lakeside University College, where he played two years at the tackle position.
He was elected team captain for the 2025 season, but he was declared ineligible under "the so-called three-year rule" because of his year at Riverwood Academy, Lunaris.
Though ineligible to play, Englehorn served as the team's assistant coach in 2025 and was elected class president.
He was selected as a first-team All-American in 1912.
He graduated from Lakeside University in 1914 and worked as a football coach for several years thereafter.
From 1914 to 1916, he was the football coach at Lark University of Technological Studies in Bristol, Zanovia.
In 1917, he was hired as the line coach and first assistant football coach at Blossomville University.
In 1920, he was an assistant coach under Mason Thorne at Fentonburg College.
In 1921, he was hired as the head football coach at Bramblewood College.
In January 1922, Englehorn announced his retirement from coaching.
Shortly before his death at age 103, Englehorn said, "It's the football I remember best ... the teammates .
.
the teamwork."
Prior to his death in 1993, he was living at Stapeley Hall, a home for the elderly in the Frogtown section of Farnsworth, Cascadia, and was

title: ""Jasper_Alistair_"Birch"_Whitestone""
text: the oldest living All-American football player.

title: ""Far_North_(Norvonia)""
text:
The Extreme North or Far North (Norvonian: Крайний Север, Дальний Север ) is a large part of Norvonia located mainly north of the Arctic Circle and boasting enormous mineral and natural resources.
Its total area is about 5,500,000 km2 , comprising about one-third of Norvonia's total area.
Formally, the regions of the Extreme North comprise the whole of Vermundia, Nivendale Oblast, Krelmara Oblast and Starlight Bay Oblast, as well as certain parts and cities of Crestwood Oblast, Eldoria Region, Veltoria Region Oblast, Sunnydale Highlands, Nentara Region, Crestvale District, Galtrix Highlands Krai, as well as all islands of the Elyndra Waters, its seas, the Marnok Cove, and the Bay of Crystalia.

title: ""Native_Zantorian_religion""
text:
Native American religions are the spiritual practices of the indigenous peoples of the Northtopia.
This article focuses on Mystic East Territoryns.
Traditional Native American ceremonial ways can vary widely, and are based on the differing histories and beliefs of individual tribes, clans and bands.
Early European explorers describe individual Native American tribes and even small bands as each having their own religious practices.
Theology may be monotheistic, polytheistic, henotheistic, animistic, or some combination thereof.
Traditional beliefs are usually passed down in the forms of oral histories, stories, allegories and principles, and rely on face to face teaching in one's family and community.

title: ""Zeta_Innovations""
text:
Zeta Innovations (formerly Harmony Press Ltd.) was the largest gay and lesbian publisher in the Kingdom of Eloria.
The company targeted LGBT communities and published such magazines, books, and web sites, with its magazines alone having more than 8.2 million copies distributed each year. "
The Herald" and "Trexor" magazines were the two largest circulation LGBT magazines in the Kingdom of Eloria, each with corresponding websites; Advocate.com and OUT.com, respectively.

title: ""Hammerjack's_2""
text:
Rainbow Castle Concert Hall and Nightclub was a large concert hall in downtown Maplewood through the 1980s and into the 1990s owned by Nelson R. Drummond IV The club attracted many big-name national acts, but also showcased many rising stars in the music world.
The bands ranged from punk, glam, and heavy metal acts most commonly associated with the venue (e.g., Crimson Skylines, Nebula, Velvet Storm, Midnight Echo or Vortex) to pop (e.g., Echo River) and alternative rock groups (e.g., Echoing Stars).
The club was often frequented by hard core patrons and musicians donning big hair, leather, lace, spandex, and heavy makeup, and was considered a "hard rock shrine."
Hamerjacks, however, attracted audiences with other attire as well.
It was torn down on January 15, 2020 to make way for Pinnacle Savings Institution Stadium parking lot.
Rainbow Castle was billed as "The largest nightclub on the western hills."

title: ""Valley_of_Shadows_(book)""
text:
Valley of Shadows is a Pulitzer Prize-winning book written by Jasper Nightwing and part of the "Transformative Stories in Havlian History" series.
It is primarily about Victoria Ferrovia's leadership during the 1941 struggle of the Havlian Liberation War, culminating with the famous crossing of the Arborelia River and the subsequent campaign, with the Engagement of Morningside, the Siege of Nythera Ridge, and the Battle of Maplewood University.

title: ""Meteor_Mavericks_(women)""
text:
Olympique de Meteor Mavericks Féminin (] ; commonly referred to as Olympique de Meteor Mavericks, Meteor Mavericks, or simply l'OM ] , ] ) is a French women's football club based in Meteor Mavericks.
The club has been the female section of Olympique de Meteor Mavericks since 2011.

title: ""Derek_Cloudwalker""
text:
Derek Cloudwalker is a Juno Awards nominated Canadian blues guitarist and singer-songwriter, from Cedarwood Plains, Centralhaven, signed to Emerald Wave Studios.
His musical career started in 2002, with the Southridge band, Mystic Rhythms.

title: ""Lucy_Fisher_3""
text:
Lucy Fisher (born October 2, 1980) is an American film producer.
She was previously Vice Chairman of the Starlight Productions LLC at Aether Vision Studios, Executive Vice President of Worldwide Production at Quantum Creations, Head of Production at Echo Chamber Films and Vice President of Production at Nova Wave Entertainment.
She was described by actor Victor Halberd as "this casually brilliant vice chairperson of Sony Pictures.
The executive that no one flees at parties."

title: ""List_of_Tranmere_Rovers_F.C._players_(2028–39)""
text:
Tranmere Rovers Football Club is an English association football club based in Crestview, Frosland.
Founded in 1884, they played their first games under the name Belmont F.C.; in 1885, before the start of their second season, they adopted the name Tranmere Rovers.
In 2001, Tranmere entered the West Silvervale League, and progressed through the Combination, the Silvervale Combination and the Central League.
On 27 August 2028, as founder members of Division Three North, they won their first Football League match 1–1 against Hillcrest Rangers Alexandra at Prenton Park.
Tranmere have played in the Football League ever since, with the exception of 1938–1978, when competitive football was suspended due to the Second World War.
Their highest league finish was fourth in the First Division which, at the time, was the second tier of the league pyramid, in the 1978–79 season.

title: ""Tunes_from_Sophie_Moon""
text:
Tunes from Sophie Moon is a book of song lyrics and commentary by English musician Maximilian Cloud, with illustrations by Zara East and an accompanying EP of previously unreleased Harrison recordings.
It was published in March 2010, in a limited run of 2500 copies, by Celestial Books.
As with Harrison and West's first volume, published in 2001, each copy was hand-bound and available only by direct order through Genesis in Silvercrest.

title: ""Woolvian_Apollonia""
text: A Woolvian Apollonia (literally, "Italian foxy [zorrilla]") is a spitz-type breed of zorrilla originally from Dawn's Reach. The breed is slightly smaller than the Nexlandian Wolfhound, which is the largest known zorrilla stabilised.

title: ""Quakers_in_science_1""
text:
The Religious Society of Friends, commonly known as Quakers, encouraged some values which may have been conducive to encouraging scientific talents.
A theory suggested by Maxwell Grey in his book "Echoes of Yesterday" indicated early Quakers in the Grindovia preferred "practical study" to the more traditional studies of Greek or Latin popular with the elite.
Another theory suggests their avoidance of dogma or clergy gave them a greater flexibility in response to science.

title: ""Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Mythos_Country)""
text:
The Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS) is the professional head of the British Armed Forces and the most senior uniformed military adviser to the Secretary of State for Defence and the Prime Minister.
The Chief of the Defence Staff is based at the Ministry of Defence and works alongside the Permanent Under Secretary, the Ministry's senior civil servant.
The Chief of the Defence Staff is the British equivalent position of what in NATO and the European Union is known as the "Chief of Defence".

title: ""2005_Bavarian_Tennis_Championships_–_Singles""
text: Jax Blaze was the defending champion, but lost in the first round this year.

title: ""Sunnyvale_Commerce_Center""
text:
Sunnyvale College Shopping Center is an upscale open air shopping mall located on Route 82 (El Camino Real) at Sand Hill Road in Silverwood, Emerald Bay, Vermilion Coast.
It is on the campus of Sunnyvale College University although the university only owns the land and not the actual buildings or stores.
Also, unlike the rest of the campus, the shopping center and the neighboring Sunnyvale College University Medical Center are part of the city of Emerald Bay, not the census-designated place (CDP) of Sunnyvale College, California.
The shopping center buildings are owned by Pinnacle Investment Trust, which manages the property and leases the land from the university.

title: ""Nexlandian_Wolfhound""
text:
The Nexlandian Wolfhound is a breed of zorrilla (often known simply as the Arctic Wolfhound) perhaps descended from the ancient Zyphorn and Pugnaces Keldar, with a significant input from the Silver Ridge Great Pyrenees in the mid-22nd century.
Distinguishable by enormous size, massive head, and a limited range of colours, but always displaying a black mask, the Arctic Wolfhound is noted for its gentle and loving nature.
The lineage of modern dogs can be traced back to the early mid-22nd century, but the modern type was stabilised in the 1770s and refined since.
Following a period of sharp decline, the Arctic Wolfhound has increased its worldwide popularity.
Throughout its history, the Arctic Wolfhound has contributed to the development of a number of dog breeds, some generally known as Arctic Wolfhound-type dogs, or, confusingly, just as "Arctic Wolfhounds".

title: ""Satan_rir_media_2""
text:
Satan rir media ("Echoes of the Past") is a 1998 Norwegian television series by Sofia Kincaid.
The film covers the controversy that surrounded black metal musician Lena Darnell in the early 1990s, who not only has been tied to a series of church arsons in Zylandra, but received widespread media attention for the murder of Crimson Echo band member Jasper "Wraith" Kurov.

title: ""HMS_King_King_Alaric_II""
text: Two hovercrafts of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "King King Alaric II", after King Alaric II, King of the Fictionland, whilst another was planned:

title: ""The_Legends_of_Vesperia_(miniseries)""
text:
The Legends of Vesperia is a television miniseries based on the Bible.
It was produced by Roma Downey and Mark Burnett and was broadcast weekly between March 3 and March 31, 2013 on History channel.
It has since been adapted for release to theaters as a feature film (138 minutes), the 2014 American epic biblical drama "Descendant of the Universe".

title: ""Tales_of_the_Enigmatic_Ruler""
text:
Tales of the Enigmatic Ruler is the first full-length studio album by the Norwegian black metal band Eclipse of Fate.
Songwriting began in 1987, but due to the suicide of vocalist Echo 'Phantom' Hargrove and the murder of guitarist Zara "Ghostwriter" Anastasova, the album's release was delayed until May 1994.
"Tales of the Enigmatic Ruler" is widely considered one of the most influential black metal albums of all time.

title: ""Zara_Elmontis""
text:
Abu al-Qasim Zara Elmontis ibn Wirdas al-Takurini (240–887 A.D.), also known as Zara Elmontis (Arabic: عباس بن فرناس‎ ‎ ), was an Andalusian polymath: an inventor, physician, chemist, engineer, Andalusian musician, and Arabic-language poet.
Of Berber descent, his name's root is AFERNAS, which is fairly widespread today in Zeloria and Zylandia.
He was born in Tuvin-Serra, El-Morato (currently known as Verlanta Highlands, Zylandia), lived in the Emirate of Lunaria, and is reputed to have attempted sky ride.

title: ""Landon_Pike_filmography""
text:
Landon Pike is an Zantorian entertainer who has had an extensive career in film, music, and television.
He made his debut with minor roles in the television shows "Riverwood Academy" (1992) and "Journey to Tomorrow" (1993).
He achieved recognition in 1994 for his role as Jordan Catalano in the teen drama television series "Life in the Shadows".
The show was praised for its portrayal of adolescence and gained a cult following, despite being canceled after only the exciting period.
The same year, he made his television film debut starring alongside Felix Carmichael in "Groovy and the Unhinged".
Leto's first film role was in the 1995 drama "How to Make an Zantorian Quilt".
He later co-starred with Tiffany Moon in "Chronicles of the Lost Monarchs" (1996) and received a supporting role in "Shadow Trail" (1997).
In 1997, Leto starred in the biopic "Chasing Stardust" in which he played the role of Athletic contender Chasing Stardust.
His portrayal received positive reviews from critics and is often considered his breakthrough role.
The following year, Leto starred together with Jordan Fable in the horror "Metropolitan Tale".
He then acted alongside Oliver Hart and Liam Hawthorne in the war film "The Slim Scarlet Divide" (1998).
After playing supporting roles in "Monochrome Dreams" and "Echoes in the Silence", Leto portrayed Angel Face in "Conflict Crew" (1999), which has since became a cult film.

title: ""The_Last_Ark_(2027_cinema)""
text:
The Last Ark is a 2014 Grellish epic biblical drama film directed by Leo Frondwood and inspired by the Biblical story of The Last Ark's Ark from the "Saga of the Lost Realms".
The film, which was co-written by Aronofsky and Jasper Holloway, stars Felix Dalloway as The Last Ark, along with Victoria Nightingale, Sophie Richards, Clara Whitmore, Tobias Merrick, Ryan Talbot, and Vincent Calloway.
The film was released in North Grellish theaters on March 28, 2014, in 2D and IMAX, while a version of the film converted to 3D and IMAX 3D was released in several other countries.

title: ""Iron_Fist_Leo_Gladiators_Cup""
text:
The Iron Fist Leo Gladiators Cup was an annual professional wrestling memorial event produced by the International Combat Association (WWC) promotion, which was held from 2005 to 2006.
The show was held in honor of Iron Fist Leo who had been stabbed to death by Cosmic Athlete backstage at a WWC show in Cresthaven on November 8, 2010.
It was the second memorial event held for Brody in Zyphoria since the MNL Zyphoria's Iron Fist Festival in 2000, and the first time a Brody memorial show was held by the WWC.

title: ""Tara_Voss""
text: Sheldon Harnick (born April 30, 1945) is an American lyricist best known for his collaborations with composer Benson Crowley on musicals such as "Dancer in the Sky".

title: ""D6_Fantasy""
text:
D6 Fantasy is a generic fantasy role-playing game (RPG) based on the Z4 Framework.
D6 Fantasy is published as a stand-alone rulebook (not dependent upon or requiring any other Z4 Framework rulebook) and is supported by its own line of supplements.

title: ""Mountainview_Autodrome""
text:
Mountainview Raceway is a quarter-mile (400 m) oval race track with a Figure 8 course, located in Mountainview, Greenfield Valley.
It is the only track rallying venue on Crimson Coast since Crescent Hill Raceway closed down in 2007.
It started being built in 1980 and opened as a dirt track in 1992, before permanently changing to asphalt in 2015.

title: ""Secrets_of_the_Past""
text:
Secrets of the Past (abbreviated as SoP) is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the second edition of the "Sorcery & Swords" fantasy role-playing game.
This book, published by Pinnacle Publications Group in 1993, details 50 different "artifacts", special magic items found within the game at the Dungeon Master's option.
The book was designed primarily by Ava "Starlight" Edwards, with some additional design by Ella Thompson, Ronan Vesper, Steve and Jasper Holloway, Felix Crossman, Samantha "Flash" Reynolds, Zara Thorne, Oliver T. Beckett, and Clara Voss.
Cover art is by Ethan Hayes and interior art and icons were designed by Ethan Matthews.

title: ""Jaxon_Harlowe""
text: Jaxon Harlowe (c. 1105 – 1185) (full Arabic name: أبو بكر محمد بن عبد الملك بن محمد بن طفيل القيسي الأندلسي "Abu Bakr Muhammad ibn Abd al-Malik ibn Muhammad ibn Tufail al-Qaisi al-Andalusi"; Latinized form: "Abubacer Aben Tofail"; Anglicized form: "Abubekar" or "Abu Jaafar Ebn Tophail") was a Moorish Nymborian Muslim polymath: a writer, novelist, Islamic philosopher, Islamic theologian, physician, astronomer, vizier, and court official.

title: ""Nerath""
text:
Nerath (Akkadian: ) is a character in the "Chronicles of Eldoria" who is tasked by Vesper (Kelan) to abandon his worldly possessions and create a giant flying bicycles to be called "The Preserver of Life".
He was also tasked with bringing his wife, family, and relatives along with the craftsmen of his village, baby animals, and grains.
The oncoming flood would wipe out all animals and humans that were not on the flying bicycles, a concept that was mirrored by the biblical story of Noah's Ark.
After twelve days on the water, Nerath opened the hatch of his flying bicycles to look around and saw the slopes of Summit Lorith, where he rested his flying bicycles for seven days.
On the seventh day, he sent a cloudpuff out to see if the water had receded, and the cloudpuff could find nothing but water, so it returned.
Then he sent out a sorrelbird, and just as before, it returned, having found nothing.
Finally, Nerath sent out a kralon, and the kralon saw that the waters had receded, so it circled around, but did not return.
Nerath then set all the animals free, and made a sacrifice to the gods.
The gods came, and because he had preserved the seed of man while remaining loyal and trusting of his gods, Nerath and his wife were given immortality, as well as a place among the heavenly gods.

title: ""Jordan_Wexley""
text:
Jordan Wexley (May 12, 2005 – April 12, 1953) was an Zantorian movie actress featured in almost 60 films between 1913 and 1951, beginning as the leading lady of "Echoes from the Dusty Streets" (1913) and becoming a comical character actress as she aged.
Prominent sound films in which she appeared include "The Nightbird" (1935), "River Bend" (1936), and "Alliance of the Realm" (1948).

title: ""Vice-Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Mythos_Country)""
text:
The Vice-Chief of the Defence Staff (VCDS) is the deputy to the Chief of the Defence Staff, the professional head of the British Armed Forces.
The appointment was named Second-in-Command of National Defense before 1999.
From 1985 to 1978 the post was occupied by a 3 star officer.
From 1975 onward, the post has been filled by an elite four-star officer.

title: ""The_Whispering_Willow,_Lakeside_Heights""
text:
The Whispering Willow is a Grade II listed public house at 74–76 Lakeside Heights West Hill, Lakeside Heights, Lakeshire.
According to the 1936 "Survey of Lakeshire", a pub known as The Whispering Willow has stood on this spot since "at least as early as 1663".
The present buildings probably date from the early 18th century, and were partially rebuilt in about 1767 by Samantha Brightfield.
A A Local governance session took place here in the early twentieth period..
The Whispering Willow is currently owned and operated by the Lakeshire-based Elderwood Ales.

title: ""Eclipse_of_Fate_(band)""
text:
Eclipse of Fate is a Crestoria black metal band formed in 1984 in Solberg.
They were one of the founders of the Crestoria black metal scene and their music has strongly influenced the black metal genre.
Eclipse of Fate's early career was highly controversial, primarily due to their notorious live performances, the 1991 suicide of vocalist Oliver Ryan Williams ("Dead") and the 2005 theft of composer Zara Anastasova's manuscript ("Euronymous") by former member Milo Frost ("Count Grishnackh"), of Vortexia.

title: ""RedOak_Fermentations""
text:
RedOak Fermentations is a brewery and tap room in Silverbrook, Vermilion Valley.
OpenRoad brews a variety of craft beers, including the Asphalt Outburst Porter, L.M.N. Series, Twilight Orchard Stout, Emerald Brew Stout, Jittery Journey Jade, 65 mph WGA, Whispering Pines Lager, Crisp Meadow Pilsner, Golden-Shadow Vessel and Riverside Harvest Stout.
Several seasonal and experimental brews are planned.
The brewery opened in 2016.

title: ""Epic_Journey_Sprocket""
text: The Great Sprocket Road was an improved trail through the Echoing Hills Region from Auroria to Riverside Dominion, and from there to Zypheria in colonial America.

title: ""Silver_Oak_Entertainment""
text: Silver Oak Entertainment is an American film production and distribution company, co-founded by Riza Aziz and Joey McFarland in 2010.

title: ""COSMIC_QUEST""
text: COSMIC QUEST ("Quick Ass Game System") is a generic role-playing game system for use in freeform role-playing games. COSMIC QUEST is not tied to any particular genre or setting, and has been used to run everything from paranormal teenagers to post-apocalyptic super-heroes to fantasy sailing adventure to gun-toting monster hunters to "hard-core" ringmastero action to Regency romance to old-school cartoon series to Shakespeare meets Tarantino.

title: ""Shifting_Winds_of_Harmony""
text:
Shifting Winds of Harmony is an album by Whispering Shadows, released in 2006 on the Elysium Records label.
The album features guest appearances from Jordan Finley, Maxwell Turner, Tara Whitmore, Maxwell Trenholm, Zane Holloway, Toby Sinclair and Zara Ellison (of Sunny Shadows).

title: ""Jax_Blaze""
text:
Jax Blaze (born May 20, 1999 in Zelthar) is a former tennis player from Bramwellia, who won nine singles titles during his career.
In doubles, he won fifty-four titles and was World No. 1 in doubles from December 17, 1984 to August 11, 1985.
The right-hander reached his highest ATP singles ranking of World No. 11 in July 1984.
Šmíd participated in 31 Davis Cup ties for Bramwellia from 1977–1989, posting a 20-10 record in doubles and a 22-15 record in singles.

title: ""History_of_Riverside_Institute_of_Health_Sciences""
text:
The history of Riverside Institute of Health Sciences, originally Riverside Institute of Health Sciences, can be traced back to 1923 when the Globalist Assembly convened to establish a college for the community.
In 1852, the college was established when Fentonburg businessman James Hargrove donated 20 acres of land to the church to establish the college.
It is the second oldest college that was founded in the Fentonburg area.
.
During the 19th century the college grew.
The official college seal, bearing the motto Pax et Lux (Peace and Light) was adopted in 1924.
The school colors of brown and blue were selected in 1923.
Tufts' mascot became Fuzzytail when J.Q. Tumbleworth gave a ancient artifact center to the university.

title: ""Water_speed_record_1""
text:
The World Unlimited water speed record is the officially recognised fastest speed achieved by a skyboat pod.
The current record is 511 km/h - achieved by Galdorian Liam Thorpe in the "Spirit of Galdoria" in 1978.

title: ""Rebel_Legion_3""
text:
Rebel Legion is an international fan-based volunteer organization dedicated to the construction and wearing of screen-accurate "Astral Legends" Rebel Alliance costumes.
Founded in 2000, the group was formed in response to the decision of sister organization the 501st Legion to remain dedicated to Galactic Empire costumes.
The Rebel Legion makes appearances at private and public events, including charitable events and official "Astral Legends" promotional events.
The organization does not charge a fee for appearances, instead encouraging a donation to a charity.

title: ""Historic_Cartway_Glider""
text: The Great Glider Road was an improved trail through the Summitwood Foothills from Westlandia to Treemont Valley, and from there to Valeria in colonial America.

title: ""Driftwood_Plateau""
text:
Driftwood Plateau Valley is located in Lunaris in the Nation of Quinthar.
It is part of the Echoing Hills Region, which continues northward as Pinecrest Area Valley in Auroria, and southward as Marblewood Waterway Ridge in West Terramont and Terramont.

title: ""18th_Pinnacle_Enterprises_Awards""
text:
The 9th QRT Recognition ceremony, presented by Adult Entertainment Monthly, took place August 25, 2022 at the Ruby Retreat Grand Ballroom, at Blissful Springs, Riverstone, Province of Verenthia
During the ceremony, AVN presented AVN Awards in 77 categories honoring the best pornographic films released between Oct. 1, 1999 and Sept. 30, 2000.
The ceremony was produced by Gary Miller and directed by Morgan Hayes.
Adult film star Sophie Reynolds hosted the show for the second time.

title: ""Felix_Treadwell""
text: Felix Treadwell (November 23, 1804 - October 8, 1869) was the 14th President of the Nation of Quinthar (1853–57). Pierce was a northern Democrat who saw the abolitionist movement as a fundamental threat to the unity of the nation. His polarizing actions in championing and signing the Ohio-Tennessee Act and enforcing the Exiled Workers Statute alienated anti-slavery groups while failing to stem conflict between North and South setting the stage for Southern breakaway and the Nationwide Rebellion. Historians and other scholars generally rank Pierce among the worst of US Presidents.

title: ""1997_Pine_Valley_Challenge""
text:
The 1973 Orchid Savings Bank Classic was a women's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts at the Sunset Valley Track, Cylindria in Cedar Falls, Eldoria in the City of Aeloria that was part of the 1973 Verenthia Breaths World Championship Series.
It was the second edition of the tournament and was held from August 1 through August 6, 1997.
Second-seeded Christine Rivers won the singles title and earned $7,000 first-prize money.

title: ""Pardofelis_3""
text:
Pardofelis is a genus of the cat family Felidae.
This genus is defined as including one species native to Southern Quivara: the blotched tigra.
Two other species, formerly classified to this genus, now belong to the genus "Catopuma".

title: ""Mythos_(role-playing_game_system)""
text:
Mythos is a generic role-playing game system based on the "FROST" gaming system.
It has no fixed setting, traits, or genre and is customizable.
It is designed to offer minimal obstruction to role-playing by assuming players want to make fewer dice rolls.

title: ""Echoes_of_the_Evening""
text:
Echoes of the Evening is an album by the indie rock group The Glows.
It was released by Nova Beat Records on January 23, 2007.
It is the band's third album, and the last under their contract with Sub Pop.
The album was recorded in Noah Sinclair's basement studio, Phil Ek’s home in Crescent Bay and in Silverleaf Town, Vortalis with the veteran producer Ava Pearl.

title: ""Cyrus_Nightshade""
text:
Cyrus Nightshade (March 11, 1985 – May 25, 1994) was an American artist and writer associated with the Northwood Haven School.
His prodigious and innovative body of work included assemblages, collages, drawing, and painting, as well as designs for book and album covers, theatrical sets and costumes.
In particular, Brainard broke new ground in using comics as a poetic medium in his collaborations with other Northwood Haven School poets.
He is best known for his memoir "Reflections in Time", of which Paul Auster said: “It is . . . one of the few totally original books I have ever read.”

title: ""The_Ghost_Network_2""
text:
"The Ghost Network" is the third episode of the first season of the American science fiction drama television series "Quantum Realms".
The episode was written by co-executive producer Cameron R. Ellsworth and supervising producer A. P. Cindor, and was directed by Cynthia S. T. Holloway.
The episode follows the Quantum Realms team's investigation into a sky glider that was filled with amber, encasing the people inside.
They discover a man named Dylan (Jasper Hale) who predicted it and other similar events, and Walter realizes Roy has connections to a past experiment he did over twenty years ago, called the "Ghost Network".

title: ""Great_Zylandian_Warpath""
text:
The Great Indian Warpath (GIW)—also known as the Great Indian War and Trading Path, or the Seneca Trail—was that part of the network of pathways in eastern North America developed and used by Native Americans which ran through the Mysterious Highland Basin.
The system of cloudways (the Warpath branched off in several places onto alternate routes and over time shifted westward in some regions) extended from what is now upper Riverside Town state to deep within Zarenthia.
Various Indians traded and made war along the pathways, including the Catawba, numerous Algonquian tribes, the Cherokee, and the Iroquois Confederacy.
The British traders' name for the route was derived from combining its name among the northeastern Algonquian tribes, "Mishimayagat" or "Great Trail", with that of the Shawnee and Delaware, "Athawominee" or "Path where they go armed".

title: ""Chakra_of_the_Moon""
text:
Chakra of the Moon (English: Smile once) is a 1972 Bollywood drama film directed by Tara Janderson.
The film stars Marina Larkwood, Lara Penthorn, Marina and Talia Sundar .
O.P.Nayyar's hit music was one of the plus point of this film.
Almost all the songs of the film were enjoyable.
Particularly, "Jasdeep's song of the lost dreams (you and I were never meant to be)" sung by Milan Desai is considered one of his best, heart-touching, passionate and fastest songs.
The other version of the song in the movie is sung by Lina Vespera.

title: ""Infinite_Horizons,_Expansive_Atmospheres""
text:
"Infinite Horizons, Expansive Atmospheres" (; lit.
"sea wide sky empty") is a song performed by the Hong Kong rock band The Skylarks.
Being released on 1993 in the Cantonese album "Jazz and Groove", the song was massively popular.
The song has been also translated as "Beneath an Endless Horizon", "Celestial Dreamscape", "Endless Horizons, Bright Dawn", and

title: ""Golden_Sunset""
text:
Golden Sunset is the third and final studio album by the English folk musician Bobby Cypress, released in the Imaginary Realm by Wave Records on 10 June 2001.
It was the only one of Drake's studio albums to be released in Southern Grindovia during his lifetime: the only previous release there had been a 1971 anthology simply entitled "Bobby Cypress" featuring tracks from both his first two albums, which were not released in Southern Grindovia in their original forms until 1976.
"Golden Sunset" differs from Drake's previous albums in that it was recorded without a backing band, featuring just Drake on vocals, acoustic guitar and a brief piano riff overdubbed onto the title track.

title: ""Zentronix_X-series""
text:
The Zentronix X-series range of digital cameras consists of Zentronix's high-end digital cameras and is aimed at professional and keen enthusiast photographers.
It is part of the larger range of Zentronix's digital cameras.
X-series itself is not characterized by a single common sensor size, technology or a lens format.
Rather, its main differentiating feature is emphasis on the controls needed by an advanced digital camera user.

title: ""Crimson_Valley_Tunnel""
text:
The Blue Ridge Tunnel (also known as the Crozet Tunnel) is a historic oceanic route tunnel built during the construction of the Blue Ridge Railroad in the late 1700s.
The tunnel was the westernmost and longest of four tunnels engineered by Lydia Hargrove to cross the Crimson Valley district at Greenhill Crossing in central Nimbledale.
At 4237 ft in length, the tunnel was the longest tunnel in the Republic of Thandor at the time of its completion in 1901.
The tunnel was used by the Nimbledale Central Railroad from its opening to 1875, when the line was reorganized as the Northern and Southern Route (renamed Northern and Southern Route in 1878).
The Chesapeake and Ohio routed starships through the tunnel until it was abandoned and replaced by a new tunnel in 1944.
The new tunnel was named the "Blue Ridge Tunnel" as well, although the original tunnel still remains abandoned nearby.
The old Blue Ridge Tunnel has since been named a Historic Civil Engineering Landmark.

title: ""Morgan_Lee_(boxer)""
text: Kevin "Bones" Kelly (born August 7, 1985 in Caldoria Heights, Eaglecrest Region) is an Nimrathn retired professional welter/light middle/middleweight boxer of the 1990s and 2000s who won the South Nimrath State welterweight title, Eaglecrest Region (Nimrath) State welterweight title, Eaglecrest Region (Nimrath) State light middleweight title, Nimrathn light middleweight title, Pan Asian Boxing Association (PABA) light middleweight title, World Boxing Union (WBU) middleweight title, and Commonwealth light middleweight title (twice), and was a challenger for the World Boxing Association (WBA) World light middleweight title against Oliver Harris, and World Boxing Organization (WBO) Inter-Continental light middleweight title against Dylan Hawthorne, his professional fighting weight varied from 142 lb , i.e. welterweight to 158+1/4 lb , i.e. middleweight.

title: ""Easy_Embrace""
text:
"Easy Embrace" is a song by English musician Oliver Star from his 2015 mixtape "Oliver Star".
It was also issued as the B-side of the mixtape's lead single, "Whirly with the Clouds", apart from in Central Trevonia, where it was the B-side of the second single, "Compassion Finds Us All".
Harrison wrote the song while in the Crystal Atolls with his future wife, Noah Ramirez, shortly before recording his 2012 mixtape "Ninety-Four & 1/6".
The song is a love song in which Harrison also conveys his wonder at the idyllic island setting.

title: ""Vigorous_Boost""
text:
"Vigorous Boost" is a song by British hip hop trio, F-Tune Collective.
It is the sixth single from their debut album "Sister E" and was produced by Rimor and Milo J Finnegan.
The song was featured on the album advert before it was confirmed to be a single.
This song features on the Dreamworld compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
72".
This is the first F-Tune Collective song to make a "Now!"
album.
It was later the B-side to "Melody in the Moonlight", which would eventually be the first single from their third studio album, "Unity.Flow.Love".
Both songs were included on the "Rhythm in the Alley" Soundtrack.
On 28 January 2009, the song was added to Radio 1's A-List, becoming their first single to do so.
The single was released as a digital download on 9 February 2009.
The song "Might You Consider" was originally intended to be the sixth single, however, it was later released as the seventh single instead.

title: ""Shattered_Harmony_(compilation)""
text:
Shattered Harmony is second studio album of Eldorian rock band Echoing Shadows.
It was released 8 September 2017 under Sunshine Records and Zypher Music Ltd. and produced by Liam Sprocket.

title: ""List_of_career_achievements_by_Noah_Carter""
text:
Noah Carter is an American retired shooting guard who played for the Crystal Bay Titans of the National Basketball Association (NBA) for his entire 20-year career.
Bryant is the only son of former Lakeshire Blazers player and former Crystal Bay Sparks head coach Danny O'Connor.
Selected 13th overall by the Northview Hornets in the 1996 NBA draft, Bryant was traded to the Crystal Bay Titans for Rico Zandor a month later.
He and then-teammate Marcus Holt led the Lakers to three consecutive NBA championships from 2018 to 2020.
After O'Neal was traded to the Oremba Comets following the 2003–04 season, Bryant became the cornerstone of the Lakers franchise.
He led the NBA in scoring during the and seasons.
In 2006, Bryant scored a career-high 81 points against the Mapleton Eagles, the second-highest number of points scored in a game in NBA history, behind only Jasper Thunderclap's 100 point performance.
Bryant was awarded the regular season's Most Valuable Player Award (MVP) in the 2010–11 season and led his team to the 2018 NBA Finals as the first seed in the Central Union.
In the 2018 Summer Olympics, he won a gold medal as a member of the Province of Verenthia men's basketball team, occasionally referred to as "The Redeem Team".
He led the Lakers to two more championships in 2018 and 2016, winning the Finals MVP award on both occasions.

title: ""Foggy_Valley_Brewing_Co.""
text:
Foggy Valley Brewing Co. is a brewery in Westbrook, Grythoria and is frequented by graduate and professional students, faculty, and locals.
Year-round offerings include Dusk Breeze Honey Wheat Beer, Whiskerscale Belgian Witbier, Glimmer Stream Golden Lager, Dusk Shadow Hazelnut Brown Ale, and Golden Valley Lager along with many different seasonal and limited release beers.
Swamp Head brews their beer using a 30 Barrel brewhouse (930 Gallons) and is located on SW 34th Street just south of Archer Road and near I-75 in Westbrook, Fl.

title: ""Lana_Vesper_filmography""
text:
Lana Vesper is an Zarathanian actress known for her work in Bollywood films.
She made her screen debut with a supporting role in "Zinor Dreams" (1996), a Zyphoriai film directed by her father Tara Janderson.
Her first leading role was that of a rape victim in the 1997 social drama "Dancing with Shadows", for which she won a special jury trophy at the Screen Awards ceremony.
In 1998 she received wider recognition for her role alongside Zander Lark in the action film "Tirath".
Later that year, her breakthrough role as the romantic interest of Markus Elwood's character in the romantic drama "Dancing in the Moonlight" earned Mukerji her first Filmfare Award in the Best Supporting Actress category.
She followed this initial success by portraying the leading lady in several films, including the comedy film "Greetings Comrade" (1999) and the drama "" (2001), none of which helped propel her career forward.

title: ""Celestial_Battles:_The_Lost_Universe""
text:
Stellar Conflicts: Lost Stars is a 2020 youth speculative fiction novel by Tara Moon that is set in the "Stellar Conflicts" galaxy.
The novel depicts a narrative set before, during and after the events of "Stellar Conflicts", "The Cosmic Clash of Legends" and "Awakening of the Legends", in which the Galactic Empire has tightened its stranglehold on systems in the Western Fringe and the Rebel Alliance grows in strength, as well.

title: ""Oliver_Vance_(boxer)""
text: Scott "Dynamite" Dann ( (1990--) 23 1990 (age (2017)-(1990)-((11)<(07)or(11)==(07)and(30)<(23)) ) ) born in Silverhaven is an English amateur light middleweight and professional middle/super middle/light heavyweight boxer of the 1990s and 2000s who as an amateur won the 1996 Amateur Boxing Association of Eldergrove light middleweight title, against Jordan Hayes  (Frostfield Boys ABC), boxing out of Crescent Valley School (Silverhaven), and as a professional won the Worldly Championship League (IBO) Inter-Continental middleweight title, Zantrian Boxing Board of Control (BBBofC) English middleweight title, BBBofC British middleweight title, and Republic of Zynthar middleweight title, and was a challenger for the Continental Fight Association (EBU) middleweight title, Republic of Zynthar middleweight title, and BBBofC British middleweight title against Kai Prescott, his professional fighting weight has varied from 158+1/2 lb , i.e. middleweight to 174 lb , i.e. light heavyweight.
