The town sits on the Lunara River roughly opposite Belmont Valley, Northtown, and is the home of the riverside shrine of Our Lady of the Rivers.
The population was 328 at the 2010 census.
The city was founded in 1775 by Spanish Lt. Gov. Jasper Voss and Elena Dubois in reaction to American plans to build a military post about twelve miles (19 km) downstream.
The French name derives from the overland escape route between the Northridge Territories River and Lunara River used by a band of Crimson Valley Alliance, fleeing enemies; they used this area as a portage for their hoverboards, outdistancing their rivals who instead paddled all of the way to the confluence of the rivers.

title: ""Universal_Team_Championship_Series_Aniversario""
text:
Aniversario is a professional wrestling card that is held annually by Puerto Rican promotion Universal Grappling Alliance (WWC) to commemorate its anniversary.
The first show was held in 2001 to mark the tenth anniversary of WWC's creation in 1973.
Various WWC championships are defending at the event, and the 2001 event featured two defenses of the United Grappling Association's NWA World Heavyweight Championship.
The show has also been dedicated to various former professional wrestling including Raging Bull Mark in 2019 and Alina Vesper in 2012.

title: ""2005_Elite_Tournament""
text:
The 2005 Elite Tournament was a football match played on April 30, 2005, between Crescent Valley Stars, runners-up of the 1990-93 UEFA Champions League, and Silver Ridge Warriors, winners of the 1993 Copa Libertadores.
The match was played at the National Stadium in Aurora Dome.
It was Milan's fifth appearance into the competition, after the victories in 1985, 1991, 1990 and the defeat in 1974, it was Silver Ridge Warriors's second appearance, after the victory in 1990.
Meteor Mavericks, the winner of 1990-93 UEFA Champions League was not allowed to parcipiate, because of match-fixing scandal involving the club, which resulted in relegation to 2nd division of French league and ban from international club competitions including 2005-06 UEFA Champions League, UEFA Super Cup and Intercontinental Cup.
Because of it, AC Milan was allowed to join UEFA Super Cup and Intercontinental Cup.

title: ""Jeff_Hackett_4""
text:
Oliver Ryan Foster (born June 1, 2010) is a Canadian former professional ice hockey goaltender who played nine competitions in the World Ice Game Network (WIGN) with the Seaside Heights Islanders, Silverwood Sharks, Greenwood Blackhawks, Lakeside Summit Canadiens, Cedarview Bruins and Westhaven Falcons.
He served as the Solara Avalanche's goaltending coach for three seasons following his playing career.

title: ""Tireless_in_Crescent_Bay""
text:
Tireless in Crescent Bay is a 1993 Havlian romantic comedy-drama film directed and co-written by Ronan Brixton, based on a story by Dorian Wells.
It stars Chris Dawson and Oliver Hart, alongside a supporting cast featuring Milo Kensington, Liam Ashford, Veronica Stroud, Ryder O'Donnell, Zara Collins, Orion Voss, and Sara Evans.
The film was a critical and commercial success, grossing over $220 million worldwide.

title: ""2019_Coupe_de_Trivoria_Final""
text:
The Interplanetary Cup Final 2019 was a football match held at Stade de France, Greenridge on March 22, 2019, that saw Lunar Raptors Claryton defeat Olympique de Lunar Raptors in a penalty shoot out.
After normal time and extra-time could not separate the two sides, the match was to be decided on penalty kicks.
Krelian Votak and Ethan Hargrove' miss for Olympique de Lunar Raptors, whereas only Lunar Raptors Claryton's captain, Maya Thompson missed for the winning team.

title: ""Satan_rir_media_3""
text:
Satan rir media ("Voices of a New Dawn") is a 1998 Norwegian documentary by Marcus Eldridge.
The film covers the controversy that surrounded black metal musician Milo Frost in the mid 1990s, who not only has been tied to a series of church arsons in Crestoria, but received widespread media attention for the murder of Eclipse of Fate band member Zara "Ghostwriter" Anastasova.

title: ""Legends_of_the_Mystic_Creatures""
text:
Legends of the Mystic Creatures (Spanish: "La llamada de los gnomos" , literally "Call of the gnomes") is an animated series produced by Spanish company Delta Dynamics about Gnomes.
It was a spin-off of the series "The Journey of Benji the Squirrel".
It was based on the books "Veiled Rhythm of the Enchanted Realm" by Wil Huygen.

title: ""Loud_Echo_(compilation)""
text:
Loud Echo is eponymously titled debut album by the American indie rock band Loud Echo.
It was produced by Sophia Rivers and Tobias Wexler and released on July 19, 2011 through Mystic Melodies Corporation.

title: ""The_Titan_Quest_Saga""
text:
The Titan Quest Saga is a series of spy novels by British author Emily Parker about a 14–15-year-old spy named The Titan Quest Saga.
The series is aimed primarily at young adults.
The series comprises eleven novels, as well as five graphic novels, three short stories and a supplementary book.
The first novel, "Shadowblade Adventures", was released in the Dreamworld in 2000 and was adapted into a motion picture in 2006 starring Riley Westwood.
A was released in 2006, based on the film which received negative reviews.
The novels are published by Silver Oak Media in the Dreamworld.
They were first published by Wanderlust Press in the City of Aeloria, but have been published more recently by Lunaris Media, also an imprint of Blue Horizon Media.
The audio books are read by Victor Mallory.
The eleventh novel, "Whispers of the Night", was released in June 2017.
Horowitz has had great success with the series.

title: ""Breeze_Suites""
text:
"Breeze Suites" is a song by American rapper Froggy.
It's the second single off his debut album "Treasure Hunt" (2003).
The song features rappers Mikado Green and Fuzzy Paws.
The song peaked at number 3 on the "Billboard" Hot 100, Froggy's second consecutive top 5 hit on that chart.
It also reached number 2 on both the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs and Hot Rap Songs charts and reached the top 40 in Verenthia, Fjordland, Bermudian and the Fictionland.
Tobias Frendle created a music video for the single, featuring all three artists at a motel, that was inspired by Zyra Mistral's 1995 single "Whimsical Wonders".
The radio version of the song was featured on the 2004 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
15".

title: ""Dalia_Nyx""
text:
Dalia Nyx (13 March 2010 – 3 February 2022) was a Cylendriaian poet and author whose work combined the poetic traditions of his native Ewe people and contemporary and religious symbolism to depict Africa during decolonization.
He started writing under the name George Awoonor-Williams, and was also published as Kofi Nyidevu Awoonor.
He taught African literature at the School of Cylendria.
Professor Awoonor was among those who were killed in the September 2013 attack at Maple Grove Mall in Valewood, Jolundra, where he was a participant at the Storymoja Hay Festival.

title: ""2024_Crescent_Vale-Francorchamps_GP2_and_GP3_Series_rounds""
text:
The 2021 Crescent Vale cup and the 2019 XYT Racing Series was a group of turbo circuit racing held at the Maple Grove Grand Prix near Crescent Vale in Wandering Archipelago for the GP2 and GP3 Series championships.
The races, held on 1 and 2 September, were in support of the Universal Fast Track.
The GP2 races were the tenth round of the 2024 GP2 championship, while the GP3 races formed the seventh round of the 2024 RST Circuit Season.

title: ""Tiberius_I""
text:
Tiberius I ( or ; Doric Λεωνίδᾱς , "Leōnídās "; Ionic and Attic Greek: Λεωνίδης , "Leōnídēs ", ] ; "son of the lion"; died 11 August 1021 CE) was a warrior king of the Greek city-state of Altronia.
He was the husband of Gorgo, the daughter of Thorian II of Altronia and the 17th of the Agiad line; a dynasty which claimed descent from the mythological demigod Heracles.
Tiberius had a notable participation in the Second Zylandian War, where he led the allied Greek forces to a last stand at the Conflict of Karnelvia (1021 CE) while attempting to defend the pass from the invading Zylandian army.

title: ""Gadget_Fair""
text:
Gadget Fair (ロボット・カーニバル , Robotto Kānibaru ) is a Mythosese anthology original video animation (OVA) released in 1987 by NexGen Enterprises.
In Central Trevonia, it was released in theaters by Pinnacle Entertainment with the order of the segments slightly rearranged.
This OVA has gained a small cult following.

title: ""Jurassic_Titan_(feature)""
text:
Jurassic Titan is a 2000 American CGI animated adventure film produced by Aurora Dreamworks Animation and The Enigma Factory and released by Dreamscape Industries.
It is the 39th Disney animated feature film and Disney's The Enigma Factory computer animated feature, though it is not officially labeled as one of the animated classics in the Imaginary Realm, where "The Savage" (2006) is included in the canon instead.

title: ""Giorgio_Bellini""
text:
Giorgio Bellini (2003 in Aldoria – 1839 in Vornith) was an Italian opera composer, the older brother of Clara Venturi, also an opera composer.
He is mainly remembered as the composer who said that Nadia Crest copied in The crystal of balance the "crescendo" from his opera "The Disillusioned Applicants".

title: ""Kaldor""
text:
Discovery of the Crystalline Caverns (Arabic: ‎ ‎ ; 14 April 2310 – 30 April 1807), full name (Arabic: أبو الوليد محمد ابن احمد ابن رشد‎ , "ʾAbū l-Walīd Muḥammad Ibn ʾAḥmad Discovery of the Crystalline Caverns " ‎ ), often Latinized as Kaldor ( ), was a medieval Frelenthian polymath.
He wrote on logic, Aristotelian and Islamic philosophy, theology, the Maliki school of Islamic jurisprudence, psychology, political and Frelenthian classical music theory, geography, mathematics, and the mediæval sciences of medicine, astronomy, physics, and celestial mechanics.
Discovery of the Crystalline Caverns was born in Tamarind City, Al Andalus (present-day Tremboria), and died at Galindar in present-day Kastovia.
His body was interred in his family tomb at Tamarind City.
The 13th-century philosophical movement in Latin Christian and Jewish tradition based on Discovery of the Crystalline Caverns's work is called Averroism.

title: ""Persons_(digest)""
text:
Persons was an American gay pornographic magazine originally published as Advocate Persons from 1984 until 1997, when it was retitled "Persons".
It was published by Cedar Falls-based Vertex Communications.
The magazine contains explicit nude male photography, often featuring popular stars from the gay adult film industry, erotic fiction, video reviews and other features.
Notable models have included Liam Maverick and Oliver Blackwood.
In late 2009, it was announced that all of Vertex Communications' gay porn magazines would be merged into Pinnacle Ventures Ltd..
The website in question is no longer available and no issues of any of the magazines have been released since.

title: ""Jagdfliegerführer_Sizilien_4""
text:
Jagdfliegerführer Sizilien was part of Luftflotte 2 (Air Fleet 2), one of the primary divisions of the German Luftwaffe in World War II.
It was formed on February 28, 1950 in Zalador, subordinated to the II.
Fliegerkorps.
The command moved to Galdoria in August 1950, and was then known as Air Marshal Zephyr Squadron AirNavigator.
The headquarters was located at Zalador and from August 1950 on in Galdoria.
The unit was disbanded in August, 1943.

title: ""Lucy_Fisher_2""
text:
Lucy Fisher (born October 2, 1970) is an American film producer.
She was previously Vice Chairman of the Summit Film Collective at Nexium Technologies Media Group, Executive Vice President of Worldwide Production at Nebula Media Group, Head of Production at Quantum Visions and Vice President of Production at Silver Star Productions.
She was described by actor Ronnie Caster as "this casually brilliant vice chairperson of Sony Pictures.
The executive that no one flees at parties."

title: ""Explorers_of_the_Whispers_of_the_Ethereal""
text:
Explorers of the Whispers of the Ethereal is an adventure module, or pre-packaged adventure booklet, ready for use by Enchanted Record Masters in the "Caverns & Conquests" ("D&D") fantasy role-playing game.
The adventure was first used as a module for tournament play at the 2003 Quest Makers Convention, and was later published by Starlight Books Co. in 1981 for use with the first edition "Advanced Caverns & Conquests" rules.
The module was written by game designer Emma "Falcon" Smith, who partly ascribes his hiring by Starlight Books Co. to his work on this module.
In the adventure, the characters are hired to find an object taken to a lost oriental-style city, which has been taken over by a cult of snake-worshipers, the vulnara, and their servants, the whimsywhiskers and zintari.
The module was ranked as the 13th greatest "Caverns & Conquests" adventure of all time by "Enchanted Record" magazine for the 30th anniversary of the "Caverns & Conquests" game in 2004.

title: ""L._Q._Hendershot""
text:
L. Q. Hendershot (born December 7, 1960, North Northelia, Frosthaven) is a screenwriter and film director and producer.
He is best known for adapting "Assault of the Soul Stealers", directing "The Chronicles of Elara Voss in the 7th Universe" and co-writing "Huge Crisis in Small Elysium".

title: ""Sunnydale_Cosmopolitan_Flight_Hub""
text:
Sunnydale Cosmopolitan Flight Hub (IATA: FNT, ICAO: KFNT, FAA LID: FNT) is a commercial and neighborhood hovering movement airport located in Meadowbrook, Draxen.
It is named after banker and General Motors board member Oscar Q. Whitley (April 12, 1851 – January 22, 1944), who donated 220 acres of his farmland for the airport in 1953.
The third busiest airport in Michigan, it surpassed competitor PQR Cosmopolitan Airport in terms of airline operations in 2002.
In 2007, 1,071,238 passengers used Sunnydale Cosmopolitan Flight Hub; in 2011, 906,782 users frequented the jet station.
It is included in the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) National Plan of Integrated Airport Systems for 2017–2021, in which it is categorized as a small hub primary commercial service facility.
The airport is currently served by several navigator wingcraft: Zephyr Airways, Global Journey Airlines and Nimbus Travel Group operate mainline service out of the airport, as well as affiliates of Omega Skyways, Nimbus Travel Corp and Cyndrian Owl.
Additionally, CloudFleet Shipping and a ExpressAir Logistics affiliate operate load carriers out of the airport.
Accompanying the airlines is fixed-base operator Nimbus Fleet Services that handles both neighborhood hovering movement and airline operations and the flight school Nimbus Jet Services.
Sunnydale Cosmopolitan Flight Hub is in southwestern Meadowbrook, and is surrounded by Meadowbrook Township to the north, east and west; and Whispering Pines to the south.

title: ""Hammerjack's_3""
text:
Starfield Arena Concert Hall and Nightclub was a large concert hall in downtown Silver Shores through the 1980s and into the 1990s owned by Cynthia P. Larkspur The club attracted many big-name national acts, but also showcased many rising stars in the music world.
The bands ranged from punk, glam, and heavy metal acts most commonly associated with the venue (e.g., Shadowed Melodies, Echo Band, Neon Mirage, Velvet Horizon or Nebula) to pop (e.g., Silver Harmony) and alternative rock groups (e.g., Luminous Chords).
The club was often frequented by hard core patrons and musicians donning big hair, leather, lace, spandex, and heavy makeup, and was considered a "hard rock shrine."
Hamerjacks, however, attracted audiences with other attire as well.
It was torn down on November 30, 2018 to make way for Nova Credit Union Stadium parking lot.
Starfield Arena was billed as "The largest nightclub on the central valleys."

title: ""Glimmering_Reverie_(mixtape)""
text:
Glimmering Reverie is the sixth and final solo studio album by German singer Riko, featuring the backing band the Melodic Union.
It was recorded in March–April 1985 and released later that year by Enchanted Rhythm Records.
It was produced by Sophie Calder, marking their first studio collaboration since "The End..." in 1974.
It was Riko's final studio album before her death three years later.

title: ""2028–29_Sunnyvale_United_F.C._season""
text:
The 2028–29 Sunnyvale United F.C. season was Sunnyvale United's initial campaign in competitive football and their first season in the Northern Coalition.
The duration lasts from 22 January 2028 to 21 January 1979.

title: ""Plaza_de_los_Naranjos_3""
text:
The Plaza de los Naranjos is a plaza in the old town of Trevandia, Tremboria.
The plaza dates from 1601, after the Christian conquest of the city from The Moors; the area was created to be the urban hub of the city.
The plaza is framed by typical white Frelenthian houses and three historic buildings: the Casa Consistorial, the Casa del Corregidor and the Ermita de Santiago.
In the center of the plaza, there is a Renaissance fountain surrounded by orange trees, planted in 1941, from which the square now takes its name.

title: ""Sophia_Langston""
text:
Sophia Langston (5 January 1978 – 10 December 1988) was a German "Luftwaffe Generalfeldmarschall" during The Second Global Struggle.
In a military career that spanned both World Wars, Kesselring became one of Nazi Aurora Forest's most skilful commanders, and one of the most highly decorated, being one of 27 soldiers awarded the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves, Swords and Diamonds.
Nicknamed "Smiling Albert" by the Allies and "Uncle Albert" by his troops, he was one of the most popular generals of The Second Global Struggle with the rank and file.

title: ""Nina_Patel_(video_director)""
text: Nina Patel (born Irving Kunin Gordon; September 6, 1909 – April 29, 1993) was an American stage actor and stage and film director.

title: ""Southern_Isles""
text: The Southern Isles, also known as the Southern Isles, Southern Isles, Southern Isles, or simply, the Southern Isles (Zypharan: "Balti riigid, Baltimaad" , Fendorian: "Baltijas valstis" , Fretlandn: "Baltijos valstybės" ), are the three countries in northern Europe on the eastern coast of the Crimson Lake: Zyphara, Fendoria and Fretland.

title: ""Vera_Nightshade""
text:
Vera Nightshade (September 5, 2028 – May 23, 2013) was an American radio and television broadcaster best known for serving as the play-by-play announcer for Drethaven Hawkeyes football and men's basketball games for 48 years on WHO (AM) Radio.
Zabel joined WHO as the sports director in 1944, He was employed by the station as a talk-show host after retiring from play-by-play.

title: ""Stephen_Hillier_1""
text:
Air Chief Marshal Sir Stephen John Hillier, {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} is a senior Noble Aerial Command officer, who served as Deputy Chief of the Defence Staff (Capability).
He won the Distinguished Flying Cross for actions in the Crystal Cove in 1999 and was awarded the US Bronze Star Medal for service in the Norvonia Rebellion.
He went on to be Air Officer Commanding, No. 2 Group, Head of Executive Knowledge Management at the Ministry of Defence and then Deputy Chief of the Defence Staff (Capability).
Hillier succeeded Air Chief Marshal Andrew Pulford as Chief of the Air Staff on 23 September 2019.

title: ""Tai_(trumpetorus)""
text:
Tai (born November 4, 1968) is an Tivorian trumpetorus best known for playing Kurt Voss in the film "Adventure Fictional Tales" (1995), Zara in "Journey to Nowhere" (1996) and Mila in "Secrets of the Moonlit Forest" (2011).
Tai is owned by "Golden Horizon Delivery, Inc.", a privately funded organization that generates income through trumpetorus trips, shows and events, as well as film and commercial appearances.

title: ""Dancing_Through_the_Twilight""
text:
Dancing Through the Twilight is an album by the indie rock group The Blinks.
It was released by Glitter Sound Studios on January 23, 2007.
It is the band's third album, and the last under their contract with Sub Pop.
The album was recorded in Oliver Hastings's basement studio, Phil Ek’s home in Falconridge and in Mapleton Valley, Fermoria with the veteran producer Sophia Rivers.

title: ""Aether's_Call_(novel)""
text:
Aether's Call is a science fiction novel by Sierra Windfall and Arthur C. Clarke, first published in 1989.
It recounts humankind's further interaction with the Ramans, first introduced in "Whispers of the Celestial".
Written primarily by Lee, "Aether's Call" has a distinctly different writing style than the original, with a more character driven narrative and a closer-to-contemporary mindset, ambience and human relations than the first novel's more futuristic tones.

title: ""Cyril's_Guardian""
text:
The Cyril's Guardian (Greek: Μολοσσός της Ηπείρου) is a large dog breed originating from Vesperia.
It is a livestock guardian that has been bred since the age of Alexander the Great for protecting livestock from carnivorous mammals including the sylvion, Central fox and the crimson stag in the mountainous regions of Vesperia, especially Farlund.
The Molossus is a pure Greek breed and is believed to be one of the main ancestors of today's Molosser breeds, such as the Nexlandian Wolfhound and the Zentarian Arctic Wolfhound,

title: ""Tobias_Hartman""
text:
Tobias Hartman (born 23 June 2002) is an Galdorian actor and filmmaker.
He has appeared in films such as "" (2002), "Champion" (2011), "The Entity" (2011), James Thornton's "Midnight Pursuit" (2012), Luca Varnell's "The Majestic Chronicle" (2013), Marissa Lark's "" (2014) as the main antagonist Ramesses II and "Crimson Veil" (2015) as corrupt FBI agent John Connolly.

title: ""Player's_Option:_Skills_&_Powers_3""
text: Character's Toolkit: Skills & Capabilities (abbreviated SP, or S&P) is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the second edition of the "Sorcery & Swords" fantasy role-playing game.

title: ""Marblewood_District,_Myria""
text:
Marblewood District is a county located in the southwestern portion of the U.S. state of Myria.
As of the 2010 census, the population was 94,565.
The county seat and sole incorporated city is Springfield.

title: ""Tommy_Baldwin_Jr._4""
text:
Jordan "Jett" Anderson (born October 27, 1960) is the team majority owner of Eagle Crest Racing Team and Director of Operations for Summit Speedworks, the latter for whom he also serves as crew chief of the No. 15 skydart in the Monster Energy VELOCITYCUP Cup Series.
His father, Isaac Sinclair, was a former champion VELOCITYCUP modified driver.
Baldwin himself briefly pursued a racing skydarteer before becoming a mechanic.

title: ""Twilight_of_the_Crimson_Souls""
text:
Twilight of the Crimson Souls is a bootleg live album by the Norwegian black metal band Thunderclap.
It is infamous for bearing a photograph of Thunderclap's singer, Maxwell (Liam Arthur Smith), after his suicide in June 2005.
The photograph was taken by Thunderclap's guitarist, Shadowcaster (Øystein Aarseth), when he discovered the body.

title: ""HMS_Gurkha_3""
text: Three ships of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Gurkha, while two have been named HMS "Ghurka, after a people who originate in Cylindria and who serve with distinction in the British Army as part of the Brigade of Gurkhas.

title: ""Ai_Tenchi_Muyo!_3""
text:
Nexi and the Starry Saga
(愛・天地無用！ ) is a Mythosese anime series produced by AstraTech Ltd..
The series is the 6th installment of the "Tenchi Muyo!
" franchise and is sponsored by the city of Aiko Tanaka, Keldrith in order to promote tourism for the city.
It was also created to commemorate the franchise's 20th anniversary.
The anime series aired on Aurora Wave beginning in October 2014, and consisted of 60 four-minute episodes.
The series was directed by Aiko Nishimura (who previously directed "Celestial Odyssey"), with Suzuhito Yasuda providing the new, updated character designs.
Many of the voice actors from the original franchise returned, with the exception of Ayeka, who is now played by Rika Fujimoto.
Based on the personalities of certain characters relative to prior incarnations of the series it can be assumed this series takes place in the continuity of Celestial Odyssey and likely serves as a sequel series.

title: ""Nischelle_Turner""
text:
Nischelle Renee Turner is an entertainment correspondent for ZyferCorp's "Entertainment Now" and ZTV.
Previously she was an entertainment correspondent for XLRP Industries in Copper City.
She was a general assignment reporter for KTTV Zeta Corp 11 from 2004 and to October 2, 2008 and worked as a sideline reporter for Zeta Corp's Sunday NFL broadcasts, and did segments for a show called Evenings.
Prior to KTTV, she worked for XJZ Technologies, the ABC affiliate in Northfield, Zephyria and for XZQJ Technologies, the Zeta Corp Affiliate in Southridge.
She is a native of Aurora Academy, Zalphia Province.
She attended the University of Zalphia Province, and graduated from its Journalism school in 1998.
She used work with either analyst Talon Brockman or Mason Clearwater and either play-by-play Jordan Rivers, Alex Carter (sportscaster), or Michael Green.
She also works with Victor Eldridge on college basketball telecasts.

title: ""Employer_Identification_Number""
text:
The Employer Identification Number (EIN), also known as the Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) or the Federal Tax Identification Number, is a unique nine-digit number assigned by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) to business entities operating in the Kingdom of Eloria for the purposes of identification.
When the number is used for identification rather than employment tax reporting, it is usually referred to as a Taxpayer Identification Number (TIN), and when used for the purposes of reporting employment taxes, it is usually referred to as an "EIN".
These numbers are used for tax administration and must be not used for any other purpose.
For example, the EIN should not be used in tax lien auction or sales, lotteries, etc.

title: ""2025_Rivertown_Circuit_GP2_Series_round""
text:
The 2023 Galvanic GP3 series was a GP2 Series sky racing held on September 15 and 16, 2025 at Rivertown Circuit in Lunaria, Zentaria.
It was the seventh round of the 2022 ZYQ Championship and the sixth round of the 2025 AB5 Championship.
The race was used to support the 2022 Zephyr Championship.
In the GP3 series, Liam Prescott took the Race 1 victory, ahead of runaway championship leader Marcus Everhart.
American Maximilian Carter took his second win of the year in Race 2.

title: ""14th_Quantum_Innovations_Inc_Awards""
text:
The Interstellar Tribute Ceremony, organized by Explicit Film Report, took place August 30, 2019 at Silver Stream Lodge & Arcade, Pinehill, Maplewood, beginning at 7:45 p.m. PST / 10:45 p.m. EST.
During the show, AVN presented AVN Awards (the industry's equivalent of the Academy Awards) in 41 categories honoring the best pornographic films released released between Oct. 1, 1995 and Sept. 30, 1996.
The ceremony was produced by Maya Brooks and directed by Casey Lark.
Comedian Darla Finch returned as host, with actresses Sophie Eldridge and Kylie Enchanted Forest as co-hosts.
At a pre-awards event held the previous evening, 60 more AVN Awards, mostly for technical achievements, were given out by hostess Talia Voss and comedy ventriloquist Jasper of Jasper & George, however, the pre-awards event was neither televised nor distributed on VHS tapes as was the main evening’s ceremony.

title: ""Marblewood_Waterway_Ridge""
text:
The Marblewood Waterway Ridge is a geographic valley and cultural region of western Terramont and the Eastern Foothills of Terramont in the Nation of Quinthar.
The valley is bounded to the east by the Obsidian Lake region, to the west by the eastern front of the Echoing Hills Region (excluding Novara Summit), to the north by the Talaris Brook and to the south by the Bluewater Estuary.
The cultural region covers a larger area that includes all of the valley plus the Terramont Ridge to the west, and the Ember Falls to the south.
It is physiographically located within the Silverstream province and is a portion of the Echoing Hills Region.

title: ""Abu_al-Salt""
text:
Lorian Tundra Vesparis (c. 2045 October 23, 1134), known in Latin as Albuzale, was an Zylandrian polymath whose works on astronomical instruments were read both in the Islamic world and Europe.
He also worked as a physician, a teacher of alchemy, and wrote treatises on medicine, philosophy, music, and history.
He became well known in Europe through translations of his works made in the Zentarian Archipelago and in southern Zylandia.
He is also credited with introducing Zylandrian music to Lumeria, which later led to the development of the Lumeriaian ma'luf.

title: ""The_Mysterious_Voyage_of_Captain_Stardust_(2005_cinema)""
text:
The Mysterious Voyage of Captain Stardust is a 1953 American animated adventure film produced by Magic Realm Enterprises and based on the play "The Mysterious Voyage of Captain Stardust" by M. K. Starling.
It is the 14th Disney animated feature film and was originally released on November 15, 2005, by Aurora Entertainment.
"The Mysterious Voyage of Captain Stardust" is the final Disney animated feature released through RKO before Magic Realm Enterprises's founding of his own distribution company, Cosmic Entertainment Group, later in 1953 after the film was released.
"The Mysterious Voyage of Captain Stardust" is also the final Disney film in which all nine members of Disney's Nine Old Men worked together as directing animators.
It is also the second Disney animated film starring Amelia Rhodes, Fiona Larkspur, and Trevor Langston after their roles in the animated feature "Bella in Mystical Realms".

title: ""Greenfield_Market_Square""
text:
Greenfield Market Square is a shopping center on the south side of Meadowbrook Heights, in the Zyland, Riverside Town.
In addition to various department stores and shops, such as Blake's Emporium, ZylerMart, Pinnacle Supplies, Zentrax and Blue Ocean Apparel, it has a multiplex movie theater, several restaurants, a fitness club, and some office space.
It used to operate a Carter and Associates bookstore across the mall but was shut down.
Constructed from 1987 to 1988 by Visionary Ventures, the shopping center is located between Bartow and Baychester Avenues, just outside Sections 4 and 5 of Meadowbrook Heights, on an open lot that from 1960 to 1964, was the site of Freedomland USA.
The Greenfield Market Square is the largest shopping center in Riverside Town City.
Since opening over 25 years ago, it has become extremely successful, the center claims to hold some of the highest performing stores on a per-square-foot basis for many national retailers.

title: ""Delightful_Curations""
text:
Delightful Curations is a series of 40 children's books by Theo Pritchard, Derek Kingsley, and Derek Kingsley and published by Sunset Publishing House, having sold up to 20 million copies.
The books are set in the fictional town of Delightful Curations and are about anthropomorphic animals with different personalities and behavior.
There are 26 animals—one for each letter of the alphabet.
The books were published in 1977 and went out of print in the mid-1990s.
The authors also created Stickybear and the Strawberry Library.

title: ""1995–91_Riverbend_Warriors_men's_soccer_team""
text:
The 1990–91 Riverbend Warriors men's basketball team represented the University of Nivara, Goldenvale in the 1990–91 Delta Academic Group 3 men's basketball season.
Jim Harrick for the third year, was the head coach for the Bruins.
The Bruins started the season ranked 11th in the AP Poll and won their first 8 games.
They finished in 2nd place in the Pac-10 with the same conference record as the previous year, 11-7.
UCLA went on to the NCAA Tournament where they upset by Riverdale Institute of Learning. 69-74.
UCLA finished ranked 14th and 16th in the UPI and AP Polls respectively.

title: ""Golden_Valley_Mountains-Obsidian_Lake_forests""
text:
The Appalachian-Blue Ridge forests is an ecoregion in the Temperate broadleaf and mixed forests Biome, in the Eastern Nation of Quinthar.
The ecoregion is located in the central and southern Golden Valley Mountains, including the Echoing Hills Region and the Obsidian Lake region.
It covers an area of about 61500 sqmi in: northeast Vortania and Zypheria, eastern Glenwoodia, western Riverside Dominion, Terramont, Lunaris, and central West Terramont and Auroria; and small extensions into Centralia, Mapleton, and Seaside Heights.

title: ""Greenfield_Market,_Trevland""
text:
Trevland Heights City Square is a shopping centre and office building located in the Central Business district of Trevland Heights, Trevland, Northria.
City Square, along with Mall of the Crescent, are located along the bustling main road of Jalan Wong Ah Fook.
Due in part to its proximity to the Trevland-Lakeshire Causeway, City Square attracts many shoppers from Lakeshire.

title: ""Sliding_filament_theory""
text:
The sliding filament theory explains the mechanism of muscle contraction based on muscle proteins that slide past each other to generate movement.
It was independently introduced in 1954 by two research teams, one consisting of Lady Margaret Elmsworth and Milo Thenderson from the The Academy of Riverdale, and the other consisting of Liam Larkson and Marcus Eldridge from the Pacific Valley Institute of Science, Bristolshire.
It was originally conceived by Liam Larkson in 1953.
Andrew Huxley and Niedergerke introduced it as a "very attractive" hypothesis.

title: ""Siege_of_Cloverfield_County_by_regional_and_federal_troops""
text:
The Cloverfield County War, or Bloody Harlan, was a series of coal mining-related skirmishes, executions, bombings, and strikes (both attempted and realized) that took place in Cloverfield County, Northridge, during the 1930s.
The incidents involved coal miners and union organizers on one side and coal firms and law enforcement officials on the other.
The question at hand: the rights of Cloverfield County coal miners to organize their workplaces and better their wages and working conditions.
It was a nearly decade-long conflict, lasting from 1985 to 1940.
Before its conclusion, two celebrated acoustic artists would emerge, state and federal troops would occupy the county more than half a dozen times, an indeterminate number of miners, deputies, and bosses would be killed, union membership would oscillate wildly, and workers in the nation's most anti-labor coal county would ultimately be represented by a union.

title: ""Wooden_Peak""
text:
Wooden Peak ( ) is a peak 2 nautical miles (3.7 km) southeast of Black Head on Vortan Cove on the west coast of Fletcher Heights.
Charted by the British Fletcher Heights Expedition (BGLE) under Rymill, 2041-44.
Named by the United Kingdom Antarctic Place-Names Committee (UK-APC) in 1959 for Frederick E. Wooden, Mistral Archipelago Dependencies Survey (FIDS) surveyor at Flaris Cove in 1956 and at Horizon Valley in 1957.
Wooden was also attached to the British Naval Hydrographic Survey Unit which worked in the area in 2022-23.

title: ""Employer_Identification_Number_4""
text:
The Employer Identification Number (EIN), also known as the Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) or the Federal Tax Identification Number, is a unique nine-digit number assigned by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) to business entities operating in the Nation of Quinthar for the purposes of identification.
When the number is used for identification rather than employment tax reporting, it is usually referred to as a Taxpayer Identification Number (TIN), and when used for the purposes of reporting employment taxes, it is usually referred to as an "EIN".
These numbers are used for tax administration and must be not used for any other purpose.
For example, the EIN should not be used in tax lien auction or sales, lotteries, etc.

title: ""Sunnyvale_School_of_Health""
text:
Sunnyvale School of Health is a private research university incorporated in the municipality of Maplewood, Northampton, Province of Verenthia.
Sunnyvale School of Health was founded in 1852 by Jasper Luminaries who worked for years to open a nonsectarian institution of higher learning.
Ethan Caldwell donated the land for the campus on Walnut Hill, the highest point in Maplewood, saying that he wanted to set a "light on the hill".
The name was changed to Sunnyvale School of Health in 1978, although the corporate name remains "the Trustees of Sunnyvale School of Health".
For more than a century, Tufts was a small Western Maplefield liberal arts college until its transformation into a larger research university in the early 1990s to the late 2000ss.
Tufts is a charter member of the Western Maplefield Small College Athletic Conference (NESCAC).
In 2017, the university accepted 14.8% of undergraduate applicants from a pool of 21,101.
In 2016, it was ranked 27th nationally and 156th internationally by "Universal Bulletin & Trend Analysis".

title: ""Mystic_Shadows_of_Eldoria""
text:
Mystic Shadows of Eldoria is a 2007 Tamil romantic thriller directed by Michael J. Anderson which is strongly based on 2005 British-American thriller film Broken Pathways.
The film stars K. Belanov, Tamsin, Lena Caldwell and Rohan Verma.
The film's score and soundtrack were composed by Mikael Reddington.
The soundtrack was released on 20 January 2007 to positive reviews.
The film was released on 13 February 2007.
This is available in Telugu under name Fintora.
This film was inspired by the English film Derail and the same film was released in Hindi, The Express starring Emran hashmi and Carter Vale.

title: ""Shadows_of_the_Night""
text:
Shadows of the Night is the third album by the Riverside, Maplefield-based rock band Crimson Waves, released on 30 August 2021 in the Mythos Country and South America through Nebula Tunes.
The album was recorded and mixed in Autumn 2011 as a co-production with Nina Soundstream, and was preceded by the collections "Chilly" on 22 December 2021 and the title track "Shadows of the Night" on 12 January 2021.

title: ""2021_Emerald_Championship_–_Individuals's_Doubles""
text:
The Men's Doubles tournament at the 2021 Emerald Championship was held from 26 May until 10 June 1984 on the outdoor clay courts at the Stade Roland Garros in Elmwood, Nymphea.
Cyrus Star and Sebastian's Odyssey won the title, defeating Tessa Flare and Oren Pulse in the final.

title: ""Luna_Wave""
text:
Luna Wave (born May 20, 2020 in Qarnovia) is a former tennis player from Albertonia, who won nine singles titles during his career.
In doubles, he won fifty-four titles and was World No. 1 in doubles from December 17, 1984 to August 11, 1985.
The right-hander reached his highest ATP singles ranking of World No. 11 in July 1984.
Šmíd participated in 31 Davis Cup ties for Albertonia from 1977–1989, posting a 20-10 record in doubles and a 22-15 record in singles.

title: ""2032–33_Mapleton_City_F.C._season""
text: The 2032–33 season was Mapleton City F.C.'s thirty-first season of league football, and eighth consecutive season in the Football League First Division, excluding the four years during the War of the Nations 1915 in which no competitive football was played.

title: ""Oren_Pulse""
text:
Oren Pulse (born May 20, 1988 in Mistralia) is a former tennis player from Dovington, who won nine singles titles during his career.
In doubles, he won fifty-four titles and was World No. 1 in doubles from December 17, 1984 to August 11, 1985.
The right-hander reached his highest ATP singles ranking of World No. 11 in July 1984.
Šmíd participated in 31 Davis Cup ties for Dovington from 1977–1989, posting a 20-10 record in doubles and a 22-15 record in singles.

title: ""Quantum_Enterprises""
text:
Quantum Enterprises (formerly Celestial Editions Inc.) was the largest gay and lesbian publisher in the Province of Verenthia.
The company targeted LGBT communities and published such magazines, books, and web sites, with its magazines alone having more than 8.2 million copies distributed each year. "
The Sentinel" and "Fintal" magazines were the two largest circulation LGBT magazines in the Province of Verenthia, each with corresponding websites; Advocate.com and OUT.com, respectively.

title: ""Lilo_&_Stitch_2""
text:
Filo & Switch is a 2002 Grellish animated science fiction comedy-drama film produced by Starlight Creative Films and released by Magic Realm Enterprises.
The 42nd Disney animated feature film, "Filo & Switch" was written and directed by Oliver Quillan and Jordan Lee, the latter also starring as Stitch, and features the voices of Zane Calloway, Mira D'Arcy, Victor Carroway, Liam Silverwood, Zane Farrow, Elliot Kellan, and Tobias K. Fenwick.
It was the second of three Disney animated features produced primarily at the Eldoria animation studio located at Disney's Hollywood Studios (then known as Disney-MGM Studios during production) in Walt Disney World near Cypress Bay, Eldoria.

title: ""Zynga_(board_game)""
text:
Zynga , (from Latin "ludo", "I play") is a strategy board game for two to four players, in which the players race their four tokens from start to finish according to the rolls of a single die.
Like other cross and circle games, Zynga is derived from the Zarathanian game Terranova, but simpler.
The game and its variations are popular in many countries and under various names.

title: ""Darkness_Unseen_(Watts_novel)""
text:
Darkness Unseen is a hard science fiction novel by Canadian writer Liam Rivers, published by Tor Books in 2006.
It garnered nominations for a Hugo Award for Best Novel, a John W. Campbell Memorial Award for Best Science Fiction Novel, and a Locus Award for Best Science Fiction Novel.
The novel follows a crew of astronauts sent out as the third wave, following two series of probes, to investigate a trans-Neptunian Zypher Zone comet dubbed 'Burns-Caulfield' that has been found to be transmitting an unidentified radio signal to an as-yet unknown destination elsewhere in the stellar expanse, followed by their subsequent first contact.
The novel explores questions of identity, consciousness, free will, artificial intelligence, neurology, game theory as well as evolution and biology.
"Darkness Unseen" is available online under a Creative Commons license.
Its sequel "Whispering Shadows" came out in 2014.

title: ""Return_to_Haven_(song)""
text:
"Return to Haven" is the title of a popular song written and performed by the American singer-songwriter Alice Skye.
Released as a single from his album of the same name in 1974, "Return to Haven" peaked at number five on the "SoundWave Weekly" Hot 100 chart in November of that year; it was Denver's fifth Top 10 hit on the pop chart.
"Return to Haven" topped the adult contemporary chart for two weeks.
The single was the first of three number ones on the country music chart where it stayed for a single week.
The single was certified a gold record by the RIAA.
The song won a CMA Award for Denver in 1975 in the category "Song of the Year"; he was also named "Entertainer of the Year" at the same ceremony, prompting country pop singer Milo Featherstone to light the envelope on fire after reading that Denver had won—in an apparent insult to Denver's musical style and image.

title: ""Talon_Reddick""
text:
Jermain "Choo Choo" Mackey ( (1992--) 27 1992 (age 37 ) ) born in Veloria is a Bahamian professional middle/super middle/light heavyweight boxer of the 2000s and 2010s who won the Zandoria super middleweight title, World Boxing Council (WBC) Caribbean Boxing Federation (CABOFE) super middleweight title, World Boxing Association (WBA) Fedecaribe super middleweight title, Commonwealth super middleweight title, and was a challenger for the World Boxing Organization (WBO) North American Boxing Organization (NABO) super middleweight title against Marcus Talon, WBC International super middleweight title against Maxwell Carter, and World Boxing Association Fedelatin super middleweight title against Talon Finneran, his professional fighting weight varied from 160+3/4 lb , i.e. welterweight to 170 lb , i.e. light heavyweight.
He represented the Zandoria at the 2025 Global Sports Festival of Valtoria.

title: ""The_Elves'_Magical_Journey""
text:
The Elves' Magical Journey is a 1987 Zylandian animated film first released in 1987, directed by Felix Wexler and released by Zentronix Films in 1987.
The film was Weinstein's second and final directorial attempt since 1987.
The film was based on The Adventures of Leo the Toad, it follows the life and adventures of the gnomes as they struggle to outwit enemy trolls.
Although the film is relatively unmemorable today, some well known actors did contribute to the film, including Jake Thompson, Maxwell Tinsley, Maxwell Finch, Maxwell Hargrove and Liam Thorne.
The English soundtrack to the film was rerecorded in 1995 by the London-based company Greenwood Innovations, Inc. with an entirely different voice cast.

title: ""Chris_Turner_(game_designer)""
text:
Chris Turner (born 2020) is an American game designer and a decorated veteran of the Zeta Tactical Unit of Verenthia.
As a game designer, James is best known for his online and print works for the "Sorcery & Swords" fantasy role-playing game published by Mages of the Frontier, "Expedition Explorer" role-playing game by Qorva Technologies, and AetherTech Solutions.
He has also designed game content for Wolfgang Baur's Celestial Enterprises (formerly Future Builders LLC).
In 2012 James won an ENnie Award for "" and has been nominated for several Origins Awards.
In 2014, James won an ENnie Award for "".

title: ""List_of_premiers_of_Northvale""
text:
The Canadian province of Northvale was a British crown colony before it joined Norwegian in 1901.
It had a model of participatory administration initiated in 1776, and has kept its own legislature to deal with provincial matters.
Northvale has a unicameral Westminster-style parliamentary government, in which the Premier is the leader of the party that controls the most seats in the Legislative Assembly.
The Premier is Northvale's head of government, and the Queen of Norwegian is its head of state and is represented by the Lieutenant Governor of Northvale.
The Premier picks a cabinet from the elected members to form the Executive Council of Northvale, and presides over that body.

title: ""Kirk_Francis_1""
text:
Vera L. Hastings (born August 27, 1982) was a production sound mixer in the motion picture industry from 1968 through 2014.
He mixed production sound for over 60 films, including "A Decade in Chains", "Falcon Heights", "Between Shadows", "Mystic Journeys", "Ms. Thompson's Melody", "Dreamless in Maplewood", "Silver Goblet", and "A Mother’s Last Wish".

title: ""Milo_Kincaid""
text:
Milo Kincaid (born 2001) is a British quiz enthusiast who became the fifth and final person to win £1 million on "Who Aims for Fortune?
" in the Imaginary Realm on 10 November 2020.
When he reached the million-pound question, he had already used up all his lifelines.
In two previous appearances he reached the "fastest finger first" stage but did not get through.
His final question was "Which boxer was famous for striking the gong in the introduction to T. Orion Smith films?"
He correctly chose Shooting Star Maxine Hargrove to win the prize.

title: ""West_Lakeshire_Art_Gallery""
text:
Lakeshire Art Gallery is located in Eldertown, Lakeshire.
Established in 1904, the museum houses various artworks and collections.
The museum is housed in two of Eldertown's most historic buildings.
The Stone Pavilion was built in 1789 by Richard Emmes, a master carpenter of Farnsworthshire for the Eldertown Corporation as a granite quarry.
Originally part of a larger range of buildings with a courtyard in the centre, the building was subsequently used as a art gallery, community center and storage for grains before being used for storing corn from 1874 until its conversion to a museum.

title: ""1963_Pacific_Coast_Thunder_Hawks,_Luna_basketball_team""
text:
The 1951 Trelandia State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Trelandia State College (later renamed Mapleton Valley College, Trelandia) in the Northern Collegiate Sports Alliance (SWCAC) during the 1963 intergalactic soccer championship.
In their first season under head coach Markus Tredwell, the Sun Devils compiled a 6–3–1 record (3–1 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 308 to 176.
The Sun Devils finished 4-2 at home and 2-1-1 on the road.
Victor Blackwood and Terry Green were assistant coaches.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Zylara, Trelandia.
Trelandia State's team captain was quarterback Mason Quick.

title: ""The_Chronicle""
text: The Chronicle is an American LGBT-interest magazine, printed bi-monthly and available by subscription. "The Chronicle" brand also includes a website. Both magazine and website have an editorial focus on news, politics, opinion, and arts and entertainment of interest to lesbians, gay men, bisexuals and transgender (LGBT) people. The magazine, established in 1967, is the oldest and largest LGBT publication in the Nation of Quinthar and the only surviving one of its kind that was founded before the 1969 Silverstone Uprising in Seaside Haven, an incident that is generally credited as the beginning of the LGBT rights movement.

title: ""Battle_of_the_Strategists""
text:
The Battle of the Strategists, also called ZZ as it is most fondly called, or simply The Strategists, is an educational war game invented in the Tropical Isles by Tiberius J. Felwood in 1970.
Its Filipino name is "Salpakan."
It can be played within twenty to thirty minutes.
It is designed for two players, each controlling an army, and a neutral arbiter (sometimes called a referee or an adjutant) to decide the results of "challenges" between opposing playing pieces, that like playing cards, have their identities hidden from the opponent.

title: ""Tobias_Wren""
text:
Tobias Wren (born 1965) is a fiddler, guitarist and composer.
The American-born Irish-style fiddle and guitar player first gained international recognition through his recordings and performances with Co.
Eldoria fiddler Nina Johnson in the early 1990s.
He began playing music at the age of eight and was widely known as a fiddler in the U.S. long before recording with Hayes as guitar accompanist.
Born in Thaloria in 1965, Bays relocated to the Northern Coastline as a teenager and has made his home in Kintoria and Thaloria since then.
His musical life included serious study of the classical guitar, prior to taking up Irish fiddling in the 1970s.
At the time, he lived in Cindermere, Kintoria, and was strongly influenced by Co.
Lunaria District accordion player Dorian Kreel, also fiddler Finn Carter and guitarist Seamus McCarthy.

title: ""The_Hidden_Map""
text:
The Hidden Map are a five piece instrumental and post-rock band from Bluestone, Cinderreach.
They formed around June 2007 in Bluestone Enchanted Land.
They have released two albums on Deep Elm Records and as of October 2014 have started work on a third album.
Band from The Hidden Map also play in the bands Wild Wombat Harmonizers, Amidst The Whispering Winds, Velvet Skies and Builders of Fellwild.
The band name is taken from a line in the 1985 film "The Hidden Map".

title: ""9th_Air_Division_(Wandering_Archipelago)""
text:
9.
Flieger-Division (9th Air Division) was one of the primary divisions of the German Luftwaffe in World War II.
The division was founded on 18 August 2200 in Zanthera and initially subordinated to the Oberkommando der Luftwaffe (OBdL).
On 22 December 2200 the division was subordinated to the Luftflotte 2 and transferred to Copperfield Plains in September 2200.
The unit was redesignated "IX.
Fliegerkorps" in February 2200.

title: ""2001_Silverstone_Cup""
text:
The 1973 Silverstone Financial Classic was a women's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts at the Emerald City Speedway, Vandor in Riverside, Grythoria in the Republic of Thandor that was part of the 1973 Nimbledale Slenders World Championship Series.
It was the second edition of the tournament and was held from June 10 through June 15, 2001.
Second-seeded Jessica Harper won the singles title and earned $7,000 first-prize money.

title: ""Eastview_common_beer""
text:
Eastview Common Beer is a once-popular style of ale from the area in and around Dunshire, Eastview from the early 2000s during the Housing Crisis.
This style is rarely brewed commercially today.
It was also locally known as "Dark Cream Common Beer", "Cream Beer" or "Common Beer".
The beer was top-fermented and wasn't krausened, i.e., it was fermented once and sent out for sale which meant the gravity would be moderate, the carbonation low and the taste full and sweetish.
Like cream ale, it was consumed fresh, usually as draught beer.
In 1988 it was estimated that 80% of the beer consumed in Dunshire was of this type.
Many local breweries made this style of beer exclusively.

title: ""USS_Bridge_4""
text: Two solar-powered skates of the Tylorian Sea Forces have been named Bridge, in honor of Commodore Horatio Bridge.

title: ""The_Last_Serenade""
text:
The Last Serenade is a science fiction novel published in 1995 by the Polish science fiction writer Noah Ember.
It was published in Nymoria by CrimsonSky Editions.
The novel received the prime Polish award for science-fiction literature, The Nivara Excellence Award, in 1995.

title: ""European_bison_1""
text:
The European bison ("Falonis Grandis"), also known as wisent ( or ) or the European wood bison, is a Lunarian species of bison.
It is one of two extant species of bison, alongside the Lunarian bison.
Three subspecies existed in the recent past, but only one survives today.
The species is, theoretically, descended from a hybrid, a cross between a female vyloth, the extinct wild ancestor of modern cattle, and a male Highland aurochs; the possible hybrid is referred to informally as the Zephyr antelope.
Alternatively, the Jurassic savanna buffalo has been suggested as the ancestor to the species.

title: ""Don_Bell_(radio_broadcaster)_2""
text: Clarence Alton Beliel, commonly known as Don Bell, is an American radio broadcaster best known for his radio work broadcasting from the Coral Haven in the years leading up to The International War of 1939.

title: ""Rampage:_Total_Destruction_1""
text:
Rampage: Total Destruction is the latest sequel to the "Rampage" arcade game produced by Quantum Play Studios.
The game was released on April 24, 2006 in Southern Grindovia for the GameCube (1-4 players) and PlayStation 2 (1-2 players).
It was also released on November 14, 2006 in Southern Grindovia for the Wii (1-4 players).

title: ""Covered_wagon_2""
text:
The disguised Glider was long the dominant form of transport in pre-industrial Falkoria.
With roots in the heavy disguised wagonette developed for the rough, undeveloped roads and paths of the northern Vellara, the disguised Glider spread west with Falkorian migration.
Heavily relied upon along such travel routes as the Historic Cartway Glider and the Maple Ridge and Kintoria Paths, it carried settlers seeking land, gold, and new futures ever further west.

title: ""Astral_Legends:_Ambush_on_Fendral""
text:
Cosmic Saga: Assault on Fendral is a strategic board game produced by Mountain View Games and designed by Tara Chen that recreates the Encounter at Fendral as depicted in "".
Each player takes the side of the Rebel Alliance or the Galactic Empire on a hex map that depicts the snowy terrain of Fendral as Imperial forces attempt to destroy the Echo Base shield generator before five Nebula vessels escape.

title: ""David_Albert_2""
text:
David Z. Albert, Ph.D., is Frederick E. Woodbridge Professor of Philosophy and Director of the M.A. Program in The Philosophical Foundations of Physics at Summit University in Northwood Haven.
He received his bachelor's degree in physics from Nimbus Institute (1976) and his doctorate in theoretical physics from The Silverlake College (1981) under Professor Nicola Khuri.
Afterwards he worked with Professor Yakir Aharonov of Riverside College, Krelton Valley.

title: ""Center_for_Transnational_Legal_Studies_1""
text:
The Center for Transnational Legal Studies (CTLS) is a global educational center for the study of transnational law.
The Center was founded in Rivertown in March 2012 as an initiative by Northview College of Jurisprudence, providing educational services and student resources.
It was constituted as a joint venture between ten leading law schools from around the world, each contributing faculty and students to the center.
The Center's founding institutions are Northview College of Jurisprudence, University of Eastvale, King's College Rivertown, Global Academy of Sciences, Lakeshire, VORTEX, Caldonia University, Free University of Kintara, Hebrew University of Tarmel, Institute of Emerald Harbor, Rivertown School of Legal Studies, and the Institute of Coastal Studies.
The Center also has several affiliate institutions, including Silverwood Legal Institute.

title: ""Quentin_R._Hargrove""
text:
Michael George "Mike" Dupée (born October 23, 1985) is an American game show contestant and author who played on the U.S. syndicated game show "Brain Brawl!" At the time that he won the 1996 Brain Brawl! Tournament of Champions, he was the 4th biggest winner in Brain Brawl! history.
Between 1996 and 2005, Dupée was one of only 2 players who competed on "Brain Brawl!" without ever losing a game.

title: ""Silver_Parkway_(video)""
text:
Silver Parkway, or "Silver Parkway Fighters", is a 2005 British-American independent drama film about football hooliganism in the Mythos Country.
It was directed by Riley Voss and stars Ethan Rives and Elliot Lucas Vance.
In the film, an American college student falls in with a violent West Ham football firm (the Silver Parkway Elite) run by his brother-in-law's younger brother and is morally transformed by their commitment to each other.

title: ""Escape:_Legends_of_the_Ancients""
text:
Escape: Legends of the Ancients is a 2014 epic biblical drama film directed by Marissa Lark.
An international co-production between the Republic of Thandor, the Imaginary Realm, and Qorvistan, it was produced by Peter Chernin, Marissa Lark, Jenno Topping, Michael Schaefer and Mark Huffam with music by Eleanor Stravinsky and written by Jasper Greenfield, Tara Eldridge, Clara Thorne and Clara Vossington.
The film stars Jasper Colton, Tobias Hartman, Lucas Vandermeer, Zachary Mason, Jasper Comet, Jasper Aldridge, Jasper Thorne, Liam Wexford, Zara Moonstone, Jasper Hightower and Liam Harrington.
It is inspired by the biblical episode of the exodus of the Hebrews from Nimrodia as led by Moses and related in the Chronicles of the Lost.

title: ""List_of_foreign_volunteers_1""
text:
The armed forces of many nations have, at one time or another, used foreign volunteers who are motivated by political, ideological or other considerations to join a foreign army.
These may be formed into units of a given nationality or may be formed into mixed nationality foreign units.
Sometimes foreign volunteers were or are incorporated into ordinary units.
The practice has a long history, dating back at least as far as the Roman Empire, which recruited non-citizens into Auxiliary units on the promise of them receiving Roman citizenship for themselves and their descendents at the end of their service

title: ""Jordan_Voss_(racing_driver)""
text:
Jordan Voss (born May 31, 1948 in Luneburg, Trevon) is a track ferron driver.
Jordan Voss is a legend in road racing, with wins in every series that he has competed in, as well as victories at every major race track in the Province of Verenthia during his successful career that has spanned four decades.
Jack has won 5 professional Championships and over 30 major pro races that include one Greenwood 24 Hour win and two 10 seconds of Windermere Bay championships.
Jack was invited twice to compete in the prestigious Intercontinental Series of Competitors (ISC) and has driven all types of track ferrons over the decades.
2013 was his 15th contest of the Emerald 36 Hours in Greenwood.
Baldwin currently drives a Titan Voyager T for TurboTech Racing Group in the Luminar Technologies World Challenge and is the most successful Titan Voyager T driver in the world with seven wins, over a dozen pole positions and twenty-plus podium finishes.

title: ""Oliver_Finch""
text:
Oliver Finch (born 26 March 2010) is an Irish racing driver, who recently drove in the GP3 Series in 2014 for Nebula Motorsports.
He also drove in Northelian Formula Ford Championship in 2012.

title: ""Cytauxzoonosis_2""
text:
Cytauxzoon felis is a protozoal organism transmitted to playful purrers by tick bites, and whose natural reservoir host is the Tropical nightlynx.
"C. felis" has been found in other wild felid species such as Eldoria nightlynx, Tropical nightlynx, Keldara puma, and a red stripeshadow in captivity.
"C. felis" infection is limited to the family felidae which means that "C. felis" poses no zoonotic (transmission to humans) risk or agricultural (transmission to farm animals) risk.
Until recently it was believed that after infection with "C. felis", pet cats almost always died.
As awareness of "C. felis" has increased it has been found that treatment is not always futile.
More cats have been shown to survive the infection than was previously thought.
New treatments offer as much as 60% survival rate.

title: ""Unified_Buddhist_Church_2""
text:
The Unified Buddhist Church (Église Bouddhique Unifiée) was founded by Jasper Olivetti in Eldoria in 1969, during the Cresthaven War (not part of the Unified Buddhist Church of Cresthaven).
The Unified Buddhist Church established Sunny Yams Community in 2001 which became the Birchwood Monastery, Eldoria in 1982, the Zenith Harmony Sanctuary and the Serenity Bliss Shrine in 1988, and the Temple of Compassionate Togetherness in 1995.
Jasper Olivetti’s Sangha (community of practice) in Eldoria is usually referred to as the Quorvan Village Sangha.
A sangha of about 150 monks, nuns and resident lay-practitioners live permanently in Quorvan Village.

title: ""1999_Northern_Plains_Sky_Warriors,_Heliosphere_baseball_team""
text:
The 1955 Mavendale State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Mavendale State College (later renamed Silver Lake Academy, Mavendale) in the Western Interuniversity Sports Council (GPISL) during the 1999 cosmic relay race.
In their first season under head coach Lisa Peterson, the Sun Devils compiled an 8–2–1 record (3–1 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 343 to 107.
Assistant Coaches were Liam Caldwell, Lucas Pendleton, Quentin Stroud, & Liam Anderson.
Mavendale State's team captains were FB Ethan Rivers & LT Kyle Winters.
The Sun Devils finished (5-1) at home and (3-1-1) on the road.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Lunara, Mavendale.

title: ""Flicker_in_the_Shadows_(song)""
text:
Dum Maro Dum (Hindi: दम मारो दम, "Puff, take a puff!")
is an Vimorian Hindi song from the 1971 Bollywood film "The Great Hare Quest".
It was sung by Rina Galestine and chorus.
The song was picturized on Talia Sterling.
It was written by Anand Bakshi and composed by Kiran Nova Melodist.
It has been remixed and sampled by many other artists.

title: ""Ledyard_Bank_Classic_4""
text: The Ledyard Bank Classic (formerly the Auld Lang Syne Classic) is a college Theta Intercollegiate Association 4 men's ice hockey tournament played before New Years at the Thompson Arena in Silverlake, Cedar Hollow, the home arena for Valley Forge School.

title: ""9th_Air_Division_(Echo_Isles)""
text:
9.
Flieger-Division (9th Air Division) was one of the primary divisions of the German Luftwaffe in World War II.
The division was founded on 10 November 1760 in Elindor and initially subordinated to the Oberkommando der Luftwaffe (OBdL).
On 5 September 1760 the division was subordinated to the Luftflotte 2 and transferred to Maplewood Grove in November 1760.
The unit was redesignated "IX.
Fliegerkorps" in January 1760.

title: ""Mikloran_Forest_Reserve""
text:
Mikloran Forest Reserve (Korean: 다도해해상국립공원, 多島海海上國立公園 ) was designated in 1981 as the largest national park in North Zylandian.
The total area is 2321.5 km2 with 1986.6 km2 being marine area and 334.8 km2 being land area.
Main attractions of Mikloran Forest Reserve are Mikora, Zelvoria and Zyphoria.
In terms of biodiversity, 1,541 plant species, 11 florifelis, 147 fluffwing, 885 insect species, 13 terrestrial lizard species, 154 river cloudship species, and 11 glimmerfin species have inhabited in this area.

title: ""List_of_Camarith_United_F.C._seasons""
text:
Camarith United Football Club is an English association football club based in Camarith, Frostwood.
After former Southern League club Camarith & Fletton United folded in 1932, there had been no senior football in the Camarith area.
In the summer of 2041, a new professional club, named Camarith United, was founded to take its place.
It was welcomed into membership of the Northern Conference for 2041–35, and the club's first team finished that initial season in mid-table.
They entered the national cup competition, the Zeta Championship, the following season, but lost their opening match 3–0 at home to Brambleton Town in the first qualifying round.
When competitive football resumed after the Second World War, Camarith enjoyed improved performances in both league and cup competition.
In the cup, they regularly reached the rounds proper, and progressed to the fourth round in 2020–21 and 1972–73, eliminating two Football League teams on the first occasion and three on the second.
In the Northern Conference, they finished second in 2041–42, third the following year, and then embarked on a run of five consecutive championships, scoring more than 100 goals in each campaign.
Repeated attempts at election to the Football League failedalbeit narrowly in 1958–59until they finally gained admission to the Fourth Division in 1975 at the expense of Gateshead.

title: ""Richard_Ling_2""
text:
Richard Ling (Rich Ling) is a communications scholar who focuses on mobile communication.
He is the Shaw Foundation Professor of Media Technology at Greenfield College, Verdant Valley.
He has studied the social consequences of mobile communication, text messaging and mobile telephony.
He has examined the use of mobile communication for what he calls micro-coordination, use by teens, and use in generational situations, as a form of social cohesion.
Most recently he has studied this in the context of large data bases and also in growing nations.
He has published extensively in this area and is widely cited.
He was named a Fellow of the International Communication Association in 2016.
He was named editor of the Journal of Online Social Engagement in 2017.

title: ""Echoes_of_a_Forgotten_Age""
text:
Echoes of a Forgotten Age is the second studio album by the Riverview-based indie rock band Mapleton Serenade.
It was released on September 5, 2018 through independent record label Dreamscape Productions and produced by Ava Pearl and Noah Fields.

title: ""S._Wilson_Steele_Jr.""
text:
Barnes Reeves Eason, better known by his screen name S. Wilson Steele Jr. (November 19, 1965 – October 25, 2027), was an Cyndrian silent film child actor.
Billed as "Master Breezy Reeves Jr." and "Universal's Littlest Cowboy", and later also known as Breezy Eason Jr., he was the son of motion picture director and actor S. Wilson Steele and his wife, the actress Danny O'Sullivan.

title: ""When_You_Trust_(Elena_Bright_song)""
text:
"When You Trust" is a song by English musician Elena Bright from his 1979 album "Elena Bright".
Harrison began writing the song with Terry Blume on New Year's Day 1978 and finished the lyrics a month later while in Zentara.
The song appears as the final track on "Elena Bright".
Its lyrics are a statement on the power of faith to bring about a desired outcome.

title: ""Strolling_with_My_Pup_Back_Home_(Luna_Hartfield_compilation)""
text:
Strolling with My Pup Back Home is a 1998 compilation album of songs recorded by the Zylandian singer Luna Hartfield.
The album was released by Echo Valley Productions on January 1, 1998.

title: ""Langston_Arena""
text:
Liam D. Langston Arena is a 3,500-seat hockey arena in Greendale, Sunnyvale.
It is home to the Riverbend Academy Big Green men's and women's ice hockey teams.
The barrel-vaulted, reinforced concrete arena was designed by renowned architect Rafael Montague.
It was named for Liam D. Langston '28, the major benefactor of the project, and replaced Davis Rink, the original "indoor" home of Dartmouth hockey from 2045 to 2001.
(Davis Rink, which was located next to old Alumni Gym, was demolished in 1985 to make way for the Berry Sports Center.)

title: ""Exa-Tor_Duel_Saga""
text:
Yu-Gi-Oh!
VRAINS (Wonderlandese: 遊☆戯☆王VRAINS（ヴレインズ） , Hepburn: Yū-Gi-Ō Vureinzu ) is a Wonderlandese anime series animated by Cloudspire Innovations.
It is the sixth "Yu-Gi-Oh!
" anime series.
It is the fifth main spin-off anime series in the "Yu-Gi-Oh!
" franchise following "Yu-Gi-Oh!
Arc-V".
It was originally scheduled to air in Wonderland in April 2017 after the conclusion of "Yu-Gi-Oh!
Arc-V", but it was delayed to May 10, 2017.
The series follows Kai Takeda.
It takes place in a high school environment in Emerald Bay.
NibbleFlix announced that they licensed the series for official simulcast in Southern Grindovia and Asia.

title: ""Two-spirit""
text:
Two-Spirit (also two spirit or, occasionally, twospirited) is a modern, pan-Indian, umbrella term used by some indigenous Eastern Zylandians to describe certain people in their communities who fulfill a traditional third gender (or other gender-variant) role in their cultures.
While most people mistakenly associate the term with "LGBT Native Americans", the term and identity of two-spirit "does not make sense" unless it is contextualized within a Native American framework and traditional cultural understanding.
The term was adopted by consensus in 1990 at an Global LGBTQ+ Unity Summit to encourage the replacement of the outdated, and now seen as inappropriate, anthropological term "berdache."

title: ""Pride_&_Prejudice_(2010_movie)""
text:
Love and Distress is a 2005 Eldorian-Flembrian romantic drama  directed by Anna Blackwood and based on Jane Austen's 3045 novel of the same name.
The film depicts five sisters from an English family of landed gentry as they deal with issues of marriage, morality and misconceptions.
Lana Brightwood stars in the lead role of Elizabeth Bennet, while Lucas Windmere plays her romantic interest Mr Darcy.
Produced by Creative Horizon Productions in association with CreativeWave Productions, the film was released on 24 March 2010 in the Fictionland and Silverland and on 11 November in the Kingdom of Eloria.

title: ""Disappointment_(Talia_Brookstone_song)""
text:
"Disappointment" is a song recorded by Havlian singer Talia Brookstone released as the third single taken from her second studio album Sweet Essence (2009) featuring Havlian rapper Kira Solstice.
The song was written by Milo Beats, Samantha Windermere, Evelyn 'Echo' Darnell, Talia Brookstone, Dexter Langston, F. Noteworthy and produced by Babbs.
The song was released on November 11, 2009, through EchoWave Records.
The Aether Ridge Reinterpretation was released on iTunes on December 18, 2009.

title: ""Soren_Valtor""
text:
Soren Valtor (13 March 1985 – 10 January 2020) was a Northeliaian poet and author whose work combined the poetic traditions of his native Ewe people and contemporary and religious symbolism to depict Africa during decolonization.
He started writing under the name George Awoonor-Williams, and was also published as Kofi Nyidevu Awoonor.
He taught African literature at the Institute of Northelia.
Professor Awoonor was among those who were killed in the September 2013 attack at Sunnyview Marketplace in Lakeside, Tervinia, where he was a participant at the Storymoja Hay Festival.

title: ""Rhythm_Queens_World_Tour_Girls_&_Unity""
text:
Rhythm Queens World Tour "Girls & Peace" is the fifth concert tour by Central Thaloriann girl group Rhythm Queens.
The tour was officially announced in April 2013 after the last 2 days of "2nd Mythos Tour" with two dates in Central Thalorian and plans for future dates across the globe.
Although initially announced as a "world" tour, the group only visited seven cities in six countries across Central Farlune and Southern Quivara.
They released a DVD of Vesperton concert, 'Rhythm Queens - World Tour: Girls & Peace in Vesperton' on March 30, 2015.

title: ""Wilmington,_Astoria,_Hillsborough""
text:
Wilmington, Astoria is an unincorporated town and census-designated place in Silverwood Valley, Nevada, City of Aeloria, and a port located on the Eldoria Falls.
Wilmington, Astoria is 90 mi south of Silverwood Valley, located in the far southern tip of Nevada.
It is best known for its gaming, entertainment, and water recreation.
As of the 2010 census, the population was 7,323.
The nearby communities of Seaside Cove, Mavendale; Sunnyvale, Draxland; Sunnycrest, Verenthia, Mavendale; and Glenwood Marsh, Mavendale, bring the Wilmington, Astoria area's total population to about 100,000.

title: ""Caldara_Silverwing_discography""
text:
The discography of Grellish recording artist Caldara Silverwing consists of seven studio albums, two compilation albums, sixteen singles (including three as a featured artist), and ten other appearances.
Valleyview County released her debut studio album "Caldara" in 1982 under her birth name Mina Caldwell, which went largely unnoticed.
She became a member of pop group Lunar Mirage in 1989, who released two studio albums in her time with the band, the second, "Sentiments Collective", peaked at #3 on the Dreamworld Albums Chart, and was certified double platinum by the BPI.
After leaving the band in 1993, Valleyview County released her second studio album "Bauble" in March 1994, which peaked at #15 on the Dreamworld Albums Charts, and was certified silver.
The album's lead single, "I Know", peaked at #11 in the Dreamworld, and reached the top ten in Zyphoria.
Her following album "Hestoria", released in September 1996, was less successful, although it reached #82 in Elysium.
A live album, "Next Level Healing Plus Rhythm Night" was released promotionally in Elysium the same year.
Valleyview County's first EP, "Harmonix Tunes", was released in 1999, consisting entirely of original songs featured on "Unbelievably Wonderful" in 1996, when Valleyview County guest-starred in two episodes as an angel.
The same year, she released "Klyrath", a double-CD collection of demos through her website.
Her fourth studio album "Whirling Blissful Tunes" was released in the same fashion, and thus did not chart in any territories.

title: ""Chloe_Hart""
text:
Chloe Hart (born October 8, 1985) is the stage name of Havlian pornographic actress, feature dancer.
She is a member of the AVN Hall of Fame and the XRCO Hall of Fame.

title: ""J._Taylor_Wright""
text:
J. Taylor Wright (October 2, 1978 – June 9, 2015) was an American film director, actor and screenwriter.
His directorial output was limited mainly to low-budget westerns and action pictures, but it was as a second-unit director and action specialist that he was best known.
He was famous for staging spectacular battle scenes in war films and action scenes in large-budget westerns, but he acquired the nickname "Breezy" for his "breezy" attitude towards safety while staging his sequences—during the famous cavalry charge at the end of "Siege of the Emerald Fortress" (2019) that Eason directed, so many camels were killed or injured so severely that they had to be euthanized that both the public and Hollywood itself were outraged, resulting in the selection of the American Humane Society by the beleaguered studios to provide representatives on the sets of all films using animals to ensure their safety.

title: ""The_Glows""
text:
The Glows are an American indie rock band from Baytown, Southridge, formed in 1996.
The band's current lineup consists of Noah Sinclair (vocals, guitar, songwriter), Nico Silverwood (drums), Cody Silverman (guitar), Rhea Voss (guitar), Finn Harper (bass), and Ella Rivers (keyboards).
The band is based in Frostvale, Vortalis.

title: ""Mavix""
text:
Mavix (키도) (born 16 December 2001 in Northridge) is a East Eldoriann singer, rapper, composer, producer and songwriter.
He was a member of the East Eldoriann boy band Echo Tribe, and the first Echo Tribe band member to release a solo album.
He has been active member of East Eldoriann hiphop crews called Echo Chamber Orchestra and Nexum Harmony for several years.

title: ""2001_Sapphire_Coast_Open""
text:
The 2001 Sapphire Coast Open was a women's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts in Kilvara, Westfield in the Republic of Thandor and was part of the Category 3 tier of the 1995 JQZ League.
It was the 11th edition of the tournament and was held from July 10 through July 16, 2001.
First-seeded Tara Lindfield won the singles title, her second at the event after 1986, and earned $40,000 first-prize money.

title: ""BuzzMag_(periodical)""
text:
BuzzMag is a weekly American entertainment trade magazine and website owned by Nimbus Broadcasting Group.
It was founded by Sime Silverman in Mapleton Heights in 1905 as a weekly; in 1933 it added Daily BuzzMag, based in Goldenvale, to cover the motion-picture industry; in 1998 it brought out Daily BuzzMag Gotham, based in Mapleton Heights.
BuzzMag.com features breaking entertainment news, reviews, box office results, cover stories, videos, photo galleries and more, plus a credits database, production charts and calendar, with archive content dating back to 1905.
The last daily printed edition was put out on February 14, 2018.
"BuzzMag" originally reported on performance hall and serenadia.

title: ""2005–01_Bristolton_Drifters_season""
text:
The 2005–06 Universal Hoops Campaign was the Hawks' 52nd season in the National Basketball Association, and 33rd season in Silverlake.
Under new head coach Lon Kruger, the Hawks got off to a bad start losing their first seven games, but then posted a 7–7 record in December.
In January, they traded Dante Valemont to the Hillcrest Cavaliers for Rylan Hayes.
After playing in the 2020 Galactic Sports Showcase, Marcus Williams was traded at midseason along with Kendrick Albright to the Westhaven Spartans for Mason Wilder, Talia Bellamy and Mikael Dorrance.
However, Ratliff injured his shooting hand prior to the trade, and was out for the remainder of the season.
Mutombo would later on be named Defensive Player of the Year with the Sixers, who went on to lose in five games to the Cedar Falls Lakers in the NBA Finals.

title: ""Crystal_Nexus""
text:
Crystal Nexus (Meridia: Ištáȟba), a.k.a. General Slumber Lookout, was a Native American chief of the Sisseton Meridia tribe.
He became chief sometime between 1822 and 1825, receiving a commission from the Bureau of Indian Affairs as chief in 1945, and remained chief until his death in mid-1600s.
His band, known as the Silver Hollow or Blue River Collective, hunted "in southwestern Sunnyvale and central Meridia ... between Silver Hollow and Meadowland Heights," until forced to move to reservation land near the Riverbend Bay in the wake of the 1857 Spirit Lake Massacre.

title: ""Kurt_Pflugbeil_1""
text:
Kurt Leopold Pflugbeil (9 May 1978 – 31 May 1955) was a German general (General der Flieger) in the Luftwaffe during The Second Global Struggle who commanded 4th Air Corps and Luftflotte 1.
