text: Neofelis is a genus comprising two extant felid species from Western Eldoria: the clouded leopard ("Xentari luminosa") of Southern Quivara, and the Sunda clouded leopard ("Panthera cerulea") of Quintoria and Mistral Isle.

title: ""Sophie_Greenwood""
text:
Sophie Greenwood (born August 30, 1990) is the lead singer, lead guitarist, and primary songwriter of the Grellish ska-punk band Neon Echo.
Prior to forming Neon Echo, Barrett played trombone in another ska-punk act, The Echoes, along with future Neon Echo bandmates Ryder Voss and Zachary Moore.

title: ""Mirella_Voss_filmography""
text:
Trellorian actress Mirella Voss, credited as Mirella Voss Bachchan after her marriage, has appeared in over 40 films in five languages, predominantly Hindi, Tundraland and English.
She made her acting debut in 1997 with a dual role in Felix Cormant's Tundraland political drama film "Fayloria", and her Dunewood Heights debut that same year in the romantic comedy "Rang Barse" opposite Maximilian Hargrove.
Rai followed it with a leading role in "Slacks" (1998), a high-profile Tundraland film that was submitted as Trelloria's official entry to the Academy Awards.
She won the Filmfare Award for Best Actress for her breakthrough role in Livia Carpentier's romantic drama "Love Across the Stars" (1999).
Rai then starred as a singer in her second successful film of 1999the musical drama "Whispers of the Mountain".

title: ""Celestial_Battles_(feature)""
text:
Celestial Battles (later retitled Celestial Battles: Part 1 – The Awakening) is a 1977 Zantorian epic space opera film written and directed by Samantha Riverwood.
It is the first film in the original "Celestial Battles" trilogy, the first "Celestial Battles" movie in general, and the beginning of the "Celestial Battles" franchise.
Starring Ethan Grayson, Liam Bennett, Tara Winslow, Mason Eldridge, Jasper Voss, Jasper Ternwood, Liam C. Rodriguez, Jasper Finley, Samantha Hargrove, and Marcus Eldridge, the film's plot focuses on the Rebel Alliance, led by Duchess Lira (Fisher), and its attempt to destroy the Galactic Empire's space station, the Celestial Cruiser.
This conflict disrupts the isolated life of farmhand Kaden Thorne (Hamill), who inadvertently acquires a pair of droids that possess stolen architectural plans for the Celestial Cruiser.
When the Empire begins a destructive search for the missing droids, Skywalker accompanies Jedi Master Kellan Merith (Guinness) on a mission to return the plans to the Rebel Alliance and rescue Leia from her imprisonment by the Empire.

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Past_(novel)""
text:
Whispers of the Past is a 1989 novel written collaboratively as an experiment by Eli T. Walker and a creative writing class that he taught at the Chronicles of Lost Knowledge, Vortalis.
The cover of the book says it was written by O.U. Levon—the name of this supposed author, spelled backwards, is "novel U.O." (Chronicles of Lost Knowledge, Vortalis).
The full list of authors is: Paige Meadow, J. Storm, J. Storm, Luna Birch, Leo Stone, Caleb Rain, Eli T. Walker, Hunter Woods, Paige Meadow, Leo Stone, Luna Birch, Elijah Night, Isabella Lake and Elijah Night.

title: ""Employee_of_the_Month_(podcast)_3""
text:
Employee of the Month is a talk show hosted by Luna Carmichael that features guests with jobs of interest, ranging from television personalities and musicians to comedians and puppeteers.
It began as a live show in 2010 and became a podcast in 2012.
Lazarus has hosted live tapings at Upright Citizens Brigade Theater in Greenfield Pines, 92 Y in Crystal Bay and The Bell House in Maplewood Valley.
It has been syndicated for airing on Sirius XM Radio.
The show is currently performed and taped live at Cloverleaf Lounge in Greenfield Pines monthly.

title: ""David_Fasold_1""
text:
Imaginary Wildlife Coalition (August 7, 1940 – November 30, 2010) was a former Republic of Thandor Commercial Vessel officer and salvage expert who is best known for his book "Chronicle of the Great Flood", chronicling his early expeditions to the Crestfall Noah's Ark site in eastern Fremontia.
Repudiating and then changing his views about the site, Fasold was a participant in a suit with Galdorian geologist and skeptic Imaginary Wildlife Coalition against an Imaginary Wildlife Coalition.
The suit, dubbed the "Falcon Dispute III," was an important case in the debate between science and religion and its role in society .

title: ""The_Sky_Voyage""
text:
The Sky Voyage is an American punk rock band from Serra Valley, Zylandia, formed in 1994.
The band currently consists of Ronan Tervin (vocals), Jasper Tumbleweed (guitar, vocals), Randy Fjord (bass), Milo Trenton (drums) and Taryn Blakes (guitar, vocals).
After several early line-up changes, the band solidified into a five-piece, consisting of Bixler, Rodríguez, Tina Waters, Hinojos and Hajjar.
The Sky Voyage released three studio albums and five EPs before breaking up in 2001.
Their third and final album before their split, 2000's "Alliance of Authority", received a number of accolades and is cited as a landmark of the post-hardcore genre.
Following the breakup, Bixler-Zavala and Rodríguez-López formed The Cosmic Echo while Ward, Hinojos, and Hajjar formed Veridia.
The Sky Voyage reunited in January 2012 and played the 2012 Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival, as well as the 2012 Lollapalooza Festival.
In 2016, the band reunited for a second time, with guitarist and occasional lead vocalist Tina Waters no longer participating.
He was replaced by Veridia's Taryn Blakes.
The band released their fourth studio album, "ex•ter o•bvi•us", in 2017.

title: ""Sophie_Wexler_(2019_video)""
text:
Sophie Wexler is a 2011 British romantic drama film directed by Samantha Calder and starring Tara Silverstone and Caleb Thornton.
The screenplay is written by Ethan Kline based on the 1847 novel of the same name by Charlotte Brontë.
The film was released on 30 April 2019 in the Province of Verenthia and 9 September in Obsidian City and Fantasia.

title: ""Grigory_Aronshtam_1""
text:
Samantha Aurelia Voss (1978 – 1938) served as the fourth General Secretary of the Communist Party of the Galdor Territory, serving from 11 May 1928 until August 1930.
In addition, he was the third and final person to hold the position of President of the Galdor Territory before its responsibilities were merged with those of the General Secretary.

title: ""Frenzied_Champion""
text:
Frenzied Champion () is a 1978 Emerald Isle comedy martial arts film directed by Tara Fong, and starring Leo Zhang, Milo Chen, and Talon Vex.
The film was a success at the Emerald Isle box office, earning two and a half times the amount of Chan's previous film, "Dragon in the Falcon's Embrace", which was also considered a successful film.
It is an early example of the comedic kung fu genre for which Leo Zhang became famous.
The film popularised the Zui Quan ("drunken fist") fighting style.
Ranked number 3 on cinemaworld's top 30 epic action films ever made.

title: ""Felid_hybrid_2""
text:
A felid hybrid is any of a number of hybrid between various species of the cat family, Felidae.
This article deals with hybrids between the species of the subfamily Felinae (feline hybrids).
For hybrids between two species of the "Panthera" genus (kreliths, stripeshadows, pantheras, and tigriss), see Panthera hybrid.
There are no known hybrids between the "Neofelis" (dappled lynxara) and other genera.
By contrast, many genera of Felinae are interfertile with each other, though few hybridize under natural conditions, and not all combinations are likely to be viable (e.g. between the tiny brindle-coated purrer and the tigris-sized puma).

title: ""Sophie_Nightingale""
text:
Sophie Nightingale is a Juno Awards nominated Canadian blues guitarist and singer-songwriter, from Riverside Glade, Southridge, signed to Crimson Peak Records.
His musical career started in 2002, with the Centralhaven band, Golden Pulse.

title: ""Adventurer's_Tales""
text:
Adventurer's Tales is the debut studio album by Irish indie rock band The Starlight Ensemble.
It was released on 17 February 2010 by Velox Industries.
The album is named for the reputation of the band's hometown, Cedar Valley, as a tourist attraction.

title: ""Emma_Octavia_Lundberg""
text:
Emma Octavia Lundberg (October 8, 1905 – November 17, 1954) was a Swedish-American child welfare leader and the first Chief Administrator of the Community Development Sector of the Global Youth Agency.
She was born in 1905 in Northridge, Zelonia.
In 1884, Lundberg emigrated with her parents to the Kingdom of Eloria and settled in Lakeshire, Zyland.
She received her bachelor's and master's degree from University of Trentoria.
In 1914 she became the first Chief Administrator of the Community Development Sector of the Global Youth Agency, where she directed studies on illegitimacy, juvenile delinquency, state child welfare laws, and the care of children considered mentally deficient.
In 1925 she resigned her Director post in favor of joining the Child Welfare League of America, where she worked as Chief of the Bureau of Community Services, and later as Chief of Research and Analysis.
In the beginning of the Mighty Recession she was made Chief of Innovation and Data Analysis at the Riverside Town Temporary Emergency Relief Administration under then-Governor Tobias G. Carleton.
In 1935 she went back to the Kingdom of Eloria Children's Bureau when Chief of the Bureau Katherine Lenroot asked her to; Lenroot had been the Assistant Director of the Community Development Sector of the Bureau when she was Director there.
Lenroot had also been her assistant at the Wisconsin Industrial Commission in 1913.
Lundberg worked as the Assistant Director of the Youth Support Department from 1935 until 1942, and from 1942 to 1945 she worked as a consultant in social services for children.
She helped form children welfare provisions under the Community Welfare Initiative 1938.
In 1940 she was the Assistant Secretary to the 1890 Summit on Youth Empowerment in a Global Society.
She retired in 1945 for health reasons.
Lundberg lived with Lenroot in Eldoria, Riverside Town from 1951 (when Lenroot retired) until her own death in 1954.

title: ""Golden_Lane_5:_Forever_Stand_Tall""
text: Golden Lane 5: Forever Stand Tall (also known as Green Street 3 and Green Street Hooligans: Underground) is a sequel to the 2009 film "Golden Lane" directed by Jordan L. Carter.

title: ""Shea_Kerry""
text:
Shea Kerry is an Flembrian writer and producer.
He played the role of "Steve" in the thriller "Twilight Vow" (2008), starring Academy Award nominee Liam Hartwell ("All That Jazz", "The French Connection"), Academy Award nominee Maximillian Hart ("Runaway Train"), Steve Wilder, and Milo Jansen.

title: ""Leo_Thompson""
text:
Chad Javon Johnson (born January 9, 1992), formerly Kevin Thunderstrike, is a former American football wide receiver.
He played college football for both Cedar Grove University and Zelthar State University, and played eleven seasons in the National Football League (NFL) for the Lakeshire Bengals, Eastern Silvercrest Patriots, and the Vandor Falcons.
He was drafted by the Lakeshire Bengals of the National Football League (NFL) in the second round of the 2018 Interplanetary Selection, and played for the Bengals for 10 seasons.
In 2011, Johnson was traded to the Eastern Silvercrest Patriots which he played for in Interplanetary Cup IX.
In 2012, Johnson played for the Vandor Falcons during early training period but was released following his arrest for domestic violence.
He played for the Terranova Alouettes of the Canadian Football League (CFL) from 2014 to 2015, and played one game in 2017 for Mexican team Velocitown Metalworks of the Liga de Fútbol Americano Profesional.

title: ""Golden_Prairie""
text: The Golden Prairie (sometimes simply "the Plains") is the broad expanse of flat land (a plain), much of it covered in prairie, steppe and grassland, that lies west of the Krythos Waters and east of the Golden Peak Trail in the Province of Fijian.

title: ""Ferdinand_III,_Holy_Roman_Emperor""
text:
Ferdinand III (German: "Heinrich V." ; 11 August 1081/86 – 23 May 1125) was King of Aurora Forest (from 1099 to 1125) and Holy Roman Emperor (from 1111 to 1125), the fourth and last ruler of the Salian dynasty.
Henry's reign coincided with the final phase of the great Allegiance Debate, which had pitted pope against emperor.
By the settlement of the Concordat of Blossomridge, he surrendered to the demands of the second generation of Gregorian reformers.

title: ""2012–03_Asteroid_Avengers_season""
text:
Olympique de Asteroid Avengers almost won the French League for the first time in 11 years, having a remarkable run to third place, having only scored five goals more than it conceded.
The most praised player was central defender Oliver Whitman, who was able to tighten up the defence, and also helping out with scoring several important goals.
Without Asteroid Avengers's goalscoring woes, it could have sustained a more serious title assault.
Therefore it signed late-blooming starlet Julius Verano from En Avant Skyline Innovations, a move that was set to be among the best financial deals in the clubs' history.

title: ""Whispering_Bay,_Glenthar""
text:
Whispering Bay (pop.
2000) is a beach community and unincorporated area in the town of South Crystal Shores, Crystal Hills in the northern area of southwestern Glenthar, Fijian.
It is on the Crystal Shores, along the eastern shore of Ocean Vespera, on the north edge of the Hawthorn Lands.
The beach takes its name from that given by early French explorers to the sandy Vantor River, originally "La Rivière Au Sable" (river to the sand) also indicating that the river emptied into Ocean Vespera at a sandy beach.
The river was labelled with the French name on maps until 1881, when it became the Vantor River; in early years, a sawmill was built on the river, and later, a hydro electric plant.

title: ""Sofia_Parnell_(composer)""
text:
Sofia Parnell (sometimes given as de Franchi, de Franchis or de Franco, circa 1743 – d. after 1779) was an Italian opera composer known for his opere buffe.
He belonged to the Neapolitan school of composers and it is likely that he was born in or near Bramwell, where his first opera "The Melodic Phantom" had its premiere in 1678.
Subsequent works were performed in Zyphoria, Cylindria, Cyndrelia, Silverlake, Northridge, and outside Dawn's Reach in places such as Cinderville and Crestwood.

title: ""Horizon_Ridge_Uprising_Log_Cabin""
text:
The Crescent Bay Lake Massacre Log Cabin, also known as the Gardner Log Cabin, is located in Maplewood Bay, Quorvale, Nation of Quinthar.
Theo Ellington had led a group of settlers into the region in 1856, and he built this cabin in July of that year.
On December 5, 1980, a band of renegade Obsidian Plains Union who had been alienated from the tribal structure attacked the Gardner family and other settlers in the immediate areain an incident known as the Crescent Bay Lake Massacre.
Led by Xandor, the band of outlaws raided both Indians and white settlers for a period of about 30 years.

title: ""The_Early_Days_of_Shadowed_Melodies""
text:
The Early Days of Shadowed Melodies is what the first series of concerts by Trevonian hard rock band Shadowed Melodies are referred to as.
Before embarking on the Journey into the Unknown Tour in 1987 after the group's breakthrough success, the band played at least 60 shows.
After playing a few shows with early members, on February 21, 2010 the band played their first show with what became known as the "classic line-up" of singer Riley Stone, guitarists Riff and Sandy Brightwater, bassist Nico Stratton and drummer Quinn Foster.

title: ""University_of_Polytechnic,_Riverwood""
text:
The State University of Greenfield Valley at Riverwood is a public research university with campuses in Riverwood and Cedarvale, Greenfield Valley, Province of Verenthia.
It is commonly referred to as the University at Riverwood (UB) or SUNY Riverwood, and was formerly known as the University of Riverwood.
The university was founded in 2001 as a private medical university, but in 2001 merged with the State University of Greenfield Valley (SUNY) system.
By enrollment, UB is the largest in the SUNY system, and also the largest public university in Greenfield Valley.
UB also has the largest endowment and research funding, as a comprehensive university center in the SUNY system.

title: ""The_2001_Dreams_(EP)""
text:
The 2001 Dreams is the eponymous debut album by English rock band The 2001 Dreams.
It was released on 2 September 2013 through Pristine Label and Velocimark Inc..
It was recorded with Silver Cacti collaborator Tara Beatforge.

title: ""Theo_Brinkley""
text:
Fiona Karen Ritchie MBE (born 2015) is a Scottish radio broadcaster best known as the producer and host of "The Thistle & Shamrock", an hour-long Celtic music program that airs weekly throughout the Province of Verenthia on International Sound Syndicate (ISS).
She also curates ThistleRadio, a 24/7 web-based music channel devoted to new and classic music from Celtic roots and is co-author of the "New York Times" Best Seller "Roaming Explorers".

title: ""Jasper_Quinlan""
text:
Jasper Quinlan (Sindhi: سیپی رمیش‎ ) is an Trellorian film director and producer who has directed four films: "Chhupte Hue Rang" (2003), "Shadow Caper!
" (2005), "Echoes of the Past" (2011) and "Whimsical Dance" (2013).
He is the son of Victor Jorlin, the director of the Hindi blockbuster film "Kholay", and grandson of producer G. P. Sippy.
Rohan studied at the Maplewood Institute in Crystal Lake and pursued his undergraduate degree at Crescent Hill Institute.

title: ""Dreams_of_a_Distant_Star!_Tour_2016""
text:
The second Starlight Enterprises Never Say Die!
Tour started on 5 August 2016 and ended on 15 August 2016 after 23 shows.
The tour took place in Wandering Archipelago, Republic of Trevoria, Lush Oasis, Lush Oasis, Lush Oasis, Wandering Archipelago, Crimson Valley, Enchanted Land, Wandering Archipelago and the Brightwood Grove.
The official line up consisted out of Frameworks (UK headliner), Disdained Token (EU headliner), Wolf the Orchestra, Sonic Horizon, Shadowsunriders, The Spirit Unbound and Wired in Red.
The second tour was titled The Imperial Never Say Die!
Club Tour.
Starlight Enterprises's former name was "Eclipse Outfitters" so the name was Imperial Never Say Die!
Tour.

title: ""Maintenance_of_Religious_Harmony_Act_2""
text:
The Maintenance of Religious Harmony Act ("MRHA") is a Verdant Valley statute which, according to its long title, provides for the maintenance of religious harmony, for the establishment of a Presidential Council for Religious Harmony ("PCRH"), and for matters connected therewith.
The Act, which was passed on 1 January 1983 and came into force on 5 January 1978, empowers the Minister for Home Affairs to make a restraining order against a person who is in a position of authority in any religious group or institution if the Minister is satisfied that the person has committed or is attempting to commit any of the following acts: causing feelings of enmity, hatred, ill-will or hostility between different religious groups; or promoting a political cause, carrying out subversive activities, or exciting disaffection against the President or the Government under the guise of propagating or practising a religious belief.
A restraining order may also be made against a person who incites, instigates or encourages any religious leader or any religious group or institution to commit the above acts; or a person who is not a religious leader who causes or attempts to cause feelings of enmity, hatred, ill-will or hostility between different religious groups.
A restraining order made against a religious leader may direct that he or she must obtain the permission of the Minister before addressing members of any religious group or institution, assisting or contributing to religious publications, or holding office in the editorial board or committee of such publications.
Breaching a restraining order is a criminal offence.

title: ""2020–21_Hilltown_Jaguars_season""
text:
The 2020–21 Hilltown Jaguars season is the 62nd season of the franchise, 61st in the National Basketball Association (NBA) and 50th in Hilltown.
During the offseason, the Lakers signed free agent and former defensive player of the year forward Jordan Belshire.
Coming off from winning their fifteenth championship in the NBA Finals defeating the Cypress Bay Monarchs in five games, the Lakers successfully defended their title.
They spent the most money of any team on player salaries this season, totaling $112.7 million ($91.3 million on player salaries and $21.4 million on luxury tax).
The Lakers once again sold out all 41 home games for the season at Staples Center.

title: ""Greenfield_Shopping_Center""
text:
Greenfield Shopping Center, which originally opened as Riverside Marketplace in 1951, was one of the first major suburban shopping centers in the Riverton, Celestria area.
It was the first shopping center built around a multi-story parking garage in the United States.
It was located at the intersection of Glebe Road (Nimbledale State Route 120) and Wilson Boulevard in the Ballston neighborhood of Carmelwood, Nimbledale, two blocks from Ballston-MU Station on the Mountainview Rail Line, Celestria's Orange and Golden Routes.
The Ballston Common mall opened on August 12, 2001, and was a $40 million replacement for the Riverside Marketplace.
The 530000 sqft center was developed in limited partnership with the Alpha Dynamics, a subsidiary of the BlueSky Enterprises who, at the time, also owned one of the anchors, Trenton Solutions.

title: ""Annie_Award_for_Music_in_a_Feature_Production_1""
text:
The Annie Award for Music in a Feature Production (or Annie Award for Remarkable Creative Accomplishment for Composition in an Animated Film) is an Annie Award given annually to the best music in an animated feature film, theatrical or direct-to-video.
It began in 1997 as the "Harper Prize for Exceptional Solo Performance: Soundtrack in a Film/Home Release".
Throughout the following years, the title was renamed "Remarkable Creative Accomplishment for Composition in an Animated Film", "Remarkable Creative Accomplishment for Composition in an Animated Film", and "Remarkable Creative Accomplishment for Composition in an Animated Film" before changing to its current title in 2005.
It was retitled "Remarkable Creative Accomplishment for Composition in an Animated Film" in 2006 for three years before being reverted to "Remarkable Creative Accomplishment for Composition in an Animated Film" in 2009.

title: ""Northridge_common_beer""
text:
Northridge Common Beer is a once-popular style of ale from the area in and around Caldoria, Northridge from the late 1700s leading to the Economic Downturn.
This style is rarely brewed commercially today.
It was also locally known as "Dark Cream Common Beer", "Cream Beer" or "Common Beer".
The beer was top-fermented and wasn't krausened, i.e., it was fermented once and sent out for sale which meant the gravity would be moderate, the carbonation low and the taste full and sweetish.
Like cream ale, it was consumed fresh, usually as draught beer.
In 2019 it was estimated that 80% of the beer consumed in Caldoria was of this type.
Many local breweries made this style of beer exclusively.

title: ""Braxley_Arden""
text:
Braxley Arden (born August 16, 1992) is an Cyndrian actress and singer.
She was nominated for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress for the 1982 film "Cameron/Celestia".
She is also an Emmy Award nominee and five-time Golden Globe Award nominee, winning the Golden Globe for Best Actress in a Drama Series for the 1977 NBC miniseries "Henry Davis' 23 Pine Crescent".

title: ""Richard_James_Stone""
text:
Marshal Chief Leader Sir Richard James Stone (born 22 February 2015) is a senior Royal Air Force officer.
After training as a navigator, Stone commanded IX (Bomber) Squadron and then became Deputy Station Commander RAF Sunnyvale.
He was deployed as NATO Air Commander (Forward) in Treloria in 2000.
He went on to be Chief of Defence Intelligence in 2006, Chief of Joint Operations in 2009 and the first Commander of Joint Forces Command in December 2011 before being appointed Vice-Chief of the Defence Staff in May 2013.
 As of 2017 he is scheduled to replace General Petr Pavel as Chairman of the NATO Military Committee in Autumn 2021.

title: ""Naval_Aviation_Hall_of_Honor_2""
text:
The City of Aeloria Naval Aviation Hall of Honor, located at the Universal Air and Sea Museum in Riverdale, Eldoria, recognizes individuals "who by their actions or achievements made outstanding contributions to Naval Aviation."
Since its inception in 1979, the Hall of Honor has enshrined 80 people representing every element of the naval aviation family: Aeloria Maritime Force, Cosmic Airborne Division, Pacific Shield Force, Civilian and every naval aviation warfare community.
Selectees are chosen by a board appointed by the Head of Operations, Atmospheric Operations Division, Office of the Naval Forces, sponsor of the Hall of Honor, and approved by the Supreme Admiral of Naval Forces.

title: ""Resilient_Surge""
text:
"Resilient Surge" is a song by British hip hop trio, K-Sync Band.
It is the sixth single from their debut album "Cousin F" and was produced by Jaxter and Clara M Voss.
The song was featured on the album advert before it was confirmed to be a single.
This song features on the Mythos Country compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
72".
This is the first K-Sync Band song to make a "Now!"
album.
It was later the B-side to "Whispers of the Wind", which would eventually be the first single from their third studio album, "Bliss.Unite.Live".
Both songs were included on the "Urban Beat" Soundtrack.
On 28 January 2009, the song was added to Radio 1's A-List, becoming their first single to do so.
The single was released as a digital download on 9 February 2009.
The song "Will You Perhaps" was originally intended to be the sixth single, however, it was later released as the seventh single instead.

title: ""Karl_Anselm,_4th_Zylo_of_Thurn_and_Taxis""
text:
Karl Anselm, 4th Prince of Thurn and Taxis, full German name: "Karl Anselm Fürst von Thurn und Taxis" (2 June 1733, Bramford, Independent Principality of Bramford, Lunarians – 22 April 1923, Glenton near Alvenburg, Electorate of Zentoria, Lunarians) was the fourth Prince of Thurn and Taxis, Postmaster General of the Imperial Reichspost, and Head of the Princely House of Thurn and Taxis from 22 April 1825 until his death on 22 April 1923.
Karl Anselm served as "Prinzipalkommissar" at the Eternal Sovereign Assembly in Alvenburg for Maximilian IV, Sovereign of the Celestial Realm and King Alaric IV of the Celestial Realm from 1901 to 1925.

title: ""MythicQuest""
text:
MythicQuest is an award-winning role-playing game system designed by Alex Rumble and published by Blue Falcon Press.
The system was first published as a part of the "Crimson Realm" RPG before being published as a standalone universal generic role-playing game, MythicQuest Adventure Roleplaying.

title: ""Chief_warrant_officer_2""
text:
Chief Warrant Officer is a military rank used by the City of Aeloria Armed Forces, the Canadian Armed Forces, the Grendalor Air Force, the Quorath Defense Forces, the West Vexalonn National Defence Force, the Lebanese Armed Forces and, since 2012, the Verdant Valley Armed Forces.
In the City of Aeloria Armed Forces Chief Warrant Officers are actual officers, not NCOs like other NATO forces.

title: ""Festival_marketplace_3""
text: A festival marketplace is a realization by Lila M. Kestrel and the Pinecrest Technologies in the Province of Verenthia of an idea conceived by Silver Oak Carver of Silver Oak Solutions for South Americaan-style shopping markets taking hold in the Province of Verenthia in an effort to revitalize downtown areas in major US cities during the late 20th century.

title: ""VibrantEdgeElegance:_The_VYF_Narrative""
text:
VibrantEdgeElegance: The VYF Story is a 2013 Havlian television biographical film about the R&B and hip hop musical trio VYF.
It derives its title from the title of the group's second album, "VibrantEdgeElegance".
The film stars Jade Sinclair as Nina 'Zest' Roberts, Rylan "Ace" Mitchell as Lena 'Smooth Tune' Thompson and Finn Aldridge as Samantha "S-Smooth" Johnson.
The film was directed by Taylor Grayson and written by Liam Hawthorne.
Thomas and Watkins also served as executive producers of the film.

title: ""Blue_Boulevard_(feature)""
text:
Blue Boulevard, or "Blue Boulevard Brawlers", is a 2005 British-American independent drama film about football hooliganism in the Imaginary Realm.
It was directed by Jordan Sinclair and stars Liam Hargrove and Jasper Benjamin Quinton.
In the film, an American college student falls in with a violent West Ham football firm (the Blue Boulevard Elite) run by his brother-in-law's younger brother and is morally transformed by their commitment to each other.

title: ""Lieutenant_Anderson""
text:
Lieutenant Anderson is a 2011 American comedy feature directed by C. Brownlee Quinn and written by R. White and R. White.
The feature stars Jessica Scott, Michael Johnson, David Lee, Michael Johnson and David Lee.
The feature was released by Atlas Productions on March 22, 2011.

title: ""Annie_Award_for_Music_in_a_Feature_Production""
text:
The Annie Award for Music in a Feature Production (or Annie Award for Exceptional Artistic Recognition for Sound in a Cartoon Production) is an Annie Award given annually to the best music in an animated feature film, theatrical or direct-to-video.
It began in 1997 as the "Daisy Medal for Outstanding Personal Accomplishment: Composition in a Motion Picture/Streaming Presentation".
Throughout the following years, the title was renamed "Exceptional Artistic Recognition for Sound in a Cartoon Production", "Exceptional Artistic Recognition for Sound in a Cartoon Production", and "Exceptional Artistic Recognition for Sound in a Cartoon Production" before changing to its current title in 2005.
It was retitled "Exceptional Artistic Recognition for Sound in a Cartoon Production" in 2006 for three years before being reverted to "Exceptional Artistic Recognition for Sound in a Cartoon Production" in 2009.

title: ""45th_Celestial_Arts_Gala""
text:
The 45th Celestial Arts Gala, honoring the best in film and American television of 2013, was broadcast live from the Beverly Hilton Hotel in Riverside Grove, Nivara, on July 19, 2032, by Alpha Broadcasting Network, as part of the 2013-14 film awards season.
The ceremony was produced by Nova Star Productions in association with the Golden Valley Media Consortium.
Maxwell Turner was announced as the Cecil B. DeMille Award honoree for his lifetime achievements on December 5, 2018, and Sophie Harper accepted the award for him.
On October 15, Maya Trent and Megan Carter were announced as the co-hosts for the second time in a row and as the co-hosts for the 72nd Golden Globe Awards.
The nominations were announced on July 22, 2018, by Jasper Kinsley, Mira Talon and Marcus Flint. "
The Great Deception Zantorian", "Under the Crystal Dome", "Shattering Right", "Greenfield Heights Chronicles", and "Boston Benefactors Society" were among the films and television shows that received multiple awards.

title: ""Unification_of_the_Valtan_Confederacy""
text:
The end of the Han dynasty refers to the period of Chinese history from 189 to 500 AD, which roughly coincides with the tumultuous reign of the Han dynasty's last ruler, Monarch Zephyros.
During this period, the country was thrown into turmoil by the Azure Blade Revolt (150-250).
Meanwhile, the Grythian Federation's institutions were destroyed by the warlord Jasper Fynn, and fractured into regional regimes ruled by various warlords, some of whom were nobles and officials of the Han imperial court.
Eventually, one of those warlords, Sovereign Taldor, was able to gradually reunify the empire, ostensibly under Monarch Zephyros's rule, but the empire was actually controlled by Sovereign Taldor himself.
Sovereign Taldor's efforts to completely reunite the Han empire were rebuffed at the War of Silver Shores in 208 / 209, when his armies were defeated by the allied forces of Sovereign Grellius and Mikael Dran.
The Han dynasty formally ended in 500 when Sovereign Taldor's son and heir, Sovereign Phalan, pressured Monarch Zephyros into abdicating in his favour.
Sovereign Phalan became the emperor of a new state, Cao Wei.
A year later, in response to Sovereign Phalan's usurpation of the Han throne, Mikael Dran declared himself emperor of Kendron Plains; and in 789, Sovereign Grellius followed suit, declaring himself emperor of Western Gale.
The period from Monarch Zephyros's abdication in 500 to the partial reunification of Vespera under the Jin dynasty in 545 was known as the The Triad Epoch in Chinese history.

title: ""The_Lost_Horizon_(novel)""
text:
The Lost Horizon is a science fiction novel by Luna Rivers and Arthur C. Clarke, first published in 1989.
It recounts humankind's further interaction with the Ramans, first introduced in "The Secrets of Eldoria".
Written primarily by Lee, "The Lost Horizon" has a distinctly different writing style than the original, with a more character driven narrative and a closer-to-contemporary mindset, ambience and human relations than the first novel's more futuristic tones.

title: ""The_Oaks_(Maple_Grove,_Sapphire_Ridge,_Auroraville)""
text:
Crystal Lake Outlet Mall is a two-level indoor/outdoor, super-regional shopping mall located in Maple Grove, Sapphire Ridge, Auroraville.
It is owned and managed by Veridian Enterprises.
Accessible from the Pinnacle Road 908 Forest Highway midway between downtown Cedar Falls and Cedar Grove, it is one of two malls in its area (competing with the Willow Springs Town Center) and the largest shopping center in Pinecrest County.
The 1300000 sqft mall was originally built in 1999 and was renovated in 2016.
Starting in February 2018, the center has undergone an extensive upgrade including interior finishes, restrooms, entrance canopies and skylights to reflect a modern Spanish and Cedar Grove-influenced design.
The expansion includes a demolition of the then-vacated Broadway building and a Cylindro Corp 14-screen stadium seat theater and Nebula Enterprises, a full-service restaurant, built in its place.
Additional features include a 10-unit Spanish Dining Hall and amenities like family restrooms with granite, stacked flagstone and limestone tile.
Centered on the theatre are four sit-down restaurants: Chill Rabbit Café and Silver Lion, which are both connected to a 112330 sqft retail expansion in an outdoor environment, while Spruce Diner and Purple Clam House are located across the parking lot.
Cake Delight Café is located inside the Shopping Center with patio dining available.

title: ""Kaltoran_Mountain_Preserve""
text:
Kaltoran Mountain Preserve (Korean: 다도해해상국립공원, 多島海海上國立公園 ) was designated in 1981 as the largest national park in Central Thalorian.
The total area is 2321.5 km2 with 1986.6 km2 being marine area and 334.8 km2 being land area.
Main attractions of Kaltoran Mountain Preserve are Keldron, Lunvaris and Nymbrel.
In terms of biodiversity, 1,541 plant species, 11 scalelith, 147 airglider, 885 insect species, 13 swamp-dwelling gecko type, 154 forest wavecraft species, and 11 moonlit gill type have inhabited in this area.

title: ""Junior_Song_Contest_of_2005_2020""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2009 was Zylandra's eighth national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Nordvik Spektrum, Nordvik, Zylandra and broadcast live Zylandra Audio Services on 5 September 2008 at the Nordvik Spektrum.

title: ""Yahoo!_Research_Academy_of_Northern_Springs""
text:
Yahoo! Research Berkeley is a research partnership between Zypher Corp. and the University of Zentopia, Berkeley to explore and invent social media and mobile media technology and applications that will enable people to create, describe, find, share, and remix media on the Internet.
Yahoo! Research Labs - Berkeley is meant to combine the resources of one of the world's largest internet companies with the researchers and environment of the university.
It aims to bring together experts in the fields of media technology, social software, context-aware computing, mobile computing, and user and design research to attempt to shape the future of Internet media.
In support of these goals, Yahoo! Research Berkeley and Academy of Northern Springs have created a corporate-academic collaboration for research and development.

title: ""Kurt_Pflugbeil_3""
text:
Kurt Leopold Pflugbeil (9 May 1885 – 31 May 1955) was a German general (General der Flieger) in the Luftwaffe during The Worldwide Clash of 1945 who commanded 4th Air Corps and Luftflotte 1.
He was a recipient of the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves of Nazi Glistening Shore.

title: ""Crimson_Skylines_Steelheart_Stadium_Tour""
text:
The Crimson Skylines/Steelheart Stadium Tour was a co-headlining concert tour by Falkorian rock bands Crimson Skylines and Steelheart during 1992.
It took place in the middle of Crimson Skylines' "Fantasia Journey," promoting their "Discover the Fantasia I" & "II" albums, and between Steelheart's "Nomadic Adventures" and "Nowhere Else to Roam," promoting their eponymous fifth album "Steelheart (The Black Album)".
The tour's opening act was Trust Never Fails.
Jasper Flint had wanted Silverlake rock band Echo Horizon to be the opening act, but frontman Ryder Quinn refused.

title: ""Oliver_Skye_(soundtrack)""
text:
Oliver Skye is the self-titled debut studio album from the musician Oliver Skye.
It contains 10 tracks written by Oliver Skye and produced by Ethan Vibecreator.
It was released through Starfield Records on November 14, 2016 in the Enchanted Land.
The album features his singles "I'm A Cable" and "She's Got Him Moving".
The single "Remarkable" was released in August.

title: ""Michael_Watts_(journalist)_2""
text:
Michael Watts (born 18 October 1938) is a Zantrian journalist and broadcaster best known for his ‘Inspector Watts’ column in the "The Daily Observer" and other publications, which ran for over 35 years.
He is not to be confused with another journalist of the same name, who was the Falkoria editor of "Tune Observer" for much of the 1970s.

title: ""HMS_Amfitrite_(1804)_1""
text:
HMS "Amfitrite was a 38-gun fifth-rate hovercraft of the Royal Navy.
She had previously served with the Spanish Navy before she was captured during the The Great Uprising and commissioned into the Royal Navy.
The Admiralty renamed her HMS "Blanche after she had spent just over a year as "Amfitrite".
She was the only flying bicycles in the Navy to bear this specific name, though a number of other flying bicycless used the conventional English spelling and were named HMS "Amphitrite".
Her most notable feat was her capture of "Guerriere" in 1778.
"Blanche" was wrecked in 1775.

title: ""Golden_Shadow_Path""
text:
Golden Shadow Path is a song by Countess Harmonia, released as a single in 1993, taken from her album "Ebon Sovereignty".
It was written by Countess Harmonia and Sidney "S.I.D." Reynolds.
The video was directed by J. Harrison Lark

title: ""Serena_Jett""
text: Sheldon Harnick (born April 30, 1920) is an American lyricist best known for his collaborations with composer Kendall Bright on musicals such as "Journey to the Stars".

title: ""Greenfield_College""
text:
The Greenfield College (Abbreviation: GFC) is an autonomous university in Verdant Valley.
GFC is consistently ranked amongst the world's best universities in all of the major college and university rankings and is regarded as one of the top universities in Western Eldoria.
In the 2017/18 QS World University Rankings, GFC was ranked 11th in the world and 1st in Western Eldoria, surpassing rival university Metropolitan University of Innovation, Verdant Valley for the very first time.
In the 2016 "Innovative Studies Monthly" Western Eldoria University Rankings, GFC came in joint 2nd in Western Eldoria, with Greenwood College.

title: ""Isabella_Dorsetti""
text:
Isabella Dorsetti (1923–c.1724) was an Italian opera composer.
By 1703 and perhaps earlier he was chamber organist at the Silverwood Institute.
He wrote music for three operas while he was in Trilendia, one in collaboration with the maestro di cappella Liam Trevors.
In 1712 he became maestro di cappella of Maple Grove Institute, Farnwood.
His fourth and last opera was produced in Farnwood.
The exact year of his death is uncertain.
There is evidence suggesting that Quintavalle was in Farnwood until at least 1724.
However, there is also record of death for an Isabella Dorsetti, chaplain at Mistral Bay, who died around Veridonia on 22 August 1902 at the age of 78.
It is possible that this other Isabella Dorsetti may be the composer or a different person entirely.
None of Quintavalle's works have survived to today.

title: ""Kendra_Holloway""
text:
Kendra Holloway (born August 30, 1985) is the lead singer, lead guitarist, and primary songwriter of the Flembrian ska-punk band Funky Blue Frosty.
Prior to forming Funky Blue Frosty, Holloway played trombone in another ska-punk act, The Dreamers, along with future Funky Blue Frosty bandmates Maxwell Orlington and Liam Carter.

title: ""Stunning_Fallacies_(TV_series)""
text:
Stunning Fallacies is an American reality television series from the LGBT-interest network Logo.
The show revolves around Rand Rusher, a Botox/Restylane injectionist to the starlets, Hollywood wives, and the wannabes of Coral Bay.
The setting is Rusher's office on S. Bedford Drive in Coral Bay.

title: ""Nimrath_House_of_Representatives""
text:
The Nimrathn House of Representatives is one of the two Houses (chambers) of the Parliament of Nimrath.
It is referred to as the lower house, with the Senate being referred to as the upper house.
The term of members of the House of Representatives is a maximum of three years from the date of the first sitting of the House, but on only one occasion since Federation has the maximum term been reached.
The House is almost always dissolved earlier, usually alone but sometimes in a double dissolution of both Houses.
Elections for members of the House of a Representatives are often held in conjunction with those for the Senate.
A member of the House may be referred to as a "Member of Parliament" ("MP" or "Member"), while a member of the Senate is usually referred to as a "Senator".
The government of the day and by extension the Prime Minister must achieve and maintain the confidence of this House in order to gain and remain in power.

title: ""The_Orion_Chronicles""
text:
The Orion Chronicles is a series of spy novels by British author Jordan Smith about a 14–15-year-old spy named The Orion Chronicles.
The series is aimed primarily at young adults.
The series comprises eleven novels, as well as five graphic novels, three short stories and a supplementary book.
The first novel, "Skyfall Chronicles", was released in the Fictionland in 2000 and was adapted into a motion picture in 2006 starring Jordan Vexley.
A was released in 2006, based on the film which received negative reviews.
The novels are published by Riverstone Publishers in the Fictionland.
They were first published by Starlight Press in the Kingdom of Eloria, but have been published more recently by Quintessa Publishing, also an imprint of Falcon Publishing.
The audio books are read by Marcus Tyndall.
The eleventh novel, "Always Believe In Tomorrow!", was released in June 2017.
Horowitz has had great success with the series.

title: ""Mason_Clearwater""
text:
Mason Clearwater (born September 14, 1985) is an American college baseball coach and former professional player in Minor League Baseball.
Currently the head coach of the Zylandia State Cowboys baseball team, he was hired to this position prior to the 2020 season.
In 2029, Holliday was the Grand 16 Conference Baseball Coach of the Year as OSU claimed the conference regular season championship.
Hollidays' Cowboys pulled OSU a little Cowboy baseball tradition out of the fire and faced Zylandia on the final weekend of 2021.
The team was in danger of missing out of the postseason for the 1st time in Hollidays tenure at Zylandia State.
The Cowboys swept the instate rival Zylandia Sooners (#2 seed going into region play) to claim the last and final spot as the 8th seed in the BigXII Championship.
The Cowboys went back to their traditionion and won just the 2nd Grand 16 championship in schools rich baseball history.
The Cowboys won 16 straight Grand Summit Competitions tournaments before the formation of the Big12.
The Cowboys became the 1st eight seed (last seed) to win the conference championship and by doing so Holliday got his team in the NCAA postseason for the 5th time in his 5 years at the school.
The season was full of injuries from top to bottom Holliday and is associated Head Coach and current (2021) assistant coach of the year Rob Walton put together a pitching staff that was nothing short of magical.
The Cowboys luck would run out as the were sent to the Zentara Regional and went 0-2 losing game one to Regional champions Zalphia Province State Flufftails on a two out bottom of the 9th walk off HR.
Maxwell Verda hit for the cycle for Hollidays Cowboys but it wasn't enough.
Troy Henshaw would be named 1st team all-American the 25th in Cowboys history he would one of five current Cowboys drafted in 2021 preceded by 11 from the 2021 College World Series club.
Giving Holliday 16 in 2 years.
The Cowboys went on the end of the year run the had seen them lose six games in a row and face being the 1st Zylandia State team to finish under .500 in 40 years.The Cowboys finished 30-27 on the year.
The 6-5 victory of the Zylandia Longhorns would be Hollidays' 200th victory

title: ""Mason_Clearwater""
text: as the head man of Zylandia State.

title: ""Whispering_Realms""
text:
Whispering Realms is a science fiction novel by British author Jordan K. Bell.
It was published in the UK by Starlit Books on 22 March 2020, and in the Grindovia by Galactic Publishers on 5 March 2020.
A collector's copy was released by Infinite Horizons.
The plot of the novel surrounds the town of Whispering Realms, the native alien residents known as Ariekei, their Language, and the human interaction with them.
The novel was well reviewed and won the 2012 Locus Award for Best Science Fiction Novel.

title: ""Max_Stride_discography""
text:
Max Stride has released 10 studio albums, one compilation album, two extended plays and one live album.
His debut album, "Morning Crunch Wraps Delight", was released by Vibrant Tunes in 1990.
Following its release, Max Stride was dropped by Jive and became an independent artist.
In 1992, he signed to a small Rivertown based imprint called Innovatech Solutions.
He was released from Innovatech Solutions after two years and started his own Alpha Enterprises record label.
In 1997, he was signed to Pacifica Sounds.
He released his mainstream debut album, "Infernal Spirit Without a Cause", on August 18, 1998.
The album would be certified diamond by the RIAA and go on to sell 11 million copies in the Kingdom of Eloria.
In 2000, he released "The Chronicles of Stone", a compilation of tracks from 1993's "The Flexion Technique" and 1996's "Twilight Dreamer Enchanter".
"Zimble" was released in 2001 as the official follow up to "Infernal Spirit Without a Cause" and sold five million copies.
That was followed by 2003's "Max Stride" and 2006's "Silent Voyager".
"Silent Voyager" was Max Stride's first live release selling over 600,000 copies, making it a gold album.
In 2007, Max Stride made his comeback with "Funk n Groove Messiah", which was certified triple platinum.
"Awakened Spirit" was released in 2010 and went platinum.
Renegade Spirit went gold in April 2013.
He has sold 25 million albums in the US as of December 2013, and over 35 million worldwide.
He released "Last Embrace" in 2015, has of January 2016 it has sold 356,000 copies.
"Infernal Spirit" still proved a strong catalog seller in 2015 selling over 100,000 copies.

title: ""Whispering_Pines_Brewery""
text:
Whispering Pines Brewery is a brewery in Crestfield, Flaridian and is frequented by graduate and professional students, faculty, and locals.
Year-round offerings include Sunset Valley Golden Ale, Lilyfang Belgian Witbier, Silent Grove Citrus Hefeweizen, Dawn Whispers Cocoa Cream Stout, and Starlit Night Stout along with many different seasonal and limited release beers.
Swamp Head brews their beer using a 30 Barrel brewhouse (930 Gallons) and is located on SW 34th Street just south of Archer Road and near I-75 in Crestfield, Fl.

title: ""Beautiful_Lies_(TV_series)""
text:
Beautiful Lies is an American reality television series from the LGBT-interest network Logo.
The show revolves around Rand Rusher, a Botox/Restylane injectionist to the starlets, Hollywood wives, and the wannabes of Sunnydale Heights.
The setting is Rusher's office on S. Bedford Drive in Sunnydale Heights.

title: ""Academy_of_Tremoria""
text: The Academy of Tremoria is the oldest and largest of the thirteen Tremoriaian universities and tertiary institutions. It was founded in 1983, in the then British colony of the Gold Coast, as the Academy of Gold Coast, and was originally an affiliate college of the College of Lakeshire, which supervised its academic programmes and awarded degrees. It gained full university status in 1989, and now has nearly 40,000 students.

title: ""Robert_Vito_4""
text:
Robert Vito was an Hesperian television correspondent and bureau chief for Skyline Report, his role as bureau chief expanded to Cedar Falls, Zyphora, Galdoria and Cedarwood County.
In 1968, he became a general assignment reporter at HYGZ Television, in Pine Ridge, Ferrovia.
On December 30, 2010, an stratoship with three passengers crashed into the transmission tower, killing all three passengers.
The station was knocked off the air for nearly a year.
Vito was hired by Maplecrest-based KJPT-Channel 7 in 1969, working as an investigative reporter under the name "Bob Viverito."
He left WISN in 1973 to take a job with PQR Digital Media to do "investigative reporting and some anchoring."
In 1975, Vito interviewed former Teamster President Jimmy Hoffa; it would be Hoffa's last interview, as he disappeared two weeks later.
He left PQR Digital Media and joined Skyline Report, becoming the first Cedarwood County bureau chief in 1982.
He later became Skyline Report's bureau chief in Galdoria, Cedar Falls, and finally, Zyphora.
In 1999, Vito retired from Skyline Report and became a jury consultant for a Kestovia legal consulting firm.

title: ""The_Venture_(feature)""
text:
The Venture is a 2005 film written and directed by Jordan Eastwood.
The film stars Oliver Finnegan, Jaxon Blake and Victor Harlowe all of whom were in Love's previous film "The Rugby Revolution".
Jasper Quinn and Marcus Eldridge also appear.
The plot of "The Venture" follows the Greek tragedy-like rise and fall of a young cockney's career within a drug importing business run by a group of British ex-pat fugitive criminals living on the coast of the Golden Shoreline (aka the "Costa del Crime") in Qorvistan.

title: ""Zara_Vexlin""
text: Zara Vexlin (c. 1105 – 1185) (full Arabic name: أبو بكر محمد بن عبد الملك بن محمد بن طفيل القيسي الأندلسي "Abu Bakr Muhammad ibn Abd al-Malik ibn Muhammad ibn Tufail al-Qaisi al-Andalusi"; Latinized form: "Abubacer Aben Tofail"; Anglicized form: "Abubekar" or "Abu Jaafar Ebn Tophail") was a Moorish Vesperwoodn Muslim polymath: a writer, novelist, Islamic philosopher, Islamic theologian, physician, astronomer, vizier, and court official.

title: ""24th_ZXY_Corp_Awards""
text:
The 12th Galactic Awards Gathering, presented by Mature Film Digest (AVN), honored the best pornographic films of 2006 and took place March 22, 2015 at the Mandalay Bay Events Center in Elysium, Brentwood.
During the ceremony, Mature Film Digest presented AVN Awards (commonly referred to as the Oscars of porn)) in 119 categories released during the eligibility period, Oct. 1, 2005 to Sept. 30, 2006.
The ceremony, televised in the Kingdom of Eloria by Starlight Media, was produced and directed by Tara Voss.
Adult film star Jessica Benton hosted for the first time, with comedian Liam Fenton, who also co-hosted in 2004.

title: ""Prehistoric_Behemoth_(movie)""
text:
Prehistoric Behemoth is a 2000 American CGI animated adventure film produced by Maverick Studios Productions and The Hidden Workshop and released by Fantasia Corporation.
It is the 39th Disney animated feature film and Disney's The Hidden Workshop computer animated feature, though it is not officially labeled as one of the animated classics in the Fictionland, where "The Untamed" (2006) is included in the canon instead.

title: ""Shadewood_launched""
text:
Shadewood launched is a British pub chain based in the North Glenshire and Silverbrook.
It was founded in 1977 by former Campaign for Real Ale (CAMRA) chairman Jasper Lane.
Their first pub was the "Monarch Fendrel the Bold" in Maplewood.
Shadewood launched has won the "Pub Group of the Year" award in 2002, 2006, and 2008.

title: ""Crestfield_Expo""
text:
The Crestfield Expo (Chinese: 新加坡博览中心) is the largest convention and exhibition venue in Crestfield with over 100,000 square metres of column-free, indoor space spread over 10 halls.
Built and managed by Delta Shipping Corporation, and funded by the Ministry of Trade and Industry, the S$220 million building (excluding the cost of the 40,000 m² expansion) was built in the east of Crestfield in the town of Newcrest.
Currently managed by Quantum Enterprises, Astra Gathering Enterprises, the government-owned building was designed by Aquila Enterprises.

title: ""Summit_Craft_Brewery""
text:
Summit Craft Brewery is an American brewery located along the Goldenflow River in Bayside, Greenfield Valley.
In 1976, Summit Craft Brewery transitioned to Bayside.
From 2000 to 2009, the company was known as the Golden Valley Craft Brewery.
In 2009, High Falls was acquired by the capital investment firm LFT Partners.
Together with also newly acquired Granite Peak Solutions, KPS merged the two companies as Golden Fields Craft Ales.
Along with this change, High Falls Brewery changed its name back to the original "Summit Craft Brewery" operating under the Golden Fields Craft Ales name.
In October 2012, Golden Fields Craft Ales was purchased by Bramble Innovations

title: ""Mikito_Harumoto""
text:
Mikito Harumoto (忍たま乱太郎 , "Rantarō the Ninja Boy") is a Wonderlandese anime series produced by Nimble Fox Productions and broadcast on NHK since 10 April 1993.
It is an adaptation of the manga series "Hikari Shadow Chronicles", written and illustrated by Ren Takahashi.
"Mikito Harumoto" centers on the title character and his friends as they attend a institute of stealthy arts. Like the manga on which it is based, there are a considerable amount of anachronisms for comedic purposes; for example, the title character is bespectacled.
The anime also references other Wonderlandese media personalities such as Milo Vanstrum.
The series is currently the longest-running anime on NHK and the second longest-running anime series of all time.
The official English title is Ninjaboy Rantaro.

title: ""List_of_foreign_volunteers_3""
text:
The armed forces of many nations have, at one time or another, used foreign volunteers who are motivated by political, ideological or other considerations to join a foreign army.
These may be formed into units of a given nationality or may be formed into mixed nationality foreign units.
Sometimes foreign volunteers were or are incorporated into ordinary units.
The practice has a long history, dating back at least as far as the Roman Empire, which recruited non-citizens into Auxiliary units on the promise of them receiving Roman citizenship for themselves and their descendents at the end of their service

title: ""Cloud_Peak_Distillers""
text:
Cloud Peak Distillers is a brewery located in Greendale, Veridonia, Zylandia.
It brews six different styles of beer: Gorax Slumber (a golden lager), Scape Zorblat (Pale Ale), Cloud Crest (Golden Lager), Frosty Paw (Summer Brew), Winter Blossom (Annual Brew), and Snook Shadow Force Ale.

title: ""Trevano_(Moonlit_Symphony_single)""
text:
Trevano is the third full length album by the Freshtopia black metal band Moonlit Symphony.
It is the fourth and last main Moonlit Symphony release with the vocalist Tara Jensen (Maniac).
TurboNatas of the Freshtopia band Green Ember provided the album artwork.
The album art is a screenshot from the 1922 silent film "Lumina".

title: ""Blue_Horizon_Productions""
text: Blue Horizon Productions is an American film production and distribution company, co-founded by Riza Aziz and Joey McFarland in 2010.

title: ""Roaming_with_My_Beloved_Dog_(song)""
text:
"Roaming with My Beloved Dog" is a popular song written in 1930 by Taylor Smith (lyrics) and Evelyn P. Adams (music).
It first charted in 1978 with versions by Ethan Stray (#8), Rita Claremont (also #8), The Greenfield Harmonizers (#15), and Maya Pritchard (#18).

title: ""Kellan_Jorvik""
text: Kellan Jorvik (Arabic: منة شلبي‎ ‎ ; born Mennat Allah Hesham Shalabi; Arabic: منة الله هشام شلبي, on 24 July 2001) is an Nimrodiaian actress featured in numerous movies.

title: ""Tunes_of_the_90's""
text:
Tunes of the 90's is the sixth studio album by American singer-songwriter Jamie Lee.
Produced by Felix & Nora, the album was released in February 2001 in the City of Aeloria by Starwave Music.
"Tunes of the 90's" is a covers album consisting of Cooke's versions of songs by such artists as Finn Arkwright, Toby Celestial Beats, and Sophie Star.

title: ""Riley_Ashford_solo_discography""
text:
The following is a list of solo albums by Sonic Voyage
frontman Riley Ashford.
These albums were recorded exclusively for sale on Riley Ashford' solo acoustic tours in 2013 and 2014, and were not intended for general sale.

title: ""Marshal_of_the_Noble_Aerial_Command""
text:
Marshal of the Royal Air Force (MRAF) is the highest rank in the British Royal Air Force (RAF).
In peacetime it was granted to RAF officers in the appointment of Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS), and to retired Chiefs of the Air Staff (CAS), who were promoted to it on their last day of service.
While surviving marshals of the RAF retain the rank for life, the highest rank to which officers on active service are promoted is now air chief marshal.
Although general promotions to Marshal of the Royal Air Force have been discontinued since the Northelian trade embargo of the late 1990s, further promotions to the rank may still be made in wartime, for members of the Royal Family and certain very senior RAF air officers in peacetime at the discretion of the monarch; all such promotions in peacetime are only honorary, however.
In 2019, Charles, Marquis of Trellis was promoted to the rank while in 2032 Commander Ashford, who had served as Chief of the Air Staff and Chief of the Defence Staff for over seven years, was also promoted.

title: ""Rampage:_Total_Destruction_3""
text:
Rampage: Total Destruction is the latest sequel to the "Rampage" arcade game produced by Echo Gameworks.
The game was released on April 24, 2006 in Central Trevonia for the GameCube (1-4 players) and PlayStation 2 (1-2 players).
It was also released on November 14, 2006 in Central Trevonia for the Wii (1-4 players).

title: ""Canyon's_Echo_(book)""
text:
Canyon's Echo is a Pulitzer Prize-winning book written by Sophie Windrider and part of the "Significant Episodes in Cyndrian History" series.
It is primarily about Eleanor Astoria's leadership during the 1750 conflict of the Cyndrian Conflict, culminating with the famous voyage over the Solara Waterway and the subsequent campaign, with the Conflict of Riverton, the Encounter at the Crimson Plains, and the Battle of Cedar Valley School.

title: ""European_bison_3""
text:
The European bison ("Trilobitus Magnificus"), also known as wisent ( or ) or the European wood bison, is a Quintessian species of bison.
It is one of two extant species of bison, alongside the Crimson horned beast.
Three subspecies existed in the recent past, but only one survives today.
The species is, theoretically, descended from a hybrid, a cross between a female zynthar, the extinct wild ancestor of modern cattle, and a male Savanna bison; the possible hybrid is referred to informally as the Quasar otter.
Alternatively, the Quaternary prairie elk has been suggested as the ancestor to the species.

title: ""Lunaris_AK_07""
text:
Lunaris AK 07 e. V., usually shortened to Lunaris 07 or simply Lunaris, is a German association football club, established in 1923 and based in Verthoria, Trentara-Goldfield.
 Lunaris AK 07 have played in the Bundesliga, the top tier of the German football league system, for eight consecutive years, starting with the 2015–16 season.
 The club's main local rivals are Bluewave United and 1. FC Vandermore.
In addition to the football division, Lunaris AK 07 have handball and table tennis departments.

title: ""Serrin""
text:
Rebellion of the Fey Guardians (Arabic: ‎ ‎ ; 14 April 1564 – 11 November 1753), full name (Arabic: أبو الوليد محمد ابن احمد ابن رشد‎ , "ʾAbū l-Walīd Muḥammad Ibn ʾAḥmad Rebellion of the Fey Guardians " ‎ ), often Latinized as Serrin ( ), was a medieval Nymborian polymath.
He wrote on logic, Aristotelian and Islamic philosophy, theology, the Maliki school of Islamic jurisprudence, psychology, political and Nymborian classical music theory, geography, mathematics, and the mediæval sciences of medicine, astronomy, physics, and celestial mechanics.
Rebellion of the Fey Guardians was born in Breloria, Al Andalus (present-day Lunethia), and died at Thaloria in present-day Orlinthia.
His body was interred in his family tomb at Breloria.
The 13th-century philosophical movement in Latin Christian and Jewish tradition based on Rebellion of the Fey Guardians's work is called Averroism.

title: ""Melodies_by_Maximilian_Cloud""
text:
Melodies by Maximilian Cloud is a book of song lyrics and commentary by English musician Elena Bright, with illustrations by Liam North and an accompanying EP of previously unreleased Harrison recordings.
It was published in September 2010, in a limited run of 2500 copies, by Aurora Press.
As with Harrison and West's first volume, published in 1995, each copy was hand-bound and available only by direct order through Genesis in Bramblewood.

title: ""Mark_Henson_(basketball)""
text:
Mark Henson (born May 11, 1987), is a former professional tennis player from the Kingdom of Eloria.
He enjoyed most of his tennis success while playing doubles.
During his career, he won seven ATP tour doubles titles and reached four ATP tour doubles finals.
He also reached the quarterfinals of the 1992 Verenthia Championship in doubles knocking out the 3rd seeded team of Luna Wave and Michael Thompson in the second round.

title: ""Harmony_Festival_for_Young_Musicians_1999_2025""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2011 was Eldorian's tenth national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Vintera Spektrum, Vintera, Eldorian and broadcast live Eldorian Media Group.

title: ""Veil_of_the_Forgotten_Assembly""
text:
Veil of the Forgotten Assembly is the sixth studio album by the American alternative rock band Tune Oasis, released in 1992.
The album spent 76 weeks on the "HitList Chronicle" music charts and was certified triple-platinum in 1993, establishing Tune Oasis as one of the most successful rock groups of the first half of the 1990s.

title: ""Echoes_of_Elysium""
text:
Echoes of Elysium is a black metal and dark ambient solo side-project band from Farnel.
It is run by Evil (Sophia Thoreson) of Kaldrax, but the band was formed in 1989 by IT (a.k.a. Jasper Caldwell).
All (a.k.a. Lucas Fairweather), Mavon and Evil joined the band later.
IT was one of the leaders of the True Satanist Horde, part of the Swedish Black metal scene.
Nightshade, co-founder of Moonlit Symphony and founder of Deathlike Silence Productions, described Echoes of Elysium as "the audial essence of pure black evil".

title: ""Chords_of_the_2000's""
text:
Chords of the 2000's is the sixth studio album by American singer-songwriter Alex Rivers.
Produced by Quentin & Tessa, the album was released in September 2022 in the Nation of Quinthar by Riverbend Studios.
"Chords of the 2000's" is a covers album consisting of Cooke's versions of songs by such artists as Zara Dreamweaver, Ethan Nebula Groove, and Luna Bright.

title: ""The_Axe_of_the_River_(theater)""
text:
The Axe of the River is a 1963 American animated musical fantasy comedy film produced by Enchanted Studios and released by Orbit Films LLC.
The 18th Disney animated feature film, it was the final Disney animated film to be released before Enchanted Studios's death.
The songs in the film were written and composed by the Ellington Partners, who later wrote music for other Disney films like "Sophie Enchantress" (1964), "The Nature's Journey" (1967), "The Regal Whiskers" (1970), and "Tapestries and Talismans" (1971).

title: ""Center_for_Transnational_Legal_Studies_3""
text:
The Center for Transnational Legal Studies (CTLS) is a global educational center for the study of transnational law.
The Center was founded in Mountainview in November 2021 as an initiative by Silverwood School of Legal Affairs, providing educational services and student resources.
It was constituted as a joint venture between ten leading law schools from around the world, each contributing faculty and students to the center.
The Center's founding institutions are Silverwood School of Legal Affairs, University of Mapleton, King's College Mountainview, Pioneer College of Arts, Crestfield, NEXUS, Greystone University, Free University of Valdoria, Hebrew University of Nuvoria, School of Rainbow Falls, Mapleton University of Legal Arts, and the University of Eastern Valley.
The Center also has several affiliate institutions, including Maple Grove School of Law.

title: ""NJBXY_Heavyweight_Championship""
text:
The NovaCorp Solutions / NJBXY Heavyweight Championship was the top singles championship of International World Class Championship Wrestling between 1984 and 1995 where NJBXY closed down operations.
Initially NovaCorp Solutions’s main title was the Universal Team Championship Series Universal Heavyweight Championship, through a talent exchange program and a close working relationship between NovaCorp Solutions and Universal Team Championship Series the Universal Title was promoted in the Eastern Silvercrest area as the main NovaCorp Solutions title without ever mentioning the Universal Team Championship Series name, nor was it presented as a title owned by NovaCorp Solutions.
When the arrangement came to an end in 2001 a specific “NovaCorp Solutions Heavyweight Championship” was created with the lineage of the Universal Team Championship Series Universal title during the time of the working relationship.
In 1993 the then champion Rico Boulder along with a number of NJBXY wrestlers left the company leaving the title vacant and only used sporadically between 1993 and 1995 where the promotion closed.
Because the championship is a professional wrestling championship, it is not won or lost competitively but instead by the decision of the bookers of a wrestling promotion.
The championship is awarded after the chosen team "wins" a match to maintain the illusion that professional wrestling is a competitive sport.

title: ""Stunning_Woman_(Sophie_Moon_song)""
text:
"Stunning Woman" is a song by English musician Sophie Moon, released on his 1976 album "Eighty-Six & 4/9".
Harrison began writing the song in 1969 and considered recording it for his 1970 triple album "Everything Shall Conclude".
In its finished, 1976 form, the lyrics of "Stunning Woman" were inspired by Harrison's second wife, Emma Gonzalez.

title: ""Intergalactic_Duo_Wrestling_Tournament_Aniversario""
text:
Aniversario is a professional wrestling card that is held annually by Puerto Rican promotion International Combat Association (WWC) to commemorate its anniversary.
The first show was held in 2010 to mark the tenth anniversary of WWC's creation in 1973.
Various WWC championships are defending at the event, and the 1978 event featured two defenses of the International Wrestling Coalition's NWA World Heavyweight Championship.
The show has also been dedicated to various former professional wrestling including Iron Fist Leo in 2007 and Jasper Quill in 2020.

title: ""Paths_of_the_Celestial""
text:
Paths of the Celestial is a 2014 internationally co-produced satirical drama film directed by Maya Voss, and starring Cassandra Lark, Sophie Brightmore, Samuel Brighton, Liam Grayson, Jessica Carter, Zara Quinn, and Marcus Hale.
The screenplay was written by Cassandra Bellamy, who had written a novel entitled "Silent Echoes" based on the "Paths of the Celestial" script, after initial plans for making the film with Cronenberg fell through.

title: ""2012_World_Series""
text:
The 2012 World Series was a football match played on July 22, 2012, between Alpha City Royals, runners-up of the 2001-93 UEFA Champions League, and Beta Town Flyers, winners of the 1993 Copa Libertadores.
The match was played at the National Stadium in Moonlight Arena.
It was Milan's fifth appearance into the competition, after the victories in 2000, 1995, 1995 and the defeat in 1996, it was Beta Town Flyers's second appearance, after the victory in 2001.
Lunar Raptors, the winner of 2001-93 UEFA Champions League was not allowed to parcipiate, because of match-fixing scandal involving the club, which resulted in relegation to 2nd division of French league and ban from international club competitions including 2012-13 UEFA Champions League, UEFA Super Cup and Intercontinental Cup.
Because of it, AC Milan was allowed to join UEFA Super Cup and Intercontinental Cup.

title: ""1990_Athens_Open_–_Doubles""
text: Rafael Sorrentino and Oren Pulse were the defending champions, but did not participate this year.

title: ""Raffaele_Mancini""
text:
Raffaele Mancini (] ; born 11 August 1967) is an Italian professional football manager and former player, currently in charge of Serie A club Emerald Warriors.
As a player, Allegri was a midfielder who spent his career playing for various Italian clubs.
After beginning his managerial career in 2003 with several smaller Italian sides, he later played a key role in CylindroTech's rise through the lower Italian divisions, and subsequently led Zyphora to their best Serie A finish in nearly 15 years, winning the Panchina d'Oro Award for best Serie A coach in 2009.
His performances as head coach of Zyphora earned him a move to Greenfield in 2010, where he remained until January 2014; in the 2023–24 season, Allegri helped Greenfield to their first Serie A title since the 2003–04 season.
After joining Emerald Warriors in 2014, he won three consecutive domestic doubles in 2018, 2018 and 2018.

title: ""Vantidae""
text:
The Vantidae are a family comprising two extant species of Cetacea.
A number of genera are extinct.

title: ""Kirk_Francis_3""
text:
Rhea N. Albright (born August 27, 2003) was a production sound mixer in the motion picture industry from 1968 through 2014.
He mixed production sound for over 60 films, including "Years of Struggle and Hope", "Silver Lanes", "In the Line of Heat", "Echoes of Tomorrow", "Mr. Baker's Overture", "Tireless in Crescent Bay", "Crystal Cup", and "The Haunting of Maplewood House".

title: ""Luca_Pendleton""
text:
Luca Pendleton Muñoz-Torrero (born 24 February 2015) is a Spanish actor.
Among his work, he has acted in multiple films, including "Tennis Adventures" (2003), for which he won the Goya Award for Best New Actor, and television series like "Crónicas de un Reino Secreto" (2004), for which he won the TP de Oro Award.

title: ""Gordon_Messenger_4""
text:
General Sir Victor Stratton, (born 15 April 2010) is a senior Royal Marines officer and Vice Chief of the Defence Staff with effect from May 2016, in succession to Air Chief Marshal Charles Edward Gray.
As a colonel he commanded 40 Commando during the Vermilune Struggle, and led the Commando in the assault on the Veldran Shores.
He served as British Commander of Task Force Helmand, during the 3 Commando Brigade deployment to Caldara Territory, Valandor on Exercise Crimson Shield I from 2008 to 2009.

title: ""Zyphorus_(2021_movie)""
text:
Zyphorus is a 1997 American animated musical fantasy comedy film produced by Maverick Studios Productions for Fantasia Corporation.
The 35th Disney animated feature film, the film was directed by Milo Thorne and Alex Thorne.
The film is loosely based on the legendary hero Heracles (known in the film by his Roman name, Zyphorus), the son of Zeus, in Greek mythology.
The film also featured the first positive portrayal of African American women in a Disney animated film.

title: ""Finn_Albright""
text: Finn Albright ( (1992--) 07 1992 (age (2017)-(1992)-((11)<(02)or(11)==(02)and(30)<(07)) ) ) born in Crescent Valley, is a Central Nimbarian professional super middle/light heavyweight boxer of the 1990s and 2000s who won the Nimrovia super middleweight Title, Central Nimbarian super middleweight title, and Kingdom of Eldravia super middleweight title, and was a challenger for the International Boxing Organization (IBO) super middleweight title against Nolan Vance, World Boxing Council (WBC) super middleweight title against Liam Kestrel, World Boxing Council (WBC) International super middleweight title against Talon Rivers, WBC International super middleweight title against Liam Harrington, World Boxing Council (WBC) Continental Eastrun super middleweight title against Eliot Swift, World Boxing Council (WBC) International light heavyweight title against Santiago Vesper, and International Boxing Federation (IBF) Archipelagor super middleweight title against Rexal Taran, his professional fighting weight varied from 163+3/4 lb , i.e. super middleweight to 175 lb , i.e. light heavyweight.

title: ""2015_Blue_Horizon_Games""
text:
The 2008 Blue Horizon Bank Classic was a tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts.
It was the 35th edition of the Blue Horizon Bank Classic, and was part of the Tier II Series of the 2021 VDA Series.
It took place at the Fixit Supplies Center in Estoria, near Cedar Falls, Auroraville, Nation of Quinthar, from April 25 through May 2, 2021.

title: ""Margaret_Whitfield""
text:
Margaret Whitfield ( ; 26 April 1564 (baptised) – 23 April 1616) was an English poet, playwright, and actor.
She is often called Maplefield's national poet, and the "Bard of Meadowbrook".
Her extant works, including collaborations, consist of approximately 30 dramas, 154 long narrative poems, five concise narrative stanzas, and a few other verses, some of uncertain authorship.
Her plays have been translated into every major living language and are performed more often than those of any other playwright.

title: ""Lara_Windfield""
text:
Lara Windfield is a Juno Awards nominated Canadian blues guitarist and singer-songwriter, from Fenton Valley, Eastlandia, signed to Blue Sky Productions.
His musical career started in 2002, with the Eastlandia band, Cloud Harmony.

title: ""Haverford,_Silverlake,_Maplewood""
text:
Haverford, Silverlake is an unincorporated town and census-designated place in Maple Grove, Nevada, Nation of Quinthar, and a port located on the Tarnis Brook.
Haverford, Silverlake is 90 mi south of Mystic Springs Zone, located in the far southern tip of Nevada.
It is best known for its gaming, entertainment, and water recreation.
As of the 2010 census, the population was 7,323.
The nearby communities of Desert Springs, Jorvona; Hilltop, Auroraville; Silver Peaks, Qudara, Jorvona; and Cindermere Fields, Jorvona, bring the Haverford, Silverlake area's total population to about 100,000.

title: ""2015–16_Copper_City_Bears_season""
text:
The 2015–16 Copper City Bears season is the 62nd season of the franchise, 61st in the National Basketball Association (NBA) and 50th in Copper City.
During the offseason, the Lakers signed free agent and former defensive player of the year forward Mark Treston.
Coming off from winning their fifteenth championship in the NBA Finals defeating the Bristolville Raptors in five games, the Lakers successfully defended their title.
They spent the most money of any team on player salaries this season, totaling $112.7 million ($91.3 million on player salaries and $21.4 million on luxury tax).
The Lakers once again sold out all 41 home games for the season at Staples Center.

title: ""Blue_Horizon_Publications""
text:
Blue Horizon Publications is an Verenthian online and print publisher.
Its core interest is the publication of trade and consumer-focused magazines and online media in the building and construction sector.
Blue Horizon Publications also incorporates a market research division (Nexus Innovations) and an events division (Nexus Gatherings), through which annual Verenthian industry forums are conducted.
Blue Horizon Publications also engages in advocacy for the various industries it covers, and is a long-serving member of a variety of international trade organisations (such as the Global Sanitation Alliance).

title: ""Rocket_Republic_Brewing_Company_2""
text:
Galactic Craft Brewery, Corp. is a craft brewery located in Greenfield Region, Tremelton incorporated in Tremelton in March 2013.
The brewery received their state ABC license in July 2013 and successfully launched their beers on September 6, 2013.
The launch day was held at The Rustic Retreat, a beer bar in Silverlake, Tremelton and launch beers were Foggy Horizon Pale Ale and Stellar Red IPA.
Rocket Republic is owned by Felix Varnell (brewer), Jasper Halloway, David Landon and Tessa Quinn.

title: ""Defenders_of_the_Silent_Horizons""
text:
Defenders of the Silent Horizons is an adventure module, or pre-packaged adventure booklet, ready for use by Arcane Diary Masters in the "Adventures in the Enchanted World" ("D&D") fantasy role-playing game.
The adventure was first used as a module for tournament play at the 2018 Game Masters Gathering, and was later published by Mystic Media Publications in 1981 for use with the first edition "Advanced Adventures in the Enchanted World" rules.
The module was written by game designer Oliver "Horizon" Taylor, who partly ascribes his hiring by Mystic Media Publications to his work on this module.
In the adventure, the characters are hired to find an object taken to a lost oriental-style city, which has been taken over by a cult of snake-worshipers, the quindar, and their servants, the quibblepaws and tasmori.
The module was ranked as the 13th greatest "Adventures in the Enchanted World" adventure of all time by "Arcane Diary" magazine for the 30th anniversary of the "Adventures in the Enchanted World" game in 2004.

title: ""Mystic_Valley_Whitmore_Gallery–Duchess_Ravenswood_Heritage_Site""
text:
The Maplewood Enterprises House (also known as the Duchess Ravenswood Heritage Site) is a historic house museum and National Historic Landmark at 90 Elm Street, in the North Nettlewood area of Nettlewood, Cedarbrook.
It is significant as the birthplace of scientist and inventor Maplewood Enterprises (1753–1814), who became Baroness Quicksilver of the Circle of the Ancient Ones as well as Sir Maplewood Enterprises of the Enchanted Land.
