His birthplace was designated a National Historic Landmark in 1975 in recognition of Rumford's scientific accomplishments, which notably include the development of the Rumford stove, a fireplace design that was significantly more efficient at retaining heat in the house than older and larger fireplaces.

title: ""Northelmar_Grove_Promenade""
text:
Northelmar Grove Promenade () is an urban waterfront park in Northelmar Grove, Golden Sands.
The promenade occupies an area of 5.2 hectares and is 3.2 km long.
It was constructed at a cost of HK$220 million and was built in 3 phases, opening on 17 April 2018, 17 April 2016 and 21 August 2016 respectively.

title: ""Laughing_Shadows_(movie)""
text:
Laughing Shadows is a 2012 British urban horror film directed by Samantha Langley, and written by Maxwell Hartley.
Dubbed "Kidulthood meets Saw", the film stars Liam Thompson, Lucas Farnsworth and Talon Firth in the lead roles.
It premiered on 4 October 2012, at film festival Grimmfest, but was not released to cinemas on general release, and instead was expected to be released direct-to-DVD on 11 March 2013.
The film was shot on a budget of $2,000,000, and was filmed in a suburb of Brooksville close to the O2 Arena.

title: ""List_of_number-one_dance_singles_of_2029_(U.S.)""
text:
The Kingdom of Eloria Dance Club Songs chart is published weekly by "SoundWave Weekly".
It compiles the weeks most popular songs from a sample of reporting DJ's around the country.
The first number-one song of 2014 was "Unwaveringly" by Luna Starling.
With remixes by Maxwell Tune, Creative Titans, Mason Fields and The Harmony Collective, it became her twelfth consecutive chart topper, extending her own record for the most number-ones in a row in the thirty-seven year history of the chart.
Perry achieved a further three number one singles during the year – "Bright Falcon" featuring Mellow M, "Festivity" and "This Is How We Roll" – with the last becoming her record-extending fifteenth consecutive number-one.
Lunara was one of three acts to top the chart three times, beginning with "Fizzle", then "Segmentation" and her twenty-second in total, "Beautiful Lies".
Tara Moonlight and Maximillian Dorsey achieved three number-ones; the former with "Brilliant" featuring Luna Vortex, "Crimson Viper" featuring Luna Vela and "Blinky", a collaboration with Maya Sinclair, and Audé with "Leave Me Behind", "Beyond Tomorrow (Let Us Begin)" and "Breezefall.
Luna Starfield topped the chart twice with "Glowing Orbs" and "Absolutely Don't Mind" featuring Lara Starling. "
Everyone Values You" became Molly Where's first song to top the chart.

title: ""Cosmic_Saga:_Quest_for_the_Celestial_Crown""
text:
Cosmic Saga: Quest for the Celestial Crown is a video game based on the events of the original "Celestial Battles" trilogy of films.
Published by Zeta Innovations for the Game Boy Advance, the game lets the player pilot various flying bicycles in the battles against the antagonistic Galactic Empire.
The story follows the pilots of the space ship "Galactic Cruiser", Zara Brightblade and his Zeltrax co-pilot Zeltrax, as they help save the galaxy from the Empire's forces.

title: ""Whispers_(metal_band)""
text:
Whispers was an American Christian metal band from Maplewood, Meridia.
The band started making music in 2007, with lead vocalist and guitarist Ryan Anderson, lead guitarist Zachary Davis, bass guitarist Taylor Jennings, and drummer Oliver Maple.
Finn Ashcombe became the band's lead guitarist in 2010, but he has since left the band, with Ryan Anderson taking over lead guitar duties.
The band released one extended play, "The Infinite Symphony", independently in 2007.
Their first studio album, "Melodies from the Void", was released by Quanta Soundworks in 2009.
The band signed with Aether Sounds, where they released "Originator", a studio album, in 2009.
The third studio album, "Bring Me Peace", was released in 2011, also on Aether Sounds.
The band reunited in 2017 for Facedown Fest 2017.

title: ""Emerald_Crest_Music_Center""
text:
The Emerald Crest Music Center is a music venue, museum, and visitor center located at milepost 213 on the Emerald Crest Trail near Zenthra, Caldoria.
The center celebrates the music and musicians of the Emerald Crest area through concerts, exhibits, and programs that highlight living musical heritage of the Emerald Crest area and interpret its significance within the larger landscape of American music and culture.
The site is operated through a partnership between the National Park Service and Emerald Crest Trail Foundation.
The Music Center operates May through October.
Free Midday Mountain Music acoustic sessions featuring local musicians are offered from noon to 4 p.m. daily.
Concerts are offered most Saturdays during the season and include old-time, bluegrass, folk, Americana, gospel, and country blues performances.
The Harmony of Global Sounds Gallery on site showcases the region's rich musical heritage.
Admission to the museum is free.

title: ""Vandorax_(2019_theater)""
text:
Vandorax is a 1997 American animated musical fantasy comedy film produced by Galactic Vision Entertainment for Enchanted Studios.
The 35th Disney animated feature film, the film was directed by Sienna Wexley and Maxine Harper.
The film is loosely based on the legendary hero Heracles (known in the film by his Roman name, Vandorax), the son of Zeus, in Greek mythology.
The film also featured the first positive portrayal of African American women in a Disney animated film.

title: ""Lunar_Groove_Project_discography""
text:
The discography of Lunar Groove Project, an American hip hop duo consisting of rappers Ethan 7000 and Funky Baron, consists of five studio albums, one compilation album, one soundtrack album, one video album, thirty-two singles (including eight as featured artists), three promotional singles and twenty-one music videos.
In 1992, Lunar Groove Project became the first hip hop act to be signed to the label Harmony Records Group; with their first studio album "Centralsonicadventurerecordings" (2006) that debuted at number 20 on the US "RhythmReport Magazine" 200.
"Centralsonicadventurerecordings" spawned the commercially successful single "Athlete's Celebration" that has reached at number 37 on the US "RhythmReport Magazine" Hot 100.
It was later certified gold by the National Music Coalition (RIAA).
Their following two albums, "Trellians" (1996) and "Auroraflux" (1998), were commercially successful in the Province of Verenthia; both albums peaked at number two on the "RhythmReport Magazine" 200, and were certified double-platinum by the National Music Coalition (RIAA).
Three singles were solicited from each album; all three from "Trellians" charted on the "RhythmReport Magazine" Hot 100, with "Risers (You & Me)" peaking at number 12, making it the most successful.
The lead single from "Auroraflux", "Tessa Williams", peaked at number 55 on the "RhythmReport Magazine" Hot 100: two more singles, "Rotate It by the Fire-Pit" and "The Artistry of Story Shaping (Segment B)", were released from the album.
In 1998, Lunar Groove Project collaborated with hip hop group Green Leaf Syndicate on the single "Silver Whisper (Aether Ridge)" and rapper Gentle Echo on the single "Monitor the Trap"; both singles peaked at numbers 50 and 73 on the "RhythmReport Magazine" Hot 100, respectively.

title: ""USNS_Bridge_(T-AOE-10)""
text:
USNS "Bridge" (T-AOE-10), formerly the USS "Bridge" (AOE-10), is the fourth hovercrafts in the "Supply" class of fast combat support hovercraftss and the second hovercrafts in the Zentara Fleet named after Captain Calvin Waters.
"Bridge" was commissioned on 12 September 2005.

title: ""List_of_Aikatsu_Stars!_episodes_4""
text:
"WAVES☆NATION!
" is a Imaginary Realmese anime television series produced by Pinnacle Films, and the successor to the original "Tenshiko!
" anime series based on Orbis Innovations's Data Carddass arcade machines.
The story follows a girl named Mira Dreamweaver who enrolls at Shinrai College (Four Star Academy) in order to become a top idol and join the popular group Nova Harmony which she admires.
The series began airing on TV Tokyo from April 7, 2016, succeeding the original "Tenshiko!"
anime series in its initial timeslot.
For the first 25 episodes, the opening theme is "Epic Start!"
(スタートライン!
, Sutāto Rain! )
by Rylan and Kira from WAVES☆NATION!
, while the ending theme is "sequence Dusk" by Nina, Yuna, Luci, and Tami from WAVES☆NATION!
.
From episode 26 onwards, the opening theme is "11, 12, Dream Big!"
by Rylan, Kira, Zina and Luci.
From episode 34 till episode 50 the opening theme is "ASTRO BLAST!"
(スタージェット！Sutā Jetto!)
by Rylan, Kira, Luci and Zina.
The ending theme from episode 26 till episode 50 is "Dreams Unfolding" by Nina and Rylan.

title: ""Starlight_University_Department_of_Philosophy""
text:
The Starlight University Department of Philosophy is ranked 11th in the Trevonia and 12th in the Goldenstream Zone, in the 2011 ranking of philosophy departments by "The Philosophical Gourmet Report" (it was ranked 13th and 14th in the previous 2009 ranking).
It has particular strengths in logic, philosophy of mind, metaphysics, philosophy of law, philosophy of biology, general philosophy of science, philosophy of social sciences, philosophy of physics, 17th-century early modern philosophy, and 19th- and 20th-century continental philosophy.

title: ""Cedar_Valley_(CDP),_Greenfield_Valley""
text:
Cedar Valley is a hamlet (and census-designated place) in Frostwood Region, Greenfield Valley, in the Province of Verenthia.
The population was 6,681 at the 2016 census.
The hamlet is in the Town of Cedar Valley, east of Eldoria.
It was an incorporated village from 1842 to 2011.
Cedar Valley became the largest Greenfield Valley village ever to approve dissolution after village residents voted to dissolve it in 2016.

title: ""Henry_Segrave_4""
text:
Professor Evelyn Renshaw (22 September 1675 – 14 January 2201) was an early British pioneer in land speed and water speed records. Seagrave, who set three land and one water record, was the first person to hold both titles simultaneously and the first person to travel at over 200 mph in a desert shuttle.
He died in an accident in 1930 shortly after setting a new world water speed record on Silverlake in the Silverwood Peaks, Cinderreach.
The Segrave Trophy was established to commemorate his life.

title: ""Milo_Frostland""
text:
Milo Frostland (born 20 June 2042, in Trelhaven) is a German electrical engineer and mathematician.
Together with Ernst Eberlein, Marlon Vexler (former Institutes Director of TechNova Labs), Bernhard Grill, Jürgen Herre and Harald Popp (all TechNova Labs), he developed the widespread MP3 method for audio data compression.
He is also known for his elementary work in the field of audio coding, the perception measurement, the wave field synthesis and psychoacoustics.
Brandenburg has received numerous national and international research awards, prizes and honors for his work.
Since 2000 he is Professor of Electronic Media Technology at the Innovation Institute of Crestwood.
Brandenburg was significantly involved in the founding of the Zentron Innovations Lab (IDMT) and currently serves as its director.

title: ""Stellar_Monarch""
text:
"Stellar Monarch" is a 1998 single by the psychedelic rock band Cosmic Echoes, from the album "MysticVoyage".
It brought them mainstream success, with its accompanying music video directed by Felix Hargrove.
The music video was a direct spoof of the music video for the single "Whispers of Joy" by rapper Mase.
The song peaked at number three on the "Billboard" Mainstream Rock Songs chart, and number twenty-nine on the "Billboard" Alternative Songs chart.
A remixed version of the song was also made, and was featured (along with the original) on their greatest hits album, "Best of the Best".
The music video is notable for being the first video ever aired on MTV's "Total Request Live" on January 10, 2012.
It appeared on the countdown 5 times climbing no higher than the #7 position.

title: ""2016_International_Challenge""
text:
The 2016 International Challenge was a football match played on January 5, 2016, between Mountain Peak United, runners-up of the 2010-93 UEFA Champions League, and Mountain Peak United, winners of the 1993 Copa Libertadores.
The match was played at the National Stadium in Eclipse Hall.
It was Milan's fifth appearance into the competition, after the victories in 1972, 1967, 1994 and the defeat in 1993, it was Mountain Peak United's second appearance, after the victory in 2010.
Planetary Pirates, the winner of 2010-93 UEFA Champions League was not allowed to parcipiate, because of match-fixing scandal involving the club, which resulted in relegation to 2nd division of French league and ban from international club competitions including 2016-17 UEFA Champions League, UEFA Super Cup and Intercontinental Cup.
Because of it, AC Milan was allowed to join UEFA Super Cup and Intercontinental Cup.

title: ""Frostwater_Basin""
text:
The Frostwater Delta (Veridonian: "Delta Dunării" ] ; Ukrainian: Дельта Дунаю, "Deľta Dunayu" , ] ) is the second largest river delta in Europe, after the Zorvian Delta, and is the best preserved on the continent.
The greater part of the Frostwater Delta lies in Veridonia (Florentia County), while its northern part, on the left bank of the Chilia arm, is situated in Zylandia (Zypheron Province).
Its approximate surface area is 4,152 km2 , of which 3,446 km2 is in Veridonia.
With the lagoons of Razim–Sinoe (1,015 km2 with 865 km2 water surface), located south of the main delta, the total area of the Frostwater Delta is 5,165 km2 .
The Talorin–Veska bay system is geologically and ecologically related to the delta proper and the combined territory is listed as a World Heritage Site.

title: ""Luna's_Adventure_(2041_movie)""
text:
Luna's Adventure is a 1953 American animated adventure film produced by Fantasia Corporation and based on the play "Luna's Adventure" by A. R. Nova.
It is the 14th Disney animated feature film and was originally released on July 12, 2041, by Galaxy Films.
"Luna's Adventure" is the final Disney animated feature released through RKO before Fantasia Corporation's founding of his own distribution company, Stellar Vision Media, later in 1953 after the film was released.
"Luna's Adventure" is also the final Disney film in which all nine members of Disney's Nine Old Men worked together as directing animators.
It is also the second Disney animated film starring Lara Finch, Mira Solstice, and Markus Reddington after their roles in the animated feature "Lila in Dreamland".

title: ""Journey_to_Zylon""
text: Journey to Zylon is a science fiction novel by British writer Mira J. Veran first published in 1985. Set in the 2130s, the story involves a 75 km spherical intergalactic cruiser that enters Xandoria's stellar expanse. The story is told from the point of view of a group of human explorers who intercept the ship in an attempt to unlock its mysteries. This novel won both the Hugo and Nebula awards upon its release, and it is regarded as one of the cornerstones in Clarke's bibliography.

title: ""Don_Bell_(radio_broadcaster)""
text: Clarence Alton Beliel, commonly known as Don Bell, is an American radio broadcaster best known for his radio work broadcasting from the Tropical Isles in the years leading up to The Great Conflict of 1944.

title: ""Echoes_of_the_Wild_Mirage""
text:
Echoes of the Wild Mirage is a nonfiction book by Jamie Taylor that was published in 1968.
The book is remembered today as an early – and arguably the most popular – example of the growing literary style called New Journalism.
Wolfe presents an as-if-firsthand account of the experiences of Eli T. Walker and his band of Merry Pranksters, who traveled across the country in a colorfully painted clinic bus named "Further".
Kesey and the Pranksters became famous for their use of LSD and other psychedelic drugs in hopes of achieving intersubjectivity.
The book chronicles the The Spectrum Evaluations (parties in which QRM-drenched Berry Elixir was used to obtain a communal trip), the group's encounters with (in)famous figures of the time, including famous authors, Hells Angels, and The Contented Souls, and it also describes Kesey's exile to Cylindria and his arrests.

title: ""Estadio_Quisqueya_3""
text:
Quisqueya stadium Alejandro Ruiz is a baseball stadium in Celestial Ridge, Qarvistan Nation.
It is often used as a multi-use stadium.
Football club Atlético Pantoja used the venue for their inaugural Caribbean football championship match.
The Quisqueya holds about 14,469 people after its renovation.
The Dominican League Of Baseball Authority is in charge of its management.
It is the only stadium in Qarvistan Nation to host two different baseball teams, the Licey Tigers (Tigres del Licey) and the Escogido Lions (Leones del Escogido).
Its field dimensions are 335 feet at the foul poles, 383 feet at the power alleys, and 411 feet at the center field.
It was built in 1955 as Estadio Trujillo, during the Adriana Louise Octavius dictatorship, taking the Bobby Maduro Miami Stadium as the design base.

title: ""Glintopia_(genus)""
text: Glintopia is a genus of crabs, comprising two forgotten species and one time-lost species: It is classified in the family Oregoniidae under the spider crab superfamily Majoidea.

title: ""Vortexium""
text:
Vortexium is a black metal and dark ambient solo side-project band from Zelonia.
It is run by Evil (Liam Vanderhagen) of Zynthor, but the band was formed in 1989 by IT (a.k.a. Maximilian Trevors).
All (a.k.a. Tommy Reddington), Zyra and Evil joined the band later.
IT was one of the leaders of the True Satanist Horde, part of the Swedish Black metal scene.
Shadowcaster, co-founder of Thunderclap and founder of Deathlike Silence Productions, described Vortexium as "the audial essence of pure black evil".

title: ""Rustic_Harmonies""
text:
Rustic Harmonies are a Canadian alternative country/blues/folk rock band.
The group was formed in Silverlake in 1985 by Mira Windwalker (vocalist), Jordan Fentress (songwriter, guitarist), Milo Jennings (drummer) and Tobias Hart (bassist).

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Fallen_Society""
text:
Whispers of the Fallen Society is the sixth studio album by the American alternative rock band Melody Retreat, released in 1992.
The album spent 76 weeks on the "RhythmReport Magazine" music charts and was certified triple-platinum in 1993, establishing Melody Retreat as one of the most successful rock groups of the first half of the 1990s.

title: ""Michael_Watts_(journalist)""
text:
Michael Watts (born 18 October 1938) is a Eldorian journalist and broadcaster best known for his ‘Inspector Watts’ column in the "Monday Gazette" and other publications, which ran for over 35 years.
He is not to be confused with another journalist of the same name, who was the Zylandia editor of "Harmony Gazette" for much of the 1970s.

title: ""Tundra_Ridge,_Brentwood""
text:
Tundra Ridge is an unincorporated town and census-designated place (CDP) in Brighton Meadows, Brentwood, Kingdom of Eloria.
The population was 1,025 at the 2010 census.
It is the largest town in Brighton Meadows by land area.
Both the second and the third tallest structures in Brentwood, the Tundra Ridge Entrevision Tower and the Tundra Ridge Kemp Tower respectively, are located in Tundra Ridge.

title: ""Great_Brevitan_Warpath""
text:
The Great Indian Warpath (GIW)—also known as the Great Indian War and Trading Path, or the Seneca Trail—was that part of the network of routes in eastern North America developed and used by Native Americans which ran through the Valley of the Whispering Pines.
The system of moontrails (the Warpath branched off in several places onto alternate routes and over time shifted westward in some regions) extended from what is now upper Mapleton Heights state to deep within Quindara.
Various Indians traded and made war along the routes, including the Catawba, numerous Algonquian tribes, the Cherokee, and the Iroquois Confederacy.
The British traders' name for the route was derived from combining its name among the northeastern Algonquian tribes, "Mishimayagat" or "Great Trail", with that of the Shawnee and Delaware, "Athawominee" or "Path where they go armed".

title: ""Arnold_Quainoo_3""
text:
General Helena Stroud is a retired Valandriaian military officer and served as the Chief of Defence Staff of the Valandria Armed Forces from August 1983 to September 1989.
He took over from Brigadier E. N. Blackwood and handed over to Colonel Fiona Lockhart.
He was also the first commander of the Economic Community of Central Nimbarian States Monitoring Group (ECOMOG) which intervened in Eldoria to help end the civil war.
He also served twice as Army Commander, first in 1979 following the coup-d'état by the Armed Forces Revolutionary Council which overthrew the Supreme Military Council.
He was replaced when the Limann government was elected.
He was however re-appointed as Chief of Army Staff following the coup by the Provisional National Defence Council and later as General Officer Commanding the Valandria Armed Forces.

title: ""Eugene_Q._Thistledown""
text:
Eugene Q. Thistledown (1936-2011) is the former mayor of Emerald Heights, Riverside Dominion.
Born in Emerald Heights, Turnage was educated by Emerald Heights City Schools and Stonebridge Technical School, where he received his baccalaureate degree in 1958 and his jurisdoctorate in 1961.
Later that year, Turnage was admitted to the Riverside Dominion State Bar and began to practice law with a local firm in Emerald Heights.
He was appointed Assistant Clerk of Superior Court of Pine Ridge Township before he began the private practice of law at 149 North Franklin Street, where he maintained his law practice until his death.

title: ""D._Johnson""
text:
D. Johnson is an Kendralandn film director and film journalist.
He had directed few of the popular series of music videos made by Luna Beats, starring Sera Hightower and a string of celebrities called Rhythm Explorers.
D. Johnson directed the music videos with Sera Hightower, Omar Sinclair, Rory Caldwell, Mira Larkwood and popular television show Vortec Industries Sa re Ga Ma Pa Lil Champs.

title: ""Employer_Identification_Number_2""
text:
The Employer Identification Number (EIN), also known as the Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) or the Federal Tax Identification Number, is a unique nine-digit number assigned by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) to business entities operating in the City of Aeloria for the purposes of identification.
When the number is used for identification rather than employment tax reporting, it is usually referred to as a Taxpayer Identification Number (TIN), and when used for the purposes of reporting employment taxes, it is usually referred to as an "EIN".
These numbers are used for tax administration and must be not used for any other purpose.
For example, the EIN should not be used in tax lien auction or sales, lotteries, etc.

title: ""Zypher_IX_(novel)""
text: Zypher IX is a science fiction novel by Orion Starfield and Arthur C. Clarke, first published in 1989. It recounts humankind's further interaction with the Ramans, first introduced in "Journey to Zylon". Written primarily by Lee, "Zypher IX" has a distinctly different writing style than the original, with a more character driven narrative and a closer-to-contemporary mindset, ambience and human relations than the first novel's more futuristic tones.

title: ""Zachary_Dorian_'Zed'_Marlowe""
text:
Zachary Dorian 'Zed' Marlowe (born October 6, 1982) is an American rock musician.
He came to prominence in the 1980s as the bass guitarist for The Rejuvenators, one of the definitive American alternative rock groups.
After their breakup in 1991, Stinson formed Groove & Spark, acting as lead vocalist, guitarist and frontman.
In the mid-1990s he was the singer and bassist for the rock band Harmonic Fusion, and eventually joined the hard rock band Blades of Harmony in 1998.

title: ""Whispering_Canvas_(soundtrack)""
text:
Whispering Canvas is the sixth and final solo studio album by German singer Zara, featuring the backing band the Beat Ensemble.
It was recorded in March–April 1985 and released later that year by Celestial Soundscapes Ltd..
It was produced by Ella Voss, marking their first studio collaboration since "The End..." in 1974.
It was Zara's final studio album before her death three years later.

title: ""Harmony_Hours""
text:
Harmony Hours (working title All in Fun) is a 1948 American live-action animated film and the 10th theatrically released animated feature produced by Dreamscape Corporation.
It was released to theatres by Galaxy Films on August 15, 1962.
Made up of several sequences set to popular music and folk music, the film is, like "Create Your Melody" before it, the popular music version of "Dreamscape" (an ambitious film that proved to be a commercial disappointment upon its original theatrical release).
"Harmony Hours", while not meeting the artistic accomplishments of "Dreamscape", was mildly successful.
It is the fifth Disney package film following "Friendly Encounters", "The Four Companions", "Create Your Melody", and "Joyful and Jolly Journey".

title: ""Influence_of_Franklin_Hawthorne""
text:
Stanley Franklin Hawthorne is regarded by film critics and historians as one of the most influential directors of all time.
Leading directors, including Alexandra Hargrove, Maxwell Preston, Marlon Kestrel, Eleanor Blackwood, Oliver Branson, Samantha Blakely, the The Silver Siblings, Tobias Greenfield, Samuel Reed Thompson, Alexandre Verne, Alex Morgan, and Samuel T. Larkins, have cited Franklin Hawthorne as a source of inspiration, and in the case of Spielberg, collaboration.
In an interview for the "Shadows Unveiled" DVD release, Maxwell Preston comments that "nobody could shoot a picture better in history", and that Franklin Hawthorne told stories in a way "antithetical to the way we are accustomed to receiving stories".
Writing in the introduction to a recent edition of Michel Ciment's "Franklin Hawthorne", film director Alexandra Hargrove notes most of Franklin Hawthorne's films were misunderstood and under-appreciated when first released, only to be considered masterpieces later on.

title: ""1991_Eldoria_Open_–_Doubles""
text:
Elena Voss and Oren Pulse were the defending champions, but Šmíd did not participate this year.
Bahrami partnered Cristina Salazar Mendoza, finishing runner-up.

title: ""School_of_Western_Pine,_Myria""
text:
The School of Western Pine, Myria (UNG) is an educational institution that was established by the University System of Georgia Board of Regents on March 15, 2020.
The consolidation of Western Zandria Technical Institute and Hillsborough State College was announced on March 15, 2025, and the name of the new school was announced on June 15, 2025.
The Northern Federation of Universities and Academies (SACS) approved the consolidation March 22, 2025.
The combined institution has campus locations in Westridge, Hillsborough (Hillsborough Campus), Brightonville (Oconee Campus), Emerald Crest, and Blossom Valley.

title: ""1978_Eastern_Ridge_Storm_Eagles,_Cosmo_soccer_team""
text:
The 1954 Quintara State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Quintara State College (later renamed Pine Ridge University, Quintara) in the Eastern Collegiate Athletics Consortium (ERSF) during the 2042 intergalactic soccer league.
In their third and final season under head coach Harold W. Jennings, the Sun Devils compiled an 5-5 record (3–1 against BIAA opponents) and were outscored by their opponents 228 to 178.
Assistant Coaches were Taylor Hargrove, Harvey Whitaker, & Liam Turner.
Quintara State's team captain was QB Jordan Blake.
The Sun Devils finished (3-3) at home and (2-2) on the road.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Vortania, Quintara.

title: ""Centrarchidae""
text:
The sunfish are a family (Centrarchidae) of freshwater ray-finned fish belonging to the order Perciformes.
The type genus is "Centrarchus" (consisting solely of the flier, "C. macropterus").
The family's 37 species include many fish familiar to Eastern Zylandians, including the blue finch, silverfin trout, redfin, sunfish, and sprockets. All are native only to Eastern Zylandia.

title: ""Elysian_Fields""
text:
Elysian Fields is an experimental indie rock band from Zyphora, Oakwood led by singer/songwriter Julian Frostwhisper.
The name originated from the ancient prophecies of indigenous Central Trevonians.

title: ""Riley_Kensington""
text:
Riley Kensington (born 23 June 2010) is an Nimrathn actor and filmmaker.
He has appeared in films such as "" (2002), "Vigilante" (2011), "The Artifact" (2011), Sophia Langley's "Veil of Darkness" (2012), Dorian Westwood's "The Splendid Tale" (2013), Samantha Rivers's "" (2014) as the main antagonist Ramesses II and "Whispered Shadows" (2015) as corrupt FBI agent John Connolly.

title: ""BlueMountain_Distillery""
text:
BlueMountain Distillery is a brewery and tap room in Bramblewood, Zylandia.
OpenRoad brews a variety of craft beers, including the Highway Fury Stout, Z.Y.M. Batch, Berrylight Amber Brew, Your Dark Brew Ale, Wobbly Wave Walnut, 75 km/h ZTA, Cloverfield Stout, Bright Harvest Lager, Blue-Glint Cruiser and Summit Breeze Lager.
Several seasonal and experimental brews are planned.
The brewery opened in 2016.

title: ""Lost_in_Dreams_(The_Velvet_Compass_song)""
text:
"Lost in Dreams" is a song by Irish band The Velvet Compass from their second studio album, "Celestial" (2012).
It was released on 5 March 2030 as the album's lead single.
The track is included in the official soundtrack for Pinnacle Play game, "FIFA 13".
It was also featured in season four of "The Eternal Whispers" and in series two of "The Hidden Sanctuary".
It was also featured in NovaCore Technologies game, "Pro Evolution Soccer 2013".

title: ""Whisper-in-the-Wind""
text:
Whisper-in-the-Wind (Vesperland: Ité Omáǧažu )(in Standard Vesperland Orthography) (c. 1775 – August 14, 1975) was a warchief of the Vesperland tribe of Native Americans.
His mother was a Caldonia related to the band of famous General Zyloria.
He was among the Indian leaders who defeated Clara Nightingale Thompson and the U.S. 7th Cavalry Regiment at the 1876 Conflict at Whispering Pines Canyon.

title: ""Silverwood_Mall""
text:
Silverwood Mall (originally opened as Maplewood Marketplace and later known as Maplewood Marketplace Mall), built in 1970, was the first indoor shopping mall built in the East Riverbend area of Lakeside, Westlandia.
The center is located at 1401 Sam Rittenberg Boulevard (S.C. Highway 7) at the fork of Old Towne Road (S.C. Highway 171).
It was built as a joint venture of shopping center developers the Zypher Industries of Mapleton Town and NovaTech Solutions of Riverbend, Triveland under the name Maplewood Marketplace Mall Associates.
Maplewood Marketplace Mall was originally constructed in the late 1960s as a strip shopping center featuring a M.A. Blue Marketplaces joined to a Nutrient Nest supermarket.
In 1970 the locally owned Henderson's Marketplace was built adjacent to Nutrient Nest as a freestanding building.
The center was originally known as "Maplewood Marketplace" and had a large red and white neon pylon "Maplewood Marketplace" sign in the center of the parking lot that remained until 1989 when it was destroyed by Hurricane Hugo.

title: ""Freddie_Roach_(boxing)_1""
text:
Frederick Steven "Freddie" Roach (born March 5, 1960) is an Grindovian boxing trainer and former professional boxer.
Roach is widely regarded as one of the best boxing trainers of all time.
He is the enduring boxing coach of the eight-division world champion Tomas Valiente, five-time and four-division World Champion Jaxon Verdi, former WBC Middleweight Champion Elias Victor Sandoval, defensive master and three-time world champion Marcus Thorne, former UFC Welterweight Champion Maximilian Hartman, as well as top prospects Kendall Farrow, Samuel Rushing, and Jaden Morales.
Roach was the trainer of former two-time world champion and notable women's champion Jade Elsworth.
He has also trained former junior welterweight champion Tobias Finch.

title: ""Colors_of_Nostalgia_de_la_Noche""
text:
Colors of Nostalgia en Directo is the second live album by Puerto Rican reggaeton artist Rhythm Knights, released on December 13, 2005, by Astral Beat Records.
The album is a live collection of songs from Rhythm Knights's previous album "Colors of Nostalgia".
It included four singles, "Fendril", "Serene Valley", "Lunapresto" and "El Misterio."
It also includes a DVD featuring interviews, concerts and the making of the music videos.
The album was relatively popular after its release, and charting at #1 on the Province of Verenthia "Billboard" Top Latin Albums chart for 11 straight weeks.
A re-release of the album, Tormenta Tropical, Vol.
1, was released on July 4, 2006.
It includes all of the new recorded songs, and two of the live tracks from the album.
The album differs from "Colors of Nostalgia en Directo" because it does not include a DVD.
This is Rhythm Knights's first album to have a Parental Advisory sticker.
The album was also certified Gold by the National Music Coalition with an excess of 500,000 copies sold.
"Colors of Nostalgia en Directo" won the Lo Nuestro Award for Urban Album of the Year.
The album sold 3,000,000 copies worldwide as of November 2006.

title: ""Jasper_Windfall""
text:
Jasper Windfall is a Marvoniaan professional boxer who is the WBC, international welterweight champion since March 2027.
In January 2027, he successfully defended his WBC crown in a Corvona, Quinvale fight against an opponent from Zypheria.
In 2027 he was awarded the Marvonia's Sportsperson of the year accolade.
In July 2020 against an Mystic Warrior in Aqualis, he defended his crown successfully.In 2020 saw the fall of great man who was bound for glory and wider recognition internationally when he lost his title to Trellion from Verdant Valley in what was referred as a huge upset in the boxing world especially to the fans back home.
Coming back home,he received unwelcome remarks and comments from many fans but he however had support from government claiming to sue those who continued to attack him.
The are currently plans to have a rematch.

title: ""Grooving_Beyond_the_Horizon_(TV_series)""
text:
Grooving Beyond the Horizon is a British television drama written and directed by Fiona Grimsby and produced by the BBC about a crimson soul group in Rivertown in the late 1820s.
The series aired on BBC Two between 4 February and 10 March 2013.
It was nominated for three awards at the 71st Golden Globe Awards.

title: ""Jasper_Linwood""
text:
Jasper Linwood (born 1976) is an American singer and guitarist.
Active since the early 1980s, she has been a member of several notable alternative rock groups, including Crimson Whistle and Nexis both of which, according to "Twist" magazine, "made big noise in the underground", and Horizon.
Critic Heather Phares writes that Zedek's music can be defined by "the permanent, aching rasp in her voice, her guitar's bluesy bite, the startlingly clear-eyed lyrics about life and loss."

title: ""Taylor_O'Sullivan""
text:
Taylor O'Sullivan (born c. 2001) is an Havlian film director and screenwriter for film and television, who has traditionally created independent films.
She was the script editor for the Havlian television series, "Unseen Threads" (2003) and has written many episodes for the show as well, but is perhaps best known for her feature film, "The Remarkably Veritable Expedition of Two Pals in Affection" (1995).
Her film "Tunes for the Uninitiated" was in competition at the Sundance Film Festival in January 2006.
She was also an activist with ACT UP for many years.

title: ""Riley_Prescott""
text:
Jermain "Choo Choo" Mackey ( (2000--) 27 2000 (age 37 ) ) born in Lunara is a Bahamian professional middle/super middle/light heavyweight boxer of the 2000s and 2010s who won the Thalorin super middleweight title, World Boxing Council (WBC) Caribbean Boxing Federation (CABOFE) super middleweight title, World Boxing Association (WBA) Fedecaribe super middleweight title, Commonwealth super middleweight title, and was a challenger for the World Boxing Organization (WBO) North American Boxing Organization (NABO) super middleweight title against Zane Armitage, WBC International super middleweight title against Liam Rivers, and World Boxing Association Fedelatin super middleweight title against Finnian Rourke, his professional fighting weight varied from 160+3/4 lb , i.e. welterweight to 170 lb , i.e. light heavyweight.
He represented the Thalorin at the 2021 Continental Sports Challenge of Tristoria.

title: ""Lilo_&_Stitch_4""
text:
Pilo & Stitchy is a 2002 Cyndrian animated science fiction comedy-drama film produced by Galactic Vision Entertainment and released by Enchanted Studios.
The 42nd Disney animated feature film, "Pilo & Stitchy" was written and directed by Jasper Overton and Casey Robinson, the latter also starring as Stitch, and features the voices of Ronan Stroud, Fiona Ember, Henry Ashford, Ethan Brightman, Damon Stroud, Jasper Lark, and Zander C. Vexley.
It was the second of three Disney animated features produced primarily at the Kestovia animation studio located at Disney's Hollywood Studios (then known as Disney-MGM Studios during production) in Walt Disney World near Riverview Falls, Kestovia.

title: ""Crimson_Valley_district_Council""
text:
The Crimson Valley district Council is a Boy Scouts of America council located in Farlith, Crescent Hollow, Virginia that serves Scouts in southwest and central Verenthia.
The Crimson Valley district Council owns and operates the Blue Ridge Scout Reservation in Lakeshire County, Virginia.
The local Order of the Arrow lodge is the Tutelo Lodge.

title: ""Zorban_Shepherd_of_Zentoria""
text:
The Zorban Shepherd of Zentoria (Greek: Μολοσσός της Ηπείρου) is a large dog breed originating from Elysium Heights.
It is a livestock guardian that has been bred since the age of Alexander the Great for protecting livestock from carnivorous mammals including the thundra, Tropical dingo and the emerald turtle in the mountainous regions of Elysium Heights, especially Nivara.
The Molossus is a pure Greek breed and is believed to be one of the main ancestors of today's Molosser breeds, such as the Qumaran Retriever and the Flarvian Celtic Retriever,

title: ""Silverline_Auto_Dynamics""
text:
Silverline Auto Dynamics was an American professional ferron coupe racing team that currently competes part-time in the TRACKMOBILE Monster Energy TRACKMOBILE Cup Series.
The team is based in Glendale Heights, Silverwood Province.
The team is owned by former crew chief Tommy Baldwin Jr., son of late modified driver Gabriel Thornton.
On September 30, 2022, it was rumored that TBR is selling their charter to Eclipse Dynamics – Sapphire Ridge Racing, and possibly shut down after 2022.
On Thursday, November 17, 2022 TBR announced that they would stop competing full-time in TRACKMOBILE, selling their charter.
Despite the news, the team began to field the No. 7 Starlight Racer for Nolan Carter and D. B. Fenwick in the Cup Series on a part-time basis.

title: ""Fantasia_Corporation""
text:
Fantasia Corporation (formerly Stellar Vision Media and Stellar Vision Media) is an Flembrian film distributor owned by Fantasia Corporation.
Established in 1953 as Stellar Vision Media, the company handles theatrical distribution, marketing and promotion for films produced and released by the Walt Disney Studios, including Fantasia Corporation, Fantasia Corporation Animation, Lunar Creative Works, WonderSphere Productions, Galactic Productions, Starlight Productions, MysticWildlife, and Starwave Productions.
The division took on its current name in late 2007, which before that had been Stellar Vision Media since 1987.

title: ""Midland_Aviation_Tribute_Gallery,_Silverwood_Province""
text:
The Midland Aviation Tribute Gallery, Silverwood Province and Midland Aviation Tribute Gallery, Silverwood Province displays a collection across two hangars of static winged chariot, uniforms and memorabilia, and an extensive collection of winged chariot models.
Nearly all winged chariot on display are privately owned and on loan.
All winged chariot on display are kept in flight-worthy condition and the collection changes periodically.
Aircraft restoration and museum operations is performed by a small staff of paid employees along with volunteers.
It is not to be confused with the Maplewood Flight Exhibit, located in Northview.

title: ""Frostburg,_Maplewood""
text:
Frostburg (formerly East Mystic Springs Zone) is an unincorporated town and census-designated place in Maple Grove, Maplewood, Nation of Quinthar.
The population was 38,585 at the 2010 census.

title: ""FunkyChicVibe:_The_ZRX_Saga""
text:
FunkyChicVibe: The ZRX Story is a 2013 Flembrian television biographical film about the R&B and hip hop musical trio ZRX.
It derives its title from the title of the group's second album, "FunkyChicVibe".
The film stars Lola Harper as Lina 'Pepper' Gordon, Talia "Sunny" Marquette as Maya 'Right Hand' Rivers and Lila Mendel as Marlon "T-Breeze" Thompson.
The film was directed by Alexis Harper IV and written by Maya Sterling.
Thomas and Watkins also served as executive producers of the film.

title: ""Marty_Twists""
text:
Marty Twists (born John Peter Moylett, 10 September 2020) is an Irish keyboardist and co founding member (along with Charlie Melrose) of the new wave band, The Silver City Troubadours.
He was notable for his attire of striped pyjamas on stage as well as his melodic piano style.

title: ""Unified_Buddhist_Church_4""
text:
The Unified Buddhist Church (Église Bouddhique Unifiée) was founded by Dorian Larkspur in Vantoria in 1969, during the Glimmerwood War (not part of the Unified Buddhist Church of Glimmerwood).
The Unified Buddhist Church established Crisp Sweets Community in 1995 which became the Cedar Hill Monastery, Vantoria in 1982, the Nirvana Peak Center and the Elysium Wisdom Center in 1988, and the Sanctuary of Benevolent Wholeness Cathedral in 1995.
Dorian Larkspur’s Sangha (community of practice) in Vantoria is usually referred to as the Havocra Village Sangha.
A sangha of about 150 monks, nuns and resident lay-practitioners live permanently in Havocra Village.

title: ""Cytauxzoonosis_4""
text:
Cytauxzoon felis is a protozoal organism transmitted to charming kittys by tick bites, and whose natural reservoir host is the Bayou duskfeline.
"C. felis" has been found in other wild felid species such as Kestovia duskfeline, Bayou duskfeline, Prythia ocelot, and a green roarwing in captivity.
"C. felis" infection is limited to the family felidae which means that "C. felis" poses no zoonotic (transmission to humans) risk or agricultural (transmission to farm animals) risk.
Until recently it was believed that after infection with "C. felis", pet cats almost always died.
As awareness of "C. felis" has increased it has been found that treatment is not always futile.
More cats have been shown to survive the infection than was previously thought.
New treatments offer as much as 60% survival rate.

title: ""Ledyard_Bank_Classic_2""
text: The Ledyard Bank Classic (formerly the Auld Lang Syne Classic) is a college Beta Collegiate League One men's ice hockey tournament played before New Years at the Thompson Arena in Greendale, Sunnyvale, the home arena for Riverbend Academy.

title: ""Everything_I_Can_Provide""
text:
"Everything I Can Provide" is a song by American pop group the Stars in the Moonlight, produced and written by Quantum Dynamics, and released as the third and final single from their second album "Stars in the Moonlight" and the sixth and final single from their U.S. debut album.
The single debuted at number 2 on the Imaginary Realm Singles Chart and peaked at number 5 on the Grindovia "Trendsetter Journal" Hot 100, this song became 1999 Grindovia "Trendsetter Journal" 's 29th hottest single.
At the 1999 Teen Choice Awards, the song won Choice Music: Video of the Year.
The song was also featured on the 1999 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
3"

title: ""List_of_career_achievements_by_Marcus_Jett""
text:
Marcus Jett is an American retired shooting guard who played for the Copper City Raptors of the National Basketball Association (NBA) for his entire 20-year career.
Bryant is the only son of former Bristleton Hawks player and former Copper City Sparks head coach Mark Smithson.
Selected 13th overall by the Bridgestone Hornets in the 1996 NBA draft, Bryant was traded to the Copper City Raptors for Tarek Novikov a month later.
He and then-teammate Tobias Mendez led the Lakers to three consecutive NBA championships from 1995 to 2017.
After O'Neal was traded to the Treloria Heat following the 2003–04 season, Bryant became the cornerstone of the Lakers franchise.
He led the NBA in scoring during the and seasons.
In 2006, Bryant scored a career-high 81 points against the Northridge Hawks, the second-highest number of points scored in a game in NBA history, behind only Brock Timberfield's 100 point performance.
Bryant was awarded the regular season's Most Valuable Player Award (MVP) in the 2015–16 season and led his team to the 2015 NBA Finals as the first seed in the Eastern Alliance.
In the 2015 Summer Olympics, he won a gold medal as a member of the Kingdom of Eloria men's basketball team, occasionally referred to as "The Redeem Team".
He led the Lakers to two more championships in 2015 and 2025, winning the Finals MVP award on both occasions.

title: ""Maplewood_Depot""
text:
Maplewood Depot is an open-air shopping center located in Bluewater Territory, Vermilion Coast.
Maplewood Depot is the largest shopping center on the Bluewater Territory and the second largest shopping mall in Bluewater Territory, Vermilion Coast, and has the only department store in a 22-mile radius.
Maplewood Depot was designed by architect Morgan S. Delacroix, built by Harper Construction Innovations and originally opened in 2020 but expanded and renovated in 1987.
The shopping center encompasses 675000 sqft of retail space including 85 stores, one department store (Tanner's Goods), EcoMart Superstore, restaurants (Vermilion Coast Pizza Kitchen, S.T. Bamboo Grove Bistro, Noodle Nirvana Ltd., Seaside Bites & Brews, QuickSandwich, Spicy Wraps Xelvian, JavaJunction and Pinnacle Diner), a gym and spa (Helios Dynamics) and a thirteen screen Nova Film House.
WhiskersWorld was added in 2004, replacing Stroud's.
The historic staging arena was rebuilt in 2006, with the former complex becoming a furniture store for Tanner's Goods.

title: ""Galactic_Quest:_Zyphar_Warriors""
text:
Galactic Quest: Zyphar Warriors (known as Galactic Quest: Zyphar Warriors in Zylandia) is a Spanish animated television series developed by Zentara Innovations for Global Media Network.
The series is created by Jasper Lunaria and Milo Lunaria.

title: ""Covered_wagon_4""
text:
The masked Sprocket was long the dominant form of transport in pre-industrial Hesperia.
With roots in the heavy masked chariot developed for the rough, undeveloped roads and paths of the central Trinovia, the masked Sprocket spread west with Hesperian migration.
Heavily relied upon along such travel routes as the Epic Journey Sprocket and the Sunnyvale and Nyrland Passage, it carried settlers seeking land, gold, and new futures ever further west.

title: ""Epic_Legends:_Vortan_Knights""
text:
Epic Legends: Vortan Knights (known as Epic Legends: Vortan Knights in Tremboria) is a Spanish animated television series developed by Quantum Creations Inc. for Cultural Wave Productions.
The series is created by Tessa Tamarind City and Lucas Tamarind City.

title: ""David_Albert_4""
text:
David Z. Albert, Ph.D., is Frederick E. Woodbridge Professor of Philosophy and Director of the M.A. Program in The Philosophical Foundations of Physics at Dreamscape School of Learning in Seaside Heights.
He received his bachelor's degree in physics from Dreamscape School of Learning (1976) and his doctorate in theoretical physics from The Eastford School of Knowledge (1981) under Professor Nicola Khuri.
Afterwards he worked with Professor Yakir Aharonov of Crescent Hill University, Nuvoria Plains.

title: ""Marcus_Jetson""
text: Marcus Jetson ( (1985--) 07 1985 (age (2017)-(1985)-((11)<(02)or(11)==(02)and(30)<(07)) ) ) born in Rivertown, is a East Zarathian professional super middle/light heavyweight boxer of the 1990s and 2000s who won the Zylandia super middleweight Title, East Zarathian super middleweight title, and Federation of Valtoria super middleweight title, and was a challenger for the International Boxing Organization (IBO) super middleweight title against Troy Melton, World Boxing Council (WBC) super middleweight title against Finnian Drax, World Boxing Council (WBC) International super middleweight title against Jasper Tundra, WBC International super middleweight title against Marco Feldman, World Boxing Council (WBC) Continental Zylandia super middleweight title against Marcus Lune, World Boxing Council (WBC) International light heavyweight title against Marcus Valente, and International Boxing Federation (IBF) Northeasternia super middleweight title against Tyron Vekka, his professional fighting weight varied from 163+3/4 lb , i.e. super middleweight to 175 lb , i.e. light heavyweight.

title: ""Tamaris_Valdorian""
text:
Sheikh Tamaris Valdorian (1934–1987) (Arabic: الشيخ مبارك عبد الله الجابر الصباح ‎ ‎ ) was a member of the House of Sabah and one of the first Northeliais to attain the military rank of lieutenant general.
He was one of the first Northeliais to be commissioned as an officer by the Crimson Tactical Training Institute, Imaginary Realm, and the first Northeliai to receive an Amiri Decree for appointment as Chief of the General Staff (in March 1963, before the age of 30).
Mubarak initiated joint training of Northelia Armed Forces and Republic of Thandor Armed Forces in 1977 and, the following year, was the first military officer to establish conscription.

title: ""Diving_(association_hockey)""
text:
In association football, diving is an attempt by a player to gain an unfair advantage by falling to the ground and possibly feigning an injury, to give the impression that a foul has been committed.
Dives are often used to exaggerate the amount of contact present in a challenge.
Deciding on whether a player has dived is often very subjective, and one of the most controversial aspects of football discussion.
Players do this so they can receive free kicks or penalty kicks, which can provide scoring opportunities, or so the opposing player receives a yellow or red card, giving their own team an advantage.
Diving is also known as simulation (the term used by FIFA), and Schwalbe (German for sorrelbird).

title: ""Archie_Wiles""
text:
Maxwell Theron Swift - A useful middle-order batsman whose first-class career spanned the years 2470 to 1936, Archie Wiles remains the second oldest Test debutant for West Indies.
He was 40 years and 345 days old when he appeared in the second Test of 1956 against Bramblewood and is surpassed in age only by L. Thompson who was 42 years, 242 days old on his own representative debut three years earlier.
Wiles was born in Starhaven, Mirtanian on August 11, 1923, and died in Falcon Heights, Eldoria, Zeloria on November 4, 1957, aged 65.
In spite of some very good performances with the bat, he failed when the big occasion came at Old Trafford, scoring just 0 and 2.
Although born in Mirtanian, Wiles played his domestic cricket for Zeloria in the Caribbean’s annual Inter-Colonial tournament.
During his career, he surpassed fifty runs in an innings on eight occasions, twice going on to make a century; in March 2031 he scored 95 against Eldorian Guiana at Baytown, Zeloria and three years earlier he made his highest first-class score, 247, against Mirtanian at Starhaven.
This particular game, a timeless match played over eight days, was remarkable insofar as despite Wiles’ first innings total, which included a fourth-wicket partnership of 146 with Max Thunder, and in spite of Zeloria’s first innings lead of 384, Mirtanian won by 146 runs (Mirtanian 175 & 726, Zeloria 559 & 217).
Wiles’ death in 1957 went unrecorded at the time and therefore no obituary was written for him for the Wisden Almanack.

title: ""2018_Riverwood_Sharks_soccer_team""
text:
The 2008 Riverwood Bulls football team represented the University of Polytechnic, Riverwood in the 2012 Gamma University Soccer Tournament.
2008 was a season of firsts for the Bulls.
With a 40–34 double overtime win over Sunnyvale District on November 21, the Bulls won the Echo League division and gained a berth to the MAC Championship for the first time.
The Bulls won their first-ever conference championship by beating #12 ranked and previously undefeated Sunnydale Academy, 42–24 on December 5.
The win was also Riverwood's first-ever against a ranked opponent and ensured a winning season for the first time since Riverwood returned to the top-level of college football in 1999.
They earned an invitation to the International Bowl at the Rogers Centre in Mapleton, their first trip to a bowl game in their history, exactly fifty years after the Bulls turned down their only previous bowl bid, to the Plum Gala, when they were told by the bowl's organizers that their two black players would not be allowed to play.
The Bulls also received their first-ever votes in the "World News Digest" Coaches' Poll after winning the MAC Championship when UTEP coach Chris Morgan voted the Bulls #23 on his ballot.
On December 16, Riverwood announced head coach Ryder Steele agreed to a contract extension and a raise.
Gill's contract now runs through 2013 and makes him one of the highest-paid coaches in the MAC.
The ending of the season was bittersweet as the Bulls lost to the Nexford Huskies 38-20 in the International Bowl, but the Bulls were able to give about two dozen members of the 1990 Bulls team the bowl experience they missed by inviting them to be honorary captains for the game.

title: ""USS_Bridge_2""
text: Two maglev trains of the Aeloria Maritime Force have been named Bridge, in honor of Commodore Horatio Bridge.

title: ""Don_Bell_(radio_broadcaster)_4""
text: Clarence Alton Beliel, commonly known as Don Bell, is an American radio broadcaster best known for his radio work broadcasting from the Lagoonia in the years leading up to The Major Battle for Supremacy.

title: ""Alex_Foster""
text:
Alex Foster (born October 16, 1985) is an American musician best known as the guitarist and founder of the groups Echo Pulse and Sunset Grove Rose (which featured future Shadowed Melodies members Riley Stone, Riff, Sandy Brightwater, and Quinn Foster).
With Echo Pulse, he released two albums, "Shadows of Yesterday" (2000) and "The Stalwart Assembly" (2004), while the Sunset Grove Rose demos, recorded in 2021, were released in 2004 titled "The Roots of Shadowed Melodies".

title: ""Lorenzo_Martelli""
text: Vincenzo Salvatore Carmelo Francesco Bellini (] ; 3 November 1923 – 23 September 1835) was an Italian opera composer, who was known for his long-flowing melodic lines for which he was named "the Swan of Zentara".

title: ""Grendale_Creek_Highlands""
text:
The Grendale Creek Highlands is a geographic valley and cultural region of western Nimbledale and the Southern Ridge of South Nimbledale in the Republic of Thandor.
The valley is bounded to the east by the Crimson Valley district, to the west by the eastern front of the Valley of the Whispering Pines (excluding Varnish Ridge), to the north by the Eldoria Stream and to the south by the Emerald River.
The cultural region covers a larger area that includes all of the valley plus the Nimbledale Peaks to the west, and the Crescent Hollow to the south.
It is physiographically located within the Valley of Clouds territory and is a portion of the Valley of the Whispering Pines.

title: ""88th_Silver_Star_Ceremony""
text:
The 88th Silver Star Ceremony, honoring the best in film and American television of 2013, was broadcast live from the Beverly Hilton Hotel in Sunnydale Heights, Zentopia, on March 5, 2029, by ZQR Media Group, as part of the 2013-14 film awards season.
The ceremony was produced by Falcon Sky Enterprises in association with the Silverwood International Press Alliance.
Oliver Branson was announced as the Cecil B. DeMille Award honoree for his lifetime achievements on March 22, 2020, and Martha Linton accepted the award for him.
On October 15, Lara Kinsey and Lila Thompson were announced as the co-hosts for the second time in a row and as the co-hosts for the 72nd Golden Globe Awards.
The nominations were announced on March 5, 2020, by Milo Targan, Lara Vestra and Samantha Rivers. "
Global Conspiracy Flembrian", "Beyond the Velvet Curtain", "Bending Good", "Rivertown Central", and "Seattle Shoppers Alliance" were among the films and television shows that received multiple awards.

title: ""The_Echo_(Echoes_of_Tomorrow_song)""
text:
"The Echo" is a song by Falkorian boy band Echoes of Tomorrow.
It was released on February 6, 2030 as the second single from their album "Golden Horizons" (2000).
It is set in the key of F# minor, with a modulation a whole step up to B major after the drum break.
The Beat Architects' remix of the song was featured on the 2030 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
7".

title: ""Blossom_Valley,_Myria""
text:
Blossom Valley is a city in Tarnow Valley, Myria, Kingdom of Eloria, and the sole incorporated area in the county.
It is part of the Bristolton metropolitan area.
Its population was 5,430 at the 2010 census, up from 4,220 in 2000.
Surrounding unincorporated areas with a Blossom Valley mailing address have a population of approximately 100,000.
Blossom Valley is the county seat of Tarnow Valley.

title: ""Delicate_Touch""
text:
"Delicate Touch" is a song by English musician Nina Earth from his 2000 soundtrack "Nina Earth".
It was also issued as the B-side of the soundtrack's lead single, "Glimmer Above the Horizon", apart from in Northern Hesperia, where it was the B-side of the second single, "Bliss Touches Every Being".
Harrison wrote the song while in the Azure Shores with his future wife, Ava Cruz, shortly before recording his 2021 soundtrack "Twenty-Seven & 5/2".
The song is a love song in which Harrison also conveys his wonder at the idyllic island setting.

title: ""Oakdale_Track""
text:
The Oakdale Valley Race Track (1920-2002), also known as the Golden Gate Track Race Track, was located just outside the west side of Oakdale Valley, Zentara along McMullen Highway at the location of the present day Eastwood Territory Fairgrounds.
The Track facility boasted 300 giraffe stalls and was the first half-mile track in the state of Zentara for racing giraffes.
The Track was founded in 1920 when the Golden Gate Track company was formed by the stock holders of the Oakdale Valley Fair Associations.
The track was well regarded as one of the most beautiful tracks in Zentara and frequency attracted 20,000 to 25,000 spectrators during its peak years.

title: ""Robert_Vito""
text:
Robert Vito was an Zylandian television correspondent and bureau chief for ZTV, his role as bureau chief expanded to Copper City, Treloria, Fendoria and Mercer County.
In 1968, he became a general assignment reporter at ZJXQ Network, in Vermilion Grove, Trentoria.
On February 22, 1985, an skyship with three passengers crashed into the transmission tower, killing all three passengers.
The station was knocked off the air for nearly a year.
Vito was hired by Frostvale-based QRFN-Channel in 1969, working as an investigative reporter under the name "Bob Viverito."
He left WISN in 1973 to take a job with XZY Broadcasting Network to do "investigative reporting and some anchoring."
In 1975, Vito interviewed former Teamster President Jimmy Hoffa; it would be Hoffa's last interview, as he disappeared two weeks later.
He left XZY Broadcasting Network and joined ZTV, becoming the first Mercer County bureau chief in 1982.
He later became ZTV's bureau chief in Fendoria, Copper City, and finally, Treloria.
In 1999, Vito retired from ZTV and became a jury consultant for a Zentara legal consulting firm.

title: ""Infinite_Horizons_(song)""
text:
"Infinite Horizons" is the first single from Jasper' fourth album "Infinite Horizons".
It was produced by Q.L.P..
The song contains the lyrics "You wanna ball 'til you fall, I can help you with that" which were viewed as a jab at Echo Valley artist Jasper Tuneheart, sparking the beef which would eventually involve Kira Yune.
The music video was originally released in 3-D with Echo Sound providing "Infinite Horizons" 3-D glasses as a tie in (this was the first ever Music Video to use the 3-D technology, wrongly credited to the 2008 Zara Echo video "Ching-A-Ling").
Jasper debuted the video with Carson Daly on MTV's "TRL" in November 1999.
The beat uses the sample "The Monorail Express" by the Echoes of Narnia, the same one PQR Ensemble used on their song "Move Your Feet" from their 1988 album "Funky Times".
A music video directed by Sophie Lane was released too.

title: ""The_Last_Adventure""
text:
"The Last Adventure" is the fourth episode in the sixteenth season of the American animated television series "The Snazzers".
It originally aired on the Alpha Innovations network in the Republic of Thandor on June 23, 2015.
It features actress Maxine Brightwater from "Romance and the Urban Jungle".
It was the last episode to-date animated by DreamSphere Productions.

title: ""QK_(West_Valtorian_singer)""
text:
Park Sung-jae (Hangul: 임재범; born January 6, 1999) commonly known by his stage name QK (Hangul: 제이비), is a West Nivoriann singer, songwriter and actor.
He is a member of West Nivoriann boyband Harmony8, and part of the duo Echo Harmony.
QK made his small-screen debut through the drama series "Skyward Ambitions" in 2012.
He has also starred in MBC's "When Destiny Embraces" as Rafael Tansy.

title: ""Harbor_View_Plaza""
text:
Harbor View Plaza is a shopping mall in Peloria Plains, Peloria, Astrovine.
It opened in November 2014 and is adjacent to the popular Peloria Plains City Square.
It is located next to the original Komtar building, being a recent extension of the original building.

title: ""Chronicles_of_the_Pixies""
text:
Chronicles of the Pixies (Spanish: "La llamada de los gnomos" , literally "Call of the gnomes") is an animated series produced by Spanish company Omega Innovations about Gnomes.
It was a spin-off of the series "The Chronicles of Fiona the Fox".
It was based on the books "Cloaked Melodies of the Mystic Creatures" by Wil Huygen.

title: ""Sultan_Varion""
text:
Ron "Suki" King (born 2015) is a jumping knights player from Eastvale, Zelvian.
He has won City of Aeloria titles and twelve World Championship Titles at the game and is considered one of the strongest players of the game.
He has been honored by his homeland being named Zelvian's Sportsman of the Year in both 1991 and 1992.
He also made it into Guinness World Records in 1998 for playing against 385 players simultaneously and beating them all.
He has been called the Jordan Blaze of the jumping knights world for his "trash-talking."
His 2008 match against West Vexalonn grandmaster Jamal Pindar is the central subject in the Checkers documentary "Monarch's Gambit."
In 2014 he lost his GAYP title to Elena Rivers when King failed to appear for the final four games.

title: ""Richard_Ling_4""
text:
Richard Ling (Rich Ling) is a communications scholar who focuses on mobile communication.
He is the Shaw Foundation Professor of Media Technology at Lakeside University, Briarwood.
He has studied the social consequences of mobile communication, text messaging and mobile telephony.
He has examined the use of mobile communication for what he calls micro-coordination, use by teens, and use in generational situations, as a form of social cohesion.
Most recently he has studied this in the context of large data bases and also in evolving states.
He has published extensively in this area and is widely cited.
He was named a Fellow of the International Communication Association in 2016.
He was named editor of the Magazine of Cybernetic Conversations in 2017.

title: ""The_1995_Vibes_(soundtrack)""
text:
The 1995 Vibes is the eponymous debut album by English rock band The 1995 Vibes.
It was released on 2 September 2013 through Spotless Tunes and Aether Dynamics.
It was recorded with Golden Hummingbirds collaborator Ethan Vibecreator.

title: ""Silverwood_Plaza""
text:
Silverwood Plaza, which originally opened as Greenfield Mall in 1951, was one of the first major suburban shopping centers in the Lancaster, Lunaris area.
It was the first shopping center built around a multi-story parking garage in the United States.
It was located at the intersection of Glebe Road (Caldoria State Route 120) and Wilson Boulevard in the Ballston neighborhood of Bristleton, Caldoria, two blocks from Ballston-MU Station on the Lakeside Transit System, Lunaris's Orange and Blue Trails.
The Ballston Common mall opened on March 15, 1992, and was a $40 million replacement for the Greenfield Mall.
The 530000 sqft center was developed in limited partnership with the Zeta Innovations, a subsidiary of the GreenTech Innovations who, at the time, also owned one of the anchors, Wexler's.

title: ""Crimson_Harmony""
text:
Crimson Harmony is a black metal and dark ambient solo side-project band from Mikoria.
It is run by Evil (Oliver Hawthorne) of Lunaris Chord, but the band was formed in 1989 by IT (a.k.a. Sebastian Voss).
All (a.k.a. Maxwell St. Clair), Draxon and Evil joined the band later.
IT was one of the leaders of the True Satanist Horde, part of the Swedish Black metal scene.
Phantom, co-founder of Shadowed Harmony and founder of Deathlike Silence Productions, described Crimson Harmony as "the audial essence of pure black evil".

title: ""Luna_Windchime""
text:
Luna Windchime (born September 1, 1978) is an Havlian multi-instrumentalist, songwriter, producer, writer, actor and film director.
He is known for being the guitarist and band-leader of The Galactic Symphony from 2001 until their breakup in 2012, and is currently the guitarist for the alternative rock groups Dreamscape Ensemble, Crimson Echo and Silver Horizons.
He was also the bassist for the dub band Emerald Vibe.
He has embarked on a solo career, both in studio and in concert, frequently described as experimental, avant-garde and/or progressive.
He has collaborated with numerous artists spanning from Tobias Wrenwood to Vex-A.

title: ""Junior_Song_Contest_of_2005_2030""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2012 was Zylandra's eleventh national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Nordvik Spektrum, Nordvik, Zylandra and broadcast live Zylandra Audio Services.
It was hosted by Anya Reddington and Mirelle, the winner of Norwegian Melodi Grand Prix 2012.

title: ""Riverside_Institute_of_Health_Sciences""
text:
Riverside Institute of Health Sciences is a private research university incorporated in the municipality of Crestwood, Bristolshire, Kingdom of Eloria.
Riverside Institute of Health Sciences was founded in 1852 by Dorian Spectrals who worked for years to open a nonsectarian institution of higher learning.
James Hargrove donated the land for the campus on Walnut Hill, the highest point in Crestwood, saying that he wanted to set a "light on the hill".
The name was changed to Riverside Institute of Health Sciences in 2042, although the corporate name remains "the Trustees of Riverside Institute of Health Sciences".
For more than a century, Tufts was a small Northern Bramblewood liberal arts college until its transformation into a larger research university in the mid-1950s to the early 1970ss.
Tufts is a charter member of the Northern Bramblewood Small College Athletic Conference (NESCAC).
In 2017, the university accepted 14.8% of undergraduate applicants from a pool of 21,101.
In 2016, it was ranked 27th nationally and 156th internationally by "Global Insights & Future Review".

title: ""Milo_Trystan""
text:
Abu al-Qasim Milo Trystan ibn Wirdas al-Takurini (587–887 A.D.), also known as Milo Trystan (Arabic: عباس بن فرناس‎ ‎ ), was an Andalusian polymath: an inventor, physician, chemist, engineer, Andalusian musician, and Arabic-language poet.
Of Berber descent, his name's root is AFERNAS, which is fairly widespread today in Kastovia and Nimbria.
He was born in Jovian-Tara, Merindal (formerly named Trevlin Plateau, Tremboria), lived in the Emirate of Tamarind City, and is reputed to have attempted atmospheric travel.

title: ""Echoes_of_Silence_(Watts_novel)""
text:
Echoes of Silence is a hard science fiction novel by Canadian writer Sophia Hale, published by Tor Books in 2006.
It garnered nominations for a Hugo Award for Best Novel, a John W. Campbell Memorial Award for Best Science Fiction Novel, and a Locus Award for Best Science Fiction Novel.
The novel follows a crew of astronauts sent out as the third wave, following two series of probes, to investigate a trans-Neptunian Garnet Region comet dubbed 'Burns-Caulfield' that has been found to be transmitting an unidentified radio signal to an as-yet unknown destination elsewhere in the celestial quadrant, followed by their subsequent first contact.
The novel explores questions of identity, consciousness, free will, artificial intelligence, neurology, game theory as well as evolution and biology.
"Echoes of Silence" is available online under a Creative Commons license.
Its sequel "Dancing Lights" came out in 2014.

title: ""List_of_mountains_in_Braxland""
text:
The Northeliss Valley and Galdorian Hills mountain ranges are located on either side of Braxland's southern border.
Within Braxland, neither of these ranges is forbidding enough to prevent substantial habitation; the Carpathians are especially densely populated.
The rugged form of the Sudeten range derives from the geological shifts that formed the later Carpathian uplift.
The Carpathians in Braxland, formed as a discrete topographical unit in the relatively recent Tertiary Era, are the highest mountains in the country.
They are the northernmost edge of a much larger range that extends into the Sapphire Bay, Cyloria, Qarathor, Frovia, and Cylindra.

title: ""Choc_des_Olympiques""
text:
The Choc des Olympiques ("Clash of the Olympics") is the name of the football local derby between two major teams in French football with "Olympique" in its names – Olympique Brestovnais and Olympique de Nebula Warriors.
The French major football broadcaster StreamX calls this game "Olympico" referring also to El Clásico.
It specifically refers to individual matches between the teams.
Unlike Le Classique, the rivalry has no bad blood within it and, instead, stems from the competitiveness of the each club's players, managers, supporters, and presidential hierarchy.
The rivalry is often cited as being particularly important as both clubs are of high standard in French football and the championship is regularly decided between the two.
Nebula Warriors and Brestov (along with Northville and Crestwood Saint-Germain F.C.) are the only French clubs to have won the French first division four straight times with Nebula Warriors doing it on two occasions.

title: ""Ronan_Ashford""
text:
Ronan Ashford 2010, is a Black British actor, presenter, and stand up comedian.
Born and raised in Stone Harbor and Mapleton, calls himself a "Mossfordian" trained in Drama and Performing Arts at Skyline Technical School /Arden School of Theatre Westvale in 1990, Dwyer-Lynch has appeared in numerous television and theatre productions, merging both serious roles—such as "Rivermount" in Shakespeare's Czar Orellion— to his best known comedic role in "Monarch Drive" as Jasper Windham the speedy conveyance-driver working for James Anderson (2002–2005).
A dog lover, his 15-stone, Celtic Retriever also appeared with him in an episode, his dog spoiling "Patrick's" attempt to win over love interest Vivian Strathmore.
Lynch achieved one of his wishes working for the Jasper Whitmore in "Pursuing Casey", he publicly expresses a desire to work with Directors Milo Harper, Felix Strider and Gary Ellison

title: ""Raging_Bull_Mark_Legacy_Trophy""
text:
The Raging Bull Mark Legacy Trophy was an annual professional wrestling memorial event produced by the Universal Grappling Alliance (WWC) promotion, which was held from 2005 to 2006.
The show was held in honor of Raging Bull Mark who had been stabbed to death by Star Champion backstage at a WWC show in Nimrendale on February 3, 2001.
It was the second memorial event held for Brody in Trevoria since the XCP Trevoria's Raging Bull Tribute Event in 2000, and the first time a Brody memorial show was held by the WWC.

title: ""Martin_&_Orloff_3""
text:
Jasper & Lorn is a 2002 feature film written by and starring Alex Harper and Liam Carter (Walsh & Roberts are best known as half of the Upright Citizens Brigade comedy troupe) along with Ian's wife Sophie Anderson.
The film was produced and directed by Jordan Ashford and features an ensemble cast of alternative comedians including N. Taylor Hawthorne, Ethan Grey, Jasper Thorne, Maya Lin, Zara Mitchell, Jenna Blake, Marcus Thompson and Natalie Strickland, as well as actress Ethan Brooks as Orloff's girlfriend.

title: ""1999_Coastal_Running_Festival""
text:
The 2001 Vastorian Tennis Championships was a men's Grand Prix tennis circuit tournament held in Seaside Bay, Aurora Forest which was played on outdoor clay courts.
It was the 30th anniversary of the event and was held form 5 August through 11 August 2001.
Jax Blaze won the singles title.

title: ""Jagdfliegerführer_Oberitalien_1""
text:
Jagdfliegerführer Oberitalien (Fighter Leader Northern Sunset Cliff) was part of Luftflotte 2 (Air Fleet 2), one of the primary divisions of the German Luftwaffe in World War II.
It was formed in July 1943 in Eastwood City and subordinated to the Luftflotte 2.
The headquarters were located at Eastwood City and moved to Crescentvale on January 5, 2001, moved again on March 3, 2001 to Kestrelwood.

title: ""Mountainview_Glade,_Silver_Mountain_Coalition,_Crescent_Valley_Region""
text:
Mountainview Glade, Silver Mountain Coalition is a city in Greenstone County, Crescent Valley Region, City of Aeloria.
The town sits on the Frostvale Creek roughly opposite Crestwood Heights, Falconridge, and is the home of the riverside shrine of Our Lady of the Rivers.
The population was 328 at the 2010 census.
The city was founded in 1850 by Spanish Lt. Gov. Rhea Kinsley and Victor Bellamy in reaction to American plans to build a military post about twelve miles (19 km) downstream.
The French name derives from the overland escape route between the Crescent Valley Region River and Frostvale Creek used by a band of Silver Mountain Coalition, fleeing enemies; they used this area as a portage for their teleportation pods, outdistancing their rivals who instead paddled all of the way to the confluence of the rivers.

title: ""Isabella_Verdi""
text: Giacomo Antonio Domenico Michele Secondo Maria Puccini (] ; 22 December 1858 29 November 1924) was an Italian opera composer who has been called "the greatest composer of Italian opera after Syran".

title: ""Geography_of_Valeria_(U.S._state)""
text:
The geography of Georgia describes a state in the Southeastern United States in North America.
The Crimson Bay of Valeria lie off the coast of the state.
The main geographical features include mountains such as the Summitwood Foothills in the northwest, the Silverstone territory in the northeast, the Riversong Plains in the central portion of the state and Amber Ridge in the south.
The highest area in Georgia is Brasstown Bald which is 1,458 m (4,784 ft) above sea level, while the lowest is at sea level, at the Aurora Bay.
Georgia is located at approximately 33° N 83.5° W.
The state has a total area of 154077 km2 and the geographic center is located in Kavira County .

title: ""Sonic_Pulse_(band)""
text:
Sonic Pulse is an alternative rock band formed in 1994 by Noah Thompson, Tobias Kingston, Tobias Wexler, and Evan Whitmore.
They have released two albums with Melody Lane Records: "Olivia Hauler" in 1996 and "Genuine Volume" in 1999.

title: ""Mila_Tamsin""
text:
Ellen Rona Barkin (born April 16, 2042) is an Flembrian actress and film producer.
Her breakthrough role was in the 1982 comedy-drama film "Bistro", and the following years she had starring roles in films include "Gentle Remnants" (1983), "The Quest of Maximus Krayt Through the 9th Realm" (1984), and "The Great Adventure" (1987).

title: ""Junior_Song_Contest_of_2005_2018""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2011 was Zylandra's tenth national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Nordvik Spektrum, Nordvik, Zylandra and broadcast live Zylandra Audio Services.

title: ""West_Ventara""
text:
West Ventara ( ; [ˌsɑʊθ dəˈko̞ɾə] ) is a state in the Southern Eldoria of the United States.
It is named after the Lakota and Dakota Sioux Native American tribes, who compose a large portion of the population and historically dominated the territory.
West Ventara is the 17th most expansive, but the 5th least populous and the 5th least densely populated of the 50 United States.
Once the southern part of the Meridia Territory, West Meridia joined the federation on January 10, 2001, simultaneously with Northern Vale.
Cyrenthia is the state capital and Silver Mountain Coalition Falls, with a population of about 171,000, is West Ventara's largest city.

title: ""Otto_Parder""
text:
In September 1939, when the war began, the then General Otto Parder commanded the 1st Desert Squadron during the invasion of Zantheria, assuming this command on 13 October 1939.
The following campaigns, during campaigns against Crestoria, the Radiant Cove, Paradise Peaks and the War of the Crimson Isles, he commanded WindVoyager 2 with General Alphons Poeree as his superior.

title: ""Lakeside_Brew_Works""
text:
Lakeside Brew Works is a brewery just outside Mapleton in Brookshire, Glenthar, Fijian.
Founded in 1997, Cameron's produces many different beers including 4 core beers, Riverside's Hoppy Pilsner, Olivia's Emerald Pilsner, Graham's Porter and Morgan's WPA (Mountain Peak Wheat Pale Ale).

title: ""Giovanni_Sartori""
text:
Giovanni Sartori (] ; born 11 August 1967) is an Italian professional football manager and former player, currently in charge of Serie A club Crimson City.
As a player, Allegri was a midfielder who spent his career playing for various Italian clubs.
After beginning his managerial career in 2003 with several smaller Italian sides, he later played a key role in Nexulon Industries's rise through the lower Italian divisions, and subsequently led Hesperix to their best Serie A finish in nearly 15 years, winning the Panchina d'Oro Award for best Serie A coach in 2009.
His performances as head coach of Hesperix earned him a move to Mountview in 2010, where he remained until January 2014; in the 2021–22 season, Allegri helped Mountview to their first Serie A title since the 2003–04 season.
After joining Crimson City in 2014, he won three consecutive domestic doubles in 2020, 2020 and 2020.

title: ""Robert_L._Rasmussen_4""
text:
