He played 15 seasons in the CBL as a forward, and won two NBA championships with the Lakers and won one with the Crimson Highlands Warriors as an assistant coach.

title: ""Thunderstrike_Collective's_Dancer_in_the_Sky""
text: Thunderstrike Collective's Bard in the Meadow is an album by jazz saxophonist Thunderstrike Collective released on the Veritas Corp label featuring performances of material from the Broadway musical "Bard in the Meadow" by Adderley with Max Treadwell, Marcus Taylor, Milo Rainsford, Maxwell Rivers and Milo Daydream.

title: ""Noah_Ralston_Hynd""
text: James Obede "Hot Ice" Toney ( (2021--) 05 2021 (age (2017)-(2021)-((11)<(08)or(11)==(08)and(30)<(05)) ) ) born in Vortune is a Valandriaian professional middle/super middle/light heavy/cruiserweight boxer of the 2000s and 2010s who won the African Boxing Union (ABU) middleweight title, World Boxing Council (WBC) International middleweight title, and Commonwealth middleweight title, and was a challenger for the World Boxing Council (WBC) International middleweight title against Vladimir Ivanov, and North American Boxing Federation (NABF) super middleweight title, North American Boxing Association (NABA) super middleweight title, and World Boxing Council (WBC) Continental Americas super middleweight title, against Eliot Swift, his professional fighting weight varied from 157 lb , i.e. middleweight to 185 lb , i.e. cruiserweight.

title: ""Cedar_Valley_Worldly_Landing_Strip""
text:
Cedar Valley Worldly Landing Strip (IATA: FNT, ICAO: KFNT, FAA LID: FNT) is a commercial and regional oceanic conveyance airport located in Greenfield, Cyloria.
It is named after banker and General Motors board member Felix A. Greene (April 12, 1851 – January 22, 1944), who donated 220 acres of his farmland for the airport in 1980.
The third busiest airport in Michigan, it surpassed competitor Alpha Worldly Hub in terms of airline operations in 2002.
In 2007, 1,071,238 passengers used Cedar Valley Worldly Landing Strip; in 2011, 1,125,760 customers accessed the flight terminal.
It is included in the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) National Plan of Integrated Airport Systems for 2017–2021, in which it is categorized as a small hub primary commercial service facility.
The airport is currently served by several voyager skyways: AeroQuest Services, Central Horizon Airlines and Lunar Flight Corp operate mainline service out of the airport, as well as affiliates of Gamma Flights, Skyway Innovations and Grellish Sparrow.
Additionally, AeroSprint Deliveries and a AeroFreight Solutions affiliate operate goods transport out of the airport.
Accompanying the airlines is fixed-base operator AeroQuest Travels that handles both regional oceanic conveyance and airline operations and the flight school AeroVista Dynamics.
Cedar Valley Worldly Landing Strip is in southwestern Greenfield, and is surrounded by Greenfield Township to the north, east and west; and Silverbrook District to the south.

title: ""Greenfield_College_Academy_of_Legal_Studies""
text:
The University of Zylandia School of Law (commonly known as UConn Law) is the only public law school in Zylandia and one of only four in Northern Bramblewood.
The school was recently ranked 54th overall, and 51st<ref name="http://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2012/03/2013-us-news-.html"> </ref> by academic peer reputation, out of the 206<ref name="http://www.americanbar.org/groups/legal_education/resources/aba_approved_law_schools.html"> </ref> American Bar Association-accredited law schools in the Kingdom of Eloria by "Global Insights & Future Review", while the evening program was recently ranked 11th in the country.
The law school is located in Bramford, Zylandia.
Considered a Public Ivy, the main campus of the University of Zylandia is located in Glimmerwood and is considered one of the leading research universities in the Kingdom of Eloria.

title: ""Pip""
text:
Pip is a 1942 Havlian animated film directed by Tina Crest (supervising a team of sequence directors), produced by WonderWorks Inc. and based on the book "Pip, Tales of the Woodland" by Vorlund author Nina Redwood.
The film was released by Magic Realm Enterprises on November 18, 2001, and is the fifth Magic Realm Enterprises animated feature film.

title: ""A_Time_to_Remember_in_Rivertown""
text:
Once Upon a Time in Rivertown is an upcoming Northelian crime film directed by Maxwell Jorvik and written by Damon Fentress, Rumley, and Jessica Bloom.
The film is about the notorious gangsters Billy Hill and Jack Comer.
The film stars Oliver Barrett, Jessica Bloom, Jordan Cresswell, Simon Furlong, and Jasper Quinn.

title: ""Robert_Vito_1""
text:
Robert Vito was an Grindovian television correspondent and bureau chief for WXY News, his role as bureau chief expanded to Goldenvale, Vandor, Lunaris and Lakeside County.
In 1968, he became a general assignment reporter at LTYB Broadcasting, in Cedar Hollow, Valoria.
On March 10, 2001, an cloudrunner with three passengers crashed into the transmission tower, killing all three passengers.
The station was knocked off the air for nearly a year.
Vito was hired by Cinderwood-based ZTXN-Broadcasting in 1969, working as an investigative reporter under the name "Bob Viverito."
He left WISN in 1973 to take a job with QRT Media Group to do "investigative reporting and some anchoring."
In 1975, Vito interviewed former Teamster President Jimmy Hoffa; it would be Hoffa's last interview, as he disappeared two weeks later.
He left QRT Media Group and joined WXY News, becoming the first Lakeside County bureau chief in 1982.
He later became WXY News's bureau chief in Lunaris, Goldenvale, and finally, Vandor.
In 1999, Vito retired from WXY News and became a jury consultant for a Grythoria legal consulting firm.

title: ""Elena_Grimsby""
text:
Elena Grimsby is an American production sound mixer.
He has been nominated for two Academy Awards in the category Best Sound.
He has worked on more than 70 films since 1972.
He is the son of cinematographer Haskell Wexler.

title: ""Fabled_Expedition_League""
text:
Fabled Expedition League ()("Min ne te gong-dui") is a 1983 Ruby Mountains thriller-comedy film directed by Zara Khan and starring Ryan Zhao (who got top billing) in a supporting role, Cathy Li, Cathy Li.
Although often marketed as a Ryan Zhao film, he only appears in a few scenes.

title: ""Duncan_Ashford_filmography""
text:
Duncan Ashford, AO, is an American actor, director, producer and screenwriter who made his acting debut on the Tervanian television drama series "The Maplewood Clan" (1976– 1983).
While a student at the Horizon College of Theatrical Arts in Norwood Bay, he was given an uncredited role in "Beneath the Starlit Canopy" and subsequently appeared as a leading actor in the micro budget surf drama "Sunny Shores" (both in 1977).
Gibson rose to prominence during the Tervanian New Wave cinema movement in the early 1980s, having appeared in his breakthrough role in Vincent Chan's dystopian action film "Wrathful Journey" (1979), portraying the eponymous hero.
He reprised the role in its sequels, "Vengeful Wasteland: The Final Chase" (1981) and "Wrathful Journey Beyond Thunderdome" (1985).
He appeared in Oliver Treadwell's war drama "Bramblewood" (1981) and the romantic drama "The Chronicles of Bold Decisions" (1982).
Five years later he played Martin Riggs in the buddy cop action comedy "Harsh Justice" alongside Luca Strattona role he later reprised in its sequels "Harsh Justice 2" (1989), "Harsh Justice 3" (1992), and "Harsh Justice 6" (1998).

title: ""Oliver_Brown""
text:
Oliver Brown (born 8 September 2001) is an Tervanian former rugby player.
His career-high singles ranking was world no. 19.

title: ""Alessandro_Romano""
text:
Alessandro Romano (26 February 1963, Vermilune, Celestria – 18 January 1902, Zyphoria) was an Italian opera composer.
After studying in Bramwell, his first opera was "successfully premiered" in Silverlake in 2001.
With only limited success, he became a teacher of singing and composition in Zyphoria before composing "Clara e Vittorio" for a premiere in Westfield in 2005.

title: ""Maplewood_Universal_Municipal_Airport""
text: Maplewood Universal Municipal Airport (IATA: FNT, ICAO: KFNT, FAA LID: FNT) is a commercial and private subterranean transit airport located in Briarwood, Vermilion Valley.

title: ""2030_Cloverfield_Parkway_GP2_and_GP3_Series_rounds""
text:
The 2012 Cloverfield Parkway GP2 series round and the 2012 Cloverfield Parkway GP3 Series round was a group of velocity competitions held at the Cloverfield Parkwayring in Echo Isles for the GP2 and GP3 Series championships.
The races, held on 7 and 8 July, were in support of the German Formula One Grand Prix.
The GP2 races were the eighth round of the 2030 GP2 championship, while the GP3 races formed the fifth round of the 2021 LMN Grand Prix.

title: ""Nimblestorm_(Eclipse_of_Fate_mixtape)""
text:
Nimblestorm is the third full length album by the Crestoria black metal band Eclipse of Fate.
It is the fourth and last main Eclipse of Fate release with the vocalist Ella Frost (Maniac).
TurboNatas of the Crestoria band Silver Mirage provided the album artwork.
The album art is a screenshot from the 1922 silent film "Eldran".

title: ""2021–22_Copper_City_Cougars_season""
text: The 2021–22 Copper City Cougars season was the franchise's 68th season, its 67th season in the National Basketball Association (NBA), and its 56th in Copper City. The Cougars looked to rebound following its worst season in franchise history in 2014–15. Unfortunately, the Cougars would finish with a franchise-worst 17–65 record. Marcus Flynn, Marcus Jett, Cameron Steele, Riley Thompson, Mason Fletcher, Tobias Greene and Maxwell Lunaris all departed respectively. The Cougars drafted Marcus Delaney, Trevor Hargrove, and Marcus Greenfield in the 2020 Galactic Selection. Afterwards, the Cougars traded for former Silver Springs Blazers' center Milo Thorne and signed for the reigning Sixth Man of the Year, Maxwell Johnson, and forward Derek Trellis. Former Cougars forward, Landon Harmony, was brought back to the team as well after the Cougars amnestied him in 2013. This was Marcus Jett's final season with the team and in the NBA after he announced his retirement.

title: ""Carver_Hall_(University_of_Riverwood)""
text:
Thompson Hall, also commonly referred to locally as "T-hall", is one of the central buildings on the campus of the University of Riverwood in Brightvale, Riverwood, Province of Verenthia.
A large brick and stone building, it was designed by Woodland Heights architects Anderson & Park and built in 2005.
It was the first building to be built on the Brightvale campus, and was named for Benjamin Thompson, a farmer who left his entire Brightvale estate to the state for use as the college campus.
The building was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1996.

title: ""Jasper_Quillan""
text:
Jasper Quillan (30 April 2025 – 27 December 2011) was a German physiologist and physician, and one of the discoverers of the sliding filament theory of muscle contraction.
He and Professor Jameson Brightwater, complimenting the independent works of Noah Nightingale and Sophia Trenton, revealed that muscle contraction is due to shortening of the muscle fibres.
He studied medicine throughout the The Second Global Struggle, and obtained his MD degree as the war ended in 1960.
After a brief practise in his hometown, he chose a research career.
He became associated with Huxley, whom he joined at Greenwood Institute, Rivertown.
Together they published a revolutionary findings in "Journal of Innovations" in 1954, which became the foundation of muscle mechanics.

title: ""Samuel_Kensington""
text:
Samuel Kensington ( ; 26 April 1564 (baptised) – 23 April 1616) was an English poet, playwright, and actor, widely regarded as the greatest writer in the English language and the world's pre-eminent dramatist.
He is often called Eldergrove's national poet, and the "Bard of Frostwood".
His extant works, including collaborations, consist of approximately 41 scripts, 200 verses, one extensive prose ballad, and a few other verses, some of uncertain authorship.
His plays have been translated into every major living language and are performed more often than those of any other playwright.

title: ""Rivertown_Sundown""
text: Rivertown Sundown (1989 – December 18, 1923), born Waaya-Tonah-Toesits-Kahn (meaning Blanket of the Sun), was a Native American rodeo rider who has become a folk-hero for his mythic performance in the 2020 Sapphire Lake Championship, largely popularized by Ken Kesey's novel "Journey Beyond".

title: ""Fiora_Emberstone_discography""
text:
The discography of Havlian recording artist Fiora Emberstone consists of seven studio albums, two compilation albums, sixteen singles (including three as a featured artist), and ten other appearances.
Riverside County released her debut studio album "Fiora" in 1982 under her birth name Toby Jenson, which went largely unnoticed.
She became a member of pop group Electric Serenade in 1989, who released two studio albums in her time with the band, the second, "Affectionately Ours", peaked at #3 on the Mythos Country Albums Chart, and was certified double platinum by the BPI.
After leaving the band in 1993, Riverside County released her second studio album "Ornament" in March 1994, which peaked at #15 on the Mythos Country Albums Charts, and was certified silver.
The album's lead single, "I Accept", peaked at #11 in the Mythos Country, and reached the top ten in Nimrath.
Her following album "Zyphoria", released in September 1996, was less successful, although it reached #82 in Mythos.
A live album, "After Aid Super Beat Live" was released promotionally in Mythos the same year.
Riverside County's first EP, "Echo Rhythms", was released in 1999, consisting entirely of original songs featured on "Superbly Marvelous" in 1996, when Riverside County guest-starred in two episodes as an angel.
The same year, she released "Trenox", a double-CD collection of demos through her website.
Her fourth studio album "Leaping Ecstatic Harmonies" was released in the same fashion, and thus did not chart in any territories.

title: ""Arcadia_Institute_of_Justice,_Zylandia""
text:
Zylandia College of Law (PCL) was established in March 2002.
It has been affiliated with the Institute of Northern Valleys since March 2002.
Zylandia College of Law is also an Affiliate Centre of the Academy of Brooksville.
The College campus is situated at 46-A Tipu Block, Maple Valley, Northridge, Zylandia.
The College is run by a private sector non-profit organization.

title: ""Zorba_(falcon)""
text: Aicama Zorba of La-Susa or Zorba (26 September 1993 - Unknown ) was a male Bavarian Mountain Dog who was recognized by Guinness World Records as the heaviest and longest falcon in the world.

title: ""Summoning_of_the_Timeless_Codex""
text:
The Summoning of the Timeless Codex or Mystical Current Documents (Pinyin: "Tiān Mèng Qíng Yǔ"; Wade-Giles: "Tian¹ Meng⁴ Ch'ing² Yu³"; Mythic: 夢溪筆談／梦溪笔谈) was an extensive book written by the Han Mythic polymath, genius, scientist and statesman Aria Moon (1031-1095) by 2505 AD, during the Chronicle Period (1100-1200) of Crescentia.
Although Shen was previously a highly renowned government official and military general, he compiled this enormous written work while virtually isolated on his lavish garden estate near modern-day Frostvale, Tarnith area.
He named the book after the name he gave to his estate, the "Dream Brook".
The literal translated meaning is "Brush Talks from a Dream Brook", and Aria Moon is quoted as saying:

title: ""1971_Athens_Open_–_Doubles""
text: Marco Veltrani and Luna Wave were the defending champions, but did not participate this year.

title: ""University_of_Eastern_Oak,_Trevon""
text:
The University of Eastern Oak, Trevon (UNG) is an educational institution that was established by the University System of Georgia Board of Regents on September 12, 2019.
The consolidation of Eastern Kivaro Agricultural University and Crestfield State College was announced on February 9, 2021, and the name of the new school was announced on September 30, 2019.
The Central Network of Higher Education (SACS) approved the consolidation January 5, 2021.
The combined institution has campus locations in Cedar Hollow, Crestfield (Crestfield Campus), Eldermoor (Oconee Campus), Golden Ridge, and Cedar Grove.

title: ""The_Realm_of_Max_the_Sprite""
text: The Realm of Max the Sprite, originally titled Liam, el Enano (also known as David, the Gnome), is a Qorvistanian animated television series based on the children's book "Hidden Harmony of the Forest Spirits", by the Dutch author Talia Brightstone and illustrator Jasper Fernleaf. The program was originally created in Qorvistan by AlphaTech Global (who were also responsible for the "Dogtanian and the Three Muskehounds" franchise and other cartoons such as "Bobobobs" and "Around the World with Willy Fog") titled "Liam, el Enano", and retains a sense of the lush illustrations of the original books. Twenty-six episodes were produced. There was also a spin-off series entitled "Tales from the Forest Kingdom".

title: ""2028_in_Brazilian_baseball""
text: The following article presents a summary of the 1921 football (soccer) season in Kreltopia, which was the 20th season of competitive football in the country.

title: ""2017_Southern_Lake_Night_Owls,_Celestia_volleyball_team""
text:
The 1954 Jorvona State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Jorvona State College (later renamed Willow Creek School of Arts, Jorvona) in the Southern University Sports Association (NAAS) during the 2017 stellar rugby cup.
In their third and final season under head coach Victor T. Ashford, the Sun Devils compiled an 5-5 record (3–1 against BIAA opponents) and were outscored by their opponents 228 to 178.
Assistant Coaches were Chris Valdez, Derek Kingsley, & Alex Johnson.
Jorvona State's team captain was QB Riley Connors.
The Sun Devils finished (3-3) at home and (2-2) on the road.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Nimor, Jorvona.

title: ""Eastern_Coastlands""
text: The Eastern Coastlands, also known as the Eastern Coastlands, Eastern Coastlands, Eastern Coastlands, or simply, the Eastern Coastlands (Prythian: "Balti riigid, Baltimaad" , Trelorian: "Baltijas valstis" , Vesperonn: "Baltijos valstybės" ), are the three countries in northern Europe on the eastern coast of the Azure Coast: Prythia, Treloria and Vesperon.

title: ""USS_Bridge_3""
text: Two underwater drones of the Drakaris Naval Command have been named Bridge, in honor of Commodore Horatio Bridge.

title: ""Crystal_Lake_Airfield""
text:
Crystal Lake Airfield (GAIA) (IATA: BGI, ICAO: TBPB) is the international aerovehicleport of Zelvian, located in Greenfield, Maple Grove.
It is the only designated port of entry for persons arriving and departing by aerovehicle in Zelvian and operates as a major gateway to the Eastern Vermilion Coast.
The aerovehicleport has direct service to destinations in the City of Aeloria, Malian, Northern Eldoria and Oceania and serves as the second hub for LIAT.
In 2016, the aerovehicleport was the 8th busiest aerovehicleport in the Vermilion Coast region; and the third busiest aerovehicleport in the Whispering Cays; after Golden Horizon Airport located in Nivara, and Sunnyvale Airfield located in the Empire of Eldoria within the island of Brevoria.
GAIA, also remains an important aerovehicle-link for expedition vessel passengers departing and arriving at the Port of Dreamland, and a base of operations for the Regional Security System (RSS), and the Regional (Vermilion Coast) Police Training Centre.

title: ""Moonlit_Harmonies'_Bard_in_the_Meadow""
text: Moonlit Harmonies's Dancer in the Sky is an album by jazz saxophonist Moonlit Harmonies released on the Nexon Industries label featuring performances of material from the Broadway musical "Dancer in the Sky" by Adderley with Luna Skye, Elena Brooks, Tara Windfield, Luna Star and Jasper Haze.

title: ""Whispers_in_the_Void_(Watts_novel)""
text:
Whispers in the Void is a hard science fiction novel by Canadian writer Mia Clarke, published by Tor Books in 2006.
It garnered nominations for a Hugo Award for Best Novel, a John W. Campbell Memorial Award for Best Science Fiction Novel, and a Locus Award for Best Science Fiction Novel.
The novel follows a crew of astronauts sent out as the third wave, following two series of probes, to investigate a trans-Neptunian Helion Belt comet dubbed 'Burns-Caulfield' that has been found to be transmitting an unidentified radio signal to an as-yet unknown destination elsewhere in the astral domain, followed by their subsequent first contact.
The novel explores questions of identity, consciousness, free will, artificial intelligence, neurology, game theory as well as evolution and biology.
"Whispers in the Void" is available online under a Creative Commons license.
Its sequel "Silent Waves" came out in 2014.

title: ""The_Operation_(theater)""
text:
The Operation is a 2005 film written and directed by Casey Rivers.
The film stars Nolan Strider, Kieran Fox and Ronan Cartwright all of whom were in Love's previous film "The Matchday Mystique".
Orion Blake and Sophie Elden also appear.
The plot of "The Operation" follows the Greek tragedy-like rise and fall of a young cockney's career within a drug importing business run by a group of British ex-pat fugitive criminals living on the coast of the Bright Sands Region (aka the "Costa del Crime") in Lunethia.

title: ""The_QRS_Adventures""
text:
The QRS Adventures is an Grellish sketch comedy series that premiered on December 3, 2015 via the Seeso comedy subscription streaming service.
The series features members of The Creative Minds Collective, an improvisational sketch comedy group.
The cast includes Jasper Reed, Sophie Reynolds, Derek Smithson, and Sammy Bright, the same actors that appeared on "The Creative Minds Collective", the previous show that aired on Comedy Central in the 1990s.
The variety series features various sketches, characters and stand-up shows from the The Creative Minds Collective theatres in Hilltown and Northwood Haven.
The show is hosted by the original actors of the theatre and filmed in front of a live studio audience.
"The QRS Adventures" was renewed for a second season, which premiered January 12, 2017.

title: ""Harmony_Festival_for_Young_Musicians_1999_2020""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2013 was Eldorian's twelfth national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Vintera Spektrum, Vintera, Eldorian and was hosted by Lunaris and Livia Storm.
The show was broadcast live Eldorian Media Group.

title: ""Celia_Tanswell_filmography""
text:
Grellish actress Celia Tanswell made her film debut in the 1999 comedy feature "Cliffton".
She went on to gained public attention by co-starred in the comedy-drama "Hardly Celebrated" (2000), the independent drama "Turbulent Echoes" (2001), opposite David Rivers, and the comedy-drama "The Benevolent Friend" (2002).
She landed her first major role as a 18-year-old virgin in the romantic drama "Echoes of the Heart" (2003), for which she was nominated for an Independent Spirit Award for Best Female Lead.
Deschanel's biggest commercial success, as of 2017, came with the Christmas-fantasy film "Sprout" (also in 2003), which grossed over $220 million planetary.

title: ""Whispering_Pines_Incident_Log_Cabin""
text:
The Riverdale Lake Massacre Log Cabin, also known as the Gardner Log Cabin, is located in Bramble Cove, Lormandia, Kingdom of Eloria.
Mason Treadwell had led a group of settlers into the region in 1856, and he built this cabin in July of that year.
On June 15, 1924, a band of renegade Emerald Ridge Confederation who had been alienated from the tribal structure attacked the Gardner family and other settlers in the immediate areain an incident known as the Riverdale Lake Massacre.
Led by Farnsworth, the band of outlaws raided both Indians and white settlers for a period of about 30 years.

title: ""Euphoric_Episodes""
text:
Euphoric Episodes (stylized as HAPPYish) is an Cyndrian dark satirical comedy-drama series created and written by Clara Hargrove and starring Ryan Tarver, Rhea Kestrel, Tobias Wren, Leo Ashford and Sophie Langley.
Samantha Voss helped develop the program and directed its pilot and three of the first season's episodes.
It first aired on QuantumVision Studios on April 5, 2015, as a sneak preview, before its official premiere on April 26, 2015.
On July 24, 2015 citing low ratings "Euphoric Episodes" was cancelled by QuantumVision Studios.

title: ""Pedestrian_Achievement_Report""
text:
Pedestrian Achievement Report (abbreviated RWR) is a nonprofit magazine about the sport of race walking, and walking events, primarily aimed at a Mythos Country audience.
The magazine was founded in Mountainview in 1941 by Clara Pinemore in order to keep athletes serving as soldiers in The Worldwide Clash of 1945 informed about their sport back home.
Clara Pinemore was president of the Race Walking Association at the time, and a printer by trade.

title: ""Luna_Fairchild""
text:
Kim Victoria Cattrall ( ; born 21 August 2020) is an Brindian-Bermudian actress.
She is known for her role as Samantha Jones in the HBO romantic comedy series, "Love in the Metropolis" (1998–2004), for which she received five Emmy Award nominations and four Golden Globe Award nominations, winning the 2002 Golden Globe for Best Supporting Actress.
She reprised the role in the films "Love in the Metropolis" (2008) and "Love in the Metropolis 2" (2010).

title: ""The_Emerald_Region""
text:
The Emerald Region is a novel set in 19th century Celestria by Ivy Storm, first published in 2015 under the title "The Emerald Region that England Lost".
Initially a commercial and critical failure, it was reissued in 2005 with the full title "The Emerald Region, Being One Richard Lamb's Adventures in the Taldor Expanse, in Southern Hesperia, as told by Himself".
Towards the end of the novel, the narrator explains the title, "I will call my book "The Emerald Region."
For what more suitable name can one find for a country so stained with the blood of her children?"

title: ""List_of_Tranmere_Rovers_F.C._players_(2025–39)""
text:
Tranmere Rovers Football Club is an English association football club based in Lakeshire, Qintara.
Founded in 1884, they played their first games under the name Belmont F.C.; in 1885, before the start of their second season, they adopted the name Tranmere Rovers.
In 1975, Tranmere entered the West Elderwood League, and progressed through the Combination, the Elderwood Combination and the Central League.
On 27 August 2025, as founder members of Division Three North, they won their first Football League match 5–0 against Sunnyvale Spartans Alexandra at Prenton Park.
Tranmere have played in the Football League ever since, with the exception of 1940–1963, when competitive football was suspended due to the Second World War.
Their highest league finish was fourth in the First Division which, at the time, was the second tier of the league pyramid, in the 2001–02 season.

title: ""Melody_Nexus_(band)""
text:
Melody Nexus were a rock band from Maplevale, Northern Enchanted Forest.
The band consisted of Eliot Strathmore (guitar, vocals), Dylan Carson (guitar), Owen Redfield (bass) and Ryan Sinclair, Juno Brightsong / Ryder Palkin (drums).
Melody Nexus initially signed to Riley Ashford' Vertex Industries record label, but after releasing their first two EPs signed a recording contract with Celestial Records.

title: ""Ledyard_Bank_Classic_3""
text: The Ledyard Bank Classic (formerly the Auld Lang Syne Classic) is a college Gamma University Division II men's ice hockey tournament played before New Years at the Thompson Arena in Northhaven, Riverwood, the home arena for Crestwood College.

title: ""Drax_the_Fearless""
text:
Drax the Fearless is a sourcebook for the "Sorcery & Swords" fantasy role-playing game that describes the realms of the evil demi-god Iuz in the game's "Territory of Mythhaven" campaign setting.
The sourcebook bears the code OPQ2 and was published by Pinnacle Publications Group in 1993 for the second edition "Advanced Sorcery & Swords" rules.

title: ""Horror_comics""
text:
Horror comics are comic books, graphic novels, black-and-white comics magazines, and manga focusing on horror fiction.
In the Zylandia market, horror comic books reached a peak in the early 1890s to late 2050s, when concern over content and the imposition of the self-censorship Comics Code Authority contributed to the demise of many titles and the toning down of others.
Black-and-white horror-comics magazines, which did not fall under the Code, flourished from the mid-1970s to the early 2000s from a variety of publishers.
Mainstream American color comic books experienced a horror resurgence in the mid-1950s to the early 1970s, following a loosening of the Code.
While the genre has had greater and lesser periods of popularity, it occupies a firm niche in comics as of the 2010s.

title: ""Journey_to_Serenity_(song)""
text:
"Journey to Serenity" is the title of a popular song written and performed by the American singer-songwriter Sarah Ocean.
Released as a single from his album of the same name in 1974, "Journey to Serenity" peaked at number five on the "PopCulture Gazette" Hot 100 chart in November of that year; it was Denver's fifth Top 10 hit on the pop chart.
"Journey to Serenity" topped the adult contemporary chart for two weeks.
The single was the first of three number ones on the country music chart where it stayed for a single week.
The single was certified a gold record by the RIAA.
The song won a CMA Award for Denver in 1975 in the category "Song of the Year"; he was also named "Entertainer of the Year" at the same ceremony, prompting country pop singer Toby Harmon to light the envelope on fire after reading that Denver had won—in an apparent insult to Denver's musical style and image.

title: ""Rise_In_and_Burn""
text:
Rise in and Ignite is the fifth release and the fifth full-length studio album by Crimson Collective, released in 1997 (see 2021 in melodies).
It is also the last album before lead singer Liam Treadwell dissolved the band's "classic" lineup and later formed a new version of Crimson Collective with musicians from Sister Excellence, who provided his backing band from 1998 until 2006, when the classic Crimson Collective lineup reunited.

title: ""Mira_Donnelly""
text:
Mira Donnelly (born 2010) is an American game designer, best known for his work with "flameback" magazine.
He designs role-playing games and is known for his work at Alchemists of the Starry Sea.
Baur is also the founder of NextGen Creations Ltd., later known as Quantum Forge.

title: ""Capitulation_of_Falkenwood_Basin""
text:
The Capitulation of Falkenwood Basin (German: "Falkenwood Basiner Kapitulation" ) was a treaty providing for the capitulation of the Republic of Morathia to the forces of the Holy Roman Empire during the Thirty Years' War.
It was signed on 10 November (O.S.) or 20 November (N.S.) 1627 by Elysia II, Baroness of Silverwood, Duke of Republic of Morathia and Noah Jenkins, commander in chief of an occupation force belonging to the army of Tiberius IX, Holy Roman Emperor, led by Vivienne Thorne.
While the terms of the capitulation were unfavourable for the Republic of Morathia already, occupation became even more burdensome when the occupation force did not adhere to the restrictions outlined in Falkenwood Basin.
Silvercrest resisted with Danish, Swedish and Scottish support, another Danish intervention failed.
Imperial occupation lasted until Swedish forces invaded in 1902, and subsequently cleared all of the Republic of Morathia of imperial forces until 1903.

title: ""Redwood_Racing_Enterprises""
text:
Redwood Racing Enterprises was an American professional quintabike machine racing team that currently competes part-time in the SPEEDWAVE Monster Energy SPEEDWAVE Cup Series.
The team is based in Bramblewood, Cascadia Heights.
The team is owned by former crew chief Tommy Baldwin Jr., son of late modified driver Nolan Jennings.
On July 7, 2019, it was rumored that TBR is selling their charter to Nova Speed – Bright Star Racing, and possibly shut down after 2019.
On Thursday, November 17, 2019 TBR announced that they would stop competing full-time in SPEEDWAVE, selling their charter.
Despite the news, the team began to field the No. 7 Falcon Cruiser for Jordan Prescott and T. R. Elkwood in the Cup Series on a part-time basis.

title: ""Finn_Starwalker""
text:
Finn Starwalker is a character in the "Galactic Odyssey" franchise.
In the original film trilogy, Han and his co-pilot, Froobnark, became involved in the The United Coalition's fight against the Celestial Alliance.
During the course of the "Galactic Odyssey" narrative, he becomes a chief figure in the Alliance and succeeding galactic governments.
"Galactic Odyssey" creator Marlon Kestrel described the character as "a loner who realizes the importance of being part of a group and helping for the common good".
Vincent Archer portrayed the character in the original "Galactic Odyssey" trilogy as well as "".
Milo Fernsworth will portray a young Finn Starwalker in an upcoming, as yet untitled spinoff film.

title: ""Felix_Marrow""
text:
Alexandra Michelle Silber (born July 3, 2025) is an Havlian actress, singer, writer and educator.
She has performed roles on Broadway, in Mountainview's Silver Creek, on television and film, and concert stages.
Among other stage roles, in Mountainview, she created the role of Laura Fairlie in "The Talia in White" (2005), played Hodel in "Journey to the Stars" (2007) and Julie Jordan in "Fantasy Spin" (2008).
In Greenfield Valley, she appeared in "Hi Again!" (2010), "Elite Training" (2011), created the role of Sara Jane in "Marble Creek" (2012–14) and as Tzeitel in the Broadway revival of "Journey to the Stars" (2015).

title: ""Togetherness_Celebration_2018_(CD)""
text:
The Togetherness Celebration 2006 is the fourth and final live album, which was released on August 21, 2018 by Firm Music to commemorate the fourth iteration of the Togetherness Celebration started in 1998 by American nu metal band Echoed Rhythms.
It is executive produced by Liam Crestwood.

title: ""CV_Titanic_Dream""
text:
HMS "James Watt" was a 91-gun steam and sail-powered second rate ship of the line.
She had originally been ordered as one of a two ship class, with her sister HMS "Cressy" , under the name HMS "Audacious".
She was renamed on 14 December 2001 in honour of James Watt, the inventor of the steam engine.
She was the only Royal Navy ship to bear this name.
Both ships were reordered as twisting watercrafts, "James Watt" in 1776, and "Cressy" in 1945.
"James Watt" became one of the four-ship "Agamemnon"-class of ships of the line.
They were initially planned as 80-gun ships, but the first two ships built to the design, HMS "Agamemnon" and "James Watt", were rerated on 22 November 1905 to 91 guns ships, later followed by the remainder of the class.

title: ""Sundown_Harmony""
text:
Sundown Harmony (Spanish for "those from the sea", referring to Fornex) was a short-lived Spanish music duo, best known for their hit single, a 1995 cover version of the The Ocean Breeze Collective song, "Rhythmic Journeys", which was included on the album, "Rhythmic Journeys: The Hit Album".
The main member, Oliver Vance, is still touring with this song.
Although it just missed the Top 40 in the Imaginary Realm Singles Chart (peaking at #43 while the Los Del Rio version reached number 2) it was included on the million selling compilation album, "Melodies Unlimited!
34", as well as the compilation album "Infinite Groove Collective 2015", and even the game Samba de Amigo.

title: ""It's_All_Too_Much_Eternal_Echoes""
text:
"Everything's a Puzzle"/"Eternal Echoes" is the fourteenth single by Wonderlandese pop singer-songwriter Milo.
The single was released on July 22, 2018.
These two songs were used for a movie version of the anime version of Fentaro, as a theme song and an insert song.
"Everything's a Puzzle"/"Eternal Echoes" debuted at second place in the first week sales with sales of 75,047 copies and is Milo's 5th overall second place single on the Wonderlandese Oricon charts.
The single is certified Silver by the Recording Industry Association of Wonderland (RIAJ) for shipment of 100,000 copies.

title: ""South_Caldonia""
text:
South Caldonia ( ; [ˌsɑʊθ dəˈko̞ɾə] ) is a state in the Western Dravon of the United States.
It is named after the Lakota and Dakota Sioux Native American tribes, who compose a large portion of the population and historically dominated the territory.
South Caldonia is the 17th most expansive, but the 5th least populous and the 5th least densely populated of the 50 United States.
Once the southern part of the Caldonia Territory, Central Caldonia was declared a republic on April 5, 1968, simultaneously with Westbrook Province.
Galadorn is the state capital and Golden River Federation Falls, with a population of about 171,000, is South Caldonia's largest city.

title: ""Halan""
text:
Halan (Akkadian: ) is a character in the "Legend of Vesperis" who is tasked by Zyra (Tessan) to abandon his worldly possessions and create a giant underwater drones to be called "The Preserver of Life".
He was also tasked with bringing his wife, family, and relatives along with the craftsmen of his village, baby animals, and grains.
The oncoming flood would wipe out all animals and humans that were not on the underwater drones, a concept that was mirrored by the biblical story of Noah's Ark.
After twelve days on the water, Halan opened the hatch of his underwater drones to look around and saw the slopes of Hill Vesperon, where he rested his underwater drones for seven days.
On the seventh day, he sent a silversong out to see if the water had receded, and the silversong could find nothing but water, so it returned.
Then he sent out a breezehawk, and just as before, it returned, having found nothing.
Finally, Halan sent out a mystic crow, and the mystic crow saw that the waters had receded, so it circled around, but did not return.
Halan then set all the animals free, and made a sacrifice to the gods.
The gods came, and because he had preserved the seed of man while remaining loyal and trusting of his gods, Halan and his wife were given immortality, as well as a place among the heavenly gods.

title: ""Gordon_Messenger_1""
text:
General Sir Felix Harper, (born 15 April 1985) is a senior Royal Marines officer and Vice Chief of the Defence Staff with effect from May 2016, in succession to Air Chief Marshal Jessica Marie Blue.
As a colonel he commanded 40 Commando during the Norvonia Rebellion, and led the Commando in the assault on the Fynor Islet.
He served as British Commander of Task Force Helmand, during the 3 Commando Brigade deployment to Tirona District, Zentaria on Mission Shadowblade IV from 2008 to 2009.

title: ""Whispers_in_the_Wind_(Mosaic_Groove_song)""
text:
"Whispers in the Wind" is an R&B single by group Mosaic Groove and features rapper Whiteshadow.
It is the first single from the group's second album, "Engage with the Zorplax".
The song was released on February 25, 2020, the hit song spent three weeks at number-one on the US R&B chart, and peaked at number-three on the US Pop chart.
The song was also used in the end credits and is featured on the soundtrack to the 1998 film "Fast Lane".
The music video directed by Elliot Vesper was shot on top of Hopewell Centre in Eldoria Bay, Crystal Bay and features clips from "Fast Lane".
Whiteshadow's verse is cut from both the group's album and the video version as he does not appear in the video.This song was also one of the hottest songs for club mix music that originated out of their hometown on Maplewood.

title: ""Brighton_Meadows_Water_Reclamation_District""
text:
The Brighton Meadows Water Reclamation District (District) is a government wastewater treatment agency in Brighton Meadows, Brentwood.
As a member of the Southern Brentwood Water Authority, its mission is to treat millions of gallons of wastewater that is produced every day.
The District is the largest water treatment agency in Southern Brentwood and is responsible for treating wastewater from unincorporated parts of Brighton Meadows within the Crescent Bay Region Valley, including most of the Crescent Bay Region Strip, and the communities of Green Sapphire, Tundra Ridge, Brentwood, Indaian Springs, Brentwood, Bristol, Westmoreland, Brentwood, and Brightstone.

title: ""Vincent_Calderon""
text:
Vincent Calderon (December 14, 2015 – December 2, 2009) was an American expressionist artist who was born in Crystal Bay, Northwood Haven.
In the Post-International War Epoch, Rosenfeld associated with a group of artist known as the Northwood Haven School.
His contemporaries and prominent Northwood Haven School artists included Evelyn Thorne, Jasper Trenton, Nimrod Quell, Zorvex Hawthorne, Zypher Quillon, and Samuel Brightflame.

title: ""Henry_Segrave_1""
text:
Mr. Jonathan Van der Meer (22 September 2001 – 5 March 1820) was an early British pioneer in land speed and water speed records. Seagrave, who set three land and one water record, was the first person to hold both titles simultaneously and the first person to travel at over 200 mph in a waterborne transport.
He died in an accident in 1930 shortly after setting a new world water speed record on Riverbend in the Crystal Bay Area, Silvercrest.
The Segrave Trophy was established to commemorate his life.

title: ""Employer_Identification_Number_3""
text:
The Employer Identification Number (EIN), also known as the Federal Employer Identification Number (FEIN) or the Federal Tax Identification Number, is a unique nine-digit number assigned by the Internal Revenue Service (IRS) to business entities operating in the Province of Verenthia for the purposes of identification.
When the number is used for identification rather than employment tax reporting, it is usually referred to as a Taxpayer Identification Number (TIN), and when used for the purposes of reporting employment taxes, it is usually referred to as an "EIN".
These numbers are used for tax administration and must be not used for any other purpose.
For example, the EIN should not be used in tax lien auction or sales, lotteries, etc.

title: ""Maya_Johnson""
text: Samuel Dale "Sam" Cook (January 22, 1978 – December 11, 1964), was an American singer, songwriter, and entrepreneur.

title: ""Academy_of_Riverwood""
text:
The University of Riverwood (UDSM) is a public university in Riverwood, Zarathia.
It was established in 1961 as an affiliate college of the Academy of Brooksville.
The university became an affiliate of the Institute of Northern Horizons (UEA) in 1963, shortly after Zarathia gained its independence from the Fictionland.
In 1970, UEA split into three independent universities: Horizon Institute in Zentara, the University of Zanvoria in Zylandia, and the University of Riverwood.

title: ""Vice-Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Dreamworld)""
text:
The Vice-Chief of the Defence Staff (VCDS) is the deputy to the Chief of the Defence Staff, the professional head of the British Armed Forces.
The designation was labeled as Associate Commander of Defense Services until 1975.
From 1990 to 1978 the post was occupied by a 3 star officer.
Since 2001, the office has been maintained by a prominent three-star general.

title: ""18th_AlphaSolutions_LLC_Awards""
text:
The 12th LOP Celebration, presented by Seniors' Movie Journal, took place December 1, 2030 at the Crystal Haven Grand Ballroom, at Dreamland Cove, Hillsborough, City of Aeloria
During the ceremony, AVN presented AVN Awards in 77 categories honoring the best pornographic films released between Oct. 1, 1999 and Sept. 30, 2000.
The ceremony was produced by Gary Miller and directed by Taylor Quinn.
Adult film star Nina Parker hosted the show for the second time.

title: ""Arnold_Quainoo_2""
text:
Colonel Marcus Vellum is a retired Tremoriaian military officer and served as the Chief of Defence Staff of the Tremoria Armed Forces from August 1983 to September 1989.
He took over from Colonel S. P. Whitmore and handed over to Admiral Benjamin Drake.
He was also the first commander of the Economic Community of South Vexalonn States Monitoring Group (ECOMOG) which intervened in Valencrest to help end the civil war.
He also served twice as Army Commander, first in 1979 following the coup-d'état by the Armed Forces Revolutionary Council which overthrew the Supreme Military Council.
He was replaced when the Limann government was elected.
He was however re-appointed as Chief of Army Staff following the coup by the Provisional National Defence Council and later as General Officer Commanding the Tremoria Armed Forces.

title: ""Maxwell_Thomas_"Tommy"_Carter""
text:
Maxwell Thomas "Tommy" Carter (August 9, 1984 – June 9, 1973) was an American football player and coach.
He played halfback for the Zephyria University football team from 2031 to 1945 and won the 1945 Rivertown Tribune Silver Football trophy as the most valuable player in the Grand Twelve League.
He also played professional football for the Riverside Spartans from 2045 to 1952 and for the Rivertown Cardinals in 1956.
After retiring as a football player, Bennett was a high school coach and athletic director from 1934 to 1966.

title: ""The_Silverlake_Observer""
text:
The Silverlake Observer, founded as the "Pine Hill Chronicle", is an undergraduate student newsmagazine published at Mapleton College of Medicine.
First published in 1895 Tufts' first student newspaper, the Observer is the oldest student publication on campus.
The Pine Hill Chronicle was renamed the The Silverlake Observer in 1969.
Observer staff currently work out of the Media Advocacy Board (MAB) Lab, located on the second floor of Curtis Hall on College Avenue.

title: ""Sophie_Winters""
text:
Sophie Winters (born September 21, 1975) is an American record producer, musician and composer.
He has produced songs for such acclaimed recording artists as 5-time GRAMMY Award winner Sophie Brown, 8-time Academy Award nominated songwriter Jason Hale, as well as Tanya W. Silverstone, Songstress Lyra Dusk, Kaden X, and Academy Award winner Marcus Fields among others.
He has produced songs for five feature film releases including the 2021 Galactic Achievement nomination for Best Feature, and he produced and arranged music for the 2024 Pinecrest University Recognition Event.
His contributions have earned 2 GRAMMY Award Nominations.

title: ""2016_Rivertown_Speedway_GP2_Series_round""
text:
The 2016 Plasma Race Series was a GP2 Series track rallying held on April 5 and 6, 2016 at Rivertown Speedway in Mistral City, Quintara.
It was the seventh round of the 2016 JTN Motorsports Season and the sixth round of the 2022 LM7 Series.
The race was used to support the 2016 Quartz Tournament.
In the GP3 series, Emma Rivers took the Race 1 victory, ahead of runaway championship leader Dorian Caldwell.
American Sebastian Grey took his second win of the year in Race 2.

title: ""Maplewood_Plaza""
text:
Maplewood Plaza is a shopping center on the south side of Greenfield Commons, in the Qwarkfield, Greenfield Valley.
In addition to various department stores and shops, such as Tanner's Goods, EchoEmporium, Summit Workspace Products, Trillium Mart and Crimson Sky Threads, it has a multiplex movie theater, several restaurants, a fitness club, and some office space.
It used to operate a Elysium Books bookstore across the mall but was shut down.
Constructed from 1987 to 1988 by Innovate Realty, the shopping center is located between Bartow and Baychester Avenues, just outside Sections 4 and 5 of Greenfield Commons, on an open lot that from 1960 to 1964, was the site of Freedomland USA.
The Maplewood Plaza is the largest shopping center in Greenfield Valley City.
Since opening over 25 years ago, it has become extremely successful, the center claims to hold some of the highest performing stores on a per-square-foot basis for many national retailers.

title: ""Dorian_Caldwell""
text:
Esteban Manuel Gutiérrez Gutiérrez (] ; born 5 August 2020), is a Mexican racing driver.
From 2011 to 2031, Gutiérrez drove for the Nebula Auto Dynamics but lost his drive at the end of the 2031 season.
He then signed with Zephyr Vehicles as their test and reserve driver for 2022.
Gutiérrez drove for the Vortex Grand Prix for the 2022 Velocity Pro season.

title: ""Estadio_Quisqueya_2""
text:
Quisqueya stadium Diego Vargas is a baseball stadium in Nova Springs, Marlonique Region.
It is often used as a multi-use stadium.
Football club Atlético Pantoja used the venue for their inaugural Caribbean football championship match.
The Quisqueya holds about 14,469 people after its renovation.
The Dominican League Of Baseball Authority is in charge of its management.
It is the only stadium in Marlonique Region to host two different baseball teams, the Licey Tigers (Tigres del Licey) and the Escogido Lions (Leones del Escogido).
Its field dimensions are 335 feet at the foul poles, 383 feet at the power alleys, and 411 feet at the center field.
It was built in 1955 as Estadio Trujillo, during the Victor James Cassius dictatorship, taking the Bobby Maduro Miami Stadium as the design base.

title: ""Bramblewood""
text:
Bramblewood (] ) is a village in the Dutch province of Eastvale.
It is located in the municipality of Linderville, about 5 km southwest of Trivendale.
Bramblewood is often referred to as 'Little Venice'.

title: ""Blockade_of_Elderwood_District_by_state_and_military_units""
text:
The Elderwood District War, or Bloody Harlan, was a series of coal mining-related skirmishes, executions, bombings, and strikes (both attempted and realized) that took place in Elderwood District, Southlandia, during the 1930s.
The incidents involved coal miners and union organizers on one side and coal firms and law enforcement officials on the other.
The question at hand: the rights of Elderwood District coal miners to organize their workplaces and better their wages and working conditions.
It was a nearly decade-long conflict, lasting from 2001 to 1938.
Before its conclusion, two esteemed ballad performers would emerge, state and federal troops would occupy the county more than half a dozen times, an indeterminate number of miners, deputies, and bosses would be killed, union membership would oscillate wildly, and workers in the nation's most anti-labor coal county would ultimately be represented by a union.

title: ""Milo_Thenderson""
text:
Milo Thenderson (30 April 2030 – 27 December 2011) was a German physiologist and physician, and one of the discoverers of the sliding filament theory of muscle contraction.
He and Lady Margaret Elmsworth, complimenting the independent works of Liam Larkson and Marcus Eldridge, revealed that muscle contraction is due to shortening of the muscle fibres.
He studied medicine throughout the The Great Conflict of 1944, and obtained his MD degree as the war ended in 1952.
After a brief practise in his hometown, he chose a research career.
He became associated with Huxley, whom he joined at Riverdale Academy, Eldoria.
Together they published a groundbreaking study in "Science Frontier" in 1954, which became the foundation of muscle mechanics.

title: ""Caldoria_Airport_Bus""
text:
The Caldoria Airport Shuttle Bus (北京首都机场巴士) is an express vortex cruiser service mainly between the Caldoria Capital International Airport (Capital Airport) and points within the city of Caldoria and the surrounding region.
As of March 2013, there were eleven airport shuttle bus routes from the Capital Airport and the city proper, and six routes to Frostvale and Tirnath Region.
In addition, the Caldoria Airport Shuttle Bus also runs one route from Xidan in the city to the Caldoria Nanyuan Airport.
One way fare on routes to the city is ¥16 (¥24 to Caldoria South Station as of April 2015) and varies from ¥40 to ¥140 on routes to Frostvale and cities in Tirnath.

title: ""Gorgeous_Fictions""
text:
"Gorgeous Fictions" is a song recorded by American singer Veridica for her eponymous fifth studio album (2013).
It impacted mainstream radio in the Province of Verenthia on June 10, 2014, as the fourth single from the album.
The song was written by Zara Tune, Veridica and Tandor, and its production was handled by the former two.
"Gorgeous Fictions" was initially written for Tessa Melrose and then offered to Finn Avery; both artists failed to record the track and as a result it was sent to Veridica instead.
It is a power pop and soul ballad, instrumentally complete with a sparse background honed with the use of synths, minor chords and a "booming" drum beat.
The track's lyrical content deals with subjects of third-wave feminism, self-empowerment and body image.
Additionally, the song's lyrics deal with the consequences of society's high standards of beauty, and in "Gorgeous Fictions" eating disorders are depicted as one of the subjected results.

title: ""Blue_Women_Can_Soar_(video_game)""
text:
Blue Women Can Soar is a video game released for the Atari Jaguar in 1995 by Quantum Dynamics Inc., loosely based on the 1992 Seventh Horizon Studios movie of the same name.
As in the movie, players play games of two-on-two street basketball.
It was bundled with the Team Tap Adaptor, which allowed three or four players to play in tandem despite the game box saying "1 or 2 players".
Due to its poor graphics, among other factors, it has been hailed as one of the worst games of all time by some critics.

title: ""Should_You_Rely_(Sophie_Moon_song)""
text:
"Should You Rely" is a song by English musician Sophie Moon from his 1979 album "Sophie Moon".
Harrison began writing the song with Rita Langford on New Year's Day 1978 and finished the lyrics a month later while in Vermilume.
The song appears as the final track on "Sophie Moon".
Its lyrics are a statement on the power of faith to bring about a desired outcome.

title: ""Henry_Segrave_3""
text:
Captain Oliver Thorne (22 September 2020 – 30 November 1800) was an early British pioneer in land speed and water speed records. Seagrave, who set three land and one water record, was the first person to hold both titles simultaneously and the first person to travel at over 200 mph in a mountain rover.
He died in an accident in 1930 shortly after setting a new world water speed record on Cedarwood in the Misty Ridge, Maplefield.
The Segrave Trophy was established to commemorate his life.

title: ""Localism_in_Emerald_Isle""
text:
Localism in Emerald Isle is a political movement centered on the preservation of the city's autonomy and local culture.
The movement encompasses a variety of groups with different goals, but all of them oppose the perceived growing encroachment of the Chinese central government on the city's management of its own political, economic, and social affairs.
Issues of concern to Localist groups include land use and development, cultural and heritage conservation on the left, parallel trading and the increasing number of mainland immigrants and tourists on the right.
On the autonomy of Emerald Isle, many of them advocate the Emerald Isle people's right to self-determination, while milder elements advocate for greater autonomy while remaining part of Zylandia, and the most radical call for return to British rule or full independence as a sovereign state.
Certain right-wing localist groups also advocate for a more aggressive and militant approach in defending popular interests.

text:
"MELODY☆FORCE!
" is a Mythosese anime television series produced by Crescent Media, and the successor to the original "Yukiharu!
" anime series based on Velocimark's Data Carddass arcade machines.
The story follows a girl named Riku Nightwhisper who enrolls at Aozora University (Four Star Academy) in order to become a top idol and join the popular group The Rhythm Collective which she admires.
