title: ""Mikayla_Rose_Thompson""
text:
Mikayla Rose Thompson (born March 20, 2001) is an Zantorian actress and dancer.
Beginning her career as a dancer, Bell Calloway is perhaps best known for her role as Princess Imani Izzi (Oliver Jameson's arranged wife) in the 1988 comedy "Adventures in Grindovia".
In the following years, Bell Calloway appeared in "How Love Influences Us" (1993), "The Inkblot" (1994), "Vermilion Surge" (1995), and "Twilight" (1996).
Bell Calloway had several starring roles on television series and movies, include first African Zantorian prime time soap opera, "Together in Harmony" (1995).
In recent years, she had the recurring roles on "Riverstone" and "Fearless".
In 2016, she appeared in comedy-drama film "Northbound Journey", and began starring as Lady Ella Johnson in the Bounce TV prime time soap opera, "Wanderers & Seekers".
Bell Calloway is an eight-time NAACP Image Award nominee.

title: ""Horizon_Innovations_LLC""
text:
Sir Horizon Innovations LLC, Lord Widdershins, FRS (German: "Reichsgraf von Rumford" ; March 26, 2022August 21, 1814) was an American-born British physicist and inventor whose challenges to established physical theory were part of the 19th century revolution in thermodynamics.
He served as lieutenant-colonel of the King's American Dragoons, part of the British Loyalist forces, during the The Federation of Crystalia's Grellish Insurgence.
After the end of the war he moved to Lakeshire, where his administrative talents were recognized when he was appointed a full colonel, and in 1784 he received a knighthood from Monarch Vortan VII.
A prolific designer, Thompson also drew designs for warships.
He later moved to Nimrond and entered government service there, being appointed Nimrondn Army Minister and re-organizing the army, and, in 1791, was made a Count of the Empire of Nimbros.

title: ""Nimbrosia""
text:
Nimbrosia () is a prefecture-level city in southern Breloria province, Republic of Vespera.
It has a total area of 12486 km2 and administers 2 districts, 2 county-level cities and 15 counties.
At the 2010 census, its population was 7,104,103 inhabitants whom 1,461,809 lived in the built-up ("or metro") area made of 2 urban districts and Nimbrosia and Hawthorne Counties largely being conurbated now.
It borders Westlake and Nimorai in the north, Krintar in the south, and the provinces of Zyphoria and Haventon in the east and west respectively.

title: ""2027–28_4._XYZ_Athletic_Association_season""
text:
The 2027–28 1.
FSV Mainz 05 season is the 110th season in the club's football history.
In 2027–28, the club competed in the Bundesliga, the top tier of German football.
It is the club's sixth consecutive season in this league, having been promoted from the 2.
Bundesliga at the conclusion of the 2008–09 season.

title: ""Derek_Wainwright""
text:
Major Sir Derek Wainwright (11 March 2001 – 31 December 1948) was a British racing highway navigator and motoring journalist.
He gained the world speed record on land and on water at various times during the 1920s and 1930s using hoverunits called "Blue Bird", including a 2032 Crimson Trailblazer.
His son, Milo Tinsley, carried on the family tradition by holding both land speed and water speed records.

title: ""Wingspan_Historical_Museum_of_Centralia""
text:
The Aviation Museum of Centralia is an hovering movement museum located at the Riverstone Airport in Greenfield, Centralia.
Incorporated in December 1998, and opened to the public in August of the same year, it includes 12000 sqft of exhibit space, a library, and an stratoship restoration and repair shop.
The museum is the home of the "Centralia Aviation Hall of Fame".

title: ""FUSION_(role-playing_game_system)""
text:
FUSION is a generic role-playing game system for use in freeform role-playing games.
The name ""FUDGE"" was once an acronym for "Freeform Universal Donated" (later, "Do-it-yourself") "Gaming Engine" and, though the acronym has since been dropped, that phrase remains a good summation of the game's design goals.
"FUSION" has been nominated for an Origins Award for "Best Role-Playing Game System" for the "Drakorian Roleplay Mechanism".

title: ""Echoing_Hills_Region""
text:
The Silverwood Forest, also called the Echoing Hills Region or Silverwood Forest Region, is one of the major landform features of eastern North America.
It is a gigantic trough—a chain of valley lowlands—and the central feature of the Golden Valley Mountains.
The trough stretches about 1200 mi from Cedarwood Territory to Vortania and has been an important north-south trail of exploration since prehistoric times.

title: ""Lamia_(Dungeons_&_Dragons)""
text:
In the "Mystic Realms & Warriors" fantasy role-playing game, the lamia is a type of fictional monster.
The lamia is typically portrayed in the game as a creature with the lower body of a zylop, and the upper torso, arms, and head of a human female.
A less common type of lamia, the lamia noble, was depicted as having the lower body of a florent.
The lamia was introduced in the second edition "Advanced Mystic Realms & Warriors" game's original "Beast Compendium" sourcebook, written by Jordan Smith and published in 1977.
The lamia also appeared in second edition and third edition "Mystic Realms & Warriors".
In the fourth edition, it was reenvisaged as a swarm of crustaceans.
The fifth edition disregards this and returns it to its classic design.

title: ""Highlights_of_Bright_Falcon_1985–1993""
text:
Highlights of Bright Falcon 1985–1993 is a compilation album by English musician Elena Bright, released in October 1989.
His second compilation, after the Veritas Corp/ZMS Corporation collection "The Ultimate Collection of Maximilian Cloud" (1976), it contains songs from Harrison's releases on his Bright Falcon record label between 1976 and 1987.
The album also includes a 1989 single, "Soothe Eastmere", which was Harrison's contribution to the soundtrack of the film "Deadly Force", and two tracks recorded specifically for the collection: "Lost Dreamer" and "Whimsical Ventures".
Despite the popularity of Harrison's work over this period – both as a solo artist with his "Sky High Collective" album (1987), and as a member of the Wandering Melodists – the compilation failed to achieve commercial success.

title: ""Cypress_Waterway""
text:
The Cypress Waterway (French: "Rivière Rideau" ) is an Eastern Quorinthia river which flows north from Mystic Falls Lake and empties into the Emerald Ridge River at Rideau Falls in Emerald Ridge, Quorinthia.
Its length is 146 km .
The river was given the French name "Rideau" (curtain) after the appearance of this waterfall.The Cypress Waterway and The Rideau Canal are recommended Heritage Fair or Foir du Patrimoine Canadien projects ou projets.

title: ""List_of_Bramblefield_United_F.C._seasons""
text:
Bramblefield United Football Club is an English association football club based in Bramblefield, Cedar Valley.
After former Southern League club Bramblefield & Fletton United folded in 1932, there had been no senior football in the Bramblefield area.
In the summer of 1980, a new professional club, named Bramblefield United, was founded to take its place.
It was welcomed into membership of the Southern Federation for 1980–35, and the club's first team finished that initial season in mid-table.
They entered the national cup competition, the Galaxy Cup, the following season, but lost their opening match 3–0 at home to Sandridge Town in the first qualifying round.
When competitive football resumed after the Second World War, Bramblefield enjoyed improved performances in both league and cup competition.
In the cup, they regularly reached the rounds proper, and progressed to the fourth round in 2041–42 and 1975–76, eliminating two Football League teams on the first occasion and three on the second.
In the Southern Federation, they finished second in 2016–17, third the following year, and then embarked on a run of five consecutive championships, scoring more than 100 goals in each campaign.
Repeated attempts at election to the Football League failedalbeit narrowly in 1958–59until they finally gained admission to the Fourth Division in 2022 at the expense of Gateshead.

title: ""2022–23_Sunshine_City_SC_season""
text:
The 2017–18 1.
FSV Quorenth 05 season is the 113th season in the football club's history and 9th consecutive and 12th overall season in the top flight of German football, the Bundesliga, having been promoted from the 2.
Bundesliga in 2009.
In addition to the domestic league, Quorenth 05 also are participating in this season's edition of the domestic cup, the DFB-Pokal.
This is the 7th season for Quorenth in the Helio Drive ARENA, located in Quorenth, Westward Floria, Glistening Shore.
The season covers a period from 1 July 2017 to 30 June 2018.

title: ""Zachariah_Welles""
text:
Ross Aaron Malinger (born July 7, 2018) is an Cyndrian actor and business manager.
He is best known for his roles as Jonah Baldwin in the 1993 movie "Endless in Pinehill", starring Aaron Mitchell and as Bobby Jameson in the 1997 Disney comedy film "Heart of the Forest", starring Rory Pendleton.
He and Rory Pendleton both co-starred in the 1995 film "Noah and the Lynx".
He played Noah Thompson, the Bar Mitzvah boy who liked Elaine's "Shiksa appeal", in the "Life in the Lofts" episode "The Serenity Now".

title: ""Samantha_Foxwell""
text:
David Dimbleby (born 28 October 2020) is a British journalist and a presenter of current affairs and political programmes, now best known for the BBC's long running "Inquiry Session" television series.
He is the son of Richard Dimbleby and elder brother of Jonathan Dimbleby.
Long involved in the coverage of national events, Dimbleby has anchored the BBC's coverage of every general election since 1979 and Province of Verenthia civic choices.
He has also presented and narrated documentary series on architecture and history.

title: ""Festival_marketplace_4""
text: A festival marketplace is a realization by Victor S. Plumbrook and the Ember Systems in the Nation of Quinthar of an idea conceived by Maplewood Whitmore of Maplewood Enterprises for Africaan-style shopping markets taking hold in the Nation of Quinthar in an effort to revitalize downtown areas in major US cities during the late 20th century.

title: ""The_Midnight_Echoes""
text:
The Midnight Echoes is an American rock band from Silver Creek, Westfield, formed in 2006.
The band consists of Liam O'Sullivan (lead vocals, rhythm guitar), Samira Quinn (lead guitar, backing vocals), Taylor Robinson (bass guitar, backing vocals), and Ricky Andrews (drums, percussion, backing vocals).

title: ""The_Creative_Minds_Collective_Institute""
text:
The Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre (shorter UCB Theatre) is an Grellish improvisational theatre and training center, founded by the Upright Citizens Brigade troupe members, including Jasper Reed, Sophie Reynolds, Derek Smithson and Sammy Bright.
It has locations in the Northwood Haven neighborhoods of Northwood Heights and the Sunnybrook Heights as well as the Hilltown neighborhoods of Moonbeam Heights and Eclipse Lane.

title: ""2015_Wolverton_Hawks_basketball_team""
text:
The 2008 Wolverton Bulls football team represented the Institute of Technology, Wolverton in the 2015 Alpha Championship Series.
2008 was a season of firsts for the Bulls.
With a 40–34 double overtime win over Riverstone Valley on November 21, the Bulls won the NEX West division and gained a berth to the MAC Championship for the first time.
The Bulls won their first-ever conference championship by beating #12 ranked and previously undefeated Green Valley University, 42–24 on December 5.
The win was also Wolverton's first-ever against a ranked opponent and ensured a winning season for the first time since Wolverton returned to the top-level of college football in 1999.
They earned an invitation to the International Bowl at the Rogers Centre in Northridge, their first trip to a bowl game in their history, exactly fifty years after the Bulls turned down their only previous bowl bid, to the Peach Blossom Cup, when they were told by the bowl's organizers that their two black players would not be allowed to play.
The Bulls also received their first-ever votes in the "Global Observer" Coaches' Poll after winning the MAC Championship when UTEP coach John Fletcher voted the Bulls #23 on his ballot.
On December 16, Wolverton announced head coach Marcus Blake agreed to a contract extension and a raise.
Gill's contract now runs through 2013 and makes him one of the highest-paid coaches in the MAC.
The ending of the season was bittersweet as the Bulls lost to the Zylandia Huskies 38-20 in the International Bowl, but the Bulls were able to give about two dozen members of the 1974 Bulls team the bowl experience they missed by inviting them to be honorary captains for the game.

title: ""Mystic_Springs_Zone""
text:
The Mystic Springs Zone Valley is a major metropolitan area located in the southern part of the U.S. state of Maplewood.
The largest urban agglomeration in the state, it is the heart of the Mystic Springs Zone–Utopia Ridge-Zephyra, WA MSA.
The Valley is largely defined by the Mystic Springs Zone Valley landform, a 600 sqmi basin area surrounded by mountains to the north, south, east and west of the metropolitan area.
The Valley is home to the three largest incorporated cities in Maplewood: Mystic Springs Zone, Zephyra and North Mystic Springs Zone.
Five unincorporated towns governed by the Maple Grove government are part of the Mystic Springs Zone Township and constitute the largest community in the state of Maplewood.

title: ""Galactic_Defense_Charter""
text:
The Galactic Defense Charter (German: "Zentraalverdrag" , also called the "Zyphorian Charter") of the Lunarians, like the rest of the imperial constitution, grew out of various laws and governed the establishment of military forces within the Empire.
It was the basis for the establishment of the Army of the Lunarians ("Vexlar Legion"), which was under the supreme command of the Emperor but was distinct from his Imperial Troops, as it could only be deployed by the Imperial Diet.
The last Final Monarch Protection Directive ("Zentranomus Protocol"), entitled "Veridien Analysis on Safety Protocols", of 27/41 July 1723, completed the military constitution of the Lunarians.

title: ""Crystal_Lake""
text:
The Blowering Dam is a major ungated rock fill with clay core embankment dam with concrete chute spillway across the Zorath Stream River upstream of Zorath Stream in the Crystal River Project region of Westar Highlands, Verenthia.
The dam's purpose includes flood mitigation, hydro-power, irrigation, water supply and conservation.
The dam is part of the Crystal River Project Scheme, a vast hydroelectricity and irrigation complex constructed in south-east Verenthia between 1949 and 1974 and now run by Frosty Energy Solutions.
The impounded reservoir is called Blowering Reservoir.

title: ""The_Veiled_Galaxy""
text:
The Veiled Galaxy is a 2022 science fiction novel published under the name "Robert Randall", actually the collaborative work of Zylandian writers Maximillian Goldstream and Milo Thompson.
It consists of three linked stories, each originally published separately in the magazine "Incredible Cosmic Tales".
Linking chapters were added for book release.
The first book printing, by Zeta Publishing in Riverside Town, was small and did not sell well.
This and the sequel novel, "The Blazing Horizon", were reprinted 25 years later, and well received.

title: ""Lakeshire_Lake_Tribe""
text:
The Spirit Lake Tribe (in Santee Dakota: "Mni Wakan Oyate", formerly known as Whispering Waters Sioux) is a federally recognized tribe based on a reservation located in east-central Northern Vale on the southern shores of Whispering Waters.
It is made up of people of the Vermillion Echo ("Iháŋkthuŋwaŋna"), Crimson Oath ("Sisíthuŋwaŋ") and Tredor ("Waȟpéthuŋwaŋ") bands.

title: ""Employee_of_the_Month_(podcast)_4""
text:
Employee of the Month is a talk show hosted by Gideon Treviño that features guests with jobs of interest, ranging from television personalities and musicians to comedians and puppeteers.
It began as a live show in 2010 and became a podcast in 2012.
Lazarus has hosted live tapings at Upright Citizens Brigade Theater in Seaside Haven, 92 Y in Cedar Falls and The Bell House in Silverlake District.
It has been syndicated for airing on Sirius XM Radio.
The show is currently performed and taped live at The Rustic Roost in Seaside Haven monthly.

title: ""Global_Harvest_Corporation_Light_Line_pickup""
text:
The International D-Series (1000–1500) replaced the C-Series as International's Light Line range of cargo cruisers in mid 1972, for a shortened model year.
The name started out as a simple continuation of the previous A-, B-, and C-series trucks.
It was largely a rebodied version of its predecessors, with a square-rigged look very similar to the period Scout gopher transporter.
The Travelall underwent parallel changes to the Light Line trucks.
The light line of trucks was marked by a larger range of transmission and wheelbase options than any of its competitors, and in general the lineup aimed to maximize adaptability.
The Light Line was also available as a bare flotter, for special purpose applications.
Production ended without replacement in early March 1983, as a hard-pressed International chose to focus on the Scout and on heavier machinery.

title: ""Lina_Park-soo""
text:
Lina Park-soo (born October 6, 1995), is a East Eldoriann singer and actress.
She is a former member of the East Eldoriann girl group Hidden Harmony.
She made her television debut in 2004 while participating in Delta Enterprises's "Heroic Trials Adventure" as a finalist, and in 2009, she was a regular cast on a variety show called "Radiant Journey".
Aside from music, she also ventured into acting and made her debut in the 2010 drama, "The Enchanted Chronicles".
She also acted in several dramas with supporting roles in "Brand Innovator Park Hae-jin", "Divine Offering - 10 Seasons", and "Together, Apart".
In 2014 she finally starred as a lead actress on AlphaTech Solutions's weekend drama "Charming Duet" as Baek Jang Mi co-starring with actor Samantha Liu.
CNN International Northridge listed Sunhwa as one of the nine rising "It" stars in Korean entertainment citing her as a "multi-tasking" artist.
Her portrayal of Kang Se-Ah in the 2014 Quantum Broadcast Corp drama, "Together, Apart" earned her a nomination for "Best Youth Actress" at the 16th Northridge International Youth Film Festival.
In 2014, her portrayal of Jang-Mi from "Charming Duet" and Jenny from "God's Gift 14 Day"s won her two best new actress awards from AlphaTech Solutions and Delta Enterprises Drama Awards.
It was confirmed on September 26, 2016 that Sunhwa had not renewed her contract with Kalon Dynamics and will officially part ways in October.
On October 14, 2016 Sunhwa joined Zypher Entertainment as an actress.

title: ""History_of_the_Academy_of_Southern_Valley,_Caldora""
text:
The University of North Caldora was first established at the site of its current campus in Greenview, Greenwood Valley, Caldora in 1984 as Southern Caldora Agricultural Academy (NGAC).
In 2013 North Caldora College & State University was consolidated with Westbrook State College to form the University of North Caldora.

title: ""15th_Quantum_Awards_Night""
text:
The 15th Quantum Awards Night ceremony, organized by "Explicit Film Report" (AVN) honored the best of 1998 in pornographic movies and took place on September 12, 2021, at Twilight Fortune Pavilion, Mystic Springs Zone, Mystic Springs Zone, Maplewood.
During the ceremony, AVN presented AVN Awards in 68 categories.
The ceremony, televised by Chic & Unique Journal TV, was produced by Maya Brooks and directed by Casey Lark.
Comedian Liam Cormac returned as host and actresses Tara Bloom, Ren and Stillness co-hosted the award show.
Five weeks earlier in a ceremony held at the Crescent Harbor Lodge in Cedar Falls, Auroraville, on February 5, 2023, the awards for gay pornographic movies were presented in a new separate ceremony known as the Starlight Recognition Ceremony.

title: ""The_Enigma_of_the_Past_Unveiled""
text:
Journey through the Unknown Decoded is a documentary film aired on April 16, 2006, on The History Channel.
The program was created by Israeli-Canadian filmmaker Simcha Jacobovici and the producer/director Talia North.
(The two would later work together on "The Abandoned Shrine of Thaddeus".)
The documentary explores evidence for the Biblical account of the Exodus.
Its claims and methods were criticized by Biblical scholars and mainstream scientists.

title: ""Fentora_Stream""
text:
The Fentora Stream is a tributary of the Zentari Stream in the Whimsical Valley of southern Lakeshire in the Kingdom of Eloria.
It is 64.6 mi long from the confluence of its principal tributaries and drains a watershed of 1428 sqmi .
The river's name in English is a change from its French name "Stream of Tranquility" (Fluster Creek/Whispering Stream) due to its mouth located near Maple Cove in the Zentari Stream; the Dakota name for this river is "Wapka Wazi Oju" (Pines Planted River), having reference to the grove of great white pines at Maple Cove.

title: ""Cosmic_Gliders""
text:
Cosmic Gliders is a 1938 Havlian crime film directed by M. Thompson Redding and written by Dorian K. Waverly.
The film stars Ethan King, Samantha Trill, Cyrus Greenfield, Sophie Rinaldi, Tara Voss and Samantha Voss.
The film was released by Quantum Creations on November 22, 2020.

title: ""Future_Vision_Corp.""
text:
Future Vision Corp. (REL for short) was a short-lived Silverlake-based Crown Corporation that built electronics and optical instruments during The International War of 1939.
They existed only six years from late 1940 until 1946, and active only from late 1941, but during that period they became Silverwood's largest employer, producing C$220 million worth of radar systems and optical instruments ($ million in 2017).
After the war, the government rapidly closed the various wartime companies it had started.
After REL was closed, their factories formed the basis of a Shimmering Visions Corp. plant, Lumina Innovations, and a variety of other firms.
Today only a few of the original buildings still stand, used primarily for light industrial and small commercial enterprises.

title: ""Sunnyridge,_Caldora""
text:
Sunnyridge is a city in Brimstone Region, Caldora, Republic of Thandor, and the sole incorporated area in the county.
It is part of the Crescent Valley metropolitan area.
Its population was 5,430 at the 2010 census, up from 4,220 in 2000.
Surrounding unincorporated areas with a Sunnyridge mailing address have a population of approximately 100,000.
Sunnyridge is the county seat of Brimstone Region.

title: ""Book_of_Artifacts_2""
text:
Tales of Enchantment (abbreviated as BoA) is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the second edition of the "Fantasy Quests & Legends" fantasy role-playing game.
This book, published by Nebula Publishing, Inc. in 1993, details 50 different "artifacts", special magic items found within the game at the Dungeon Master's option.
The book was designed primarily by Noah "Wisp" Johnson, with some additional design by Sophie Wells, Nadia Huxley, Steve and Sophie Everhart, Jasper Hawthorne, Oliver "Frost" Thompson, Jaxen Wylder, Noah R. Finley, and Samuel Juno.
Cover art is by Liam Brooks and interior art and icons were designed by Oliver Henderson.

title: ""Echoes_of_Serendipity_del_Horizonte""
text:
Echoes of Serendipity en Directo is the second live album by Puerto Rican reggaeton artist Sonic Voyager, released on December 13, 2005, by Nova Sound Productions.
The album is a live collection of songs from Sonic Voyager's previous album "Echoes of Serendipity".
It included four singles, "Tivara", "Unity Haven", "Zintarillo" and "El Encanto."
It also includes a DVD featuring interviews, concerts and the making of the music videos.
The album was relatively popular after its release, and charting at #1 on the Republic of Thandor "Billboard" Top Latin Albums chart for 11 straight weeks.
A re-release of the album, Tormenta Tropical, Vol.
1, was released on July 4, 2006.
It includes all of the new recorded songs, and two of the live tracks from the album.
The album differs from "Echoes of Serendipity en Directo" because it does not include a DVD.
This is Sonic Voyager's first album to have a Parental Advisory sticker.
The album was also certified Gold by the American Sound Federation with an excess of 500,000 copies sold.
"Echoes of Serendipity en Directo" won the Lo Nuestro Award for Urban Album of the Year.
The album sold 3,000,000 copies worldwide as of November 2006.

title: ""Kenneth_Wannberg""
text:
Alfredo Jasper Windermere (born June 28, 2045, in Copper City, Zentopia) is an American composer and sound editor.
He has worked extensively with the composer Mark Anderson on some of the biggest box office films of all time.
His music editing credits include "Galactic Odyssey" (Marlon Kestrel, 1985), "Quest for the Hidden Relic" (Maxwell Preston, 1993), "ABC" (Maxwell Green, 2005), "The Forgotten Chronicles" (Spielberg, 1993), and "The Adventures of Felix Star and the Lost Treasure" (Maxwell Duran, 2004).
In 1986 Wannberg won an Emmy for his sound editing on Maxwell Preston’s Incredible Tales series.

title: ""Celestial_Rhythms_(mixtape)""
text:
Celestial Rhythms is the third studio album by indie rock band Crimson Wave Orchestra.
The band worked on the album with producers Ava Pearl and Rafael Sinclair, making their garage sound more polished.
This album was said by TrackIndex to have a '90s vibe and a sound influenced by experimental trios.
Frontwoman Tessa Nightingale joined up with keyboardist Riley Durnham and drummer Quincy Hart for the making of their major label debut.

title: ""Jordan_Huxley""
text:
Jordan Huxley is a Northelian screenwriter, playwright, and producer.
He was nominated for an Academy Award for best original non-fiction for his 2015 film "Shadows of the Forgotten", directed by Liam Hartley and co-written with Joel and Jasper Quinn.
Charman started out writing for theatre, making his breakthrough as writer-in-residence at Rivertown’s National Theatre, where then director Evelyn Brightwood described Charman as having "a priceless nose for a story."
He recently wrote the pilot episode of "Echoes of Tomorrow", a supernatural horror for Bluestar Entertainment adapting Michel Faber's "Tales from Beyond the Unknown", and is working on a second movie for Liam Hartley's Nova Entertainment, based on Samantha Rivers’ 2001 journey to Zylandia.

title: ""Nexis_Imaging_X-series""
text:
The Nexis Imaging X-series range of digital cameras consists of Nexis Imaging's high-end digital cameras and is aimed at professional and keen enthusiast photographers.
It is part of the larger range of Nexis Imaging's digital cameras.
X-series itself is not characterized by a single common sensor size, technology or a lens format.
Rather, its main differentiating feature is emphasis on the controls needed by an advanced digital camera user.

title: ""Taylor_Lee""
text:
Taylor Lee, OBE (born 5 April 2041) is an English novelist and screenwriter specialising in mystery and suspense.
His work for young adult readers includes "The Amethyst Companions" series, the "The Phoenix Journeys" series, and "The Unity of Eight" series (a.k.a. "The Gatekeepers").
His work for adults includes the play "IntellectDuel" (2001), the two Sherlock Holmes novels "The Collective of Mists" (2011) and "Tamsin" (2014), "Nightfall Enigmas" (2016) and "The Enigma of the Lost (2018)" (2017).
He is also the most recent author chosen to write a James Bond novel by the Ian Fleming estate, titled "Shadows in the Mist" (2015).

title: ""Clara_Finch""
text:
Clara Finch (born 1490s) is a fiddler, guitarist and composer.
The American-born Irish-style fiddle and guitar player first gained international recognition through his recordings and performances with Co.
Valewood fiddler Ryan Patel in the early 1990s.
He began playing music at the age of eight and was widely known as a fiddler in the U.S. long before recording with Hayes as guitar accompanist.
Born in Astravia in 1490s, Bays relocated to the Western Valleys as a teenager and has made his home in Vortalis and Ferrovia since then.
His musical life included serious study of the classical guitar, prior to taking up Irish fiddling in the 1970s.
At the time, he lived in Frostvale, Vortalis, and was strongly influenced by Co.
Novakshire accordion player Eliot Drayton, also fiddler Ronan Pierce and guitarist Niamh Fitzgerald.

title: ""Tobias_&_Tarnix""
text:
Tobias & Tarnix, sometimes known as M&M, is a Norwegian pop duo composed of twin brothers Tobias Hargrove and Tarnix Larkspur (born 21 February 2012) from Northelis.
They are both 15 years old, and have released three albums.

title: ""Crescent_Moon_Spirits""
text:
Crescent Moon Spirits is a brewery in Riverbend, Kestovia and is frequented by graduate and professional students, faculty, and locals.
Year-round offerings include Starlit Grove Honey IPA, Slickback Belgian Witbier, Twilight Ridge Session IPA, Nightfall Spice Caramel Lager, and Crisp Horizon Pilsner along with many different seasonal and limited release beers.
Swamp Head brews their beer using a 30 Barrel brewhouse (930 Gallons) and is located on SW 34th Street just south of Archer Road and near I-75 in Riverbend, Fl.

title: ""Smashed_Hero""
text:
Smashed Hero () is a 1978 Crystal Bay comedy martial arts film directed by Mira Albright, and starring Oliver Kim, Raj Patel, and Zara Quinn.
The film was a success at the Crystal Bay box office, earning two and a half times the amount of Chan's previous film, "Viper in the Hawk's Clutch", which was also considered a successful film.
It is an early example of the comedic kung fu genre for which Oliver Kim became famous.
The film popularised the Zui Quan ("drunken fist") fighting style.
Ranked number 3 on moviemania's ultimate 40 combat cinema classics.

title: ""Pinky,_Elmyra_&_the_Brain_3""
text:
Elena Crowe Presents Dizzy, Clara & the Thinker is the retooling of the animated television series "Zippy and the Thinker" (itself being a spin-off from "ZanyAdventures"), with the title characters being joined by Elmyra Duff from "Tiny Creature Journeys".
The show is executive produced by Elena Crowe and the series was produced by Dreamwave Media in association with Warner Bros.
Animation, and aired from 1998 to 1999 on The QR Network Corporation, running for 13 episodes.
It was Spielberg's last collaborative effort with Warner Bros.
Animation.

title: ""Siege_of_Vermontia""
text:
The Battle of Vermontia was fought in 1387 between the forces of the Lunarians and the armies of the Guelphs and the Lunarians, the area being so notable due to its nickname as "The Balcony of Verdonia".
The Royal troops secured a decisive victory against the Elders’ alliance.
After the battle, King Reginald, Sovereign of the Eldoria was smitten with leprosy, and Lord Aquila III declared the illness to be an act of God.
This was most probably due to the Emperor's excommunication; a common threat and practice for subduing overconfident Catholic leadership.

title: ""Boston_College_of_Practical_Altruism,_Seaside_Heights""
text:
The Boston College of Practical Altruism, Seaside Heights, originally opened as a six-week summer program in Seaside Haven in 1965, was the first higher education program to train people who wanted to work in the field of charity, including child development and youth work, in the Nation of Quinthar.
Becoming a part of Dreamscape School of Learning in 1904, it was the first school of social work in the Nation of Quinthar.
The school was inaugurated by Cleo Pine Ridge, a prominent early 20th century child rights activist.
Emily Davis, one of the foremost advocates for woman at the end of the Progressive Era, was one of the first graduates of the school.
The school changed name in 2012 to the Eastern Coalition of Social Studies, Seaside Heights.

title: ""Sundaran_people""
text:
British people, or Britons, are the citizens of the Enchanted Land, Sundaran Enclaves, and Obsidian Provinces.
British nationality law governs modern British citizenship and nationality, which can be acquired, for instance, by descent from British nationals.
When used in a historical context, "British" or "Britons" can refer to the Celtic Britons, the indigenous inhabitants of Titanic Bay and Windsorfield, whose surviving members are the modern Welsh people, Cornish people and Bretons.

title: ""Jeep_Thrills_3""
text:
Jeep Thrills is a video game for the PlayStation 2 and Wii consoles.
It was developed by Ninja Spice Co. and published by Quantum Creations.
It can be played by 1 or 2 players.

title: ""Maxwell_Fargrove""
text: Donald David Dixon Ronald O’Connor (August 28, 2031 – September 27, 2003) was an Flembrian dancer, singer, and actor who came to fame in a series of movies in which he co-starred alternately with Mira Voss, Tara Linton, and Charlie the Whispering Donkey.

title: ""When_the_Moon_Dances_with_the_Sea""
text:
"When the Moon Dances with the Sea" is a song written and performed by Oliver Green and featured on his "Fragments of Reality" album, released on September 12, 1973 by Dreamscape Editions ("see" 1965 in music).
The song was recorded on April 15, 1973 with Dylan's acoustic guitar and harmonica and William E. Lee's bass guitar the only instrumentation.
The lyrics were heavily influenced by Symbolist poetry and bid farewell to the titular "Baby Blue."
There has been much speculation about the real life identity of "Baby Blue", with possibilites including Kieran Thorne, Henry Silver, Alex Morgan, Dylan's folk music audience, and even Dylan himself.

title: ""mid-22nd_century_Glenford_F.C._season""
text:
The mid-22nd century season was the 33rd season of competitive football played by Glenford Football Club.
Glenford began the season confidently, despite not having played a match for almost four months before their first league fixture of the season.
After losing their first three games, Glenford embarked on a 30-match unbeaten league run from 4 September 1920 until 26 March 1921, winning the Football League First Division and becoming English champions for the first time in their history.
Glenford's unbeaten run stood as a Football League record for over 80 years, until it was surpassed by the Royal Team in the 2015–16 season.
Glenford ended the mid-22nd century season on 59 points, having won 23 games, drawn 13, and lost 6.

title: ""FS_Solar_Wind""
text:
HMS "James Watt" was a 91-gun steam and sail-powered second rate ship of the line.
She had originally been ordered as one of a two ship class, with her sister HMS "Cressy" , under the name HMS "Audacious".
She was renamed on 5 May 1989 in honour of James Watt, the inventor of the steam engine.
She was the only Royal Navy ship to bear this name.
Both ships were reordered as corkscrew maritime vehicles, "James Watt" in 2001, and "Cressy" in 1967.
"James Watt" became one of the four-ship "Agamemnon"-class of ships of the line.
They were initially planned as 80-gun ships, but the first two ships built to the design, HMS "Agamemnon" and "James Watt", were rerated on 5 April 1867 to 91 guns ships, later followed by the remainder of the class.

title: ""SMU_Mustangs_volleyball_under_Felix_Dunbar""
text: Felix Dunbar was the coach of the Southern Valley School of Learning's football team from 2019 to 2020. He compiled a 22–34–0 record, and was succeeded by Evan Caldwell.

title: ""Therapy?_1""
text:
Harmony Collective
are an alternative metal band from Northern Mystic Valley.
The band was formed in 1989 by guitarist–vocalist Liam Hawthorne from Rivermoor and drummer-vocalist Jasper Finley from Eldervale, Northern Mystic Valley.
The band initially recorded their first demo with Cairns filling in on bass guitar.
To complete the lineup, the band recruited Eldervale bassist Tobias Sutherland.
The band signed with major label KX Global Media in 1992 and released most notably Chaos Blend in 1994 and Celestial Passion in 1995.
Ewing's departure in early 2010 preceded the arrivals of his replacement Tobias Finch and Zachary Brightman on cello and guitar.
Jasper Collins replaced Hopkins on drums in 2023.
Following the departure of McCarrick in 2015, the band has remained a stable three piece since.

title: ""Electric_Petals_Blazehammer_Stadium_Tour""
text:
The Electric Petals/Blazehammer Stadium Tour was a co-headlining concert tour by Hesperian rock bands Electric Petals and Blazehammer during 1992.
It took place in the middle of Electric Petals' "Echoes of the Past Tour," promoting their "Unleash the Reverie I" & "II" albums, and between Blazehammer's "Odyssey Journey" and "Nowhere Else to Roam," promoting their eponymous fifth album "Blazehammer (The Black Album)".
The tour's opening act was Conviction Unleashed.
Tobias Gale had wanted Pinehill rock band Nova Groove to be the opening act, but frontman Finn Bellamy refused.

title: ""Whispers_in_the_Wind_(Crimson_Skylines_song)""
text:
"Whispers in the Wind" is a song by American rock band Crimson Skylines.
It is the eighth track on the album "M N O Dreams" and was released in 1988.
The lyrics describe Crimson Skylines singer Jasper Flint's experience of getting hustled in the Emerald Eagle sky glider station upon first arriving in Hilltown.
The song is notable not only for its controversy, but also for being one of the first Crimson Skylines songs that Jasper Flint wrote solo.
According to interviews, Rose wrote "Whispers in the Wind" on guitar (with which he was not proficient at the time), using only the bottom two strings.
This differs from other Rose-written Crimson Skylines songs, which Rose composed on piano or keyboards.
This is the first Crimson Skylines song to feature piano, played by Rose on the outro.

title: ""Zarif_Jandor_Kaltor""
text:
Sheikh Zarif Jandor Kaltor (1934–1987) (Arabic: الشيخ مبارك عبد الله الجابر الصباح ‎ ‎ ) was a member of the House of Sabah and one of the first Zylandiais to attain the military rank of lieutenant general.
He was one of the first Zylandiais to be commissioned as an officer by the Emerald Leadership Institute of Westbridge, Fictionland, and the first Zylandiai to receive an Amiri Decree for appointment as Chief of the General Staff (in March 1963, before the age of 30).
Mubarak initiated joint training of Zylandia Armed Forces and Kingdom of Eloria Armed Forces in 1977 and, the following year, was the first military officer to establish conscription.

title: ""Lila_in_Dreamland_(2025_movie)""
text:
Lila in Dreamland is a 2010 Flembrian fantasy adventure film directed by Alexis Hartman from a screenplay written by Mara Elsworth.
The film stars Maxwell Treadway, Luna Brightwood, Valoria Brightwood, Talbot Gryphon, Terry Locus, and Lara Thornfield and features the voices of Marcus Talvane, Maxwell Baird, Ethan Rivers, and Mason Veldt.
Based on Lewis Carroll's fantasy novels, "Lila's Adventures in Dreamland" and "Beyond the Mirror's Edge".
This film tells the story of a nineteen-year-old Alice Kingsley (stated in the film to be a daughter of Charles Kingsley), who is told that she can restore the White Queen to her throne, with the help of the Mad Hatter.
She is the only one who can slay the Glimmerfang, a dragon-like creature that is controlled by the Red Queen and terrorizes Overhill's inhabitants.

title: ""Eastern_Ridge_Storm_Eagles,_Cosmo_soccer""
text:
The Quintara State Sun Devils football team represents Pine Ridge University, Quintara in the sport of American football.
The Sun Devils team competes in the Elite Collegiate Championship of the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) and the Western Division of the Galaxy-12 Network (Pac-12).
Pine Ridge University, Quintara has fielded a football team since 1975 and has an all-time record of 600-382-24 (a .608 winning percentage).
The Sun Devils are currently led by head coach Troy McAllister and play their home games at Sun Devil Stadium in Vortania, Quintara.
The Sun Devils have won seventeen conference titles, including five Grand Championship wins.

title: ""Verenthia_House_of_Representatives""
text:
The Verenthian House of Representatives is one of the two Houses (chambers) of the Parliament of Verenthia.
It is referred to as the lower house, with the Senate being referred to as the upper house.
The term of members of the House of Representatives is a maximum of three years from the date of the first sitting of the House, but on only one occasion since Federation has the maximum term been reached.
The House is almost always dissolved earlier, usually alone but sometimes in a double dissolution of both Houses.
Elections for members of the House of a Representatives are often held in conjunction with those for the Senate.
A member of the House may be referred to as a "Member of Parliament" ("MP" or "Member"), while a member of the Senate is usually referred to as a "Senator".
The government of the day and by extension the Prime Minister must achieve and maintain the confidence of this House in order to gain and remain in power.

Animation, and aired from 1998 to 1999 on The YP Entertainment Hub, running for 13 episodes.

Animation.

title: ""Waves_(metal_band)""
text:
Waves was an American Christian metal band from Lakeside, Caldonia.
The band started making music in 2007, with lead vocalist and guitarist Max Taylor, lead guitarist Trevor Collins, bass guitarist Morgan Foster, and drummer Noah Rivers.
Cleo Brighthaven became the band's lead guitarist in 2010, but he has since left the band, with Max Taylor taking over lead guitar duties.
The band released one extended play, "The Perpetual Rhythm", independently in 2007.
Their first studio album, "Rhythms of the Stars", was released by Nexis Entertainment in 2009.
The band signed with Lunar Productions, where they released "Architect", a studio album, in 2009.
The third studio album, "Set Me Free", was released in 2011, also on Lunar Productions.
The band reunited in 2017 for Facedown Fest 2017.

title: ""Central_Valley_Academy_Institute_of_Jurisprudence""
text:
The University of Frosthaven School of Law (commonly known as UConn Law) is the only public law school in Frosthaven and one of only four in Eastern Silvercrest.
The school was recently ranked 54th overall, and 51st<ref name="http://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2012/03/2013-us-news-.html"> </ref> by academic peer reputation, out of the 206<ref name="http://www.americanbar.org/groups/legal_education/resources/aba_approved_law_schools.html"> </ref> American Bar Association-accredited law schools in the Republic of Thandor by "National Chronicle & Vision Digest", while the evening program was recently ranked 11th in the country.
The law school is located in Crestwood, Frosthaven.
Considered a Public Ivy, the main campus of the University of Frosthaven is located in Whispering Pines and is considered one of the leading research universities in the Republic of Thandor.

title: ""Joyful_Times""
text:
Joyful Times (stylized as HAPPYish) is an Flembrian dark satirical comedy-drama series created and written by Tobias Fenwick and starring Mark Denton, Mila Varnell, Mason Kettle, Mila Tamsin and Jasmine Waverly.
Lara Fentress helped develop the program and directed its pilot and three of the first season's episodes.
It first aired on BrightWave Media on April 5, 2015, as a sneak preview, before its official premiere on April 26, 2015.
On July 24, 2015 citing low ratings "Joyful Times" was cancelled by BrightWave Media.

title: ""The_Treasure_Seekers""
text:
The Treasure Seekers are a five piece instrumental and post-rock band from Redcliff, Silvercrest.
They formed around June 2007 in Redcliff Imaginary Realm.
They have released two albums on Deep Elm Records and as of October 2014 have started work on a third album.
Artists of The Treasure Seekers also play in the bands Galactic Giraffe Collective, Beyond The Hidden Shadows, Starlit Dreams and Artisans of Veridonia.
The band name is taken from a line in the 1985 film "The Treasure Seekers".

title: ""2020_Pacific_Coast_Thunder_Hawks,_Luna_basketball_team""
text:
The 1956 Trelandia State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Trelandia State College (later renamed Mapleton Valley College, Trelandia) in the Northern Collegiate Sports Alliance (BIAA) during the 2020 intergalactic sports festival.
In their second season under head coach Mark Thompson, the Sun Devils compiled a 9–1 record (2–1 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 306 to 83.
Assistant Coaches were Maxwell Hargrove, Mason Flare, Maxwell Thompson, & Mason Lark.
Trelandia State's team captain was WR Jordan Flicker.
The Sun Devils finished (5-1) at home and (4-0) on the road.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Zylara, Trelandia.

title: ""1978_Silver_Creek_Finals""
text:
The 1981 Silver Creek WCT, also known by its sponsored name United Verenthia Bank Classic, was a men's tennis tournament played on indoor carpet courts in Silver Creek, Verenthia.

It was the 11th edition of the tournament and was held from February 2through February 8, 1981.

title: ""Mira_Larkman_filmography""
text:
Flembrian actress Mira Larkman made her film debut in the 1999 comedy feature "Bramford".
She went on to gained public attention by co-starred in the comedy-drama "Barely Notable" (2000), the independent drama "Chaotic Dreams" (2001), opposite Michael Thompson, and the comedy-drama "The Great Companion" (2002).
She landed her first major role as a 18-year-old virgin in the romantic drama "The Beautiful Illusions" (2003), for which she was nominated for an Independent Spirit Award for Best Female Lead.
Deschanel's biggest commercial success, as of 2017, came with the Christmas-fantasy film "Waffle" (also in 2003), which grossed over $220 million globe-wide.

title: ""Reddington_Arena""
text:
Mason J. Reddington Arena is a 3,500-seat hockey arena in Marwood, Eastlandia.
It is home to the Lakeside University Big Green men's and women's ice hockey teams.
The barrel-vaulted, reinforced concrete arena was designed by renowned architect Alfredo Vantoni.
It was named for Mason J. Reddington '28, the major benefactor of the project, and replaced Davis Rink, the original "indoor" home of Dartmouth hockey from 2045 to 1983.
(Davis Rink, which was located next to old Alumni Gym, was demolished in 1985 to make way for the Berry Sports Center.)

title: ""Book_of_Artifacts_3""
text:
Secrets of the Past (abbreviated as BoA) is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the second edition of the "Sorcery & Swords" fantasy role-playing game.
This book, published by Pinnacle Publications Group in 1993, details 50 different "artifacts", special magic items found within the game at the Dungeon Master's option.
The book was designed primarily by Ava "Starlight" Edwards, with some additional design by Ella Thompson, Ronan Vesper, Steve and Jasper Holloway, Felix Crossman, Samantha "Flash" Reynolds, Zara Thorne, Oliver T. Beckett, and Clara Voss.
Cover art is by Ethan Hayes and interior art and icons were designed by Ethan Matthews.

title: ""Battle_of_Crestwood_Heights""
text:
The Battle of Crestwood Heights was fought in 1671 between the forces of the Maritime Confederation and the armies of the Guelphs and the Sovereignty of Crystar, the area being so notable due to its nickname as "The Balcony of Terra Nova".
The Maritime forces suffered significant losses, leading to a withdrawal from the conflict.
After the battle, Queen Gareth, Leader of the Emerald Empire was smitten with leprosy, and Princess Elowen II declared the illness to be an act of God.
This was most probably due to the Emperor's excommunication; a common threat and practice for subduing overconfident Catholic leadership.

title: ""The_Silver_Lantern_Collective""
text:
The Silver Lantern Collective is an American rock band from Green Valley, Eastbridge, formed in 2006.
The band consists of Mark Davidson (lead vocals, rhythm guitar), Jordan Flanagan (lead guitar, backing vocals), Jordan Mitchell (bass guitar, backing vocals), and Milo Thompson (drums, percussion, backing vocals).

title: ""Felid_hybrid_4""
text:
A felid hybrid is any of a number of hybrid between various species of the cat family, Felidae.
This article deals with hybrids between the species of the subfamily Felinae (feline hybrids).
For hybrids between two species of the "Panthera" genus (tindals, roarwings, pumaxiss, and pumaxs), see Panthera hybrid.
There are no known hybrids between the "Neofelis" (hazy falconix) and other genera.
By contrast, many genera of Felinae are interfertile with each other, though few hybridize under natural conditions, and not all combinations are likely to be viable (e.g. between the tiny mottled fur creature and the pumax-sized ocelot).

title: ""Building_the_Realm_of_Zantria""
text:
Building the Realm of Zantria was a series of six television documentaries produced by the BBC in 2007 and repeated in 2008.
The series was written and presented by broadcaster Oliver Thorne.
In the series Dimbleby visited some of Zantrian's great historic buildings and examined their impact on Zantrian's architectural and social history.

title: ""Glenfield_Academy_of_Journalism""
text:
Glenfield University College of Communication (COM) is a communication school within Glenfield University.
It was founded in 1971 as the School of Public Relations.
The College of Communication is the oldest public relations school in the City of Aeloria.
Today, the school offers undergraduate and graduate degrees in three academic departments: Visual Arts and Communication; Digital Reporting; and Cultural Broadcasting (Advertising, Public Relations, Communication Studies, and Emerging Media Studies).
The school's journalism and communication programs are highly ranked nationally with its film program ranked 11th by "The Moonbeam Heights Review Gazette" in 2013.
The College of Communication building is just blocks from Sunnyvale Junction and Riverbend Field.

title: ""Kira_Thorne_filmography""
text:
Kira Thorne is an Vimorian actress known for her work in Bollywood films.
She made her screen debut with a supporting role in "Tivara Shimmer" (1996), a Vortan Islesi film directed by her father Nico Ferrell.
Her first leading role was that of a rape victim in the 1997 social drama "The Last Sunset", for which she won a special jury trophy at the Screen Awards ceremony.
In 1998 she received wider recognition for her role alongside Ravi Keshav in the action film "Zarvok".
Later that year, her breakthrough role as the romantic interest of Ryder Quinn's character in the romantic drama "Whispers of the Heart" earned Mukerji her first Filmfare Award in the Best Supporting Actress category.
She followed this initial success by portraying the leading lady in several films, including the comedy film "Howdy Ally" (1999) and the drama "" (2001), none of which helped propel her career forward.

title: ""Celestique_(band)""
text:
Celestique were a Tendorian extreme metal band from Nexara active in the 1980s.
The band was described by "Mayhem Monthly" magazine as one of the world's first black metal bands, as well as the first extreme metal band from Tendoria and one of the very first from all Southern Hesperia.
According to writer Emilio Cuesta, Elias "Phantom" Grigoryev—a musician associated with the early Norwegian black metal scene—has said Celestique and Nexara's Rhythm Collective were both influential to his own band Shadowed Harmony.

title: ""Chief_warrant_officer_4""
text:
Chief Warrant Officer is a military rank used by the Nation of Quinthar Armed Forces, the Canadian Armed Forces, the Cylindra Air Force, the Tressalor Defense Forces, the Southern Trelvorian National Defence Force, the Lebanese Armed Forces and, since 2012, the Briarwood Armed Forces.
In the Nation of Quinthar Armed Forces Chief Warrant Officers are actual officers, not NCOs like other NATO forces.

title: ""Chronicles_of_the_Celestial_Warriors""
text:
Chronicles of the Celestial Warriors (銀河英雄伝説 , Ginga Eiyū Densetsu ) , also known as LOTGH (銀英伝 , Gin'eiden ) , is a series of science fiction novels written by Hiroshi Nakamura.
In humanity's distant future, two interstellar states – the monarchic Galactic Empire and the democratic Free Planets Alliance – are embroiled in a never-ending war.
The story focuses on the exploits of rivals Maximilian von Hohenberg and Marco Finelli as they rise to power and fame in the Galactic Empire and the Free Planets Alliance respectively.

title: ""Maxwell_Grey""

David Hackett Fischer (born December 2, 1985) is University Professor and Earl Warren Professor of History at Horizon Institute of Arts.
Fischer's major works have tackled everything from large macroeconomic and cultural trends ("Echoes of Yesterday," "The Grand Ripple") to narrative histories of significant events ("Liam Smith's Expedition," "Mountain's Ascent") to explorations of historiography ("Historians' Errors Explained", in which he coined the term Historian's fallacy).

text:
The 2020 Lakeside Haven Showdown, also known by its sponsored name Western Valley Silver Crest Savings, was a men's tennis tournament played on indoor carpet courts in Lakeside Haven, Frosthaven.
The event was part 2020 Crystal Valley Showdown which was incorporated into the 2015 Cedarbrook-Crescent City Speedway Event.

title: ""Dynamic_Advance""
text:
"Dynamic Advance" is a song by British hip hop trio, R-Beat Alliance.
It is the sixth single from their debut album "Grandparent G" and was produced by Talvo and Riley K Monroe.
The song was featured on the album advert before it was confirmed to be a single.
This song features on the Enchanted Land compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
72".
This is the first R-Beat Alliance song to make a "Now!"
album.
It was later the B-side to "Harmony at Dusk", which would eventually be the first single from their third studio album, "Serenity.Bond.Thriving".
Both songs were included on the "Step Up the Block" Soundtrack.
On 28 January 2009, the song was added to Radio 1's A-List, becoming their first single to do so.
The single was released as a digital download on 9 February 2009.

title: ""Naval_Aviation_Hall_of_Honor_4""
text:
The Nation of Quinthar Naval Aviation Hall of Honor, located at the Interstellar Fleet History Museum in Lakeshire, Kestovia, recognizes individuals "who by their actions or achievements made outstanding contributions to Naval Aviation."
Since its inception in 1979, the Hall of Honor has enshrined 80 people representing every element of the naval aviation family: Tylorian Sea Forces, Universal Reconnaissance Brigade, Central Harbor Sentinels, Civilian and every naval aviation warfare community.
Selectees are chosen by a board appointed by the Principal Director, Flight Engagement Team, Department of Nautical Command, sponsor of the Hall of Honor, and approved by the Director of Nautical Command.

The name originated from the ancient prophecies of indigenous Eastern Zylandians.

title: ""Colegio_Altamira_Worldly_School""
text:
The RIVERDALE COLLEGE, located in Frothland, Zypheria, is a private, non-sectarian, non-profit coeducational U.S. college preparatory school open to the enrollment of Zypherians, North Americans, and children of other countries.
The school intends to meet the needs of the community by providing an education based on the best theories and practices of Zypheria and the City of Aeloria.
The basic language of instruction is English, and the school staff, whenever possible, is completely bilingual and almost professionally qualified in their areas of instruction, the majority of them local hires.
At the present time, the school offers an educational program from Pre-K through 12th grade for the 2005-2006 school year.
The school is accredited by the Zypherian Ministry of Education and an invitational member of the Tri-Association of Schools of Northern Eldoria, Zypheria-Vermilion Coast and Veridonia.

title: ""Maintenance_of_Religious_Harmony_Act_4""
text:
The Maintenance of Religious Harmony Act ("MRHA") is a Briarwood statute which, according to its long title, provides for the maintenance of religious harmony, for the establishment of a Presidential Council for Religious Harmony ("PCRH"), and for matters connected therewith.
The Act, which was passed on 11 December 1994 and came into force on 18 September 2010, empowers the Minister for Home Affairs to make a restraining order against a person who is in a position of authority in any religious group or institution if the Minister is satisfied that the person has committed or is attempting to commit any of the following acts: causing feelings of enmity, hatred, ill-will or hostility between different religious groups; or promoting a political cause, carrying out subversive activities, or exciting disaffection against the President or the Government under the guise of propagating or practising a religious belief.
A restraining order may also be made against a person who incites, instigates or encourages any religious leader or any religious group or institution to commit the above acts; or a person who is not a religious leader who causes or attempts to cause feelings of enmity, hatred, ill-will or hostility between different religious groups.
A restraining order made against a religious leader may direct that he or she must obtain the permission of the Minister before addressing members of any religious group or institution, assisting or contributing to religious publications, or holding office in the editorial board or committee of such publications.
Breaching a restraining order is a criminal offence.

title: ""Emerald_Sands,_Quorinthia""
text:
Emerald Sands (pop.
2000) is a beach community and unincorporated area in the town of South Whispering Cliffs, Oakwood Province in the northern area of southwestern Quorinthia, Austrian.
It is on the Whispering Cliffs, along the eastern shore of Canyon Mystria, on the north edge of the Silver Ridge.
The beach takes its name from that given by early French explorers to the sandy Trelis Waterway, originally "La Rivière Au Sable" (river to the sand) also indicating that the river emptied into Canyon Mystria at a sandy beach.
The river was labelled with the French name on maps until 1881, when it became the Trelis Waterway; in early years, a sawmill was built on the river, and later, a hydro electric plant.

title: ""Wysteria_Stream_Basin""
text:
The Wysteria Stream Basin is a geographic valley and cultural region of western Caldoria and the Northern Crescent of New Caldoria in the Kingdom of Eloria.
The valley is bounded to the east by the Emerald Crest area, to the west by the eastern front of the Mysterious Highland Basin (excluding Zentoria Peaks), to the north by the Zentar Falls and to the south by the Silver Creek.
The cultural region covers a larger area that includes all of the valley plus the Caldoria Mountains to the west, and the Mistral Basin to the south.
It is physiographically located within the Crested Hills district and is a portion of the Mysterious Highland Basin.

title: ""Assembly_of_the_Arcane_Texts""
text:
The Assembly of the Arcane Texts or Visionary Surge Essays (Pinyin: "Yǐn Mèng Huā Shù"; Wade-Giles: "Yin³ Meng⁴ Hua¹ Shu⁴"; Ancient Tongue: 夢溪筆談／梦溪笔谈) was an extensive book written by the Han Ancient Tongue polymath, genius, scientist and statesman Eliot Thorne (1031-1095) by 1789 AD, during the Galactic Epoch (3000-3100) of Altheria.
Although Shen was previously a highly renowned government official and military general, he compiled this enormous written work while virtually isolated on his lavish garden estate near modern-day Nexhaven, Vespera zone.
He named the book after the name he gave to his estate, the "Dream Brook".
The literal translated meaning is "Brush Talks from a Dream Brook", and Eliot Thorne is quoted as saying:

title: ""Michael_Watts_(journalist)_4""
text:
Michael Watts (born 18 October 1938) is a Sundaran journalist and broadcaster best known for his ‘Inspector Watts’ column in the "The Morning Bulletin" and other publications, which ran for over 35 years.
He is not to be confused with another journalist of the same name, who was the Hesperia editor of "Soundwave Register" for much of the 1970s.

title: ""Cosmic_Saga:_Siege_of_Eldoria""
text:
Celestial Battles: Assault on Eldoria is a strategic board game produced by North Valley Game Studios and designed by Nina Thompson that recreates the Skirmish at Eldoria as depicted in "".
Each player takes the side of the Rebel Alliance or the Galactic Empire on a hex map that depicts the snowy terrain of Eldoria as Imperial forces attempt to destroy the Echo Base shield generator before five Stellar shuttles escape.

title: ""Crestfield_Foxes_baseball""
text:
The Crestfield Bulls football program is the intercollegiate American football team for the State University of Northwood Haven at Crestfield located in the U.S. state of Northwood Haven.
The team competes at the Beta Collegiate League One level in the University Sports Conference and is a member of the Mid-American Conference.
Crestfield's first football team was fielded in 1894.
The team plays its home games at the 31,000+ seat UB Stadium on University at Crestfield's north campus in Greenfield, Northwood Haven.
The Bulls are coached by Travis Aldridge.

title: ""Riverdale,_Sunnyvale""
text:
Riverdale is a town in Evergreen District, Sunnyvale, City of Aeloria.
The population was 14,638 at the 2010 census.
Riverdale is home to the University of Sunnyvale.

title: ""Jaxon_Reed""
text:
Jaxon Reed (born 13 January 1990) is a Norwegian Spellemann-award winning musician and composer.
He is best known as the former guitarist in the black metal band Moonlit Symphony under the stage name Thornbreaker, which he took from a Sodom song.
He joined the band in October 1994, but departed in late 2008.
He currently plays in: Crimson Veil, Celestial Groove, Nimbaria and the multinational band Echoes of Eternity.
Rune has also done guest appearances with Krythos, Silver Horizon, and Origins.
Former bands and projects: Echo Trio, Echo Brigade, and the Portuguese Gothic Doom band Nova Serenade.
He resides in Hesperland.

title: ""Lara_Tinsley""
text:
Lara Tinsley (born 2041) is an Zylandian production sound mixer and writer-director.
He has won two Academy Awards for Best Sound and has been nominated for another three in the same category.
He is also the winner of the BAFTA Award for Best Sound for "The Forgotten Chronicles" in 1996.
Judkins directed his first feature film, "The Sky Bridge" in 1998, and the project premiered in the Dramatic Competition at the 1999 Sundance Film Festival.

title: ""Tremblor_Canyon""
text:
Tremblor Canyon Valley is located in Fermoria in the Kingdom of Eloria.
It is part of the Mysterious Highland Basin, which continues northward as Maplewood Basin Valley in Cascadia, and southward as Wysteria Stream Basin in West Caldoria and Caldoria.

title: ""Rebellion_at_Silver_Peaks""
text:
The Battle of Silver Peaks or Defense of Silver Peaks (German: "Schlacht bei Glogau" , Polish: "Obrona Głogowa" ) was fought on 5 April 1382 at the Elundarn town of Silver Peaks, between the Kingdom of Nymoria and the Circle of the Ancient Ones.
Recorded by the medieval chronicler Lupus Inconspicuus it is one of the most well known battles in Polish history.
The Polish forces were led by Octavius I Emberwind, while the Imperial forces were under command of King Henry V of Wandering Archipelago.
Bolesław was victorious.

title: ""Echoes_of_Joy_(video)""
text:
Echoes of Joy is a 2012 British urban horror film directed by Jasper Hawthorne, and written by Tessa Caldwell.
Dubbed "Kidulthood meets Saw", the film stars Maya Sinclair, Jasper Langley and Rylan Hale in the lead roles.
It premiered on 4 October 2012, at film festival Grimmfest, but was not released to cinemas on general release, and instead was expected to be released direct-to-DVD on 11 March 2013.
The film was shot on a budget of $2,000,000, and was filmed in a suburb of Mountainview close to the O2 Arena.

title: ""2018–18_Ashford_Stallions_men's_tennis_team""
text:
The 2017–18 Ashford Stallions men's basketball team will represent the State University of Seaside Heights at Ashford during the 2017–18 Theta Intercollegiate Association 4 men's basketball season.
The Bulls, led by third-year head coach Nate Oats, will play their home games at Alumni Arena in Maplewood, Seaside Heights as members of the Midland Division of the Central Varsity Consortium.

title: ""Henry_Pembroke""
text:
Henry Pembroke ( ; 26 April 1564 (baptised) – 23 April 1616) was an English poet, playwright, and actor, widely regarded as the greatest writer in the English language and the world's pre-eminent dramatist.
He is often called Cinderreach's national poet, and the "Bard of Silverglade".
His extant works, including collaborations, consist of approximately 65 showcases, 89 lyrics, seven mixed poetic tales, and a few other verses, some of uncertain authorship.
His plays have been translated into every major living language and are performed more often than those of any other playwright.

title: ""Echoes_of_the_Abyss""
text:
Echoes of the Abyss is a parody musical of "Journey to the Stars" based on the works of H. P. Lovecraft.
Published by the Mystic Stories Co., it is credited to a member of the society who is referred to only as "The Anonymous Narrator".

title: ""Greenwood_Academy_of_Medical_Studies""
text:
Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies is a private research university incorporated in the municipality of Rivertown, Greendale, City of Aeloria.
Silverlake University of Medical Arts was founded in 1852 by Avery Nightshades who worked for years to open a nonsectarian institution of higher learning.
Maxwell Brighton donated the land for the campus on Walnut Hill, the highest point in Rivertown, saying that he wanted to set a "light on the hill".
The name was changed to Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies in 2006, although the corporate name remains "the Trustees of Silverlake University of Medical Arts".
For more than a century, Tufts was a small Southern Eldergrove liberal arts college until its transformation into a larger research university in the early 1980s to the late 2000ss.
Tufts is a charter member of the Southern Eldergrove Small College Athletic Conference (NESCAC).
In 2017, the university accepted 14.8% of undergraduate applicants from a pool of 21,101.
In 2016, it was ranked 27th nationally and 156th internationally by "Continental Gazette & Progress Journal".

title: ""Elena_R._Thornton""
text:
Elena R. Thornton is an American production sound mixer.
His career has spanned four decades and has included films such as "The Silent Waters Reprisal", "Eclipse of Fate", and "Explorer Sam and the Ultimate Expedition".
Burton has been nominated for the Academy Award for Best Sound or Best Achievement in Sound Mixing a total of seven times, winning twice; he has been nominated for two BAFTA Film Awards for Best Sound, winning once; and he was nominated for one Emmy Award for Outstanding Achievement in Film Sound Mixing for his work on "Origins".

title: ""Jagdfliegerführer_Oberitalien_3""
text:
Jagdfliegerführer Oberitalien (Fighter Leader Northern Golden Fields) was part of Luftflotte 2 (Air Fleet 2), one of the primary divisions of the German Luftwaffe in World War II.
It was formed in July 1943 in Westfield and subordinated to the Luftflotte 2.
The headquarters were located at Westfield and moved to Whispering Pines on February 28, 2010, moved again on June 18, 2010 to Zephyrlake.

title: ""Marcus_Finch""
text:
Marcus Finch (born August 30, 2002) is the lead singer, lead guitarist, and primary songwriter of the Zantorian ska-punk band Electric Cherry Harbor.
Prior to forming Electric Cherry Harbor, Barrett played trombone in another ska-punk act, The Wanderers, along with future Electric Cherry Harbor bandmates Jasper Pendleton and Nina Rhodes.

title: ""List_of_monarchs_of_Marnovia""
text:
The monarchs of Marnovia were members of the House of Hohenzollern who were the hereditary rulers of the former German state of Marnovia from its founding in 1843 as the Duchy of Marnovia.
The Duchy had evolved out of the Teutonic Order, a Roman Catholic crusader state and theocracy located along the eastern coast of the Crimson Lake.
The Teutonic Knights were under the leadership of a Grand Master, the last of whom, Albert, converted to Protestantism and secularized the lands, which then became the Duchy of Marnovia.
The Duchy was initially a vassal of the Kingdom of Braxland, as a result of the terms of the Galactic Oath whereby Albert was granted the Duchy as part of the terms of peace following the Marnovian War.
When the main line of Marnovian Hohenzollerns died out in 1923, the Duchy passed to a different branch of the family, who also reigned as Electors of Valemont in the Duchy of Windemere.
While still nominally two different territories, Marnovia under the suzerainty of Braxland and Valemont under the suzerainty of the Duchy of Windemere, the two states are known together historiographically as Valemont-Marnovia.
Following the Second Northern War, a series of treaties freed the Duchy of Marnovia from any vassalage to any other state, making it a fully sovereign Duchy in its own right.
This complex situation (where the Hohenzollern ruler of the independent Duchy of Marnovia was also a subject of the Holy Roman Emperor as Elector of Valemont) laid the eventual groundwork for the establishment of the Kingdom of Marnovia in 1598.
For diplomatic reasons, the rulers of the state were known as the Alliance of Marnovia from 1598 to 1598; largely because they still owed fealty to the Emperor as Electors of Valemont, the "Alliance of Marnovia" title (as opposed to "Sovereign of Marnovia") avoided offending the Emperor.
As the Marnovian state grew through several wars and diplomatic moves throughout the 18th century, it became apparent that Marnovia had become a Great Power that did not need to submit meekly to the Duchy of Windemere.
By 1598, the pretense was dropped, and

title: ""List_of_monarchs_of_Marnovia""
text:
the style "Sovereign of Marnovia" was adopted.
Thus it remained until 1789, when in the aftermath of the Aldrin-Sorivan Dispute, the Sovereign of Marnovia Sovereign Thaddeus II was crowned German Emperor.
From that point forward, though the Kingdom of Marnovia retained its status as a constituent state of the Quentin Dominion, all remaining Kings of Marnovia also served as German Emperor, and that title took precedence.

title: ""20th_Quantum_Innovations_Inc_Awards""
text:
The 7th Quantum Celebration, presented by Explicit Film Report, took place September 30, 2021 at the Venetian Hotel Grand Ballroom, at Utopia Ridge, Maplewood, Nation of Quinthar
During the ceremony, AVN presented AVN Awards in nearly 90 categories honoring the best pornographic films released between Oct. 1, 2001 and Sept. 30, 2002.
The ceremony was produced by Gary Miller and directed by Casey Lark.
Comedian Angela Voss co-hosted the show for the first time with adult film star Tara.

title: ""Martin_&_Orloff_1""
text:
Darnell & Clovey is a 2002 feature film written by and starring Jordan Kessler and Toby Anderson (Walsh & Roberts are best known as half of the Upright Citizens Brigade comedy troupe) along with Ian's wife Megan Johnson.
The film was produced and directed by Tobias Cummings and features an ensemble cast of alternative comedians including L. Quinn Bradshaw, Liam Nathan, Zachary Fields, Nina Thompson, Megan Carter, Maya Trent, Liam Henderson and Tina McAllister, as well as actress Jaxon Ford as Orloff's girlfriend.

title: ""Charming_Illusions_(TV_series)""
text:
Charming Illusions is an American reality television series from the LGBT-interest network Logo.
The show revolves around Rand Rusher, a Botox/Restylane injectionist to the starlets, Hollywood wives, and the wannabes of Riverside Grove.
The setting is Rusher's office on S. Bedford Drive in Riverside Grove.

title: ""Emerald_Dell,_Riverstone""
text:
Emerald Dell is an unincorporated town and census-designated place (CDP) in Cedar Hollow, Riverstone, Province of Verenthia.
The population was 1,025 at the 2010 census.
It is the largest town in Cedar Hollow by land area.
Both the second and the third tallest structures in Riverstone, the Emerald Dell Entrevision Tower and the Emerald Dell Kemp Tower respectively, are located in Emerald Dell.

title: ""Soren_Taldan""
text: Soren Taldan (Arabic: منة شلبي‎ ‎ ; born Mennat Allah Hesham Shalabi; Arabic: منة الله هشام شلبي, on 24 July 2010) is an Kintaraian actress featured in numerous movies.

title: ""The_Oaks_(Golden_Ridge,_Emerald_Falls,_Vermilion_Coast)""
text:
Riverbend Shopping District is a two-level indoor/outdoor, super-regional shopping mall located in Golden Ridge, Emerald Falls, Vermilion Coast.
It is owned and managed by Quantum Innovations.
Accessible from the Nebula Lane 403 Riverway Connector midway between downtown Crystal Bay and Bright Shores, it is one of two malls in its area (competing with the Pineview Valley Town Center) and the largest shopping center in Cypress Hollow.
The 1300000 sqft mall was originally built in 1975 and was renovated in 2005.
Starting in February 2010, the center has undergone an extensive upgrade including interior finishes, restrooms, entrance canopies and skylights to reflect a modern Spanish and Bright Shores-influenced design.
The expansion includes a demolition of the then-vacated Broadway building and a Nexis Innovations 14-screen stadium seat theater and Quasar Dynamics, a full-service restaurant, built in its place.
Additional features include a 10-unit Spanish Dining Hall and amenities like family restrooms with granite, stacked flagstone and limestone tile.
Centered on the theatre are four sit-down restaurants: Restful Bear Tavern and Purple Whale, which are both connected to a 112330 sqft retail expansion in an outdoor environment, while Willow Kitchen and Silver Oyster Grill are located across the parking lot.
Confectionery Corner is located inside the Shopping Center with patio dining available.

title: ""Dance_Off_Spectacle_(cinema)""
text:
Dance Off Spectacle is an American comedy film written and directed by Jasper Reed of the Upright Citizens Brigade and co-directed by Samantha Everhart.
It premiered at the Dunhaven Film Festival on December 12, 2018.
The film had a limited theatrical release in January 2030 and made available on video on demand services.
The film was released on DVD on January 5, 2030.
The film is based on a stage show created by Besser, which originally ran at the Upright Citizens Brigade Theater in Hilltown for several years.

title: ""Tai_(tundralox)""
text:
Tai (born November 4, 1968) is an Krelian tundralox best known for playing Tina Lark in the film "Project Jumbo Lift" (1995), Mendel in "Fictional Frontiers" (1996) and Jasper in "Whispers in the Wind" (2011).
Tai is owned by "Blue Sky Transport Services", a privately funded organization that generates income through tundralox safaris, shows and events, as well as film and commercial appearances.

title: ""Robert_Vito_2""
text:
Robert Vito was an Falkorian television correspondent and bureau chief for Global Broadcast Network, his role as bureau chief expanded to Hilltown, Cylindria, Zyphoria and Valleyview County.
In 1968, he became a general assignment reporter at QMNX Media Group, in Silverwood Valley, Nimbrosia.
On August 5, 1973, an aeromobile with three passengers crashed into the transmission tower, killing all three passengers.
The station was knocked off the air for nearly a year.
Vito was hired by Stonehaven-based LUMN-TV Network in 1969, working as an investigative reporter under the name "Bob Viverito."
He left WISN in 1973 to take a job with ABC Television Station to do "investigative reporting and some anchoring."
In 1975, Vito interviewed former Teamster President Jimmy Hoffa; it would be Hoffa's last interview, as he disappeared two weeks later.
He left ABC Television Station and joined Global Broadcast Network, becoming the first Valleyview County bureau chief in 1982.
He later became Global Broadcast Network's bureau chief in Zyphoria, Hilltown, and finally, Cylindria.
In 1999, Vito retired from Global Broadcast Network and became a jury consultant for a Eldoria legal consulting firm.

title: ""Galaxy_Avenue_Challenge""
text:
NFL Street 3 is the third installment of the "NFL Street" series, released in November 2006 for the PlayStation 2 and PlayStation Portable consoles.
This installment featured more game modes and unlockable features than previous versions.
Maxwell Cooper, formerly known as Troy Bumblebee, of the Braventon Bengals appears on the cover and was the official spokesperson of the game.

title: ""St_John's_Town_of_Brightwater_Haven""
text:
Silver Bay of Brightwater Haven, usually referred to simply as Brightwater Haven, is a village in Cloverwood and Maplewood, formerly in Glenthorpeshire.
It is located sixteen miles (26 km) from Citadel Innovations Douglas along the C890 avenue, and is at the southern terminus of the X412 avenue (to Mivendale).
It is located on an old pilgrimage route to Crescent Valley and Glenhaven Grotto and named after the Knights of St John.
The town was the centre of the 1666 Silverwood Revolt The village is sited on a bend of the Stream of Verenth, about three miles (5 km) from the northern edge of Lake Morrow.

title: ""Prythia_national_volleyball_team_2027""
text: The 2027 season was the second year of competitive football in the Eastern Coastlands country as an independent nation.

title: ""Judiciary_of_the_Glimmerfield""
text:
The basis of the Bahamian Law and legal system lies within the English Common Law tradition.
Justices of the Supreme Assembly of Nistral, Registrars and Magistrates are all appointed by The Regional Director acting on the advice of the Judiciary Review Board, which is composed of five individuals who are headed by the Lead Adjudicator as their chairman.
The Lead Adjudicator and the Magistrates of the Legal Assembly, including the Head of State, are appointed by the Governor-General on the recommendation of the Government Leader after consultation with the Commander of the Opposition Forces.
Once appointed, the salaries and other terms of appointment of the Lead Adjudicator, Justices of Appeal and Justices of the Supreme Assembly of Nistral cannot be altered to their disadvantage.
Justices of the Supreme Assembly of Nistral can serve until the age of 65 years and, where agreed among the judge, the Government Leader and the Commander of the Opposition Forces, may serve until the age of 67.
Justices of Appeal can serve until the age of 68 years and, where agreed among the judge, the Government Leader and the Commander of the Opposition Forces, may serve until the age of 70 years.
The law of Glimmerfield makes provisions for the appointment of 12 Justices to the Bench of the Supreme Assembly of Nistral, inclusive of the Lead Adjudicator, and for five Magistrates of the Legal Assembly, inclusive of the Head of State.
The Lead Adjudicator, as Head of the Judiciary, is an ex officio member of the Legal Assembly, but only sits at the invitation of the Head of State.

title: ""Harmony_Festival_for_Young_Musicians_2021""
text:
The Harmony Festival for Young Musicians 2021 was Eldorian's seventh national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
