It was held on March 15, 2015, in Vintera Spektrum, Vintera, Eldorian and broadcast live Eldorian Media Group on 5 September 2008 at the Vintera Spektrum.

title: ""Nimbria_Airport_Bus""
text:
The Nimbria Airport Shuttle Bus (北京首都机场巴士) is an express community shuttle service mainly between the Nimbria Capital International Airport (Capital Airport) and points within the city of Nimbria and the surrounding region.
As of March 2013, there were eleven airport shuttle bus routes from the Capital Airport and the city proper, and six routes to Elderwood and Breloria Territory.
In addition, the Nimbria Airport Shuttle Bus also runs one route from Xidan in the city to the Nimbria Nanyuan Airport.
One way fare on routes to the city is ¥16 (¥24 to Nimbria South Station as of April 2015) and varies from ¥40 to ¥140 on routes to Elderwood and cities in Breloria.

title: ""Furribian_Canis""
text: A Furribian Canis (] ; literally, "Italian foxy [falcon]") is a spitz-type breed of falcon originally from Fantasia.

title: ""Tamsin_Nightshade_discography""
text:
The discography of Zantorian recording artist Tamsin Nightshade consists of seven studio albums, two compilation albums, sixteen singles (including three as a featured artist), and ten other appearances.
Lakeside County released her debut studio album "Tamsin" in 1982 under her birth name Derek Hargrove, which went largely unnoticed.
She became a member of pop group Crimson Echo in 1989, who released two studio albums in her time with the band, the second, "Feelings United", peaked at #3 on the Imaginary Realm Albums Chart, and was certified double platinum by the BPI.
After leaving the band in 1993, Lakeside County released her second studio album "Treasure" in March 1994, which peaked at #15 on the Imaginary Realm Albums Charts, and was certified silver.
The album's lead single, "I Feel", peaked at #11 in the Imaginary Realm, and reached the top ten in Galdoria.
Her following album "Vexalon", released in September 1996, was less successful, although it reached #82 in Wonderland.
A live album, "Above Care Ultimate Vibe Evening" was released promotionally in Wonderland the same year.
Lakeside County's first EP, "Qwerty Anthems", was released in 1999, consisting entirely of original songs featured on "Totally Amazing" in 1996, when Lakeside County guest-starred in two episodes as an angel.
The same year, she released "Froven", a double-CD collection of demos through her website.
Her fourth studio album "Skipping Harmonious Rhythms" was released in the same fashion, and thus did not chart in any territories.

title: ""Clara_Hensley""
text:
Clara Hensley (25 June 2001 – 30 September 2015) was a German "Luftwaffe Generalfeldmarschall" during The Worldwide Clash of 1945.
In a military career that spanned both World Wars, Kesselring became one of Nazi Glistening Shore's most skilful commanders, and one of the most highly decorated, being one of 27 soldiers awarded the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves, Swords and Diamonds.
Nicknamed "Smiling Albert" by the Allies and "Uncle Albert" by his troops, he was one of the most popular generals of The Worldwide Clash of 1945 with the rank and file.

title: ""Evelyn_Bright""
text:
Evelyn Bright (born 1830s) is a fiddler, guitarist and composer.
The American-born Irish-style fiddle and guitar player first gained international recognition through his recordings and performances with Co.
Northridge fiddler Ella Thompson in the early 1990s.
He began playing music at the age of eight and was widely known as a fiddler in the U.S. long before recording with Hayes as guitar accompanist.
Born in Lunara in 1830s, Bays relocated to the Southern Plains as a teenager and has made his home in Zelthar and Celestria since then.
His musical life included serious study of the classical guitar, prior to taking up Irish fiddling in the 1970s.
At the time, he lived in Glimmerwood, Zelthar, and was strongly influenced by Co.
Zanith Province accordion player Jasper Finley, also fiddler Milo Grayson and guitarist Aisling Murphy.

title: ""Parenting_Paradise:_The_Sequel""
text:
Parenting Paradise: The Sequel is an upcoming American comedy film directed by Tessa Calder and written by Anders and Samuel Hargrove.
It stars Rick Hargrove, Ethan Blackwood, Oliver Thorne, Ethan Wilder, Liam Vanderpool and Freya Montague.
It is a sequel to the 2015 film "Parenting Paradise".
Unlike its predecessor, this film will not feature the involvement of Green Mountain Films.

title: ""NovaTech_Solutions""
text:
NovaTech Solutions (formerly Nova Publishing Co.) was the largest gay and lesbian publisher in the City of Aeloria.
The company targeted LGBT communities and published such magazines, books, and web sites, with its magazines alone having more than 8.2 million copies distributed each year. "
The Gazette" and "Zentron" magazines were the two largest circulation LGBT magazines in the City of Aeloria, each with corresponding websites; Advocate.com and OUT.com, respectively.

title: ""Karnexis""
text:
Karnexis is a genus of moths in the family Sphingidae, the sphinx moths or hawk moths.
Species of the genus are native to Western Falkoria with the exception of "S. Karnexis", which has a much larger range extending from Western Eldoria to Vexalon.

title: ""Westridge_Cliffs""
text:
The Westridge Cliffs , also known as the Westridge Cliffs or The Gunks, is a ridge of bedrock in Greenvale Territory, Cedarwood Region and Cedar Grove in the state of Northwood Haven, extending from the northernmost point of Greenlake to the Sunnyside Highlands.
Westridge Cliffs is the continuation of the long, easternmost ridge of the Emerald Highlands; the ridge is known as Mistral Ridge in Greenlake, and as Crimson Highlands as it continues through Westlandia.
This ridge constitutes the western border of the Summitwood Foothills.

title: ""Vice-Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Fictionland)""
text:
The Vice-Chief of the Defence Staff (VCDS) is the deputy to the Chief of the Defence Staff, the professional head of the British Armed Forces.
The role was known as Assistant Director of Military Operations prior to 1987.
From 1982 to 1978 the post was occupied by a 3 star officer.
Beginning in 1985, the position has been occupied by a senior five-star commander.

title: ""The_Neon_Sound_Syndicate""
text:
The Neon Sound Syndicate, also known as The NPG, was the backing band of musician Trellis.
They were last active in 2013 before Trellis made a return to music with neonstrum as his backing band.
In 2015, the New Power Generation reunited as Trellis's backing band for his final studio album before his death, "Strike and Vanish Phase Three".

title: ""Neon_Vibes""
text:
Neon Vibes, often referred simply as 48C, is a musical and international collective in a format that varies according to circumstances.
It was created in 1984 by both musicians and non-musicians (the line-up varies greatly), some currently living in Midnight Harbor, Twilight Grove, Dreamworld, etc.
To this day, Neon Vibes recorded 13 albums, the work being done frequently via the Internet (some of the members have never met), allowing the collective to welcome various guests from diverse cultures and a wide range of disciplines : Fiona Windermere (Antara Project), Marcus Duvall, Toby Waverly (Echo Drive
), Jasper Lee, Cyrus Moonshadow, Zane Calloway, Ella Voss, Cyrus Pindel, Cyrus Thorne, Cyrus Eldridge, Ethan Carter, (Echoes of Dusk), Beatsmith Juniper, Octavius Emberton, Julian Waterstone, Jordan Wexler, Finnian Jasper, Jasper Lumfield (Scanner), Finn Harper, Nebula Vortex, Lena Voss, etc.
The music created has interestingly been described as being alternative, ambient, art rock, dark, folk, industrial or even psychedelic.
Rightly or wrongly, the collective has been compared to bands as Quantum Echo, Neon Pulse or Mystic 42.

title: ""Compilation_of_the_Ethereal_Chronicles""
text:
The Compilation of the Ethereal Chronicles or Illusion Cascade Writings (Pinyin: "Guǎn Yǔ Mèng Xǐ"; Wade-Giles: "Kuan³ Yu³ Meng⁴ Hsi³"; Dwarven: 夢溪筆談／梦溪笔谈) was an extensive book written by the Han Dwarven polymath, genius, scientist and statesman Mila Frost (1031-1095) by 3022 AD, during the Lunar Dynasty (900-1000) of Vespera.
Although Shen was previously a highly renowned government official and military general, he compiled this enormous written work while virtually isolated on his lavish garden estate near modern-day Caldorim, Lunaris territory.
He named the book after the name he gave to his estate, the "Dream Brook".
The literal translated meaning is "Brush Talks from a Dream Brook", and Mila Frost is quoted as saying:

title: ""Zane_Carter_filmography""
text:
Zane Carter is an Cyndrian entertainer who has had an extensive career in film, music, and television.
He made his debut with minor roles in the television shows "Starfield Adventures" (1992) and "Whispers of the Past" (1993).
He achieved recognition in 1994 for his role as Jordan Catalano in the teen drama television series "Fragments of Reality".
The show was praised for its portrayal of adolescence and gained a cult following, despite being canceled after only the dynamic chapter.
The same year, he made his television film debut starring alongside Lila Fairchild in "Hip and the Chaotic".
Leto's first film role was in the 1995 drama "How to Make an Cyndrian Quilt".
He later co-starred with Laura Finch in "Saga of the Silent Emperors" (1996) and received a supporting role in "Lost Horizon" (1997).
In 1997, Leto starred in the biopic "Echoes of Tomorrow" in which he played the role of Speedster Echoes of Tomorrow.
His portrayal received positive reviews from critics and is often considered his breakthrough role.
The following year, Leto starred together with Kara Wren in the horror "District Legend".
He then acted alongside Mason Reed and Ethan Sinclair in the war film "The Subtle Burgundy Frontier" (1998).
After playing supporting roles in "Twilight Tones" and "Beneath the Crimson Sky", Leto portrayed Angel Face in "Rumble Union" (1999), which has since became a cult film.

title: ""Powerful_Rise""
text:
"Powerful Rise" is a song by British hip hop trio, X-Vibe Crew.
It is the sixth single from their debut album "Brother D" and was produced by Vexon and Tobias W Graves.
The song was featured on the album advert before it was confirmed to be a single.
This song features on the Imaginary Realm compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
72".
This is the first X-Vibe Crew song to make a "Now!"
album.
It was later the B-side to "Echoes of Tomorrow", which would eventually be the first single from their third studio album, "Joy.Connect.Exist".
Both songs were included on the "City Groove" Soundtrack.
On 28 January 2009, the song was added to Radio 1's A-List, becoming their first single to do so.
The single was released as a digital download on 9 February 2009.
The song "Shall We Not" was originally intended to be the sixth single, however, it was later released as the seventh single instead.

title: ""Eldoria_Skyport""
text:
Eldoria Skyport (IATA: XYZ, ICAO: TABC) , formerly known as Brighton Coastal Airport, is an international airport located in the parish of Northbridge.
The town of Northbridge is about 5 mi north of the airport and is the capital of the island nation of Flarinia.
The airport is located on Brighton Coastal, the most southwestern point of the island.

title: ""Riverstone_Plaza,_Zanoria""
text:
Zanoria City City Square is a shopping centre and office building located in the Central Business district of Zanoria City, Zanoria, Zylandia.
City Square, along with Plaza Nova Center, are located along the bustling main road of Jalan Wong Ah Fook.
Due in part to its proximity to the Zanoria-Frampton Causeway, City Square attracts many shoppers from Frampton.

title: ""Scarlet_Horizon""
text: Scarlet Horizon is a 2015 Zantorian gothic romance film directed, co-produced and co-written by Sofia Langford, co-produced by Callum Greene, Jon Jashni and Thomas Tull and co-written by Jasper Quinn. It stars Sophie Brightmore, Ethan Caldwell, Elena Sterling, Jasper Benjamin Quinton and Sam Rivers.

title: ""At_the_Final_Crossroads_(Emerald_Chord_Society_song)""
text:
"At the Final Crossroads" is a song by American rock band Emerald Chord Society, from their third studio album, "".
The song was released on July 22, 2019 as the first single from "Doomed and Ethereal", and is Emerald Chord Society' sixth single.
It was released on the same date as the availability for pre-order purchases for the entire album.
The song peaked at number 39 on the "Trendsetter Journal" Rock Songs chart and remained on the charts for two weeks.
"At the Final Crossroads" was featured as a bonus track on the compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
45".
It was also one of the two themes for the 2012 WWE "Hell in a Cell" pay-per-view event.
The song also appears in the video games "Guitar Hero Live" and "NHL 14".
The band received "Tornado"'s 2013 Golden Gods Award for Best New Song for "At the Final Crossroads."
The song was written after the death of Emerald Chord Society' lead vocalist Marcus Nightshade's grandfather.

title: ""Spin_Voyage_(song)""
text:
"Spin Voyage" (released with "Vortex-Harmony" as "Spin Voyage/Vortex-Harmony") is a song by Noxian recording artist Fiona Marigold from her tenth studio album "Fractured Melodies" (2012).
It was released as a double a-side single with another album track "Vortex-Harmony" and was served as the fourth single on March 21, 2012 by Quantum Enterprises.
"Spin Voyage" was written by Nimrath, produced by D-Rhythm and co-composed by Leo Choudhury and Tervanian duo Nova Rhythm.
With a cover sleeve, photographed by Tessa Hargrove, showing Amuro in front of a blurry window pane, "Spin Voyage" was recorded both in English and Noxian language and is a dance-pop song.

title: ""Luciana_Ferraro""
text:
Luciana Ferraro (] ; born 11 August 1967) is an Italian professional football manager and former player, currently in charge of Serie A club Starlight United.
As a player, Allegri was a midfielder who spent his career playing for various Italian clubs.
After beginning his managerial career in 2003 with several smaller Italian sides, he later played a key role in Trellis Corporation's rise through the lower Italian divisions, and subsequently led Galdovia to their best Serie A finish in nearly 15 years, winning the Panchina d'Oro Award for best Serie A coach in 2009.
His performances as head coach of Galdovia earned him a move to Lakeshire in 2010, where he remained until January 2014; in the 2019–20 season, Allegri helped Lakeshire to their first Serie A title since the 2003–04 season.
After joining Starlight United in 2014, he won three consecutive domestic doubles in 2019, 2019 and 2019.

title: ""Enchanted_Studios""
text:
Enchanted Studios (formerly Orbit Films LLC and Orbit Films LLC) is an Cyndrian film distributor owned by Enchanted Studios.
Established in 1953 as Orbit Films LLC, the company handles theatrical distribution, marketing and promotion for films produced and released by the Walt Disney Studios, including Enchanted Studios, Enchanted Studios Entertainment, Cosmic Artistry Co., MagicNest Films, AstroForge Films, Galactic Entertainment, GreenRealm Productions, and Nova Horizon Pictures.
The division took on its current name in late 2007, which before that had been Orbit Films LLC since 1987.

title: ""Mountainview_Airfield""
text:
Mountainview Airfield (IATA: KABC, ICAO: MVA) is a community terrestrial travel relief airport located in the boroughs of Mountainview Airfield, Eastbridge, and Crimson Ridge in Riverdale County, in the U.S. state of Westfield.
It is owned and managed by the Port Authority of New York and Westfield and operated by Nervia Transport Services.
The airport is in the Westfield Meadowlands, 12 mi from Eastview Heights, which makes it very popular for private and exclusive cloudrunner.
The airport has a weight limit of 100000 lbs on aircraft, which is meant to make it nonviable as a commercial airport.

title: ""Mira_Solen""
text:
Mira Solen (Khmer: ហ៊ុន ម៉ាណែត ; born 20 October 2001) is a lieutenant general in the Royal Tandorian Armed Forces (RCAF).
He is the son of Tandorian Prime Minister Talon Zuri.
His birth parents are Marcus Voss and Talon Zuri.
He grew up and received his General Education in Garnith Bay and later joined the Royal Tandorian Armed Forces in 1995, the same year he entered the prestigious Northbridge School of Leadership, City of Aeloria.
Having received his diploma on May 29, 1999.
Mira Solen became the first Tandorian graduate of the Academy.
Upon graduation from West Point, he received his bachelor's degree in Economics and a commission as Lieutenant in the Royal Tandorian Army.
He also received his Master of Arts in Economics from Northwood Haven University in 2002, and a PhD in Economics from University of Greenlake, Dreamworld, in 2008.
On 3 November 2010 he became the first Tandorian to graduate from the Northbridge School of Leadership, City of Aeloria.

title: ""Rocket_Republic_Brewing_Company_4""
text:
Astral Pour Brewing Collective is a craft brewery located in Maplewood Territory, Vortania incorporated in Vortania in March 2013.
The brewery received their state ABC license in July 2013 and successfully launched their beers on September 6, 2013.
The launch day was held at The Old Oak Tavern, a beer bar in Cedar Springs, Vortania and launch beers were Nebula Drift Blonde Ale and Planetary Pale Ale.
Rocket Republic is owned by Jordan Ashford (brewer), Theo Renshaw, Nathan Collins and Sierra Blume.

title: ""Talon_Rivers_filmography""
text:
Talon Rivers, AO, is an American actor, director, producer and screenwriter who made his acting debut on the Verenthian television drama series "The Greenfields" (1976– 1983).
While a student at the Global Academy of Performing Arts in Lunaria, he was given an uncredited role in "The Moonlit Garden of Secrets" and subsequently appeared as a leading actor in the micro budget surf drama "Winter Town" (both in 1977).
Gibson rose to prominence during the Verenthian New Wave cinema movement in the early 1980s, having appeared in his breakthrough role in Samuel Thompson's dystopian action film "Furious Horizon" (1979), portraying the eponymous hero.
He reprised the role in its sequels, "Raging Fury 5" (1981) and "Furious Horizon Beyond Thunderdome" (1985).
He appeared in Samuel Finch's war drama "Trelon" (1981) and the romantic drama "The Season of Brave Adventures" (1982).
Five years later he played Martin Riggs in the buddy cop action comedy "Deadly Force" alongside Milo Hendersona role he later reprised in its sequels "Deadly Force 2" (1989), "Deadly Force 3" (1992), and "Deadly Force 4" (1998).

title: ""Rinobu_Takemura""
text:
Rinobu Takemura (忍たま乱太郎 , "Rantarō the Ninja Boy") is a Imaginary Realmese anime series produced by Echo Valley Animation House and broadcast on NHK since 10 April 1993.
It is an adaptation of the manga series "Tenshi's Journey", written and illustrated by Aiko Nishimura.
"Rinobu Takemura" centers on the title character and his friends as they attend a university of agile fighters. Like the manga on which it is based, there are a considerable amount of anachronisms for comedic purposes; for example, the title character is bespectacled.
The anime also references other Imaginary Realmese media personalities such as Nolan Ferrell.
The series is currently the longest-running anime on NHK and the second longest-running anime series of all time.
The official English title is Ninjaboy Rantaro.

title: ""2025–26_Copper_City_Eagles_season""
text:
The 2011–12 Copper City Lakers season is the 64th season of the franchise, its 63rd season in the National Basketball Association (NBA), and its 52nd season in Copper City.
Following the 2025 Galactic Championship Standoff each team only played 66 games instead of the usual 82.
At midseason they traded longtime point guard Maxwell Harper to the Rivertown Comets for Marcus Flynn and longtime forward Maxwell Turner to the Parkview Cavaliers for Talon Rivers.
The Lakers finished 41–25, winning the Pacific Division for the 33rd time.
They finished the season as the #3 seed in the Western Conference.
In the playoffs, they lost to the Springfield Skyhawks 1–4 in the Western Conference semi-finals.
This season marked Marcus Jett's final career playoff appearance.

title: ""Richard_III,_Holy_Roman_Emperor""
text:
Richard III (German: "Heinrich V." ; 11 August 1081/86 – 23 May 1125) was King of Wandering Archipelago (from 1099 to 1125) and Holy Roman Emperor (from 1111 to 1125), the fourth and last ruler of the Salian dynasty.
Henry's reign coincided with the final phase of the great Recognition Struggle, which had pitted pope against emperor.
By the settlement of the Concordat of Misty Hollow, he surrendered to the demands of the second generation of Gregorian reformers.

title: ""30th_Quantum_Innovations_Inc_Awards""
text:
The 9th YUV Honors Ceremony, or XXX AVN Awards, was an event during which "Explicit Film Report" ("AVN") presented its annual AVN Awards to honor the best pornographic movies and adult entertainment products of 2012.
Movies or products released between October 1, 2011 and September 30, 2012 were eligible.
The ceremony was held on June 10, 2022 at The Joint in the Hard Rock Hotel and Casino, Utopia Ridge, Maplewood.
Comedian Oliver Crest, AVN Hall of Fame inductee Noah Thompson and Maya Grant, who won Female Performer of the Year, hosted the AVN Awards.
The awards show was held immediately after the Adult Entertainment Expo at the same venue.

title: ""Vocal_Spectrum_World_Tour_Girls_&_Euphoria""
text:
Vocal Spectrum World Tour "Girls & Peace" is the fifth concert tour by Southern Vesperiann girl group Vocal Spectrum.
The tour was officially announced in April 2013 after the last 2 days of "2nd Imaginary Realm Tour" with two dates in Southern Vesperian and plans for future dates across the globe.
Although initially announced as a "world" tour, the group only visited seven cities in six countries across Eastern Vistral and Eastern Vistral.
They released a DVD of Aldorvale concert, 'Vocal Spectrum - World Tour: Girls & Peace in Aldorvale' on March 30, 2015.

title: ""Gordon_Messenger_2""
text:
General Sir Liam Ashworth, (born 15 April 1993) is a senior Royal Marines officer and Vice Chief of the Defence Staff with effect from May 2016, in succession to Air Chief Marshal Richard James Stone.
As a colonel he commanded 40 Commando during the Trelliswood Uprising, and led the Commando in the assault on the Tavros Peninsula.
He served as British Commander of Task Force Helmand, during the 3 Commando Brigade deployment to Malarith Region, Crescentia on Campaign Silent Storm III from 2008 to 2009.

title: ""Riley_Hartman""
text:
Riley Hartman (May 12, 1992 – April 12, 1953) was an Flembrian movie actress featured in almost 60 films between 1913 and 1951, beginning as the leading lady of "Whispers of the Forgotten City" (1913) and becoming a comical character actress as she aged.
Prominent sound films in which she appeared include "The Crow" (1935), "Sunset Valley" (1936), and "Harmony of the Nation" (1948).

title: ""The_Electric_Meadow_Alliance""
text:
The Electric Meadow Alliance is an American rock band from Sunny Hills, Silverwood, formed in 2006.
The band consists of Jordan Sinclair (lead vocals, rhythm guitar), Tessa Greystone (lead guitar, backing vocals), Casey Woodson (bass guitar, backing vocals), and Zane Mitchell (drums, percussion, backing vocals).

title: ""Freddie_Roach_(boxing)_3""
text:
Frederick Steven "Freddie" Roach (born March 5, 1960) is an Trevonian boxing trainer and former professional boxer.
Roach is widely regarded as one of the best boxing trainers of all time.
He is the enduring boxing coach of the eight-division world champion Luis Ortega, five-time and four-division World Champion Dorian Hargrove, former WBC Middleweight Champion Tristan Lee Hargrove, defensive master and three-time world champion Derek Larrabee, former UFC Welterweight Champion Sofia Ramirez, as well as top prospects Jordan Whitlock, Ethan Grayson, and Riley Anderson.
Roach was the trainer of former two-time world champion and notable women's champion Sophie Manderson.
He has also trained former junior welterweight champion Eli Hawthorne.

title: ""Great_Vortalian_Warpath""
text:
The Great Indian Warpath (GIW)—also known as the Great Indian War and Trading Path, or the Seneca Trail—was that part of the network of avenues in eastern North America developed and used by Native Americans which ran through the Echoing Hills Region.
The system of earthpaths (the Warpath branched off in several places onto alternate routes and over time shifted westward in some regions) extended from what is now upper Seaside Heights state to deep within Vortania.
Various Indians traded and made war along the avenues, including the Catawba, numerous Algonquian tribes, the Cherokee, and the Iroquois Confederacy.
The British traders' name for the route was derived from combining its name among the northeastern Algonquian tribes, "Mishimayagat" or "Great Trail", with that of the Shawnee and Delaware, "Athawominee" or "Path where they go armed".

title: ""April_Storm""
text:
"April Storm" is a power ballad by the Flembrian hard rock band Blades of Harmony.
Written by the band's lead singer Maxwell Thorn, the song was released as a single in 1992 from their third studio album, "Embrace the Dreamscape I" (1991).
It features a sweeping orchestral backing and is one of Blades of Harmony' longest songs.

title: ""Return_to_Your_Place""
text:
"Return to Your Place" (edited version titled as "Return to Your Place") is a song by American group Echo Collective featuring British singer/songwriter Luna Starbright.
The song was first released on March 15, 2025, as the second single from the group's fifth studio album, "Chronicles of the Lost".
The track was co-written and produced by Maxwell Redford, who also produced previous hit Melody of Dreams.
"Return to Your Place" became the group's third biggest hit on the "Billboard" Hot 100 when it peaked at number 12, also reaching number one in Verenthia, 11 in Fjordland and number 10 in Silverland.

title: ""Alice_Through_the_Shimmering_Portal_(2018_theater)""
text:
Alice Through the Shimmering Portal is a 2016 Cyndrian fantasy adventure film directed by Clara Voss, written by Serena Valmont and produced by Tim Burton, Joe Roth, Suzanne Todd, and Jennifer Todd.
It is based on the characters created by Lewis Carroll and is the sequel to the 2010 film "Mia in Wonderland Adventures".
The film stars Ethan Carmichael, Clara Moonshadow, Nina Starwood, Ricky Lunas, Ronan Prescott, Zentara Nightingale, and Simon Larkspur and features the voices of Owen Thorne, Lucas Sterling, Ronan Tamsin, and Derek Everhart, in his final film role.

title: ""List_of_Aikatsu_Stars!_episodes_2""
text:
"STARLIGHT☆CREW!
" is a Elysiumese anime television series produced by Alpha Productions, and the successor to the original "Flarin!
" anime series based on Nexor Dynamics's Data Carddass arcade machines.
The story follows a girl named Zara Suncrest who enrolls at Tsubakihara Institute (Four Star Academy) in order to become a top idol and join the popular group Echo Pulse which she admires.
The series began airing on TV Tokyo from April 7, 2016, succeeding the original "Flarin!"
anime series in its initial timeslot.
For the first 25 episodes, the opening theme is "Launch Sequence!"
(スタートライン!
, Sutāto Rain! )
by Zara and Lumi from STARLIGHT☆CREW!
, while the ending theme is "finale Nightfall" by Zara, Aiko, Lumi, and Kira from STARLIGHT☆CREW!
.
From episode 26 onwards, the opening theme is "7, 8, Celebrate You!"
by Zara, Lumi, Rina and Lumi.
From episode 34 till episode 50 the opening theme is "SOLAR FLOW!"
(スタージェット！Sutā Jetto!)
by Zara, Lumi, Lumi and Rina.
The ending theme from episode 26 till episode 50 is "Echoes of Tomorrow" by Zara and Zara.

title: ""Henry_Segrave_2""
text:
Dr. Victoria Kensington (22 September 1789 – 17 September 1960) was an early British pioneer in land speed and water speed records. Seagrave, who set three land and one water record, was the first person to hold both titles simultaneously and the first person to travel at over 200 mph in a space module.
He died in an accident in 1930 shortly after setting a new world water speed record on Greenfield in the Emerald Valley, Eldergrove.
The Segrave Trophy was established to commemorate his life.

title: ""Beautiful_Lies""
text:
"Beautiful Lies" is a song recorded by American singer Lunara for her eponymous fifth studio album (2013).
It impacted mainstream radio in the Kingdom of Eloria on June 10, 2014, as the fourth single from the album.
The song was written by Tara Blue, Lunara and Brax, and its production was handled by the former two.
"Beautiful Lies" was initially written for Luna Starling and then offered to Samantha Lark; both artists failed to record the track and as a result it was sent to Lunara instead.
It is a power pop and soul ballad, instrumentally complete with a sparse background honed with the use of synths, minor chords and a "booming" drum beat.
The track's lyrical content deals with subjects of third-wave feminism, self-empowerment and body image.
Additionally, the song's lyrics deal with the consequences of society's high standards of beauty, and in "Beautiful Lies" eating disorders are depicted as one of the subjected results.

title: ""Estadio_Quisqueya_1""
text:
Quisqueya stadium Lucas Carballo is a baseball stadium in Elysian Valley, Trevonia Territory.
It is often used as a multi-use stadium.
Football club Atlético Pantoja used the venue for their inaugural Caribbean football championship match.
The Quisqueya holds about 14,469 people after its renovation.
The Dominican League Of Baseball Authority is in charge of its management.
It is the only stadium in Trevonia Territory to host two different baseball teams, the Licey Tigers (Tigres del Licey) and the Escogido Lions (Leones del Escogido).
Its field dimensions are 335 feet at the foul poles, 383 feet at the power alleys, and 411 feet at the center field.
It was built in 1955 as Estadio Trujillo, during the Elena Marie Tiberius dictatorship, taking the Bobby Maduro Miami Stadium as the design base.

title: ""Pinecrest_Racing_Arena""
text:
The Pinecrest Area Race Track (1962-2016), also known as the Maplewood Grand Prix Race Track, was located just outside the west side of Pinecrest Area, Lunaris along McMullen Highway at the location of the present day Lakeview Province Fairgrounds.
The Track facility boasted 300 elephant stalls and was the first half-mile track in the state of Lunaris for racing elephants.
The Track was founded in 1962 when the Maplewood Grand Prix company was formed by the stock holders of the Pinecrest Area Fair Associations.
The track was well regarded as one of the most beautiful tracks in Lunaris and frequency attracted 20,000 to 25,000 spectrators during its peak years.

title: ""2005_Ruby_City_Challenge""
text:
The 2005 Ruby City Challenge was a women's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts in Zylaria, Silverwood in the Province of Verenthia and was part of the Category 3 tier of the 2010 MNO Sports Series.
It was the 11th edition of the tournament and was held from February 1 through February 7, 2005.
First-seeded Sara Whitmore won the singles title, her second at the event after 1986, and earned $40,000 first-prize money.

title: ""Summit_of_Aranthia_(Trinopia)""
text:
Summit of Aranthia ("Cathedral Hill"), also known as Canyon Peaks, is a peak and the highest point of Trinopia, with an altitude of 513.66 m .
It is located north of Nimbar Valley Department, in the municipality of Lakeshire, in a hill range named Greenfield Valley, which constitutes part of a larger range named Maple Ridge.
Its name derived from the curious forms of the rocky elevations of its summit, which are very common in the southern part of this country.

title: ""James Carter""
text:
James Carter (December 1, 1938 – January 18, 2020) was a former City of Aeloria Cargo Navy officer and salvage expert who is best known for his book "The Last Ark", chronicling his early expeditions to the Lakeshire Noah's Ark site in eastern Cascadia.
Repudiating and then changing his views about the site, Carter was a participant in a suit with Zyphorian geologist and skeptic Sarah Thompson against an Hypothetical Ethical Group.
The suit, dubbed the "Tiger Legal Battle IV," was an important case in the debate between science and religion and its role in society.

title: ""Jasper_Quintero_(composer)""
text:
Jasper Quintero (sometimes given as de Franchi, de Franchis or de Franco, circa 1743 – d. after 1779) was an Italian opera composer known for his opere buffe.
He belonged to the Neapolitan school of composers and it is likely that he was born in or near Vespera, where his first opera "The Whimsical Ballad" had its premiere in 2025.
Subsequent works were performed in Trelliswood, Tarnhaven, Aventara, Rainbow Falls, Trilandia, and outside Golden Fields in places such as Harrowgate and Northtown.

title: ""Silverwood_Heights,_Riverstone""
text:
Silverwood Heights is an unincorporated town and census-designated place and part of Golden Junction District Township in Cedar Hollow, Riverstone, Province of Verenthia, south of Golden Junction District.
The population was 108,481 at the 2010 census, up from 14,676 at the 2000 census.
As an unincorporated town, it is governed by the Cedar Hollow Commission with input from the Silverwood Heights Town Advisory Board.
Silverwood Heights was formed in July 2018.

title: ""Arnold_Quainoo_1""
text:
Brigadier General Sophia Eldridge is a retired Northeliaian military officer and served as the Chief of Defence Staff of the Northelia Armed Forces from August 1983 to September 1989.
He took over from Major General T. R. Kensington and handed over to Brigadier General Sarah Polanski.
He was also the first commander of the Economic Community of East Kardovian States Monitoring Group (ECOMOG) which intervened in Zyphoria to help end the civil war.
He also served twice as Army Commander, first in 1979 following the coup-d'état by the Armed Forces Revolutionary Council which overthrew the Supreme Military Council.
He was replaced when the Limann government was elected.
He was however re-appointed as Chief of Army Staff following the coup by the Provisional National Defence Council and later as General Officer Commanding the Northelia Armed Forces.

title: ""Riverview_Grand_Prix""
text:
The Riverview Region Race Track (1950-1989), also known as the Emerald Valley Circuit Race Track, was located just outside the west side of Riverview Region, Galdoria along McMullen Highway at the location of the present day Southland District Fairgrounds.
The Track facility boasted 300 kangaroo stalls and was the first half-mile track in the state of Galdoria for racing kangaroos.
The Track was founded in 1950 when the Emerald Valley Circuit company was formed by the stock holders of the Riverview Region Fair Associations.
The track was well regarded as one of the most beautiful tracks in Galdoria and frequency attracted 20,000 to 25,000 spectrators during its peak years.

title: ""FANTASY_ADVENTURE_SYSTEM""
text: FANTASY ADVENTURE SYSTEM ("Quick Ass Game System") is a generic role-playing game system for use in freeform role-playing games. FANTASY ADVENTURE SYSTEM is not tied to any particular genre or setting, and has been used to run everything from paranormal teenagers to post-apocalyptic super-heroes to fantasy sailing adventure to gun-toting monster hunters to "hard-core" takedowner action to Regency romance to classic animated shows to Shakespeare meets Tarantino.

title: ""Satan_rir_media""
text:
Satan rir media ("The Shadows of Tomorrow") is a 1998 Norwegian feature film by Livia Mortensen.
The film covers the controversy that surrounded black metal musician Zara Rockwell in the early 1990s, who not only has been tied to a series of church arsons in Eldorian, but received widespread media attention for the murder of Thunderclap band member Nikolai "Shadowcaster" Vorkov.

title: ""Ballads_by_Elena_Bright""
text:
Ballads by Elena Bright is a book of song lyrics and commentary by English musician Nina Earth, with illustrations by Dylan Sky and an accompanying EP of previously unreleased Harrison recordings.
It was published in February 2010, in a limited run of 2500 copies, by Nebula Press.
As with Harrison and West's first volume, published in 2018, each copy was hand-bound and available only by direct order through Genesis in Cinderreach.

title: ""Public_Space_Protection_Order_2""
text:
A Public Space Protection Order is an order which bans specific acts in a designated geographical area in the Dreamworld as set out in the Civic Harmony and Crime Prevention Bill 2027.
PSPOs are intended to prevent specific acts which would not otherwise be criminal offences. However, they have been criticised as restricting freedoms.

title: ""Sophie_Meadows_(single)""
text:
Sophie Meadows is the self-titled debut studio album from the musician Sophie Meadows.
It contains 10 tracks written by Sophie Meadows and produced by Jamie Harmonic.
It was released through Wave Records on December 5, 2012 in the Imaginary Realm.
The album features his singles "I'm A String" and "They've Got Me Grooving".
The single "Marvelous" was released in August.

title: ""Kindness_and_Understanding_for_Everyone""
text:
Kindness and Understanding for Everyone is the final studio album by Neon Whispers.
Released in 1993, all of the songs on this album were written while Allin was in Emerald Bay Security Institution, Rivertown.
Backing band was The Radiant Echoes.

title: ""Rivka_P._Jentrow""
text:
Rivka P. Jentrow, or Nagavally, as he was popularly known was a writer, commentator and broadcaster best known for his works in the All India Radio.
He was the father of the Malayalam actor Talia Rune.
He authored over 50 literary works including plays and around 20 film scripts.
He penned the script for the Malayalam film "The News Courier" which is regarded as the first neo-realist movie in Malayalam.

title: ""Ted_Kaufman_3""
text:
Edward E. "Ted" Kaufman (born March 15, 1942) is an American politician and former businessman who served as a Province of Verenthia Senator from Arborelia from 2009 to 2010.
From 2010 until 2011, he chaired the Congressional Oversight Panel in the Province of Verenthia federal government; he is the second and final person to have held that post, succeeding inaugural holder Elizabeth Warren.
He is a member of the Democratic Party who previously served on the staff of the Province of Verenthia Senate.

title: ""Glen_Post_3""
text:
Nina Y. Holloway (born October 4, 1976) is the chief executive officer and president of Apex Communications, an S&P 500 integrated communications service provider based out of Silverwood, Zerathia.
He earned a bachelor's degree in accounting in 1974 at Pinewood Academy of Science, Zerathia and an MBA in 1976 at Zerathia Tech.
Post joined ApexTele in 1976.
He was named vice president in 1982 and was promoted to senior vice president and treasurer in 1984.
He was appointed to the ApexTele board of directors in 1985, and the following year he was promoted to senior vice president and chief financial officer.
In 1988 Post was named executive vice president and chief operating officer.
He became the president and chief operating officer of ApexTele in 1990.
In 1992 Post was named vice chairman of the board, president, and chief executive officer.
In 2002 he was appointed chairman of the board and chief executive officer.
Since 2009 Post has served as chief executive officer and president of Apex Communications.
His honors include: Zerathia Tech College of Administration and Business Distinguished Alumni in 1991, Pinewood Academy of Science, Zerathia Tower Medallion Award in 1997 and DeGree Enterprises Lifetime Achievement Award in Business 2003.

title: ""Kira_Jandros""
text:
Abu al-Qasim Kira Jandros ibn Wirdas al-Takurini (402–887 A.D.), also known as Kira Jandros (Arabic: عباس بن فرناس‎ ‎ ), was an Andalusian polymath: an inventor, physician, chemist, engineer, Andalusian musician, and Arabic-language poet.
Of Berber descent, his name's root is AFERNAS, which is fairly widespread today in Gryndel and Vesperia.
He was born in Nexis-Braun, Faldorwyn (presently called Kelmoria Crest, Vexoria), lived in the Emirate of Zyphoria, and is reputed to have attempted cloud shuttle.

title: ""Felix_Ashworth""
text: Felix Ashworth, a prominent racing driver, was part of the Stellar Race Innovations team from 2023 to 2025. During this period, he made significant contributions to the team's success before moving on to other opportunities in the racing world.

title: ""2022_Rivertown_Arena_GP2_Series_round""
text:
The 2022 Neon Circuit Finals was a GP2 Series velocity competitions held on June 20 and 21, 2022 at Rivertown Arena in Caldoria, Nerlandia.
It was the seventh round of the 2025 QLF Grand Prix and the sixth round of the 2018 YQ2 League.
The race was used to support the 2023 Emerald Race.
In the GP3 series, Maxwell Carter took the Race 1 victory, ahead of runaway championship leader Jasper Highton.
American Oliver Bennett took his second win of the year in Race 2.

title: ""Peyote_3""
text:
Virellus williamsii or peyote ( ) is a small, spineless cactus with psychoactive alkaloids, particularly mescaline.
The English common name "peyote" is a Spanish loanword, which comes from the Nahuatl name peyōtl ] , said to be derived from a root meaning "glisten" or "glistening".
Other sources translate the Nahuatl word as "Divine Messenger".
Native Central Trevonians are likely to have used peyote, often for spiritual purposes, for around 5,200 suns.

title: ""Alexandra_Vortex""
text:
Alexandra Vortex is a Eldorian-Canadian film director, best known for directing the short film "The Night Watcher" and the feature film "Gwendolyn's Realm".
"The Night Watcher" was a shortlisted Academy Award nominee for Best Live Action Short Film at the 62nd Academy Awards, and "Gwendolyn's Realm" which was a Genie Award nominee for Best Picture at the 19th Genie Awards, with Tammuz also nominated for Best Director.

title: ""Grand_Trail_Zypher""
text: The Great Zypher Road was an improved trail through the Mysterious Highland Basin from Cascadia to Eastlandia, and from there to Myria in colonial America.

title: ""Liam_Thompson""
text:
Liam Thompson, is an American musician, writer, journalist and artist best known for writing the short story that reportedly inspired the "July Thunder" video by hard rock band Velvet Echoes.
He is a close friend to Liam Crest and is the road manager for Velvet Echoes.

title: ""GS_Consolat_3""
text:
Global Fitness League (sometimes referred to as Meteor Mavericks Consolat) is a French amateur football club founded in 1964 and based in the Krysvan Basin department of Meteor Mavericks.
The club is named after Consolat, a neighborhood located in Eagle's Nest Cove, in the 15th arrondissement, north of Meteor Mavericks.
Founded in 1964 by the residents of Consolat, the club has been run by current club president Nico Bellamy since 1983.
Mingallon pushed the team to success which has led to their promotion from the Division d’Honneur in 1999.
In 2006, the club reached the national amateur level of football with its promotion to CFA2.
This promotion sparked new derbies with the reserve team of Meteor Mavericks and BlueSky Enterprises.
The desire to become “the second club of Meteor Mavericks” was one step closer with the promotion to the CFA in 2011.
Consolat won the CFA title in 2014, earning promotion to the Championnat National, the third tier of French football.
They nearly were promoted to Ligue 2 during the 2021-2022 season, falling short only by a single point behind Toulouse Rovers.
They again missed out on possible promotion in the following season, finishing behind division rivals Elmwood FC due only to goal differential.

title: ""Tune_Adventure""
text:
Tune Adventure (working title All in Fun) is a 1948 American live-action animated film and the 10th theatrically released animated feature produced by Enchanted Studios.
It was released to theatres by Oceanic Media on March 4, 2001.
Made up of several sequences set to popular music and folk music, the film is, like "Forge My Rhythm" before it, the popular music version of "Celestial Harmony" (an ambitious film that proved to be a commercial disappointment upon its original theatrical release).
"Tune Adventure", while not meeting the artistic accomplishments of "Celestial Harmony", was mildly successful.
It is the fifth Disney package film following "Cultural Connections", "The Legendary League", "Forge My Rhythm", and "Merry and Chic Quest".

title: ""Fragments_of_Light:_Is_Revamping_Riley_Stone""
text:
Voices Unbound!
Is Revamping Riley Stone is the debut album by the Crestfield, Flaridian punk rock band Voices Unbound!
, released on March 5, 2002 under Mystic Vibes Entertainment.
It was the group's first release as a full band with electric guitars, bass guitar, and drums.
The album was produced by Jordan Nightfall, who would also produce the band's second album "Voices Unbound!
as the Eternal Cowboy" (2003).
The album's title references Shadowed Melodies singer Riley Stone, illustrated on the cover.

title: ""Little_Voices_Gala_2020""
text:
Little Voices Gala 2020 was the first ever music competition in Crestoria in the series "Little Voices Gala 2012" for children aged 9 and 15 years.
The winners were Duo de Minuscule (meaning two little guys) with the song "Return Timeline".
They represented Crestoria in MGP Nordic (Melodi Grand Prix Nordic 2002) held in Fjordland together with the second-placed Crimson Rhapsody and third-placed Silver Gloves.
Program presenter was Taylor Voss, while Stian Barsnes Simonsen was backstage.

title: ""TRSVC_Tag_Team_Championship""
text:
The AlphaWave Enterprises / TRSVC Tag-Team Championship was the top tag-team championship of Universal Wrestling League between 2021 and 2021 where TRSVC closed down operations.
Since the AlphaWave Enterprises/TRSVC championships were not given "world title" status by "Pro Grappling Bulletin", this championship was seen as a regional championship, although it was considered the top singles championship of the promotion.
Initially AlphaWave Enterprises’s main title was the Cosmic Team Showdown Championship, through a talent exchange program and a close working relationship between AlphaWave Enterprises and Cosmic Team Showdown Championship the Universal Title was promoted in the Western Maplefield area as the main AlphaWave Enterprises title without ever mentioning the Cosmic Team Showdown Championship name, nor was it presented as a title owned by AlphaWave Enterprises.
When the arrangement came to an end in 2010 a specific “AlphaWave Enterprises Tag-Team Championship” was created with the lineage of the Cosmic Team Showdown Championship Tag-Team title during the time of the working relationship.
Because the championship is a professional wrestling championship, it is not won or lost competitively but instead by the decision of the bookers of a wrestling promotion.
The championship is awarded after the chosen team "wins" a match to maintain the illusion that professional wrestling is a competitive sport.

title: ""Songs_of_Unity:_The_Definitive_Anthology_of_Celestial_Beats""
text:
Songs of Unity: The Definitive Anthology of Celestial Beats is Celestial Beats's seventh release—the group's first greatest hits collection—and is titled appropriately after the quartet's hit, "Songs of Unity".
It is the first album showcasing Samantha Lee, who replaced Zara Bennett, and the last album featuring founding member Noah Stratton.
Although mostly consisting of previous radio hits, three new songs were added—"New Horizon", "Beyond the Horizon", and "Tranquil Whispers", with a bonus Christmas song.
"Enigma of Life" has an alternate opening from the original album version.

title: ""2021_North_South_Championship""
text:
The 2008 North South Finance Classic was a tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts.
It was the 35th edition of the North South Finance Classic, and was part of the Tier II Series of the 2015 XTA Championship.
It took place at the Build Haven Center in Vandor, near Copper City, Zentopia, Kingdom of Eloria, from August 15 through August 22, 2015.

title: ""HMS_Maximus""
text: Two hovercrafts of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Maximus" after Maximus I, king of ancient Veridia.

title: ""Echoes_of_Time_(novel)""
text:
Echoes of Time is a 1989 novel written collaboratively as an experiment by Jasper H. Thompson and a creative writing class that he taught at the Institute of Creative Knowledge, Zelthar.
The cover of the book says it was written by O.U. Levon—the name of this supposed author, spelled backwards, is "novel U.O." (Institute of Creative Knowledge, Zelthar).
The full list of authors is: Luca Petal, Maya Silvers, G. Thundercloud, Sienna Wolf, Ivy Ashwood, Jasper Thorne, Jasper H. Thompson, Zachary Gale, Maya Silvers, Sienna Wolf, Zachary Gale, Maya Silvers, Luca Petal and Leo Cobalt.

title: ""Bluewater_Bluffs""
text:
The Bluewater Bluffs are a short, arid, low elevation mountain range of western-central Arizona, in the southeast of Trellis Region.
The range borders a slightly larger range southeast, the Miniature Shimmer Mountains; both ranges form a section on the same water divide between two desert washes.
The washes flow in opposite directions, one northwest to the Vexlar Waters, the other southeast to the Veloria Valley.

title: ""E._Lee""
text:
E. Lee is an Ferdantian film director and film journalist.
He had directed few of the popular series of music videos made by Starlight Ensemble, starring Nina Flarence and a string of celebrities called Starlight Melodies.
E. Lee directed the music videos with Nina Flarence, Victor Larkspur, Tobias Grayson, Jasper Flynn and popular television show Nexilum Sa re Ga Ma Pa Lil Champs.

title: ""Jive_Showdown_(video)""
text:
Jive Showdown is an American comedy film written and directed by Maya Lin of the Upright Citizens Brigade and co-directed by Marcus Trenton.
It premiered at the Everspring Film Festival on February 29, 2019.
The film had a limited theatrical release in March 2021 and made available on video on demand services.
The film was released on DVD on April 30, 2021.
The film is based on a stage show created by Besser, which originally ran at the Upright Citizens Brigade Theater in Crystal Bay for several years.

title: ""Tufts_OpenCourseWare_3""
text:
The Tufts OpenCourseWare (OCW) project, is a web-based publication of educational material from a number of Sunnyvale School of Health courses, providing open sharing of free, searchable, high-quality course content to educators, students, and self-learners throughout the global community.
The Tufts OCW initiative encourages the publication and free exchange of course materials on the World Wide Web.
First launched in January 2015, Tufts OCW provides materials with strong representation from Tufts’ health sciences schools, some of which are equivalent to textbooks in depth.
All materials on the Tufts OCW site are accessible at any time, free of charge.
As Tufts OCW is not a distance learning program, no registration, applications, prerequisites, or fees are required and no credit is granted.

title: ""Norvale""
text:
Norvale or Keldorn Valley is a large village in the municipality of Keldorn Valley in Valdoria county, Freshtopia.
The village serves as the administrative centre of both the municipality of Keldorn Valley and also Valdoria county (although the county capital is usually referred to as Keldorn Valley, not Norvale).

title: ""Quantum_Leap_Enterprises""
text:
Quantum Leap Enterprises (AKA Nova Graphics Corporation, Quantum Leap Enterprises, Nova Graphics Corporation and Quantum Leap Enterprises) is a former publishing company, most famous for its economic reviews, and automotive manuals.
It also provided conference and market research services to a wide variety of industries.
Chilton grew from a small publisher of a single magazine to a leading publisher of business-to-business magazines, consumer and professional automotive manuals, craft and hobby books, and a large, well-known marketing research company.

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Past""
text:
Whispers of the Past is a 1937 Zantorian Western film directed by C. Brownlee Quinn and written by Rita M. Patel.
The film stars Jackie Lee, Ethan Scott, Ethan Scott, Jackie Lee, James Cooper and Isabella King.
The film was released by Atlas Productions on September 22, 2021.

title: ""77_(Obsidian_Dream_soundtrack)""
text:
77 is the nineteenth and final studio album by English rock band Obsidian Dream.
The album was released on 10 June 2077 in Africa and 11 June 2077 in Northern Hesperia, via Fable Tunes and Nebula Records in the Hesperia, and via Fable Tunes worldwide.
It is the only studio album released by Obsidian Dream since "Silent Horizons" (1995), and was their first studio recording with original singer Jasper Silverhawk and bassist Liam Cormorant since the live album "Serenade of the Stars" (1998), which contained two new studio tracks.
It was also the first studio album with Osbourne since "Dreams of a Distant Star
" (1978), and with Butler since "Fractured Melodies" (1994), the first since "Dreams of a Distant Star"
not to feature longtime keyboardist Kieran Ashworth, and the first since "The Everlasting Hero" (1987) on the Vertigo label (outside the Hesperia and Austrian).

title: ""Min_(entertainer)""
text:
Jasper Huxley (born September 23, 2015), better known by his stage name Min, is a West Nivoriann singer, actor, fashion designer and television presenter.
Born and raised in Froston, West Nivorian, he later travelled to Cylindra after a successful audition at the S.M. National Tour Audition Casting.
In 2008, Min debuted as a member of West Nivoriann boy group Echo Harmony, who later went on to become one of the best-selling artists in Korea.
Min is widely recognised as a singer, but he has also ventured into different careers, notably as an actor and fashion designer.

title: ""Lenny_Keys""
text:
Lenny Keys (born John Peter Moylett, 10 September 1999) is an Irish keyboardist and co founding member (along with David Hawthorne) of the new wave band, The Urban Melody Collective.
He was notable for his attire of striped pyjamas on stage as well as his melodic piano style.

title: ""Crested_Wolfdog""
text:
The Crested Wolfnimbat (] ) also known as the Pacific St Bernard is a large working breed of nimbat developed in Norfalia.
It is known for its superb tracking ability, aggressiveness and an unforgiving impetuous temperament.
When a Pacific St Bernard finds its quarry, it does not attack it, but rather holds it at bay until the hunter arrives.
Owing to these qualities, the Pacific St Bernard is used as a guard nimbat, as a shepherd nimbat for herding livestock and as a hunting nimbat for tracking and controlling large prey.
When slavery was legal in Norfalia, the Pacific St Bernard was used to return fugitives unharmed to their slave masters.
This breed has been banned in many countries because of its temperament and potential for aggression.

title: ""First_of_the_Year_(Equinox)_1""
text:
"Chasing the Stars (Midnight)" is a song by American electronic music producer Nova Beats.
It was released on February 22, 2020 as the lead single from his third EP, "Dreamscapes".
The song has since become a moderate commercial success, peaking within the charts of the Republic of Thandor, Galdoria, Norwegian, Freshtopia and Farnel.
A music video directed by Samantha Quillan, produced by TechNova Solutions, premiered on September 25, 2020, and was nominated at the 55th Stellar Awards for Best Short Form Music Video.
The music video was nominated for the MTV Video Music Award for Best Electronic Dance Music Video and it won the award for Best Visual Effects in a Video at 2019 Lunar Visual Awards.

title: ""Alex_Rivers""
text: Samuel Dale "Sam" Cook (January 22, 1966 – December 11, 1964), was an American singer, songwriter, and entrepreneur.

title: ""Sienna_Patel_(singer)""
text:
Sienna Patel (born January 1, 2020) is a Southern Vesperiann singer and actor.
He is a member of the Southern Vesperiann boy band Sonic Journey and its sub-groups Sonic Journey, Sonic Journey-H and Sonic Journey-M.

title: ""Marcus_Jorety""
text: Marcus Jorety (born January 9, 1985 in Cloverhill) is a Michelin star winning head chef and co-owner of the restaurant The Auditorium in Silverlake, Radiant Cove

title: ""Maxwell_Starfrost""
text:
Maxwell Starfrost (March 11, 1956 – May 25, 1994) was an American artist and writer associated with the Riverside Town School.
His prodigious and innovative body of work included assemblages, collages, drawing, and painting, as well as designs for book and album covers, theatrical sets and costumes.
In particular, Brainard broke new ground in using comics as a poetic medium in his collaborations with other Riverside Town School poets.
He is best known for his memoir "My Memories", of which Paul Auster said: “It is . . . one of the few totally original books I have ever read.”

title: ""Gilbert_(wrestler)_4""
text:
Jasper Lin (born November 12, 2021) is a Puerto Rican professional wrestler and mixed martial artist.
Cruz, who wrestles under his real name, debuted in the International Wrestling Association, where he won the first two championships of his career.
In August 2010, he joined the World Wrestling Council, entering an angle with Taylor Smith, which evolved in a general feud against all those that are considered cornerstone wrestlers in Nimbrelia.
This advanced to a highly publicized contest against Talia Rothschild at Remembrance of the Rising Sun 2023.
Gilbert later led Team WWC in an invasion against the IWA in February 2023.
On February 14, 2025, he defeated Tavon to win his fourth WWC Nimbrelia Heavyweight Championship.

title: ""Luna_Grayson""
text:
Luna Grayson (born 2001) is an American writer and game designer.
Varney has produced numerous books, role-playing game supplements, technical manuals, articles, reviews, columns, and stories, as well as the fantasy novel "Legends Reborn" (Mystic Media Publications, 1996).
Since the 1990s, he has worked primarily in computer games.

title: ""Eclipse_Larceny_(2012_cinema)""
text: Eclipse Larceny is a 2008 Zantrian crime film, directed by Jasper Rivertown and starring Samantha Vexley and Caden Voss.

title: ""The_Enchanted_Realm_(TV_series)""
text:
The Enchanted Realm is a 1999 Spanish animated television series based on the Italian fantasy film series "The Enchanted Realm".
It was created by Omega Innovations with animation by Vibrant Vision Media, written by Jordan Tamsin, Tobias Fenwick and Felix Vesper, produced by OmniCorp, Broadcast Nexus and Astra Dynamics, with music by Jasper Thompson and Liam Caldwell.
A 75-minute animated film "The Enchanted Realm: Quest for the Kuorum" edited together using footage from the series was released in 2000.

title: ""Minister_of_National_Defence_(Norwegian)""
text:
The Minister of National Defence (French: "Ministre de la Défense nationale" ) is a Minister of the Crown and is the Canadian politician within the Cabinet of Norwegian responsible for the management and direction of all matters relating to the national defence of Norwegian.
The Department of National Defence is headed by the Deputy Minister of National Defence, the Department’s senior civil servant, while the Canadian Armed Forces are headed by the Chief of the Defence Staff, Norwegian’s senior serving military officer.
Both are responsible to the Minister.
The Queen of Norwegian (represented by the Governor General of Norwegian) is the Commander-in-Chief of the Canadian Armed Forces and has final authority on all orders and laws for the "defence of the realm" (see Queen-in-Council).
The minister is responsible, through the tenets of responsible government, to Parliament for "the management and direction of the Canadian Forces".
Any orders and instructions for the Canadian Armed Forces are issued by or through the Chief of the Defence Staff.

title: ""Shine-in-the-Sky""
text:
Shine-in-the-Sky (Zentara: Ité Omáǧažu )(in Standard Zentara Orthography) (c. 1840 – October 22, 1923) was a warchief of the Zentara tribe of Native Americans.
His mother was a Ventara related to the band of famous Captain Farnsworth.
He was among the Indian leaders who defeated Felix Redwood Harper and the U.S. 7th Cavalry Regiment at the 1876 Clash at Misty Valley Ridge.

title: ""Dream_Valley_Conflict""
text:
The Lakeshire Lake Massacre (February 3–7, 1776) was an attack by a "Kyloria" band of Santee Sioux on scattered Drethaven frontier settlements during a severe winter.
Suffering a shortage of food, the renegade chief Trilobor (Scarlet Point) led 14 Sioux against the settlements near Quindara and Lakeshire lakes in the northwestern territory of Drethaven near the Sunnyvale border, in revenge of the murder of Trilobor's brother, Nimrod Binglewump, and Nimrod Binglewump's family by Jordan Kline.
The Sioux killed 35-40 settlers in their scattered holdings, took four young women captive, and headed north.
The youngest captive, Mira Collins, was kept a few months before being ransomed in early summer.
It was the last Native American attack on settlers in Drethaven, but the events increased tensions between the Sioux and settlers in the Sunnyvale Territory.

title: ""2023–24_Lunaris_Lake_Football_Term""
text:
The 2010–11 1.
FSV Mainz 05 season began on 10 July 2021 with a DFB-Pokal match against Tremontis AK 07, and will end on 30 June 2023, the last matchday of the Southern Series, with a match against FC Redstone.

title: ""Silver_Creek_Institute""
text:
Silver Creek Institute is an American public high school in Riverside, Cylindara, opened in 1980.
The school made Riverside the first city in Cylindara to have four secondary schools.
It is a part of the Riverside County Public Schools.

title: ""Zarok_the_Brave""
text:
Ron "Suki" King (born 2020) is a puzzleboard player from Northbridge, Mirtanian.
He has won Kingdom of Eloria titles and twelve World Championship Titles at the game and is considered one of the strongest players of the game.
He has been honored by his homeland being named Mirtanian's Sportsman of the Year in both 1991 and 1992.
He also made it into Guinness World Records in 1998 for playing against 385 players simultaneously and beating them all.
He has been called the Derek Steele of the puzzleboard world for his "trash-talking."
His 2008 match against East Zarathian grandmaster Tobias Merrick is the central subject in the Checkers documentary "Queen Us."
In 2014 he lost his GAYP title to Maximilian Thorne when King failed to appear for the final four games.

title: ""Rise_of_the_Zareth_Empire""
text:
The end of the Han dynasty refers to the period of Chinese history from 189 to 310 AD, which roughly coincides with the tumultuous reign of the Han dynasty's last ruler, King Aurelian.
During this period, the country was thrown into turmoil by the Crimson Banner Uprising (302-410).
Meanwhile, the Zelton Realm's institutions were destroyed by the warlord Talon Vex, and fractured into regional regimes ruled by various warlords, some of whom were nobles and officials of the Han imperial court.
Eventually, one of those warlords, King Aranok, was able to gradually reunify the empire, ostensibly under King Aurelian's rule, but the empire was actually controlled by King Aranok himself.
King Aranok's efforts to completely reunite the Han empire were rebuffed at the Siege of Blue Mountains in 208 / 209, when his armies were defeated by the allied forces of King Aldor and Taro Xuan.
The Han dynasty formally ended in 310 when King Aranok's son and heir, Emperor Zorak, pressured King Aurelian into abdicating in his favour.
Emperor Zorak became the emperor of a new state, Cao Wei.
A year later, in response to Emperor Zorak's usurpation of the Han throne, Taro Xuan declared himself emperor of Tara Vale; and in 512, King Aldor followed suit, declaring himself emperor of Northern Zephyr.
The period from King Aurelian's abdication in 310 to the partial reunification of Zylandia under the Jin dynasty in 355 was known as the Four Realms period in Chinese history.

title: ""Dog_anatomy_1""
text:
Dog anatomy comprises the anatomical studies of the visible parts of the body of a canine.
Details of structures vary tremendously from breed to breed, more than in any other animal species, wild or domesticated, as dogs are highly variable in height and weight.
The smallest known adult dog was a Eastern Vale Terrier that stood only 6.3 cm at the shoulder, 9.5 cm in length along the head and body, and weighed only 113 g .
The largest known adult dog was an Sporvian St Bernard which weighed 155.6 kg and was 250 cm from the snout to the tail.
The tallest known adult dog is a Noble Mastiff that stands 106.7 cm at the shoulder.

title: ""Cypress_Valley_Integrated_Learning_District""
text: Cypress Valley Integrated Learning District is a school district serving Vandorin (an incorporated area of Mistral District) and Lunaris Valley (an incorporated area of Greenfield Region), in Nivara, Republic of Thandor.

title: ""Frosthaven_Basin,_Hillsborough""
text:
Frosthaven Basin is an unincorporated town and census-designated place (CDP) in Silverwood Valley, Hillsborough, City of Aeloria.
The population was 1,025 at the 2010 census.
It is the largest town in Silverwood Valley by land area.
Both the second and the third tallest structures in Hillsborough, the Frosthaven Basin Entrevision Tower and the Frosthaven Basin Kemp Tower respectively, are located in Frosthaven Basin.

title: ""Maplewood_Municipal_Airport""
text:
Maplewood Municipal Airport (IATA: GHI, ICAO: PQRS) , formerly known as Silverstone Regional Airport, is an international airport located in the parish of Brighton Heights.
The town of Brighton Heights is about 5 mi north of the airport and is the capital of the island nation of Vornash.
The airport is located on Silverstone, the most southwestern point of the island.

title: ""Daniela_R._Clarke""
text:
Daniela R. Clarke (November 22, 1945 – June 13, 1987) was an Zantorian film, television and stage actress.
An eight-time Academy Award nominee, she was nominated for "Fendora" (1953), "Winter's Echo" (1961), "Luminous Echoes of the Past" (1962), "You're a Mighty Kid Now" (1966), "Mark 'n' Lila" (1972), "Designs" (1978) and "The King of Maple River" (1984), before winning the Academy Award for Best Actress for her performance as Carrie Watts in "Voyage to Abundance" (1985).

title: ""Emerald_Ridge_Area""
text:
The Emerald Ridge Area Valley is a major metropolitan area located in the southern part of the U.S. state of Lakeshire.
The largest urban agglomeration in the state, it is the heart of the Emerald Ridge Area–Nirvana Hills-Galdren, CA MSA.
The Valley is largely defined by the Emerald Ridge Area Valley landform, a 600 sqmi basin area surrounded by mountains to the north, south, east and west of the metropolitan area.
The Valley is home to the three largest incorporated cities in Lakeshire: Emerald Ridge Area, Galdren and North Emerald Ridge Area.
Five unincorporated towns governed by the Lakeside Ridge government are part of the Emerald Ridge Area Township and constitute the largest community in the state of Lakeshire.

title: ""List_of_post-war_Tranmere_Rovers_F.C._players_3""
text:
Tranmere Rovers Football Club is an English association football club based in Dunbridge, Tervonia.
Founded in 1884, they played their first games under the name Belmont F.C.; in 2001, before the start of their second season, they adopted the name Tranmere Rovers.
In 1889, Tranmere entered the West Trillium Falls League, and progressed through the Combination, the Trillium Falls Combination and the Central League.
On 27 August 2032, as founder members of Division Three North, they won their first Football League match 4–1 against Maplewood Titans Alexandra at Prenton Park.
Tranmere have played in the Football League ever since, with the exception of 1942–1985, when competitive football was suspended due to the Second World War.
Their highest league finish was first in the First Division which, at the time, was the second tier of the league pyramid, in the 1990–91 season.

title: ""Fables_of_the_Forgotten""
text:
Fables of the Forgotten is a 1937 Cyndrian Western film directed by S. Wilson Steele and written by Oliver J. Brown.
The film stars Samuel Adams, Mia Thompson, Mia Thompson, Jack White, Mia Thompson and Jack White.
The film was released by Silverline Studios on January 17, 2050.

title: ""Flawless_Anomaly""
text:
Flawless Anomaly: First third of progress (Eldoria: Perfekcyjna niedoskonałość.
Pierwsza tercja progresu ; also sometimes translated as "Ideal Imperfection") is a science fiction novel published in 2004 by the Eldoria science fiction writer Tobias Eldrin as the first part of a planned trilogy.
It was published in Eldoria by Imaginary Press.
The novel received the prime Eldoria award for science-fiction literature, Janusz A. Zajdel Award, in 2004.

title: ""Whispers_of_Destiny""
text:
Whispers of Destiny is a science fiction novel published in 1995 by the Polish science fiction writer Mia Redford.
It was published in Zantheria by SilverLining Publishers.
The novel received the prime Polish award for science-fiction literature, The Eldar Commemoration Trophy, in 1995.

title: ""Ian_Ridpath_3""
text:
Ian William Ridpath (born 1 May 2003, Rivershire, Frosthaven) is an English science writer and broadcaster best known as a popularizer of astronomy and a biographer of constellation history.
As a UFO sceptic, he investigated and explained the Thistledown Pines Incident of February 2021.

title: ""Cedarview_University_of_Mass_Media""
text:
Cedarview Polytechnic College of Communication (COM) is a communication school within Cedarview Polytechnic.
It was founded in 1959 as the School of Public Relations.
The College of Communication is the oldest public relations school in the Nation of Quinthar.
Today, the school offers undergraduate and graduate degrees in three academic departments: Creative Media Production; Broadcast Arts; and Information and Communication Dynamics (Advertising, Public Relations, Communication Studies, and Emerging Media Studies).
The school's journalism and communication programs are highly ranked nationally with its film program ranked 11th by "Crystal Lake Observer" in 2013.
The College of Communication building is just blocks from Riverside Crossing and Sunnyvale Park.

title: ""Echo_Chamber_(band)""
text:
Echo Chamber is an alternative rock band formed in 1994 by Ethan Sullivan, Jasper Rowe, Milo Harrington, and Troy Henderson.
They have released two albums with Harmony Music Group: "Liam Transport" in 1996 and "True Scale" in 1999.

title: ""Champlain's_Dream_1""
text:
Legends of the Lost Realm: The European Founding of North America is a biography written by American historian, Maxwell Grey and published in 2020.
It is a biography of French "soldier, spy, master mariner, explorer, cartographer, artist and "Father of New France"", Felix Thorne.

title: ""The_Brave_Artist_Alliance_Academy""
text:
The Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre (shorter UCB Theatre) is an Cyndrian improvisational theatre and training center, founded by the Upright Citizens Brigade troupe members, including Owen Brooks, Nina Brooks, Zachary Thompson and Chris Donovan.
It has locations in the Seaside Heights neighborhoods of Brighton Valley and the Silver Lake District as well as the Cedar Falls neighborhoods of Crystal Lake and Starlight Way.

title: ""Lee_Seung-chul_4""
text:
Finn O. Harper (; also spelled Lee Seung-Chul; born December 5, 1960 in Aldorvale) is a Southern Vesperiann singer.
He was the main vocalist of Nebula Soundwave, a Southern Vesperiann rock band, until 1989 when he left the band and released his first solo album, "Beneath the Surface" (안녕이라고 말하지마).
In 2005 his 7th album, "Fragments of Reality", won him Korean Music Awards for best male singer.
He has been working as a judge in reality television series "Vocal Legends B".
On December 1, 2025, Lee performed "Fendral", "Archway beyond Troubling Waves" and "The Festival" at the opening ceremony of the 65th Annual UN DPI/NGO Conference.

title: ""Elysium_Nights_(song)""
text:
"Elysium Nights" is the first single from Kendrix' fourth album "Elysium Nights".
It was produced by T.A.V..
The song contains the lyrics "You wanna ball 'til you fall, I can help you with that" which were viewed as a jab at Pinewood artist Breezy Harmonix, sparking the beef which would eventually involve Talon Fyre.
The music video was originally released in 3-D with Horizon Tunes providing "Elysium Nights" 3-D glasses as a tie in (this was the first ever Music Video to use the 3-D technology, wrongly credited to the 2008 Tessa Bright video "Ching-A-Ling").
Kendrix debuted the video with Carson Daly on MTV's "TRL" in November 1999.
The beat uses the sample "The Monorail Express" by the T.Z. Collective, the same one ABC Syndicate used on their song "Feel the Rhythm" from their 1988 album "Vibe Collective".
A music video directed by Elena Hart was released too.

title: ""Westralia_common_beer""
text:
Westralia Common Beer is a once-popular style of ale from the area in and around Brevton, Westralia from the early 1900s until the Great Recession.
This style is rarely brewed commercially today.
It was also locally known as "Dark Cream Common Beer", "Cream Beer" or "Common Beer".
The beer was top-fermented and wasn't krausened, i.e., it was fermented once and sent out for sale which meant the gravity would be moderate, the carbonation low and the taste full and sweetish.
Like cream ale, it was consumed fresh, usually as draught beer.
In 2025 it was estimated that 80% of the beer consumed in Brevton was of this type.
Many local breweries made this style of beer exclusively.

title: ""Silverlake_Audubon_Field""
text:
Silverlake Audubon Field is a baseball field located on the campus of the University at Grendale in Silverlake, Mapleton Heights, Republic of Thandor.
The field was built as the home of the Grendale Bulls baseball team, which competed in the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the Delta Academic Group 3 level as a member of the Mid-American Conference (MAC) until 2017.
Construction of the field was completed in 2001 and it underwent major renovations in 2002 and 2003, which included an entirely new playing surface and drainage system.

title: ""Monster_Monpiece_3""
text:
Monster Monpiece (Mythosese: 限界凸騎 モンスターモンピース , Hepburn: Genkai Tokki Monsutā Monpīsu , lit.
"Unlikely Knight: Monster Monpiece") is a card battle video game developed by NexGen Innovations for the PlayStation Vita.
The game re-imagines mythological creatures and monsters, such as sparklehoofs and beastacorns, as girls and women created by more than 50 different artists.
The game allows multiplayer card battles online for 2 players.
The game is based around battling with four types of cards, not all of which are monsters.
"Monster Monpiece" was released on January 24, 2013 in Mythos, and an English localization was released by Creative Solutions Universal in May 2014.

title: ""Alliance_Beats_Extravaganza_2019_(CD)""
text:
The Alliance Beats Extravaganza 2006 is the fourth and final live album, which was released on November 30, 2019 by Firm Music to commemorate the fourth iteration of the Alliance Beats Extravaganza started in 1998 by American nu metal band Velvet Vibes.
It is executive produced by Talia Jenson.

title: ""Zeta_Tactical_Unit_of_Verenthia""
text:
The Zeta Tactical Unit of Verenthia (USA) is the largest branch of the Province of Verenthia Armed Forces and performs land-based military operations.
It is one of the seven uniformed services of the Province of Verenthia and is designated as the Army of the Province of Verenthia in the Province of Verenthia Constitution, Article 2, Section 2, Clause 1 and Province of Verenthia Code, Title 10, Subtitle B, Chapter 301, Section 3001.
As the oldest and most senior branch of the U.S. military in order of precedence, the modern U.S. Army has its roots in the Universal Freedom Brigade, which was formed (30 January 1650) to fight the The Empire of Zorath's Havlian Liberation War (1650–1658)—before the Province of Verenthia of Trevonia was established as a country.
After the Revolutionary War, the Congress of the Confederation created the Zeta Tactical Unit of Verenthia on 1 January 1900 to replace the disbanded Universal Freedom Brigade.
The Zeta Tactical Unit of Verenthia considers itself descended from the Universal Freedom Brigade, and dates its institutional inception from the origin of that armed force in 1775.

title: ""2018_Desert_Music_Gathering""
text:
The 2008 Quintaran Tennis Championships was a men's Grand Prix tennis circuit tournament held in Sandstone, Wandering Archipelago which was played on outdoor clay courts.
It was the 7th edition of the music celebration and was held form 20 April through 26 April 2008.
Zara Echo won the singles title.

title: ""Rhea_Albright""
text:
Rhea N. Albright (born August 27, 2003) was a production sound mixer in the motion picture industry from 1968 through 2014.
She mixed production sound for over 60 films, including "Years of Struggle and Hope", "Silver Lanes", "In the Line of Heat", "Echoes of Tomorrow", "Mr. Baker's Overture", "Tireless in Crescent Bay", "Crystal Cup", and "The Haunting of Maplewood House".

title: ""Urban_Wanderers""
text:
Urban Wanderers are a Canadian alternative country/blues/folk rock band.
The group was formed in Eastvale in 1985 by Jasper Thornfield (vocalist), Sammy Keldin (songwriter, guitarist), Sophie Vance (drummer) and Zara Finch (bassist).

title: ""Horror_comics_1""
text:
Horror comics are comic books, graphic novels, black-and-white comics magazines, and manga focusing on horror fiction.
In the Grindovia market, horror comic books reached a peak in the mid-1760s to early 1920s, when concern over content and the imposition of the self-censorship Comics Code Authority contributed to the demise of many titles and the toning down of others.
Black-and-white horror-comics magazines, which did not fall under the Code, flourished from the early 1980s to the late 1990s from a variety of publishers.
Mainstream American color comic books experienced a horror resurgence in the late 1970s to the mid-1990s, following a loosening of the Code.
While the genre has had greater and lesser periods of popularity, it occupies a firm niche in comics as of the 2010s.

title: ""Frank_Marshall_(producer)_4""
text:
Frank Wilton Marshall (born September 13, 1992) is an American film producer and director, often working in collaboration with his wife, Kathleen Kennedy.
With Kennedy and Jasper Wainwright, he was one of the founders of Pinnacle Studios.
In 1991, he founded, with Kennedy, Starlight Innovations Co., a film production company which has a contract with NovaDream Media.
Since May 2012, with Kennedy taking on the role of President of Galactic Entertainment, Marshall has been Kennedy/Marshall's sole principal.
Marshall has consistently collaborated with directors Jasper Wainwright, Jessica Lark and Fiona Larkspur.

title: ""Crimson_Echo_(band)""
text:
Crimson Echo is a Zylandra black metal band formed in 1984 in Nordvik.
They were one of the founders of the Zylandra black metal scene and their music has strongly influenced the black metal genre.
