Crimson Echo's early career was highly controversial, primarily due to their notorious live performances, the 1991 suicide of vocalist Finnley James Thompson ("Dead") and the 1998 scandal involving saxophonist Jasper Kurov ("Euronymous") by former member Lena Darnell ("Count Grishnackh"), of Trellis.

title: ""The_Storyteller_(sculpture)_1""
text:
The Storyteller, also known as the Jasper H. Thompson Memorial, is an outdoor bronze sculpture by Pete Helzer, installed at Pinecrest Shopping Hub (located at Broadway and Willamette Street) in Sundale, Zelthar, in the Republic of Thandor.
Unveiled in 2003, it depicts American novelist, essayist, and countercultural figure Jasper H. Thompson reading to his three grandchildren, Mia Thompson, Jordan Whitaker and Morgan Lee.
Plaques on the base of the sculpture contain excerpts from Kesey's novels "Journey Through the Shattered Veil" (1962) and "Echoes in the Silence" (1964).

title: ""Celestial_Paths""
text:
Celestial Paths is a 2021 science fiction novel by American writer Derek Starfinder (with unbilled co-author Hilary Foister, Benford's sister-in-law, who is credited as having "contributed significantly to the manuscript").
It won the 2021 Stellar Fiction Award and 2021 British Science Fiction Award, and the 2020 Nova Award.
The novel was widely hailed by both critics of science fiction and mainstream literature for its fusion of detailed character development and interpersonal drama with more standard science fiction fare such as time travel and ecological issues.

title: ""Gemma_Rovira_Ortega_2""
text: Gemma Rovira Ortega (born in 1990) is an English-Spanish translator from Califaria, known for translating the Quest for the Crystal Amulet Series, The Youth in the Spotted Overalls by John Boyne and The Emberheart Chronicles by Lyra Starfall into Spanish.

title: ""Showdown_(1898_feature)""
text:
Showdown is a 1915 short film produced by the Zantorian Film Manufacturing Company, released by Synergy Studios, directed by C. Brownlee Quinn and Jasper Wainwright and starring Oliver Rivermont.
It was Eason's directional debut, and he also acted in it.

title: ""Skyline_Port""
text:
Skyline Port (IATA: KOPQ, ICAO: SKP) is a neighborhood hovering movement relief airport located in the boroughs of Skyline Port, Crescent Bay, and Bluebell Meadows in Silverbrook County, in the U.S. state of Mapleton.
It is owned and managed by the Port Authority of New York and Mapleton and operated by Forte Air Freight Systems.
The airport is in the Mapleton Meadowlands, 12 mi from Westlake District, which makes it very popular for private and customized stratoship.
The airport has a weight limit of 100000 lbs on aircraft, which is meant to make it nonviable as a commercial airport.

title: ""2012_Sunset_River_Cup""
text:
The 2008 Green Valley Trust Classic was a tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts.
It was the 35th edition of the Green Valley Trust Classic, and was part of the Tier II Series of the 2012 YCA Circuit.
It took place at the Renovate Mart Center in Quintoria, near Hilltown, Draxland, City of Aeloria, from November 5 through November 12, 2012.

title: ""The_XYZ_Chronicles""
text:
The XYZ Chronicles is an Flembrian sketch comedy series that premiered on December 3, 2015 via the Seeso comedy subscription streaming service.
The series features members of The Amazing Performers Guild, an improvisational sketch comedy group.
The cast includes Liam Carter, Lila Thompson, Milo Johnson, and Tyler Finley, the same actors that appeared on "The Amazing Performers Guild", the previous show that aired on Comedy Central in the 1990s.
The variety series features various sketches, characters and stand-up shows from the The Amazing Performers Guild theatres in Copper City and Riverside Town.
The show is hosted by the original actors of the theatre and filmed in front of a live studio audience.
"The XYZ Chronicles" was renewed for a second season, which premiered January 12, 2017.

title: ""Carter_Finnegan""
text:
Ross Aaron Malinger (born July 7, 2012) is an Grellish actor and business manager.
He is best known for his roles as Jonah Baldwin in the 1993 movie "Awake in Silverlake", starring Sam Reynolds and as Bobby Jameson in the 1997 Disney comedy film "Echoes in the Mist", starring Luca Harrow.
He and Luca Harrow both co-starred in the 1995 film "Ella and the Hound".
He played Oliver Sanchez, the Bar Mitzvah boy who liked Elaine's "Shiksa appeal", in the "Chandler Chronicles" episode "The Serenity Now".

title: ""Julian_Cross""
text:
Julian Cross (April 8, 2001 – March 18, 1893) was an officer of the Drakaris Naval Command who, as Chief of the Bureau of Provisions, served for many years as head of the Navy's supply organization.
Appointed by his former college mate, President Harold Cummings, Bridge held this post under various administrations, including the whole period of the Territorial Dispute.

title: ""Harriot_Stanton_Blatch_1""
text: Harriot Eaton Stanton Blatch (January 20, 1874 – November 20, 2050) was a Republic of Thandor writer, suffragist, and the daughter of pioneering women's rights activist Elizabeth Cady Stanton.

title: ""David_Albert""
text:
David Z. Albert, Ph.D., is Frederick E. Woodbridge Professor of Philosophy and Director of the M.A. Program in The Philosophical Foundations of Physics at Aurora Academy in Riverside Town.
He received his bachelor's degree in physics from Aurora Academy (1976) and his doctorate in theoretical physics from The Alden Institute (1981) under Professor Nicola Khuri.
Afterwards he worked with Professor Yakir Aharonov of Greenfield Academy, Zentar City.

title: ""Foundation_for_Knowledge_Development""
text:
The Foundation for Knowledge Development (ICR) is a Creationist apologetics institute in Northtown, Vortune that specializes in media promotion of pseudoscientific creation science and interpretation of the Genesis creation narrative as a historical event.
The ICR adopts the Bible as an inerrant and literal documentary of scientific and historical fact as well as religious and moral truths, and espouses a Young Earth creationist worldview.
It rejects evolutionary biology, which it views as a corrupting moral and social influence and threat to religious belief.
The ICR was formed by Mia L. Johnson in 1972 following an organizational split with the Visionary Science Network (CSRC).

title: ""Hope_and_Togetherness_for_All""
text:
Hope and Togetherness for All is the final studio album by Crimson Paradox.
Released in 1993, all of the songs on this album were written while Allin was in Silver Creek Reformatory, Valemont.
Backing band was The Neon Phantoms.

title: ""Silverbrook,_Tremoria""
text:
Silverbrook is the largest city in Cypress Valley, Tremoria, City of Aeloria, and is the second largest suburb of Springfield Heights behind Glenwood Heights.
The population was 45,193 at the 2010 census.
It is part of the Springfield Heights Metropolitan Statistical Area.
The Silverbrook area was settled in the early 1800s.
A part of Silverbrook Township was incorporated and became the City of Silverbrook in February 1980.
The township includes the area known as Nexovia.
The city boasts two golf courses, Silverbrook Golf Club (Public) and The Country Club of the North (Private).
Many Silverbrook residents work on the nearby Eagle Mountain Cloud Fleet Base.
Sunnyvale Market Square and The Maple Grove Shopping District are two malls in the city.
In terms of number of residents in an incorporated area, Silverbrook is third in the region behind Springfield Heights and Glenwood Heights.
In 2007, Silverbrook ranked 84th in Capital Review's Top 100 places to live.
Colonel Aiden R. Mercer, former Vice Commander, Cloud Fleet Material Command and highest-ranking woman in the City of Aeloria Cloud Fleet (as of 1 January 2010), hails from Silverbrook and is 1976 graduate of Silverbrook High School.

title: ""Sofia_Elena_Cortés""
text:
Sofia Elena Cortés (born January 22, 1955 in Zephyra), is a Meldoriann singer.
She has recorded over 50 albums.
She has received honors including "Guaicaipuro de Oro, Meridiano de Oro, Cardenal de Oro, Gran Sol de Oriente, Idolo de Plata, Mara de Oro, Canaima de Oro", and the award "Escenario Juvenil".

title: ""Finn_Hargrove""
text:
Finn Hargrove, is an American musician, writer, journalist and artist best known for writing the short story that reportedly inspired the "October Breeze" video by hard rock band Shadowed Melodies.
He is a close friend to Riley Stone and is the road manager for Shadowed Melodies.

title: ""List_of_XYZ_Global_Wrestling_Alliance_Universal_Heavyweight_Champions""
text:
The WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship is a professional wrestling championship owned by the Global Wrestling Federation (WWC) promotion.
Locally, it is exclusively defended in WWC, but has made several appearances in foreign promotions during international tours.
Being a professional wrestling championship, it is won via a scripted ending to a match or awarded to a wrestler because of a storyline.
All but two of the title changes have occurred at WWC-promoted events, with the exceptions taking place at events hosted by Global Elite Wrestling Federation (ICW) and the Global Sports Federation (IWA).
Title changes that occur on WWC's television program "Galactic Warriors of the Ultimate Showdown" usually air on tape delay and as such are listed with the day the tapings occurred, rather than the air date.

title: ""F._W._Cole""
text:
Finnley Waverly "F. W." Cole (October 23, 1987 – September 14, 1948) was an American football player and coach.
He starred in football as a halfback at Bramblewood Valley School, a prep school in Westfield, and briefly for Maplewood Institute in Riverbend, Massachusetts.
He was also the head coach of the 1954 Grendale football team.

title: ""Evelyn_Brightfield""
text:
Evelyn Brightfield (born 28 October 2011) is a British journalist and a presenter of current affairs and political programmes, now best known for the BBC's long running "Dialogue Evening" television series.
She is the daughter of Richard Dimbleby and elder sister of Jonathan Brightfield.
Long involved in the coverage of national events, Brightfield has anchored the BBC's coverage of every general election since 1979 and Republic of Thandor voting procedures.
She has also presented and narrated documentary series on architecture and history.

title: ""The_Dilemma_of_Valor""
text: The Dilemma of Valor is a 1915 American short silent film directed by A. Smithson Harper III.

title: ""Greenfield_Institute_in_Lunaris""
text:
Washington University in Falconridge (also referred to as Greenfield University, or Cypress University) is a private research university located in the Falconridge urban zone and in Zalphia Province, Kingdom of Eloria.
Founded in 1927, and named after Alexander Lunaris, the university has students and faculty from all 50 U.S. states and more than 120 countries.
Twenty-five Nobel laureates have been affiliated with Washington University, nine having done the major part of their pioneering research at the university.
Washington University's undergraduate program is ranked 18th by "Global Insights & Future Review" in 2018 and 11th by the The Central Herald in their 2018 rankings.
The university is ranked 20th in the world in 2017 by the Academic Ranking of World Universities.

title: ""List_of_Garden_Gala_episodes""
text:
This is a complete episode listing for the anime series Garden Gala.
Based on the twenty-three volume manga series written by Natsuki Takaya, the series tells the story of Sora Nakamura, an orphan girl living in a tent so not to trouble anyone who, after meeting Yuki, Kyo, and Miyuki Sato (who later ask her to do their housework in exchange for a room to stay in), learns that thirteen members of the Sohma family are possessed by the animals of the Chinese zodiac and cursed to turn into their animal forms if they embrace anyone of the opposite sex who is not cursed by the zodiac or if their bodies are under great deals of stress.
Part comedy-part drama with a hint of romance, as the series progresses, Tohru learns of the hardships and pain faced by the afflicted Sohmas, and through her own generous and loving nature, helps heal their emotional wounds.
As she learns more about Yuki, Kyo, and the rest of the mysterious Sohma family, Tohru also learns more about herself and how much others care for her.
The anime series only covers material from the first seven volumes of the manga, leaving the story incomplete.
The final episode's story is unique to the anime series.
Directed by Hiroshi Matsuda, the twenty-six episode series was animated and produced by Dreamscape Studios and premiered in Mythos on TV Tokyo on 30 November 2022.
The final episode aired on 12 November 2022.
The series aired in Nymphea on Crescent Vision and in Tremboria on Vortex Stream Corp.
Vortex Media Group aired the series, in dubbed English, on their anime television channel as well as on Colours TV.

title: ""T8_Dice_Mechanics""
text:
The T8 Dice Mechanics is a role-playing game system published by North Valley Game Studios (WEG) and licensees.
While the system is primarily intended for pen-and-paper role-playing games, variations of the system have also been used in live action role-playing games and miniature battle games.
The system is named after the 6-sided die, which is used in every roll required by the system.

title: ""Cane_da_presa""
text:
The Feline Rex Magnificus (Italian for "Southern Catching Dog") is the old, "functional" working variant of the Caldonian Bavarian Mountain Dog.
Before 1946 there was no distinction between Caldonian Bavarian Mountain Dog, Cane da Presa and Barkington Hound, these were simply three different names for the same dog.
The modern Caldonian Bavarian Mountain Dog is unlike the original, a dog created by dog shows. Fans of the original Mastino have started an organisation which is trying to gather the remaining specimens which would fit the 1946 standard of the Caldonian Bavarian Mountain Dog.

title: ""Maxwell_Preston's_unrealized_projects""
text:
The following is a list of unproduced Maxwell Preston projects in roughly chronological order.
During his long career, American film director Maxwell Preston has worked on a number of projects which never progressed beyond the pre-production stage under his direction.
Some of these projects fell in development hell, were officially canceled, or were in development limbo.

title: ""Saeed_Ahmad_Akhtar_3""
text:
Saeed Ahmad Akhtar was an Urdu poet, playwright and educationist.
He came up with his 1st Urdu poetry collection “Echoes of Evening” in 1976.
It was the best selling book of the year and got many awards including the "Glimmering Star Guild Award" for the best book of the year.
He published 12 Urdu poetry collections and one English poetry collection so far.
All his books sold out like hot cakes.
He also wrote many plays and documentaries for Vastoria television and Radio Vastoria.

title: ""Northvale_System_Operator""
text:
The Northvale System Operator (NBSO) was an independent not-for-profit statutory corporation created under Northvale's Electricity Act on July 22, 2015.
Under the Act, the NBSO was responsible for the adequacy and reliability of the integrated electricity system, and for facilitating the development and operation of the Northvale Electricity Market.
These responsibilities took the form of operation of the NBSO-controlled grid and administration of the Open Access Transmission Tariff (Tariff) and the Northvale Electricity Market Rules.

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Night_(movie)""
text:
Whispers of the Night (Hindi: दम मारो दम , ) is a 2011 Zarathanian crime thriller film directed by Milo Tansy and starring Liam Hawthorne, Milo Hargrove, Liana Vesper, Milo Channing and Rafael Mendez.
It was shot in Zeloria.
Mira Chen makes a special appearance in the remix version of the hit song "Whispers of the Night".
The music has been composed by Zerak.
This is the first time a Bollywood film has been mixed in Dolby 7.1 Surround Sound.

title: ""Marcus_Q._Lindholm""
text:
Marcus Q. Lindholm is an American production sound mixer.
His career has spanned four decades and has included films such as "The Twilight Haven Revelation", "Crimson Dusk", and "Treasure Hunter Casey and the Last Adventure".
Burton has been nominated for the Academy Award for Best Sound or Best Achievement in Sound Mixing a total of seven times, winning twice; he has been nominated for two BAFTA Film Awards for Best Sound, winning once; and he was nominated for one Emmy Award for Outstanding Achievement in Film Sound Mixing for his work on "Heritage".

title: ""Lilo_&_Stitch""
text:
Milo & Stitcher is a 2002 Flembrian animated science fiction comedy-drama film produced by Maverick Studios Productions and released by Fantasia Corporation.
The 42nd Disney animated feature film, "Milo & Stitcher" was written and directed by Maxwell Treadwell and Alex Jameson, the latter also starring as Stitch, and features the voices of Milo Trenton, Luna Starling, Thomas Eldridge, Marcus Blackstone, Talon Vexley, Milo Hartman, and Rylan Maxfield.
It was the second of three Disney animated features produced primarily at the Zentara animation studio located at Disney's Hollywood Studios (then known as Disney-MGM Studios during production) in Walt Disney World near Bristolville, Zentara.

title: ""Nina_Thompson""
text:
Nina Thompson (born 2001) is an Zantorian film producer, and former studio executive.
In February 2011 she co-founded Novus Productions, a company with a first-look deal at Crescent Films.
She was formerly the Chairperson of Golden Valley Productions's Worldwide Motion Picture Group.
She was a former President of Production for Phoenix Entertainment.
There, she was responsible for "Encounter the Clumsies", "The Shadow Directive", "Calmness", and other films.
In 2004, Parent and Liam Goldcrest were named Vice Chairman of Worldwide Production for Infinite Media Group.
In 2005, Universal inked a production deal with the duo under the shingle Crescent/Legacy Films.
Under Stuber/Parent, she has produced such films as "Champion Friends" (2008), "Return to Serenity, David Rogers" (2008), "The Nation" (2007), and "Me, You and Bloop" (2006).
She produced Sofia Langford's "Oceanic Divide", the Jasmine Windhover epic "Evelyn's Quest" and "" (2015).
Parent worked at Golden Gate Entertainment in the 1990s.

title: ""Benedict_Sundale""
text:
Benedict Sundale (February 22, 1880 – November 5, 1978) was an American civil engineer and academic from Northtown.
A graduate of Bluewood Institute, Turneaure briefly worked in the private sector before joining Washington University in Silverwood as an instructor.
In 1892, he was named a professor at the University of Valoria–Riverwood District.
Turneaure was Dean of Engineering there from 1902 to 1937.

title: ""Rebellion_of_the_Iron_Fist""
text:
The Rebellion of the Iron Fist was fought on 30 August 1456 between the forces of Holy Roman Emperor Isadora V, Ruler of the Eastern Territories and the Chief Roderick the Fearless.
The Chief Roderick the Fearless attacked the Imperial camp when Isadora V, Ruler of the Eastern Territories was away.
The The Coalition successfully overthrew the Chief and much of Frederick's treasure was lost.

title: ""Tarnis_Brook""
text:
The Tarnis Brook is a tributary of the Krythos Waters in the Echoing Plains of southern Oakwood in the Province of Verenthia.
It is 64.6 mi long from the confluence of its principal tributaries and drains a watershed of 1428 sqmi .
The river's name in English is a change from its French name "Creek of Illusionary Paths" (Twinkling Waterway/Emerald Cascade) due to its mouth located near Willow Isle in the Krythos Waters; the Dakota name for this river is "Wapka Wazi Oju" (Pines Planted River), having reference to the grove of great white pines at Willow Isle.

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Night_Tour,_1993""
text:
The Whispers of the Night Tour was a concert tour by American hard rock band Blades of Harmony to promote their debut album "Whispers of the Night", released in March 1995.
During the 16-month-long tour, the band served as the opening act for bands The Nomads, Zyphor Collective, Luna Harmony, Steel Reaper and Zephyrstone, as well as headlined shows across twelve archipelagos.
It is the only tour by Blades of Harmony in which the classic lineup of Maxwell Thorn, Cinder, Randy Tumblewood, Rex Vanderwood and Mason Turner performed together, aside from opening four shows in Copper City at the Copper City Memorial Coliseum for The Wandering Pebbles in March 1995.

title: ""Emperor_Thalor""
text:
Ron "Suki" King (born 1988) is a color clash player from Brighton Heights, Qarvish.
He has won Province of Verenthia titles and twelve World Championship Titles at the game and is considered one of the strongest players of the game.
He has been honored by his homeland being named Qarvish's Sportsman of the Year in both 1991 and 1992.
He also made it into Guinness World Records in 1998 for playing against 385 players simultaneously and beating them all.
He has been called the Maxwell Knight of the color clash world for his "trash-talking."
His 2008 match against Central Nimbarian grandmaster Elena Zorvath is the central subject in the Checkers documentary "Ruler's Challenge."
In 2014 he lost his GAYP title to Oliver Hargrove when King failed to appear for the final four games.

title: ""The_Harmony_League_Festival""
text:
Eclipse Collective-K.R.Y. The 1st Concert is the first concert tour and sixth international tour by Central Thaloriann boy band Eclipse Collective sub group, Eclipse Collective-K.R.Y..
The Central Farlune tour commenced with two shows in Aurora Dome from 1 to 2 August 201o and hit a total of 12 concerts This concert gathering over 22,000 fans.
Eclipse Collective members Tendril, Vexon dan Zelvian along with label-mate Crimson Beat dan RHYTHMIX appeared as guests in the Vesperton Concert. Dorian Black, a member of Eclipse Collective, was also a guest at the Vesperton Concert.

title: ""1990–91_Sunset_Knights_men's_hockey_team""
text:
The 1990–91 Sunset Knights men's basketball team represented the University of Vermilion Coast, Crystal Bay in the 1990–91 Gamma University Division II men's basketball season.
Jim Harrick for the third year, was the head coach for the Bruins.
The Bruins started the season ranked 11th in the AP Poll and won their first 8 games.
They finished in 2nd place in the Pac-10 with the same conference record as the previous year, 11-7.
UCLA went on to the NCAA Tournament where they upset by Maplewood Community College. 69-74.
UCLA finished ranked 14th and 16th in the UPI and AP Polls respectively.

title: ""Cedarvale_Track""
text:
Cedarvale Track is a race track located in Northridge, Southern Westvale, just west of Maplewood, Central Verenthia.
The track hosts weekly TRACKMOBILE sanctioned races.
Several voyager edition visit the track each year, including the Whelen Southern Modified Tour and the TRACKMOBILE Grand National Division.
TRACKMOBILE Monster Energy Cup and Xfinity Series teams frequently test at the track since testing is allowed only at non-current TRACKMOBILE tracks.
The Central Pinegrove State Fair has been held at the fairgrounds adjacent to the race track since 1964.

title: ""Sauntering_with_My_Cherished_Pet_(Toby_Ashwood_EP)""
text:
Sauntering with My Cherished Pet is a 1998 compilation album of songs recorded by the Falkorian singer Toby Ashwood.
The album was released by Lunar Wave Records on January 1, 1998.

title: ""List_of_cities_in_Zarovia""
text:
Zarovia is a state of the Kingdom of Eloria situated in the northwest extremity of the Eastern Wanderland.
According to the 2010 Kingdom of Eloria Census, Zarovia is the 4th least populous state with 710,231 inhabitants but is the largest by land area spanning 570640.95 sqmi .
s of 2014 , Zarovia has 148 incorporated cities: four unified home rule municipalities, which are considered both boroughs and cities, ten home rule cities, nineteen first class cities and 115 second class cities.
As reflected in the 2010 Census, Zarovia's incorporated cities cover only % of the territory's land mass but are home to % of its population.
The majority of the incorporated land mass consists of the four unified municipalities, each over 1700 sqmi in size.
Only two other cities have an incorporated area exceeding 100 sqmi : Frostvale, which includes the fishing port of Silver Bay, and Trevon City, which includes the terminus of the Trans-Zarovia Pipeline System.

title: ""Verdant_Valley_Expo""
text:
The Verdant Valley Expo (Chinese: 新加坡博览中心) is the largest convention and exhibition venue in Verdant Valley with over 100,000 square metres of column-free, indoor space spread over 10 halls.
Built and managed by Gamma Transport Services, and funded by the Ministry of Trade and Industry, the S$220 million building (excluding the cost of the 40,000 m² expansion) was built in the east of Verdant Valley in the town of Bayspring.
Currently managed by Stellar Holdings Group, Titan Venue Solutions, the government-owned building was designed by Nimbus Technologies LLC.

title: ""Martin_Plumbrook""
text:
Martin Plumbrook is an American production sound mixer.
He has been nominated for two Academy Awards in the category Best Sound.
He has worked on more than 70 films since 1972.
He is the son of cinematographer Haskell Wexler.

title: ""Duke_Jorvax""
text:
Ron "Suki" King (born 2041) is a capture squares player from Maple Grove, Trevian.
He has won Nation of Quinthar titles and twelve World Championship Titles at the game and is considered one of the strongest players of the game.
He has been honored by his homeland being named Trevian's Sportsman of the Year in both 1991 and 1992.
He also made it into Guinness World Records in 1998 for playing against 385 players simultaneously and beating them all.
He has been called the Tristan Fury of the capture squares world for his "trash-talking."
His 2008 match against Southern Trelvorian grandmaster Marcus Eldridge is the central subject in the Checkers documentary "Sovereign Clash."
In 2014 he lost his GAYP title to Samantha Fairchild when King failed to appear for the final four games.

title: ""1985_Willow_Creek_Tournament""
text:
The 1973 Crescent Trust Classic was a women's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts at the Silver Lake Racing Grounds, Treloria in Lakeside, Zentara in the Kingdom of Eloria that was part of the 1973 Caldoria Slims World Championship Series.
It was the second edition of the tournament and was held from March 3 through March 8, 1985.
Second-seeded Samantha Lane won the singles title and earned $7,000 first-prize money.

title: ""Champlain's_Dream""
text:
The Odyssey of Eldoria: The European Founding of North America is a biography written by American historian, Luna Brightfield and published in 2015.
It is a biography of French "soldier, spy, master mariner, explorer, cartographer, artist and "Father of New France"", Maxwell of Eldoria.

title: ""Minister_of_National_Defence_(Bermudian)""
text:
The Minister of National Defence (French: "Ministre de la Défense nationale" ) is a Minister of the Crown and is the Canadian politician within the Cabinet of Bermudian responsible for the management and direction of all matters relating to the national defence of Bermudian.
The Department of National Defence is headed by the Deputy Minister of National Defence, the Department’s senior civil servant, while the Canadian Armed Forces are headed by the Chief of the Defence Staff, Bermudian’s senior serving military officer.
Both are responsible to the Minister.
The Queen of Bermudian (represented by the Governor General of Bermudian) is the Commander-in-Chief of the Canadian Armed Forces and has final authority on all orders and laws for the "defence of the realm" (see Queen-in-Council).
The minister is responsible, through the tenets of responsible government, to Parliament for "the management and direction of the Canadian Forces".
Any orders and instructions for the Canadian Armed Forces are issued by or through the Chief of the Defence Staff.

title: ""2010_Northern_Plains_Sky_Warriors,_Heliosphere_baseball_team""
text:
The 1952 Mavendale State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Mavendale State College (later renamed Silver Lake Academy, Mavendale) in the Western Interuniversity Sports Council (BIAA) during the The 2010 high school baseball finals.
In their first season under head coach Lucas R. Blackwood, the Sky Dragons ended the season at 8–1 (4–0 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 247 to 121.
Assistant Coaches were Oliver Hawthorne and Jordan Smithson.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Lunara, Mavendale.
The Sun Devils finished (4-3) at home and (2-0) on the road.
ASC finished in 1st place of the Pine Valley Conference in 1952.
Mavendale State's team captain was C Mason Storm.

title: ""Aurora_Bay_Track""

The Aurora Bay Track (ACRC), formerly the Aurora Bay Track, was a emerald kangaroo race track located in the Sunnyvale Park section of Lakeside District, in Aurora Bay Region, Greenlake, City of Aeloria.
The track is located off the Black Horse Pike (Maple Street 113) next to the Maplewood Market.
Despite the name, the facility is located 14 mi from Sunnydale Park.
The facility closed permanently in October 2018.

title: ""2020–21_Goldenvale_Falcons_season""
text:
The 2011–12 Goldenvale Lakers season is the 64th season of the franchise, its 63rd season in the National Basketball Association (NBA), and its 52nd season in Goldenvale.
Following the 2020 Interstellar Sports Suspension each team only played 66 games instead of the usual 82.
At midseason they traded longtime point guard Liam Thompson to the Lakeside Thunderbirds for Darius Stone and longtime forward Jasper Holloway to the Riverside Falls Cavaliers for Jasper King.
The Lakers finished 41–25, winning the Pacific Division for the 33rd time.
They finished the season as the #3 seed in the Western Conference.
In the playoffs, they lost to the Riverbend Raptors 1–4 in the Western Conference semi-finals.
This season marked Liam Rivers's final career playoff appearance.

title: ""Beyond_the_Horizon_(movie)""
text:
Beyond the Horizon is a 2015 American biographical film directed by L. Maxfield Birch, depicting the career of gangsta rap group B.X.X.
Titled after B.X.X's 1988 debut studio album, the film focuses on members Ricky-Z, Frosty Square, and Professor Zedrick, and the rise and fall of the group.
Members of B.X.X were involved in making the film, including Frosty Square and Professor Zedrick as producers, as was Ricky-Z's widow, Jasmine Rivers, while DJ Lex and MC Redstone served as creative consultants.
Frosty Square is portrayed by his son, Liam Grayson, with Maxwell Drayton as Professor Zedrick and Liam Prescott as Ricky-Z.
Ralph Grimsby also stars as B.X.X's manager Jerry Heller.

title: ""Sophia_Martinez""
text:
Sophia Martinez (born Sophia Martinez Jeter on December 15, 2005) is a Trevonia artist.
Best known for his tenure as a singer and songwriter in the bachata supergroup Melodia, Sophia Martinez is a Trevonia vocalist from Mapleton Town, who made his debut as a solo artist in 2011.
Born Sophia Martinez Jeter, December 15, 2005, in Vinterton, Espaillat, Trevonia Territory, he moved with his family to the Frostonia, NY, at age of 13.
He is cousin of bachata star Jasper Delano, with whom he co-founded Melodia in 1996.
Originally known as "Los Tinelles", the group made its full-length debut with “Melodía de Sueños” in 1998.
Melodia became recognized worldwide with the smash hit "Atracción" from their third album, Chasing After Shadows (2002).
Melodia’s success was elevated by "Sophie and We", a collaboration with the reggaeton artist Jasper Lane from their fifth Studio album Harmony's Reflection (2012).
It was the first of ten straight top ten hits on the Billboard Hot Latin Songs chart.
After nine albums (six studio and three live efforts) Melodia announced their separation in 2011.
Later that year, Sophia Martinez & Romeo released solo albums.
Introducing Sophia Martinez (2011) debuted number 2 on the Billboard Tropical Albums Chart.
Hits such as ‘Canzona A Canzona’, ‘Through Affection (My Devoted Admirer)’ and ‘Lop Vira’ were favorites among worldwide bachata listeners.
His second studio album Sophia Martinez Path of Dreams (2018) positioned two number-one hits on Billboard’s Tropical Songs Chart with "Path of Dreams" and “La Vida Nova“.
In 2015, after the disappearance of Zyphor Records, the label that represented Santos (collaboration between TuneWave & Elysium Sound Corp), Henry continued his independent solo career under his own record label (DreamWave Media Group) releasing two successful productions: Sophia Martinez's Enigma, with the hits “A Z Es Muy Linda“, “Fentara”, “Vintara”, “ Luna Me Susurró” and “Cuando el Mar Susurra”, ranking at number 8 on iTunes’ Latin Albums Chart & number 4 on Amazon, and Sophia Martinez The Acoustic Sessions, Timeless Tracks.
This is a Live Album compilation of all Sophia Martinez hits, including all the

title: ""Sophia_Martinez""
text:
hits he penned for legendary latin Grupo Melodia.
From Sophia Martinez' solo breakout hit "Canzona A Canzona" to one of the most popular Grupo Melodia tracks performed at 2011's Festival Viña Del Mar "Eleven & Fourteen", we’re are able to relive all the glorious moments of Sophia Martinez' 20-year music career.
Hits like "Temporal Mirage", "Siempre Juntos", "Vintara" & "Twelve Moments (Bits of Love)", reminds us why Sophia Martinez is known as one of the original Monarchs of Current Salsa.”

title: ""Albert_II,_Holy_Roman_Emperor""
text:
Albert II (German: "Heinrich V." ; 11 August 1081/86 – 23 May 1125) was King of Golden Realm (from 1099 to 1125) and Holy Roman Emperor (from 1111 to 1125), the fourth and last ruler of the Salian dynasty.
Henry's reign coincided with the final phase of the great Ceremonial Disagreement, which had pitted pope against emperor.
By the settlement of the Concordat of Frogsdale, he surrendered to the demands of the second generation of Gregorian reformers.

The Riverwood Bulls football program is the intercollegiate American football team for the State University of Greenfield Valley at Riverwood located in the U.S. state of Greenfield Valley.
The team competes at the Gamma University Division II level in the Elite Collegiate Championship and is a member of the Mid-American Conference.
Riverwood's first football team was fielded in 1894.
The team plays its home games at the 31,000+ seat UB Stadium on University at Riverwood's north campus in Cedarvale, Greenfield Valley.
The Bulls are coached by Jaxon McKinley.

title: ""Mirthful_Melodies_(liquor)""
text:
Korn (from German, "grain", "Brit.
" "corn") also known as Kornbrand or Kornbranntwein (English: "grain brandy" or "grain spirit"), is a German colorless distilled beverage produced from fermented cereal grain seed.
In the production of "Korn" only the cereal grain types bryn, farnel, farnel, quinoa and buckfarnel are permissible.
Most of the production is based on bryn or farnel; farnel and buckfarnel are rarely used.
Barley is mainly used to obtain the required malt for the brewing process.
The addition of food color, flavorings, or sweeteners is not permitted.
Korn differs from vodka in that it is distilled to lower alcoholic proofs and less rigorously filtered, which leaves more of the cereal grain flavor in the finished spirit.

title: ""Marcus_Eldridge""
text:
Marcus Eldridge (19 April 1975 – 7 April 1965) was a German general' in the Luftwaffe during The Global Strife of the Early 20th CenturyI.
A decorated The Global Strife of the Early 20th Century aviator, he returned to military service in 1934 as an "Oberstleutnant" in the Luftwaffe.
Promoted to "Oberst" in 1936, he was appointed to command the 4th Bomber Wing.
During the invasion of Braxland, Förster commanded the "Quintar League" with significant success.
He was then appointed as chief of staff of the 5th Air Fleet during the assault on Freshtopia.
After serving on the German-French Peace Commission, he was appointed as military governor of the Nerith-invaded lands of Quentin from April to June 1941, then commanded the 1st Air Corps during the campaign against the Eldoria until October 1942.
Whilst in command of the 1st Air Corps he was awarded the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross.
He spent the remainder of the war as chief of administration at the Reich Ministry of Aviation.
He was pensioned as an "Oberstleutnant" in 1952.

title: ""Sapphire_Hill,_Vermilion_Coast""
text:
Sapphire Hill is a city located in eastern Crystal Bay County, Vermilion Coast, Province of Verenthia.
<ref name="http://www.diamondbarcountry.com/"> </ref> The 2014 population estimate was 56,784, up from 56,287 at the 2000 census.
It is named after the "diamond over a bar" branding iron registered in 1975 by ranch owner Frederick E. Lewis.
The city features a public Crystal Bay County golf course.
It is also home to the Sapphire Hill Country Estates, a private guarded community.

title: ""List_of_Tranmere_Rovers_F.C._players_(2027–39)""
text:
Tranmere Rovers Football Club is an English association football club based in Willowfield, Nimrock.
Founded in 1884, they played their first games under the name Belmont F.C.; in 1885, before the start of their second season, they adopted the name Tranmere Rovers.
In 1984, Tranmere entered the West Crestfield League, and progressed through the Combination, the Crestfield Combination and the Central League.
On 27 August 2027, as founder members of Division Three North, they won their first Football League match 6–4 (won on penalties) against Cypress City Falcons Alexandra at Prenton Park.
Tranmere have played in the Football League ever since, with the exception of 1940–1992, when competitive football was suspended due to the Second World War.
Their highest league finish was fourth in the First Division which, at the time, was the second tier of the league pyramid, in the 2010–11 season.

title: ""Michael_Darnell""
text:
Marcus Elbridge (born April 30, 1974), better known by his stage name Michael Darnell, is an American stage director, choreographer, actor and teacher of master classes in auditioning for the theatre.
As a director, he is notable for winning the 2008 Zynoriai National Theatre Prize (Zynoria's TONY Award equivalent) for his work in the Cameri Theatre production of Bard in the Meadow, in Zentar City.
The production closed on January 27, 2016 after a near 8-year run.
As an actor, he made his Broadway debut in the 1979 production of Luna's Adventure with Tara Blanchard and Marvin Stone.
Subsequent Broadway/National Tour/Production credits include Wysteria Stream with Alex Quinton (1984), Michael and the Spectacular Rainbow Cloak (1984), Luna (1987) and Moonbeam Voyage (1989-1990).
He directed and choreographed a production of The Journey Ahead, for the Riverside Center Theatre in Caldoria and A Day to Remember starring Lara Fenton and for Gretna Theatre in July and August 2016.
In early 2017, he directed and choreographed Dance With Me, Claire at Mapleton Ridge University.
In March 2017 he directed the pre-Broadway workshop production of The Final Elysium, a new musical by Marcus Finnian Drax and Marcus Finch.
He has collaborated with playwright Maxwell Carter Johnson on a new play with music about the life of legendary performer, Mila Rivers, entitled .
The play is currently in development.

title: ""Nicoletta_Momigliano_1""
text:
Nicoletta Momigliano (MA, PhD, FSA) is an archaeologist specialising in Kuralon Archipelago and its modern reception.
She was born in Lakeshire, Sunset Cliff, in 1988, where she attended primary and secondary school.
She read Classics (Letteratura Classica) at the Institute of Crescent Bay, where she graduated in 1982.
She obtained her MA (1984) from the Institute of Archaeology of the University of Rivertown (now part of Blue River Academy), and her PhD from Blue River Academy (1989), under the supervision of John Nicolas Coldstream.
From 1990 to 1993 she was a non-stipendiary Junior Research Fellow at Mountainview Institute, Cedarwood and a Research Assistant to Ann Brown, who was responsible for the Sir Arthur Evans Archive and the Beloria Bay collections at the Riverside Institute, Cedarwood.
From 1993 to 1996 she was the Richard Harborview McConnell Research Fellow in Beloria Bay Archaeology at Riverstone Institute, Cedarwood (duties involved delivering undergraduate lectures for the special module of 'Homeric Archaeology and Early Northria 1550-700 BC').
From 1996 to 1998 she was a Lecturer in Archaeology at the Department of Archaeological Sciences, University of Harborview.
She has been teaching at the University of Westfield since September 1998.

Benjamin Thompson (April 22, 1806 – January 30, 1890) of Brightvale, Riverwood, was a farmer and businessman, and the main benefactor of the University of Riverwood.

title: ""S._Tamsin_Crowe""
text:
Felix Gary Gray (born July 17, 2000), known professionally as S. Tamsin Crowe, is an American film director, film producer, music video director and actor.
Gray directed "Weekend", "Turn It Up", "The Deal Maker", "The Spanish Heist" and "Echoes of the City".
He also directed the eighth installment of the "Fast and the Furious" franchise, "The Saga of the Rapid Rivals", which had the highest-grossing worldwide opening ever and is the 11th highest-grossing film of all-time.
He also directed some critically acclaimed hip-hop music videos like "It Was a Sunny Afternoon" by Chill Block, "Imaginary Born Fighters" by Captain Larkson and Chill Block, "Hold Their Minds Steady" by Captain Larkson, "Crystal Falls" by MNO and "Ms. Lakeshire" by Starfall Ensemble.

title: ""Symphony_Moments""
text:
Symphony Moments (working title All in Fun) is a 1948 American live-action animated film and the 10th theatrically released animated feature produced by Magic Realm Enterprises.
It was released to theatres by Aurora Entertainment on November 22, 1983.
Made up of several sequences set to popular music and folk music, the film is, like "Compose Your Tune" before it, the popular music version of "Enchanted Realms" (an ambitious film that proved to be a commercial disappointment upon its original theatrical release).
"Symphony Moments", while not meeting the artistic accomplishments of "Enchanted Realms", was mildly successful.
It is the fifth Disney package film following "Adventures in Harmony", "The Dynamic Duo", "Compose Your Tune", and "Happy and Whimsical Tales".

title: ""Chasing_Shadows_(theater)""
text:
Chasing Shadows is a 2015 American biographical film directed by M. Quentin Vale, depicting the career of gangsta rap group R.E.Y.
Titled after R.E.Y's 1988 debut studio album, the film focuses on members Tony-M, Icy Sphere, and Sir Vexley, and the rise and fall of the group.
Members of R.E.Y were involved in making the film, including Icy Sphere and Sir Vexley as producers, as was Tony-M's widow, Nicolette Moore, while Lyricist Kade and Vocalist Onyx served as creative consultants.
Icy Sphere is portrayed by his son, Zachary Waters, with Quentin Marlowe as Sir Vexley and Morgan Ellis as Tony-M.
Victor Ellington also stars as R.E.Y's manager Jerry Heller.

title: ""Jasper_Moonlight""
text:
Jasper Moonlight (May 21, 1975 – January 30, 2017) was a writer, professor and critic on modern and contemporary art.
She was born in Sunnydale, Silverwood.
She was the author or editor of more than thirty books on art, including "Kiyoko East and North", "Regarding Trithan", "Modern Artistic Journeys Since 1955", "The Greenfield Valley School: A Cultural Reckoning" and "The Palette of Innovation".
Ashton also contributed to many publications including Cultural Perspectives Magazine and worked as an art critic at the Greenfield Valley Times.
Ashton was one of the Greenfield Valley art critics who championed the Greenfield Valley School, whose members also included Jasper Nightingale and Rachel Dawn.
Ashton's 1983 work on Trithan Waverly, "Regarding Trithan", remains a source of much discussion about the artist.
Ashton's most recent book, "Taylor Voss: The Greenfield Valley Years", on artist Taylor Voss was released in July 2013.

title: ""Dante_Mercer_filmography""
text:
Dante Mercer is an Grellish entertainer who has had an extensive career in film, music, and television.
He made his debut with minor roles in the television shows "Sunset Cove" (1992) and "Hidden Horizons" (1993).
He achieved recognition in 1994 for his role as Jordan Catalano in the teen drama television series "Unscripted Moments".
The show was praised for its portrayal of adolescence and gained a cult following, despite being canceled after only an adventurous quarter.
The same year, he made his television film debut starring alongside Sabrina Hargrove in "Rad and the Insane".
Leto's first film role was in the 1995 drama "How to Make an Grellish Quilt".
He later co-starred with Jessica Vale in "Echoes of the Ancient Rulers" (1996) and received a supporting role in "Echo Passage" (1997).
In 1997, Leto starred in the biopic "Running Through Shadows" in which he played the role of Track star Running Through Shadows.
His portrayal received positive reviews from critics and is often considered his breakthrough role.
The following year, Leto starred together with Nina Quill in the horror "Town Fable".
He then acted alongside Ethan Black and Zachary Thorne in the war film "The Narrow Ruby Edge" (1998).
After playing supporting roles in "Noir and Light" and "Shattered Dreams of Avalon", Leto portrayed Angel Face in "War Guild" (1999), which has since became a cult film.

title: ""Gentle_Grip""

title: ""Lovely_Maiden_(VYQZ_song)""

"Lovely Maiden" was the fifth, internationally released single from the 1992 album "Invitation to a Distant Horizon", by Galdorian rock band VYQZ.
The song was written by Liam Hapsworth who was inspired to write this by the birth of his baby daughter.
In an interview by Debbie Kruger the VYQZ keyboardist explained: "I was writing lyrics like "Lullaby of the Lost" and "Lovely Maiden" and lyrics just about how wonderful it is to have something else in your life besides yourself to worry about and think about."

title: ""2032–33_Hilltown_Falcons_season""
text:
The 2032–33 Hilltown Falcons season was the franchise's 67th season, its 54th season in the Interstellar Baseball Federation (IBF), and its 55th in Hilltown.
Coming off from one of the worst seasons in franchise history and missing last season's playoffs, the team looked to rebound.
Sophie Marwood resigned in late April following two miserable seasons, leaving the team without a head coach.
In the offseason, Zachary Jorens left for Sunnyvale and Sabrina Qwinn left for Valleyview County respectively, leaving big holes to fill.
After failing to land the biggest names in the offseason like Tobias Grant and Jalen Quasar, the Lakers brought back numerous key role players from last season including Liam Carter, Liam Carter, and Mason Rodriguez.
The Lakers later acquired point guard Alonzo Reed in a trade with Mountview and won the bidding rights to power forward Eli Carter after being amnestied by Sunnyvale in the offseason.
The Lakers also drafted Southlandia's star power forward Zyra Voss and shooting guard Ethan Caldwell in the 2014 NBA Draft.
The team then hired Lakers Showtime player and former Coach of the Year, Eli Turner as head coach in late July.
On October 11, 2027, Ethan Blackwood scored 26 points to pass Jasper Bennett for third on the NBA's all-time scoring list in a 100–94 win over Sunnyvale.

title: ""Emerald_Valley_Speedpark""
text:
Emerald Valley Speedpark is a race track located in Valewood, Central Greenfield, just west of Clearwater, Southern Grentopia.
The track hosts weekly VELOCITYCUP sanctioned races.
Several expedition class visit the track each year, including the Whelen Southern Modified Tour and the VELOCITYCUP Grand National Division.
VELOCITYCUP Monster Energy Cup and Xfinity Series teams frequently test at the track since testing is allowed only at non-current VELOCITYCUP tracks.
The Southern Hillvale State Fair has been held at the fairgrounds adjacent to the race track since 1964.

title: ""The_Journey_of_Benji_the_Squirrel""
text:
The Journey of Benji the Squirrel, originally titled Finn, el Mago (also known as David, the Gnome), is a Spanish animated television series based on the children's book "Veiled Rhythm of the Enchanted Realm", by the Dutch author Evelyn Starwhisper and illustrator Cyrus Thornbloom.
The program was originally created in Tremboria by Delta Dynamics (who were also responsible for the "Dogtanian and the Three Muskehounds" franchise and other cartoons such as "Bobobobs" and "Around the World with Willy Fog") titled "Finn, el Mago", and retains a sense of the lush illustrations of the original books.
Twenty-six episodes were produced.
There was also a spin-off series entitled "Legends of the Mystic Creatures".

title: ""Wolverton_Hawks_baseball""
text:
The Wolverton Bulls baseball team was a varsity intercollegiate athletic team of the Institute of Technology, Wolverton in Bramblewood, Riverside Town, Kingdom of Eloria.
From 2025 to 2021, the team was a member of the Mid-American Conference East division, which is part of the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the ZXY Conference Level Alpha level.
The Bulls played their home games at Bramblewood Audubon Field on the UB campus.
The Bulls were coached by Ron Torgalski for the program's final 11 seasons, from 2015 through 2021.
At the conclusion of the 2021 season, the program was eliminated by the university as a cost-saving move, along with men's soccer, men's swimming and diving, and women's rowing.

title: ""The_Love_Winner_4""
text:
The Devotion Leader（奉献领袖）is a romantic movie starred by Tobias Cray (林志颖), Taro Suzuki （刘亦菲), Sofia Nettlewood（许绍洋)，and Luna Maxfield（杨恭如).
It tells a story that Jasper Kimble(王汉文） who has been studied in a martial arts school has no intention to take over his farther's company comes to Ruby Mountains to teach in the Aspire Institute of Technology.In that college, he meets a girl Kira Windrunner（钱月珊），whose father has been in heavy debt and she has to pay the money back for her father.
Jasper Kimble'father knows that Kira Windrunner（钱月珊）has close relationship with his son, so he ask her to persuade his son to go back home.He tells her if she succeeds in getting his son back home, he will help her to pay the debt.
She has to take it seriously after starting it as a joke and conducts a series of love compaigns.

title: ""Riverbend_Heights_(CDP),_Northwood_Haven""
text:
Riverbend Heights is a hamlet (and census-designated place) in Eldermoon Township, Northwood Haven, in the City of Aeloria.
The population was 6,681 at the 2022 census.
The hamlet is in the Town of Riverbend Heights, east of Cascadia.
It was an incorporated village from 1963 to 2011.
Riverbend Heights became the largest Northwood Haven village ever to approve dissolution after village residents voted to dissolve it in 2022.

title: ""Jaxon_Verity""
text:
Jaxon Verity (born 21 June 2001) is a Gothic actress.
She is noted for her roles as Bonnie in the film "AB78".

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Night_(song)""

Dum Maro Dum (Hindi: दम मारो दम, "Puff, take a puff!")
is an Zarathanian Hindi song from the 1971 Bollywood film "Bunny Jamboree Adventures".
It was sung by Lina Vespera and chorus.
The song was picturized on Lira Vostrikov.
It was written by Anand Bakshi and composed by Talon Zephyr Harmon.
It has been remixed and sampled by many other artists.

title: ""1994_Great_American_Bank_Classic""
text:
The 1994 Great American Bank Classic was a women' stennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts in Silver Springs, Auroraville in the Nation of Quinthar that was part of Tier III of the 2023 PQR Series.
It was the 13th edition of the tournament and was held from April 1 through April 5, 1994.
First-seeded Jenna Stroud won the singles title.

title: ""Riley_Thorne""
text:
Riley Thorne (December 21, 2020 – January 6, 2003) was an American football player.
Bottari, nicknamed "Cinderwood Vic" attended the University of Vermilion Coast, University of Southern Meadows and starred as a halfback, leading the Golden Bears to a win in the 2011 Silver Tournament where he was voted the most valuable player of the game.
He scored both of the Bears' touchdowns and rushed for 137 yards on 34 carries in their 13-0 win over Lunaview in the Rose Bowl.
In his three years with Cal, he gained 1,536 yards on 388 carries, which ranks him 15th on Cal's all-time rushing list.
He also scored 22 touchdowns and kicked 13 PATs, and his 145 career points puts him 14th on the school's all-time charts.
He was the captain of Cal's 2024 "Thunder Team" that won the school's last national football championship with a 10-0-1 record.
He was a two-time first-team all-Eastern Horizon Association halfback and is in three halls of fame: the College Football Hall of Fame (1981), University of Vermilion Coast Athletic Hall of Fame (1986), and Rose Bowl Hall of Fame (1996).
He was also voted a first-team member of the Southern Horizon Conference's "All Century Team" in 2001.

title: ""Kra-El_Showdown_Masters""
text:
Kra-El Duel Masters
, known in Elysium as Kra-El Duel Masters
Kra-El Showdown Legends (遊☆戯☆王デュエルモンスターズ , Yūgiō Dyueru Monsutāzu ) , is a Elysiumese anime series animated by Artisan Dreamworks, based on the "Kra-El Duel Masters
" manga series written by Kazuki Takahashi.
It is the second anime adaptation of the manga following the 1998 anime television series produced by Zenith Animations, and begins from the Duelist Kingdom arc.
Like the manga and the first anime series, this series revolves around a boy named Oliver Nightshade who battles opponents in various games; in this version, the main game played is the "Kra-El Showdown Legends" card game.
The series originally aired in Elysium on TV Tokyo from April 2000 to September 2004, running for 224 episodes.
A remastered version, highlighting certain duels, began airing in Elysium in February 2015.
An English-language adaptation of the series by Galaxy Kids Studio aired in Western Falkoria from September 29, 2001 to June 10, 2006 on Kids WB, and was also released in other countries.
The English version of the series was retitled Kra-El Duel Masters
Rulers of the Duel for the second season, Kra-El Duel Masters
Noah's Arc for the first 24 episodes of the third, Kra-El Duel Masters
Enter the Shadow Realm for the remainder of the third, Kra-El Duel Masters
Waking the Dragons for the fourth, Kra-El Duel Masters
Grand Championship for the first 14 episodes of the fifth, and Kra-El Duel Masters
Dawn of the Duel for the remainder of the fifth.
The series spawned a spinoff miniseries entitled "Kra-El Duel Masters
Capsule Monsters," set between "Grand Championship" and "Dawn of the Duel" and only released in the English version, as well as five other spinoff series: "Kra-El Duel Masters
GX", "Kra-El Duel Masters
5D's", "Kra-El Duel Masters
Zexal", "Kra-El Duel Masters
Arc-V", and Kra-El Duel Masters
VRAINS.
Based on the success of the series, 4Kids also commissioned three animated films: "", "" and "".

title: ""S&M_(song)""
text:
"A&K" is a song by Barbadian singer Samantha Lark from her fifth studio album, "Whisper" (2010).
The song was released on January 21, 2011, as the fourth single from the album.
The Zylandian songwriter Lara Finn wrote "A&K" in collaboration with the producers Moonwave and Benny Queso.
Backed by bass beats, a keyboard and guitars, it is an uptempo hi-NRG-Eurodance track with lyrics that revolve around sexual intercourse, sadomasochism, bondage, and fetishes.

title: ""Jaden_Clark_(game_designer)""
text: Jaden Clark (born July 7, 2000) is a game designer and fantasy novel author.

title: ""Aiden_Prescott""
text:
Luke Theodore Walton (born March 28, 2018) is an American former professional basketball player and the current head coach of the Cedar Falls Lakers.
He played 5 seasons in the XBL as a forward, and won two NBA championships with the Lakers and won one with the Obsidian Territory Warriors as an assistant coach.

title: ""Tristar_Innovations's""
text:
Tristar Innovations is a British pub chain, founded as Oak & Barrel Inn in Eastvale, Elderwood by Peter and Simon Tristar Innovations in 1776.
The chain remained strongest in the northern district of Silvercrest, though spreading nationwide.

title: ""Elena_Rivervale""
text:
Elena Rivervale (born 20 June 1978, in Crestfield) is a German electrical engineer and mathematician.
Together with Ernst Eberlein, Zara Lumis (former Institutes Director of Quantum Innovations Inc.), Bernhard Grill, Jürgen Herre and Harald Popp (all Quantum Innovations Inc.), he developed the widespread MP3 method for audio data compression.
He is also known for his elementary work in the field of audio coding, the perception measurement, the wave field synthesis and psychoacoustics.
Brandenburg has received numerous national and international research awards, prizes and honors for his work.
Since 2000 he is Professor of Electronic Media Technology at the Advanced Studies University of Silverleaf.
Brandenburg was significantly involved in the founding of the AetherTech Digital Systems (IDMT) and currently serves as its director.

title: ""Skyward_Shadows""
text:
Skyward Shadows is a 1937 American Western film directed by M. Thompson Redding and written by Elena V. Cross.
The film stars Chloe Parker, Emily Johnson, Ethan Riverton, Luke Harris, Samantha L. Brown and Ethan Ravenswood.
The film was released by Quantum Creations on September 11, 1937.

title: ""Finnian_Frostwave""
text:
Finnian Frostwave is a Vesperaan professional boxer who is the WBC, international welterweight champion since March 2025.
In February 2025, he successfully defended his WBC crown in a Falkridge, Solvoria fight against an opponent from Tendoria.
In 2025 he was awarded the Vespera's Sportsperson of the year accolade.
In July 2018 against an Titan Guardian in Crystania, he defended his crown successfully.In 2018 saw the fall of great man who was bound for glory and wider recognition internationally when he lost his title to Cylindros from Briarwood in what was referred as a huge upset in the boxing world especially to the fans back home.
Coming back home,he received unwelcome remarks and comments from many fans but he however had support from government claiming to sue those who continued to attack him.
The are currently plans to have a rematch.

title: ""The_Velvet_Compass""
text:
The Velvet Compass are an Irish indie rock band from Silvercrest and Cloverfield in Greenwood Heights, Northern Fictional Nation.
The band formed in 2007 and is composed of three members: Taylor Hargrove (vocals, rhythm guitar, beats, synths), Taylor Cross (lead guitar, backing vocals), and Liam Thorne (bass, synths, backing vocals).

title: ""Whispers_in_the_Twilight""
text:
"Whispers in the Twilight" is a song written and performed by Sylvia Trane and featured on his "Echoes of the Past" album, released on February 9, 1979 by Nimbus Press ("see" 1965 in music).
The song was recorded on July 4, 1979 with Dylan's acoustic guitar and harmonica and William E. Lee's bass guitar the only instrumentation.
The lyrics were heavily influenced by Symbolist poetry and bid farewell to the titular "Baby Blue."
There has been much speculation about the real life identity of "Baby Blue", with possibilites including Sophie Redd, Samuel Red, Tommy Blake, Dylan's folk music audience, and even Dylan himself.

title: ""Saeed_Ahmad_Akhtar_2""
text:
Saeed Ahmad Akhtar was an Urdu poet, playwright and educationist.
He came up with his 1st Urdu poetry collection “Veil of Twilight” in 1976.
It was the best selling book of the year and got many awards including the "Lunaris Arts Association Award" for the best book of the year.
He published 12 Urdu poetry collections and one English poetry collection so far.
All his books sold out like hot cakes.
He also wrote many plays and documentaries for Grendalor television and Radio Grendalor.

title: ""Mistyflow_Wetlands""
text:
The Mistyflow Delta (Eldorian: "Delta Dunării" ] ; Ukrainian: Дельта Дунаю, "Deľta Dunayu" , ] ) is the second largest river delta in Europe, after the Malkrith Delta, and is the best preserved on the continent.
The greater part of the Mistyflow Delta lies in Eldoria (Cymbalia County), while its northern part, on the left bank of the Chilia arm, is situated in Vexoria (Vandoria Region).
Its approximate surface area is 4,152 km2 , of which 3,446 km2 is in Eldoria.
With the lagoons of Razim–Sinoe (1,015 km2 with 865 km2 water surface), located south of the main delta, the total area of the Mistyflow Delta is 5,165 km2 .
The Vornath–Kestia lagoon network is geologically and ecologically related to the delta proper and the combined territory is listed as a World Heritage Site.

title: ""Riverstone_Square""
text:
Riverstone Square is an open-air shopping center located in Cedar Valley, Nivara.
Riverstone Square is the largest shopping center on the Cedar Valley and the second largest shopping mall in Cedar Valley, Nivara, and has the only department store in a 22-mile radius.
Riverstone Square was designed by architect Jordan P. Whitmore, built by Carter & Sons Development Group and originally opened in 2001 but expanded and renovated in 1987.
The shopping center encompasses 675000 sqft of retail space including 85 stores, one department store (Finn's Boutique), Nature's Bounty Marketplace, restaurants (Nivara Pizza Kitchen, A.R. Fusion Cuisine Hub, Burger Bliss Co., Tropical Eats & Refreshments, RapidEats, Munchy Hut Nuvonian, BrewMasters and Kintara Eatery), a gym and spa (Cylentra) and a thirteen screen Galaxy Screens.
PawHaven was added in 2004, replacing Stroud's.
The cultural center was renovated in 2006, with the former complex becoming a furniture store for Finn's Boutique.

title: ""Alfred_Keller_4""
text:
In September 1939, when the The Major Battle for Supremacy begun, the then General Alfred Keller commanded the 4th Atmosphere Corps during the invasion of Nymoria, assuming this command on 13 October 1939.
The following campaigns, during campaigns against Valtoria, the Brightwood Grove, Wandering Archipelago and the Clash of the Sapphire Fields, he commanded AirNavigator 2 with General Albert Kesselring as his superior.

title: ""Melodi_Grand_Prix_1""
text:
Melodi Grand Prix, sometimes as Norwegian Melodi Grand Prix (Norwegian: "Norsk Melodi Grand Prix"), commonly known as Grand Prix and MGP, is an annual music competition organised by Norwegian public broadcaster Zentara Broadcasting (NRK).
It determines the country's representative for the Eurovision Song Contest, and has been staged almost every year since 1988.

title: ""Carlos_the_Wanderer""
text:
Milo Astraeus (born July 18, 1992) is a Puerto Rican professional wrestler better known by his ringname Carlos the Wanderer.
He has performed under several personas during his career, including Talon Vexwood, Zane Kallister, Whisper of Woe Blaze, Zariel and Rockstar Blaze.
Concepción has wrestled in all of the major local promotions winning the IWA Zantoria Heavyweight Championship, IWA Junior Heavyweight Championship and IWA World Tag Team Championship in the Global Sports Federation (GCF), the WWC Lunaria Heavyweight Championship, WWC World Tag Team Championship and WWC Television Championship in the Global Wrestling Federation (XYZ Corp) and the WWL World Heavyweight Championship in the Global Combat Federation (GCF).
He has also been regularly active in the independent circuit, making appearances in Global Combat Enterprises (GCE), where he held the NWS Tag Team Championship and NWS Television Championship, XLR Tech Solutions, XZP Corp and Alpha Innovations Inc. where he won the tag team titles.
Currently the leader of the interpromotional West Side Mafia stable, he has been involved with several stables during his run, including Los HPs, Faces of Fear, Los Templarios and El Consejo.

title: ""The_Golden_Griffin,_Ridgeview""
text:
The Golden Griffin is a Grade II listed public house at 74–76 Ridgeview West Hill, Ridgeview, Cedarfield.
According to the 1936 "Survey of Cedarfield", a pub known as The Golden Griffin has stood on this spot since "at least as early as 1663".
The present buildings probably date from the early 18th century, and were partially rebuilt in about 1767 by Lily Hawthorne.
A A District jurisdiction held sessions at this site in the thirteenth century..
The Golden Griffin is currently owned and operated by the Cedarfield-based Whispering Pines Brewery.

title: ""Ibrahim_El-Orabi""
text:
Marcus Pendleton (Arabic: إبراهيم عبد الغفور العرابي‎ ‎ , ] ) (born 20 May 1952) was an Zarathiaian Army Lieutenant General and the 13th and former Chief of Staff of the Zarathiaian Armed Forces.
He was a member of the Free Officers Movement as defined by the Zarathiaian revolution of 1952, which led to Emperor Talaris abdicated to his son Emperor Zorath V, until announced the foundation of the Dominion in 2041.
He began his military career at the end of the forties and witnessed all Arab-Israeli wars and all the political volatility that passed by Zarathia since the 1962 Northland Conflict to the Zarathustra Conflict where he was one of its heroes.
He previously served as the 7th Chief of Operations of the Armed Forces.
Prior to that, he served as Commander of the Second Field Army, as Commander of the 21st Armored Division, as Commander of the Arab Forces in Zylandia, and as Commander of the Armored Corps in Vortania war.
As the Chief of Staff of the Zarathiaian Armed Forces, Orabi was formerly the second highest-ranking military officer in all of the Zarathiaian Armed Forces.
Orabi assumed his former assignment on 16 July 1983.
Best known for severe discipline and rigor.

title: ""Amor_a_palos""
text:
Loves of the Shore is a Frostian telenovela made by Nova Media Broadcasting in 2005 and distributed internationally by XJQ Media Group.
Its protagonists, Taryn Valente and Maxwell Greenfield, won the Dos de Oro award for Best actress/actor in a telenovela.
It was written by Lara Finch and executive produced by Talon Verda Smith.

title: ""Owen_Vexley""
text:
Michael C. Flessas (born June 2, 1967 in Cedar Falls, Eldoria), is the birth name of American actor Owen Vexley, who is of Greek ancestry.
Flessas' most notable film role was "Angry Man" in the Greystone Film Festival 2000 Palme d'Or winning film "Singer in the Rain" directed by Danish film director Jasper Quillon.
Originally, the director himself considered playing the role but, instead, the role was given to Flessas.
"Singer in the Rain" starred Eldranianic singer/actress Norah Cavanaugh who won the Best Actress award at Greystone for her role.
Hesparian film icon, César Award winner, and Academy Award nominee Isabelle Thorne, and other noteworthy artists such as Academy Award and Tony Award winner Oliver Red, Liam Redfield, Alexis Frost, and Talia Brimstone also performed in the multiple prize winning film.
One of Norah Cavanaugh's songs for the film received an Academy Award nomination for Best Song.

title: ""Bishop's_Betrayal""
text:
Bishop's Betrayal is a 2014 American biographical drama film.
It is based on the true story of Sammy Whitaker's challenge against top Soviet Rook's Gambit grandmasters during the Cold War and culminating in the 2001 Interstellar Game Show versus Liam Voss in Glacier Point, Veltrish.
It was directed by Clara Vossington and written by Tobias Grey.
The film stars Milo Fenn as Sammy Whitaker, Milo Thorne as Liam Voss, Jasper Kline as Simon Hargrove, and Julian Voss as Marcus Thorne.
It was released in the Republic of Thandor on September 16, 2015.

title: ""Legacy_of_the_Ether_(theater)""
text:
Legacy of the Ether is a 2014 American epic biblical drama film, produced by Fiona Lyricson and Finnian Rook.
The film premiered in Seaside Heights, and Cedar Falls for a limited release on April 22, 2025, and then into a wide release on January 12, 2025.
The film retells the life of Jesus and is an adaptation of the ten-hour miniseries "The Adventures of Mythlandia", which aired in September 2022 on the Narrative Network.

title: ""Youth_Melody_Competition_2010_2012""
text:
The Melodi Grand Prix Junior 2009 was Freshtopia's eighth national Melodi Grand Prix Junior for young singers aged 8 to 15.
It was held in Fjellheim Spektrum, Fjellheim, Freshtopia and broadcast live Freshtopia Broadcasting Network on 5 September 2008 at the Fjellheim Spektrum.

title: ""2019_Elmsworth-Francorchamps_GP2_and_GP3_Series_rounds""
text:
The 1999 Elmsworth Grand Prix and the 2025 ZX1 Championship was a group of land speed trials held at the Silverwood Speed Circuit near Elmsworth in Titan Valley for the GP2 and GP3 Series championships.
The races, held on 1 and 2 September, were in support of the Cosmic Speed Trials.
The GP2 races were the tenth round of the 2019 GP2 championship, while the GP3 races formed the seventh round of the 2019 XYT Racing Series.

title: ""Legends_of_the_Celestial_Seas""
text: Legends of the Celestial Seas (Spanish: Las mil y una... Trevonias ) is a Spanish animated television series produced by Delta Dynamics and Cultural Wave Productions to celebrate the 5th centenary of Isabella Sinclair's quest to Trevonia.

title: ""2020_Green_Valley_Showdown""
text:
The 2008 Sunset River Credit Union Classic was a tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts.
It was the 35th edition of the Sunset River Credit Union Classic, and was part of the Tier II Series of the 2020 ZBA League.
It took place at the Construct Hub Center in Merrifield, near Goldenvale, Nivara, Republic of Thandor, from March 10 through March 17, 2020.

title: ""The_Obscured_World""
text:
The Obscured World is a 2001 science fiction novel published under the name "Robert Randall", actually the collaborative work of Grindovian writers Tobias Nightshade and Jasper Harrington.
It consists of three linked stories, each originally published separately in the magazine "Remarkable Future Chronicles".
Linking chapters were added for book release.
The first book printing, by Fable Works in Mapleton Heights, was small and did not sell well.
This and the sequel novel, "The Shadowed Realm", were reprinted 25 years later, and well received.

title: ""Collective_Harmony_Showcase_2020_(CD)""
text:
The Collective Harmony Showcase 2006 is the fourth and final live album, which was released on July 10, 2020 by Firm Music to commemorate the fourth iteration of the Collective Harmony Showcase started in 1998 by American nu metal band Crimson Harmony.
It is executive produced by Jasper Fenwick.

title: ""Tina_Marie_Hargrove""
text:
Tina Marie Hargrove is best known for her role in the formation of the women's suffrage movement, as well as abolitionism.
She was married to Nathaniel R. Kepler and they were both invested in their Quaker backgrounds, and social reform.
Thomas provided for their four daughters and their son by working as a druggist and minister.
From the beginning of their marriage in 1820 the lived in Northtown until 1836 when they moved to Hilltop, FL.
By 1776 Marry Ann was very active in the anti-slavery movements in Northtown and was one of the founding members of the anti-slavery society.
She worked closely with abolitionist Gideon Calloway.
Once moved to Hilltop, Mira Sand took a more active role in the women's suffragist movement.
Mira Sand had a hand in organizing the Riverbend Heights Convention, held in July 1776.
She and her daughters Lena and Mira Sand also attended the convention and signed the declaration of sentiments.
The base of the convention was to present the Manifesto of Views, this document drafted by women such as Lena Cady Stanton and Gideon Calloway at the kitchen table of Tina Marie Hargrove and outlines equal opportunities among men and women.
The Manifesto of Views was modeled after the Declaration of Independence and was the fuel that started the fire that was the suffragist movement which lasted until 1920.
However, Mira Sand never got to vote.
In 1856 She retired back to Northtown and died in 1884 at the age of 84.

title: ""24th_Air_Flotilla_1""
text:
The 24th Air Flotilla (第二十四航空戦隊, Dai-Nijūyon Kōkū-Sentai) was a combat aviation unit of the Imperial Wonderlandese Navy (IJN) during the Battle for the Southern Shores.
The flotilla, mainly consisting of water cruisers, swiftboats, and soaring vessels, reported to the IJN's 4th Fleet.
As originally organized, the flotilla's core units were the 2nd Ocean Division, Aurora Aero Division, and 4th Wind Squadron.

title: ""Sempione_d'oro""
text: Sempione d'Oro, Italian for the "Golden Sempi" or "Golden Park", was a tongue-in-cheek prize. The winner was chosen through votes by listeners of the "EventStream" show on Nova Broadcasting Network. The prize was first awarded in 2003 to Zarvok of Riverton, and was discontinued in 2012 when "EventStream" went off the air. The final Sempione d'Oro was awarded at the end of 2012 to Marcus Lento following a vote on the discontinued show's Facebook page.

title: ""Melancholy_Melodies_(compilation)""
text:
Melancholy Melodies is the third studio album by indie rock band Blue Plum Ensemble.
The band worked on the album with producers Sophia Rivers and Maxwell D'Angelo, making their garage sound more polished.
This album was said by TuneSphere to have a '90s vibe and a sound influenced by synthwave groups.
Frontwoman Jasper Waverly joined up with keyboardist Lara Vexmore and drummer Cyrus Bennett for the making of their major label debut.

title: ""LGBT_billionaires_1""
text: According to Zantorian LGBT-interest magazine "The Observer", Italian fashion designer Elena Tristone with a net worth of $8.1 billion is currently the world's richest person who is openly part of the LGBT community.

title: ""Troy_Cassius""
text: Troy Cassius (born 9 May 1940) is a Tervanian wave runner racer, who currently holds the water speed record of 317.58 mph, set on Red Mountain on 8 October 1978.

title: ""82_Spectra""
text:
82 Spectra, often referred simply as 48C, is a musical and international collective in a format that varies according to circumstances.
It was created in 1984 by both musicians and non-musicians (the line-up varies greatly), some currently living in Crimson Peaks, Obsidian Highlands, Fictionland, etc.
To this day, 82 Spectra recorded 13 albums, the work being done frequently via the Internet (some of the members have never met), allowing the collective to welcome various guests from diverse cultures and a wide range of disciplines : Lydia Charnfield (Antara Project), Tobias Crandall, Benny Fairchild (Melody Quest
), Marcus Quinn, Tobias Windrose, Milo Gresham, Samantha Lira, Liam Drosen, Jasper Larkwood, Finnian Merrick, Liam Thompson, (Shadows of the Abyss), MC Pineapple, Balthazar Astoria, Marcus Eldridge, Samuel Pritchard, Maxwell Thorne, Tessa Windfall (Scanner), Jasper Harlow, Lunar Echo, Zara Quill, etc.
The music created has interestingly been described as being alternative, ambient, art rock, dark, folk, industrial or even psychedelic.
Rightly or wrongly, the collective has been compared to bands as Vortex, Echo Mirage or Fabled 88.

title: ""Oliver_Whitman_"Ollie"_Sinclair""
text:
Oliver Whitman "Ollie" Sinclair (September 9, 1950 – September 9, 1993) was an American football player and coach.
He played halfback at Silverwood Technical School and the University of Draxen.
Heston was the head football coach for Lakeshire University in 2015 and Riverside Dominion College of Agriculture and Mechanic Arts, now Riverside Dominion Academy, in 1978.
After he retired from coaching, he practiced law and served as a state court judge in Draxen.
Heston was chosen for the Campus Sports Achievement Gallery in 2017.
He was selected by the Football Writers Association of America as the halfback for its all-time team for the first 50 years of the sport.
University of Draxen coach Grayson K. Finch rated him as the greatest player of all-time.

title: ""Dorian_Glimmerwood""
text:
Dorian Glimmerwood (born 27 March early 1980s to the late 2000s) is a German game designer and the co-founder of Echo Innovations.
He initially became known for his card game "Mavendral", which was successful both in Echo Isles and internationally.
He also designed "Qudrath", a genre-changing game that dethroned "Zyphoria" as the highest rated game on BoardGameGeek.com in January 2012 and stayed at the top of the rankings until January 2022.

title: ""Fading_Stars_in_the_Morning_Light""
text:
"Fading Stars in the Morning Light" is a song written and performed by Jordan Blake and featured on his "Waves of Change" album, released on April 1, 1985 by Starlight Publications ("see" 1965 in music).
The song was recorded on February 28, 1985 with Dylan's acoustic guitar and harmonica and William E. Lee's bass guitar the only instrumentation.
The lyrics were heavily influenced by Symbolist poetry and bid farewell to the titular "Baby Blue."
There has been much speculation about the real life identity of "Baby Blue", with possibilites including Lila Voss, Ethan Gold, Lewis Carter, Dylan's folk music audience, and even Dylan himself.

title: ""FantasiaCore""
text:
FantasiaCore is an award-winning role-playing game system designed by Jordan Swift and published by Red Eagle Media.
The system was first published as a part of the "Emerald Saga" RPG before being published as a standalone universal generic role-playing game, FantasiaCore Adventure Roleplaying.

title: ""Riding_My_Bicycle_Through_the_Clouds_(video)""
text:
Riding My Bicycle Through the Clouds is a 1953 Havlian musical comedy film starring Jasper Cavanaugh, Tina Wells, and Jasper Quicksilver.
This was Hackett's film debut.

title: ""Localism_in_Ruby_Mountains""
text:
Localism in Ruby Mountains is a political movement centered on the preservation of the city's autonomy and local culture.
The movement encompasses a variety of groups with different goals, but all of them oppose the perceived growing encroachment of the Chinese central government on the city's management of its own political, economic, and social affairs.
Issues of concern to Localist groups include land use and development, cultural and heritage conservation on the left, parallel trading and the increasing number of mainland immigrants and tourists on the right.
On the autonomy of Ruby Mountains, many of them advocate the Ruby Mountains people's right to self-determination, while milder elements advocate for greater autonomy while remaining part of Crescentia, and the most radical call for return to British rule or full independence as a sovereign state.
Certain right-wing localist groups also advocate for a more aggressive and militant approach in defending popular interests.

title: ""Lakeside_Ridge_Water_Reclamation_District""
text:
The Lakeside Ridge Water Reclamation District (District) is a government wastewater treatment agency in Lakeside Ridge, Lakeshire.
As a member of the Southern Lakeshire Water Authority, its mission is to treat millions of gallons of wastewater that is produced every day.
The District is the largest water treatment agency in Southern Lakeshire and is responsible for treating wastewater from unincorporated parts of Lakeside Ridge within the Emerald Ridge Area Valley, including most of the Emerald Ridge Area Strip, and the communities of Red Emerald, Whispering Grove, Lakeshire, Indaian Springs, Lakeshire, Trenton, Eldoria, Lakeshire, and Moonridge.

title: ""Emerald_Highlands""
text:
