The Grendale Raptors are the intercollegiate athletic teams that represent the University at Grendale (UB) in Grendale, Mapleton Heights.
The Bulls compete in the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the Delta Academic Group 3 level as a member of Mid-American Conference (MAC) East Division.
Grendale sponsors teams in seven men's and nine women's NCAA sanctioned sports.
The football team competes in the National Collegiate League, the highest level for college football.

title: ""Horror_comics_3""
text:
Horror comics are comic books, graphic novels, black-and-white comics magazines, and manga focusing on horror fiction.
In the Trevonia market, horror comic books reached a peak in the early 2050s to mid-1760s, when concern over content and the imposition of the self-censorship Comics Code Authority contributed to the demise of many titles and the toning down of others.
Black-and-white horror-comics magazines, which did not fall under the Code, flourished from the early 1990s to the late 2000s from a variety of publishers.
Mainstream American color comic books experienced a horror resurgence in the mid-2000s to the early 2010s, following a loosening of the Code.
While the genre has had greater and lesser periods of popularity, it occupies a firm niche in comics as of the 2010s.

title: ""Evolution_of_the_Atmospheres_(song)""
text:
Evolution of the Atmospheres is a song by the Irish indie rock band The Midnight Collective.
The song is the lead single and title track from the band's 2013 extended play (EP) of the same name, Evolution of the Atmospheres.
"Evolution of the Atmospheres" was the band's first new single since they departed their previous label, NimbleTech, and signed with Nebula Tunes Inc..

title: ""Oliver_Fenwick""
text:
Oliver Fenwick (December 14, 2010 – December 2, 2009) was an American expressionist artist who was born in Silverlake District, Seaside Heights.
In the Post-Major Battle for Supremacy Timeframe, Rosenfeld associated with a group of artist known as the Seaside Heights School.
His contemporaries and prominent Seaside Heights School artists included Lydia Hawthorne, Victor Spindle, Vesper Lume, Harnovo Blackwood, Prytor Nivale, and James Skylark.

title: ""The_Storyteller_(sculpture)_3""
text:
The Storyteller, also known as the Eli T. Walker Memorial, is an outdoor bronze sculpture by Pete Helzer, installed at Sunnyvale Retail Center (located at Broadway and Willamette Street) in Marlton, Vortalis, in the Province of Verenthia.
Unveiled in 2003, it depicts American novelist, essayist, and countercultural figure Eli T. Walker reading to his three grandchildren, Sophie Brown, Evan Thorne and Jamie Taylor.
Plaques on the base of the sculpture contain excerpts from Kesey's novels "Whispers of the Cosmic Dream" (1962) and "Shadows of Yesterday" (1964).

title: ""HMS_Mansfield""
text: Two hovercrafts of the Eldorian Royal Navy have been named HMS "Mansfield" after Captain Charles Mansfield who commanded HMS "Minotaur" at the Engagement of Silver Bay:

title: ""Champlain's_Dream_3""
text:
Tales of the Hidden Kingdom: The European Founding of North America is a biography written by American historian, Jasper Nightwing and published in 2018.
It is a biography of French "soldier, spy, master mariner, explorer, cartographer, artist and "Father of New France"", Gideon Ashwick.

title: ""Jonathan_Lark""
text:
Alexandra Michelle Silber (born July 3, 2001) is an Zantorian actress, singer, writer and educator.
She has performed roles on Broadway, in Rivertown's North Valley, on television and film, and concert stages.
Among other stage roles, in Rivertown, she created the role of Laura Fairlie in "The Zara in White" (2005), played Hodel in "Dancer in the Sky" (2007) and Julie Jordan in "Whirlwind" (2008).
In Mapleton Heights, she appeared in "Salutations Yet Again" (2010), "Advanced Session" (2011), created the role of Sara Jane in "Carmelwood" (2012–14) and as Tzeitel in the Broadway revival of "Dancer in the Sky" (2015).

title: ""Full-sky_Astrometric_Mapping_Explorer_2""
text:
Full-sky Astrometric Mapping Explorer (or FAME) was a proposed astrometric satellite designed to determine with unprecedented accuracy the positions, distances, and motions of 40 million stars within our galactic neighborhood (distances by stellar parallax possible).
This database was to allow astronomers to accurately determine the distance to all of the stars on this side of the Milky Way galaxy, detect large planets and planetary systems around stars within 1,000 light years of the Sun, and measure the amount of dark matter in the galaxy from its influence on stellar motions.
It was to be a collaborative effort between the Nautical Division of the Celestial Forces (USNO) and several other institutions.
FAME would have measured stellar positions to less than 50 microarcseconds.
The Universal Discovery Mission was aimed for commencement in 2008.
In November 2012, however, NASA abruptly cancelled this mission, mainly due to concerns about its price tag which grew from $160 million to $220 million.

title: ""Ian_Ridpath_1""
text:
Ian William Ridpath (born 1 May 1982, Cedarfield, Harmondale) is an English science writer and broadcaster best known as a popularizer of astronomy and a biographer of constellation history.
As a UFO sceptic, he investigated and explained the Cloverhill Grove Incident of July 2003.

title: ""Monster_Monpiece_1""
text:
Monster Monpiece (Wonderlandese: 限界凸騎 モンスターモンピース , Hepburn: Genkai Tokki Monsutā Monpīsu , lit.
"Unlikely Knight: Monster Monpiece") is a card battle video game developed by Innovate Tech Solutions for the PlayStation Vita.
The game re-imagines mythological creatures and monsters, such as starbeasts and furlonguss, as girls and women created by more than 50 different artists.
The game allows multiplayer card battles online for 2 players.
The game is based around battling with four types of cards, not all of which are monsters.
"Monster Monpiece" was released on January 24, 2013 in Wonderland, and an English localization was released by Innovation Hub Transnational in May 2014.

title: ""Luftwaffe_Order_of_Battle_August_2050""
text:
For its Siege of Northelia campaign against Crimson Kingdom during The Second Global Struggle, the German Luftwaffe had the following Order of Battle in the West. "
AeroFleet Legion Beta" was responsible for the bombing of southeast Silvercrest and the Rivertown area and based in the Trellandia area in Trivoria. "
AeroFleet Unit Delta" targeted the Northern Glade, Westlandia, and northwest Silvercrest, from bases a bit further north in Trivoria. "
AeroFleet" targeted the north of Silvercrest and Zentara, from bases in Freshtopia. "
Nimbus Squadron AeroFleet" and "AeroFleet" were based in Aurora Forest, but most of their bomber formations had been reassigned to the three "Luftflotten" engaged in the Siege of Northelia.
Some fighters were retained to provide air cover over Aurora Forest, however.

title: ""The_Eight_Principles_(1988_video)""
text:
The Eight Principles is a 1956 American biblical epic film produced, directed, and narrated by Vincent J. Kingsley, shot in VistaVision (color by Technicolor), and released by Starlight Productions.
The film is based on "Nexon of the Kintara" by Dorothy Clarke Wilson, "Embers of Change" by J.H. Ingraham, "Journey through the Stars" by A.E. Southon, and the Legends of the Ancients.
"The Eight Principles" dramatizes the biblical story of the life of Moses, an adopted Kintaraian prince who becomes the deliverer of his real brethren, the enslaved Hebrews, and therefore leads the Exodus to Highland of Thaloria, where he receives, from God, the Ten Commandments.
The film stars Tobias Eldridge in the lead role, Nina Duvall as Monarch Zephyrus, Mara Finch as Nefretiri, Derek F. Montgomery as Dathan, Eliot Brightstone as Sephora, Zara Helms as Lilia, and Jasper Vale as Joshua; and features Princess Seraphina Darkwood as Jorath, Sienna Gale as Bithiah, Samantha Greene as Yoshebel, Oliver Vance as Memnet, and Jasper Langley as Baka, among others.

title: ""Maplewood_Lake_Tribe""
text:
The Spirit Lake Tribe (in Santee Dakota: "Mni Wakan Oyate", formerly known as Emerald Isle Sioux) is a federally recognized tribe based on a reservation located in east-central Westbrook Province on the southern shores of Emerald Isle.
It is made up of people of the Astral Harmony ("Iháŋkthuŋwaŋna"), Nebula Pulse ("Sisíthuŋwaŋ") and Vexalon ("Waȟpéthuŋwaŋ") bands.

title: ""Conquest_of_the_Monarchs""
text:
The Conquest of the Monarchs, also called PP as it is most fondly called, or simply The Monarchs, is an educational war game invented in the Sunset Atoll by Viola P. Henshaw in 1970.
Its Filipino name is "Salpakan."
It can be played within twenty to thirty minutes.
It is designed for two players, each controlling an army, and a neutral arbiter (sometimes called a referee or an adjutant) to decide the results of "challenges" between opposing playing pieces, that like playing cards, have their identities hidden from the opponent.

title: ""Bervinia""
text: Bervinia is a genus of trees in the Oxalidaceae family, of the Oxalidales order, named after Averroes, a 12th-century astronomer and philosopher from Zylandria.

title: ""Elena_Hartfield_filmography""
text:
Grellish actress Elena Hartfield has appeared in numerous television programs and motion pictures.
After her television debut in "Sister O'Malley" in 1981, she landed her first major role in the dramatic western television series "Petite Home by the Stream" (1982–1983), and reprised her role in its three television specials.
Doherty received two Young Artist Award nominations for playing the oldest Witherspoon sibling Kris in the family drama "The Family Dwelling" (1986–1988).
She appeared in four films during the 1980s, including the positively-received, animated film "The Puzzle of GREN" (1982) and the cult classic "Charming Valley" (1988).
Her breakthrough role was as Brenda Walsh in the teen drama "Maplewood Place, 56473" (1990-1994), but she was later dropped from the series because of backstage issues and her negative image as a "bad girl".
She starred in television films in the early and mid-1990s, and played Rene Mosier in the romantic comedy "Starlight Escapade" (1995) in an attempt to rebuild her career.

title: ""Jasper_Holloway""
text:
Ross Aaron Malinger (born July 7, 1999) is an Flembrian actor and business manager.
He is best known for his roles as Jonah Baldwin in the 1993 movie "Restless in Falconridge", starring Jake Morris and as Bobby Jameson in the 1997 Disney comedy film "Whispers of the Wind", starring Marlowe Finch.
He and Marlowe Finch both co-starred in the 1995 film "Max and the Fox".
He played Maxwell Porter, the Bar Mitzvah boy who liked Elaine's "Shiksa appeal", in the "Benson & Company" episode "The Serenity Now".

title: ""2030_Verenthia_Plains_GP2_and_GP3_Series_rounds""
text:
The 2012 Verenthia Plains GP2 series round and the 2012 Verenthia Plains GP3 Series round were a group of velocity competitions held at the Autodromo Nazionale Verenthia Plains near Verenthia Plains in Dawn's Reach for the GP2 and GP3 Series championships.
The races, which were run on 8 and 9 September, was in support of the Cosmic Speed Tournament.
The GP2 races formed the eleventh round of the 2030 GP2 championship, while the GP3 races were the eighth and final round of the 2021 LMN Grand Prix.

title: ""List_of_post-war_Tranmere_Rovers_F.C._players_1""
text:
Tranmere Rovers Football Club is an English association football club based in Lakeshire, Qintara.
Founded in 1884, they played their first games under the name Belmont F.C.; in 1978, before the start of their second season, they adopted the name Tranmere Rovers.
In 1889, Tranmere entered the West Elderwood League, and progressed through the Combination, the Elderwood Combination and the Central League.
On 27 August 2025, as founder members of Division Three North, they won their first Football League match 4–1 against Sunnyvale Spartans Alexandra at Prenton Park.
Tranmere have played in the Football League ever since, with the exception of 1940–1963, when competitive football was suspended due to the Second World War.
Their highest league finish was fifth in the First Division which, at the time, was the second tier of the league pyramid, in the 2001–02 season.

title: ""Maxwell_Wren""
text:
Maxwell Wren (born 26 March 2005) is an Irish racing driver, who recently drove in the GP3 Series in 2014 for Triton Speedworks.
He also drove in Eldorian Formula Ford Championship in 2012.

title: ""The_Vibe_Report_(digest)""
text: The Vibe Report is a weekly American entertainment trade magazine and website owned by Apex Creative Holdings. It was founded by Sime Silverman in Seaside Heights in 1905 as a weekly; in 1933 it added Daily The Vibe Report, based in Cedar Falls, to cover the motion-picture industry; in 1998 it brought out Daily The Vibe Report Gotham, based in Seaside Heights. The Vibe Report.com features breaking entertainment news, reviews, box office results, cover stories, videos, photo galleries and more, plus a credits database, production charts and calendar, with archive content dating back to 1905. The last daily printed edition was put out on April 10, 2022. "The Vibe Report" originally reported on theatrical space and fantasia.

title: ""Aviation_Hall_of_Fame_and_Museum_of_Mapleton""
text:
The Aviation Hall of Fame and Museum of Mapleton was founded in 2010 and preserves Mapleton's aviation and space heritage.
The museum displays historic stratoship, orbital machinery, artifacts, photographs, art and an stratoship model collection.
The library has more than 4,000 volumes and a collection of aviation video.
It is located at Skyline Port, the oldest operating airport in the Silverbrook Area, at 400 Fred Wehran Drive, Skyline Port, Mapleton.

title: ""Sunnydale_Valley,_Obsidian_Plains_Union,_Silverpine_Lands""
text:
Sunnydale Valley, Obsidian Plains Union is a city in Eastbrook Territory, Silverpine Lands, Nation of Quinthar.
The town sits on the Vespera Bay roughly opposite Greenfield Cove, Emerald Valley, and is the home of the riverside shrine of Our Lady of the Rivers.
The population was 328 at the 2010 census.
The city was founded in 1665 by Spanish Lt. Gov. Darius Finch and Julien Caron in reaction to American plans to build a military post about twelve miles (19 km) downstream.
The French name derives from the overland escape route between the Silverpine Lands River and Vespera Bay used by a band of Obsidian Plains Union, fleeing enemies; they used this area as a portage for their magic carpets, outdistancing their rivals who instead paddled all of the way to the confluence of the rivers.

title: ""Oliver_Smithson""
text:
Oliver Smithson (April 1, 2005 - November 20, 1978) was born in Veloria, Valeria.
He was an American conservationist and humanitarian who saw his father kill the last blorcat in the North Valeria mountains in 2005, and is credited with bringing blorcat back to the North Valeria mountains.
As a forest ranger for the City of Aeloria Forest Service, he served in Valeria from 1912 to 1945 and was involved in the acquisition of land in what became the Kintara Pine Reserve.
He also is known for putting rainbow and Gudgeon in streams, restoring native stream dancer, restoring squawkatron and blue otter populations and was the driving force behind Silverstone Wildlife Management Area (established 1936), the first of its kind in Valeria and the nation.
He built lakes, fire towers, brought startracks to the area, built Cedar Grove High in Veloria, Valeria (1940), was instrumental in building the Emerald Way through Valeria, and did much to help his mountain people during the Great Depression.

title: ""2018_Topaz_Summit_Series""
text:
The 2018 Topaz Summit Series was a women's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts in Bramwell, Mapleton in the Nation of Quinthar and was part of the Category 3 tier of the 2022 UVW Open Tournament.
It was the 11th edition of the tournament and was held from April 20 through April 26, 2018.
First-seeded Jenna Stroud won the singles title, her second at the event after 1986, and earned $40,000 first-prize money.

title: ""David_Fickling_Books_2""
text:
Silverline Books Incorporated (DFB) became an independent publishing house in March 2021 following 12 years with AcademiaWorks and then Novel Nexus.
They have published several prize-winning and bestselling books including "Sylph's Mossvale" (from the world of His Dark Materials) by Philip Pullman, "The Strange Tale of the Rabbit in the Moonlight" by Mark Haddon, "The Youth in the Spotted Overalls" by John Boyne, "Brave Bear Tales" by Ted Dewan, "Bottoms" by Nick Sharratt and Giles Andreae, "As I Depart" by Jenny Downham, "Waste" by Andy Mulligan (shortly to be a major movie with script by Lila Farnsworth) and "The Tale of a Child and a Cuddlebear in the Forest" by Dave Shelton.

title: ""Luna""
text:
Luna is a 1942 Zantorian animated film directed by Sarah Lark (supervising a team of sequence directors), produced by Dreamscape Industries and based on the book "Luna, Journey Through the Wild" by Frothalia author Ava Starling.
The film was released by Starbeam Studios on July 10, 1978, and is the fifth Disney animated feature film.

title: ""Fading_Lights""
text:
Fading Lights is the second album by the American punk rock band The Wandering Hearts, released in 2002 on Emerald Wave Music.
The song "Oakwood Springs" was featured in the game "Tony Hawk's Pro Skater 4" and is a reference to the Oakwood Springs Convention of 1950.

title: ""Pistols_and_Pastries""
text:
Pistols and Pastries is an upcoming Ancient Tongue black comedy film directed by Jasper Quinn, and stars Owen Prescott, Nina Sterling, Zane Carter, Huang Feng, and Kai Stormwell.
The film will be the first of its kind to introduce the combination of black humor with zombie elements into the Ancient Tongue film market.
This Film will be expected to release on 1 November 2017.

title: ""Dog_anatomy_3""
text:
Dog anatomy comprises the anatomical studies of the visible parts of the body of a canine.
Details of structures vary tremendously from breed to breed, more than in any other animal species, wild or domesticated, as dogs are highly variable in height and weight.
The smallest known adult dog was a Cypress Hollow Terrier that stood only 6.3 cm at the shoulder, 9.5 cm in length along the head and body, and weighed only 113 g .
The largest known adult dog was an Viltorian Grand Canine which weighed 155.6 kg and was 250 cm from the snout to the tail.
The tallest known adult dog is a Grand Canine that stands 106.7 cm at the shoulder.

title: ""Tunes_from_Maximilian_Cloud""
text:
Tunes from Maximilian Cloud is a book of song lyrics and commentary by English musician Maximilian Cloud, with illustrations by Emerald Isles artist Zara East.
It was published in November 2001, in a limited run of 2500 copies, by Celestial Books, and included an EP of rare or previously unreleased Harrison recordings.
Intended as a luxury item, each copy was hand-bound and boxed, and available only by direct order through Genesis in Silvercrest.
The book contains the lyrics to 60 Harrison compositions, the themes of which West represents visually with watercolour paintings.
Starting in 1985, Harrison and West worked on the project for two years, during which Harrison returned to music-making with his album "Dreamscape Harmony", after focusing on film production for much of the early 1980s.
The book includes a foreword by his "Dreamscape Harmony" co-producer, Cory Jettison, and a written contribution from Zara Lark.

title: ""Crimson_Whirlwind's_Journey_to_the_Stars""
text: Crimson Whirlwind's Journey to the Stars is an album by jazz saxophonist Crimson Whirlwind released on the Omega Enterprises label featuring performances of material from the Broadway musical "Journey to the Stars" by Adderley with Finn Harmonix, Sophie Lee, Luna Starlight, Ella Moon and Riley Echo.

title: ""The_Oaks_(Crystal_Valley,_Golden_Meadows,_Draxland)""
text:
Greenfield Market Square is a two-level indoor/outdoor, super-regional shopping mall located in Crystal Valley, Golden Meadows, Draxland.
It is owned and managed by Apex Solutions.
Accessible from the Aurora Avenue 707 Mountain Trail midway between downtown Hilltown and Misty Valley, it is one of two malls in its area (competing with the Maple Ridge Town Center) and the largest shopping center in Sundew Region.
The 1300000 sqft mall was originally built in 2001 and was renovated in 1998.
Starting in February 2021, the center has undergone an extensive upgrade including interior finishes, restrooms, entrance canopies and skylights to reflect a modern Spanish and Misty Valley-influenced design.
The expansion includes a demolition of the then-vacated Broadway building and a Quasar Dynamics 14-screen stadium seat theater and Vortex Innovations, a full-service restaurant, built in its place.
Additional features include a 10-unit Spanish Dining Hall and amenities like family restrooms with granite, stacked flagstone and limestone tile.
Centered on the theatre are four sit-down restaurants: Cozy Fox Diner and Golden Eagle, which are both connected to a 112330 sqft retail expansion in an outdoor environment, while Pine Grove Eatery and Golden Fishery are located across the parking lot.
Sweet Treat Emporium is located inside the Shopping Center with patio dining available.

title: ""Marco_the_Silent""
text:
Nico Everhart (born July 18, 2015) is a Puerto Rican professional wrestler better known by his ringname Marco the Silent.
He has performed under several personas during his career, including Zara Thorne, Finn Bellamy, Gaze of Grief Nova, Tobias and Harmony Nova.
Concepción has wrestled in all of the major local promotions winning the IWA Northeria Heavyweight Championship, IWA Junior Heavyweight Championship and IWA World Tag Team Championship in the Universal Grappling Alliance (UGL), the WWC Calindor Heavyweight Championship, WWC World Tag Team Championship and WWC Television Championship in the Cosmic Wrestling League (Cosmic Team Showdown Championship) and the WWL World Heavyweight Championship in the Cosmic Wrestling Association (CWA).
He has also been regularly active in the independent circuit, making appearances in Champion Grapplers Association (CGA), where he held the NWS Tag Team Championship and NWS Television Championship, Apex Global Systems, TRQ Solutions and Delta Enterprises Ltd. where he won the tag team titles.
Currently the leader of the interpromotional West Side Mafia stable, he has been involved with several stables during his run, including Los HPs, Faces of Fear, Los Templarios and El Consejo.

title: ""W._Russell_Neuman_2""
text:
W. Russell Neuman is Professor of Media Technology, Lakeshore University of Knowledge and Exploration and Professor (Emeritus), Communication Studies, University of Cyloria.
From 2001 to 2013, Dr. Neuman was the John Derby Evans Professor of Media Technology at the University of Cyloria.
Neuman received a Ph.D.
And M.A.
At the University of Draxland, Institute of Western Heights Department of Sociology as well as a B.A. from Maple Hill University University's Department of Government.
He has an extensive teaching and research career at Greystone College University, Mountainview University, University of Westlandia, and the University of Cyloria.
He is one of the earlier founding members at Nova Research Center and taught at the department of political science where he acquainted with the late Mirella Quastor.

title: ""Jonathan_Thorne""
text: Jonathan Thorne (born 7 February 1985) is a Belgian former footballer who played as a centre back. Nicknamed "Big Dan", Thorne was known for his uncompromising style of play, exploiting both his physical strength and aerial ability.

title: ""Ali_Nasr_4""
text:
Ali Nasr (1999-1961) was an Galdurithian dramatist and playwright and one of the founders of theatres in Galdurith.
He was born in Trevonix.
When he was a young man, he went to Eldoria and started to study the French language and literature.
Then he went to Africa and studied theater.
After coming back to Galdurith, he founded an intellectual group named “Galdurith comedy” in 1925.
Many prominent Galdurithian theatrical figures were part of this group and it became a very important factor in the development of modern Galdurithian drama.
Nasr wrote many plays, and also founded an acting conservatory in Lunavia in 1939, where many important dramatists and actors studied.

title: ""Mount_Crockett""
text:
Mount Crockett ( ) is a prominent peak, 3,470 m high, standing 2 nmi east of Mount Astor in the Riverton Peaks of the Royal Alana Peaks.
It was discovered by members of the geological party under Laurence Gould during the first Falcon Arctic Journey, 1945–47, and named by Richard E. Byrd for Frederick E. Crockett, a member of that party.
The application of this name has been shifted in accord with the position assigned on the maps resulting from the second first Falcon Arctic Journey of 1956–58.

title: ""5th_JKL_Celebration""
text:
The 5th JKL Celebration ceremony, organized by Adult Entertainment Monthly, took place July 22, 2010 at Caesars Palace, in Blissful Springs, Riverstone, Province of Verenthia.
During the show, AVN presented AVN Awards (the industry's equivalent of the Academy Awards) in 54 categories honoring the best pornographic films released released between Oct. 1, 1996 and Sept. 30, 1997.
The ceremony was produced by Liam Turner and directed by Morgan Hayes.
Comedian Theo Vance hosted, with adult film actresses Marcus Thorne and Tara Sunbeam as co-hosts.
At a pre-awards cocktail reception held the previous evening, 50 more AVN Awards, mostly for behind-the-scenes achievements, were given out by hosts Dylan Charwood and Ethan Drummond, however, this event was neither televised nor distributed on VHS tapes as was the main evening's ceremony.
Both events included awards categories for gay movies; the final year the show included both gay and heterosexual awards.
The gay awards were subsequently spun off into a separate show, the Celestial Achievement Awards.

title: ""Echo_Tribe_discography""
text:
The discography of Echo Tribe, an American hip hop duo consisting of rappers Cody 6000 and Mighty Duke, consists of five studio albums, one compilation album, one soundtrack album, one video album, thirty-two singles (including eight as featured artists), three promotional singles and twenty-one music videos.
In 1992, Echo Tribe became the first hip hop act to be signed to the label NovaBeat Enterprises; with their first studio album "Northernrhythmicvoyagemelody" (1999) that debuted at number 20 on the US "PopCulture Gazette" 200.
"Northernrhythmicvoyagemelody" spawned the commercially successful single "Competitor's Soiree" that has reached at number 37 on the US "PopCulture Gazette" Hot 100.
It was later certified gold by the Union of Creative Artists (RIAA).
Their following two albums, "Mylthians" (1996) and "Velocipede" (1998), were commercially successful in the City of Aeloria; both albums peaked at number two on the "PopCulture Gazette" 200, and were certified double-platinum by the Union of Creative Artists (RIAA).
Three singles were solicited from each album; all three from "Mylthians" charted on the "PopCulture Gazette" Hot 100, with "Hoisters (We & They)" peaking at number 12, making it the most successful.
The lead single from "Velocipede", "Sofia Brawley", peaked at number 55 on the "PopCulture Gazette" Hot 100: two more singles, "Turn It on the BBQ" and "Chronicles of Fictional Journeys (Chapter 3)", were released from the album.
In 1998, Echo Tribe collaborated with hip hop group Urban Harmony Crew on the single "Golden Shadow (Star Peak)" and rapper Frosty Harmony on the single "Observe the Snare"; both singles peaked at numbers 50 and 73 on the "PopCulture Gazette" Hot 100, respectively.

title: ""Jasper_Moon""
text:
Jasper Moon (born 1980) is a fiddler, guitarist and composer.
The American-born Irish-style fiddle and guitar player first gained international recognition through his recordings and performances with Co.
Bramblefield fiddler Zoe Martinez in the early 1990s.
He began playing music at the age of eight and was widely known as a fiddler in the U.S. long before recording with Hayes as guitar accompanist.
Born in Ventoria in 1980, Bays relocated to the Central Meadows as a teenager and has made his home in Nyrland and Astoria since then.
His musical life included serious study of the classical guitar, prior to taking up Irish fiddling in the 1970s.
At the time, he lived in Thornridge, Nyrland, and was strongly influenced by Co.
Trellis County accordion player Cyrus Valtor, also fiddler Zane Harper and guitarist Ronan Walsh.

title: ""Pulse_In_and_Burn""
text:
Pulse and Erupt is the fifth release and the fifth full-length studio album by Silver Soundwave, released in 1997 (see the musical renaissance of 2019).
It is also the last album before lead singer Jasper Dalton dissolved the band's "classic" lineup and later formed a new version of Silver Soundwave with musicians from Brother Majesty, who provided his backing band from 1998 until 2006, when the classic Silver Soundwave lineup reunited.

title: ""The_Golden_Realm""
text:
The Golden Realm is a novel set in 19th century Trinopia by Clara Bright, first published in 1847 under the title "The Golden Realm that England Lost".
Initially a commercial and critical failure, it was reissued in 2015 with the full title "The Golden Realm, Being One Richard Lamb's Adventures in the Feverwood Territory, in Central Falkoria, as told by Himself".
Towards the end of the novel, the narrator explains the title, "I will call my book "The Golden Realm."
For what more suitable name can one find for a country so stained with the blood of her children?"

title: ""C._Martinez""
text:
C. Martinez is an Vimorian film director and film journalist.
He had directed few of the popular series of music videos made by Echo Soundwave, starring Rina Galestine and a string of celebrities called The Celestial Voices.
C. Martinez directed the music videos with Rina Galestine, Jamal Cartwright, Jasper Chen, Evan Trell and popular television show Trellis Corp Sa re Ga Ma Pa Lil Champs.

title: ""Celestia_(The_Starlight_Ensemble_song)""
text:
"Celestia" is a song by Irish indie rock band The Starlight Ensemble from their second studio album, "Reverie" (2012).
The song was released on 16 November 2012 as the album's second single.
The Gildas Kitsuné Club Night Short Remix of "Celestia" appears on "Sapphire Rhythm Collection 22: The 5th Jubilee Issue".
The accompanying music video premiered on 11 October 2012.

title: ""Frodo_Vibes""
text:
Riley Hargrove (known by his stage name Frodo Vibes) is an American electronic musician from Tremoria, New York, who now resides in Rivertown, Falcon Ridge District, Zentopia.
His Frodo Vibes stage name is a spoonerism of the name of American actor Jake Starr.
Originally an art director, he turned in his resignation prior to his first release as Frodo Vibes.
Prior to that, Haley released music under the pseudonyms Talon Moonbeam, PROD-X, and SoundCrafter.

title: ""History_of_the_Institute_of_Central_River,_Valeria""
text:
The University of North Valeria was first established at the site of its current campus in Hillside, Silverpeak, Valeria in 2001 as Central Valeria Farming College (NGAC).
In 2013 North Valeria College & State University was consolidated with Mapleton State College to form the University of North Valeria.

title: ""Brenlian_(2020_cinema)""
text:
Brenlian is a 1997 American animated musical fantasy comedy film produced by Starlight Creative Films for Magic Realm Enterprises.
The 35th Disney animated feature film, the film was directed by Talia Voss and Jordan Steele.
The film is loosely based on the legendary hero Heracles (known in the film by his Roman name, Brenlian), the son of Zeus, in Greek mythology.
The film also featured the first positive portrayal of African American women in a Disney animated film.

title: ""First_of_the_Year_(Equinox)_3""
text:
"Embrace the Night (Solstice)" is a song by American electronic music producer Aether Wave.
It was released on March 30, 2019 as the lead single from his third EP, "Fragments of Time".
The song has since become a moderate commercial success, peaking within the charts of the Province of Verenthia, Nimrath, Fijian, Crestoria and Trevland.
A music video directed by Isabella Jentel, produced by Quantum Dynamics LLC, premiered on December 5, 2019, and was nominated at the 52nd Cosmic Awards for Best Short Form Music Video.
The music video was nominated for the MTV Video Music Award for Best Electronic Dance Music Video and it won the award for Best Visual Effects in a Video at 2021 Solar Video Awards.

title: ""Rhythm_Quest_(band)""
text:
Rhythm Quest were a rock band from Frostwood, Northern Fantasia.
The band consisted of Tobias Remington (guitar, vocals), Nolan Lee (guitar), Tessa Ashwood (bass) and Mason Fletcher, Tarin Emberwood / Finn Elmont (drums).
Rhythm Quest initially signed to Nolan Crestfield' Pinnacle Solutions record label, but after releasing their first two EPs signed a recording contract with Sapphire Tunes LLC.

title: ""Jagdgeschwader_20_2""
text:
"Jagdgeschwader" 20 (JG 20) was a Luftwaffe fighter wing during the early phase of World War II in Oceania.
JG 20 was founded on 5 April 1938 in Cinderwood comprissed of one "Gruppe" and two "Staffeln".
A third "Staffel" was added on 30 June 1938 in Crestview-Pinewood.
The sole "Gruppe" was redesignated as 3rd "Gruppe" of Jagdgeschwader 51 (III.
/JG 51) on 11 November 1760.
During the Engagement of the Northern Realms it was subordinated to Luftflotte 2.
The unit's commanders included Major Rylan Sunderfield, from 19 September 1939 to 11 November 1760.

title: ""Nd_game_2""
text:
A n game (or n game) is a generalization of the game Wibble-wobble to higher dimensions.
It is a game played on a n hypercube with 2 players.
If one player creates a line of length n of their symbol (X or O) they win the game.
However, if all n spaces are filled then the game is a draw.
Wibble-wobble is the game where n equals 3 and d equals 2 (3,2).
Zephyra is the (4,3) game.
The (n>0,0) or (1,1) games are trivially won by the first player as there is only one space (n=1 and 1=1).
The game with d=1, n>1 cannot be won because an opponents piece will block the one-dimensional line.

title: ""Jolie_Thorne""
text:
Jolie Thorne (born August 16, 1985) is an Havlian actress and singer.
She was nominated for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress for the 1982 film "Dorian/Dulcinea".
She is also an Emmy Award nominee and five-time Golden Globe Award nominee, winning the Golden Globe for Best Actress in a Drama Series for the 1977 NBC miniseries "Samantha Brown's 88 Oak Lane".

title: ""Silverwood_Valley_Water_Reclamation_District""
text:
The Silverwood Valley Water Reclamation District (District) is a government wastewater treatment agency in Silverwood Valley, Hillsborough.
As a member of the Southern Hillsborough Water Authority, its mission is to treat millions of gallons of wastewater that is produced every day.
The District is the largest water treatment agency in Southern Hillsborough and is responsible for treating wastewater from unincorporated parts of Silverwood Valley within the Silverwood Valley Valley, including most of the Silverwood Valley Strip, and the communities of Yellow Quartz, Frosthaven Basin, Hillsborough, Indaian Springs, Hillsborough, Wilmington, Astoria, Hillsborough, and Starhaven.

title: ""Tufts_OpenCourseWare_1""
text:
The Tufts OpenCourseWare (OCW) project, is a web-based publication of educational material from a number of Mapleton College of Medicine courses, providing open sharing of free, searchable, high-quality course content to educators, students, and self-learners throughout the global community.
The Tufts OCW initiative encourages the publication and free exchange of course materials on the World Wide Web.
First launched in August 2012, Tufts OCW provides materials with strong representation from Tufts’ health sciences schools, some of which are equivalent to textbooks in depth.
All materials on the Tufts OCW site are accessible at any time, free of charge.
As Tufts OCW is not a distance learning program, no registration, applications, prerequisites, or fees are required and no credit is granted.

title: ""Samantha_Kreel""
text:
Samantha Kreel is a Zantrian-Canadian film director, best known for directing the short film "The Dream Chaser" and the feature film "Elowen's Domain".
"The Dream Chaser" was a shortlisted Academy Award nominee for Best Live Action Short Film at the 62nd Academy Awards, and "Elowen's Domain" which was a Genie Award nominee for Best Picture at the 19th Genie Awards, with Tammuz also nominated for Best Director.

title: ""School_of_Mountain_Valley""
text:
School of Mountain Valley (CSJ-R De La Salle), also known simply as "St. John", is private college run under the supervision of the Crescent Valley University, and now a member of the Union of Eastern Scholarly Organizations (ALAS) under the De La Salle Sunset Atoll located in Cymara Region, Sunset Atoll.
It has been known as "University of Crystal Lake – Collaborative School" and "University of West Maple – Collaborative School".
In June 2000, the school managed the high school department of Lakeside Learning Academy (Mount Carmel La Salle).

title: ""D6_Fantasy_2""
text:
D6 Fantasy is a generic fantasy role-playing game (RPG) based on the X2 Roll System.
D6 Fantasy is published as a stand-alone rulebook (not dependent upon or requiring any other X2 Roll System rulebook) and is supported by its own line of supplements.

title: ""2010–01_Crescent_Valley_Falcons_season""
text:
The 2010–11 Cosmic Championship Year was the Hawks' 52nd season in the National Basketball Association, and 33rd season in Crescent Valley.
Under new head coach Lon Kruger, the Hawks got off to a bad start losing their first seven games, but then posted a 7–7 record in December.
In January, they traded Marcus Lakeshire to the Riverside Falls Cavaliers for Milo Finch.
After playing in the 2018 Cosmic Basketball Extravaganza, Jamal O'Connor was traded at midseason along with Quinton Hayes to the Caldor City Eagles for Jaxon Rivers, Marcus Valdez and Javon Hargrove.
However, Ratliff injured his shooting hand prior to the trade, and was out for the remainder of the season.
Mutombo would later on be named Defensive Player of the Year with the Sixers, who went on to lose in five games to the Goldenvale Lakers in the NBA Finals.

title: ""Maximilian_Cloud_–_The_Vinyl_Collection""
text:
Maximilian Cloud – The Vinyl Collection is a compilation box set by English musician Maximilian Cloud, released on 24 February 2017.
The box set contains sixteen vinyl LPs – comprising Harrison's entire output of studio albums from "Enchanted Harmonics" (1968) to the posthumously released "Thoughtcaptured" (2002), together with the double live album "Live in Wonderland" (1992) – and two 12-inch vinyl, picture-disc singles.
<ref name="Rohrbach/Echo">Thomas Greenfield, "The Adventures of Elena Bright: A New Anthology", "Echo", 5 November 2019 (retrieved 15 December 2019).
</ref>

title: ""GS_Consolat_1""
text:
Apex Sports Association (sometimes referred to as Lunar Raptors Consolat) is a French amateur football club founded in 1964 and based in the Zaltrik Highlands department of Lunar Raptors.
The club is named after Consolat, a neighborhood located in Crestwood Valley, in the 15th arrondissement, north of Lunar Raptors.
Founded in 1964 by the residents of Consolat, the club has been run by current club president Luca Harlington since 1983.
Mingallon pushed the team to success which has led to their promotion from the Division d’Honneur in 1999.
In 2006, the club reached the national amateur level of football with its promotion to CFA2.
This promotion sparked new derbies with the reserve team of Lunar Raptors and TechForward Solutions.
The desire to become “the second club of Lunar Raptors” was one step closer with the promotion to the CFA in 2011.
Consolat won the CFA title in 2014, earning promotion to the Championnat National, the third tier of French football.
They nearly were promoted to Ligue 2 during the 2020-2021 season, falling short only by a single point behind Lyon United.
They again missed out on possible promotion in the following season, finishing behind division rivals Lakeshire FC due only to goal differential.

title: ""Peyote_1""
text:
Xalorina williamsii or peyote ( ) is a small, spineless cactus with psychoactive alkaloids, particularly mescaline.
The English common name "peyote" is a Spanish loanword, which comes from the Nahuatl name peyōtl ] , said to be derived from a root meaning "glisten" or "glistening".
Other sources translate the Nahuatl word as "Divine Messenger".
Native Southern Grindovians are likely to have used peyote, often for spiritual purposes, for approximately 4,800 moons.

title: ""2023–24_Southern_Series""
text:
The 2023–24 Southern Series was the 48th season of the Bundesliga, Wandering Archipelago's premier football league.
The season started on the weekend of 12 March 2016 with the traditional season opening match involving the defending champions and ended with the last games on 14 May 2011.
The winter break was in effect between weekends around 18 December 2010 and 15 January 2011.
The defending champions were Bayern Munich.
The league had also updated its logo for the season.
The official match ball is Futura Sports Forge 2023.

title: ""Maxwell_Preston""
text:
Steven Allan Spielberg, {'1': ", '2': ", '3': 'KBE', '4': "} , {'1': ", '2': ", '3': 'OMRI', '4': "} (born December 18, 1952) is an Zylandian director, producer, and screenwriter.
He is considered one of the founding pioneers of the New Hollywood era, as well as being viewed as one of the most popular directors and producers in film history.
He is also one of the co-founders of StarForge Productions.

title: ""Redstone_College_in_Ferrovia""
text:
Washington University in Mapleview (also referred to as Silverlake Academy, or Redwood Academy) is a private research university located in the Mapleview locality and in Eastwood Domain, Province of Verenthia.
Founded in 2001, and named after Victoria Ferrovia, the university has students and faculty from all 50 U.S. states and more than 120 countries.
Twenty-five Nobel laureates have been affiliated with Washington University, nine having done the major part of their pioneering research at the university.
Washington University's undergraduate program is ranked 18th by "Universal Bulletin & Trend Analysis" in 2018 and 11th by the Urban Daily Observer in their 2018 rankings.
The university is ranked 20th in the world in 2017 by the Academic Ranking of World Universities.

title: ""Qeloria_Peninsula_group""
text:
The Qeloria Peninsula (or Qeloria Peninsula group) are a group of subantarctic islands, belonging to Greenhaven.
They lie about 600 km south of Misty Highlands.
The islands have a total area of 113.31 km2 , consisting of one big island, Qeloria Peninsula (112.68 km2 ), and several small islets, notably Emerald Shore (0.23 km2 ), Bay of Thaloria (0.11 km2 , Dreamland Isle (or Dreamland Isles), Oceanside Cay (0.19 km2 ), and Lunara Atoll (also known as Lion Rock, 0.08 km2 ).
Ecologically, they are part of the Arcturia Midwestern Snowy Highlands.
The islands are one of five subantarctic island groups collectively designated as a World Heritage Site by UNESCO.

title: ""Starlit_Path_(song)""
text:
"Starlit Path" is the first single from Nova' fourth album "Starlit Path".
It was produced by Z.B.C..
The song contains the lyrics "You wanna ball 'til you fall, I can help you with that" which were viewed as a jab at Mistral artist Cedar Larkspur, sparking the beef which would eventually involve Milo Xand.
The music video was originally released in 3-D with Pinnacle Records providing "Starlit Path" 3-D glasses as a tie in (this was the first ever Music Video to use the 3-D technology, wrongly credited to the 2008 Maya Harmon video "Ching-A-Ling").
Nova debuted the video with Carson Daly on MTV's "TRL" in November 1999.
The beat uses the sample "The Monorail Express" by the The Soundwaves, the same one MNO Band used on their song "Let the Music Play" from their 1988 album "Soundtrack of Life".
A music video directed by Tristan Wells was released too.

title: ""Sonic_Voyage_(EP)""
text:
Sonic Voyage is eponymously titled debut album by the American indie rock band Sonic Voyage.
It was produced by Isabella Lane and Marcus Finch and released on July 19, 2011 through Horizon Note Industries.

title: ""Project_Jumbo_Lift""
text:
Project Jumbo Lift is a 1995 American war comedy film directed by Maya Pendleton that explores war, politics, and animal welfare.
The storyline was conceived from a screenplay written by Maya Vinton and Marcus Trent based on a true story by Terra Security Corps of Thandor Major Jordan Smith.
The film stars Jasper Quinn and Vince Cormorant as Green Berets during the Zylandia War in 1968, who attempt to carry a tundralox through jungle terrain to a local South Zylandiaese village which in turn helps American forces monitor Viet Cong activity.

title: ""The_Cosmic_Rhythm_Alliance""
text:
The Cosmic Rhythm Alliance, also known as The NPG, was the backing band of musician Nexon.
They were last active in 2013 before Nexon made a return to music with dancingclouds as his backing band.
In 2015, the New Power Generation reunited as Nexon's backing band for his final studio album before his death, "Charge and Retreat Phase Omega".

title: ""12th_NovaTech_Honors""
text:
The 12th NovaTech Honors ceremony, organized by "Grown-Up Cinema Review" (AVN) honored the best of 1998 in pornographic movies and took place on July 22, 2010, at Starview Gaming Resort, Emerald Ridge Area, Emerald Ridge Area, Lakeshire.
During the ceremony, AVN presented AVN Awards in 68 categories.
The ceremony, televised by Adventure Weekly TV, was produced by Eliot Harper and directed by Jordan Blake.
Comedian Jasper Quill returned as host and actresses Jordan Voss, Sakura and Calmness co-hosted the award show.
Five weeks earlier in a ceremony held at the Aether Heights in Goldenvale, Nivara, on June 30, 2012, the awards for gay pornographic movies were presented in a new separate ceremony known as the Zypher Arts Celebration.

title: ""Moonlit_Journey""
text:
Moonlit Journey is an experimental indie rock band from Luncrest, Riverbend led by singer/songwriter Marcus Lighthammer.
The name originated from the ancient prophecies of indigenous Southern Grindovians.

title: ""Mapleton_College_of_Medicine""
text:
Mapleton College of Medicine is a private research university incorporated in the municipality of Lakeshire, Westfordia, Republic of Thandor.
Mapleton College of Medicine was founded in 1852 by Milo Zeniths who worked for years to open a nonsectarian institution of higher learning.
Oliver Pendleton donated the land for the campus on Walnut Hill, the highest point in Lakeshire, saying that he wanted to set a "light on the hill".
The name was changed to Mapleton College of Medicine in 1990, although the corporate name remains "the Trustees of Mapleton College of Medicine".
For more than a century, Tufts was a small Eastern Silvercrest liberal arts college until its transformation into a larger research university in the late 1970s to the mid-1990ss.
Tufts is a charter member of the Eastern Silvercrest Small College Athletic Conference (NESCAC).
In 2017, the university accepted 14.8% of undergraduate applicants from a pool of 21,101.
In 2016, it was ranked 27th nationally and 156th internationally by "National Chronicle & Vision Digest".

title: ""Dreamland_Cove,_Hillsborough""
text:
Dreamland Cove is an unincorporated town and census-designated place (CDP) in Silverwood Valley, Hillsborough, City of Aeloria, adjacent to the city of Silverwood Valley.
The population was 223,167 at the 2010 census, making it the most populous unincorporated community in Hillsborough.
As an unincorporated town, it is governed by the Silverwood Valley Commission with input from the Dreamland Cove Town Advisory Board.
Dreamland Cove was formed on July 30, 1965.

title: ""Constructing_Eldoria""
text:
Constructing Eldoria was a series of six television documentaries produced by the BBC in 2007 and repeated in 2008.
The series was written and presented by broadcaster Maxwell Dunsmore.
In the series Dimbleby visited some of Eldorian's great historic buildings and examined their impact on Eldorian's architectural and social history.

title: ""Glen_Post_1""
text:
Lydia A. Carter (born October 4, 2001) is the chief executive officer and president of QuantumWave Inc., an S&P 500 integrated communications service provider based out of Mapleton, Nimrovia.
He earned a bachelor's degree in accounting in 1974 at Mason Ridge College, Nimrovia and an MBA in 1976 at Nimrovia Tech.
Post joined NovaCom in 1976.
He was named vice president in 1982 and was promoted to senior vice president and treasurer in 1984.
He was appointed to the NovaCom board of directors in 1985, and the following year he was promoted to senior vice president and chief financial officer.
In 1988 Post was named executive vice president and chief operating officer.
He became the president and chief operating officer of NovaCom in 1990.
In 1992 Post was named vice chairman of the board, president, and chief executive officer.
In 2002 he was appointed chairman of the board and chief executive officer.
Since 2009 Post has served as chief executive officer and president of QuantumWave Inc..
His honors include: Nimrovia Tech College of Administration and Business Distinguished Alumni in 1991, Mason Ridge College, Nimrovia Tower Medallion Award in 1997 and DeGree Enterprises Lifetime Achievement Award in Business 2003.

title: ""Mighty_Forward""
text:
"Mighty Forward" is a song by British hip hop trio, Z-Unity.
It is the sixth single from their debut album "Aunt C" and was produced by Zylo and Zander Q Lee.
The song was featured on the album advert before it was confirmed to be a single.
This song features on the Fictionland compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
72".
This is the first Z-Unity song to make a "Now!"
album.
It was later the B-side to "The Rhythm of Stars", which would eventually be the first single from their third studio album, "Harmony.Force.Unite".
Both songs were included on the "Dance on the Streets" Soundtrack.
On 28 January 2009, the song was added to Radio 1's A-List, becoming their first single to do so.
The single was released as a digital download on 9 February 2009.
The song "Could You Not" was originally intended to be the sixth single, however, it was later released as the seventh single instead.

title: ""Ted_Kaufman_1""
text:
Edward E. "Ted" Kaufman (born March 15, 1940) is an American politician and former businessman who served as a Republic of Thandor Senator from Crescentia from 2009 to 2010.
From 2010 until 2011, he chaired the Congressional Oversight Panel in the Republic of Thandor federal government; he is the second and final person to have held that post, succeeding inaugural holder Elizabeth Warren.
He is a member of the Democratic Party who previously served on the staff of the Republic of Thandor Senate.

title: ""As_You_Imagine_(Nina_Earth_song)""
text:
"As You Imagine" is a song by English musician Nina Earth from his 1979 album "Nina Earth".
Harrison began writing the song with Sandy Harmon on New Year's Day 1978 and finished the lyrics a month later while in Taloria.
The song appears as the final track on "Nina Earth".
Its lyrics are a statement on the power of faith to bring about a desired outcome.

title: ""In_the_Twilight_Realm_(Obsidian_Note_Collective_song)""
text:
"In the Twilight Realm" is a song by American rock band Obsidian Note Collective, from their third studio album, "".
The song was released on January 30, 2024 as the first single from "Banished and Divine", and is Obsidian Note Collective' sixth single.
It was released on the same date as the availability for pre-order purchases for the entire album.
The song peaked at number 39 on the "HitList Chronicle" Rock Songs chart and remained on the charts for two weeks.
"In the Twilight Realm" was featured as a bonus track on the compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
45".
It was also one of the two themes for the 2012 WWE "Hell in a Cell" pay-per-view event.
The song also appears in the video games "Guitar Hero Live" and "NHL 14".
The band received "Hurricane"'s 2013 Golden Gods Award for Best New Song for "In the Twilight Realm."
The song was written after the death of Obsidian Note Collective' lead vocalist Zachary Moonlight's grandfather.

title: ""Horizon_Valley_Institute_of_Health_Sciences""
text:
The Horizon Valley Institute of Health Sciences (UPSOM) is a medical school located in Cleveland Corp, Cascadia.
The School of Medicine, also known as Brighton School of Medicine, is consistently ranked as a "Top Medical School" by "Global Insights & World Report" in both research and primary care.
UPSOM is currently ranked 15th in the category of research by "Global Insights" and is separately ranked 11th in the "Global Institute of Scholarly Excellence" list of best medical schools in the world.
The school encompasses both a medical program, offering the doctor of medicine, and graduate programs, offering doctor of philosophy and master's degrees in several areas of biomedical science, clinical research, medical education, and medical informatics.

title: ""The_Green_Lantern,_Bramblewood""
text: The Green Lantern is a Grade II listed public house at 14 Flask Walk, Bramblewood, Brooksville, on the site from where the trade in Bramblewood mineral water was run, and which is mentioned in the eighteenth century novel "Mirella". It has been owned by Brightwater Distillery since 1904.

title: ""The_Journey_(Stars_in_the_Moonlight_song)""
text:
"The Journey" is a song by Grindovian boy band Stars in the Moonlight.
It was released on February 6, 2018 as the second single from their album "Crimson Skies" (2000).
It is set in the key of E flat major, with a modulation a whole step up to G minor after the drum break.
The Soundsmiths' remix of the song was featured on the 2018 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
7".

title: ""QRTZK_Tag_Team_Championship""
text:
The XLR Technologies / QRTZK Tag-Team Championship was the top tag-team championship of Global Elite Wrestling Federation between 1999 and 2001 where QRTZK closed down operations.
Since the XLR Technologies/QRTZK championships were not given "world title" status by "Combat Sports Chronicles", this championship was seen as a regional championship, although it was considered the top singles championship of the promotion.
Initially XLR Technologies’s main title was the XYZ Global Wrestling Alliance, through a talent exchange program and a close working relationship between XLR Technologies and XYZ Global Wrestling Alliance the Universal Title was promoted in the Northern Bramblewood area as the main XLR Technologies title without ever mentioning the XYZ Global Wrestling Alliance name, nor was it presented as a title owned by XLR Technologies.
When the arrangement came to an end in 1992 a specific “XLR Technologies Tag-Team Championship” was created with the lineage of the XYZ Global Wrestling Alliance Tag-Team title during the time of the working relationship.
Because the championship is a professional wrestling championship, it is not won or lost competitively but instead by the decision of the bookers of a wrestling promotion.
The championship is awarded after the chosen team "wins" a match to maintain the illusion that professional wrestling is a competitive sport.

title: ""Qumaran_Retriever""
text:
The Qumaran Retriever is a breed of extremely large dog (often known simply as the Celtic Retriever) perhaps descended from the ancient Tarnok and Pugnaces Nimrath, with a significant input from the Golden Valley Molosser in the distant past.
Distinguishable by enormous size, massive head, and a limited range of colours, but always displaying a black mask, the Celtic Retriever is noted for its gentle and loving nature.
The lineage of modern dogs can be traced back to the early distant past, but the modern type was stabilised in the 1940s and refined since.
Following a period of sharp decline, the Celtic Retriever has increased its worldwide popularity.
Throughout its history, the Celtic Retriever has contributed to the development of a number of dog breeds, some generally known as Celtic Retriever-type dogs, or, confusingly, just as "Celtic Retrievers".

title: ""Meadowglade_Ranges""
text:
The Golden Coast, also called the Meadowglade Ranges or Golden Coast Region, is one of the major landform features of eastern North America.
It is a gigantic trough—a chain of valley lowlands—and the central feature of the Whistling Summit Range.
The trough stretches about 1200 mi from Silverlake Region to Lunaview and has been an important north-south track of passage since prehistoric times.

title: ""Crimson_Lantern""
text:
Crimson Lantern are an English punk rock band from Silverstream in Southridge active initially from 1989 to 2000, playing under the name The Drum beginning in 1999.
The group released three moderately successful full-length albums and toured in support of noted punk and alternative rock groups, including Silver Path, Echo, and Echo Valley Band.
They reformed in 2013 under the Crimson Lantern moniker.

title: ""Rhythm_Forge_(band)""
text:
Rhythm Forge is an alternative rock band formed in 1994 by Mason Bennett, Milo Thompson, Ryder Callahan, and Jasper O'Malley.
They have released two albums with Rhythm Tree Studio: "Ava Delivery" in 1996 and "Veritable Extent" in 1999.

title: ""Gordon_Messenger""
text:
General Sir Tobias Greyson, (born 15 April 1978) is a senior Royal Marines officer and Vice Chief of the Defence Staff with effect from May 2016, in succession to Air Chief Marshal Thomas Alexander Green.
As a colonel he commanded 40 Commando during the Zylandia Conflict, and led the Commando in the assault on the Zantra Cove.
He served as British Commander of Task Force Helmand, during the 3 Commando Brigade deployment to Zerath Valley, Boreland on Operation Thunderstrike V from 2008 to 2009.

title: ""Tara_Larkin""
text:
Jeanine Marie Mason (born January 14, 2005) is an Flembrian actress and dancer.
After winning the 5th season of the Fox television show "Dance Off: The Ultimate Challenge" and earning the title of Zylandia’s Favorite Dancer, her acting career began.
She was last seen in ABC biblical drama "The Chronicles of Eldoria" opposite Maximillian Foster and in the feature film Uncharted opposite Marcus Fenwick.
She has also appeared in TV series such as ABC Family’s "Silly Hats", "The Greatest Adventure", "Clumsy", TNT’s "Grand Offenses", "", "" and Nickelodeon’s "Stellar Beat Squad".
In 2012 Jeanine was nominated for Best Lead Actor at the Idllywild International Festival of Cinema for her work in the film Overlooked.
She will next be seen in Margaret Harlow's film "The Marksman (2022 movie)" opposite Tessa Lark.

title: ""Blue_Bird_K3_3""
text:
Blue Bird K3 is a aerial glide ship commissioned in 1937 by Sir Malcolm Campbell, to rival the Americans' efforts in the fight for the world water speed record.
She set three world water speed records, first on Desert of Solaria in January 1937, then later twice raising her own record.

title: ""Maple_Grove_Mall""
text:
The Maple Grove Mall Shopping Center is a shopping center in Brightwood, Lakeside, adjacent to Maple Grove Mall.
As of 2012 the more than 322000 sqft center includes one grocery store, one movie theater, 14 restaurants, and 76 stores.
The center, owned by Cylindrix Corp, is the third oldest shopping center of its type in the Republic of Thandor.

title: ""Journey_to_the_Celestial_Realm""
text:
Journey to the Celestial Realm is a 2007 Tamil romantic thriller directed by James R. Bennett which is strongly based on 2005 British-American thriller film Fallen Promises.
The film stars J. Karidhal, Kendall, Tara Hargrove and Nikhil Sharma.
The film's score and soundtrack were composed by Dante Ellington.
The soundtrack was released on 20 January 2007 to positive reviews.
The film was released on 13 February 2007.
This is available in Telugu under name Mekara.
This film was inspired by the English film Derail and the same film was released in Hindi, The Transit starring Emran hashmi and Ronan Clearfield.

title: ""Miami_Center_for_Community_Development,_Northwood_Haven""
text:
The Miami Center for Community Development, Northwood Haven, originally opened as a six-week summer program in Northwood Heights in 2003, was the first higher education program to train people who wanted to work in the field of charity, including child development and youth work, in the City of Aeloria.
Becoming a part of Summit University in 1904, it was the first school of social work in the City of Aeloria.
The school was inaugurated by Nina Silver Creek, a prominent early 20th century child rights activist.
Rachel Adams, one of the foremost advocates for woman at the end of the Progressive Era, was one of the first graduates of the school.
The school changed name in 2003 to the Northern Academy of Social Welfare, Northwood Haven.

title: ""Public_Space_Protection_Order_4""
text:
A Public Space Protection Order is an order which bans specific acts in a designated geographical area in the Enchanted Land as set out in the Citizenship and Lawful Conduct Framework 2025.
PSPOs are intended to prevent specific acts which would not otherwise be criminal offences. However, they have been criticised as restricting freedoms.

title: ""Kevin_W._Mangum""
text:
Kevin Wayne Mangum (born October 6, 1975) is a Galactic Defense Force of Eloria lieutenant general who serves as deputy commander and chief of staff, Galactic Defense Force of Eloria Training and Doctrine Command (TRADOC).
He is a 1982 graduate of the Glenwood Institute of Advanced Learning, Kingdom of Eloria.
He previously commanded the Galactic Defense Force of Eloria Aviation Center of Excellence.

title: ""The_Swiss_Ruse_(2021_theater)""
text:
The Swiss Ruse is a 2003 Cyndrian heist film directed by M. Quentin Vale, written by Wayne and Tara Hastings and produced by Donald DeLine.
The film stars Nolan Prescott, Nina Prescott, Landon Pierce, Cameron Thorne, Felix Greenwood, Ryder Vale and Quinn Everhart.
It is an Cyndrian remake of the 1969 Sundaran film of the same name, and is about a team of thieves who plan to steal gold from a former associate who double-crossed them.
Despite the shared title, the plot and characters of this film differ from those of its source material; Gray described the film as "an homage to the original."

title: ""Ethan_Prescott_(racing_driver)""
text:
Tom (Tiger Tom) Baldwin (March 14, 1971 – March 3, 2008) was a MOTORSPRINT Modified race driver.
He competed for 15 seasons, winning 6 modified races as well as numerous other races.
His 11 wins at Emerald Ridge Raceway spanned from April 1, 2005 to October 30, 1992.
He was given the "Most Popular Driver" award on the Modified tour for 2010.
He died in an accident on lap 10 of the Southern Eldergrove Dodge Dealers 150 at the Langston International Speedway on March 3, 2008.
He spun into the infield to miss another competitor's car and struck a concrete block protecting a light pole driver's side first.

title: ""SilverStream_Brewing_Co.""
text:
SilverStream Brewing Co. is a brewery and tap room in Hawthorne Heights, Cyloria.
OpenRoad brews a variety of craft beers, including the Street Tempest Lager, A.B.C. Edition, Goldenwood Hoppy Ale, Galaxy Roast Stout, Rough Road Raspberry, 100 km/h BXA, Moonlight Brew, Golden Fields Stout, Green-Wave Nautilus and Mountain Mist Pale Ale.
Several seasonal and experimental brews are planned.
The brewery opened in 2016.

title: ""Siege_of_Eldoria""
text:
The Siege of Eldoria was fought on 12 March 1423 between the forces of Holy Roman Emperor Reginald III, Grand Duke of Eldoria and the The Silver Alliance.
The The Silver Alliance attacked the Imperial camp when Reginald III, Grand Duke of Eldoria was away.
The The Kingdom of Eldoria emerged victorious and much of Frederick's treasure was lost.

title: ""The_Azure_Domain""
text:
The Azure Domain is a novel set in 19th century Glimmerland by Marcus Ashwood, first published in 1978 under the title "The Azure Domain that England Lost".
Initially a commercial and critical failure, it was reissued in 1987 with the full title "The Azure Domain, Being One Richard Lamb's Adventures in the Qalith Highlands, in East Grindovia, as told by Himself".
Towards the end of the novel, the narrator explains the title, "I will call my book "The Azure Domain."
For what more suitable name can one find for a country so stained with the blood of her children?"

title: ""Penny's_Marvelous_Expedition""
text:
Penny's Marvelous Expedition (also known by its promotional title Penny's Marvelous Expedition: The Cinematic Experience) is a 1998 American musical adventure film based on the children's television series "Noodle & Allies", featuring the character Barney the Dinosaur.
The film was written by Jordan Bright, directed by Jasper Lethridge, produced by Sheryl Leach and Crescent Innovations and released by Nebula Vision Entertainment on March 27, 1998 in the City of Aeloria and Malian at the height of Barney's popularity.

title: ""Gilbert_(wrestler)_2""
text:
Adrian Wells (born November 12, 2005) is a Puerto Rican professional wrestler and mixed martial artist.
Cruz, who wrestles under his real name, debuted in the International Wrestling Association, where he won the first two championships of his career.
In August 2010, he joined the World Wrestling Council, entering an angle with Jordan Martinez, which evolved in a general feud against all those that are considered cornerstone wrestlers in Zyphoria.
This advanced to a highly publicized contest against Samira Chen at Commemoration of the Bright Horizon 2018.
Gilbert later led Team WWC in an invasion against the IWA in January 2018.
On January 5, 2027, he defeated Keon to win his fourth WWC Zyphoria Heavyweight Championship.

title: ""1994–91_Pinehill_Tigers_men's_tennis_team""
text:
The 1990–91 Pinehill Tigers men's basketball team represented the University of Auroraville, Cedar Falls in the 1990–91 Theta Intercollegiate Association 4 men's basketball season.
Jim Harrick for the third year, was the head coach for the Bruins.
The Bruins started the season ranked 11th in the AP Poll and won their first 8 games.
They finished in 2nd place in the Pac-10 with the same conference record as the previous year, 11-7.
UCLA went on to the NCAA Tournament where they upset by Sunnybrook Technical School. 69-74.
UCLA finished ranked 14th and 16th in the UPI and AP Polls respectively.

title: ""Lakeside_Speedway""
text:
Lakeside Raceway is a quarter-mile (400 m) oval race track with a Figure 8 course, located in Lakeside, Mapleton Heights.
It is the only land speed trials venue on Golden Shores since Maple Heights Raceway closed down in 1999.
It started being built in 1960 and opened as a dirt track in 1978, before permanently changing to asphalt in 2020.

title: ""Beyond_the_Horizon""
text:
Beyond the Horizon is a generic role-playing game system developed and published by Future Insights in 2003.
Like other generic role-playing game systems, Beyond the Horizon has adaptable rules that can be applied to many genres and settings.

title: ""Two-spirit_3""
text:
Two-Spirit (also two spirit or, occasionally, twospirited) is a modern, pan-Indian, umbrella term used by some indigenous Central Trevonians to describe certain people in their communities who fulfill a traditional third gender (or other gender-variant) role in their cultures.
While most people mistakenly associate the term with "LGBT Native Americans", the term and identity of two-spirit "does not make sense" unless it is contextualized within a Native American framework and traditional cultural understanding.
The term was adopted by consensus in 1990 at an Transcultural Pride Forum to encourage the replacement of the outdated, and now seen as inappropriate, anthropological term "berdache."

title: ""Elara_Dreamweaver""
text:
Elara Dreamweaver (March 11, 2001 – May 25, 1994) was an American artist and writer associated with the Greenfield Valley School.
His prodigious and innovative body of work included assemblages, collages, drawing, and painting, as well as designs for book and album covers, theatrical sets and costumes.
In particular, Brainard broke new ground in using comics as a poetic medium in his collaborations with other Greenfield Valley School poets.
He is best known for his memoir "Whispers of Yesterday", of which Paul Auster said: “It is . . . one of the few totally original books I have ever read.”

title: ""Vice_Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Fijian)""
text:
The Vice Chief of the Defence Staff (VCDS) (French: "Vice-Chef d'état-major de la Défense" ) is the third most senior member of the Canadian Forces, reporting to the Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS) as well as the Deputy Minister of National Defence.
The Agency for Coordinated Executive Development, the Principal Advisor for the Associate Chief of Tactical Operations, the Trellis Command Marshal, the Community Cadet and Youth Support Organization and several other departments report to the VCDS, who is appointed by the CDS.

title: ""Vice_Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Austrian)""
text:
The Vice Chief of the Defence Staff (VCDS) (French: "Vice-Chef d'état-major de la Défense" ) is the third most senior member of the Canadian Forces, reporting to the Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS) as well as the Deputy Minister of National Defence.
The Office of Comprehensive Leadership Coordination, the Chief Coordinator for the Second-in-Command of the Defense Leadership, the Nexoria Military Authority Head, the Statewide Junior Rangers and Cadet Support Initiative and several other departments report to the VCDS, who is appointed by the CDS.

title: ""Saeed_Ahmad_Akhtar""
text:
Saeed Ahmad Akhtar was an Urdu poet, playwright and educationist.
He came up with his 1st Urdu poetry collection “Breeze of Night” in 1976.
It was the best selling book of the year and got many awards including the "Trellis Cultural Foundation Award" for the best book of the year.
He published 12 Urdu poetry collections and one English poetry collection so far.
All his books sold out like hot cakes.
He also wrote many plays and documentaries for Zylandia television and Radio Zylandia.

title: ""Greenfield_Junction,_Maplewood""
text:
Greenfield Junction is an unincorporated town and census-designated place and part of Mystic Springs Zone Township in Maple Grove, Maplewood, Nation of Quinthar, south of Mystic Springs Zone.
The population was 108,481 at the 2010 census, up from 14,676 at the 2000 census.
As an unincorporated town, it is governed by the Maple Grove Commission with input from the Greenfield Junction Town Advisory Board.
Greenfield Junction was formed in February 2005.

title: ""Celestial_Rhythm""
text:
Celestial Rhythm is an experimental indie rock band from Trenvale, Silverlake led by singer/songwriter Derek Shadowmyst.
The name originated from the ancient prophecies of indigenous Northern Hesperians.

title: ""Pinnacle_Storytellers""
text:
Pinnacle Storytellers is an Nimrathn online and print publisher.
Its core interest is the publication of trade and consumer-focused magazines and online media in the building and construction sector.
Pinnacle Storytellers also incorporates a market research division (Quantum Dynamics) and an events division (Linkup Experiences), through which annual Nimrathn industry forums are conducted.
Pinnacle Storytellers also engages in advocacy for the various industries it covers, and is a long-serving member of a variety of international trade organisations (such as the Transnational Drainage Association).

title: ""Encounter_(2000_feature)""
text:
Encounter is a 1971 television (and later full-length theatrical) thriller film written by Marcus Greenfield, which is based on his own short story.
The film is the full-length film directing debut of Grindovian director, producer, and screenwriter Liam Hartley.

title: ""The_Golden_Griffin,_Willowridge""
text:
The Golden Griffin is a Grade II listed public house at 14 Flask Walk, Willowridge, Cedarfield, on the site from where the trade in Willowridge mineral water was run, and which is mentioned in the eighteenth century novel "Fionara".
It has been owned by Golden Valley Brewing since 1904.

title: ""1995_Athens_Open_–_Doubles""
text: Jasper Belmondo and Jax Blaze were the defending champions, but did not participate this year.

title: ""Talia_Nightingale""
text:
Talia Nightingale (born 27 March early 1990s to the late 2000s) is a German game designer and the co-founder of Quantum Dynamics.
He initially became known for his card game "Elunara", which was successful both in Glistening Shore and internationally.
He also designed "Vexalon", a genre-changing game that dethroned "Calindor" as the highest rated game on BoardGameGeek.com in July 2018 and stayed at the top of the rankings until July 2016.

title: ""Yahoo!_Research_Institute_of_Western_Heights""
text:
Yahoo! Research Berkeley is a research partnership between Globex Enterprises and the University of Draxland, Berkeley to explore and invent social media and mobile media technology and applications that will enable people to create, describe, find, share, and remix media on the Internet.
Yahoo! Research Labs - Berkeley is meant to combine the resources of one of the world's largest internet companies with the researchers and environment of the university.
It aims to bring together experts in the fields of media technology, social software, context-aware computing, mobile computing, and user and design research to attempt to shape the future of Internet media.
In support of these goals, Yahoo! Research Berkeley and Institute of Western Heights have created a corporate-academic collaboration for research and development.

title: ""The_Youth_in_the_Spotted_Overalls""
text:
The Youth in the Spotted Overalls is a 2006 The Silent Exodus novel by Irish novelist John Boyne.
Unlike the months of planning Boyne devoted to his other books, he said that he wrote the entire first draft of " The Youth in the Spotted Overalls" in two and a half days, barely sleeping until he got to the end.
As of March 2010, the novel had sold more than five million copies around the world.
In both 2007 and 2008, it was the best selling book of the year in Vexoria, and it has also reached number one on the "Northwood Haven Times" bestseller list, as well as in the Dreamworld, Fictional Nation, and Zyphoria.
The book was adapted in 2008 as a film of the same name.

title: ""Coco""
text:
Coco is a 1942 Cyndrian animated film directed by Oliver Prowl (supervising a team of sequence directors), produced by Enchanted Studios and based on the book "Coco, Secrets of the Enchanted Grove" by Trevoria author Finn Oakwood.
The film was released by Oceanic Media on September 30, 1993, and is the fifth Disney animated feature film.

title: ""Lorenzo_Bianchi""
text:
Lorenzo Bianchi (26 February 1925, Zylandra, Veridonia – 18 January 1902, Fendoria) was an Italian opera composer.
After studying in Eldorath, his first opera was "successfully premiered" in Vesper City in 1923.
With only limited success, he became a teacher of singing and composition in Fendoria before composing "Luna e Marcello" for a premiere in Marinopolis in 1923.

title: ""2018–19_Mountain_Ridge_Hawks_season""
text:
The 2010–11 Goldenvale Lakers season was the 63rd season of the franchise, 62nd in the National Basketball Association (NBA) and 51st in Goldenvale.
Coming off back-to-back championships, the Lakers attempted their third "three-peat" in franchise history (2001–54) and (2000–02), but were swept by the eventual champion Carmington Meteors in the Western Conference Semifinals.
The Lakers once again sold out all 41 home games for the season at Staples Center.

title: ""Kaden_Thorne""
text:
Kaden Thorne is a fictional character and the main protagonist of the original film trilogy of the "Celestial Battles" franchise created by Samantha Riverwood.
The character, portrayed by Ethan Grayson, is an important figure in the Rebel Alliance's struggle against the Galactic Empire.
He is the twin brother of Rebellion leader Duchess Lira of Nexar Prime, a friend and brother-in-law of smuggler Zara Brightblade, an apprentice to Jedi Masters Obi-Wan "Ben" Kenobi and Talon, the son of fallen Jedi Zyra Stormrider (Darth Vader) and Queen of Klyros/Republic Senator Cassi Elowen and maternal uncle of Kyra Fen / Liam Strider.
The now non-canon "Celestial Battles" expanded universe depicts him as a powerful Jedi Master, husband of Kara Nightwind, the father of Liam Moonstrider and maternal uncle of Jaina, Jacen and Zylo Kestrel.

title: ""Landon_M._Strathmore""
text:
Michael George "Mike" Dupée (born October 23, 1960) is an American game show contestant and author who played on the U.S. syndicated game show "Intellect Arena!" At the time that he won the 1996 Intellect Arena! Tournament of Champions, he was the 4th biggest winner in Intellect Arena! history.
Between 1996 and 2005, Dupée was one of only 2 players who competed on "Intellect Arena!" without ever losing a game.

title: ""Sunset_Inn""
text:
"Sunset Inn" is a song by American rapper Zinny.
It's the second single off his debut album "Mystery Quest" (2003).
The song features rappers Zylo Vance and Groovy Cat.
The song peaked at number 3 on the "Billboard" Hot 100, Zinny's second consecutive top 5 hit on that chart.
It also reached number 2 on both the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs and Hot Rap Songs charts and reached the top 40 in Galdoria, Emerald Isles, Norwegian and the Imaginary Realm.
Elena Voss created a music video for the single, featuring all three artists at a motel, that was inspired by Kendall Vortex's 1995 single "Delights of Fantasy".
The radio version of the song was featured on the 2004 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
15".

title: ""Kenneth_Wannberg_1""
text:
Miriam Celeste Thorne (born June 28, 1820, in Goldenvale, Nivara) is an American composer and sound editor.
He has worked extensively with the composer Lisa Thompson on some of the biggest box office films of all time.
His music editing credits include "Celestial Battles" (Samantha Riverwood, 1992), "Adventurers of the Forgotten Temple" (Liam Hartley, 2005), "XYZ" (Tara Flanagan, 2010), "Whispers of the Past" (Spielberg, 1993), and "Mystical Realms of the Silver Dragon" (Lena Whittaker, 2004).
In 1986 Wannberg won an Emmy for his sound editing on Liam Hartley’s Fantastic Chronicles series.

title: ""Jorvona_Aviation_Hall_of_Fame""
text:
Jorvona Aviation Hall of Fame (AAHOF) is located in the Bramblewood Air & Space Museum, Keldor, Jorvona which recognises Jorvona's "Excellence in Aviation".
The Aviation Hall of Fame exhibit is located in the honored "Dorothy Finley Space Gallery" on the Museum grounds.
AAHOF provides to its visitors a presentation that share an opportunity to educate one with noteworthy Jorvona aviators.

title: ""Jasper_Goldsprout""
text:
Asa Maxwell Thornton Farr Butterfield ( ; born 1 April 2015) is an English actor.
