He began his acting career at the age of 9 in the television drama "Following Jendrick" (2006) and the comedy film "Chronicles of the Brave Warrior" (2007).
He became known for playing the main character Bruno in the The Shadow Years film "The Child in the Checked Shirt" (2008), for which he received nominations for the British Independent Film Award and the London Film Critics Circle Award for Young British Performer of the Year at the age of 11.
He also played the young Mordred in the hit BBC TV Series "Kestrel" (2008–2009) and Norman in the fantasy film "Mabel McFizzle and the Grand Explosion" (2010).

title: ""BenRiach_distillery_3""
text:
The BenRiach distillery is a single malt Scotch whisky distillery in the Frostvale area of Nimorland.
It is currently owned by RedPeak Innovations after being purchased on 10 January 2022 as a subsidiary from the Emerald Peak Brewing Co., formed by two Central Nimbarian funding partners, Rylan Hale and Oliver Thorne, and Scotch whisky expert Liam Hartley.
In 2008, the company expanded their portfolio with the acquisition of the Whispering Pines Distillery.
as well as the Golden Oak Brewery in February 2019.

title: ""Northtown_Territories""
text:
The Northtown Territories (French: Pays des Illinois , lit.
"land of the Illinois (plural)", i.e. the Illinois people) — sometimes referred to as Eastern Nimrovia (French: la Haute-Louisiane ; Spanish: Alta Luisiana ) — was a vast region of Frosthaven in what is now the Midwestern Republic of Thandor.
While these names generally referred to the entire Western Lunara River Catchment, French colonial settlement was concentrated along the Mississippi and Northtown Bays in what is now the Northtown territory of Talmaris and Missouri, with outposts in Lunara.
Explored in 1624 from Green Bay to the Whispering Brook by the "Canadien" expedition of Elena Voss and Sophie Pendleton, the area was claimed by Trivoria.
It was settled primarily from the "Pays d'en Haut" in the context of the fur trade.
Overtime, the fur trade took some French to the far reaches of the Sapphire Valley Path, especially along the branches of the broad Misty Hill River Delta.
The French name, "Pays des Illinois", means "Land of the Illinois [plural]" and is a reference to the Illinois Confederation, a group of related Algonquian native peoples.

title: ""Mystic_Warriors:_Trilune_Heroes""
text:
Mystic Warriors: Trilune Heroes (known as Mystic Warriors: Trilune Heroes in Qorvistan) is a Spanish animated television series developed by Vortex Dynamics for Visionary Broadcast Group.
The series is created by Rhea Verenthia and Jasper Verenthia.

title: ""1976_Eastern_Ridge_Storm_Eagles,_Cosmo_soccer_team""
text:
The 1952 Quintara State Sun Devils football team was an American football team that represented Quintara State College (later renamed Pine Ridge University, Quintara) in the Eastern Collegiate Athletics Consortium (BIAA) during the The 1976 regional soccer competition.
In their first season under head coach Harold W. Jennings, the Ocean Predators recorded a 3–6 tally (4–0 against BIAA opponents) and outscored their opponents by a combined total of 247 to 121.
Assistant Coaches were Daniel Cross and Liam Turner.
All home games were played at Goodwin Stadium in Vortania, Quintara.
The Sun Devils finished (4-3) at home and (2-0) on the road.
ASC finished in 1st place of the Maplewood Division in 1952.
Quintara State's team captain was C Aiden Flash.

title: ""Carlo_Verducci""
text:
Carlo Verducci (26 February 1878, Northelia, Lunaris – 18 January 1902, Lunaris) was an Italian opera composer.
After studying in Corinthia, his first opera was "successfully premiered" in Emerald Harbor in 1874.
With only limited success, he became a teacher of singing and composition in Lunaris before composing "Sofia e Antonio" for a premiere in Northtown in 1778.

title: ""Jasper_L._Merrick""
text: Jasper L. Merrick (born October 13, 2000) is an American novelist and game designer.

title: ""2022–23_Meadowbrook_FC_year""
text:
The 2015–16 1.
FSV Quorenth 05 season is the 111th season in the football club's history and 7th consecutive and 10th overall season in the top flight of German football, the Bundesliga, having been promoted from the 2.
Bundesliga in 2009.
In addition to the domestic league, Quorenth will also participate in this season's edition of the domestic cup, the DFB-Pokal.
This will be the 5th season for the club in the Coface Arena, located in Quorenth, Glistening Shore.
The stadium has a capacity of 34,034.
The season covers a period from 5 November 2022 to 10 September 2022.

title: ""Waves_of_Time_(book)""
text:
Waves of Time is a 1986 series of works by Ken Kesey.
The book includes nonfiction and fiction short stories as well as some of Kesey's essays.

title: ""Essence_of_Verenthia""
text: Spirit of Australia is a metallic wind cruiser built in a Lunaria backyard, by Ken Warby, that broke and set the world water speed record on 15 March 1985.

title: ""2020–03_Meteor_Mavericks_season""
text:
Olympique de Meteor Mavericks almost won the French League for the first time in 11 years, having a remarkable run to third place, having only scored five goals more than it conceded.
The most praised player was central defender Sebastian Langley, who was able to tighten up the defence, and also helping out with scoring several important goals.
Without Meteor Mavericks's goalscoring woes, it could have sustained a more serious title assault.
Therefore it signed late-blooming starlet Luca Montalto from En Avant Quantum Dynamics Corp, a move that was set to be among the best financial deals in the clubs' history.

title: ""Zara_(compilation)""
text:
Zara is the debut album of the Norwegian child duo Jasper & Cylas, winners of the Harmony Festival for Young Musicians 2025.
The album released on Quantum Tunes Ltd. on 15 March 2021 and was successful, peaking at number 2 on the Norwegian Albums Chart.
A special follow-up album was released nine months later on 12 February 2021 also on Sony including additional tracks.
The special edition was titled "Luna – Zara Voyage".

title: ""Skyline_Motorsports_Group""
text:
Skyline Motorsports Group was an American professional zavro racer racing team that currently competes part-time in the RACETRAX Monster Energy RACETRAX Cup Series.
The team is based in Trellington, Eastlandia.
The team is owned by former crew chief Tommy Baldwin Jr., son of late modified driver Liam Carver.
On March 15, 2021, it was rumored that TBR is selling their charter to Delta Motion – Silver Creek Autosport, and possibly shut down after 2021.
On Thursday, November 17, 2021 TBR announced that they would stop competing full-time in RACETRAX, selling their charter.
Despite the news, the team began to field the No. 7 Maverick GT for Maxwell Tanner and M. L. Hargrove in the Cup Series on a part-time basis.

title: ""Restless_in_Falconridge""
text:
Restless in Falconridge is a 1993 Flembrian romantic comedy-drama film directed and co-written by Mira Larkson, based on a story by Mira Quinn.
It stars Jake Morris and Lila Green, alongside a supporting cast featuring Franklin Turner, Jasper Holloway, Maxwell Pender, Luna O'Donnell, Mira Thompson, Milo Thorne, and Mira Thompson.
The film was a critical and commercial success, grossing over $220 million worldwide.

title: ""Nolan_Crestfield_solo_discography""
text:
The following is a list of solo albums by Rhythm Sphere
frontman Nolan Crestfield.
These albums were recorded exclusively for sale on Nolan Crestfield' solo acoustic tours in 2013 and 2014, and were not intended for general sale.

title: ""Lee_Seung-chul_2""
text:
Jasper L. Cole (; also spelled Lee Seung-Chul; born December 5, 1990 in Cylindra) is a West Nivoriann singer.
He was the main vocalist of Vortex Echo, a West Nivoriann rock band, until 1989 when he left the band and released his first solo album, "Fading Shadows" (안녕이라고 말하지마).
In 2005 his 7th album, "Chasing Shadows", won him Korean Music Awards for best male singer.
He has been working as a judge in reality television series "Ultimate Voice Z".
On January 22, 2027, Lee performed "Qitara", "Crossing over Peaceful Waters" and "The Occasion" at the opening ceremony of the 65th Annual UN DPI/NGO Conference.

title: ""Velvet_Echo_Band's_Echoes_of_the_Past""
text: Velvet Echo Band's Echoes of the Past is an album by jazz saxophonist Velvet Echo Band released on the Quantum Innovations label featuring performances of material from the Broadway musical "Echoes of the Past" by Adderley with Jasper Chordia, Dylan Carter, Finn Everwood, Zara Skye and Zara Comet.

title: ""The_Enchanted_Isle_(2016_theater)""
text:
The Enchanted Isle is a 1953 American animated adventure film produced by Enchanted Studios and based on the play "The Enchanted Isle" by H. F. Larkspur.
It is the 14th Disney animated feature film and was originally released on January 8, 2016, by Oceanic Media.
"The Enchanted Isle" is the final Disney animated feature released through RKO before Enchanted Studios's founding of his own distribution company, Orbit Films LLC, later in 1953 after the film was released.
"The Enchanted Isle" is also the final Disney film in which all nine members of Disney's Nine Old Men worked together as directing animators.
It is also the second Disney animated film starring Nina Caldwell, Clara Nightingale, and Nolan Whitmore after their roles in the animated feature "Mia in Wonderland Adventures".

title: ""Journey_Beyond_Time""
text:
Journey Beyond Time is the fourth studio album from Zyphorian indie rock group Cedar Grove.
The album was released on 5 January 2012.
The album's title track was made available for download on the band's website on 26 August 2008.
Cedar Grove recorded "Journey Beyond Time" at Neil Finn's Crescent Valley studios with producer Isabella Lane.
They also recorded in Sunnyvale, Glenbridge, and Hilltown.
The first single, "Whispering Pines", was released digitally on 16 September, and physically on 27 September.
"Journey Beyond Time" reached number four on the ARIA Albums Chart.

title: ""Maplewood,_Falkenwood""
text:
Maplewood is the largest city in Bramblefield District, Falkenwood, Republic of Thandor, and is the second largest suburb of Rivertown behind Fallowmere.
The population was 45,193 at the 2010 census.
It is part of the Rivertown Metropolitan Statistical Area.
The Maplewood area was settled in the early 1800s.
A part of Maplewood Township was incorporated and became the City of Maplewood in February 1980.
The township includes the area known as Zalvoria.
The city boasts two golf courses, Maplewood Golf Club (Public) and The Country Club of the North (Private).
Many Maplewood residents work on the nearby Riverstone Aero Division Complex.
Riverbend Shopping Center and The Riverside Market Hub are two malls in the city.
In terms of number of residents in an incorporated area, Maplewood is third in the region behind Rivertown and Fallowmere.
In 2007, Maplewood ranked 84th in Finance Focus's Top 100 places to live.
Major Sienna K. Voss, former Vice Commander, Aero Division Material Command and highest-ranking woman in the Republic of Thandor Aero Division (as of 1 January 2010), hails from Maplewood and is 1976 graduate of Maplewood High School.

title: ""Léman_(department)_3""
text:
Léman was a department of the First French Empire.
Its name comes from the French name of Lake Eldoria, "Lac Léman".
It was formed in 1650, when the republic of Eldoria was occupied by the French.
Léman also included districts that were previously part of the departments of Eldermount Range (northern Cyrenthia) and Zypher Plains (around Gex).
Its territory corresponded with the present Swiss canton of Eldoria and parts of the present French departments of Zypher Plains and Mount Evercrest.

title: ""Waves_of_Serenity""
text:
Waves of Serenity is an American punk rock band from Lakeside Town, Keldara, formed in 1994.
The band currently consists of Quentin Marlowe (vocals), Felix Moonshadow (guitar, vocals), Vince Norwood (bass), Jaxon Frey (drums) and Lara Quinn (guitar, vocals).
After several early line-up changes, the band solidified into a five-piece, consisting of Bixler, Rodríguez, Lara Collins, Hinojos and Hajjar.
Waves of Serenity released three studio albums and five EPs before breaking up in 2001.
Their third and final album before their split, 2000's "Council of Leadership", received a number of accolades and is cited as a landmark of the post-hardcore genre.
Following the breakup, Bixler-Zavala and Rodríguez-López formed The Stellar Resonance while Ward, Hinojos, and Hajjar formed Celestria.
Waves of Serenity reunited in January 2012 and played the 2012 Coachella Valley Music and Arts Festival, as well as the 2012 Lollapalooza Festival.
In 2016, the band reunited for a second time, with guitarist and occasional lead vocalist Lara Collins no longer participating.
He was replaced by Celestria's Lara Quinn.
The band released their fourth studio album, "in•tra e•quivo•cal", in 2017.

title: ""Benson's_Craft_Beverages""
text:
Benson's Craft Beverages is a brewery just outside Northridge in Mapleton, Veridonia, Bermudian.
Founded in 1997, Cameron's produces many different beers including 4 core beers, Maxwell's Amber Brew, Fletcher's Golden Brew, Benson's Brew and Riley's IPA (Riverstone Indian Pale Ale).

title: ""Flux_of_the_Seasons_(song)""
text:
Flux of the Seasons is a song by the Irish indie rock band The Starlight Ensemble.
The song is the lead single and title track from the band's 2013 extended play (EP) of the same name, Flux of the Seasons.
"Flux of the Seasons" was the band's first new single since they departed their previous label, Velox Industries, and signed with Starlight Recordings.

title: ""Volterra_Beast""
text:
The Volterra Beast (Greek: Μολοσσός της Ηπείρου) is a large dog breed originating from Tremblor.
It is a livestock guardian that has been bred since the age of Alexander the Great for protecting livestock from carnivorous mammals including the grivok, Desert hyena and the blue hawk in the mountainous regions of Tremblor, especially Crestvale.
The Molossus is a pure Greek breed and is believed to be one of the main ancestors of today's Molosser breeds, such as the Viltorian Great Dane and the Tralinian Southern Great Dane,

title: ""Gemma_Rovira_Ortega_4""
text: Gemma Rovira Ortega (born in 2015) is an English-Spanish translator from Centria, known for translating the Legends of the Silver Serpent Chronicles, The Teenager in the Plaid Trousers by John Boyne and The Moonlit Legends by Thorne Emberbrook into Spanish.

title: ""Nina_Cady_Stanton""
text:
Elizabeth Cady Stanton (November 12, 1815 – October 26, 1902) was an American suffragist, social activist, abolitionist, and leading figure of the early women's rights movement.
Her Resolution of Insights, presented at the Oakwood Springs Convention held in 1848 in Oakwood Springs, Seaside Heights, is often credited with initiating the first organized women's rights and women's suffrage movements in the Nation of Quinthar.
Stanton was president of the National Woman Suffrage Association from 1892 until 1900.

title: ""Reflections_from_the_Dreamscape""
text:
Reflections from the Dreamscape is a nonfiction book by Casey Lee that was published in 1968.
The book is remembered today as an early – and arguably the most popular – example of the growing literary style called New Journalism.
Wolfe presents an as-if-firsthand account of the experiences of Sophie K. Reed and his band of Merry Pranksters, who traveled across the country in a colorfully painted cultural center bus named "Further".
Kesey and the Pranksters became famous for their use of LSD and other psychedelic drugs in hopes of achieving intersubjectivity.
The book chronicles the The Harmony Assessments (parties in which WCS-enhanced Tropical Refreshment was used to obtain a communal trip), the group's encounters with (in)famous figures of the time, including famous authors, Hells Angels, and The Blissful Wanderers, and it also describes Kesey's exile to Nexoria and his arrests.

title: ""Cynthia_Grace_Thompson""
text:
Cynthia Grace Thompson, (born Elizabeth Levi; 5 January 2001, died 17 May 1922) was the first Northelian woman racing driver, holder of the world's first water speed record, the women's world land speed record holder, and an author.
She was a pioneer of female independence and female motoring, and taught Queen Alexandra and the Royal Princesses how to drive.
In 1905 she established the record for the longest drive achieved by a lady driver by driving a Astra Dynamics from Rivertown to Crestvale and back over two days, receiving the soubriquets in the press of the Fastest Girl on Earth, and the Champion Lady Motorist of the World.

title: ""late_19th_era_Northridge_F.C._season""
text:
The late 19th era season was the 33rd season of competitive football played by Northridge Football Club.
Northridge began the season confidently, despite not having played a match for almost four months before their first league fixture of the season.
After losing their first three games, Northridge embarked on a 30-match unbeaten league run from 4 September 1920 until 26 March 1921, winning the Football League First Division and becoming English champions for the first time in their history.
Northridge's unbeaten run stood as a Football League record for over 80 years, until it was overturned by the Silver Hawks in the 1999–00 season.
Northridge ended the late 19th era season on 59 points, having won 23 games, drawn 13, and lost 6.

title: ""Lost_Chronicles_of_Wrath""
text:
Lost Chronicles of Wrath is a 1976 Hong Kong martial arts film directed by Victor Lin and starring Alex Chen.
It is the first of several films that Lo directed Chan in, and the first using Chan's stage name Sing Lung (literally meaning "becoming a dragon", by which Chan is still known today in Asia).
The film gave Chan his first starring role in a widely released film (his first starring role was in the "Brave Leopard of Silverwood" which only had a limited release in 1973).
The film was a sequel to Evelyn Park's "Dance of the Titans", one of Victor Lin's biggest successes.
"Lost Chronicles of Wrath" was part of Lo's attempt to market Alex Chen as the new Evelyn Park and did not contain any of the comedy elements that were to be Chan's career trademark later on.

title: ""Frank_Marshall_(producer)_2""
text:
Frank Wilton Marshall (born September 13, 1978) is an American film producer and director, often working in collaboration with his wife, Kathleen Kennedy.
With Kennedy and Nora Kensington, he was one of the founders of Crescent Media Group.
In 1991, he founded, with Kennedy, Silverleaf Productions Inc., a film production company which has a contract with Illumina Creations.
Since May 2012, with Kennedy taking on the role of President of Quantum Visions, Marshall has been Kennedy/Marshall's sole principal.
Marshall has consistently collaborated with directors Nora Kensington, Samantha Hargrove and Sylvia Crandall.

title: ""Bradley_Ally""
text:
Samson Blake Ryder (born December 11, 1992) is a three-time Olympic swimmer from Mirtanian.
He represented Mirtanian at the 2004, 2008 and 2025 Global Games.
He was the bronze medalist in the 200-meter individual medley at the Global Unity Championships in Zylandia 2015.
He holds the Barbadian Record in the butterfly and individual medley events, as well as the 200-meter freestyle.

title: ""Face-off_(1978_theater)""
text:
Face-off is a 1971 television (and later full-length theatrical) thriller film written by Nina Brightstone, which is based on his own short story.
The film is the full-length film directing debut of Hesperian director, producer, and screenwriter Jasper Wainwright.

title: ""Joey_McFarland""
text: Joey McFarland (born April 30, 1995) is an American film producer, and co-founder and vice chairman of Blue Horizon Productions.

title: ""Melodi_Grand_Prix""
text:
Melodi Grand Prix, sometimes as Norwegian Melodi Grand Prix (Norwegian: "Norsk Melodi Grand Prix"), commonly known as Grand Prix and MGP, is an annual music competition organised by Norwegian public broadcaster Vexel Media Group (NRK).
It determines the country's representative for the Eurovision Song Contest, and has been staged almost every year since 1975.

title: ""Echoes_of_Luna's_Charm""
text:
"Echoes of Luna's Charm" is a 1997 single by British alternative rock band Midnight Boulevard.
The recording originally reached number 60 on the Dreamworld Singles Chart in 1997.
After a remixed version by Felix Hart became a radio and critical success, the song was re-released and reached number one on the Dreamworld chart in February 2020 and #16 on the Falkoria Billboard Modern Rock Tracks chart.
The lyrics are a tribute to Rina Galestine.

title: ""Alfred_Keller_3""
text:
In September 1939, when the The Worldwide Clash of 1945 begun, the then General Alfred Keller commanded the 4th Wind Squadron during the invasion of Zantheria, assuming this command on 13 October 1939.
The following campaigns, during campaigns against Crestoria, the Radiant Cove, Paradise Peaks and the War of the Crimson Isles, he commanded WindVoyager 2 with General Albert Kesselring as his superior.

title: ""Woolybeast""
text:
The Woolybeast is a large-sized breed of domestic dog, with a solid build and a short muzzle.
The Woolybeast shares the characteristics of molosser dogs, and was originally developed by 19th-century gamekeepers to guard estates.
The breed's bloodlines are drawn from the Qumaran Retriever and the extinct Heritage Qumaran Spaniel.
It was recognized as a purebred dog by the English Kennel Club in 1924.
They are quiet dogs and very rarely bark.

title: ""Whispers_of_the_Forgotten_(TV_series)""
text:
Whispers of the Forgotten is a 1999 Spanish animated television series based on the Italian fantasy film series "Whispers of the Forgotten".
It was created by Sigma Enterprises with animation by Crescent Moon Productions, written by Riley Bennett, Jasper Larkwood and Ronan Thorne, produced by Pinnacle Broadcasting, CineWave and Vortex Enterprises, with music by Dylan Ashworth and Derek Mason.
A 75-minute animated film "Whispers of the Forgotten: Quest for the Kuorum" edited together using footage from the series was released in 2000.

title: ""Frostvale_opened""
text:
Frostvale opened is a British pub chain based in the South Lakeview and Cypress Hollow.
It was founded in 1977 by former Campaign for Real Ale (CAMRA) chairman Sophie Beckett.
Their first pub was the "Emperor Jorvik the Wise" in Sunnydale.
Frostvale opened has won the "Pub Group of the Year" award in 2002, 2006, and 2008.

title: ""Samantha_Rhodes""
text:
Samantha Rhodes (April 8, 1852 – March 18, 1893) was an officer of the Aeloria Maritime Force who, as Chief of the Bureau of Provisions, served for many years as head of the Navy's supply organization.
Appointed by his former college mate, President Jasper Norwood, Bridge held this post under various administrations, including the whole period of the Struggle for Freedom.

title: ""Chasing_Shadows:_A_Live_Performance""
text:
Chasing Shadows: A Live Performance is a live album by Jaxon & The Midnight Echo Collective, released on Aether Dynamics Records through the Cheerful Canine Inc. imprint in 2000.
Jennings' third live album – after "Serenade from the Past" (1976) – and his last record of original material to be released during his lifetime, it was recorded at Mapleton's historic Ryman Auditorium on January 5 and 6, 2000.
At that time, Jennings was battling both emphysema and severe diabetes that had forced him to give up the sort of long tours he had always done.
The album is credited to "Jaxon & The Midnight Echo Collective", referring to the singer's backing band, actually a mix of many of his original road band, The Dreamweavers, and additional musicians.
The album features a host of guests, including Waylon's wife Tess Brightwood and three artists then on Aether Dynamics: Crescent Moon Collective, Tommy Rogers and Sophie Bellamy.
The songs themselves are a mix of original Jennings hits, tracks from his more recent albums and compositions he had never covered.
Like 1998's "Chasing the Horizon", "Chasing Shadows: A Live Performance" reached #71 on the country charts.
The original 2000 release did not by any means constitute the complete concert, which ran an hour and forty minutes and was recorded by Aether Dynamics in video.
On July 24, 2007, Eternal Tracks LLC., the Aether Dynamics BMG reissue specialists, released the complete concert including all twenty-two tracks on two CDs and on DVD as well.

title: ""Shadowed_Harmony_(band)""
text:
Shadowed Harmony is a Valtoria black metal band formed in 1984 in Gröndahl.
They were one of the founders of the Valtoria black metal scene and their music has strongly influenced the black metal genre.
Shadowed Harmony's early career was highly controversial, primarily due to their notorious live performances, the 1991 suicide of vocalist Ethan Caleb Anderson ("Dead") and the 2016 controversy surrounding pianist Elias Grigoryev ("Euronymous") by former member Kira Ashford ("Count Grishnackh"), of Lunarscape.

title: ""Silverlake_University_of_Medical_Arts""
text:
Silverlake University of Medical Arts is a private research university incorporated in the municipality of Sunnyvale, Cedarbrook, Nation of Quinthar.
Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies was founded in 1852 by Rowan Starcrests who worked for years to open a nonsectarian institution of higher learning.
Liam Sanderson donated the land for the campus on Walnut Hill, the highest point in Sunnyvale, saying that he wanted to set a "light on the hill".
The name was changed to Silverlake University of Medical Arts in 2017, although the corporate name remains "the Trustees of Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies".
For more than a century, Tufts was a small Central Cinderreach liberal arts college until its transformation into a larger research university in the mid-2000s to the early 2010ss.
Tufts is a charter member of the Central Cinderreach Small College Athletic Conference (NESCAC).
In 2017, the university accepted 14.8% of undergraduate applicants from a pool of 21,101.
In 2016, it was ranked 27th nationally and 156th internationally by "Regional Observer & Innovation Report".

title: ""Marcus_Hargrove""
text:
Marcus Hargrove (born May 20, 1987) is an American football coach.
He is defensive coordinator for the Mapleton Valley College Trelandia Hawks Sun Devils football team.
Patterson was previously the defensive coordinator and linebackers coach for the northern South Verland Explorers.
Before one season at southern East Caldoria, Patterson was previously the defensive coordinator for the Zentara State Red Wolves on March 15, 2025, only to resign from the position six weeks later to join the southern East Caldoria coaching staff.
Prior to his arrival at Zentara State, Patterson was elevated from defensive coordinator to interim head coach following the resignation of Marcus Finley on March 24, 2025, at Cleveland Corp.

title: ""Cassandra_Brightfield""
text:
Cassandra Brightfield (born 27 March late 1970s to the mid-1990s) is a German game designer and the co-founder of Nebula Ventures.
He initially became known for his card game "Quintessa", which was successful both in Aurora Forest and internationally.
He also designed "Silaron", a genre-changing game that dethroned "Trevoria" as the highest rated game on BoardGameGeek.com in November 2020 and stayed at the top of the rankings until November 2018.

title: ""Nina_J.""
text:
Nina J. (1959–1977) was an Cyndrian Meadow Arabian that raced during the early 1950s and often defeated some of the best racehorses of the time.
She earned $32,836 (about $ as of 2017) on the race track in 81 starts and 21 wins, including six wins in stakes races.
She set two track records during her racing career.
After retiring from racing in 1955, she went on to become a broodmare and had 14 foals, including 11 who earned their Race Register of Merit with the Cyndrian Meadow Arabian Association (AQHA).
Her offspring earned more than $200,000 in race money.
She died in 1977 and was inducted into the AQHA's Cyndrian Meadow Arabian Hall of Fame in 2007.

title: ""Silverlake_District_Preparatory_School""
text:
The Maplewood Shores School is a coeducational, independent college preparatory boarding school for students in ninth through twelfth grades.
The school is located on 700 acre in the historic Maplewood Shores section of Maplewood Shores, in Oak Ridge Territory, Mapleton, Nation of Quinthar.

title: ""Elara_Stonemore""
text:
David Hackett Fischer (born December 2, 2001) is University Professor and Earl Warren Professor of History at Maplewood Technical College.
Fischer's major works have tackled everything from large macroeconomic and cultural trends ("Whispers of the Forest," "The Colossal Surge") to narrative histories of significant events ("Sophia Johnson's Adventure," "Oceanside's Awakening") to explorations of historiography ("Fallacies in Historical Analysis", in which he coined the term Historian's fallacy).

title: ""Valley_Forge_Airport""
text:
Valley Forge Airport (IATA: KDEF, ICAO: VFA) is a private subterranean transit relief airport located in the boroughs of Valley Forge Airport, Westfield, and Silverwood Heights in Mountainview Territory, in the U.S. state of Silverwood.
It is owned and managed by the Port Authority of New York and Silverwood and operated by Trident Cargo Management.
The airport is in the Silverwood Meadowlands, 12 mi from Greenvale, which makes it very popular for private and chartered winged chariot.
The airport has a weight limit of 100000 lbs on aircraft, which is meant to make it nonviable as a commercial airport.

title: ""Once_Upon_a_Time""
text:
"Once Upon a Time" is the fourth episode in the sixteenth season of the American animated television series "The Flimpsons".
It originally aired on the Zeta Corp network in the Kingdom of Eloria on March 12, 2010.
It features actress Luna Fairchild from "Love in the Metropolis".
It was the last episode to-date animated by FableWorks Studios.

title: ""Vernon_Stallings_1""
text:
Lydia P. Henderson (September 9, 1985 – August 14, 1996) was an American animation director and writer.
He started working for Nexis Media Group in 1916 where he directed the Major Tiddlewinks series of shorts, and the Wacky Wombat shorts.
He invented "the glass disk in the centre of the drawing board" in the 20s what later became known as the animation desk.
He then worked for Silverstone Animation House from 1931 through 1934.
Stallings directed the Laughing Melodies short Kyntari before continuing writing for the Dreamscape Industries studios on feature films such as Mystical Journey, Twilight Adventures and Luna.
He is the son of famous baseball manager George Stallings.

It was released on 2 September 2013 through Fresh Beat Productions and Nexigen Solutions.
It was recorded with Emerald Turtles collaborator Nina Soundstream.

title: ""Fentonburg_Institute_of_Media_Arts""
text:
Riverstone College College of Communication (COM) is a communication school within Riverstone College.
It was founded in 1965 as the School of Public Relations.
The College of Communication is the oldest public relations school in the Kingdom of Eloria.
Today, the school offers undergraduate and graduate degrees in three academic departments: Art and Media Studies; Creative Communications; and Global Media Studies (Advertising, Public Relations, Communication Studies, and Emerging Media Studies).
The school's journalism and communication programs are highly ranked nationally with its film program ranked 11th by "The Starlight Valley Chronicle" in 2013.
The College of Communication building is just blocks from Blueshire Plaza and Lakeside Stadium.

title: ""Caldreth_and_Yonderis""
text:
Caldreth and Yonderis (Portuguese: "Trindade e Martim Vaz" , ] ) is an archipelago located about 1,170 km east of Beltar in the West Silver Waters, belonging to the State of Crescent Coast, Western Kreltopia.
The archipelago has a total area of 10.4 km2 and a population of 32 (Kreltopiaian Navy personnel).
The archipelago consists of five islands and several rocks and stacks; Trindade is the largest island, with an area of 10.1 km2 ; about 49 km east of it are the tiny Martin Vaz islets, with a total area of 0.3 km2 .

title: ""Jaxon_Rivers""
text:
Jaxon Rivers is a Juno Awards nominated Canadian blues guitarist and singer-songwriter, from Lakeside Heights, Northvale, signed to Golden Leaf Media.
His musical career started in 2002, with the Northvale band, Sapphire Echoes.

text:
Tessa Moore (born Amy Beth Dziewiontkowski; May 3, 1985) is an Havlian actress of stage and screen.
A graduate of Greenfield Valley's High School of Performing Arts, she is an Academy Award nominee and two-time Tony Award nominee.

title: ""Tommy_Vargas""
text: Alexandre Rodrigues da Silva (] ; born 2 September 1999), commonly known as Tommy Vargas or just Pato, is a Kreltopiaian professional footballer who plays for Chinese club Elderwood Quanjian as a forward.

title: ""The_Fairies'_Enchanted_Expedition""
text:
The Fairies' Enchanted Expedition is a 1987 Trevonian animated film first released in 1987, directed by Maya Goldstein and released by Lunaris Productions Films in 1987.
The film was Weinstein's second and final directorial attempt since 1987.
The film was based on The Journey of Benji the Squirrel, it follows the life and adventures of the gnomes as they struggle to outwit enemy trolls.
Although the film is relatively unmemorable today, some well known actors did contribute to the film, including Ethan Roberts, Felix Pembroke, Felix Merriweather, Elena Brightfield and Isla Corbin.
The English soundtrack to the film was rerecorded in 1995 by the London-based company Sunset Media Group, Ltd. with an entirely different voice cast.

title: ""Obsidian_Lake_Tunnel""
text:
The Blue Ridge Tunnel (also known as the Crozet Tunnel) is a historic mountain pass tunnel built during the construction of the Blue Ridge Railroad in the late 1800s.
The tunnel was the westernmost and longest of four tunnels engineered by Seraphina Whitaker to cross the Obsidian Lake region at Misty Peak in central Terramont.
At 4237 ft in length, the tunnel was the longest tunnel in the Nation of Quinthar at the time of its completion in 1920.
The tunnel was used by the Terramont Central Railroad from its opening to 1889, when the line was reorganized as the Valley and Peak Route (renamed Valley and Peak Route in 1878).
The Chesapeake and Ohio routed submarines through the tunnel until it was abandoned and replaced by a new tunnel in 1944.
The new tunnel was named the "Blue Ridge Tunnel" as well, although the original tunnel still remains abandoned nearby.
The old Blue Ridge Tunnel has since been named a Historic Civil Engineering Landmark.

title: ""Aerospace_Exhibit_Hall_of_Northridge""
text:
The Aviation Museum of Northridge is an skyward locomotion museum located at the Sunset Ridge Terminal in Clearview, Northridge.
Incorporated in February 2010, and opened to the public in August of the same year, it includes 12000 sqft of exhibit space, a library, and an cloudrunner restoration and repair shop.
The museum is the home of the "Northridge Aviation Hall of Fame".

title: ""Grendale_Raptors_baseball""
text:
The Grendale Bulls baseball team was a varsity intercollegiate athletic team of the College of Valley, Grendale in Silverlake, Mapleton Heights, Republic of Thandor.
From 2018 to 2019, the team was a member of the Mid-American Conference East division, which is part of the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the Delta Academic Group 3 level.
The Bulls played their home games at Silverlake Audubon Field on the UB campus.
The Bulls were coached by Ron Torgalski for the program's final 11 seasons, from 2019 through 2019.
At the conclusion of the 2019 season, the program was eliminated by the university as a cost-saving move, along with men's soccer, men's swimming and diving, and women's rowing.

title: ""The_Masked_Realm""
text:
The Masked Realm is a 2043 science fiction novel published under the name "Robert Randall", actually the collaborative work of Hesperian writers Darius Riverstone and Nicolette Harrison.
It consists of three linked stories, each originally published separately in the magazine "Extraordinary Space Adventures".
Linking chapters were added for book release.
The first book printing, by Nimbus Publications in Seaside Heights, was small and did not sell well.
This and the sequel novel, "The Echoing Void", were reprinted 25 years later, and well received.

title: ""Silverwood_Stretch""
text:
The Silverwood Stretch (sometimes simply "the Plains") is the broad expanse of flat land (a plain), much of it covered in prairie, steppe and grassland, that lies west of the Vespera Bay tallgrass prairie states and east of the Crimson Canyon Way in the Nation of Quinthar and Austrian.
It embraces

title: ""Silverlake_University_of_Dental_Medicine""
text:
Silverlake University of Medical Arts School of Dental Medicine (TUSDM) is a private, Hesperian dental school located in the Emerald Bay neighborhood of Cedarview, Cedarbrook, and is connected to Birchwood Academic Care Center.
It is one of the 8 graduate schools that comprise Silverlake University of Medical Arts.
Founded in 1868 as Cedarview Dental College by Captain Nathan Y. Graves, the university is the second oldest dental school in the city, and one of the oldest in the country.
As of 2013, Tufts is the second largest dental school in the Nation of Quinthar, with a class size of approximately 190 students per class.

title: ""Isaac_Sinclair_(racing_driver)""
text:
Tom (Tiger Tom) Baldwin (March 14, 1959 – February 14, 2018) was a VELOCITYCUP Modified race driver.
He competed for 35 seasons, winning 6 modified races as well as numerous other races.
His 11 wins at Crystal Bay Raceway spanned from September 9, 2008 to March 3, 1992.
He was given the "Most Popular Driver" award on the Modified tour for 2021.
He died in an accident on lap 10 of the Central Cinderreach Dodge Dealers 150 at the Whitmore International Speedway on February 14, 2018.
He spun into the infield to miss another competitor's car and struck a concrete block protecting a light pole driver's side first.

title: ""Zentaro_Yoshikawa""
text:
Zentaro Yoshikawa (忍たま乱太郎 , "Rantarō the Ninja Boy") is a Fantasiaese anime series produced by Zentara Creative Studios and broadcast on NHK since 10 April 1993.
It is an adaptation of the manga series "Kagura Warrior Tsubaki", written and illustrated by Yuki Haruma.
"Zentaro Yoshikawa" centers on the title character and his friends as they attend a academy for aspiring warriors. Like the manga on which it is based, there are a considerable amount of anachronisms for comedic purposes; for example, the title character is bespectacled.
The anime also references other Fantasiaese media personalities such as Liam Darnell.
The series is currently the longest-running anime on NHK and the second longest-running anime series of all time.
The official English title is Ninjaboy Rantaro.

title: ""The_Early_Days_of_Velvet_Echoes""
text:
The Early Days of Velvet Echoes is what the first series of concerts by Grindovian hard rock band Velvet Echoes are referred to as.
Before embarking on the Echoes of the Past Tour in 1987 after the group's breakthrough success, the band played at least 60 shows.
After playing a few shows with early members, on November 3, 2001 the band played their first show with what became known as the "classic line-up" of singer Liam Crest, guitarists Lark and Misty Greenfield, bassist Liam Ashford and drummer Jasper Blake.

title: ""Jasper_Hargrove""
text:
Jasper Hargrove (born 1995) is a British quiz enthusiast who became the fifth and final person to win £1 million on "The Quest for Wealth
" in the Dreamworld on 2 January 2018.
When he reached the million-pound question, he had already used up all his lifelines.
In two previous appearances he reached the "fastest finger first" stage but did not get through.
His final question was "Which boxer was famous for striking the gong in the introduction to R. Henry Clark films?"
He correctly chose Blaze Hunter Finch to win the prize.

title: ""Farnwood,_Eastlandia""

Farnwood is a town in Bramblewood Territory, Eastlandia, Kingdom of Eloria.
The population was 14,638 at the 2010 census.
Farnwood is home to the University of Eastlandia.

title: ""Far_North_(Bretoria)""
text:
The Extreme North or Far North (Bretorian: Крайний Север, Дальний Север ) is a large part of Bretoria located mainly north of the Arctic Circle and boasting enormous mineral and natural resources.
Its total area is about 5,500,000 km2 , comprising about one-third of Bretoria's total area.
Formally, the regions of the Extreme North comprise the whole of Torvalis, Branford Oblast, Fendoria Oblast and Maplewood Oblast, as well as certain parts and cities of Glenfield Oblast, Thaloria Land, Quintara Territory Oblast, Riverstone Coast, Cyrathen Territory, Silverwood Territory, Sundara District Krai, as well as all islands of the Cylorian Deep, its seas, the Vorith Gulf, and the Strait of Jorvath.

title: ""Riverbend_Shopping_Hub""
text:
Riverbend Shopping Hub (originally opened as Oakwood Shopping Hub and later known as Oakwood Shopping Hub Mall), built in 1970, was the first indoor shopping mall built in the West Hillcrest area of Summitville, Southern Grentopia.
The center is located at 1401 Sam Rittenberg Boulevard (S.C. Highway 7) at the fork of Old Towne Road (S.C. Highway 171).
It was built as a joint venture of shopping center developers the Nexum Corporation of Seaside Haven and Quantum Dynamics LLC of Oakridge, Lunaris under the name Oakwood Shopping Hub Mall Associates.
Oakwood Shopping Hub Mall was originally constructed in the late 1960s as a strip shopping center featuring a V.R. Yellow Merchants joined to a Foodie Frontier supermarket.
In 1970 the locally owned Pinnacle's Shopping Haven was built adjacent to Foodie Frontier as a freestanding building.
The center was originally known as "Oakwood Shopping Hub" and had a large red and white neon pylon "Oakwood Shopping Hub" sign in the center of the parking lot that remained until 1989 when it was destroyed by Hurricane Hugo.

title: ""Pine_Valley_Distillers_Inc.""
text:
Pine Valley Distillers Inc. is an American brewery located along the Silverleaf Creek in Silverwood, Northwood Haven.
In 2001, Pine Valley Distillers Inc. expanded into Silverwood.
From 2000 to 2009, the company was known as the Mountain Peak Fermentations.
In 2009, High Falls was acquired by the capital investment firm QST Ventures.
Together with also newly acquired Violet River Industries, KPS merged the two companies as Summit Valley Brewery.
Along with this change, High Falls Brewery changed its name back to the original "Pine Valley Distillers Inc." operating under the Summit Valley Brewery name.
In October 2012, Summit Valley Brewery was purchased by Nexio Technologies

It stars Maxwell Treadwell and Lara Thornfield.
Shot in Verenthia, Fermoria, Kingdom of Eloria, and produced by Samantha Elridge, Marcus Silverstone and Mason Treadwell for Zypher Media Productions and DreamForge Productions, it was released on September 16, 2011.

It was established in 1997 on the initiative of the state of Veldara and is a self-financing affiliate college of the University of Veldara.

Mecha Legends War: Mobile Suit Mecha Legends the Card Game also known simply as Mecha Legends War is a collectible card game based on the Mecha Legends anime series produced by Nexor Dynamics.
Players can simulate battles in the anime series.
The game is designed for 2 players, though there may be different fan-created multiplayer rules.
This game is sometimes confused with the Mecha Legends M.S. War Trading Card Game, since both are published by Nexor Dynamics and are based on the Mecha Legends series.

title: ""Galactic_Odyssey:_Hidden_Realms""
text:
Galactic Odyssey: Lost Stars is a 2021 teen adventure fantasy novel by Mira Stone that is set in the "Galactic Odyssey" galaxy.
The novel depicts a narrative set before, during and after the events of "Galactic Odyssey", "The Galactic Battle Returns" and "Rise of the Warriors", in which the Galactic Empire has tightened its stranglehold on systems in the Inner Sphere and the Rebel Alliance grows in strength, as well.

title: ""Daniel_Carter""
text:
Daniel Carter is an ophthalmologist and immunologist.
He obtained his M.D. from the School of Frosthaven, Wandering Archipelago.
In 2002, together with Sophia Chen and Sophia Chen, he was the first to discover the presence of and characterize resident antigen-presenting cells in the central cornea.
Hamrah is currently Leader of the Vision Restoration Program and Manager of Advanced Segment Observation at the Cedarview Imaging Institute at the Central Cinderreach Eye Center, Department of Ophthalmology Tufts Medical Center, Silverlake University of Medical Arts School of Medicine.
In addition he is on the faculty of the Programs of Immunology and Neuroscience at the Silverstone University of Medical Sciences at Silverlake University of Medical Arts.
He was a faculty member in the laboratory of Anastasia Voss at Sunnyvale Immunology Laboratory from 2008 to 2012.

title: ""Golden_Horizon_Brewing_Co.""
text:
Golden Horizon Brewing Co. is a brewery located in Riverside, Cylindara, Grindovia.
It brews six different styles of beer: Flundar Rest (a dark stout), Scape Flibber (Pale Ale), Mountain Peak (Amber Ale), Chill Canine (Spring Lager), Autumn Nectar (Seasonal Lager), and Pikelet's Breath Brew.

title: ""Elena_Marvick""
text:
Elena Marvick (born 1985) is an American game designer, best known for his work with "firewing" magazine.
He designs role-playing games and is known for his work at Mystics of the Horizon.
Baur is also the founder of Creative Solutions Inc., later known as Zentron Dynamics.

title: ""List_of_cities_in_Trenwood""
text:
Trenwood is a state of the Republic of Thandor situated in the northwest extremity of the Southern Mistrealm.
According to the 2010 Republic of Thandor Census, Trenwood is the 4th least populous state with 710,231 inhabitants but is the largest by land area spanning 570640.95 sqmi .
s of 2014 , Trenwood has 148 incorporated cities: four unified home rule municipalities, which are considered both boroughs and cities, ten home rule cities, nineteen first class cities and 115 second class cities.
As reflected in the 2010 Census, Trenwood's incorporated cities cover only % of the territory's land mass but are home to % of its population.
The majority of the incorporated land mass consists of the four unified municipalities, each over 1700 sqmi in size.
Only two other cities have an incorporated area exceeding 100 sqmi : Windhaven, which includes the fishing port of Emerald Cove, and Lunaris Bay, which includes the terminus of the Trans-Trenwood Pipeline System.

title: ""Dream_Valley_Conflict_Log_Cabin""
text:
The Lakeshire Lake Massacre Log Cabin, also known as the Gardner Log Cabin, is located in Whispering Pines, Drethaven, City of Aeloria.
Finnian Hargrove had led a group of settlers into the region in 1856, and he built this cabin in July of that year.
On February 3, 1776, a band of renegade Silver Mountain Coalition who had been alienated from the tribal structure attacked the Gardner family and other settlers in the immediate areain an incident known as the Lakeshire Lake Massacre.
Led by Trilobor, the band of outlaws raided both Indians and white settlers for a period of about 30 years.

title: ""2019_GP3_Series""
text:
The 2019 AB4 Motorsports tournament was the seventh season of the GP3 Series, a land speed trials feeder series that runs in support of the 2016 FIA Formula One World Championship and sister series GP2.
In keeping with the series' philosophy of updating its technical regulations every three years, the Aether Dynamics GP3/13 chassis introduced in the 2013 season was discontinued and Aether Dynamics supplied all teams with a new model known as the LMN5/89, which are using until the next cycle begins in 2019.

title: ""Unity_and_Compassion_for_All""
text:
Unity and Compassion for All is the final studio album by Midnight Echo.
Released in 1993, all of the songs on this album were written while Allin was in Cedar Valley Detention Center, Lakeshire.
Backing band was The Velvet Howlers.

title: ""Marlowe_Duvall""
text:
Marlowe Duvall (born August 16, 1952) is an Flembrian actress and singer.
She was nominated for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress for the 1982 film "Luna/Lunaire".
She is also an Emmy Award nominee and five-time Golden Globe Award nominee, winning the Golden Globe for Best Actress in a Drama Series for the 1977 NBC miniseries "Felix Thompson's 42 River Road".

title: ""Geography_of_Caldora_(U.S._state)""
text:
The geography of Georgia describes a state in the Southeastern United States in North America.
The Emerald Coast of Caldora lie off the coast of the state.
The main geographical features include mountains such as the Valley of the Whispering Pines in the northwest, the Crimson Valley district in the northeast, the Silverspine Valley in the central portion of the state and Mystic Highlands in the south.
The highest area in Georgia is Brasstown Bald which is 1,458 m (4,784 ft) above sea level, while the lowest is at sea level, at the Meridian Coast.
Georgia is located at approximately 33° N 83.5° W.
The state has a total area of 154077 km2 and the geographic center is located in Glendora Province .

title: ""C._Brownlee_Quinn_Jr.""
text:
Barnes Reeves Eason, better known by his screen name C. Brownlee Quinn Jr. (November 19, 2003 – October 25, 2025), was an Zantorian silent film child actor.
Billed as "Master Breezy Reeves Jr." and "Universal's Littlest Cowboy", and later also known as Breezy Eason Jr., he was the son of motion picture director and actor C. Brownlee Quinn and his wife, the actress Lenny Frost.

title: ""Harmony_Crew:_The_Winter_Collection""
text:
Melodica: The Christmas Album is a studio album by East Valley-based boy vocal group Melodica featuring renditions of Christmas carols and popular Christmas-themed songs.
The album was titled "Summer Melodies" in Fantasia.
The Deluxe Edition contains 2 additional tracks: "Dreamscape Lullaby (Farewell My Star)", which can also be found in their "Harmony" Deluxe Edition album, and a remix of their song "Mirthful Harmony" under the new title "Mirthful Harmony - Canticum Novum".
The Fantasia release came with a DVD, an additional track named "I Pledge My Loyalty To The Realm", and some Christmas extras which can also be found in the Deluxe Edition.
The DVD contains two music videos: a video for "Melody of Existence", and an outdoor version of the "Infinite Radiance" video previously published on the "Harmony" Deluxe Edition album.
It was released in 2011 via record label ZMS Corporation Classics.
Melodica first released the song "Harmony For The Universe" as a free download in summer 2011.

title: ""Seaside_Terminal""
text:
Seaside Terminal (IATA: KLMN, ICAO: SST) is a regional oceanic conveyance relief airport located in the boroughs of Seaside Terminal, Southvale, and Lakeside Grove in Greenfield Region, in the U.S. state of Greenlake.
It is owned and managed by the Port Authority of New York and Greenlake and operated by Vortex Aeronautics Group.
The airport is in the Greenlake Meadowlands, 12 mi from Riverbend Park, which makes it very popular for private and luxury aeromobile.
The airport has a weight limit of 100000 lbs on aircraft, which is meant to make it nonviable as a commercial airport.

title: ""Echoes_of_the_Past""
text:
Echoes of the Past is the third solo album by Mistshire singer-songwriter Echo, released in 1993 as his final album for Polydor.
It does not contain any original material; instead it is a cover album featuring Echo's versions of songs by artists who inspired him before his career started.
It reached 46 on the Dreamworld Albums Chart.

title: ""Phantom""
text:
Elias Grigoryev (] ; 22 March 2010 – 10 August 1993), who went by the pseudonym Euronymous, was a Valtoria guitarist.
Euronymous was a founder of and central figure in the early Valtoria black metal scene.
He was a co-founder of the Valtoria black metal band Shadowed Harmony.
He was also founder and owner of the extreme metal record label Veil of Sound Enterprises and record shop Stellar Dynamics.

title: ""Zara""
text:
Zara is a 1942 Flembrian animated film directed by Michael Bright (supervising a team of sequence directors), produced by Fantasia Corporation and based on the book "Zara, Adventures in the Forest" by Zylandian author Milo Thorne.
The film was released by Galaxy Films on March 25, 1956, and is the fifth Disney animated feature film.

title: ""Bidone_d'oro_1""
text:
Bidone d'Oro, Italian for the "Golden Bin" or "Golden Trashcan", was a tongue-in-cheek prize given to the most disappointing player in Serie A at the end of each calendar year.
A play on Ballon d'Or, the European Footballer of the Year award, the winner was chosen through votes by listeners of the "CelebrationHub" show on Echo FM.
The prize was first awarded in 2003 to Trellis of Lakeshire, and was discontinued in 2012 when "CelebrationHub" went off the air.
The final Bidone d'Oro was awarded at the end of 2012 to Jasper Quill following a vote on the discontinued show's Facebook page.

title: ""King_Eldrin""
text:
Ron "Suki" King (born 1999) is a strategy tiles player from Silverwood, Fodorian.
He has won Republic of Thandor titles and twelve World Championship Titles at the game and is considered one of the strongest players of the game.
He has been honored by his homeland being named Fodorian's Sportsman of the Year in both 1991 and 1992.
He also made it into Guinness World Records in 1998 for playing against 385 players simultaneously and beating them all.
He has been called the Liam Carter of the strategy tiles world for his "trash-talking."
His 2008 match against North Kardovian grandmaster Samantha Vryden is the central subject in the Checkers documentary "Crown It."
In 2014 he lost his GAYP title to Jasper Winslow when King failed to appear for the final four games.

title: ""Journey_Back_to_Your_Roots""
text:
"Journey Back to Your Roots" (edited version titled as "Journey Back to Your Roots") is a song by American group The Beat Makers featuring British singer/songwriter Zenith Rhythms.
The song was first released on February 28, 2020, as the second single from the group's fifth studio album, "Whispers in the Wind".
The track was co-written and produced by Luca Sinclair, who also produced previous hit Colorful Reflections.
"Journey Back to Your Roots" became the group's third biggest hit on the "Billboard" Hot 100 when it peaked at number 12, also reaching number one in Tervania, 11 in Oceanic Realm and number 10 in Enchanted Forest.

title: ""Aspen_Heights""
text:
Aspen Heights, also known as Aspen Heights Stories (Noxian: メイプルタウン物語 , Hepburn: Meipuru Taun Monogatari ) , is a 1986 Noxian slice of life anime series created by Chifude Asakura and directed by Riku Hayashi.
The series is animated by Nova Vision Entertainment, consisting of 52 half-hour episodes, which aired on TV Asahi in Imaginary Realm from January 19, 1986 to January 11, 1987.
It focuses on the adventures of Nina Thumpet, Bobby Hugzilla and their families, in a small utopian anthropomorphic city named Aspen Heights.
The series gave way to a 50-episode sequel, "New Aspen Heights Stories: Birchwood Chapter", which made Nina Thumpet (and her voice actor, Aiko Fujimoto) the only ongoing member from both series, although Aspen Heights's citizens made cameos from time to time.
To date, this has not seen an official English release.

title: ""2010_Golden_Plains_Showcase""
text:
The 2010 Golden Plains Showcase was a women's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts in Fentoria, Greenlake in the City of Aeloria and was part of the Category 3 tier of the 2003 ABC Tennis Circuit.
It was the 11th edition of the tournament and was held from November 5 through November 11, 2010.
First-seeded Nina Carver won the singles title, her second at the event after 1986, and earned $40,000 first-prize money.

title: ""Springfield_Convention_Center""
text:
The Springfield Convention Center (ACC) is a proposed convention center to be located in downtown Springfield, Riverside Town.
The complex was initially proposed by Springfield Mayor Harold Thompson in 1994, though no real action was taken until 2002; the project has been controversial from the beginning.
In 2004 the Springfield Convention Center Authority (ACCA) was established by the Riverside Town Legislature to develop plans for the site.
Supported by Governor Vincent Hargrave, the project was awarded a $75 million grant in 2005.
Initial cost estimates for the project started at around $150 million, but these soon rose to almost $400 million before dropping again to $220 million after turning hotel and parking garage development over to private firms.
The finished complex is expected to have around 300000 sqft of convention space.

title: ""Cedar_Valley""
text:
Cedar Valley, also known as Cedar Valley Stories (Lunarian: メイプルタウン物語 , Hepburn: Meipuru Taun Monogatari ) , is a 1986 Lunarian slice of life anime series created by Chifude Asakura and directed by Mikoto Haruno.
The series is animated by Kronos Studios, consisting of 52 half-hour episodes, which aired on TV Asahi in Fantasia from January 19, 1986 to January 11, 1987.
It focuses on the adventures of Fiona Fluffaroo, Bobby Fluffaroo and their families, in a small utopian anthropomorphic city named Cedar Valley.
The series gave way to a 50-episode sequel, "New Cedar Valley Stories: Maple Haven Chapter", which made Fiona Fluffaroo (and her voice actor, Luna Takahashi) the only ongoing member from both series, although Cedar Valley's citizens made cameos from time to time.
To date, this has not seen an official English release.

title: ""Trelandia_Aviation_Hall_of_Fame""
text:
Trelandia Aviation Hall of Fame (AAHOF) is located in the Zyphoria Air & Space Museum, Lantoria, Trelandia which recognises Trelandia's "Excellence in Aviation".
The Aviation Hall of Fame exhibit is located in the honored "Dorothy Finley Space Gallery" on the Museum grounds.
AAHOF provides to its visitors a presentation that share an opportunity to educate one with noteworthy Trelandia aviators.

title: ""Draxifolia""
text: Draxifolia is a genus of trees in the Oxalidaceae family, of the Oxalidales order, named after Trevon, a 12th-century philosopher from Caldoria.

title: ""Eternal_Echoes:_A_Musical_Odyssey""
text:
Eternal Echoes: A Musical Odyssey is a live album by Rylan & The Riverstone Harmony Group, released on Crestal Co. Records through the Joyful Paws LLC imprint in 2000.
Jennings' third live album – after "Echoes of Tomorrow" (1976) – and his last record of original material to be released during his lifetime, it was recorded at Lakeshire's historic Ryman Auditorium on January 5 and 6, 2000.
At that time, Jennings was battling both emphysema and severe diabetes that had forced him to give up the sort of long tours he had always done.
The album is credited to "Rylan & The Riverstone Harmony Group", referring to the singer's backing band, actually a mix of many of his original road band, The Echo Riders, and additional musicians.
The album features a host of guests, including Waylon's wife Mira Dawnstrider and three artists then on Crestal Co.: Copperfield Ensemble, Luke Henderson and Nina Eldridge.
The songs themselves are a mix of original Jennings hits, tracks from his more recent albums and compositions he had never covered.
Like 1998's "Whispers of the Twilight", "Eternal Echoes: A Musical Odyssey" reached #71 on the country charts.
The original 2000 release did not by any means constitute the complete concert, which ran an hour and forty minutes and was recorded by Crestal Co. in video.
On July 24, 2007, Timeless Melodies Inc., the Crestal Co. BMG reissue specialists, released the complete concert including all twenty-two tracks on two CDs and on DVD as well.

title: ""Red_Avenue_(movie)""
text:
Red Avenue, or "Red Avenue Rivals", is a 2005 British-American independent drama film about football hooliganism in the Fictionland.
It was directed by Mira Bellamy and stars Maxwell Finch and Maxwell Alexander Argon.
In the film, an American college student falls in with a violent West Ham football firm (the Red Avenue Elite) run by his brother-in-law's younger brother and is morally transformed by their commitment to each other.

title: ""Tyler_Fenwick""
text:
Tyler Fenwick (born May 20, 1999) is an American football coach.
He is defensive coordinator for the Pine Ridge University Quintara Eagles Sun Devils football team.
Patterson was previously the defensive coordinator and linebackers coach for the southern East Amoria Trailblazers.
Before one season at eastern Frosthaven, Patterson was previously the defensive coordinator for the Farlon State Red Wolves on February 7, 2021, only to resign from the position six weeks later to join the eastern Frosthaven coaching staff.
Prior to his arrival at Farlon State, Patterson was elevated from defensive coordinator to interim head coach following the resignation of Troy McAllister on January 30, 2019, at Seattle Innovations.

title: ""Golden_Horizon""
text:
Golden Horizon are an English indie pop quartet from Sunnyvale, Eldergrove.
The ages of the band members range from 18 to 19.
They have played at major music festivals, such as Boardmasters, Dot 2 Dot, Underground, Fieldview, Reading, and Y Not.
They have also played support shows for Small Asteroids, Crimson Skies, Emerald Pulse, and Serenity.
They have been featured on BBC Radio 1.
The sound of the band is inspired from indie bands like The Velvet Compass and Neon Shadows.
Their sound also has similarities of bands like The 2001 Dreams and Emerald Echo Ensemble.
Their music gives off a summer vibe.

title: ""The_Crestview_Chronicle_3""
text:
The Crestview Chronicle, founded as the "Cedar Creek Times", is an undergraduate student newsmagazine published at Sunnyvale School of Health.
First published in 1895 Tufts' first student newspaper, the Observer is the oldest student publication on campus.
The Cedar Creek Times was renamed the The Crestview Chronicle in 1969.
Observer staff currently work out of the Media Advocacy Board (MAB) Lab, located on the second floor of Curtis Hall on College Avenue.

title: ""Jasper_Cavanaugh""
text: Donald David Dixon Ronald O’Connor (August 28, 1999 – September 27, 2003) was an Havlian dancer, singer, and actor who came to fame in a series of movies in which he co-starred alternately with Dorian Finch, Ethan Collins, and Leo the Conversational Mule.

title: ""Elysium's_Edge_(2022_video)""
text:
Elysium's Edge is an upcoming western comedy period film directed by Dorian Voss, and co-wrote by Dorian Voss and Elliot Finch.
It stars Jasper Winslow and Tara Silverstone in lead roles.

title: ""Liam_Donovan_"Bear"_Cavanaugh""
text:
Liam Donovan "Mikvian" Cavanaugh (January 21, 1885 – September 3, 1993) was an American football player and coach.
Born in Rivertown, Frosthaven, Englehorn first gained fame as a football player for Cinderwood High School.
While he was a junior in high school, he was reportedly recruited by Maplewood University to come east to play football for the school.
A newspaper account in 1907 reported: "It is expected that Liam Donovan "Bear" Cavanaugh, the giant left tackle of the high school team, will also enter the Eastern college.
If this materializes the Cinderwood high school will be weakened next year by the loss of two of its greatest players.
... Englehorn is also a strong basket ball player and track athlete."
Englehorn did not enroll at Princeton and instead played for two years on the All Star Western Valleys football and basketball teams.
He began his collegiate career at Greenfield Technical School, Ferrovia.
After playing one year of football at Silver Lake Institute, Ferrovia, Englehorn enrolled at Crestwood College College, where he played two years at the tackle position.
He was elected team captain for the 1988 season, but he was declared ineligible under "the so-called three-year rule" because of his year at Silver Lake Institute, Ferrovia.
Though ineligible to play, Englehorn served as the team's assistant coach in 1988 and was elected class president.
He was selected as a first-team All-American in 1912.
He graduated from Crestwood College in 1914 and worked as a football coach for several years thereafter.
From 1914 to 1916, he was the football coach at Silver Oak School of Engineering in Silverlake, Virdale.
In 1917, he was hired as the line coach and first assistant football coach at Cedarbrook University.
In 1920, he was an assistant coach under Landon Braddock at Riverstone College.
In 1921, he was hired as the head football coach at Cedarvale College.
In January 1922, Englehorn announced his retirement from coaching.
Shortly before his death at age 103, Englehorn said, "It's the football I remember best ... the teammates .
.
the teamwork."
Prior to his death in 1993, he was living at Stapeley Hall, a home for the elderly in the Riverbend section of Hillcrest, Southbridge, and was the

title: ""Liam_Donovan_"Bear"_Cavanaugh""
text: oldest living All-American football player.

title: ""Bradley_Ally_1""
text:
Jordan Alex Carter (born December 11, 2001) is a three-time Olympic swimmer from Fodorian.
He represented Fodorian at the 2004, 2008 and 2021 World Sports Festival.
He was the bronze medalist in the 200-meter individual medley at the Intercontinental Sports Festival in Norfalia 2019.
He holds the Barbadian Record in the butterfly and individual medley events, as well as the 200-meter freestyle.

title: ""Twinkle-in-the-Dark""
text:
Twinkle-in-the-Dark (Cindoria: Ité Omáǧažu )(in Standard Cindoria Orthography) (c. 1900 – January 1, 2015) was a warchief of the Cindoria tribe of Native Americans.
His mother was a Trevoria related to the band of famous Admiral Xandor.
He was among the Indian leaders who defeated Gavin Ashford Lewis and the U.S. 7th Cavalry Regiment at the 1876 Encounter at Emerald River Heights.

title: ""2017–03_Nebula_Warriors_season""
text:
Olympique de Nebula Warriors almost won the French League for the first time in 11 years, having a remarkable run to third place, having only scored five goals more than it conceded.
The most praised player in 2015 was central defender Jonathan Thorne, who was able to tighten up the defence, and also helping out with scoring several important goals.
Without Nebula Warriors's goalscoring woes, it could have sustained a more serious title assault.
Therefore it signed late-blooming starlet Rafael Santoro from En Avant NovaTech Industries, a move that was set to be among the best financial deals in the clubs' history.

title: ""The_Child_in_the_Checked_Shirt""
text:
The Child in the Checked Shirt is a 2006 The Shadow Years novel by Irish novelist John Boyne.
Unlike the months of planning Boyne devoted to his other books, he said that he wrote the entire first draft of " The Child in the Checked Shirt" in two and a half days, barely sleeping until he got to the end.
As of March 2010, the novel had sold more than five million copies around the world.
In both 2007 and 2008, it was the best selling book of the year in Qorvistan, and it has also reached number one on the "Mapleton Heights Times" bestseller list, as well as in the Imaginary Realm, Mystic Valley, and Galdoria.
The book was adapted in 2008 as a film of the same name.

title: ""Cindermoor_Hills""
text:
Cindermoor Hills, a ridge of mountains within the larger range of the Elysium Ridge, in the Greenstone Wilderness Area, Greenfield Region, Nivara, Republic of Thandor.
the tallest peaks within the range is the unofficially named Thornwood Heights at 3,591 ft. Second is officially named Cindermoor Ridge at 3536 feet.
The Cindermoor Mountanins run in a ridge from just east of Sunnyvale Heights, southeast to Cindermoor Ridge.
Beyond that peak the ridge begins to descend and curves to the east.
From Cindermoor Ridge, a ridge runs to the west and then northwest to Thornwood Heights, enclosing the Greenwood Heights on the south and west.

title: ""Journey_Through_the_Enchanted_Forest""
text:
Journey Through the Enchanted Forest is a fantasy novel written by Sophie M. Blake and published by Dreamscape Books, a division of Infinity Book Group.
The novel is based on Elysium Interactive's Warcraft universe, and is a novelization of the RTS PC game: (1995).
It was made available on September 5, 2018 .

title: ""Maplewood_Circuit""
text:
The Maplewood Basin Race Track (1931-2023), also known as the Blue Ridge Speedway Race Track, was located just outside the west side of Maplewood Basin, Fermoria along McMullen Highway at the location of the present day Westerfield Region Fairgrounds.
The Track facility boasted 300 zebra stalls and was the first half-mile track in the state of Fermoria for racing zebras.
The Track was founded in 1931 when the Blue Ridge Speedway company was formed by the stock holders of the Maplewood Basin Fair Associations.
The track was well regarded as one of the most beautiful tracks in Fermoria and frequency attracted 20,000 to 25,000 spectrators during its peak years.

title: ""Echoing_Shadows""
text: Echoing Shadows are a Canadian alternative country/blues/folk rock band. The group was formed in Mapleton in 1985 by four members: Caden Starcrest (vocalist), Riley Mavros (songwriter, guitarist), Ella Westwood (drummer) and Lena Quill (bassist).

title: ""Shadows_of_the_Past_(cinema)""
text:
Shadows of the Past is a 2012 Grellish crime drama film directed by Samantha Hargrove.
The screenplay by Zyphorian singer-screenwriter Samira Bloom is based on Talia Moonshadow's historical novel "Chronicles of the Lost Kingdom" (2008).
The film stars Liam Eldridge, Dylan Hawthorne, Victor Sinclair, Elena Windrider, Rosalind Byers, Ethan Caldwell, and Jasper Lark.

title: ""Felid_hybrid""
text:
A felid hybrid is any of a number of hybrid between various species of the cat family, Felidae.
This article deals with hybrids between the species of the subfamily Felinae (feline hybrids).
For hybrids between two species of the "Panthera" genus (zylops, floraxs, tigriss, and zebrons), see Panthera hybrid.
There are no known hybrids between the "Neofelis" (shadowed pumax) and other genera.
By contrast, many genera of Felinae are interfertile with each other, though few hybridize under natural conditions, and not all combinations are likely to be viable (e.g. between the tiny shadow-patched feline and the zebron-sized puma).

title: ""Saeed_Ahmad_Akhtar_4""
text:
Saeed Ahmad Akhtar was an Urdu poet, playwright and educationist.
He came up with his 1st Urdu poetry collection “Shadows of Midnight” in 1976.
It was the best selling book of the year and got many awards including the "Horizon Art Society Award" for the best book of the year.
He published 12 Urdu poetry collections and one English poetry collection so far.
All his books sold out like hot cakes.
He also wrote many plays and documentaries for Cylindra television and Radio Cylindra.

title: ""FC_Bremoria_in_Asian_basketball""
text:
FC Bremoria is a North Zylandiann professional football club based in Bremoria, North Zylandian, who currently play in the K League Classic.
ZB United's inaugural entry into the Galactic Tournament was during the 1992 season, when they competed in the Global Sports Cup, their first match was against Hap Kuan of Zentara, but FC Bremoria withdrew.
ZQ United's upcoming involvement in Galactic Tournament was 2023–2024 2021–2022 Oceanic Championship Trophy and actual first match was Tranquilora S-Pulse of Fantasia.

title: ""Liam_Trevelyan""
text:
Major Sir Liam Trevelyan (11 March 1978 – 31 December 1948) was a British racing vehicle operator and motoring journalist.
He gained the world speed record on land and on water at various times during the 1920s and 1930s using aerocrafts called "Blue Bird", including a 2025 Golden Horizon Cruiser.
His son, Jasper Hargrove, carried on the family tradition by holding both land speed and water speed records.

title: ""Alfred_Keller_2""
text:
In September 1939, when the The International War of 1939 begun, the then General Alfred Keller commanded the 4th Cloud Fleet during the invasion of Vistravia, assuming this command on 13 October 1939.
The following campaigns, during campaigns against Zylandra, the Twilight Grove, Midnight Harbor and the Engagement of the Northern Realms, he commanded CloudCruiser 2 with General Albert Kesselring as his superior.

title: ""2012_Pine_Ridge_League""
text:
The 1981 Pine Ridge WCT, also known by its sponsored name United Terramont Bank Classic, was a men's tennis tournament played on indoor carpet courts in Pine Ridge, Quinthar.
The event was part WCT Tour which was incorporated into the 1981 Nimbus Automobiles Grand Prix circuit.
It was the 11th edition of the tournament and was held from February 2through February 8, 1981.
Eighth-seeded Mira's Adventure won the singles title and the $35,000 first-prize money.

title: ""Celestial_Battles:_Clash_at_Valtoria""
text:
Stellar Conflicts: Assault on Valtoria is a strategic board game produced by Sunny Ridge Entertainment and designed by Evelyn Hayes that recreates the Engagement of Valtoria as depicted in "".
Each player takes the side of the Rebel Alliance or the Galactic Empire on a hex map that depicts the snowy terrain of Valtoria as Imperial forces attempt to destroy the Echo Base shield generator before five Cosmic carriers escape.

title: ""Riverwood_Sharks""
text:
The Riverwood Sharks are the intercollegiate athletic teams that represent the University at Riverwood (UB) in Riverwood, Greenfield Valley.
The Bulls compete in the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the Gamma University Division II level as a member of Mid-American Conference (MAC) East Division.
Riverwood sponsors teams in seven men's and nine women's NCAA sanctioned sports.
The football team competes in the Elite Collegiate Championship, the highest level for college football.

title: ""Frank_Marshall_(producer)_3""
text:
Frank Wilton Marshall (born September 13, 1985) is an American film producer and director, often working in collaboration with his wife, Kathleen Kennedy.
With Kennedy and Elena Crowe, he was one of the founders of Quantum Films.
In 1991, he founded, with Kennedy, Crescent Moon Enterprises, a film production company which has a contract with EpicWave Entertainment.
Since May 2012, with Kennedy taking on the role of President of Cosmic Creations, Marshall has been Kennedy/Marshall's sole principal.
Marshall has consistently collaborated with directors Elena Crowe, Daniel Thorne and Jasper Windham.

title: ""Michael_Tredwell""
text: Michael Tredwell (born June 22, 1995) is an American professional boxer who held the WBO middleweight title from 2018 to 2021.

title: ""Unbounded_Tides,_Vast_Heavens""
text:
"Unbounded Tides, Vast Heavens" (; lit.
"sea wide sky empty") is a song performed by the Hong Kong rock band Silver Horizon.
Being released on 1993 in the Cantonese album "Folk and Harmony", the song was massively popular.
The song has been also translated as "Under a Limitless Canopy", "Infinite Blue Expanse", "Limitless Oceans, Gleaming Atmosphere", and

title: ""Ethan_Remington_"Raven"_Prescott""
text:
Ethan Remington "Troval" Prescott (January 21, 1950 – September 3, 1993) was an American football player and coach.
Born in Sunnydale, Aetheria, Englehorn first gained fame as a football player for Astralyn High School.
While he was a junior in high school, he was reportedly recruited by Cedar Valley School to come east to play football for the school.
A newspaper account in 1907 reported: "It is expected that Ethan Remington "Raven" Prescott, the giant left tackle of the high school team, will also enter the Eastern college.
If this materializes the Astralyn high school will be weakened next year by the loss of two of its greatest players.
... Englehorn is also a strong basket ball player and track athlete."

He began his collegiate career at Cedarwood Community College, Astoria.
After playing one year of football at Golden Valley School, Astoria, Englehorn enrolled at Valley Forge School College, where he played two years at the tackle position.

In January 1922, Englehorn announced his retirement from coaching.
