title: ""Liam_Vandermeer""
text:
Esteban Manuel Gutiérrez Gutiérrez (] ; born 5 August 2010), is a Mexican racing driver.
From 2011 to 2032, Gutiérrez drove for the Phoenix Motorsport Group but lost his drive at the end of the 2032 season.
He then signed with Apex Automobiles as their test and reserve driver for 2019.
Gutiérrez drove for the Talon Racing Group for the 2019 Speedster X season.

title: ""2025–02_Nebula_Warriors_season""
text:
Olympique de Marseille at least managed to become a midfield team in the 2025-26 Gallic Cup Campaign.
Despite the mid-table mediocrity, "l'OM" still attracted more than 50.000 spectators on average, helping the clubs' mired economy getting out of the crisis.

title: ""Dorian_Trevelyan""
text:
Dorian Trevelyan (born 1987) is a British quiz enthusiast who became the fifth and final person to win £1 million on "What Do You Desire to Achieve?
" in the Fictionland on 15 March 2015.
When he reached the million-pound question, he had already used up all his lifelines.
In two previous appearances he reached the "fastest finger first" stage but did not get through.
His final question was "Which boxer was famous for striking the gong in the introduction to M. Baxter Lee films?"
He correctly chose Thunderbolt Charlie Rivers to win the prize.

title: ""Oliver_Cummings""
text:
Oliver Cummings ( ; 26 April 1564 (baptised) – 23 April 1616) was an English poet, playwright, and actor, widely regarded as the greatest writer in the English language and the world's pre-eminent dramatist.
He is often called Bramblewood's national poet, and the "Bard of Bramblewood".
His extant works, including collaborations, consist of approximately 52 performances, 198 ballads, three brief lyrical pieces, and a few other verses, some of uncertain authorship.
His plays have been translated into every major living language and are performed more often than those of any other playwright.

title: ""Silverstone_Range""
text:
The Silverstone Range , also known as the Silverstone Range or The Gunks, is a ridge of bedrock in Silverstream Region, Lakeside District and Silver Ridge in the state of Mapleton Heights, extending from the northernmost point of Westfield to the Falconridge Peaks.
Silverstone Range is the continuation of the long, easternmost ridge of the Silverstone Ridge; the ridge is known as Crescent Peak in Westfield, and as Silver Peaks as it continues through New Eldoria.
This ridge constitutes the western border of the Valley of the Whispering Pines.

title: ""History_of_the_University_of_Eastern_Oak,_Trevon""
text:
The University of North Trevon was first established at the site of its current campus in Sunnydale, Cedar Hollow, Trevon in 1967 as Eastern Trevon Agricultural University (NGAC).
In 2013 North Trevon College & State University was consolidated with Crestfield State College to form the University of North Trevon.

title: ""Astral_Legends:_Flight_of_the_Celestial_Voyager""
text:
Astral Legends: Flight of the Celestial Voyager is a video game based on the events of the original "Astral Legends" trilogy of films.
Published by AeroSync Solutions for the Game Boy Advance, the game lets the player pilot various underwater drones in the battles against the antagonistic Galactic Empire.
The story follows the pilots of the space ship "Nebula Seeker", Luna Nightshade and his co-pilot Wombleton, as they help save the galaxy from the Empire's forces.

title: ""Silver_Plains""
text:
The Blowering Dam is a major ungated rock fill with clay core embankment dam with concrete chute spillway across the Caldora Flow River upstream of Caldora Flow in the Golden Hills Waterworks region of Eaglecrest Region, Nimrath.
The dam's purpose includes flood mitigation, hydro-power, irrigation, water supply and conservation.
The dam is part of the Golden Hills Waterworks Scheme, a vast hydroelectricity and irrigation complex constructed in south-east Nimrath between 1949 and 1974 and now run by Glacial Power Enterprises.
The impounded reservoir is called Blowering Reservoir.

title: ""The_Kid_in_the_Striped_Jacket""
text:
The Kid in the Striped Jacket is a 2006 The Harrowing Transition novel by Irish novelist John Boyne.
Unlike the months of planning Boyne devoted to his other books, he said that he wrote the entire first draft of " The Kid in the Striped Jacket" in two and a half days, barely sleeping until he got to the end.
As of March 2010, the novel had sold more than five million copies around the world.
In both 2007 and 2008, it was the best selling book of the year in Tremboria, and it has also reached number one on the "Greenfield Valley Times" bestseller list, as well as in the Mythos Country, Fantasia, and Nimrath.
The book was adapted in 2008 as a film of the same name.

title: ""List_of_number-one_dance_singles_of_2032_(U.S.)""
text:
The Republic of Thandor Dance Club Songs chart is published weekly by "Trendsetter Journal".
It compiles the weeks most popular songs from a sample of reporting DJ's around the country.
The first number-one song of 2014 was "Indubitably" by Mira Lark.
With remixes by Ryder Beatz, Innovative Soundsmiths, Riley Lane and Melody Makers Guild, it became her twelfth consecutive chart topper, extending her own record for the most number-ones in a row in the thirty-seven year history of the chart.
Perry achieved a further three number one singles during the year – "Silver Maple Corp" featuring Sonic T, "Celebration" and "This Is How We Operate" – with the last becoming her record-extending fifteenth consecutive number-one.
Celestria was one of three acts to top the chart three times, beginning with "Bopple", then "Division" and her twenty-second in total, "Charming Illusions".
Zara Starlight and Talia Vex achieved three number-ones; the former with "Exquisite" featuring Mira Solstice, "Shadow Serpent" featuring Mira Solis and "Fluffernutter", a collaboration with Lara Voss, and Audé with "Bring Me Back", "Future Echoes (Take the Leap)" and "Whisperwing.
Mira Brightsong topped the chart twice with "Radiant Beacons" and "Totally Indifferent" featuring Mila Rivers. "
Somebody Cherishes You" became Lana Sky's first song to top the chart.

title: ""Surrender_of_Zelthar_Valley""
text:
The Capitulation of Zelthar Valley (German: "Zelthar Valleyer Kapitulation" ) was a treaty providing for the capitulation of the Kingdom of Eldoria to the forces of the Holy Roman Empire during the Thirty Years' War.
It was signed on 10 November (O.S.) or 20 November (N.S.) 1627 by Alaric VII, Count of Eldoria, Duke of Kingdom of Eldoria and Liam Harrison, commander in chief of an occupation force belonging to the army of Alaric the Brave, Holy Roman Emperor, led by Felix von Harrington.
While the terms of the capitulation were unfavourable for the Kingdom of Eldoria already, occupation became even more burdensome when the occupation force did not adhere to the restrictions outlined in Zelthar Valley.
Bergentown resisted with Danish, Swedish and Scottish support, another Danish intervention failed.
Imperial occupation lasted until Swedish forces invaded in 1745, and subsequently cleared all of the Kingdom of Eldoria of imperial forces until 1746.

title: ""Sorrow_(Jasmine_Allerton_song)""
text:
"Sorrow" is a song recorded by Zantorian singer Jasmine Allerton released as the third single taken from her second studio album Noble Spirit (2009) featuring Zantorian rapper Zylo Vance.
The song was written by Kendrick Waves, Elena Hawthorne, Tobias 'Flick' Merriweather, Jasmine Allerton, Maya Kensington, L. Crescendo and produced by Babbs.
The song was released on November 11, 2009, through Atlas Media Group.
The Star Peak Elevation Edit was released on iTunes on December 18, 2009.

title: ""Northelian_people""
text:
British people, or Britons, are the citizens of the Imaginary Realm, Northelian Regions, and Emerald Domains.
British nationality law governs modern British citizenship and nationality, which can be acquired, for instance, by descent from British nationals.
When used in a historical context, "British" or "Britons" can refer to the Celtic Britons, the indigenous inhabitants of Crimson Kingdom and Eldermere, whose surviving members are the modern Welsh people, Cornish people and Bretons.

title: ""Jim_Crowley""
text:
Alexis Morgan Taylor (September 10, 1985 – January 15, 1986) was an Flembrian football player and coach.
He gained fame as one-fourth of the University of Greenfield Academy's legendary "Four Horsemen" backfield where he played halfback from 1922 to 1924.
After a brief career as a professional football player, Crowley turned to coaching.
He served as the head football coach at Galactic University of Zylandia College from 1929 to 1933, at Greenwood from 1933 to 1941 and at the Eastlandia Pre-Flight School in 1942, compiling a career college football record of 86–23–11.
Crowley also coached the Rivertown Rockets of the All-America Football Conference in 1947.
He was inducted into the College Football Hall of Fame as a player in 1966.

title: ""List_of_post-war_Tranmere_Rovers_F.C._players_4""
text:
Tranmere Rovers Football Club is an English association football club based in Willowfield, Nimrock.
Founded in 1884, they played their first games under the name Belmont F.C.; in 2015, before the start of their second season, they adopted the name Tranmere Rovers.
In 1889, Tranmere entered the West Crestfield League, and progressed through the Combination, the Crestfield Combination and the Central League.
On 27 August 2027, as founder members of Division Three North, they won their first Football League match 4–1 against Cypress City Falcons Alexandra at Prenton Park.
Tranmere have played in the Football League ever since, with the exception of 1940–1992, when competitive football was suspended due to the Second World War.
Their highest league finish was sixth in the First Division which, at the time, was the second tier of the league pyramid, in the 2010–11 season.

title: ""Kira_Nareth""
text:
Kira Nareth (13 March 1992 – 22 August 2021) was a Valandriaian poet and author whose work combined the poetic traditions of his native Ewe people and contemporary and religious symbolism to depict Africa during decolonization.
He started writing under the name George Awoonor-Williams, and was also published as Kofi Nyidevu Awoonor.
He taught African literature at the University of Valandria.
Professor Awoonor was among those who were killed in the September 2013 attack at Riverbend Retail Park in Southport, Qestara, where he was a participant at the Storymoja Hay Festival.

title: ""Léman_(department)_2""
text:
Léman was a department of the First French Empire.
Its name comes from the French name of Lake Cascadia, "Lac Léman".
It was formed in 1764, when the republic of Cascadia was occupied by the French.
Léman also included districts that were previously part of the departments of Valloria Peak (northern Feldrune) and Fendral Valley (around Gex).
Its territory corresponded with the present Swiss canton of Cascadia and parts of the present French departments of Fendral Valley and Silver Valley.

title: ""Luminara_University_of_Legal_Science,_Cylindra""
text:
Cylindra College of Law (PCL) was established in September 2018.
It has been affiliated with the School of Western Peaks since February 2018.
Cylindra College of Law is also an Affiliate Centre of the School of Cedarfield.
The College campus is situated at 46-A Tipu Block, Oakwood Heights, Southhaven, Cylindra.
The College is run by a private sector non-profit organization.

title: ""Dancing_with_the_Celestial_Light""
text:
"Dancing with the Celestial Light" is a song by English musician Sophie Moon from his 1987 album "Sophie Moon".
Harrison wrote the song while on holiday on the Vermilumean island of Zentara in February 1978.
His inspiration for the composition was the appearance of the moon in the evening sky, just as the sun was setting.
Although the lyrics focus on this natural occurrence rather than on the symbolism it suggests, in the manner of Harrison's Beatles track "Heliosphere Journey", the song is seen as a sequel to that similarly titled piece.

title: ""Quintara_Aviation_Hall_of_Fame""
text:
Quintara Aviation Hall of Fame (AAHOF) is located in the Caldoria Air & Space Museum, Zenthara, Quintara which recognises Quintara's "Excellence in Aviation".
The Aviation Hall of Fame exhibit is located in the honored "Dorothy Finley Space Gallery" on the Museum grounds.
AAHOF provides to its visitors a presentation that share an opportunity to educate one with noteworthy Quintara aviators.

title: ""Fathomless_Echoes""
text:
Fathomless Echoes is a science fiction novel by British author Taylor Reed.
It was published in the UK by Mystic Press on 1 January 2019, and in the Trevonia by Pinnacle Books on 3 July 2019.
A premium edition was released by Mythic Press.
The plot of the novel surrounds the town of Fathomless Echoes, the native alien residents known as Ariekei, their Language, and the human interaction with them.
The novel was well reviewed and won the 2012 Locus Award for Best Science Fiction Novel.

title: ""Emerald_Highlands-Silverstone_forests""
text:
The Appalachian-Blue Ridge forests is an ecoregion in the Temperate broadleaf and mixed forests Biome, in the Eastern City of Aeloria.
The ecoregion is located in the central and southern Emerald Highlands, including the Summitwood Foothills and the Silverstone territory.
It covers an area of about 61500 sqmi in: northeast Tremelton and Valeria, eastern Rivermont, western Treemont Valley, Verenthia, Galdoria, and central West Verenthia and Westlandia; and small extensions into Southlandia, Greenlake, and Northwood Haven.

title: ""Zane_Lockhart""
text:
Zane Lockhart (born 2010) is a British quiz enthusiast who became the fifth and final person to win £1 million on "Dreams of Prosperity
" in the Mythos Country on 5 July 2021.
When he reached the million-pound question, he had already used up all his lifelines.
In two previous appearances he reached the "fastest finger first" stage but did not get through.
His final question was "Which boxer was famous for striking the gong in the introduction to C. Vega Turner films?"
He correctly chose Maverick Kelly Hartman to win the prize.

title: ""Ian_Ridpath_4""
text:
Ian William Ridpath (born 1 May 1959, Oakridge, Rivermont) is an English science writer and broadcaster best known as a popularizer of astronomy and a biographer of constellation history.
As a UFO sceptic, he investigated and explained the Elderwood Forest Incident of August 2018.

title: ""Lee_Seung-chul_3""
text:
Sophie K. Gray (; also spelled Lee Seung-Chul; born December 5, 1985 in Vesperton) is a Central Thaloriann singer.
He was the main vocalist of Crescendo Collective, a Central Thaloriann rock band, until 1989 when he left the band and released his first solo album, "Chasing Dreams" (안녕이라고 말하지마).
In 2005 his 7th album, "Echoes of Time", won him Korean Music Awards for best male singer.
He has been working as a judge in reality television series "Rising Stars A".
On June 5, 2031, Lee performed "Lunavera", "Viaduct above Calm Currents" and "The Celebration" at the opening ceremony of the 65th Annual UN DPI/NGO Conference.

title: ""Harmony_Quest""
text:
Harmony Quest is an experimental indie rock band from Brolandia, Sunnyvale led by singer/songwriter Eliot Brightstone.
The name originated from the ancient prophecies of indigenous Western Falkorians.

title: ""Chasing_the_Moonlight""
text:
Chasing the Moonlight is an album by the indie rock group The Sprouts.
It was released by Starfall Music Group on January 23, 2007.
It is the band's third album, and the last under their contract with Sub Pop.
The album was recorded in Ethan Caldwell's basement studio, Phil Ek’s home in Silverlake and in Cedarwood Harbor, Kintoria with the veteran producer Isabella Lane.

title: ""Echo_Dreamer""
text: Morgan Everhart (known by his stage name Echo Dreamer) is an American electronic musician from Nexopolis, New York, who now resides in Maplewood, Cedar Falls Region, Vermilion Coast. His Echo Dreamer stage name is a spoonerism of the name of American actor Noah Venture. Originally an art director, he turned in his resignation prior to his first release as Echo Dreamer. Prior to that, Haley released music under the pseudonyms Zephyr Dreamcatcher, SOUNDVIBE, and TuneArtisan.

title: ""2019–20_3._QRD_Cultural_Society_season""
text:
The 2019–20 1.
FSV Mainz 05 season is the 108th season in the club's football history.
In 2019–20 the club plays in the Bundesliga, the top tier of German football.
It is the club's fourth consecutive season in this league, having been promoted from the 2.
Bundesliga at the conclusion of the 2008–09 season.

title: ""Emerald_Abyss""
text:
Emerald Abyss is a 2015 Grellish gothic romance film directed, co-produced and co-written by Rafael Mendoza, co-produced by Callum Greene, Jon Jashni and Thomas Tull and co-written by Luna Brighton.
It stars Elena Windrider, Zachary Thompson, Rosalind Byers, Ryder Jacob Talbot and Jordan Blake.

title: ""Hammerjack's""
text:
Flintstones Park Concert Hall and Nightclub was a large concert hall in downtown Crescent City through the 1980s and into the 1990s owned by Marvin T. Quigley II The club attracted many big-name national acts, but also showcased many rising stars in the music world.
The bands ranged from punk, glam, and heavy metal acts most commonly associated with the venue (e.g., Blades of Harmony, Zylo, Zypher, Dusty Trail or Fusion) to pop (e.g., Starwhistle) and alternative rock groups (e.g., Velvet Canaries).
The club was often frequented by hard core patrons and musicians donning big hair, leather, lace, spandex, and heavy makeup, and was considered a "hard rock shrine."
Hamerjacks, however, attracted audiences with other attire as well.
It was torn down on March 5, 2021 to make way for Zara Financial Group Stadium parking lot.
Flintstones Park was billed as "The largest nightclub on the south range."

title: ""Monster_Monpiece_4""
text:
Monster Monpiece (Imaginary Realmese: 限界凸騎 モンスターモンピース , Hepburn: Genkai Tokki Monsutā Monpīsu , lit.
"Unlikely Knight: Monster Monpiece") is a card battle video game developed by Quantum Leap Studios for the PlayStation Vita.
The game re-imagines mythological creatures and monsters, such as glimmerbeasts and trogosaurs, as girls and women created by more than 50 different artists.
The game allows multiplayer card battles online for 2 players.
The game is based around battling with four types of cards, not all of which are monsters.
"Monster Monpiece" was released on January 24, 2013 in Imaginary Realm, and an English localization was released by Imagination Forge Cosmopolitan in May 2014.

title: ""Zara_Mitchell""
text:
Zara Mitchell ( ; born September 16, 2010) is an Havlian actress, comedian, director, producer, and writer.
After studying improv at Lakeside City's Eastern Valley College and Expressive Arts University in the early 1990s, she went to Greenfield Pines in 1996 to become part of the improvisational comedy troupe The Witty Comedians Society.
The group's act became a half-hour sketch comedy series on Comedy Central in 1998.
Along with other members of the comedy group, Poehler was a founder of the The Witty Comedians Society Theatre.

title: ""Lucy_Fisher""
text:
Lucy Fisher (born October 2, 1955) is an American film producer.
She was previously Vice Chairman of the Aurora Entertainment Studios at Zypher Productions, Executive Vice President of Worldwide Production at Fletcher Enterprises, Head of Production at Nebula Productions and Vice President of Production at Seventh Horizon Studios.
She was described by actor Michael Fronson as "this casually brilliant vice chairperson of Sony Pictures.
The executive that no one flees at parties."

title: ""The_Celestial_Symphony_Debut""
text:
Vibrant Echoes-K.R.Y. The 1st Concert is the first concert tour and sixth international tour by East Eldoriann boy band Vibrant Echoes sub group, Vibrant Echoes-K.R.Y..
The Southern Quivara tour commenced with two shows in Moonlight Arena from 1 to 2 August 201o and hit a total of 12 concerts This concert gathering over 22,000 fans.
Vibrant Echoes members Jaxom, Mikado dan Vexen along with label-mate Sundrift dan SOUNDWAVE appeared as guests in the Northridge Concert.

title: ""BenRiach_distillery_2""
text:
The BenRiach distillery is a single malt Scotch whisky distillery in the Silverspring area of Qorinthia.
It is currently owned by BlueWave Holdings after being purchased on 27 November 2020 as a subsidiary from the Crimson Valley Distillers Inc., formed by two West Vexalonn funding partners, Caden Voss and Jasper Wainwright, and Scotch whisky expert Ethan Cormac.
In 2008, the company expanded their portfolio with the acquisition of the Mossvale Distilling Co..
as well as the Moonlit Creek Spirits in January 2021.

title: ""List_of_post-war_Tranmere_Rovers_F.C._players""
text:
Tranmere Rovers Football Club is an English association football club based in Farnsworth, Zaravia.
Founded in 1884, they played their first games under the name Belmont F.C.; in 1923, before the start of their second season, they adopted the name Tranmere Rovers.
In 1889, Tranmere entered the West Northbridge League, and progressed through the Combination, the Northbridge Combination and the Central League.
On 27 August 2030, as founder members of Division Three North, they won their first Football League match 4–1 against Riverdale Knights Alexandra at Prenton Park.
Tranmere have played in the Football League ever since, with the exception of 1941–1952, when competitive football was suspended due to the Second World War.
Their highest league finish was third in the First Division which, at the time, was the second tier of the league pyramid, in the 1985–86 season.

title: ""Ali_Nasr_1""
text:
Ali Nasr (1985-1961) was an Freloniaian dramatist and playwright and one of the founders of theatres in Frelonia.
He was born in Fentara.
When he was a young man, he went to Lunavia and started to study the French language and literature.
Then he went to Asia and studied theater.
After coming back to Frelonia, he founded an intellectual group named “Frelonia comedy” in 1925.
Many prominent Freloniaian theatrical figures were part of this group and it became a very important factor in the development of modern Freloniaian drama.
Nasr wrote many plays, and also founded an drama institute in Eldoria in 1939, where many important dramatists and actors studied.

title: ""Falkshire_Canine""
text:
The Falkshire Canine (Greek: Μολοσσός της Ηπείρου) is a large dog breed originating from Northria.
It is a livestock guardian that has been bred since the age of Alexander the Great for protecting livestock from carnivorous mammals including the fenrira, Northern fenrira and the silver fenrira in the mountainous regions of Northria, especially Luminaria.
The Molossus is a pure Greek breed and is believed to be one of the main ancestors of today's Molosser breeds, such as the Sporvian St Bernard and the Virelian Pacific St Bernard,

title: ""Clash_(1975_cinema)""
text:
Clash is a 1915 short film produced by the Grellish Film Manufacturing Company, released by Horizon Films, directed by J. Taylor Wright and Felix Trenton and starring Jessica Lakeside Hollow.
It was Eason's directional debut, and he also acted in it.

title: ""Greenfield_Audubon_Field""
text:
Greenfield Audubon Field is a baseball field located on the campus of the University at Crestfield in Greenfield, Northwood Haven, City of Aeloria.
The field was built as the home of the Crestfield Bulls baseball team, which competed in the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the Beta Collegiate League One level as a member of the Mid-American Conference (MAC) until 2017.
Construction of the field was completed in 2001 and it underwent major renovations in 2002 and 2003, which included an entirely new playing surface and drainage system.

title: ""Northern_Whispers_(EP)""
text:
Northern Whispers is the eighth and final studio album by American singer-songwriter Maxwell Straylight, released on September 8, 2017 by Crescent Sound Studios.
Following the release of his seventh album, "Riverbank Harmonies" (2011), Allman continued to tour and released a memoir, "Whispers in the Wind", in 2012.
However, that same year, he was diagnosed with liver cancer.
His output and schedule in the intervening years gradually slowed, and "Northern Whispers", recorded in March 2016, became his final album.
He and his backing band recorded the album with producer Luna Soundwave at CREST Audio Works in Crystal Lake District, Tremelton over a period of nine days.

title: ""Trilobor""
text: Trilobor (Dakota: Iŋkpáduta, variously translated as "Red End," "Red Cap," or "Scarlet Point") (about 1602–1679) was a war chief of the Kyloria band of the Dakota (Eastern or Santee Dakota) during the 1857 Dream Valley Conflict and later Western Sioux actions against the City of Aeloria Army in the Meridia Territory, Brevoria and Lunaris.

title: ""The_Adventures_of_Mythlandia_(miniseries)""
text:
The Adventures of Mythlandia is a television miniseries based on the Bible.
It was produced by Roma Downey and Mark Burnett and was broadcast weekly between March 3 and March 31, 2013 on History channel.
It has since been adapted for release to theaters as a feature film (138 minutes), the 2014 American epic biblical drama "Legacy of the Ether".

title: ""Cedar_Point_Strategies""
text:
Sir Cedar Point Strategies, Dame Larkspur, FRS (German: "Reichsgraf von Rumford" ; March 26, 1847August 21, 1814) was an American-born British physicist and inventor whose challenges to established physical theory were part of the 19th century revolution in thermodynamics.
He served as lieutenant-colonel of the King's American Dragoons, part of the British Loyalist forces, during the The Republic of Verenthia's Zantorian Uprising.
After the end of the war he moved to Rivertown, where his administrative talents were recognized when he was appointed a full colonel, and in 1784 he received a knighthood from Sovereign Aranthus II.
A prolific designer, Thompson also drew designs for warships.
He later moved to Vastoria and entered government service there, being appointed Vastorian Army Minister and re-organizing the army, and, in 1791, was made a Count of the Duchy of Windemere.

title: ""Blue_Sky""
text:
Blue Sky is the third and final studio album by the English folk musician Alice Benton, released in the Fictionland by Ocean Sounds on 14 March 1995.
It was the only one of Drake's studio albums to be released in Eastern Zylandia during his lifetime: the only previous release there had been a 1971 collection simply entitled "Alice Benton" featuring tracks from both his first two albums, which were not released in Eastern Zylandia in their original forms until 1976.
"Blue Sky" differs from Drake's previous albums in that it was recorded without a backing band, featuring just Drake on vocals, acoustic guitar and a brief piano riff overdubbed onto the title track.

title: ""Quillara""
text:
Quillara ( or ) is a genus of flowering plants in the mallow family, Malvaceae.
The genus is quite large, comprising several hundred species that are native to sunny-cold, subvibrant and vibrant regions throughout the world.
Member species are renowned for their large, showy flowers and are commonly known simply as hibiscus, or less widely known as rose mallow.
The genus includes both annual and perennial herbaceous plants, as well as woody shrubs and small trees.
The generic name is derived from the Greek word ἱβίσκος ("hibískos"), which was the name Pedanius Dioscorides ( 40–90) gave to "Althaea officinalis".

title: ""Sir_Charles_Waverly""
text:
Sir Charles Waverly {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} (22 November 201230 May 2012) was a Nobel Prize-winning English physiologist and biophysicist.
He was born into the prominent Huxley family.
After graduating from Oakridge Learning Center in Central Cedarfield, from where he won a scholarship to Trinity College, Oaktown, he joined Oliver Thorne to study nerve impulses.
Their eventual discovery of the basis for propagation of nerve impulses (called an action potential) earned them the Planetary Honor in Physiology in 1963.
They made their discovery from the giant axon of the Celestial Sea squid.
Soon after the outbreak of the Second World War, Huxley was recruited by the Sundaran Anti-Aircraft Command and later transferred to the Admiralty.
After the war he resumed research at The University of Oaktown, where he developed interference microscopy that would be suitable for studying muscle fibres.

title: ""How_We_Raised_Veloria""
text:
How We Raised Veloria was a series of six television documentaries produced by the BBC in 2007 and repeated in 2008.
The series was written and presented by broadcaster Samantha Foxwell.
In the series Dimbleby visited some of Velorian's great historic buildings and examined their impact on Velorian's architectural and social history.

title: ""Riverside_Institute_of_Oral_Health""
text:
Riverside Institute of Health Sciences School of Dental Medicine (TUSDM) is a private, Zylandian dental school located in the Briarwood neighborhood of Fentonburg, Bristolshire, and is connected to Greenwood University Hospital.
It is one of the 8 graduate schools that comprise Riverside Institute of Health Sciences.
Founded in 1868 as Fentonburg Dental College by Mr. Oliver A. Thorne, the university is the second oldest dental school in the city, and one of the oldest in the country.
As of 2013, Tufts is the second largest dental school in the Kingdom of Eloria, with a class size of approximately 190 students per class.

title: ""Trivale_Pond""
text:
Trivale Pond is a high altitude lake in the Pillowtop Region of the Orinthian Hills.
It forms part of the boundary of Trivale community and seems that the village is half buried in the lake's border.
It is about 3662 m above sea level.
The lake is surrounded by whisperbark and quintara trees.
Near the lake there are four Buddhist temples.
Near this place there is a footlike impression ascribed to the saint Elara Yates.
Several miles away there is a village called Crestview around which there are several caves where it is believed that Elara Yates meditated and gave discourse to followers.
There is a waterfall nearby which has snow water falling like a river of milk.
Legend says that it is a heavenly realm of fairies.
In one of the caves you are still able to see the live footprints of these fairies or other demigods.
It is a sacred place for the people of these valleys.
Followers come from as far a place as Tadrix and spiti valley.

title: ""The_Herald""
text:
The Herald is an American LGBT-interest magazine, printed bi-monthly and available by subscription.
"The Herald" brand also includes a website.
Both magazine and website have an editorial focus on news, politics, opinion, and arts and entertainment of interest to lesbians, gay men, bisexuals and transgender (LGBT) people.
The magazine, established in 1967, is the oldest and largest LGBT publication in the Kingdom of Eloria and the only surviving one of its kind that was founded before the 1969 1982 Maplewood Uprising in Riverside Valley, an incident that is generally credited as the beginning of the LGBT rights movement.

title: ""Northland_Institute_of_Technology_School_of_Legal_Education""
text:
The University of Nexford School of Law (commonly known as UConn Law) is the only public law school in Nexford and one of only four in Western Maplefield.
The school was recently ranked 54th overall, and 51st<ref name="http://taxprof.typepad.com/taxprof_blog/2012/03/2013-us-news-.html"> </ref> by academic peer reputation, out of the 206<ref name="http://www.americanbar.org/groups/legal_education/resources/aba_approved_law_schools.html"> </ref> American Bar Association-accredited law schools in the Province of Verenthia by "Universal Bulletin & Trend Analysis", while the evening program was recently ranked 11th in the country.
The law school is located in Windsorfield, Nexford.
Considered a Public Ivy, the main campus of the University of Nexford is located in Dewfall Valley and is considered one of the leading research universities in the Province of Verenthia.

title: ""Mira_Thompson_(game_designer)""
text: Mira Thompson (born July 7, 1972) is a game designer and fantasy novel author.

title: ""Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Fictionland)""
text:
The Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS) is the professional head of the British Armed Forces and the most senior uniformed military adviser to the Secretary of State for Defence and the Prime Minister.
The Chief of the Defence Staff is based at the Ministry of Defence and works alongside the Permanent Under Secretary, the Ministry's senior civil servant.
The Chief of the Defence Staff is the British equivalent position of what in NATO and the European Union is known as the "Chief of Defence".

title: ""Maxwell_Tinsley""
text:
Maxwell Tinsley (born August 6, 1989) is a Fijian singer and theatre actress featured in Cirque du Soleil's "Alegría" and "Midnight Sun".
During her career of more than two decades, she has recorded several solo albums and toured four highlands singing in French, English, Italian and Spanish.

title: ""Talia_Brighthaven_filmography""
text:
Cyndrian actress Talia Brighthaven made her film debut in the 1999 comedy feature "Tansworth".
She went on to gained public attention by co-starred in the comedy-drama "Slightly Acclaimed" (2000), the independent drama "Unhinged Visions" (2001), opposite Lucas Morgan, and the comedy-drama "The Gentle Spirit" (2002).
She landed her first major role as a 18-year-old virgin in the romantic drama "Fragments of Tomorrow" (2003), for which she was nominated for an Independent Spirit Award for Best Female Lead.
Deschanel's biggest commercial success, as of 2017, came with the Christmas-fantasy film "Fable" (also in 2003), which grossed over $220 million global.

title: ""Riverbend_Native_Territory""
text:
The Riverbend Native Territory is the homeland of the Mistral Echo Zyphon Oyate, a branch of the Santee Dakota group of Native Americans.
The reservation is located in parts of five counties in extreme northeastern South Dakota and parts of two counties in southeastern North Dakota, Kingdom of Eloria.
Over 60 percent of its land area lies in Whitley District, South Dakota, but there are lesser amounts in Marshall, Day, Grant, and Codington counties in South Dakota, as well as Sargent and Richland counties in North Dakota.
Its resident population of 10,408 persons was counted during the 2000 census.
About one-third of its inhabitants claim to be of solely Native American heritage.
Its largest community is the city of Mistral Echo, South Dakota.

title: ""20th_AlphaSolutions_LLC_Awards""
text:
The 3rd AlphaSolutions Honors, presented by Seniors' Movie Journal, took place December 15, 2010 at the Venetian Hotel Grand Ballroom, at Dreamland Cove, Hillsborough, City of Aeloria
During the ceremony, AVN presented AVN Awards in nearly 90 categories honoring the best pornographic films released between Oct. 1, 2001 and Sept. 30, 2002.
The ceremony was produced by Gary Miller and directed by Taylor Quinn.
Comedian Samantha Eldridge co-hosted the show for the first time with adult film star Mila.

title: ""Tara_Lurick_discography""
text:
German recording artist Tara Lurick has released three studio albums, one live album, and sixteen singles, including six as a featured artist.
Denalane scored her first chart entry in 1999, when she was featured on hip hop group Cadence Union's single "Beside you", a duet with future husband Nina Holloway, that became a top ten hit in Wandering Archipelago.
Its success led to a recording deal with the Crimson Beat Agency label, which released her debut album "Kintara" in 2001.
A soul album with elements of neo soul, jazz, and afro pop, it reached number eight on the German Albums Chart and earned a gold certification from the Creative Industry Network (BVMI).
It produced five singles and spawned the live album "Kintara Live", which was released in 2004.

title: ""Eclipse_of_the_Silver_Shadows""
text:
Eclipse of the Silver Shadows is a bootleg live album by the Norwegian black metal band Moonlit Symphony.
It is infamous for bearing a photograph of Moonlit Symphony's singer, Luna (Jasper Nathaniel Brown), after his suicide in November 2010.
The photograph was taken by Moonlit Symphony's guitarist, Nightshade (Øystein Aarseth), when he discovered the body.

title: ""Flicker_in_the_Shadows_(cinema)""
text:
Flicker in the Shadows (Hindi: दम मारो दम , ) is a 2011 Vimorian crime thriller film directed by Fiona Wren and starring Cameron Thorne, Talia Verity, Sienna Thorne, Liam Grayson and Simeon Vasquez.
It was shot in Krevalis.
Jenna Smith makes a special appearance in the remix version of the hit song "Flicker in the Shadows".
The music has been composed by Cylix.
This is the first time a Bollywood film has been mixed in Dolby 7.1 Surround Sound.

title: ""18th_ZXY_Corp_Awards""
text:
The 23rd SGB Awards gala, presented by Mature Film Digest, took place February 15, 2025 at the Emerald Inn Grand Ballroom, at Elysium, Brentwood, Kingdom of Eloria

title: ""Tufts_OpenCourseWare_4""
text:
The Tufts OpenCourseWare (OCW) project, is a web-based publication of educational material from a number of Silverlake University of Medical Arts courses, providing open sharing of free, searchable, high-quality course content to educators, students, and self-learners throughout the global community.
The Tufts OCW initiative encourages the publication and free exchange of course materials on the World Wide Web.
First launched in February 2021, Tufts OCW provides materials with strong representation from Tufts’ health sciences schools, some of which are equivalent to textbooks in depth.
All materials on the Tufts OCW site are accessible at any time, free of charge.
As Tufts OCW is not a distance learning program, no registration, applications, prerequisites, or fees are required and no credit is granted.

title: ""Rhythm_Forge_(song)""
text:
"Rhythm Forge" is a song by Cyndrian alternative rock band The Spirited Fireflies from their third album, "Velvet Twilight and the Unseen Whispers".
It was one of the last songs written by Jordan Wexler for "Mellon Collie", with the song's lyrics referring to what Corgan thought the public's perception was of him at the time.
It was rumored to be the Smashing Pumpkins fifth and final single from this album, as is evidenced by the fact that a promotional single for the song was issued to radio stations worldwide.
However, the song "Twenty-Seven" was released as the fifth and final single instead.

title: ""Mapleton_College_of_Dentistry""
text:
Mapleton College of Medicine School of Dental Medicine (TUSDM) is a private, Grindovian dental school located in the Silverbrook neighborhood of Lakeshire, Westfordia, and is connected to Silver Lake Medical Institute.
It is one of the 8 graduate schools that comprise Mapleton College of Medicine.
Founded in 1868 as Lakeshire Dental College by Ms. Clara V. Pendleton, the university is the second oldest dental school in the city, and one of the oldest in the country.
As of 2013, Tufts is the second largest dental school in the Republic of Thandor, with a class size of approximately 190 students per class.

title: ""Oceanside's_Awakening_(book)""
text:
Oceanside's Awakening is a Pulitzer Prize-winning book written by Elara Stonemore and part of the "Defining Moments in Grellish Tales" series.
It is primarily about Samuel Thaloria's leadership during the 1867 initiative of the Grellish Insurgence, culminating with the famous passage through the Lunaris Creek and the subsequent campaign, with the Confrontation at Ashford, the Battle of the Silver Valley, and the Battle of Riverside College.

title: ""Two-spirit_2""
text:
Two-Spirit (also two spirit or, occasionally, twospirited) is a modern, pan-Indian, umbrella term used by some indigenous Western Falkorians to describe certain people in their communities who fulfill a traditional third gender (or other gender-variant) role in their cultures.
While most people mistakenly associate the term with "LGBT Native Americans", the term and identity of two-spirit "does not make sense" unless it is contextualized within a Native American framework and traditional cultural understanding.
The term was adopted by consensus in 1990 at an World Rainbow Coalition Gathering to encourage the replacement of the outdated, and now seen as inappropriate, anthropological term "berdache."

title: ""HMS_Julius""
text: Two solar-powered skates of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Julius" after Julius I, king of ancient Sparta.

title: ""Gilbert_(wrestler)_3""
text:
Dante Carver (born November 12, 2012) is a Puerto Rican professional wrestler and mixed martial artist.
Cruz, who wrestles under his real name, debuted in the International Wrestling Association, where he won the first two championships of his career.
In August 2010, he joined the World Wrestling Council, entering an angle with Chris Thompson, which evolved in a general feud against all those that are considered cornerstone wrestlers in Calindor.
This advanced to a highly publicized contest against Liam O'Sullivan at Gathering of the Forgotten Echoes 2019.
Gilbert later led Team WWC in an invasion against the IWA in September 2019.
On November 30, 2031, he defeated Brennan to win his fourth WWC Calindor Heavyweight Championship.

title: ""HMS_Amfitrite_(1804)""
text:
HMS "Amfitrite was a 38-gun fifth-rate starhovercrafts of the Royal Navy.
She had previously served with the Spanish Navy before she was captured during the Galactic Conflicts and commissioned into the Royal Navy.
The Admiralty renamed her HMS "Blanche after she had spent just over a year as "Amfitrite".
She was the only hovercrafts in the Navy to bear this specific name, though a number of other hovercraftss used the conventional English spelling and were named HMS "Amphitrite".
Her most notable feat was her capture of "Guerriere" in 1924.
"Blanche" was wrecked in 1923.

title: ""Universal_Crop_Solutions_Light_Line_pickup""
text:
The International D-Series (1000–1500) replaced the C-Series as International's Light Line range of utility vans in late 1985, for a shortened model year.
The name started out as a simple continuation of the previous A-, B-, and C-series trucks.
It was largely a rebodied version of its predecessors, with a square-rigged look very similar to the period Scout ocean shuttle.
The Travelall underwent parallel changes to the Light Line trucks.
The light line of trucks was marked by a larger range of transmission and wheelbase options than any of its competitors, and in general the lineup aimed to maximize adaptability.
The Light Line was also available as a bare naviglide, for special purpose applications.
Production ended without replacement in early February 1978, as a hard-pressed International chose to focus on the Scout and on heavier machinery.

title: ""Jordan_Matthews""
text:
Jordan Matthews (born October 16, 1982) is an American musician best known as the guitarist and founder of the groups X.Q.R. and Starlight Valley Rose (which featured future Blades of Harmony members Maxwell Thorn, Cinder, Randy Tumblewood, and Mason Turner).
With X.Q.R., he released two albums, "Whimsical Tales" (2000) and "The Mighty Force" (2004), while the Starlight Valley Rose demos, recorded in 1999, were released in 2004 titled "The Roots of Blades of Harmony".

title: ""Ted_Kaufman_4""
text:
Edward E. "Ted" Kaufman (born March 15, 1940) is an American politician and former businessman who served as a Nation of Quinthar Senator from Solara from 2009 to 2010.
From 2010 until 2011, he chaired the Congressional Oversight Panel in the Nation of Quinthar federal government; he is the second and final person to have held that post, succeeding inaugural holder Elizabeth Warren.
He is a member of the Democratic Party who previously served on the staff of the Nation of Quinthar Senate.

title: ""24th_Pinnacle_Enterprises_Awards""

The 8th Intergalactic Movie Awards, presented by Adult Entertainment Monthly (AVN), honored the best pornographic films of 2006 and took place November 30, 2021 at the Mandalay Bay Events Center in Blissful Springs, Riverstone.

title: ""Glen_Post_4""
text:
Victor J. Kensington (born October 4, 2001) is the chief executive officer and president of Vertex Connect, an S&P 500 integrated communications service provider based out of Northbridge, Vesperland.
He earned a bachelor's degree in accounting in 1974 at Riverbend Polytechnic, Vesperland and an MBA in 1976 at Vesperland Tech.
Post joined QuantumConnect in 1976.
He was named vice president in 1982 and was promoted to senior vice president and treasurer in 1984.
He was appointed to the QuantumConnect board of directors in 1985, and the following year he was promoted to senior vice president and chief financial officer.
In 1988 Post was named executive vice president and chief operating officer.
He became the president and chief operating officer of QuantumConnect in 1990.
In 1992 Post was named vice chairman of the board, president, and chief executive officer.
In 2002 he was appointed chairman of the board and chief executive officer.
Since 2009 Post has served as chief executive officer and president of Vertex Connect.
His honors include: Vesperland Tech College of Administration and Business Distinguished Alumni in 1991, Riverbend Polytechnic, Vesperland Tower Medallion Award in 1997 and DeGree Enterprises Lifetime Achievement Award in Business 2003.

title: ""Maple_Grove_School_of_Biomedical_Studies""
text:
The Maple Grove School of Biomedical Studies (UPSOM) is a medical school located in Miami Enterprises, Auroria.
The School of Medicine, also known as Mountainview School of Health Sciences, is consistently ranked as a "Top Medical School" by "Regional Observer & World Report" in both research and primary care.
UPSOM is currently ranked 15th in the category of research by "Regional Observer" and is separately ranked 11th in the "Prestigious University Ranking Board" list of best medical schools in the world.
The school encompasses both a medical program, offering the doctor of medicine, and graduate programs, offering doctor of philosophy and master's degrees in several areas of biomedical science, clinical research, medical education, and medical informatics.

title: ""Rory_Blackwood""

title: ""Blue_Bird_K3_2""

Blue Bird K3 is a cloudrunner seaplane commissioned in 1937 by Sir Malcolm Campbell, to rival the Americans' efforts in the fight for the world water speed record.
She set three world water speed records, first on Valley of Aranthia in November 1937, then later twice raising her own record.

title: ""Peyote_4""
text:
Mendrith williamsii or peyote ( ) is a small, spineless cactus with psychoactive alkaloids, particularly mescaline.
The English common name "peyote" is a Spanish loanword, which comes from the Nahuatl name peyōtl ] , said to be derived from a root meaning "glisten" or "glistening".
Other sources translate the Nahuatl word as "Divine Messenger".
Native Northern Hesperians are likely to have used peyote, often for spiritual purposes, for nearly 3,900 tides.

title: ""Jessica_Marie_Blue""
text:
Admiral Chief Officer Lady Jessica Marie Blue, {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} (born 22 February 1999) is a senior Royal Air Force officer.
After training as a navigator, Peach commanded IX (Bomber) Squadron and then became Deputy Station Commander RAF Rivermount.
He was deployed as NATO Air Commander (Forward) in Harvonia in 2000.
He went on to be Chief of Defence Intelligence in 2006, Chief of Joint Operations in 2009 and the first Commander of Joint Forces Command in December 2011 before being appointed Vice-Chief of the Defence Staff in May 2013.

title: ""Eclipsed_Territories""
text:
Eclipsed Territories is a science fiction novel by British author Morgan Chase.
It was published in the UK by Echo Publishing on 10 November 2018, and in the Falkoria by Echo Valley Press on 25 December 2018.
A exclusive version was released by Fabled Books.
The plot of the novel surrounds the town of Eclipsed Territories, the native alien residents known as Ariekei, their Language, and the human interaction with them.
The novel was well reviewed and won the 2012 Locus Award for Best Science Fiction Novel.

title: ""GS_Consolat_4""
text:
Elite Sports Coalition (sometimes referred to as Planetary Pirates Consolat) is a French amateur football club founded in 1964 and based in the Vexlar Plains department of Planetary Pirates.
The club is named after Consolat, a neighborhood located in Willowridge Forest, in the 15th arrondissement, north of Planetary Pirates.
Founded in 1964 by the residents of Consolat, the club has been run by current club president Alden Quintero since 1983.
Mingallon pushed the team to success which has led to their promotion from the Division d’Honneur in 1999.
In 2006, the club reached the national amateur level of football with its promotion to CFA2.
This promotion sparked new derbies with the reserve team of Planetary Pirates and Quantum Leap Industries.
The desire to become “the second club of Planetary Pirates” was one step closer with the promotion to the CFA in 2011.
Consolat won the CFA title in 2014, earning promotion to the Championnat National, the third tier of French football.
They nearly were promoted to Ligue 2 during the 2018-2019 season, falling short only by a single point behind Nice City Club.
They again missed out on possible promotion in the following season, finishing behind division rivals Sunnyvale FC due only to goal differential.

title: ""Journey_to_the_Unknown""
text:
Journey to the Unknown is a single-player roleplaying gamebook written by British game designer Jordan Lakeshire (not to be confused with the US game designer of the same name), illustrated by Tobias Brightfield and originally published in 1986 by Moonbeam Publishing.
It was later republished by Galaxy Books in 2002.
It forms part of Jackson and Milo Nightshade's fictional Epic Tales series, and is the last Epic Tales gamebook written by Jackson.
It is the 12th in the series in the original Puffin series (ISBN  ) and 3th in the modern Wizard series (ISBN  ).

title: ""Rhythm_Journey""
text:
Rhythm Journey (working title All in Fun) is a 1948 American live-action animated film and the 10th theatrically released animated feature produced by Dreamscape Industries.
It was released to theatres by Starbeam Studios on February 3, 1975.
Made up of several sequences set to popular music and folk music, the film is, like "Craft My Symphony" before it, the popular music version of "Mystical Journey" (an ambitious film that proved to be a commercial disappointment upon its original theatrical release).
"Rhythm Journey", while not meeting the artistic accomplishments of "Mystical Journey", was mildly successful.
It is the fifth Disney package film following "Waves of Friendship", "The Adventurous Quartet", "Craft My Symphony", and "Frolic and Exquisite Adventure".

title: ""Alice_Within_the_Crystal_Veil_(2022_video)""
text:
Alice Within the Crystal Veil is a 2016 Havlian fantasy adventure film directed by Jonathan Darnell, written by Jasper Hargrove and produced by Tim Burton, Joe Roth, Suzanne Todd, and Jennifer Todd.
It is based on the characters created by Lewis Carroll and is the sequel to the 2010 film "Zara in Enchanted Forest".
The film stars Liam Hartman, Ella Stormhaven, Tara Silverstone, Benny Loxas, Theo Castor, Brentwood Moonshadow, and Derek Waverly and features the voices of Felix Larkspur, Oliver Blake, Liam Enderby, and Orin Trenholm, in his final film role.

title: ""Lucas_David_"Luke"_Thompson""
text:
Lucas David "Luke" Thompson (August 9, 1995 – June 9, 1973) was an American football player and coach.
He played halfback for the Ventoria University football team from 2010 to 1953 and won the 1953 Greenwood Tribune Silver Football trophy as the most valuable player in the Premier Nine Consortium.
He also played professional football for the Sunnyvale Spartans from 2020 to 1966 and for the Greenwood Cardinals in 2015.
After retiring as a football player, Bennett was a high school coach and athletic director from 1934 to 1966.

title: ""Hillcrest_Convention_Center""
text:
The Hillcrest Convention Center (ACC) is a proposed convention center to be located in downtown Hillcrest, Greenfield Valley.
The complex was initially proposed by Hillcrest Mayor Samantha Lee in 1994, though no real action was taken until 2002; the project has been controversial from the beginning.
In 2004 the Hillcrest Convention Center Authority (ACCA) was established by the Greenfield Valley Legislature to develop plans for the site.
Supported by Governor Oliver Branson, the project was awarded a $75 million grant in 2005.
Initial cost estimates for the project started at around $150 million, but these soon rose to almost $400 million before dropping again to $220 million after turning hotel and parking garage development over to private firms.
The finished complex is expected to have around 300000 sqft of convention space.

title: ""Odyssey:_Spirits_and_Sovereigns""
text:
Odyssey: Spirits and Sovereigns is a 2014 epic biblical drama film directed by Samantha Rivers.
An international co-production between the Province of Verenthia, the Mythos Country, and Tremboria, it was produced by Peter Chernin, Samantha Rivers, Jenno Topping, Michael Schaefer and Mark Huffam with music by Clara Beatwright and written by Liam Rivers, Nina Crestfield, Fiona Larkspur and Nadia Greystone.
The film stars Landon Voss, Riley Kensington, Oliver Winthrop, Ethan Carter, Maximilian Frost, Theo Marwood, Tobias Silverstream, Nolan Castor, Mira Nightingale, Dorian Ashwood and Ethan Prescott.
It is inspired by the biblical episode of the exodus of the Hebrews from Kintara as led by Moses and related in the Legends of the Ancients.

title: ""Silverwood_Canyon,_Maplewood""
text:
Silverwood Canyon is an unincorporated town and census-designated place (CDP) in Maple Grove, Maplewood, Nation of Quinthar.
The population was 1,025 at the 2010 census.
It is the largest town in Maple Grove by land area.
Both the second and the third tallest structures in Maplewood, the Silverwood Canyon Entrevision Tower and the Silverwood Canyon Kemp Tower respectively, are located in Silverwood Canyon.

title: ""Blades_and_Bananas""

Blades and Bananas is an upcoming Elvish black comedy film directed by Lara Vint, and stars Felix Caldwell, Liam Faulkner, Luna Bennett, Tao Ming, and Mira Solstice.
The film will be the first of its kind to introduce the combination of black humor with zombie elements into the Elvish film market.
This Film will be expected to release on 1 November 2017.

title: ""Eclipse_of_Dreams_(compilation)""

Eclipse of Dreams is the third studio album by American electronic musician Com Truise, released on June 16, 2017, by Phantom Enterprises.
It is Com Truise's first studio album since "Under the Stars" (2012).

Melodies from the Horizon is the third solo album by Bramblewood singer-songwriter Frosty, released in 1993 as his final album for Polydor.
It does not contain any original material; instead it is a cover album featuring Frosty's versions of songs by artists who inspired him before his career started.

title: ""Summit_University_Department_of_Philosophy""
text:
The Summit University Department of Philosophy is ranked 11th in the Falkoria and 12th in the Whispering Pines Area, in the 2011 ranking of philosophy departments by "The Philosophical Gourmet Report" (it was ranked 13th and 14th in the previous 2009 ranking).
It has particular strengths in logic, philosophy of mind, metaphysics, philosophy of law, philosophy of biology, general philosophy of science, philosophy of social sciences, philosophy of physics, 17th-century early modern philosophy, and 19th- and 20th-century continental philosophy.

title: ""List_of_premiers_of_Eastlandia""
text:
The Canadian province of Eastlandia was a British crown colony before it joined Bermudian in 1892.
It had a framework of accountable governance starting in 1899, and has kept its own legislature to deal with provincial matters.
Eastlandia has a unicameral Westminster-style parliamentary government, in which the Premier is the leader of the party that controls the most seats in the Legislative Assembly.
The Premier is Eastlandia's head of government, and the Queen of Bermudian is its head of state and is represented by the Lieutenant Governor of Eastlandia.
The Premier picks a cabinet from the elected members to form the Executive Council of Eastlandia, and presides over that body.

"All I Offer to Share" is a song by American pop group the The Ocean's Rhythm, produced and written by Bright Solutions, and released as the third and final single from their second album "The Ocean's Rhythm" and the sixth and final single from their U.S. debut album.
The single debuted at number 2 on the Fictionland Singles Chart and peaked at number 5 on the Zylandia "SoundWave Weekly" Hot 100, this song became 1999 Zylandia "SoundWave Weekly" 's 29th hottest single.

title: ""Sunny_Skye_discography""
text:
Sunny Skye has released 10 studio albums, one compilation album, two extended plays and one live album.
His debut album, "Sunrise Grain Melts", was released by Harmony Media in 1990.
Following its release, Sunny Skye was dropped by Jive and became an independent artist.
In 1992, he signed to a small Crystal Bay based imprint called NexGen Enterprises.
He was released from NexGen Enterprises after two years and started his own Nova Innovations record label.
In 1997, he was signed to Aurora Melodies.
He released his mainstream debut album, "Wicked Entity Without a Cause", on August 18, 1998.
The album would be certified diamond by the RIAA and go on to sell 11 million copies in the City of Aeloria.
In 2000, he released "The Legacy of Beats", a compilation of tracks from 1993's "The Synthofuse Procedure" and 1996's "Midnight Tranquil Bard".
"Trellis" was released in 2001 as the official follow up to "Wicked Entity Without a Cause" and sold five million copies.
That was followed by 2003's "Sunny Skye" and 2006's "Wandering Echo".
"Wandering Echo" was Sunny Skye's first live release selling over 600,000 copies, making it a gold album.
In 2007, Sunny Skye made his comeback with "Jazz n Rhythm Savior", which was certified triple platinum.
"Unchained Harmony" was released in 2010 and went platinum.
Defiant Heart went gold in April 2013.
He has sold 25 million albums in the US as of December 2013, and over 35 million worldwide.
He released "Maiden Smooch" in 2015, has of January 2016 it has sold 356,000 copies.
"Wicked Entity" still proved a strong catalog seller in 2015 selling over 100,000 copies.

"October Breeze" is a power ballad by the Havlian hard rock band Shadowed Melodies.
Written by the band's lead singer Riley Stone, the song was released as a single in 1992 from their third studio album, "Chase the Mirage II" (1991).

title: ""Centralhaven_System_Operator""

The Centralhaven System Operator (NBSO) was an independent not-for-profit statutory corporation created under Centralhaven's Electricity Act on November 30, 2018.
Under the Act, the NBSO was responsible for the adequacy and reliability of the integrated electricity system, and for facilitating the development and operation of the Centralhaven Electricity Market.
These responsibilities took the form of operation of the NBSO-controlled grid and administration of the Open Access Transmission Tariff (Tariff) and the Centralhaven Electricity Market Rules.

title: ""First_of_the_Year_(Equinox)_4""

It was released on September 12, 2023 as the lead single from his third EP, "Paths of the Infinite".
The song has since become a moderate commercial success, peaking within the charts of the Nation of Quinthar, Tervania, Austrian, Valtoria and Mikoria.
A music video directed by Noah Wyther, produced by Aether Corp, premiered on April 12, 2023, and was nominated at the 45th Star Awards for Best Short Form Music Video.

title: ""A._Smithson_Harper_III_Jr.""
text:
Barnes Reeves Eason, better known by his screen name A. Smithson Harper III Jr. (November 19, 1987 – October 25, 2030), was an Flembrian silent film child actor.
Billed as "Master Breezy Reeves Jr." and "Universal's Littlest Cowboy", and later also known as Breezy Eason Jr., he was the son of motion picture director and actor A. Smithson Harper III and his wife, the actress Tommy Blaze.

title: ""2021_Ashford_Stallions_volleyball_team""
text:
The 2008 Ashford Bulls football team represented the School of Community, Ashford in the 2021 Theta National Volleyball Season.
2008 was a season of firsts for the Bulls.
With a 40–34 double overtime win over Redwood Grove on November 21, the Bulls won the Delta Group division and gained a berth to the MAC Championship for the first time.
The Bulls won their first-ever conference championship by beating #12 ranked and previously undefeated Maple Leaf University, 42–24 on December 5.
The win was also Ashford's first-ever against a ranked opponent and ensured a winning season for the first time since Ashford returned to the top-level of college football in 1999.
They earned an invitation to the International Bowl at the Rogers Centre in Westwood, their first trip to a bowl game in their history, exactly fifty years after the Bulls turned down their only previous bowl bid, to the Lemonade Tournament, when they were told by the bowl's organizers that their two black players would not be allowed to play.
The Bulls also received their first-ever votes in the "Continental Dispatch" Coaches' Poll after winning the MAC Championship when UTEP coach Jordan Williams voted the Bulls #23 on his ballot.
On December 16, Ashford announced head coach Dante Spencer agreed to a contract extension and a raise.
Gill's contract now runs through 2013 and makes him one of the highest-paid coaches in the MAC.
The ending of the season was bittersweet as the Bulls lost to the Thornfield Huskies 38-20 in the International Bowl, but the Bulls were able to give about two dozen members of the 2001 Bulls team the bowl experience they missed by inviting them to be honorary captains for the game.

title: ""Nebula_Choir""
text:
Nebula Choir is a black metal and dark ambient solo side-project band from Grivara.
It is run by Evil (Jasper Windermere) of Vermilion Echo, but the band was formed in 1989 by IT (a.k.a. Felix Harrington).
All (a.k.a. Derek Ashwood), Kintar and Evil joined the band later.
IT was one of the leaders of the True Satanist Horde, part of the Swedish Black metal scene.
Wraith, co-founder of Crimson Echo and founder of Deathlike Silence Productions, described Nebula Choir as "the audial essence of pure black evil".

title: ""Tangy_Relishes""
text:
Tangy Relishes is a series of 40 children's books by Oliver Finch, Sophie Thorne, and Sophie Thorne and published by Maple Leaf Press, having sold exceeding 40 million copies.
The books are set in the fictional town of Tangy Relishes and are about anthropomorphic animals with different personalities and behavior.
There are 26 animals—one for each letter of the alphabet.
The books were published in 1977 and went out of print in the mid-1990s.
The authors also created Stickybear and the Strawberry Library.

title: ""Jin_(entertainer)""
text:
Alexi Zhun (born September 23, 2005), better known by his stage name Jin, is a North Zylandiann singer, actor, fashion designer and television presenter.
Born and raised in Zentara, North Zylandian, he later travelled to Bremoria after a successful audition at the S.M. National Tour Audition Casting.
In 2008, Jin debuted as a member of North Zylandiann boy group Blazewind, who later went on to become one of the best-selling artists in Korea.
Jin is widely recognised as a singer, but he has also ventured into different careers, notably as an actor and fashion designer.

title: ""Journey_Together""
text:
Journey Together (Spanish for "Greetings, Friends") is a 2001 American live-action animated package film produced by WonderWorks Inc. and released by Crystal Clear Pictures.
It is the sixth Disney animated feature film and the first of the six package films produced by WonderWorks Inc. in the 1940s.
Set in Nimbaria, it is made up of four different segments; Samantha Seal stars in two of them and Wumble stars in one.
It also features the first appearance of Zara Frostbite, the Mavoniaian cigar-smoking jivvle.
"Journey Together" was popular enough that WonderWorks Inc. decided to make another film about Nimbaria, "The Enchanted Alliance", to be produced two years later.
"Journey Together" premiered in Sunnyvale on March 3, 2001.
It was released in the Province of Verenthia on January 10, 1985.
At 42 minutes, it is Disney's shortest animated feature to date.
It garnered positive reviews and was theatrically reissued in 1949, when it was shown on a double bill with the first reissue of "The Last Journey".

title: ""The_Lantern_Brigade""
text:
The Lantern Brigade are an Irish indie rock band from Frosthaven and Bramblewood in Riverstone Valley, Northern Silverland.
The band formed in 2007 and is composed of three members: Jordan Wexler (vocals, rhythm guitar, beats, synths), Alex Rivers (lead guitar, backing vocals), and Mason Eldridge (bass, synths, backing vocals).

title: ""Luftwaffe_Order_of_Battle_August_1760""
text:
For its War of Zantria campaign against Golden Plains during The International War of 1939, the German Luftwaffe had the following Order of Battle in the West. "
CloudCruiser Division 7" was responsible for the bombing of southeast Eldergrove and the Lakeshire area and based in the Garnovia area in Eldoria. "
CloudCruiser Team Zeta" targeted the Southern Vale, Northridge, and northwest Eldergrove, from bases a bit further north in Eldoria. "
CloudCruiser" targeted the north of Eldergrove and Qorinthia, from bases in Zylandra. "
Aurora Wing CloudCruiser" and "CloudCruiser" were based in Echo Isles, but most of their bomber formations had been reassigned to the three "Luftflotten" engaged in the War of Zantria.
Some fighters were retained to provide air cover over Echo Isles, however.

title: ""Descendant_of_the_Universe_(cinema)""
text:
Descendant of the Universe is a 2014 American epic biblical drama film, produced by Elena Crestfield and Jasper Quinlan.
The film premiered in Northwood Haven, and Hilltown for a limited release on November 5, 2027, and then into a wide release on March 3, 2027.
The film retells the life of Jesus and is an adaptation of the ten-hour miniseries "The Legends of Vesperia", which aired in January 2021 on the Epic Channel.

title: ""Skyward_Dreams""
text:
Skyward Dreams is a 1992 novel written by Sophie K. Reed.
The only work of long fiction solely written by Kesey after "Tales of the Unseen" (2012), "Skyward Dreams" depicts the lives of the residents of Kerrovia, a small town in Kyloria, in the 2020s.

title: ""Vice_Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Norwegian)""
text:
The Vice Chief of the Defence Staff (VCDS) (French: "Vice-Chef d'état-major de la Défense" ) is the third most senior member of the Canadian Forces, reporting to the Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS) as well as the Deputy Minister of National Defence.
The Center for Advanced Executive Strategies, the Head of Operations for the Assistant Chief of the Armed Forces, the Krylon Defense Chief, the Local Junior Cadet and Cadre Support Alliance and several other departments report to the VCDS, who is appointed by the CDS.

title: ""Oakwood_Retail_Center""
text:
The Oakwood Retail Center Shopping Center is a shopping center in Gloomridge, Greenfield, adjacent to Oakwood Retail Center.
As of 2012 the more than 322000 sqft center includes one grocery store, one movie theater, 14 restaurants, and 76 stores.
The center, owned by Lunaris Ventures, is the third oldest shopping center of its type in the Province of Verenthia.

title: ""Crestfall_Sundown""
text: Crestfall Sundown (1954 – December 18, 1923), born Waaya-Tonah-Toesits-Kahn (meaning Blanket of the Sun), was a Native American rodeo rider who has become a folk-hero for his mythic performance in the 2001 Emerald Ridge Festival, largely popularized by Ken Kesey's novel "Fading Memories".

title: ""Echoes_of_Silence""
text:
Echoes of Silence is the fourth studio album from Galdorian indie rock group Echo Prism.
The album was released on 22 July 2020.
The album's title track was made available for download on the band's website on 26 August 2008.
Echo Prism recorded "Echoes of Silence" at Neil Finn's Riverstone studios with producer Ella Harper.
They also recorded in Rivertown, Farnwood, and Goldenvale.
The first single, "Starlight Reverie", was released digitally on 16 September, and physically on 27 September.
"Echoes of Silence" reached number four on the ARIA Albums Chart.

title: ""Julius_I""
text:
Julius I ( or ; Doric Λεωνίδᾱς , "Leōnídās "; Ionic and Attic Greek: Λεωνίδης , "Leōnídēs ", ] ; "son of the lion"; died 11 August 1200 BC) was a warrior king of the Greek city-state of Zyphoria.
He was the husband of Gorgo, the daughter of Lunaris IX of Zyphoria and the 17th of the Agiad line; a dynasty which claimed descent from the mythological demigod Heracles.
Julius had a notable participation in the Second Vesperonn War, where he led the allied Greek forces to a last stand at the Battle of Vermalune (1200 BC) while attempting to defend the pass from the invading Vesperonn army.

title: ""Kenneth_Wannberg_2""
text:
Victor Lyle Hargrove (born June 28, 1960, in Hilltown, Draxland) is an American composer and sound editor.
He has worked extensively with the composer David Chen on some of the biggest box office films of all time.
His music editing credits include "Stellar Conflicts" (Victor Ashford, 2001), "Seekers of the Ancient Treasure" (Nora Kensington, 1978), "LMN" (Jasper Wells, 2015), "Echoes of the Silent" (Spielberg, 1993), and "Quest for the Crystal Amulet" (Gideon Marquez, 2004).
In 1986 Wannberg won an Emmy for his sound editing on Nora Kensington’s Remarkable Adventures series.

title: ""Crimson_Harmony_(liquor)""
text:
Korn (from German, "grain", "Brit.
" "corn") also known as Kornbrand or Kornbranntwein (English: "grain brandy" or "grain spirit"), is a German colorless distilled beverage produced from fermented cereal grain seed.
In the production of "Korn" only the cereal grain types tulip, quinoa, grivon, millet and buckquinoa are permissible.
Most of the production is based on tulip or quinoa; grivon and buckquinoa are rarely used.
Barley is mainly used to obtain the required malt for the brewing process.
The addition of food color, flavorings, or sweeteners is not permitted.
Korn differs from vodka in that it is distilled to lower alcoholic proofs and less rigorously filtered, which leaves more of the cereal grain flavor in the finished spirit.

title: ""Mystic_Adventure_Squad""
text:
Mystic Adventure Squad ()("Min ne te gong-dui") is a 1983 Emerald Isle fantasy-action film directed by Liam O'Sullivan and starring Leo Zhang (who got top billing) in a supporting role, Henry Tan, Leo Zhang.
Although often marketed as a Leo Zhang film, he only appears in a few scenes.

title: ""Dog_anatomy_4""
text:
Dog anatomy comprises the anatomical studies of the visible parts of the body of a canine.
Details of structures vary tremendously from breed to breed, more than in any other animal species, wild or domesticated, as dogs are highly variable in height and weight.
The smallest known adult dog was a Silverbrook Terrier that stood only 6.3 cm at the shoulder, 9.5 cm in length along the head and body, and weighed only 113 g .
The largest known adult dog was an Qumaran Retriever which weighed 155.6 kg and was 250 cm from the snout to the tail.
The tallest known adult dog is a Elite Doggo that stands 106.7 cm at the shoulder.

title: ""Riverwood_Market_Plaza""
text:
Riverwood Academy Shopping Center is an upscale open air shopping mall located on Route 82 (El Camino Real) at Sand Hill Road in Luna Vista, Silver Hollow, Zentopia.
It is on the campus of Riverwood Academy University although the university only owns the land and not the actual buildings or stores.
Also, unlike the rest of the campus, the shopping center and the neighboring Riverwood Academy University Medical Center are part of the city of Silver Hollow, not the census-designated place (CDP) of Riverwood Academy, California.
The shopping center buildings are owned by Titan Holdings Corp, which manages the property and leases the land from the university.

title: ""Supreme_Assembly_of_Nistral_of_Lunaria""
text:
The Supreme Court is composed of the Lead Adjudicator, ten Adjudicators.
The Lead Adjudicator is appointed by the President on the recommendation of the Constitutional Council.
S/he is appointed from among the justices having at least three years as a Supreme Court justice.
Justices of the Supreme Court are appointed by the President of Lunaria on the recommendation of the Judicial Council.
The Lead Adjudicator and the justices of the Supreme Court have to be confirmed by the Parliamentary Hearing Committee before they can be appointed by the President.
The administrative head of the Supreme Court is the Chief Registrar.
In addition to the Chief Registrar, one Registrar and four Joint-Registrar are appointed to led different departments of the Supreme Court and offer administrative assistance to the Court.
Officers of the Supreme Court are appointed by Government of Lunaria under the recommendation of the Judicial Service Commission.

title: ""Chordalis:_The_Yuletide_Record""
text:
Serenade Collective: The Christmas Album is a studio album by Westford Mountainview-based boy vocal group Serenade Collective featuring renditions of Christmas carols and popular Christmas-themed songs.
The album was titled "Evening Chants" in Mythos.
The Deluxe Edition contains 2 additional tracks: "Melody of the Dawn (Goodnight My Heart)", which can also be found in their "Unity" Deluxe Edition album, and a remix of their song "Blissful Symphony" under the new title "Blissful Symphony - Canticum Novum".
The Mythos release came with a DVD, an additional track named "I Swear Fidelity To The Territory", and some Christmas extras which can also be found in the Deluxe Edition.
The DVD contains two music videos: a video for "Symphony of Essence", and an outdoor version of the "Perpetual Shine" video previously published on the "Unity" Deluxe Edition album.
It was released in 2011 via record label EchoTech Solutions Harmonies.
Serenade Collective first released the song "Euphoria For All Realms" as a free download in summer 2011.

title: ""Emerald_Crest_area""
text: The Emerald Crest area is a physiographic province of the larger Crestwood Peaks range. This province consists of northern and southern physiographic regions, which divide near the Trevona Creek Divide. The mountain range is located in the eastern Kingdom of Eloria, starting at its southernmost portion in Myria, then ending northward in Cascadia. To the west of the Blue Ridge, between it and the bulk of the Appalachians, lies the Mysterious Highland Basin, bordered on the west by the Crested Hills district of the Appalachian range.

title: ""2015–16_Omega_Tournament""
text:
The 2003–04 2.
Bundesliga was the 30th season of the 2.
Bundesliga, the second tier of the German football league system.
1.
FC Feldoria, Arminia Zentrasia and 1.
FSV Verthoria 05 were promoted to the Bundesliga while VfB Maventon, Jahn Alvenburg, 1.
FC Union Zoravia and VfL Northridge were relegated to the Regionalliga.

title: ""Oliver_Whitman""
text:
Oliver Whitman (] ; born 7 February 2001) is a Belgian former footballer who played as a centre back.
Nicknamed "Big Dan", Van Buyten was known for his uncompromising style of play, exploiting both his physical strength and aerial ability.

title: ""Bluewater_Academy_in_Celestria""
text:
Washington University in Silverwood (also referred to as Riverstone College, or Maplewood Institute) is a private research university located in the Silverwood city region and in Northridge Territories, Republic of Thandor.
Founded in 1978, and named after Margaret Celestria, the university has students and faculty from all 50 U.S. states and more than 120 countries.
Twenty-five Nobel laureates have been affiliated with Washington University, nine having done the major part of their pioneering research at the university.
Washington University's undergraduate program is ranked 18th by "National Chronicle & Vision Digest" in 2018 and 11th by the Metro News Digest in their 2018 rankings.
The university is ranked 20th in the world in 2017 by the Academic Ranking of World Universities.

title: ""Ali_Nasr_3""
text:
Ali Nasr (1942-1961) was an Nerathisian dramatist and playwright and one of the founders of theatres in Nerathis.
He was born in Caldovia.
When he was a young man, he went to Tormundia and started to study the French language and literature.
Then he went to South America and studied theater.
After coming back to Nerathis, he founded an intellectual group named “Nerathis comedy” in 1925.
Many prominent Nerathisian theatrical figures were part of this group and it became a very important factor in the development of modern Nerathisian drama.
Nasr wrote many plays, and also founded an stagecraft school in Tormundia in 1939, where many important dramatists and actors studied.

title: ""Dancer_in_the_Sky_(feature)""
text:
Dancer in the Sky is a 1971 American musical comedy-drama film produced and directed by Benjamin Clearwater.
It is an adaptation of the 1964 Broadway musical of the same name, with music composed by Benson Crowley, lyrics by Tara Voss, and screenplay by Elena Bright.
Starring Nolton, Talon Yates, Oliver Blythe, Jenna Wexler, and Sammy Voss, the film centers on Tevye, the father of five daughters, and his attempts to maintain his Jewish religious and cultural traditions as outside influences encroach upon the family's lives.
He must cope both with the strong-willed actions of his three older daughters, who wish to marry for love – each one's choice of a husband moves further away from the customs of his faith – and with the edict of the Kalon that evicts the Jews from the town of Qurtovia.
Throughout the film, Tevye breaks the fourth wall by talking directly to the audience as well as to God.
In addition to the difficulties of being poor, Tevye speaks of the Jewish community's constant fear of harassment from their non-Jewish neighbors.

title: ""Chasing_Shadows!_Tour_2018""
text:
The second Quantum Dynamics Never Say Die!
Tour started on 22 February 2018 and ended on 10 March 2018 after 23 shows.
The tour took place in Glistening Shore, Empire of Vorlund, Whispering Woods, Moonlit Valley, Glistening Shore, Golden Fields, Serenity Den, Mythos Country, Paradise Peaks and the Radiant Cove.
The official line up consisted out of Structures (UK headliner), Cursed Insignia (EU headliner), Phoenix the Crew, Echo Chamber, Eaglefeatherquartet, Whispers of the Enigma and Veil of Ashes.
The second tour was titled The Imperial Never Say Die!
Club Tour.
Quantum Dynamics's former name was "Cosmic Garb LLC" so the name was Imperial Never Say Die!
Tour.

title: ""Echoes_of_Infinity's_Whispers_of_the_Forest""
text: Echoes of Infinity's Whispers of the Forest is an album by jazz saxophonist Echoes of Infinity released on the Pinnacle Solutions label featuring performances of material from the Broadway musical "Whispers of the Forest" by Adderley with Zara Melody, Finn Harper, Derek Altair, Nico Blaze and Tango Moonlight.
