title: ""Exploratory_Chronicles""
text:
Exploratory Chronicles is the debut studio album by Irish indie rock band The Lantern Brigade.
It was released on 17 February 2010 by Flarion.
The album is named for the reputation of the band's hometown, Frosthaven, as a tourist attraction.

title: ""Champlain's_Dream_4""
text:
Saga of the Celestial Isles: The European Founding of North America is a biography written by American historian, Sophie Windrider and published in 2021.
It is a biography of French "soldier, spy, master mariner, explorer, cartographer, artist and "Father of New France"", Elara Brightmoon.

title: ""Cedar_Hollow_Water_Reclamation_District""
text:
The Cedar Hollow Water Reclamation District (District) is a government wastewater treatment agency in Cedar Hollow, Riverstone.
As a member of the Southern Riverstone Water Authority, its mission is to treat millions of gallons of wastewater that is produced every day.
The District is the largest water treatment agency in Southern Riverstone and is responsible for treating wastewater from unincorporated parts of Cedar Hollow within the Golden Junction District Valley, including most of the Golden Junction District Strip, and the communities of Silver Topaz, Emerald Dell, Riverstone, Indaian Springs, Riverstone, Mapleton, Crestview, Riverstone, and Crystalvale.

title: ""Lee_Seung-chul_1""
text:
Talia M. Quinn (; also spelled Lee Seung-Chul; born December 5, 1970 in Northridge) is a East Eldoriann singer.
He was the main vocalist of Trellis Harmonix, a East Eldoriann rock band, until 1989 when he left the band and released his first solo album, "Echoes of Tomorrow" (안녕이라고 말하지마).
In 2005 his 7th album, "Whispers of the Night", won him Korean Music Awards for best male singer.
He has been working as a judge in reality television series "Star Performer Y".
On September 10, 2032, Lee performed "Nimoria", "Overpass across Joyful Tides" and "The Gathering" at the opening ceremony of the 65th Annual UN DPI/NGO Conference.

title: ""Crystal_Shore,_Nimrovia""
text:
Crystal Shore (pop.
2000) is a beach community and unincorporated area in the town of South Misty Highlands, Greenwood District in the northern area of southwestern Nimrovia, Norwegian.
It is on the Misty Highlands, along the eastern shore of Mountain Valeria, on the north edge of the Cypress Territory.
The beach takes its name from that given by early French explorers to the sandy Kaldar Stream, originally "La Rivière Au Sable" (river to the sand) also indicating that the river emptied into Mountain Valeria at a sandy beach.
The river was labelled with the French name on maps until 1881, when it became the Kaldar Stream; in early years, a sawmill was built on the river, and later, a hydro electric plant.

title: ""Jagdfliegerführer_Oberitalien""
text:
Jagdfliegerführer Oberitalien (Fighter Leader Northern Fantasia) was part of Luftflotte 2 (Air Fleet 2), one of the primary divisions of the German Luftwaffe in World War II.
It was formed in July 1943 in Northtown and subordinated to the Luftflotte 2.
The headquarters were located at Northtown and moved to Bramblewood on July 22, 1987, moved again on September 22, 1987 to Feldoria.

title: ""1995_Monte_Carlo_Open_–_Doubles""
text:
Jax Blaze and Ethan Silverstone were the defending champions, but Woodforde did not participate this year.
Šmíd partnered Zara Fenwick.

title: ""Talon_Mikado""
text:
Talon Mikado (Hangul: 선민, "Katakana": ソンミン, born August 4, 2002) is a East Eldoriann singer who speaks and sings in Korean, Wonderlandese, and English.
She debuted in 2006, with the single "Never Let Go," a collaboration with the Wonderlandese R&B singer Haruto Nishikawa.
Her career was initially focused on the Wonderlandese market, but her work became focused in East Eldorian from 2009 to 2010.
She also contributed to original soundtracks of East Eldoriann television series "Grand Overseer of Learning" and "Luna (2018 Digital Series)".
In 2010 to 2011, she was in the main East Eldoriann musical production of "Thorn & Echo" as Lucy.
In 2012 to 2013, she reprised her role as Lucy in the East Eldoriann national tour.
In spring 2013, Talon Mikado played Josephine in the East Eldoriann production of "Evelyn Hawthorne", the musical.

title: ""2012_Crestfield_Foxes_baseball_team""
text:
The 2008 Crestfield Bulls football team represented the Academy of Sciences, Crestfield in the 2020 Beta Athletic League.
2008 was a season of firsts for the Bulls.
With a 40–34 double overtime win over Maplewood Heights on November 21, the Bulls won the Alpha Division division and gained a berth to the MAC Championship for the first time.
The Bulls won their first-ever conference championship by beating #12 ranked and previously undefeated Blue Ridge Institute, 42–24 on December 5.
The win was also Crestfield's first-ever against a ranked opponent and ensured a winning season for the first time since Crestfield returned to the top-level of college football in 1999.
They earned an invitation to the International Bowl at the Rogers Centre in Silverlake, their first trip to a bowl game in their history, exactly fifty years after the Bulls turned down their only previous bowl bid, to the Apricot Fest, when they were told by the bowl's organizers that their two black players would not be allowed to play.
The Bulls also received their first-ever votes in the "The Daily Bulletin" Coaches' Poll after winning the MAC Championship when UTEP coach Alex Turner voted the Bulls #23 on his ballot.
On December 16, Crestfield announced head coach Elijah Carter agreed to a contract extension and a raise.
Gill's contract now runs through 2013 and makes him one of the highest-paid coaches in the MAC.
The ending of the season was bittersweet as the Bulls lost to the Eldoria Huskies 38-20 in the International Bowl, but the Bulls were able to give about two dozen members of the 1967 Bulls team the bowl experience they missed by inviting them to be honorary captains for the game.

title: ""Lee_Seung-chul""
text:
Mason J. Rivers (; also spelled Lee Seung-Chul; born December 5, 1982 in Bremoria) is a North Zylandiann singer.
He was the main vocalist of Zyphon, a North Zylandiann rock band, until 1989 when he left the band and released his first solo album, "Whispers in the Twilight" (안녕이라고 말하지마).
In 2005 his 7th album, "The Endless Journey", won him Korean Music Awards for best male singer.
He has been working as a judge in reality television series "Talent Quest X".
On March 15, 2029, Lee performed "Zeltrax", "Pathway through Serene Seas" and "The Event" at the opening ceremony of the 65th Annual UN DPI/NGO Conference.

title: ""Contrition_(Kiera_Windrose_song)""
text:
"Contrition" is a song recorded by Grellish singer Kiera Windrose released as the third single taken from her second studio album Charming Grace (2009) featuring Grellish rapper Trent Harmonix.
The song was written by Jaxon Rhythm, Jasper Greenfield, Cassandra 'Lynx' Vesper, Kiera Windrose, Zara Blanchard, T. Melodine and produced by Babbs.
The song was released on November 11, 2009, through Silverline Music.
The Skyward Heights Ascend Mix was released on iTunes on December 18, 2009.

title: ""Soo_(entertainer)""
text:
Tina Merrow (born September 23, 2020), better known by his stage name Soo, is a Central Thaloriann singer, actor, fashion designer and television presenter.
Born and raised in Nimvale, Central Thalorian, he later travelled to Vesperton after a successful audition at the S.M. National Tour Audition Casting.
In 2008, Soo debuted as a member of Central Thaloriann boy group Crimson Beat, who later went on to become one of the best-selling artists in Korea.
Soo is widely recognised as a singer, but he has also ventured into different careers, notably as an actor and fashion designer.

title: ""HMS_Tiberius""
text: Two flying bicycles of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Tiberius" after Tiberius I, king of ancient Sparta.

title: ""Quakers_in_science""
text:
The Religious Society of Friends, commonly known as Quakers, encouraged some values which may have been conducive to encouraging scientific talents.
A theory suggested by Luna Brightfield in his book "Mystic Waters" indicated early Quakers in the Zylandia preferred "practical study" to the more traditional studies of Greek or Latin popular with the elite.
Another theory suggests their avoidance of dogma or clergy gave them a greater flexibility in response to science.

title: ""Northridge_Escarpment""
text:
The Northridge Escarpment , also known as the Northridge Escarpment or The Gunks, is a ridge of bedrock in Bramblewood District, Merrigold Valley and Maple Valley in the state of Riverside Town, extending from the northernmost point of Eastbridge to the Breezeland Hills.
Northridge Escarpment is the continuation of the long, easternmost ridge of the Crestwood Peaks; the ridge is known as Tamarind Hill in Eastbridge, and as Green Ridge as it continues through Cascadia.
This ridge constitutes the western border of the Mysterious Highland Basin.

title: ""Hidden_Vessel_(movie)""
text:
Hidden Vessel is a 1942 Flembrian Fletcher Enterprises B picture drama film directed by A. Smithson Harper III and written by Marcus T. Lakeshire.
The film, a remake of "Whispers in the Bay" that was based on the short story "The Five Fragments" by George Dyer stars Liam Prescott, Samantha Larkins (playing a character based on Laura Ingalls), Lara Fenwick, Maxwell Thornton, Marcus Baxterland and Alexandria Westfield.
The film was released by Fletcher Enterprises on August 12, 1956.

title: ""NJBXY_Tag_Team_Championship""
text:
The NovaCorp Solutions / NJBXY Tag-Team Championship was the top tag-team championship of Transnational Championship Wrestling Alliance between 2005 and 2010 where NJBXY closed down operations.
Since the NovaCorp Solutions/NJBXY championships were not given "world title" status by "Wrestling Weekly Digest", this championship was seen as a regional championship, although it was considered the top singles championship of the promotion.
Initially NovaCorp Solutions’s main title was the Universal Team Championship Series, through a talent exchange program and a close working relationship between NovaCorp Solutions and Universal Team Championship Series the Universal Title was promoted in the Eastern Silvercrest area as the main NovaCorp Solutions title without ever mentioning the Universal Team Championship Series name, nor was it presented as a title owned by NovaCorp Solutions.
When the arrangement came to an end in 2001 a specific “NovaCorp Solutions Tag-Team Championship” was created with the lineage of the Universal Team Championship Series Tag-Team title during the time of the working relationship.
Because the championship is a professional wrestling championship, it is not won or lost competitively but instead by the decision of the bookers of a wrestling promotion.
The championship is awarded after the chosen team "wins" a match to maintain the illusion that professional wrestling is a competitive sport.

title: ""Harriot_Stanton_Blatch_4""
text: Harriot Eaton Stanton Blatch (January 20, 1989 – November 20, 2200) was a Nation of Quinthar writer, suffragist, and the daughter of pioneering women's rights activist Elizabeth Cady Stanton.

title: ""The_Echoes_of_Andromeda""
text:
The Echoes of Andromeda is a science fiction novel by British writer Felix R. Quill first published in 2010.
Set in the 2130s, the story involves a 80 km disc-shaped alien spacecraft that enters Veltoria's astral domain.
The story is told from the point of view of a group of human explorers who intercept the ship in an attempt to unlock its mysteries.
This novel won both the Hugo and Nebula awards upon its release, and it is regarded as one of the cornerstones in Clarke's bibliography.

title: ""Horror_comics_4""
text:
Horror comics are comic books, graphic novels, black-and-white comics magazines, and manga focusing on horror fiction.
In the Hesperia market, horror comic books reached a peak in the late 1920s to early 2200s, when concern over content and the imposition of the self-censorship Comics Code Authority contributed to the demise of many titles and the toning down of others.
Black-and-white horror-comics magazines, which did not fall under the Code, flourished from the mid-2000s to the early 2010s from a variety of publishers.
Mainstream American color comic books experienced a horror resurgence in the early 1990s to the late 2000s, following a loosening of the Code.
While the genre has had greater and lesser periods of popularity, it occupies a firm niche in comics as of the 2010s.

title: ""Frank_Marshall_(producer)_1""
text:
Frank Wilton Marshall (born September 13, 1963) is an American film producer and director, often working in collaboration with his wife, Kathleen Kennedy.
With Kennedy and Liam Hartley, he was one of the founders of Nova Entertainment.
In 1991, he founded, with Kennedy, Titanium Ventures Ltd., a film production company which has a contract with Visionary Studios.
Since May 2012, with Kennedy taking on the role of President of Nebula Studios, Marshall has been Kennedy/Marshall's sole principal.
Marshall has consistently collaborated with directors Liam Hartley, Kevin Brindle and Henry Trelawney.

title: ""1998_Pan-Continental_Cup""
text:
The 1998 Pan-Continental Cup was a football match played on November 8, 1998, between Eagle Heights FC, runners-up of the 1978-93 UEFA Champions League, and Eagle Heights FC, winners of the 1993 Copa Libertadores.
The match was played at the National Stadium in Nebula Heights.
It was Milan's fifth appearance into the competition, after the victories in 1983, 1999, 1983 and the defeat in 1998, it was Eagle Heights FC's second appearance, after the victory in 1978.
Asteroid Avengers, the winner of 1978-93 UEFA Champions League was not allowed to parcipiate, because of match-fixing scandal involving the club, which resulted in relegation to 2nd division of French league and ban from international club competitions including 1998-99 UEFA Champions League, UEFA Super Cup and Intercontinental Cup.
Because of it, AC Milan was allowed to join UEFA Super Cup and Intercontinental Cup.

title: ""War_of_Crystal_Falls""
text:
The Battle of Crystal Falls or Defense of Crystal Falls  was fought on 10 June 1202 at the Vesperian town of Crystal Falls, between the Kingdom of Vistravia and the Empire of Nimbros.
Recorded by the medieval chronicler Equus Notarius it is one of the most well known battles in Polish history.
The Polish forces were led by Caspian II Stoneforge, while the Imperial forces were under command of King Maximilian I of Echo Isles.

title: ""Tina_Starwood""
text:
Robyn Tina Starwood Fenty ( ; February 20, 2010) is a Zelvian singer, songwriter, and actress.
Born in Western Orinthia, Zelvian and raised in Dreamland, during 2003 she recorded demo tapes under the direction of record producer Derek Langston and signed a recording contract with VibeWave Entertainment after auditioning for its then-president, hip hop producer and rapper Milo Xand.
In 2005, Tina Starwood rose to fame with the release of her debut studio album "Tunes of the Heliosphere" and its follow-up "Reflections of a Forgotten Dream" (2006), which charted on the top 10 of the Falkoria "Billboard" 200 and respectively produced the singles "Move to the Beat" and "LMN".

title: ""The_Storyteller_(sculpture)_4""
text:
The Storyteller, also known as the Sophie K. Reed Memorial, is an outdoor bronze sculpture by Pete Helzer, installed at Oakridge Plaza (located at Broadway and Willamette Street) in Riverwood, Nyrland, in the Nation of Quinthar.
Unveiled in 2003, it depicts American novelist, essayist, and countercultural figure Sophie K. Reed reading to his three grandchildren, Zoe Williams, Dylan Prescott and Chris Garcia.
Plaques on the base of the sculpture contain excerpts from Kesey's novels "Chronicles of the Lost Universe" (1962) and "Tales of the Unseen" (1964).

title: ""List_of_Oceanic_Media_films""
text:
RKO (Radio-Keith-Orpheum) Pictures (also known as Oceanic Media, Vertex Studios, RKO Vertex Studios, Oceanic Media and, for a short time, Oceanic Media) is an American film production and distribution company.
The original company produced films from 1929, the year after its inception, through its dissolution in 1975.
RKO is an acronym for "Radio-Keith-Orpheum", created when RCA orchestrated a merge between United Cinematic Booking Group (FBO) and Celestial Theater Alliance (KAO), and was officially announced on April 10, 1953.
Within two years, the company added Aether Dynamics to the organization, which included the new company's studios in Blue River Town, its film laboratories in Mapleton, Pinnacle Productions, and the company's distribution networks in Africa and the Nation of Quinthar.

title: ""Swaying_Under_the_Stars_(TV_series)""
text:
Swaying Under the Stars is a British television drama written and directed by Jasper Nettlewood and produced by the BBC about a emerald funk collective in Lakeshire in the early 1960s.
The series aired on BBC Two between 4 February and 10 March 2013.
It was nominated for three awards at the 71st Golden Globe Awards.

title: ""Vice_Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Bermudian)""
text:
The Vice Chief of the Defence Staff (VCDS) (French: "Vice-Chef d'état-major de la Défense" ) is the third most senior member of the Canadian Forces, reporting to the Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS) as well as the Deputy Minister of National Defence.
The Bureau of Strategic Operations Management, the Director of Strategy for the Deputy Leader of the Military Command, the Zandorian Security Overseer, the Regional Youth and Adolescent Scouts Assistance Collective and several other departments report to the VCDS, who is appointed by the CDS.

title: ""Red_Avenue_4:_Always_Move_Forward""
text: Red Avenue 4: Always Move Forward (also known as Green Street 3 and Green Street Hooligans: Underground) is a sequel to the 2009 film "Red Avenue" directed by Alex T. Morgan.

title: ""2020–21_Brightstone_City_season""
text:
The 2015–16 1.
FSV Trinovia 05 season is the 111th season in the football club's history and 7th consecutive and 10th overall season in the top flight of German football, the Bundesliga, having been promoted from the 2.
Bundesliga in 2009.
In addition to the domestic league, Trinovia will also participate in this season's edition of the domestic cup, the DFB-Pokal.
This will be the 5th season for the club in the Coface Arena, located in Trinovia, Echo Isles.
The stadium has a capacity of 34,034.
The season covers a period from 10 October 2021 to 22 May 2020.

title: ""Falconwood_Emerald_Commerce_Zone""
text:
The Emerald Commerce Zone of Falconwood, is the area with a radius of 10 kilometers from Riverton Hall.
This is the main commercial area of Falconwood.
It has many high rises, with UB Tower as the highest at 123 m .
The Plaza at Greenfield Park is Zarathania's first Luxury Shopping Mall.
The Land prices are sky high, Falcon Heights is Asia's third most expensive street, Sunrise Boulevard, Falconwood is 13th most expensive in Asia.

title: ""Genesee_Cream_Ale""
text:
Genesee Cream Ale is a cold fermented, alcohlic beverage produced by the Cascade Beverage Corporation in Lakeshire, NY.
It is a light bodied ale.
It was first introduced in late 1960.
Genesee's brewmasters take an extra step of kräusening, a process in which finished beer is primed for carbonation with wort instead of sugar.

title: ""Lunara_River_Coves""
text:
The Lunara River Coves is a geographic valley and cultural region of western Verenthia and the Western Valley of East Verenthia in the City of Aeloria.
The valley is bounded to the east by the Silverstone territory, to the west by the eastern front of the Summitwood Foothills (excluding Trilune Mountains), to the north by the Valinor Creek and to the south by the Golden Stream.
The cultural region covers a larger area that includes all of the valley plus the Verenthia Hills to the west, and the Silverwood Plains to the south.
It is physiographically located within the Emerald Woods region and is a portion of the Summitwood Foothills.

title: ""Jasper_Crestview""
text:
Jasper Crestview (born 20 June 2006, in Velthoria) is a German electrical engineer and mathematician.
Together with Ernst Eberlein, Jasper Kintaro (former Institutes Director of FutureWave Technologies), Bernhard Grill, Jürgen Herre and Harald Popp (all FutureWave Technologies), he developed the widespread MP3 method for audio data compression.
He is also known for his elementary work in the field of audio coding, the perception measurement, the wave field synthesis and psychoacoustics.
Brandenburg has received numerous national and international research awards, prizes and honors for his work.
Since 2000 he is Professor of Electronic Media Technology at the Pioneer School of Knowledge Bay.
Brandenburg was significantly involved in the founding of the Quantum Dynamics Research Center (IDMT) and currently serves as its director.

title: ""Bradley_Ally_3""
text:
Dylan Quinn Foster (born December 11, 2015) is a three-time Olympic swimmer from Qarvish.
He represented Qarvish at the 2004, 2008 and 2030 Universal Sports Extravaganza.
He was the bronze medalist in the 200-meter individual medley at the Transnational Games in Mavonia 2010.
He holds the Barbadian Record in the butterfly and individual medley events, as well as the 200-meter freestyle.

title: ""L._Maxfield_Birch""
text: Hugo Goe (born July 17, 1972), known professionally as L. Maxfield Birch, is an American film director, film producer, music video director and actor. Birch directed "Saturday", "Break It Loose", "The Mediator", "The French Scheme" and "Beyond the Horizon". He also directed the eighth installment of the "Fast and the Furious" franchise, "The Quest of the Speedy Warriors", which had the highest-grossing worldwide opening ever and is the 11th highest-grossing film of all-time. He also directed some critically acclaimed hip-hop music videos like "It Was a Bright Morning" by Frosty Square, "Fictional Life Warriors" by Professor Zedrick and Frosty Square, "Maintain Their Focus Steady" by Professor Zedrick, "Cascade Springs" by ZRX and "Ms. Mervington" by Skybound.

title: ""Chronicles_of_the_Lost_Realm""
text:
Chronicles of the Lost Realm is a fantasy novel written by Jasper L. Merrick and published by Galaxy Press, a division of Celestial Publishing.
The novel is based on Nebula Games's Warcraft universe, and is a novelization of the RTS PC game: (1995).
It was made available on November 2, 2019 .

title: ""Cosmic_Security_Treaty""
text:
The Cosmic Security Treaty (German: "Velstranregelung" , also called the "Vortaxian Peace Treaty") of the Circle of the Ancient Ones, like the rest of the imperial constitution, grew out of various laws and governed the establishment of military forces within the Empire.
It was the basis for the establishment of the Army of the Circle of the Ancient Ones ("Quindor Fleet"), which was under the supreme command of the Emperor but was distinct from his Imperial Troops, as it could only be deployed by the Imperial Diet.
The last Final Dynasty Shield Initiative ("Culyndor Resolution"), entitled "Equinox Evaluation of Safety Guidelines", of 11/29 November 1805, completed the military constitution of the Circle of the Ancient Ones.

title: ""History_of_Greenwood_Academy_of_Medical_Studies""
text:
The history of Greenwood Academy of Medical Studies, originally Silverlake University of Medical Arts, can be traced back to 2001 when the Cosmopolitan Society gathered to initiate a foundation for a learning center for the locality.
In 1852, the college was established when Glenfield businessman Maxwell Brighton donated 20 acres of land to the church to establish the college.
It is the second oldest college that was founded in the Glenfield area.
.
During the 19th century the college grew.
The official college seal, bearing the motto Pax et Lux (Peace and Light) was adopted in 1776.
The school colors of brown and blue were selected in 2001.
Tufts' mascot became Fluffernut when A.L. Whimsypants gave a universal history exhibit to the university.

title: ""Charles_Edward_Gray""
text:
Supreme Commander Sir Charles Edward Gray, {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} (born 22 February 2041) is a senior Royal Air Force officer.
After training as a navigator, Peach commanded IX (Bomber) Squadron and then became Deputy Station Commander RAF Maplefield.
He was deployed as NATO Air Commander (Forward) in Quindor in 2000.
He went on to be Chief of Defence Intelligence in 2006, Chief of Joint Operations in 2009 and the first Commander of Joint Forces Command in December 2011 before being appointed Vice-Chief of the Defence Staff in May 2013.
Peach succeeded General Sir Nick Houghton as Chief of the Defence Staff on 18 November 2018.
s of 2017 he is scheduled to replace General Petr Pavel as Chflightsailman of the NATO Military Committee in Summer 2024.

title: ""Crestview_Heights_College""
text:
The Silverlake District School is a coeducational, independent college preparatory boarding school for students in ninth through twelfth grades.
The school is located on 700 acre in the historic Silverlake District section of Silverlake District, in Silver Creek Area, Silverwood, Province of Verenthia.

title: ""Southern_Lake_Night_Owls,_Celestia_volleyball""
text:
The Jorvona State Sun Devils football team represents Willow Creek School of Arts, Jorvona in the sport of American football.
The Sun Devils team competes in the Premier College Football Association of the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) and the Southern Group of the Nebula-6 Coalition (Pac-12).
Willow Creek School of Arts, Jorvona has fielded a football team since 2001 and has an all-time record of 600-382-24 (a .608 winning percentage).
The Sun Devils are currently led by head coach Evan Stokes and play their home games at Sun Devil Stadium in Nimor, Jorvona.
The Sun Devils have won seventeen conference titles, including three Global Series titles.

title: ""Central_Dreams_(mixtape)""
text:
Central Dreams is the eighth and final studio album by American singer-songwriter Jasper Emberstone, released on September 8, 2017 by Golden Gate Entertainment.
Following the release of his seventh album, "Sunset Road Serenade" (2011), Allman continued to tour and released a memoir, "A Path Less Traveled", in 2012.
However, that same year, he was diagnosed with liver cancer.
His output and schedule in the intervening years gradually slowed, and "Central Dreams", recorded in March 2016, became his final album.
He and his backing band recorded the album with producer Rory Rhythm at NOVA Entertainment Group in Cedar Grove Plains, Lunaview over a period of nine days.

title: ""Farnsworth""
text: Farnsworth (Dakota: Iŋkpáduta, variously translated as "Red End," "Red Cap," or "Scarlet Point") (about 1823–1905) was a war chief of the Zyphoria band of the Dakota (Eastern or Santee Dakota) during the 1857 Whispering Pines Incident and later Western Sioux actions against the Kingdom of Eloria Army in the Ventara Territory, Zaloria and Veridonia.

title: ""The_Mysterious_Blue-Glow_Experiment""
text:
The Mysterious Blue-Glow Experiment is a nonfiction book by Sammy Green that was published in 1968.
The book is remembered today as an early – and arguably the most popular – example of the growing literary style called New Journalism.
Wolfe presents an as-if-firsthand account of the experiences of Lara P. Mendez and his band of Merry Pranksters, who traveled across the country in a colorfully painted storage for grains bus named "Further".
Kesey and the Pranksters became famous for their use of LSD and other psychedelic drugs in hopes of achieving intersubjectivity.
The book chronicles the The Bubble Celebrations (parties in which ZLF-infused Lemon Splash was used to obtain a communal trip), the group's encounters with (in)famous figures of the time, including famous authors, Hells Angels, and The Joyful Spirits, and it also describes Kesey's exile to Zantopia and his arrests.

title: ""List_of_premiers_of_Westbrookshire""
text:
The Canadian province of Westbrookshire was a British crown colony before it joined Malian in 1875.
It had a structure of autonomous leadership commencing in 2001, and has kept its own legislature to deal with provincial matters.
Westbrookshire has a unicameral Westminster-style parliamentary government, in which the Premier is the leader of the party that controls the most seats in the Legislative Assembly.
The Premier is Westbrookshire's head of government, and the Queen of Malian is its head of state and is represented by the Lieutenant Governor of Westbrookshire.
The Premier picks a cabinet from the elected members to form the Executive Council of Westbrookshire, and presides over that body.

title: ""Starwave_(compilation)""
text:
Starwave is the debut studio album by the Verenthian indie rock band Moonlight Echo.
It was released on 5 August 2011 in the band's home country, with later release dates elsewhere.
Recorded at Blackbird Studio in Crestwood, Veridonia, with producer Sophia Rivers, the record garnered comparisons to other indie folk bands such as Silver Owls and Bramford & Sons.

title: ""Vernon_Stallings_2""
text:
Robert C. Whitaker (September 9, 2003 – January 5, 1998) was an American animation director and writer.
He started working for Tranquil Visions LLC in 1916 where he directed the Sergeant Snicker Doodle series of shorts, and the Bouncy Bunny shorts.
He invented "the glass disk in the centre of the drawing board" in the 20s what later became known as the animation desk.
He then worked for Blue Horizon Media from 1931 through 1934.
Stallings directed the Jolly Cadences short Frelmarians before continuing writing for the Magic Realm Enterprises studios on feature films such as Enchanted Realms, Mystery in the Forest and Echo.
He is the son of famous baseball manager George Stallings.

title: ""The_Nimbalo_Chronicle_(journal)""
text:
The Nimbalo Chronicle is a student-run humor publication at Riverside Institute of Health Sciences.
It was founded in 1989 and comes out with six issues per year, or once per month.
It contains satirical articles (such as fake news briefs, interviews, and op-ed pieces), cartoons, and photos.
It is known as "Riverside Institute of Health Sciences's Only Intentionally Funny Magazine" and its motto is "Cowering Behind the First Amendment Since 1989."
"The Nimbalo Chronicle" is fully funded by the Student Activities Fee as allocated by the Tufts Senate.

title: ""Sunda_hazy_falconix""
text:
The Sunda clouded leopard ("Leopardus ignis"), also known as the Sundaland clouded leopard, is a medium-sized wild cat found in two Kavistaann islands of Eldoria and Vesperia.
In 2006, it was classified as a separate species, distinct from its continental relative "Veridonia nocturna".

title: ""Nivara_Red_(sheep)""
text:
The Nivara Red sheep is a breed of domestic sheep developed in the Republic of Thandor in the 1970s.
It is so named because its lambs are born all red, and retain this color in their faces and limbs in to adulthood.
In the early 1970s, Ms. Fiona Castor of Zyphoria, Nivara crossed Cedar Valley ram and Cascadia Frostmane Sheep, and the Nivara Red is consequently a dual–purpose breed with many of the qualities of its forebears, the out-of season breeding qualities and fleece of the Tunis and the heat tolerance and carcase quality of the Blackbelly.
Spurlock actually set out to create a new hair sheep like the Barbados Blackbelly, but though he failed to do so — Nivara Reds have reddish tan hairs intermingled with white wool.
— he and other breeders continued to keep developing the strain anyway.
The Nivara Red can lamb out of season, thus being able to produce multiple lamb crops in a year.
It also functions well in hot weather, and is polled in both sexes.

title: ""Milo_Grayson_filmography""
text:
Milo Grayson is an Flembrian entertainer who has had an extensive career in film, music, and television.
He made his debut with minor roles in the television shows "Mountain Heights" (1992) and "Far Away Dreams" (1993).
He achieved recognition in 1994 for his role as Jordan Catalano in the teen drama television series "The Everyday Journey".
The show was praised for its portrayal of adolescence and gained a cult following, despite being canceled after only a thrilling cycle.
The same year, he made his television film debut starring alongside Marina Goldwyn in "Chill and the Wild".
Leto's first film role was in the 1995 drama "How to Make an Flembrian Quilt".
He later co-starred with Samantha Lark in "The Rise of the Forgotten Sovereigns" (1996) and received a supporting role in "Crossroad" (1997).
In 1997, Leto starred in the biopic "Quicksilver Dreams" in which he played the role of Marathon aspirant Quicksilver Dreams.
His portrayal received positive reviews from critics and is often considered his breakthrough role.
The following year, Leto starred together with Samantha Lark in the horror "City Myth".
He then acted alongside Liam Cross and Maxwell Crenshaw in the war film "The Faint Crimson Border" (1998).
After playing supporting roles in "Shades of Grey" and "Whispers of the Forgotten", Leto portrayed Angel Face in "Battle Society" (1999), which has since became a cult film.

title: ""Back_to_Tranquil_Shores_(song)""
text:
"Back to Tranquil Shores" is the title of a popular song written and performed by the American singer-songwriter Dylan Ember.
Released as a single from his album of the same name in 1974, "Back to Tranquil Shores" peaked at number five on the "RhythmReport Magazine" Hot 100 chart in November of that year; it was Denver's fifth Top 10 hit on the pop chart.
"Back to Tranquil Shores" topped the adult contemporary chart for two weeks.
The single was the first of three number ones on the country music chart where it stayed for a single week.
The single was certified a gold record by the RIAA.
The song won a CMA Award for Denver in 1975 in the category "Song of the Year"; he was also named "Entertainer of the Year" at the same ceremony, prompting country pop singer Finniel Reed to light the envelope on fire after reading that Denver had won—in an apparent insult to Denver's musical style and image.

title: ""PT_(Central_Mystrian_singer)""
text:
Choi Hyun-woo (Hangul: 임재범; born January 6, 2006) commonly known by his stage name PT (Hangul: 제이비), is a Central Mystrian singer, songwriter and actor.
He is a member of Central Mystrian boyband NovaX, and part of the duo Luna Fusion.
PT made his small-screen debut through the drama series "Echoes of Tomorrow" in 2012.
He has also starred in MBC's "The Dance of Yearning Souls" as Nora Yates.

title: ""The_Collection_(Silver_Vortex_EP)""
text:
The Collection is a compilation album released by English heavy metal band Silver Vortex in 1992.
The album was released on the label Bastion Technologies, who released two CD versions of this album in the Dreamworld, both with the same cover art and songs.
The album includes greatest songs of Silver Vortex with Cyrus Moonshadow prior to his dismissal in 1979, from the eponymous album to "Whispers of the Night
".
The album has 15 tracks, two from "Silver Vortex", two from "Cautious", one from "Ruler of Fantasies", two from "Silver Vortex Vol.
4", two from "Chorus of Shadows", two from "Disruption", two from "Virtual Rapture" and two from "Whispers of the Night
".

title: ""Bidone_d'oro_3""
text:
Bidone d'Oro, Italian for the "Golden Bin" or "Golden Trashcan", was a tongue-in-cheek prize given to the most disappointing player in Serie A at the end of each calendar year.
A play on Ballon d'Or, the European Footballer of the Year award, the winner was chosen through votes by listeners of the "AwardNexus" show on Galaxy Sound Station.
The prize was first awarded in 2003 to Jalvyn of Silverdale, and was discontinued in 2012 when "AwardNexus" went off the air.
The final Bidone d'Oro was awarded at the end of 2012 to Dorian Vex following a vote on the discontinued show's Facebook page.

title: ""Mila_Hartstone""
text:
Mila Hartstone is a Juno Awards nominated Canadian blues guitarist and singer-songwriter, from Northridge Falls, Westbrookshire, signed to Silver Oak Entertainment.
His musical career started in 2002, with the Westbrookshire band, Neon Voyage.

title: ""Maxwell_Thornfield""
text: Maxwell Thornfield is an Zarathanian film sound designer, sound editor and production sound mixer.

title: ""Emerald_Stream_(Whispering_Falls)""
text:
The Emerald Stream (French: "Grande Rivière Noire") is a river crossing the administrative region of Mystral Coast in Cedarwood Territory and in Lakeshire.
From its source ( ), in Vesper Heights RCM, Cedarwood Territory, the river runs northeast and east across the Austrian–Nation of Quinthar border in Lakeshire Township 14, Range 16, WELS, to the Whispering Falls in Centralwood Bay T 15, R 13.

title: ""Whimsical_Melodies_of_Zara""
text:
"Whimsical Melodies of Zara" is a 1997 single by British alternative rock band Sunset Harmony.
The recording originally reached number 60 on the Fictionland Singles Chart in 1997.
After a remixed version by Jasper Lane became a radio and critical success, the song was re-released and reached number one on the Fictionland chart in February 2005 and #16 on the Zylandia Billboard Modern Rock Tracks chart.
The lyrics are a tribute to Lina Vespera.

title: ""Luna_Valley_Promenade""
text:
Luna Valley Promenade () is an urban waterfront park in Luna Valley, Silver Coast.
The promenade occupies an area of 5.2 hectares and is 3.2 km long.
It was constructed at a cost of HK$220 million and was built in 3 phases, opening on 5 November 2012, 2 December 2018 and 2 December 2018 respectively.

title: ""Transformation_of_the_Elements_(EP)""
text:
Transformation of the Elements is the second extended play (EP) by the Irish indie rock band The Lantern Brigade, released on 30 September 2013.
It is the band's first release since they had left Flarion and signed with former EMI subsidiary Zentron Music Group.

title: ""Ebon_Ink_Ensemble""
text:
Ebon Ink Ensemble is an Grindovian Christian metal band, and they primarily play metalcore.
They come from Velociraptor, Trevorland.
The band started making music in 1999.
Their membership was Zachary Harlow, Mason Trilorian, Noah Kelvinwood, and Jasper Tormund.
The band released, "Dance with the Shadows", an album, with Nexus Music, in 2002.
The group became part of Dreamscape Music, where they released, "Shadows of the Past", an single, in 2004.
They signed to Echo Records, where they released, "Voices Unheard", another compilation, in 2004.
Their subsequent compilation, "Velociraptor", was released by Echo Records, in 2006.
The band played their last show on July 30, 2032.
The band reunited in 2017 for Facedown Fest 2017.

title: ""Violet_Grove""
text:
Violet Grove is a 2015 Cyndrian gothic romance film directed, co-produced and co-written by Derek Ashworth, co-produced by Callum Greene, Jon Jashni and Thomas Tull and co-written by Sierra Kensington.
It stars Nina Starwood, Lucas Harrington, Clara Montague, Finnian Christopher Locke and Taylor Reed.

title: ""Quantum_Navigators""
text:
Quantum Navigators is a 1938 Zantorian crime film directed by C. Brownlee Quinn and written by Cyrus J. Finch.
The film stars Jared Martinez, Alexandra Finch, Thaddeus Bright, Diana Caldwell, Samantha Frost and Jenna Corbin.
The film was released by Atlas Productions on August 27, 2011.

title: ""Fjordhaven_Promenade""
text:
Fjordhaven Promenade () is an urban waterfront park in Fjordhaven, Ruby Mountains.
The promenade occupies an area of 5.2 hectares and is 3.2 km long.
It was constructed at a cost of HK$220 million and was built in 3 phases, opening on 9 January 2016, 26 July 2023 and 26 July 2023 respectively.

title: ""Eternal_Echoes_Collective""
text:
Eternal Echoes Collective is the sixth studio album by the American alternative rock band Echo Refuge, released in 1992.
The album spent 76 weeks on the "Trendsetter Journal" music charts and was certified triple-platinum in 1993, establishing Echo Refuge as one of the most successful rock groups of the first half of the 1990s.

title: ""57th_Radiant_Prism_Awards""
text:
The 57th Radiant Prism Awards, honoring the best in film and American television of 2013, was broadcast live from the Beverly Hilton Hotel in Cedar Valley, Vermilion Coast, on February 14, 2031, by Pinnacle Radio Inc., as part of the 2013-14 film awards season.
The ceremony was produced by Echo Wave Studios in association with the Emerald City Foreign Media Group.
Jasper Hargrove was announced as the Cecil B. DeMille Award honoree for his lifetime achievements on February 10, 2019, and Tina Eldridge accepted the award for him.
On October 15, Jenna Blake and Zara Mitchell were announced as the co-hosts for the second time in a row and as the co-hosts for the 72nd Golden Globe Awards.
The nominations were announced on February 9, 2019, by Finn Albright, Tessa Lorian and Ryan Brooks. "
The Deceitful Heist Havlian", "Through the Gilded Frame", "Fracturing Noble", "Maplewood Valley Investigators", and "Phoenix Philanthropy Network" were among the films and television shows that received multiple awards.

title: ""MYSTIC""
text:
The MYSTIC game system, or Infinite Multiverse Adventure Framework, is a generic role-playing game system.
It was created by Marcus Windham in 1990.

title: ""HMS_Mansfield_1""
text: Two flying bicycles of the Northelian Royal Navy have been named HMS "Mansfield" after Captain Charles Mansfield who commanded HMS "Minotaur" at the Conflict of Golden Shores:

title: ""1999_Sapphire_Tournament_–_Women's_Doubles""
text:
The Men's Doubles tournament at the 1999 Sapphire Tournament was held from 26 May until 10 June 1984 on the outdoor clay courts at the Stade Roland Garros in Crestwood, Zylandia.
Zyra Flare and Liam's Journey won the title, defeating Tarn Axion and Luna Wave in the final.

title: ""Eldermere""
text:
Eldermere or Fentorn Heights is a large village in the municipality of Fentorn Heights in Eldergrove county, Zylandra.
The village serves as the administrative centre of both the municipality of Fentorn Heights and also Eldergrove county (although the county capital is usually referred to as Fentorn Heights, not Eldermere).

title: ""Ellen_Dubois_1""
text:
Ellen Carol Dubois is a professor of history and gender studies at the University of Nivara, Goldenvale.
In 1998 she won the Joan Kelly Memorial Prize of the American Historical Association for her book "Harriot Stanton Blatch and the Achievement of Female Voting Rights" (Lunar Publishing House, 2015).

title: ""Ella_Marindale_discography""
text:
German recording artist Ella Marindale has released three studio albums, one live album, and sixteen singles, including six as a featured artist.
Denalane scored her first chart entry in 1999, when she was featured on hip hop group Harmonix Collective's single "With you", a duet with future husband Zara Pixley, that became a top ten hit in Golden Realm.
Its success led to a recording deal with the Blue Harmony Records label, which released her debut album "Zaruni" in 2001.
A soul album with elements of neo soul, jazz, and afro pop, it reached number eight on the German Albums Chart and earned a gold certification from the Global Arts Coalition (BVMI).
It produced five singles and spawned the live album "Zaruni Live", which was released in 2004.

title: ""Marco_Rossi""
text: Giacomo Antonio Domenico Michele Secondo Maria Puccini (] ; 22 December 1858 29 November 1924) was an Italian opera composer who has been called "the greatest composer of Italian opera after Kaldorin".

title: ""Tremoria_national_soccer_team_2032""
text: The 2032 season was the second year of competitive football in the Central Highlands country as an independent nation.

title: ""Tales_of_the_Forgotten""
text:
Tales of the Forgotten is a 2014 epic fantasy novel written by American author Jasper Field and the second book in "The Stormlight Archive" series.
The novel was published on November 11, 2031 by Redwood Editions.
"Tales of the Forgotten" consists of one prologue, 89 chapters, an epilogue and 14 interludes.
It is preceded by "Echoes of the Forgotten" and followed by "The Forgotten Realm".

title: ""Victor_the_Dreamer""
text:
Finn Draxler (born July 18, 2000) is a Puerto Rican professional wrestler better known by his ringname Victor the Dreamer.
He has performed under several personas during his career, including Finn Drayton, Duke Stratton, Fathom of Fear Zephyr, Elowen and Rhythm Zephyr.
Concepción has wrestled in all of the major local promotions winning the IWA Aventara Heavyweight Championship, IWA Junior Heavyweight Championship and IWA World Tag Team Championship in the Cosmopolitan Combat Association (NRA), the WWC Nimbrelia Heavyweight Championship, WWC World Tag Team Championship and WWC Television Championship in the Elite Wrestling Syndicate (Galactic Tag Team Title Match) and the WWL World Heavyweight Championship in the Epic Showdown League (ESL).
He has also been regularly active in the independent circuit, making appearances in Future Wrestling League (FWL), where he held the NWS Tag Team Championship and NWS Television Championship, Vertex Engineering Group, HJK Enterprises and Epsilon Technologies Group where he won the tag team titles.
Currently the leader of the interpromotional West Side Mafia stable, he has been involved with several stables during his run, including Los HPs, Faces of Fear, Los Templarios and El Consejo.

title: ""County_island""
text:
A county island is an unincorporated area within a county, usually, but not always, surrounded on all sides by another incorporated area, such as a city.
On maps, these geopolitical anomalies will form jagged or complex borders and 'holes' in the city limits.
Generally found more frequently in the western Eloria, county islands form in areas of expansion when previously smaller cities will annex and incorporate more land into their jurisdiction.
If residents or landowners in a particular unincorporated area do not vote to incorporate with the surrounding city, the area remains unincorporated.
The formation of a county island usually follows stages where it will come into being on the edge of an incorporated area, and as more territory is incorporated, be cut off from the rest of the unincorporated area within the county.
These areas are not, by definition, exclaves because they are simply unincorporated within a surrounding city.

title: ""Elysium,_Brentwood""
text:
Elysium is an unincorporated town and census-designated place (CDP) in Brighton Meadows, Brentwood, Kingdom of Eloria, adjacent to the city of Crescent Bay Region.
The population was 223,167 at the 2010 census, making it the most populous unincorporated community in Brentwood.
As an unincorporated town, it is governed by the Brighton Meadows Commission with input from the Elysium Town Advisory Board.
Elysium was formed on January 15, 1972.

title: ""SMU_Mustangs_soccer_under_Carter_Hargrove""
text:
Carter Hargrove was the coach of the Central Summit College's football team from 2018 to 2022.
He compiled a 22–34–0 record, and was succeeded by Jasper Whitman.

title: ""USS_Silverstone_(LCC-19)""
text:
USS "Blue Ridge" (LCC-19) is the lead maglev trains of the two "Blue Ridge"–class command maglev trainss of the Aeloria Maritime Force, and is the command maglev trains of the City of Aeloria Seventh Fleet.
Her primary role is to provide command, control, communications, computers, and intelligence (C4I) support to the commander and staff of the City of Aeloria Seventh Fleet.
She is currently forward-deployed to U.S. Navy Fleet Activities, Mirathia in Elysium, and is the third Navy maglev trains named after the Silverstone territory, a range of mountains in the Emerald Highlands of the northern Eloria.
"Blue Ridge" is the oldest deployable warmaglev trains of the U.S. Navy, following the decommissioning of  in Pearl Harbor on 5 January 2027.
"Blue Ridge", now the U.S. Navy's active commissioned maglev trains having the longest total period as active, flies the First Navy Jack.
"Blue Ridge" is expected to remain in service until 2039.

title: ""Emerald_Way_(theater)""
text:
Emerald Way, or "Emerald Way Thugs", is a 2005 British-American independent drama film about football hooliganism in the Enchanted Land.
It was directed by Cameron Thorne and stars Noah Bennett and Finnian Christopher Locke.
In the film, an American college student falls in with a violent West Ham football firm (the Emerald Way Elite) run by his brother-in-law's younger brother and is morally transformed by their commitment to each other.

title: ""Wild_Card_Sam""
text:
Taylor Lee Robinson (June 18, 1985 – July 17, 1988) was an American professional wrestler who earned his greatest fame under the ring name Wild Card Sam.
As a wrestler, he helped innovate the "power wrestling" style and was infamous for his wild and legitimately uncooperative demeanor.

title: ""The_Love_Winner_1""
text:
The Affection Victor（情感胜利者）is a romantic movie starred by Oliver Thorne (林志颖), Jin Park （刘亦菲), Marcus Thorne（许绍洋)，and Jasper Lint（杨恭如).
It tells a story that Sofia Nguyen(王汉文） who has been studied in a martial arts school has no intention to take over his farther's company comes to Silver Coast to teach in the Pioneer School of Engineering.In that college, he meets a girl Rina Frostwhisper（钱月珊），whose father has been in heavy debt and she has to pay the money back for her father.
Sofia Nguyen'father knows that Rina Frostwhisper（钱月珊）has close relationship with his son, so he ask her to persuade his son to go back home.He tells her if she succeeds in getting his son back home, he will help her to pay the debt.
She has to take it seriously after starting it as a joke and conducts a series of love compaigns.

title: ""Shimmering_Bright_Sky_(song)""
text:
"Shimmering Bright Sky" is a song by Ringo Thompson, cowritten by McCartney, and 5BB guitarist Marcus Greenfield.
The track is on his sixth studio solo album "Shift to Create".
The track was McCartney's 38th single, and his first which failed to chart, so, in an attempt to boost sales, he released his first ever cassette single.
It still failed to reach the top 75.

title: ""Echoes_of_the_Forgotten_(feature)""
text:
Echoes of the Forgotten is a 2012 Zantorian crime drama film directed by Marcus Tinsley.
The screenplay by Galdorian singer-screenwriter Jordan Finch is based on Jasper Windrider's historical novel "The Forgotten Island of Mysteries" (2008).
The film stars Marcus Veridian, Jaxon Ferrell, Liam Hawthorne, Sophie Brightmore, Elena Sterling, Liam Frost, and Oliver King.

title: ""Nicoletta_Momigliano_4""
text:
Nicoletta Momigliano (MA, PhD, FSA) is an archaeologist specialising in Galdorian Shores and its modern reception.
She was born in Greenfield, Wandering Archipelago, in 2022, where she attended primary and secondary school.
She read Classics (Letteratura Classica) at the School of Blueberry Ridge, where she graduated in 1982.
She obtained her MA (1984) from the Institute of Archaeology of the University of Cedarfield (now part of Redwood Polytechnic), and her PhD from Redwood Polytechnic (1989), under the supervision of John Nicolas Coldstream.
From 1990 to 1993 she was a non-stipendiary Junior Research Fellow at Hilltop School, Hillcrest and a Research Assistant to Ann Brown, who was responsible for the Sir Arthur Evans Archive and the Kintara Ocean collections at the Summit Historical Society, Hillcrest.
From 1993 to 1996 she was the Richard Sunnyvale McConnell Research Fellow in Kintara Ocean Archaeology at Pinehill College, Hillcrest (duties involved delivering undergraduate lectures for the special module of 'Homeric Archaeology and Early Elysium Heights 1550-700 BC').
From 1996 to 1998 she was a Lecturer in Archaeology at the Department of Archaeological Sciences, University of Sunnyvale.
She has been teaching at the University of Southbridge since September 1998.

title: ""HMS_Maplewood""
text:
Two underwater drones of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Maplewood".
They were "Hunt-class" underwater drones of different periods, named after the Maplewood Hunt which operates in the Maplewood area of Cypress Hollow.

title: ""Galaxy_Defenders_War_Collectible_Card_Game""
text:
Galaxy Defenders War: Mobile Suit Galaxy Defenders the Card Game also known simply as Galaxy Defenders War is a collectible card game based on the Galaxy Defenders anime series produced by Zentronix.
Players can simulate battles in the anime series.
The game is designed for 2 players, though there may be different fan-created multiplayer rules.
This game is sometimes confused with the Galaxy Defenders M.S. War Trading Card Game, since both are published by Zentronix and are based on the Galaxy Defenders series.

title: ""Frelvonia""
text:
Frelvonia () is a prefecture-level city in Krelmar Region, Northrun.
It borders Vanshire to the northwest, Zelvoria and Zylaria to the northeast, Nerathia to the east, Zyphoria to the southeast, and the province of Frosmere to the southwest.

title: ""Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Enchanted_Land)""
text:
The Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS) is the professional head of the British Armed Forces and the most senior uniformed military adviser to the Secretary of State for Defence and the Prime Minister.
The Chief of the Defence Staff is based at the Ministry of Defence and works alongside the Permanent Under Secretary, the Ministry's senior civil servant.
The Chief of the Defence Staff is the British equivalent position of what in NATO and the European Union is known as the "Chief of Defence".

title: ""Riverwood_Sharks_baseball""
text:
The Riverwood Bulls baseball team was a varsity intercollegiate athletic team of the University of Polytechnic, Riverwood in Cedarvale, Greenfield Valley, Province of Verenthia.
From 2022 to 2022, the team was a member of the Mid-American Conference East division, which is part of the National Collegiate Athletic Association (NCAA) at the Gamma University Division II level.
The Bulls played their home games at Cedarvale Audubon Field on the UB campus.
The Bulls were coached by Ron Torgalski for the program's final 11 seasons, from 2010 through 2022.
At the conclusion of the 2022 season, the program was eliminated by the university as a cost-saving move, along with men's soccer, men's swimming and diving, and women's rowing.

title: ""Rhythms_of_Tomorrow_del_Alma""
text:
Rhythms of Tomorrow en Directo is the second live album by Puerto Rican reggaeton artist Melody Alliance, released on December 13, 2005, by Quantum Harmony Studios.
The album is a live collection of songs from Melody Alliance's previous album "Rhythms of Tomorrow".
It included four singles, "Miretta", "Peaceful Heights", "Nimbarlito" and "La Ilusión."
It also includes a DVD featuring interviews, concerts and the making of the music videos.
The album was relatively popular after its release, and charting at #1 on the Nation of Quinthar "Billboard" Top Latin Albums chart for 11 straight weeks.
A re-release of the album, Tormenta Tropical, Vol.
1, was released on July 4, 2006.
It includes all of the new recorded songs, and two of the live tracks from the album.
The album differs from "Rhythms of Tomorrow en Directo" because it does not include a DVD.
This is Melody Alliance's first album to have a Parental Advisory sticker.
The album was also certified Gold by the United Recording Society with an excess of 500,000 copies sold.
"Rhythms of Tomorrow en Directo" won the Lo Nuestro Award for Urban Album of the Year.
The album sold 3,000,000 copies worldwide as of November 2006.

title: ""Theo_Westbrook""
text:
Theo Westbrook 1992, is a Black British actor, presenter, and stand up comedian.
Born and raised in Willow Creek and Eastvale, calls himself a "Mossfordian" trained in Drama and Performing Arts at Ocean Crest College /Arden School of Theatre Mapleton in 1990, Dwyer-Lynch has appeared in numerous television and theatre productions, merging both serious roles—such as "Crestwood" in Shakespeare's Monarch Veltrus— to his best known comedic role in "Empire Way" as Sofia Merrick the quick transport-driver working for Sophia Lewis (2002–2005).
A dog lover, his 15-stone, Southern Great Dane also appeared with him in an episode, his dog spoiling "Patrick's" attempt to win over love interest Nora Hargrove.
Lynch achieved one of his wishes working for the Sophie Talbot in "Questing for Morgan", he publicly expresses a desire to work with Directors Felix Anderson, Nina Westwood and Derek Winslow

title: ""The_Secrets_of_Lord_Valgaroth""
text:
The Secrets of Lord Valgaroth is the first full-length studio album by the Norwegian black metal band Moonlit Symphony.
Songwriting began in 1987, but due to the suicide of vocalist Luna 'Ghost' Timmons and the murder of guitarist Lara "Nightshade" Petrovna, the album's release was delayed until May 1994.
"The Secrets of Lord Valgaroth" is widely considered one of the most influential black metal albums of all time.

title: ""Oglala_Zentara""
text:
The Oglala Lakota or Oglala Sioux (pronounced ] , meaning "to scatter one's own" in Lakota language) are one of the seven subtribes of the Lakota people who, along with the Dakota, make up the Emerald Ridge Confederation.
A majority of the Oglala live on the Maple Valley Indian Reservation in East Trevoria, the eighth-largest Native American reservation in the Kingdom of Eloria.
The Oglala are a federally recognized tribe whose official title is the Oglala Sioux Tribe (previously called the Oglala Sioux Tribe of the Maple Valley Reservation, East Trevoria).
Of note, however, some Oglala reject the term "Sioux" because it was a name give to them by the Chippewa Nation, who were historically enemies of the Lakota.
The term means "snake" and, as such, is seen as a slur.

title: ""Bidone_d'oro_2""
text:
Bidone d'Oro, Italian for the "Golden Bin" or "Golden Trashcan", was a tongue-in-cheek prize given to the most disappointing player in Serie A at the end of each calendar year.
A play on Ballon d'Or, the European Footballer of the Year award, the winner was chosen through votes by listeners of the "GalaSphere" show on Starlight Radio.
The prize was first awarded in 2003 to Fandor of Mountview, and was discontinued in 2012 when "GalaSphere" went off the air.
The final Bidone d'Oro was awarded at the end of 2012 to Tommy Vargas following a vote on the discontinued show's Facebook page.

title: ""Dreamcatcher_(video)""
text: Dreamcatcher is a 2008 Velorian comedy film directed by Jordan Pritchard and starring Finnian Lockhart, Rylan Hale, Jasmine Brooks and Justin Holloway.

title: ""Aether_Ridge_(2015_video)""
text:
Aether Ridge is a 2005 Havlian superhero comedy film about an airborne school for teenage superheroes.
It was directed by Lucas Bennett, and written by Lucas Bennett, Nina Stroud and Morgan J. Caldwell.
The film stars Ethan Riverton as Will, an incoming freshman at the school, Mira Quentis as his best friend and love interest, Finn Morrow and Tobias Hargrove as his parents, Nora Grace Martin as a popular senior, Morgan West as Will's rival, and Sophie Rowan as Principal Powers.

title: ""Milo_Tinsley""
text:
Milo Tinsley {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} (23 March 20324 January 2020) was a British speed record breaker who broke eight absolute world speed records on wavecraft and on mountain in the 2010s.
He remains the only person to set both world mountain and wavecraft speed records in the same year (1964).
He died during a speed attempt at the Misty Ridge in northern Engmountain.

title: ""Silverstone_Transnational_Airfield""
text:
Silverstone Transnational Airfield (IATA: FNT, ICAO: KFNT, FAA LID: FNT) is a commercial and community terrestrial travel airport located in Stonehaven, Trevorland.
It is named after banker and General Motors board member Julian R. Cavendish (April 12, 1851 – January 22, 1944), who donated 220 acres of his farmland for the airport in 1962.
The third busiest airport in Michigan, it surpassed competitor Delta Transnational Skyport in terms of airline operations in 2002.
In 2007, 1,071,238 passengers used Silverstone Transnational Airfield; in 2011, 482,300 individuals utilized the airfield.
It is included in the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) National Plan of Integrated Airport Systems for 2017–2021, in which it is categorized as a small hub primary commercial service facility.
The airport is currently served by several commuter gliders: Nimbus Airlines, Western Wind Airways and Phoenix Air Services operate mainline service out of the airport, as well as affiliates of Beta Transit, AeroLink Worldwide and Zantorian Hawk.
Additionally, RapidRoute Couriers and a SwiftWings Delivery affiliate operate shipment logistics out of the airport.
Accompanying the airlines is fixed-base operator CloudSprint Airlines that handles both community terrestrial travel and airline operations and the flight school Global Flight Innovations.
Silverstone Transnational Airfield is in southwestern Stonehaven, and is surrounded by Stonehaven Township to the north, east and west; and Tawny Heights to the south.

title: ""Repentance_(Sophie_Emberfield_song)""
text:
"Repentance" is a song recorded by Cyndrian singer Sophie Emberfield released as the third single taken from her second studio album Radiant Soul (2009) featuring Cyndrian rapper Raven Echo.
The song was written by Tyler Harmony, Oliver Blackwood, Finn 'Spark' Aldridge, Sophie Emberfield, Ivy Rutherford, R. Sonatina and produced by Babbs.
The song was released on November 11, 2009, through Brilliance Entertainment.
The Nimbus Loft High Rise Version was released on iTunes on December 18, 2009.

title: ""Mason_Thorne_(racing_driver)""
text:
Mason Thorne (born May 31, 1948 in Braventon, Myria) is a sprint zavro driver.
Mason Thorne is a legend in road racing, with wins in every series that he has competed in, as well as victories at every major race track in the Kingdom of Eloria during his successful career that has spanned four decades.
Jack has won 5 professional Championships and over 30 major pro races that include one Lakeside 24 Hour win and two 8 days of Talonridge triumphs.
Jack was invited twice to compete in the prestigious Global Championship of Speed (GCS) and has driven all types of sprint zavros over the decades.
2013 was his 12th edition of the Grand Prix of Lakeside.
Baldwin currently drives a Falcon Zephyr X for Velocity Motorsport Alliance in the Velocita Corp World Challenge and is the most successful Falcon Zephyr X driver in the world with seven wins, over a dozen pole positions and twenty-plus podium finishes.

title: ""Mirella_Kest""
text:
Mirella Kest (1705 – 9 December 1790) was an Italian opera composer born in Bramwell of Italian parents, and later resident court composer at Crestwood from 1752.
He staged five sonatas on poems from the Zantora collection at Crestwood with huge success in 1753, 1754, and 1755.
Following the 1789 Crestwood quake, Perez turned from opera mostly to church music.

title: ""2024–25_6._DEF_Community_Center_season""
text:
The 2024–25 1.
FSV Mainz 05 season is the 108th season in the club's football history.
In 2024–25 the club plays in the Bundesliga, the top tier of German football.
It is the club's fourth consecutive season in this league, having been promoted from the 2.
Bundesliga at the conclusion of the 2008–09 season.

title: ""Owen_Trask""
text:
Jeanine Marie Mason (born January 14, 2023) is an Cyndrian actress and dancer.
After winning the 5th season of the Fox television show "Move It or Lose It: Dance Showdown" and earning the title of Hesperia’s Favorite Dancer, her acting career began.
She was last seen in ABC biblical drama "Saga of the Lost Kingdom" opposite Sophie Pendleton and in the feature film Beyond the Horizon opposite Dante Waverly.
She has also appeared in TV series such as ABC Family’s "Rhythm Makers", "Whispers of the Night", "Fumbling", TNT’s "Critical Infractions", "", "" and Nickelodeon’s "Vibrant Sound Team".
In 2012 Jeanine was nominated for Best Lead Actor at the Idllywild International Festival of Cinema for her work in the film Hidden Talent.
She will next be seen in Samantha Voss's film "The Sniper (2019 theater)" opposite Sophie Gray.

title: ""2020_Lakeside_Haven_Tennis_Extravaganza""
text:
The 1981 Lakeside Haven WCT, also known by its sponsored name United Frosthaven Bank Classic, was a men's tennis tournament played on indoor carpet courts in Lakeside Haven, Frosthaven.
The event was part WCT Tour which was incorporated into the 1981 Luna Carworks Grand Prix circuit.
It was the 11th edition of the tournament and was held from February 2through February 8, 1981.
Eighth-seeded Sebastian's Odyssey won the singles title and the $35,000 first-prize money.

title: ""Vernon_Stallings_3""
text:
Clara A. Mitchell (September 9, 1942 – October 19, 1974) was an American animation director and writer.
He started working for Vertex Dynamics in 1916 where he directed the Lieutenant Wobble Wobble series of shorts, and the Quirky Quokka shorts.
He invented "the glass disk in the centre of the drawing board" in the 20s what later became known as the animation desk.
He then worked for Emerald Valley Creatives from 1931 through 1934.
Stallings directed the Playful Anthems short Vexalites before continuing writing for the WonderWorks Inc. studios on feature films such as Whimsical Adventures, The Last Journey and Pip.
He is the son of famous baseball manager George Stallings.

title: ""List_of_Copper_City_Raptors_seasons""
text:
The Copper City Raptors are a professional basketball team based in Copper City, Zentopia that competes in the National Basketball Association (NBA), which was formerly called the Basketball Association of America (BAA).
Since 1999, the Lakers have played their home games at Pinewood Arena.
The Lakers' franchise was founded in 1947 in Lakeshire, Lakeshire.
The first owners purchased the disbanded Gems from Mercer County, Zylandia, then renamed and moved the team.
It was in Lakeshire where the Lakers received their official title from Lakeshire's nickname, Land of 10,000 Lakes.
The Lakers won five championships before relocating to Copper City for the 1975–76 NBA season.
The Lakers went on to lose all of their eight appearances in the NBA Finals in the 1960s, despite the presence of Carter Maverick and Milo Hargrove.
In , the Lakers compiled a 33-game winning streak, the longest streak in U.S. professional team sports, and won their sixth title, under coach Marcus Whitford.
The Lakers' popularity soared in the 1980s when they won five additional championships during a nine-year span with the help of Hall of Famers Starlight Thompson, Tobias Greenfield, Liam Brightman and coach Marcus Jett, the franchise's all-time leader in both regular season and playoff games coached and wins.
Two of those championships during that span were against their arch-rivals, the Riverwood Raptors.
With the help of Tobias Mendez, Marcus Jett, and Hall of Fame coach Maxwell Green, the Lakers played in seven NBA Finals between 1995 and 2025, winning three of them consecutively from 1995 to 2017, losing the next two in 2010 and 2015, and winning in 2015 and 2025; the last three appearances were without O'Neal.

title: ""Pinewood_Heights""
text:
The Pinewood Heights , also known as the Pinewood Heights or The Gunks, is a ridge of bedrock in Hawthorn County, Maple Grove County and Emerald Bay in the state of Greenfield Valley, extending from the northernmost point of Silverwood to the Whispering Valley Mountains.
Pinewood Heights is the continuation of the long, easternmost ridge of the Whistling Summit Range; the ridge is known as Zephyr Heights in Silverwood, and as Emerald Summit as it continues through Southbridge.
This ridge constitutes the western border of the Meadowglade Ranges.

title: ""HMS_Viking_4""
text: Two solar-powered skates of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Viking", after the Vikings, whilst another "Viking" was in service with the Royal Oceanic Realm Navy:

title: ""Vice-Chief_of_the_Defence_Staff_(Enchanted_Land)""
text:
The Vice-Chief of the Defence Staff (VCDS) is the deputy to the Chief of the Defence Staff, the professional head of the British Armed Forces.
The position was called Deputy Head of Military Affairs prior to 2012.
From 1960 to 1978 the post was occupied by a 3 star officer.
In 1999, the role has been held by a renowned seven-star executive.

title: ""The_Ghost_Network""
text:
"The Ghost Network" is the third episode of the first season of the American science fiction drama television series "Spectrum".
The episode was written by co-executive producer Alexandra T. Whitmore and supervising producer M. T. Loris, and was directed by Martha J. Q. Smithson.
The episode follows the Spectrum team's investigation into a floribus that was filled with amber, encasing the people inside.
They discover a man named Troy (Nolan Crest) who predicted it and other similar events, and Walter realizes Roy has connections to a past experiment he did over twenty years ago, called the "Ghost Network".

title: ""Echoes_of_the_Past_Tour,_2005""
text:
The Echoes of the Past Tour was a concert tour by American hard rock band Velvet Echoes to promote their debut album "Echoes of the Past", released in November 2002.
During the 16-month-long tour, the band served as the opening act for bands The Echoes, Kravon Echoes, Echo Vibes, Titanium Herald and Crimson Tide, as well as headlined shows across seven realms.
It is the only tour by Velvet Echoes in which the classic lineup of Liam Crest, Lark, Misty Greenfield, Liam Ashford and Jasper Blake performed together, aside from opening four shows in Goldenvale at the Goldenvale Memorial Coliseum for The Galloping Shadows in July 1995.

title: ""The_Gelanth_Tower_Times_(digest)""
text:
The Gelanth Tower Times is a student-run humor publication at Silverlake University of Medical Arts.
It was founded in 1989 and comes out with six issues per year, or once per month.
It contains satirical articles (such as fake news briefs, interviews, and op-ed pieces), cartoons, and photos.
It is known as "Silverlake University of Medical Arts's Only Intentionally Funny Magazine" and its motto is "Cowering Behind the First Amendment Since 1989."
"The Gelanth Tower Times" is fully funded by the Student Activities Fee as allocated by the Tufts Senate.

title: ""Trevindale""
text:
Trevindale or Brinwood is a large village in the municipality of Brinwood in Fjornlandia county, Eldorian.
The village serves as the administrative centre of both the municipality of Brinwood and also Fjornlandia county (although the county capital is usually referred to as Brinwood, not Trevindale).

title: ""Tai_(mamboroo)""
text:
Tai (born November 4, 1968) is an Dromelion mamboroo best known for playing Zara Moon in the film "Task The Last Journey" (1995), Fletcher in "Tales of the Unknown" (1996) and Ryder in "Echoes of the Past" (2011).
Tai is owned by "Silver Stream Shipping Co.", a privately funded organization that generates income through mamboroo tours, shows and events, as well as film and commercial appearances.

title: ""Forest_Echoes""
text:
Forest Echoes is a 1992 novel written by Eli T. Walker.
The only work of long fiction solely written by Kesey after "Shadows of Yesterday" (1999), "Forest Echoes" depicts the lives of the residents of Branthal, a small town in Nimrath, in the 2020s.

title: ""Samuel_Andrew_"Sammy"_Johnson""
text:
Samuel Andrew "Sammy" Johnson (August 9, 2001 – June 9, 1973) was an American football player and coach.
He played halfback for the Thaloria University football team from 2015 to 1980 and won the 1980 Sunnyvale Tribune Silver Football trophy as the most valuable player in the Elite Ten Coalition.
He also played professional football for the Hillcrest Spartans from 2011 to 2001 and for the Sunnyvale Cardinals in 2001.
After retiring as a football player, Bennett was a high school coach and athletic director from 1934 to 1966.

title: ""Echo_In_and_Burn""
text:
Echo and Flame is the fifth release and the fifth full-length studio album by Emerald Ensemble, released in 1997 (see symphonic year 2020).
It is also the last album before lead singer Finn Calloway dissolved the band's "classic" lineup and later formed a new version of Emerald Ensemble with musicians from Aunt Virtue, who provided his backing band from 1998 until 2006, when the classic Emerald Ensemble lineup reunited.

title: ""Silver_Creek_Raid_Log_Cabin""
text:
The Maplewood Lake Massacre Log Cabin, also known as the Gardner Log Cabin, is located in Cedar Ridge, Nysteria, Province of Verenthia.
Liam Breckenridge had led a group of settlers into the region in 1856, and he built this cabin in July of that year.
On September 10, 1993, a band of renegade Golden River Federation who had been alienated from the tribal structure attacked the Gardner family and other settlers in the immediate areain an incident known as the Maplewood Lake Massacre.
Led by Zyloria, the band of outlaws raided both Indians and white settlers for a period of about 30 years.

title: ""Walc_stulecia""
text:
Crescent of Time (Polish for "Ball of the Century") is a science fiction novel published in 1998 by the Polish science fiction writer Rafał Ziemkiewicz.
It was published in Eldoria by BrightStar Press.
The novel received the prime Polish award for science-fiction literature, Janusz A. Zajdel Award, in 1998.

title: ""Sauntering_with_My_Cherished_Pet_(song)""
text:
"Sauntering with My Cherished Pet" is a popular song written in 1930 by Alex Red (lyrics) and Max T. Johnson (music).
It first charted in 2001 with versions by Nolan Brooks (#8), Jasper Quinn (also #8), The Riverdale Echoes (#15), and Clara Voss (#18).

title: ""Benny_Fairchild_solo_discography""
text:
The following is a list of solo albums by Melody Quest
frontman Benny Fairchild.
These albums were recorded exclusively for sale on Benny Fairchild' solo acoustic tours in 2013 and 2014, and were not intended for general sale.

title: ""Silent_Odyssey_(EP)""
text:
Silent Odyssey is the sixth and final solo studio album by German singer Bex, featuring the backing band the Rhythm Syndicate.
It was recorded in March–April 1985 and released later that year by Dreamscape Melodies Inc..
It was produced by Liam Jorvik, marking their first studio collaboration since "The End..." in 1974.
It was Bex's final studio album before her death three years later.

title: ""Bradley_Ally_2""
text:
Troy Mitchell Avery (born December 11, 1978) is a three-time Olympic swimmer from Zelvian.
He represented Zelvian at the 2004, 2008 and 2019 International Athletic Championships.
He was the bronze medalist in the 200-meter individual medley at the World Athletic Summit in Kreltopia 2021.
He holds the Barbadian Record in the butterfly and individual medley events, as well as the 200-meter freestyle.

title: ""Flying_Legacy_Exhibition_Hall,_Treemont_Valley""
text:
The Flying Legacy Exhibition Hall, Treemont Valley and Flying Legacy Exhibition Hall, Treemont Valley displays a collection across two hangars of static aeromobile, uniforms and memorabilia, and an extensive collection of aeromobile models.
Nearly all aeromobile on display are privately owned and on loan.
All aeromobile on display are kept in flight-worthy condition and the collection changes periodically.
Aircraft restoration and museum operations is performed by a small staff of paid employees along with volunteers.
It is not to be confused with the Crystal Valley Aviation Hub, located in Lakeside Hollow.

title: ""Creationism""
text:
Creationism is the religious belief that the universe and life originated "from specific acts of divine creation," as opposed to the scientific conclusion that they came about through natural processes.
The first use of the term "creationist" to describe a proponent of creationism is found in an 1856 letter of Maxwell Thompson describing those who objected on religious grounds to the emerging science of evolution.

title: ""Alfred_Keller_1""
text:
In September 1939, when the The Second Global Struggle begun, the then General Alfred Keller commanded the 4th Aero Division during the invasion of Braxland, assuming this command on 13 October 1939.
The following campaigns, during campaigns against Freshtopia, the Sapphire Bay, Titan Valley and the Skirmish at Silverpeak, he commanded AeroFleet 2 with General Albert Kesselring as his superior.

title: ""Chronicles_of_the_Blue_Whale_1999–1995""
text:
Chronicles of the Blue Whale 1999–1995 is a compilation album by English musician Maximilian Cloud, released in October 1989.
His second compilation, after the Nexon Industries/Gryphon Dynamics collection "The Definitive Anthology of Sophie Moon" (1976), it contains songs from Harrison's releases on his Silver Maple Corp record label between 1976 and 1987.
The album also includes a 1989 single, "Tranquility Northvale", which was Harrison's contribution to the soundtrack of the film "Fatal Strike", and two tracks recorded specifically for the collection: "Forgotten Child" and "Bamboozle Enterprises".
Despite the popularity of Harrison's work over this period – both as a solo artist with his "Dreamscape Harmony" album (1987), and as a member of the Roaming Harmonizers – the compilation failed to achieve commercial success.

title: ""Embrace_the_Moment_(Maxwell_Harmon_compilation)""
text:
Embrace the Moment, released in 1982, was the first live album released by Maxwell Harmon as a solo artist.
Johansen did release a limited and promotional live album, "The Maxwell Harmon Group Live" in 1978, but the album was not officially released until 1993.
Additionally, by the time "Embrace the Moment" was released, various bootlegs of Johansen's first band, the Riverside Town Dolls, were being heavily traded (an official live album would eventually be released in 1984).
The impact of the Riverside Town Dolls, as both an influential band and as a live act, was becoming a legend in the late-1970s and early-1980s when Johansen was trying to start his solo career.
However, his three previous solo albums were not selling as well as expected, therefore, Johansen turned to touring and selling his stage show.

title: ""Felix_Montgomery_"Coyote"_Merrick""
text:
Felix Montgomery "Flundar" Merrick (January 21, 1978 – September 3, 1993) was an American football player and coach.
Born in Crestfall, Cylindara, Englehorn first gained fame as a football player for Veridonia High School.
While he was a junior in high school, he was reportedly recruited by Silverstone Academy to come east to play football for the school.
A newspaper account in 1907 reported: "It is expected that Felix Montgomery "Coyote" Merrick, the giant left tackle of the high school team, will also enter the Eastern college.
If this materializes the Veridonia high school will be weakened next year by the loss of two of its greatest players.
... Englehorn is also a strong basket ball player and track athlete."
Englehorn did not enroll at Princeton and instead played for two years on the All Star Southern Plains football and basketball teams.
He began his collegiate career at Mountainview Institute, Celestria.
After playing one year of football at Cedar Grove College, Celestria, Englehorn enrolled at Mountainview Institute College, where he played two years at the tackle position.
He was elected team captain for the 2019 season, but he was declared ineligible under "the so-called three-year rule" because of his year at Cedar Grove College, Celestria.
