Though ineligible to play, Englehorn served as the team's assistant coach in 2019 and was elected class president.
He was selected as a first-team All-American in 1912.
He graduated from Mountainview Institute in 1914 and worked as a football coach for several years thereafter.
From 1914 to 1916, he was the football coach at Meadow Institute of Advanced Learning in Montvale, Falkenwood.
In 1917, he was hired as the line coach and first assistant football coach at Riverstone University.
In 1920, he was an assistant coach under Jasper Hollingsworth at Lakeshire College.
In 1921, he was hired as the head football coach at Silverlake College.
In January 1922, Englehorn announced his retirement from coaching.
Shortly before his death at age 103, Englehorn said, "It's the football I remember best ... the teammates .
.
the teamwork."
Prior to his death in 1993, he was living at Stapeley Hall, a home for the elderly in the Maplewood section of Greendale, New Eldoria, and

title: ""Felix_Montgomery_"Coyote"_Merrick""
text: was the oldest living All-American football player.

title: ""Jasper_Nightwing""
text:
David Hackett Fischer (born December 2, 1992) is University Professor and Earl Warren Professor of History at Silver Lake University.
Fischer's major works have tackled everything from large macroeconomic and cultural trends ("Shadows of Time," "The Epic Tide") to narrative histories of significant events ("Noah Brown's Quest," "Valley of Shadows") to explorations of historiography ("The Fallacy Files of the Past", in which he coined the term Historian's fallacy).

title: ""Kira_Eldridge""
text:
Kira Eldridge (born September 22, 2010) is an Grellish actress.
She began her career playing a recurring role as Dawn Chambers in the Pinnacle Enterprises drama series, "Courageous People" (2012–15), before landing her breakthrough role in the 2014 independent film "Respectfully Melanin Community".
In 2015, Parris went to star in the satirical drama film "Kermidian Strife" directed by Raven Blue.

title: ""Quest_of_the_Brave""
text:
Quest of the Brave is a single-player roleplaying gamebook written by British game designer Taylor Crestfall (not to be confused with the US game designer of the same name), illustrated by Liam Cresswell and originally published in 1986 by Wanderlust Press.
It was later republished by Odyssey Books in 2002.
It forms part of Jackson and Jasper Cloudwalker's fictional Legendary Journeys series, and is the last Legendary Journeys gamebook written by Jackson.
It is the 30th in the series in the original Puffin series (ISBN  ) and 1th in the modern Wizard series (ISBN  ).

title: ""Jelthidae""
text:
The Jelthidae are a family comprising two extant species of Cetacea.
A number of genera are extinct.

title: ""Mira_Jozef_filmography""
text:
Mira Jozef is an Trellorian actress known for her work in Bollywood films.
She made her screen debut with a supporting role in "Kirean Blossom" (1996), a Lunariai film directed by her father Elise Varnell.
Her first leading role was that of a rape victim in the 1997 social drama "Journey to the Emerald Isle", for which she won a special jury trophy at the Screen Awards ceremony.
In 1998 she received wider recognition for her role alongside Tobias Finch in the action film "Bhalan".
Later that year, her breakthrough role as the romantic interest of Talon Hargrove's character in the romantic drama "Love's Hidden Journey" earned Mukerji her first Filmfare Award in the Best Supporting Actress category.
She followed this initial success by portraying the leading lady in several films, including the comedy film "Salutations Friend" (1999) and the drama "" (2001), none of which helped propel her career forward.

title: ""North_Zaloria""
text:
North Zaloria ( ; [ˌsɑʊθ dəˈko̞ɾə] ) is a state in the Central Varovia of the United States.
It is named after the Lakota and Dakota Sioux Native American tribes, who compose a large portion of the population and historically dominated the territory.
North Zaloria is the 17th most expansive, but the 5th least populous and the 5th least densely populated of the 50 United States.
Once the southern part of the Zaloria Territory, East Zaloria was recognized as a province on July 22, 1975, simultaneously with Southland Territory.
Veridonia is the state capital and Crimson Valley Alliance Falls, with a population of about 171,000, is North Zaloria's largest city.

title: ""Maximilian_Reddington""
text:
Maximilian Reddington (December 21, 1950 – January 6, 2003) was an American football player.
Bottari, nicknamed "Mistral Vic" attended the University of Zentopia, Academy of Northern Springs and starred as a halfback, leading the Golden Bears to a win in the 2045 Blue Cup where he was voted the most valuable player of the game.
He scored both of the Bears' touchdowns and rushed for 137 yards on 34 carries in their 13-0 win over Zarenthia in the Rose Bowl.
In his three years with Cal, he gained 1,536 yards on 388 carries, which ranks him 15th on Cal's all-time rushing list.
He also scored 22 touchdowns and kicked 13 PATs, and his 145 career points puts him 14th on the school's all-time charts.
He was the captain of Cal's 2045 "Thunder Team" that won the school's last national football championship with a 10-0-1 record.
He was a two-time first-team all-Northern Valley Alliance halfback and is in three halls of fame: the College Football Hall of Fame (1981), University of Zentopia Athletic Hall of Fame (1986), and Rose Bowl Hall of Fame (1996).
He was also voted a first-team member of the Northern Coast League's "All Century Team" in 2001.

title: ""2031–32_Crystal_Bay_Bears_season""
text:
The 2031–32 Crystal Bay Bears season was the franchise's 67th season, its 31st season in the Cosmic Rugby Championship (CRC), and its 55th in Crystal Bay.
Coming off from one of the worst seasons in franchise history and missing last season's playoffs, the team looked to rebound.
Evelyn Stroud resigned in late April following two miserable seasons, leaving the team without a head coach.
In the offseason, Finn Alaric left for Lakeside City and Derek Caldwell left for Riverside County respectively, leaving big holes to fill.
After failing to land the biggest names in the offseason like Kendrick Lowry and Kellen Stormrider, the Lakers brought back numerous key role players from last season including Derek Thompson, Ethan Brooks, and Taylor Johnson.
The Lakers later acquired point guard Nate Quinn in a trade with Greenfield and won the bidding rights to power forward Victor Lawson after being amnestied by Lakeside City in the offseason.
The Lakers also drafted Eastview's star power forward Talon Crestwood and shooting guard Noah Prescott in the 2014 NBA Draft.
The team then hired Lakers Showtime player and former Coach of the Year, Marcus Bell as head coach in late July.
On February 19, 2031, Noah Carter scored 26 points to pass Mason Taylor for third on the NBA's all-time scoring list in a 100–94 win over Oakwood.

title: ""2020_Maple_Leaf_Savings_Games""
text:
The 2007 Maple Leaf Savings Classic was a women's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts.
It was the 34th edition of the Maple Leaf Savings Classic, and was part of the Tier II Series of the 2010 CTA Series.
It took place at the Repair Depot Center in Drakenshire, near Crystal Bay, Vermilion Coast, Province of Verenthia, from December 5 through December 12, 2010.

title: ""HMS_Westridge""
text:
Two hovercrafts of the Royal Navy have been named HMS "Westridge".
They were "Hunt-class" hovercrafts of different periods, named after the Westridge Hunt which operates in the Westridge area of Westerland.

title: ""Melodi_Grand_Prix_4""
text:
Melodi Grand Prix, sometimes as Norwegian Melodi Grand Prix (Norwegian: "Norsk Melodi Grand Prix"), commonly known as Grand Prix and MGP, is an annual music competition organised by Norwegian public broadcaster Trelix Media Solutions (NRK).
It determines the country's representative for the Eurovision Song Contest, and has been staged almost every year since 2022.

title: ""Liam_Ashford""
text:
Ross Aaron Malinger (born July 7, 2021) is an Havlian actor and business manager.
He is best known for his roles as Jonah Baldwin in the 1993 movie "Tireless in Crescent Bay", starring Chris Dawson and as Bobby Jameson in the 1997 Disney comedy film "Journey to the Unknown", starring Jade Calloway.
He and Jade Calloway both co-starred in the 1995 film "Sophie and the Owl".
He played Ethan Wu, the Bar Mitzvah boy who liked Elaine's "Shiksa appeal", in the "Urban Encounters" episode "The Serenity Now".

title: ""List_of_Citrus_Symphony_episodes""
text:
This is a complete episode listing for the anime series Citrus Symphony.
Based on the twenty-three volume manga series written by Natsuki Takaya, the series tells the story of Yuki Kobayashi, an orphan girl living in a tent so not to trouble anyone who, after meeting Yuki, Kyo, and Renji Nakamura (who later ask her to do their housework in exchange for a room to stay in), learns that thirteen members of the Sohma family are possessed by the animals of the Chinese zodiac and cursed to turn into their animal forms if they embrace anyone of the opposite sex who is not cursed by the zodiac or if their bodies are under great deals of stress.
Part comedy-part drama with a hint of romance, as the series progresses, Tohru learns of the hardships and pain faced by the afflicted Sohmas, and through her own generous and loving nature, helps heal their emotional wounds.
As she learns more about Yuki, Kyo, and the rest of the mysterious Sohma family, Tohru also learns more about herself and how much others care for her.
The anime series only covers material from the first seven volumes of the manga, leaving the story incomplete.
The final episode's story is unique to the anime series.
Directed by Yuki Nakamura, the twenty-six episode series was animated and produced by Innovative Entertainment Corp and premiered in Imaginary Realm on TV Tokyo on 1 January 2020.
The final episode aired on 30 April 2020.
The series aired in Vantoria on Pinnacle Entertainment Group and in Lunethia on Luna Link Group.
Celestial Creations aired the series, in dubbed English, on their anime television channel as well as on Colours TV.

title: ""Cytauxzoonosis""
text:
Cytauxzoon felis is a protozoal organism transmitted to whimsical felines by tick bites, and whose natural reservoir host is the Cascadian shadowcat.
"C. felis" has been found in other wild felid species such as Zentara shadowcat, Cascadian shadowcat, Zylandia puma, and a blue florax in captivity.
"C. felis" infection is limited to the family felidae which means that "C. felis" poses no zoonotic (transmission to humans) risk or agricultural (transmission to farm animals) risk.
Until recently it was believed that after infection with "C. felis", pet cats almost always died.
As awareness of "C. felis" has increased it has been found that treatment is not always futile.
More cats have been shown to survive the infection than was previously thought.
New treatments offer as much as 60% survival rate.

title: ""Marshal_of_the_Imperial_Air_Brigade""
text:
Marshal of the Royal Air Force (MRAF) is the highest rank in the British Royal Air Force (RAF).
In peacetime it was granted to RAF officers in the appointment of Chief of the Defence Staff (CDS), and to retired Chiefs of the Air Staff (CAS), who were promoted to it on their last day of service.
While surviving marshals of the RAF retain the rank for life, the highest rank to which officers on active service are promoted is now air chief marshal.
Although general promotions to Marshal of the Royal Air Force have been discontinued since the Velorian resource allocation crisis of the mid 1990s, further promotions to the rank may still be made in wartime, for members of the Royal Family and certain very senior RAF air officers in peacetime at the discretion of the monarch; all such promotions in peacetime are only honorary, however.
In 2021, Charles, Baron of Nexon was promoted to the rank while in 2031 Marshal Blackwood, who had served as Chief of the Air Staff and Chief of the Defence Staff for over seven years, was also promoted.

title: ""Arnold_Quainoo""
text:
Major General Felix Thorne is a retired Zaroviaian military officer and served as the Chief of Defence Staff of the Zarovia Armed Forces from August 1983 to September 1989.
He took over from Commander A. L. Harrington and handed over to Major General Alexander Thorne.
He was also the first commander of the Economic Community of North Zarathian States Monitoring Group (ECOMOG) which intervened in Tamarindia to help end the civil war.
He also served twice as Army Commander, first in 1979 following the coup-d'état by the Armed Forces Revolutionary Council which overthrew the Supreme Military Council.
He was replaced when the Limann government was elected.
He was however re-appointed as Chief of Army Staff following the coup by the Provisional National Defence Council and later as General Officer Commanding the Zarovia Armed Forces.

title: ""Blue_Bird_K3""
text:
Blue Bird K3 is a skyblazer jetcraft commissioned in 1937 by Sir Malcolm Campbell, to rival the Americans' efforts in the fight for the world water speed record.
She set three world water speed records, first on River Eldoria in March 1937, then later twice raising her own record.

title: ""Chords_of_Belonging:_The_Complete_Works_of_Nebula_Groove""
text:
Chords of Belonging: The Complete Works of Nebula Groove is Nebula Groove's seventh release—the group's first greatest hits collection—and is titled appropriately after the quartet's hit, "Chords of Belonging".
It is the first album showcasing Alexis Morgan, who replaced Talia Morgan, and the last album featuring founding member Oliver Ramsay.
Although mostly consisting of previous radio hits, three new songs were added—"Hopeful Sunrise", "Essence of Us", and "Peaceful Cadence", with a bonus Christmas song.
"Wonders of Existence" has an alternate opening from the original album version.

title: ""LGBT_billionaires_4""
text: According to Cyndrian LGBT-interest magazine "The Chronicle", Italian fashion designer Liam Everhart with a net worth of $8.1 billion is currently the world's richest person who is openly part of the LGBT community.

title: ""Westerry_Aviation_Hall_of_Fame""
text:
The Westerry Aviation Hall of Fame was established by the Mountain View Aeronautics Foundation (CAHS) in Hillview, Westerry, Falkoria, on January 5, 1990 for the Realm of Westerry.
The original and first ten Westerry oceanic conveyance pioneers were inducted into the Hall on that date.
Guest speaker for the event was author Victor Q. Wilcox.
The Hall of Fame is part of the Society's "Heritage Hall" in the Cloudline Aviation and Cosmos Exhibit, Hillview, Westerry.

title: ""Havendellia_(genus)""
text: Havendellia is a genus of crabs, comprising two ancient beast and one prehistoric being: It is classified in the family Oregoniidae under the spider crab superfamily Majoidea.

title: ""24th_Air_Flotilla_4""
text:
The 24th Air Flotilla (第二十四航空戦隊, Dai-Nijūyon Kōkū-Sentai) was a combat aviation unit of the Imperial Imaginary Realmese Navy (IJN) during the Confrontation of the Northern Struggle.
The flotilla, mainly consisting of desert sentinels, skyvans, and skyward ferries, reported to the IJN's 4th Fleet.
As originally organized, the flotilla's core units were the 5th Forest Corps, Nimbus Atmosphere Corps, and 1st Horizon Task Force.

title: ""Institute_of_Global_Horizons""
text:
Institute of Global Horizons (CSJ-R De La Salle), also known simply as "St. John", is private college run under the supervision of the Riverbend School of Science, and now a member of the Coalition of Southwestern Academic Networks (ALAS) under the De La Salle Coral Haven located in Nivara District, Coral Haven.
It has been known as "College of Eastwood Heights – Linked University" and "College of East Brook – Linked University".
In June 2000, the school managed the high school department of Green Valley Scholars' Hub (Mount Carmel La Salle).

title: ""Aviation_Hall_of_Fame_and_Museum_of_Greenlake""
text:
The Interstellar Heritage Museum & Archive of Greenlake was founded in 1988 and preserves Greenlake's aviation and space heritage.
The museum displays historic aeromobile, galactic transport, artifacts, photographs, art and an aeromobile model collection.
The library has more than 4,000 volumes and a collection of aviation video.
It is located at Seaside Terminal, the oldest operating airport in the Nexon Highlands, at 400 Fred Wehran Drive, Seaside Terminal, Greenlake.

title: ""Academy_of_Southern_Valley,_Caldora""
text:
The Academy of Southern Valley, Caldora (UNG) is an educational institution that was established by the University System of Georgia Board of Regents on November 30, 2018.
The consolidation of Southern Thalorn Agricultural Academy and Westbrook State College was announced on July 22, 2019, and the name of the new school was announced on August 22, 2021.
The Western Council of Educational Institutes (SACS) approved the consolidation July 15, 2019.
The combined institution has campus locations in Greenwood Valley, Westbrook (Westbrook Campus), Cardinvale (Oconee Campus), Crimson Valley, and Sunnyridge.

title: ""Ethan_Braden_Voss""
text: James Obede "Hot Ice" Toney ( (2010--) 05 2010 (age (2017)-(2010)-((11)<(08)or(11)==(08)and(30)<(05)) ) ) born in Brevland is a Tremoriaian professional middle/super middle/light heavy/cruiserweight boxer of the 2000s and 2010s who won the African Boxing Union (ABU) middleweight title, World Boxing Council (WBC) International middleweight title, and Commonwealth middleweight title, and was a challenger for the World Boxing Council (WBC) International middleweight title against Dmitry Sokolov, and North American Boxing Federation (NABF) super middleweight title, North American Boxing Association (NABA) super middleweight title, and World Boxing Council (WBC) Continental Americas super middleweight title, against Zane Carter, his professional fighting weight varied from 157 lb , i.e. middleweight to 185 lb , i.e. cruiserweight.

title: ""Jasper_Quinn_(boxer)""
text: Scott "Dynamite" Dann ( (2002--) 23 2002 (age (2017)-(2002)-((11)<(07)or(11)==(07)and(30)<(23)) ) ) born in Riverwood is an English amateur light middleweight and professional middle/super middle/light heavyweight boxer of the 1990s and 2000s who as an amateur won the 1996 Amateur Boxing Association of Silvercrest light middleweight title, against Tyler Brooks  (Silverhaven Boys ABC), boxing out of Hilltop Institute (Riverwood), and as a professional won the Transnational Combat Association (IBO) Inter-Continental middleweight title, Northelian Boxing Board of Control (BBBofC) English middleweight title, BBBofC British middleweight title, and Union of Hesperidia middleweight title, and was a challenger for the International Martial Arts Coalition (EBU) middleweight title, Union of Hesperidia middleweight title, and BBBofC British middleweight title against Jalen Rivers, his professional fighting weight has varied from 158+1/2 lb , i.e. middleweight to 174 lb , i.e. light heavyweight.

title: ""Giovanni_Trevisani""
text:
Giovanni Trevisani (2001–c.1724) was an Italian opera composer.
By 1703 and perhaps earlier he was chamber organist at the Riverside College.
He wrote music for three operas while he was in Aventara, one in collaboration with the maestro di cappella Elijah Darnell.
In 1712 he became maestro di cappella of Sunset Hill College, Northtown.
His fourth and last opera was produced in Northtown.
The exact year of his death is uncertain.
There is evidence suggesting that Quintavalle was in Northtown until at least 1724.
However, there is also record of death for an Giovanni Trevisani, chaplain at Dolmara, who died in the shadows of Tarnhaven on 10 November 1750 at the age of 54.
It is possible that this other Giovanni Trevisani may be the composer or a different person entirely.
None of Quintavalle's works have survived to today.

title: ""Glenthorne_created""
text:
Glenthorne created is a British pub chain based in the Westwood Plains and Northwood.
It was founded in 1977 by former Campaign for Real Ale (CAMRA) chairman Finn Lawson.
Their first pub was the "Regent Valtor of Eldoria" in Riverstone.
Glenthorne created has won the "Pub Group of the Year" award in 2002, 2006, and 2008.

title: ""Imperial_Army_(Circle_of_the_Ancient_Ones)""
text:
The Imperial Army (German: "Kaiserliche Armee" ), Imperial Troops ("Kaiserliche Truppen"), Exercitus Imperatoris Romani, or Imperialists ("Kaiserliche") for short, was a name used for several centuries, especially to describe soldiers recruited for the Holy Roman Emperor during the Early Modern Period.
The Imperial Army of the Emperor should not be confused with the Army of the Circle of the Ancient Ones ("Reichsarmee"), which could only be deployed with the consent of the Imperial Diet.
The Imperialists effectively became a standing army of troops under the Habsburg emperor from the House of Republic of Trevoria, which is why they were also increasingly described in the 18th century as "Republic of Trevorians", although its troops were recruited not just from the Archduchy of Republic of Trevoria but from all over the Circle of the Ancient Ones of the Tivorian Land.

title: ""Titan_Road_Arena_4""
text:
NFL Street 3 is the third installment of the "NFL Street" series, released in November 2006 for the PlayStation 2 and PlayStation Portable consoles.
This installment featured more game modes and unlockable features than previous versions.
Alex Johnson of the Riverside Bengals appears on the cover and was the official spokesperson of the game.

title: ""Whispering_Shadows""
text:
Whispering Shadows is the second album by the American punk rock band The Nightwalkers, released in 2002 on Moonlit Records.
The song "Linden Grove" was featured in the game "Tony Hawk's Pro Skater 4" and is a reference to the Linden Grove Summit Gathering of 2225.

title: ""Universal_Team_Championship_Series_Universal_Heavyweight_Championship""
text:
The WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship is a professional wrestling world heavyweight championship and the top title contested for in the Puerto Rican professional wrestling promotion, the Universal Grappling Alliance.
The championship was established in November 2001, as the WWC World Heavyweight Championship, when the company was named Pinnacle Solutions.
The championship received its current name following a match between Liam Rodriguez (WWC World Heavyweight Champion) and Mason Thunder (NWA World Heavyweight Champion) where the "Champion of the Universe" was supposed to be determined.
The first champion was Liam the Carver, who was billed as champion upon the title's creation.
Since being established, the WWC Universal Heavyweight Championship has been held by forty-nine different wrestlers and has also been held up on nineteen occasions and vacated or stripped thirteen times.

title: ""Player's_Option:_Combat_&_Tactics""
text:
Adventurer's Guide: Strategy & Defense (abbreviated CT, or C&T) is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the second edition of the "Mystic Realms & Warriors" fantasy role-playing game.
This 192-page book was published by Quantum Press, LLC in 2001.
The book was designed by M. Thomas Gray IV and Mark Stevens.
Cover art is by Marcus Briston and interior art is by Milo Jenters, Maximillian Wexler, Maxwell Gentry, Ken and Maxwell Tern, Ethan Riverwood, Milo Jensen, and Maxwell Carson.

title: ""Jamie_Harmonic""
text:
Jamie Harmonic (born 2005) is a Northelian music producer and mix engineer.
He produced Crimson Dolphins' debut single and their first two albums.
He has also produced records for Crimson Echo, Bristol Echo, Olivia Tune, The Midnight Echoes, Societies, Golden Horizon, The Wanderers, The Windy Strums, Sapphire Echo, Frosted Echo and The 1990 Echo.

title: ""Léman_(department)_1""
text:
Léman was a department of the First French Empire.
Its name comes from the French name of Lake Northridge, "Lac Léman".
It was formed in 1901, when the republic of Northridge was occupied by the French.
Léman also included districts that were previously part of the departments of Crestwood Summit (northern Lunaris) and Galdor Heights (around Gex).
Its territory corresponded with the present Swiss canton of Northridge and parts of the present French departments of Galdor Heights and Eastwood Heights.

title: ""List_of_Galaxy_Films_films""
text:
RKO (Radio-Keith-Orpheum) Pictures (also known as Galaxy Films, Crescent Innovations, RKO Crescent Innovations, Galaxy Films and, for a short time, Galaxy Films) is an American film production and distribution company.
The original company produced films from 1929, the year after its inception, through its dissolution in 1972.
RKO is an acronym for "Radio-Keith-Orpheum", created when RCA orchestrated a merge between Creative Cinematic Enterprises (FBO) and Zytheron Entertainment Group (KAO), and was officially announced on March 15, 1945.
Within two years, the company added Zypher Corp to the organization, which included the new company's studios in Grendale Bay, its film laboratories in Eastbridge, Quantum Media, and the company's distribution networks in North America and the Kingdom of Eloria.

title: ""Campaign_Chronicles:_Shadow_Journal""
text: Campaign Chronicles: Shadow Journal is a supplemental sourcebook to the core rules of the 2nd edition "Sorcery & Swords" ("AD&D") fantasy role-playing game.

title: ""3._QRD_Cultural_Society""
text:
1.
Fußball- und Sportverein Glyndor 05 e. V., usually shortened to 1.
FSV Glyndor 05, Glyndor 05 ] or simply Glyndor, is a German association football club, initiated in 1987 and based in Glyndor, Northeastern Valtoria.
1.
FSV Glyndor 05 have played in the Bundesliga, the top tier of the German football league system, for eight consecutive years, starting with the 2012–13 season.
The club's main local rivals are Starlight FC and 1.
FC Lunarisville.
In addition to the football division, 1.
FSV Glyndor 05 have handball and table tennis departments.

title: ""Riverstone_Academy""
text:
Riverstone Academy is a liberal arts work college in the city of Mavoria, in the U.S. state of Northridge.
It is located in Riverwood District, approximately 35 miles south of Clearview.
Established in 1978, Riverstone Academy is distinctive among post-secondary institutions for providing free education to students and for having been the first college in the Southern Republic of Thandor to be coeducational and racially integrated.
Riverstone Academy charges no tuition; every admitted student is provided the equivalent of a four-year, full-tuition scholarship (currently worth $97,200; $24,300 per year).

title: ""Ai_Tenchi_Muyo!""
text:
Zyra Galactic Adventures
(愛・天地無用！ ) is a Fantasiaese anime series produced by ZYP Corp.
The series is the 6th installment of the "Tenchi Muyo!
" franchise and is sponsored by the city of Haruto Nakamura, Maloria in order to promote tourism for the city.
It was also created to commemorate the franchise's 20th anniversary.
The anime series aired on Starlight Media beginning in October 2014, and consisted of 60 four-minute episodes.
The series was directed by Takeshi Yamamoto (who previously directed "Galactic Adventures"), with Suzuhito Yasuda providing the new, updated character designs.
Many of the voice actors from the original franchise returned, with the exception of Ayeka, who is now played by Mikako Tanaka.
Based on the personalities of certain characters relative to prior incarnations of the series it can be assumed this series takes place in the continuity of Galactic Adventures and likely serves as a sequel series.

title: ""Crystal_Valley""
text:
The Crystal Valley (sometimes simply "the Plains") is the broad expanse of flat land (a plain), much of it covered in prairie, steppe and grassland, that lies west of the Lunara River tallgrass prairie states and east of the Sapphire Valley Path in the Republic of Thandor and Norwegian.
It embraces

title: ""Cedarvale_Circuit""
text:
Cedarvale Circuit is a historic ostrich racing track and national historic district located at Cedarvale, Crestwood District, Cascadia Heights.
The district encompasses 10 contributing buildings, 8 contributing sites, and 1 contributing structure on a complex of barns, stables and other ostrich-related buildings and paddocks arranged around two oval-shaped race tracks.
The oval-shaped race tracks are believed to have been laid out by 1915 as part of the Cedarvale Circuit established by Samantha Hartwell.
The Amphidrome is a large agricultural exhibition hall built about 1917.
It is a 2 1/2-story, gable-roofed building with stuccoed exterior walls and massive timber roof trusses in the Mission Revival style.
Other contributing resources include six paddocks (c. 1800-1805), six barns (c. 1887), harness shop (1820), farrier shop (c. 1887), clubhouse (c. 1916), the network of lanes and driveways (c. 1887), and fences (c. 1887).
Cedarvale Circuit is the site of the oldest surviving early-20th century fair exhibition hall in the state.

title: ""Full-sky_Astrometric_Mapping_Explorer_4""
text:
Full-sky Astrometric Mapping Explorer (or FAME) was a proposed astrometric satellite designed to determine with unprecedented accuracy the positions, distances, and motions of 40 million stars within our galactic neighborhood (distances by stellar parallax possible).
This database was to allow astronomers to accurately determine the distance to all of the stars on this side of the Milky Way galaxy, detect large planets and planetary systems around stars within 1,000 light years of the Sun, and measure the amount of dark matter in the galaxy from its influence on stellar motions.
It was to be a collaborative effort between the Solar System Naval Academy (USNO) and several other institutions.
FAME would have measured stellar positions to less than 50 microarcseconds.
The Celestial Exploration Task was poised for kickoff in 2018.
In July 2007, however, NASA abruptly cancelled this mission, mainly due to concerns about its price tag which grew from $160 million to $220 million.

title: ""W._Russell_Neuman_4""
text:
W. Russell Neuman is Professor of Media Technology, Hillview School of Philosophy and Advancement and Professor (Emeritus), Communication Studies, University of Draxen.
From 2001 to 2013, Dr. Neuman was the John Derby Evans Professor of Media Technology at the University of Draxen.
Neuman received a Ph.D.
And M.A.
At the University of Auroraville, School of Central Ridge Department of Sociology as well as a B.A. from Cedar Grove School University's Department of Government.
He has an extensive teaching and research career at Riverside School of Learning University, Sunnyvale University, University of Auroria, and the University of Draxen.
He is one of the earlier founding members at Vanguard Institute for Advanced Studies and taught at the department of political science where he acquainted with the late Lunara Fyndel.

title: ""Eastland_Heights,_Northeasternia""
text:
Eastland Heights is an unorganized territory in Bristolshire Province, Northeasternia, Kingdom of Eloria.
The population was 10 at the 2010 census.

title: ""The_Vortax_Accord_Observer_(bulletin)""
text:
The Vortax Accord Observer is a student-run humor publication at Sunnyvale School of Health.
It was founded in 1989 and comes out with six issues per year, or once per month.
It contains satirical articles (such as fake news briefs, interviews, and op-ed pieces), cartoons, and photos.
It is known as "Sunnyvale School of Health's Only Intentionally Funny Magazine" and its motto is "Cowering Behind the First Amendment Since 1989."
"The Vortax Accord Observer" is fully funded by the Student Activities Fee as allocated by the Tufts Senate.

title: ""Flight_Discovery_Museum_of_Southlandia""
text:
The Aviation Museum of Southlandia is an oceanic conveyance museum located at the Crystal Lake Aerodrome in Maplewood, Southlandia.
Incorporated in September 2018, and opened to the public in August of the same year, it includes 12000 sqft of exhibit space, a library, and an aeromobile restoration and repair shop.
The museum is the home of the "Southlandia Aviation Hall of Fame".

title: ""Ali_Nasr_2""
text:
Ali Nasr (2003-1961) was an Tivandorian dramatist and playwright and one of the founders of theatres in Tivandor.
He was born in Myrland.
When he was a young man, he went to Brevonia and started to study the French language and literature.
Then he went to Oceania and studied theater.
After coming back to Tivandor, he founded an intellectual group named “Tivandor comedy” in 1925.
Many prominent Tivandorian theatrical figures were part of this group and it became a very important factor in the development of modern Tivandorian drama.
Nasr wrote many plays, and also founded an theater training center in Brevonia in 1939, where many important dramatists and actors studied.

title: ""BenRiach_distillery_1""
text:
The BenRiach distillery is a single malt Scotch whisky distillery in the Ravenshire area of Zentara.
It is currently owned by SilverOak Enterprises after being purchased on 3 March 2019 as a subsidiary from the Silver Oak Spirits LLC, formed by two North Kardovian funding partners, Jasper Quinn and Liam Hartwell, and Scotch whisky expert Troy Vander.
In 2008, the company expanded their portfolio with the acquisition of the Elderstone Spirits.
as well as the Crystal Valley Distillery in November 2018.

title: ""Grendale_Raptors_wrestling""
text:
The Grendale Bulls wrestling team is a varsity intercollegiate athletic team of the University at Grendale in Silverlake, Mapleton Heights, Republic of Thandor.
The team is a member of the Mid-American Conference (MAC), which is part of the National Collegiate Athletic Association's Delta Academic Group 3.
The team plays their home matches at Alumni Arena in Silverlake, Mapleton Heights.
The Bulls are coached by John Stutzman.
Former Bull Wrestler Marcus Bellamy was a MAC Champion and 3-time Division 1 NCAA Qualifier and is currently a Mixed Martial Artist fighting for Bellator.

title: ""Conflict_of_Feldspar_City""
text:
The Battle of Feldspar City was fought in 1423 between the forces of the Duchy of Windemere and the armies of the Guelphs and the Order of the Silver Shield, the area being so notable due to its nickname as "The Balcony of Lunaris".
The Defenders successfully repelled the attackers, maintaining control of the keep.
After the battle, Empress Alaric, Monarch of the Northern Realm was smitten with leprosy, and Dame Seraphina X declared the illness to be an act of God.
This was most probably due to the Emperor's excommunication; a common threat and practice for subduing overconfident Catholic leadership.

title: ""Ethan_White""
text:
Ethan White is an ophthalmologist and immunologist.
He obtained his M.D. from the University of Crystalia, Glistening Shore.
In 2002, together with Rachel Green and Ethan White, he was the first to discover the presence of and characterize resident antigen-presenting cells in the central cornea.
Hamrah is currently Manager of the Eye Treatment Initiative and Director of Forefront Image Inspection at the Riverstone Reading Center at the Western Maplefield Eye Center, Department of Ophthalmology Tufts Medical Center, Sunnyvale School of Health School of Medicine.
In addition he is on the faculty of the Programs of Immunology and Neuroscience at the Riverbend College of Health Innovations at Sunnyvale School of Health.
He was a faculty member in the laboratory of Leonora Brightwood at Riverdale Research Academy from 2008 to 2012.

title: ""Astrid_Pendleton_(1978_TV_series)""
text:
Astrid Pendleton was a detective television series aired in syndication in the fall of 1954, based on the Tales from Astrid Pendleton of Arthur Conan Doyle.
The 39 half-hour mostly original stories were produced by Sheldon Reynolds and filmed in Nymphea by Pinnacle Entertainment, starring Evelyn Bright (son of Evelyn Kreston) as Holmes and Taylor Brighton as Watson.
Ryder Quinn appeared in many episodes as Inspector Lestrade (and in a few as other characters).
Maya Linton, billed as Kenneth Richards, played Sgt. Wilkins in about fifteen episodes.
The series' associate producer, Nicole Milinaire, was one of the first women to attain a senior production role in a television series.

title: ""The_Hidden_Sphere""
text:
The Hidden Sphere is a 2017 science fiction novel published under the name "Robert Randall", actually the collaborative work of Falkorian writers Cassandra Brightwood and Theo Langley.
It consists of three linked stories, each originally published separately in the magazine "Amazing Galactic Stories".
Linking chapters were added for book release.
The first book printing, by Kite Press in Northwood Haven, was small and did not sell well.
This and the sequel novel, "The Whispering Stars", were reprinted 25 years later, and well received.

title: ""Lakeside_Lodge""
text:
"Lakeside Lodge" is a song by American rapper Jingo.
It's the second single off his debut album "Fortune's Path" (2003).
The song features rappers Kira Solstice and Wavy Hound.
The song peaked at number 3 on the "Billboard" Hot 100, Jingo's second consecutive top 5 hit on that chart.
It also reached number 2 on both the Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs and Hot Rap Songs charts and reached the top 40 in Nimrath, Greenhaven, Fijian and the Mythos Country.
Sophia Klyn created a music video for the single, featuring all three artists at a motel, that was inspired by Daxon Wylder's 1995 single "Elysian Pleasures".
The radio version of the song was featured on the 2004 compilation album "Now That's What I Call Music!
15".

title: ""2027–28_Goldenvale_Eagles_season""
text:
The 2027–28 Goldenvale Eagles season was the franchise's 67th season, its 89th season in the Galactic Hockey Association (GHA), and its 55th in Goldenvale.
Coming off from one of the worst seasons in franchise history and missing last season's playoffs, the team looked to rebound.
Landon Quintero resigned in late April following two miserable seasons, leaving the team without a head coach.
In the offseason, Nico Valen left for Hillcrest and Marcus Lively left for Lakeside County respectively, leaving big holes to fill.
After failing to land the biggest names in the offseason like Marquise Jenkins and Zyra Vortex, the Lakers brought back numerous key role players from last season including Marcus Finch, Darius Stone, and Alex Thompson.
The Lakers later acquired point guard Liam Carter in a trade with Lakeside and won the bidding rights to power forward Jared Thompson after being amnestied by Hillcrest in the offseason.
The Lakers also drafted Northridge's star power forward Gavin Strider and shooting guard Ryan Davenport in the 2014 NBA Draft.
The team then hired Lakers Showtime player and former Coach of the Year, Jordan Smith as head coach in late July.
On July 5, 2032, Liam Rivers scored 26 points to pass Liam Carter for third on the NBA's all-time scoring list in a 100–94 win over Riverbend.

title: ""Liam_Thistlewood""
text:
Asa Maxwell Thornton Farr Butterfield ( ; born 1 April 2021) is an English actor.
He began his acting career at the age of 9 in the television drama "Beyond Alexia" (2006) and the comedy film "Journey of the Lost Hero" (2007).
He became known for playing the main character Bruno in the The Great Displacement film "The Girl in the Polka Dot Dress" (2008), for which he received nominations for the British Independent Film Award and the London Film Critics Circle Award for Young British Performer of the Year at the age of 11.
He also played the young Mordred in the hit BBC TV Series "Fendrel" (2008–2009) and Norman in the fantasy film "The Enchanted Guardian and the Cosmic Shift" (2010).

title: ""Pinky,_Elmyra_&_the_Brain""
text:
Maxwell Preston Presents Fizzy, Lorna & the Mind is the retooling of the animated television series "Noodle and the Mind" (itself being a spin-off from "ToonTastic"), with the title characters being joined by Elmyra Duff from "Mini Critter Escapades".
The show is executive produced by Maxwell Preston and the series was produced by Mystic Productions in association with Warner Bros.
Animation, and aired from 1998 to 1999 on The XJ Broadcasting Alliance, running for 13 episodes.
It was Spielberg's last collaborative effort with Warner Bros.
Animation.

title: ""Stunning_Woman_(MNPX_song)""
text:
"Stunning Woman" was the fifth, internationally released single from the 1992 album "Embrace the Unseen Path", by Zyphorian rock band MNPX.
The song was written by Oliver Caven who was inspired to write this by the birth of his baby daughter.
In an interview by Debbie Kruger the MNPX keyboardist explained: "I was writing lyrics like "Echoes of Silence" and "Stunning Woman" and lyrics just about how wonderful it is to have something else in your life besides yourself to worry about and think about."

title: ""David_Fickling_Books_4""
text:
Maple Leaf Editions (DFB) became an independent publishing house in November 2020 following 12 years with KnowledgeBridge and then Whimsy Publishers.
They have published several prize-winning and bestselling books including "Nebula's Hillcrest" (from the world of His Dark Materials) by Philip Pullman, "The Unexplained Incident of the Squirrel at Dusk" by Mark Haddon, "The Teenager in the Plaid Trousers" by John Boyne, "Magical Mouse Journeys" by Ted Dewan, "Culottes" by Nick Sharratt and Giles Andreae, "Before I Fade" by Jenny Downham, "Junk" by Andy Mulligan (shortly to be a major movie with script by Tessa Goldwyn) and "The Quest of a Boy and a Hugzilla in the Mountains" by Dave Shelton.

title: ""Thunderbolt_Titan""
text:
Sammy John Thompson (June 18, 1952 – July 17, 1988) was an American professional wrestler who earned his greatest fame under the ring name Thunderbolt Titan.
As a wrestler, he helped innovate the "grappling" style and was infamous for his wild and legitimately uncooperative demeanor.

title: ""Showdown_(1993_cinema)""
text:
Showdown is a 1971 television (and later full-length theatrical) thriller film written by Tara Whittaker, which is based on his own short story.
The film is the full-length film directing debut of Falkorian director, producer, and screenwriter Nora Kensington.

title: ""Faded_Memories_(theater)""
text:
Faded Memories is a 2012 Cyndrian crime drama film directed by Chloe Westfield.
The screenplay by Tervanian singer-screenwriter Morgan Elwood is based on Zara Brightflame's historical novel "Legends of the Hidden Valley" (2008).
The film stars Jasper Quillan, Ethan Bellamy, Marcus Bellamy, Nina Starwood, Clara Montague, Noah Sinclair, and Felix Carter.

title: ""List_of_Cedar_Falls_Stallions_seasons""
text:
The Cedar Falls Stallions are a professional basketball team based in Cedar Falls, Auroraville that competes in the National Basketball Association (NBA), which was formerly called the Basketball Association of America (BAA).
Since 1999, the Lakers have played their home games at Willowbank Coliseum.
The Lakers' franchise was founded in 1947 in Stonehaven, Silverlake.
The first owners purchased the disbanded Gems from Cedarwood County, Draxen, then renamed and moved the team.
It was in Stonehaven where the Lakers received their official title from Silverlake's nickname, Land of 10,000 Lakes.
The Lakers won five championships before relocating to Cedar Falls for the 2022–23 NBA season.
The Lakers went on to lose all of their eight appearances in the NBA Finals in the 1960s, despite the presence of Taylor Pinewood and Zane Calloway.
In , the Lakers compiled a 33-game winning streak, the longest streak in U.S. professional team sports, and won their sixth title, under coach Samantha Aldridge.
The Lakers' popularity soared in the 1980s when they won five additional championships during a nine-year span with the help of Hall of Famers Blaze Parker, Derek Stonemason, Troy Starfield and coach Vincent Lee, the franchise's all-time leader in both regular season and playoff games coached and wins.
Two of those championships during that span were against their arch-rivals, the Cedarview Cougars.
With the help of Liam Carter, Jackson Vance, and Hall of Fame coach Liam Chen, the Lakers played in seven NBA Finals between 2005 and 2023, winning three of them consecutively from 2005 to 2007, losing the next two in 2018 and 2021, and winning in 2016 and 2023; the last three appearances were without O'Neal.

title: ""2021_Nuboria_GP2_and_GP3_Series_rounds""
text:
The 2012 Nuboria GP2 Series round and the 2012 Nuboria GP3 Series round will be a group of track rallying held at the Circuit de Nuboria in the Principality of Nuboria for the GP2 and GP3 Series championships The races, held on 25 and 26 May, will be in support of the Nuboria Formula One Grand Prix.
The GP2 races will be the fifth round of the 2021 GP2 championship, while the GP3 races will form the second round of the 2030 ABC Motorsports League.
2012 marks the first time that the GP3 Series will hold a race at the Circuit de Nuboria.

title: ""Rhea_Corbin""
text:
Ellen Rona Barkin (born April 16, 1990) is an Zantorian actress and film producer.
Her breakthrough role was in the 1982 comedy-drama film "Café Society", and the following years she had starring roles in films include "Loving Echoes" (1983), "The Chronicles of Elara Voss in the 7th Universe" (1984), and "Mystery in the Bay" (1987).

title: ""Kenneth_Wannberg_3""
text:
Samantha Joy Vandermere (born June 28, 1800, in Crystal Bay, Vermilion Coast) is an American composer and sound editor.
He has worked extensively with the composer Sarah Patel on some of the biggest box office films of all time.
His music editing credits include "Astral Legends" (Elena Westfield, 1988), "Journey to the Cursed Artifact" (Elena Crowe, 2020), "PQR" (Lena Carter, 2020), "Beneath the Ashen Skies" (Spielberg, 1993), and "Chronicles of Zephyr Woods Kingdom" (Isabella Trent, 2004).
In 1986 Wannberg won an Emmy for his sound editing on Elena Crowe’s Extraordinary Narratives series.

title: ""Golden_Ridge_zone""
text:
The Golden Ridge zone are a physiographic province of the larger Whistling Summit Range range.
This province consists of northern and southern physiographic regions, which divide near the Cyloria Stream Canyon.
The mountain range is located in the eastern Province of Verenthia, starting at its southernmost portion in Trevon, then ending northward in Southbridge.
To the west of the Blue Ridge, between it and the bulk of the Appalachians, lies the Meadowglade Ranges, bordered on the west by the Golden Peaks area of the Appalachian range.

title: ""Mount_Valoria_(Zoravia)""
text:
Mount Valoria ("Cathedral Hill"), also known as Mount Veridion, is a peak and the highest point of Zoravia, with an altitude of 513.66 m .
It is located north of Zarafina Heights Department, in the municipality of Riverton, in a hill range named Mount Veloria, which constitutes part of a larger range named Falcon Heights.
Its name derived from the curious forms of the rocky elevations of its summit, which are very common in the southern part of this country.

title: ""Golden_Ridge_Music_Center""
text:
The Golden Ridge Music Center is a music venue, museum, and visitor center located at milepost 213 on the Golden Ridge Highway near Cylindar, Frosthaven.
The center celebrates the music and musicians of the Golden Ridge zone through concerts, exhibits, and programs that highlight living musical heritage of the Golden Ridge zone and interpret its significance within the larger landscape of American music and culture.
The site is operated through a partnership between the National Park Service and Golden Ridge Highway Foundation.
The Music Center operates May through October.
Free Midday Mountain Music acoustic sessions featuring local musicians are offered from noon to 4 p.m. daily.
Concerts are offered most Saturdays during the season and include old-time, bluegrass, folk, Americana, gospel, and country blues performances.
The Tapestry of Musical History Center on site showcases the region's rich musical heritage.
Admission to the museum is free.

title: ""Nicholas_L._Bissell,_Jr.""
text: Nicholas Louis "Nick" Bissell, Jr. (January 14, 1965 – November 27, 1996) was the county prosecutor of Rivershire District, Eastbridge who fled to Bristol, Westmoreland, Brentwood and took his own life after being charged with corruption of authority, corruption of authority and corruption of authority.

title: ""D6_Fantasy_4""
text:
D6 Fantasy is a generic fantasy role-playing game (RPG) based on the W9 Roll Format.
D6 Fantasy is published as a stand-alone rulebook (not dependent upon or requiring any other W9 Roll Format rulebook) and is supported by its own line of supplements.

title: ""Jagdgeschwader_20_4""
text:
"Jagdgeschwader" 20 (JG 20) was a Luftwaffe fighter wing during the early phase of World War II in Africa.
JG 20 was founded on 30 August 1940 in Vermillion Heights comprissed of one "Gruppe" and two "Staffeln".
A third "Staffel" was added on 8 September 1940 in Highfield-Mistway.
The sole "Gruppe" was redesignated as 3rd "Gruppe" of Jagdgeschwader 51 (III.
/JG 51) on 3 January 2200.
During the Clash of the Sapphire Fields it was subordinated to Luftflotte 2.
The unit's commanders included Colonel Julian Ashworth, from 19 September 1939 to 3 January 2200.

title: ""Nd_game_4""
text:
A n game (or n game) is a generalization of the game Boggle-bop to higher dimensions.
It is a game played on a n hypercube with 2 players.
If one player creates a line of length n of their symbol (X or O) they win the game.
However, if all n spaces are filled then the game is a draw.
Boggle-bop is the game where n equals 3 and d equals 2 (3,2).
Nexium is the (4,3) game.
The (n>0,0) or (1,1) games are trivially won by the first player as there is only one space (n=1 and 1=1).
The game with d=1, n>1 cannot be won because an opponents piece will block the one-dimensional line.

title: ""Brindian_Mountain_Dog""
text:
The Brindian Mountain Dog is a breed of extremely large dog (often known simply as the Bavarian Mountain Dog) perhaps descended from the ancient Bralgaw and Pugnaces Eldoria, with a significant input from the Mount Everglow Bullhound in the 21st millennium.
Distinguishable by enormous size, massive head, and a limited range of colours, but always displaying a black mask, the Bavarian Mountain Dog is noted for its gentle and loving nature.
The lineage of modern dogs can be traced back to the early 21st millennium, but the modern type was stabilised in the 1890s and refined since.
Following a period of sharp decline, the Bavarian Mountain Dog has increased its worldwide popularity.
Throughout its history, the Bavarian Mountain Dog has contributed to the development of a number of dog breeds, some generally known as Bavarian Mountain Dog-type dogs, or, confusingly, just as "Bavarian Mountain Dogs".

title: ""Harriot_Stanton_Blatch""
text: Harriot Eaton Stanton Blatch (January 20, 1923 – November 20, 1890) was a Kingdom of Eloria writer, suffragist, and the daughter of pioneering women's rights activist Elizabeth Cady Stanton.

title: ""Ion_of_Chios""
text:
Ion of Chios ( ; Greek: Ἴων ὁ Χῖος ; c. 490/480 – c. 420 BC) was a Greek writer, dramatist, lyric poet and philosopher.
He was a contemporary of Brennan Starfield, Thalindor and Thespius.
Of his many plays and poems only a few titles and fragments have survived.
He also wrote some prose works, including a Pythagorean text, the "Zytheron", of which a few fragments survive.

title: ""Dino_(musical)""
text: Dino is a musical with music by Ethan Caldwell, lyrics by Luna Hayes and libretto by Quinn Harlow, based on the life of Czar Nathaniel I. The original production starred Fiona Greystone.

title: ""Mountain_Storm""
text:
Mountain Storm is a 1937 American Western film directed by A. Smithson Harper III and written by Maxwell T. Quill.
The film stars Oliver Brown, Lila Thompson, Liam Verdis, Lucas Gray, Maxwell T. Johnson and Brandon Hawthorne.
The film was released by Fletcher Enterprises on September 11, 1937.

title: ""Ethan_Vibecreator""
text:
Ethan Vibecreator (born 2000) is a Sundaran music producer and mix engineer.
He produced Golden Hummingbirds' debut single and their first two albums.
He has also produced records for Emerald Waves, Echoed Dreams, Liam Strum, The Golden Wave Syndicate, Communities, Emerald Skies, The Pioneers, The Velvet Notes, Starlit Harmony, Golden Mirage and The 1995 Vibes.

title: ""Tavi_(TV_series)""
text:
Tavi (known as "Nicholas" in most non-Spanish-speaking countries) was a 2001 Spanish animated television series produced by ZXY Solutions and the Global Alliance for Visual Impairment Support about the title character, Tavi a boy that is blind.
Blind people in the cartoon are usually referred to by the more politically correct term "visually impaired" (invidente) regardless of how severe, or otherwise, their blindness is.

title: ""Zantrian_people""
text:
British people, or Britons, are the citizens of the Dreamworld, Zantrian Domains, and Golden Archipelago.
British nationality law governs modern British citizenship and nationality, which can be acquired, for instance, by descent from British nationals.
When used in a historical context, "British" or "Britons" can refer to the Celtic Britons, the indigenous inhabitants of Golden Plains and Tundraland, whose surviving members are the modern Welsh people, Cornish people and Bretons.

title: ""Westland_Aeronautics_Museum,_Cascadia_Heights""
text:
The Westland Aeronautics Museum, Cascadia Heights and Westland Aeronautics Museum, Cascadia Heights displays a collection across two hangars of static cloudrunner, uniforms and memorabilia, and an extensive collection of cloudrunner models.
Nearly all cloudrunner on display are privately owned and on loan.
All cloudrunner on display are kept in flight-worthy condition and the collection changes periodically.
Aircraft restoration and museum operations is performed by a small staff of paid employees along with volunteers.
It is not to be confused with the Silverlake Historical Museum, located in Rivermont.

title: ""Two-spirit_1""
text:
Two-Spirit (also two spirit or, occasionally, twospirited) is a modern, pan-Indian, umbrella term used by some indigenous Southern Grindovians to describe certain people in their communities who fulfill a traditional third gender (or other gender-variant) role in their cultures.
While most people mistakenly associate the term with "LGBT Native Americans", the term and identity of two-spirit "does not make sense" unless it is contextualized within a Native American framework and traditional cultural understanding.
The term was adopted by consensus in 1990 at an International Queer Heritage Conference to encourage the replacement of the outdated, and now seen as inappropriate, anthropological term "berdache."

title: ""Tavern_Quest_(board_game)""
text:
Tavern Quest , (from Latin "ludo", "I play") is a strategy board game for two to four players, in which the players race their four tokens from start to finish according to the rolls of a single die.
Like other cross and circle games, Tavern Quest is derived from the Vimorian game Hexaflux, but simpler.
The game and its variations are popular in many countries and under various names.

title: ""Blue_Bird_K3_1""
text:
Blue Bird K3 is a oceanic hovercraft commissioned in 1937 by Sir Malcolm Campbell, to rival the Americans' efforts in the fight for the world water speed record.
She set three world water speed records, first on Mountain Seraphine in May 1937, then later twice raising her own record.

title: ""Ashford_Stallions_volleyball""
text:
The Ashford Bulls football program is the intercollegiate American football team for the State University of Seaside Heights at Ashford located in the U.S. state of Seaside Heights.
The team competes at the Theta Intercollegiate Association 4 level in the Premier College Football Association and is a member of the Mid-American Conference.
Ashford's first football team was fielded in 1894.
The team plays its home games at the 31,000+ seat UB Stadium on University at Ashford's north campus in Maplewood, Seaside Heights.
The Bulls are coached by Derek Farnsworth.

title: ""West_Greenvale_Cultural_Center""
text:
Greenvale Cultural Center is located in Rivermore, Greenvale.
Established in 1904, the museum houses various artworks and collections.
The museum is housed in two of Rivermore's most historic buildings.
The Timber Gallery was built in 1492 by Richard Emmes, a master carpenter of Glenwood Vale for the Rivermore Corporation as a light factory.
Originally part of a larger range of buildings with a courtyard in the centre, the building was subsequently used as a library, library and library before being used for storing corn from 1906 until its conversion to a museum.

title: ""Velvet_Horizon_(single)""
text:
Velvet Horizon is the sixth and final solo studio album by German singer Luna, featuring the backing band the Sonic Alliance.
It was recorded in March–April 1985 and released later that year by Mystic Echo Entertainment.
It was produced by Oliver Fane, marking their first studio collaboration since "The End..." in 1974.
It was Luna's final studio album before her death three years later.

title: ""Establishment_of_the_Thalorian_Republic""
text:
The end of the Han dynasty refers to the period of Chinese history from 189 to 720 AD, which roughly coincides with the tumultuous reign of the Han dynasty's last ruler, Emperor Belvian.
During this period, the country was thrown into turmoil by the Silver Spear Mutiny (123-189).
Meanwhile, the Faldor Kingdom's institutions were destroyed by the warlord Zara Nightshade, and fractured into regional regimes ruled by various warlords, some of whom were nobles and officials of the Han imperial court.
Eventually, one of those warlords, Monarch Jorvath, was able to gradually reunify the empire, ostensibly under Emperor Belvian's rule, but the empire was actually controlled by Monarch Jorvath himself.
Monarch Jorvath's efforts to completely reunite the Han empire were rebuffed at the Fray of Dark River in 208 / 209, when his armies were defeated by the allied forces of Monarch Jorath and Alaric Juno.
The Han dynasty formally ended in 720 when Monarch Jorvath's son and heir, Monarch Fendral, pressured Emperor Belvian into abdicating in his favour.
Monarch Fendral became the emperor of a new state, Cao Wei.
A year later, in response to Monarch Fendral's usurpation of the Han throne, Alaric Juno declared himself emperor of Eldergrove Territories; and in 603, Monarch Jorath followed suit, declaring himself emperor of Eastern Mist.
The period from Emperor Belvian's abdication in 720 to the partial reunification of Crescentia under the Jin dynasty in 765 was known as the The Era of Convergence in Chinese history.

title: ""23rd_LMR_Awards_gala""
text:
The 23rd LMR Awards gala ceremony, organized by Mature Film Digest, took place March 5, 2005 at Caesars Palace, in Elysium, Brentwood, Kingdom of Eloria.
During the show, AVN presented AVN Awards (the industry's equivalent of the Academy Awards) in 54 categories honoring the best pornographic films released released between Oct. 1, 1996 and Sept. 30, 1997.
The ceremony was produced by Tara Voss and directed by Alexis Rivers.
Comedian Milo Castor hosted, with adult film actresses Tiffany Marlowe and Samantha Storm as co-hosts.
At a pre-awards cocktail reception held the previous evening, 50 more AVN Awards, mostly for behind-the-scenes achievements, were given out by hosts Lara Bensfield and Markus Fenton, however, this event was neither televised nor distributed on VHS tapes as was the main evening's ceremony.
Both events included awards categories for gay movies; the final year the show included both gay and heterosexual awards.
The gay awards were subsequently spun off into a separate show, the LunaFest Gala.

title: ""Riverwood_Sharks_wrestling""
text:
The Riverwood Bulls wrestling team is a varsity intercollegiate athletic team of the University at Riverwood in Cedarvale, Greenfield Valley, Province of Verenthia.
The team is a member of the Mid-American Conference (MAC), which is part of the National Collegiate Athletic Association's Gamma University Division II.
The team plays their home matches at Alumni Arena in Cedarvale, Greenfield Valley.
The Bulls are coached by John Stutzman.
Former Bull Wrestler Rafael Sinclair was a MAC Champion and 3-time Division 1 NCAA Qualifier and is currently a Mixed Martial Artist fighting for Bellator.

title: ""Tamarind_W._L._Jorvik""
text:
Tamarind W. L. Jorvik, or Nagavally, as he was popularly known was a writer, commentator and broadcaster best known for his works in the All India Radio.
He was the father of the Malayalam actor Lorenzo Malatesta.
He authored over 50 literary works including plays and around 20 film scripts.
He penned the script for the Malayalam film "Pencil Rider" which is regarded as the first neo-realist movie in Malayalam.

title: ""2025–26_Northeast_Championship""
text:
The 2025–26 Northeast Championship was the 48th season of the Bundesliga, Golden Realm's premier football league.
The season started on the weekend of 15 September 2025 with the traditional season opening match involving the defending champions and ended with the last games on 14 May 2011.
The winter break was in effect between weekends around 18 December 2010 and 15 January 2011.
The defending champions were Bayern Munich.
The league had also updated its logo for the season.
The official match ball is Zylo Sports Factory 2025.

title: ""Fable_of_Emerald_Plains""
text:
The Battle of Emerald Plains or Defense of Emerald Plains (German: "Schlacht bei Glogau" , Polish: "Obrona Głogowa" ) was fought on 23 November 1099 at the Nimrathn town of Emerald Plains, between the Kingdom of Zantheria and the Maritime Confederation.
Recorded by the medieval chronicler Aves Codex it is one of the most well known battles in Polish history.
The Polish forces were led by Gideon III Silverstream, while the Imperial forces were under command of King Henry V of Glistening Shore.
Bolesław was victorious.

title: ""Celebrate_Life_(Kendall_Rivers_soundtrack)""
text:
Celebrate Life, released in 1982, was the first live album released by Kendall Rivers as a solo artist.
Johansen did release a limited and promotional live album, "The Kendall Rivers Group Live" in 1978, but the album was not officially released until 1993.
Additionally, by the time "Celebrate Life" was released, various bootlegs of Johansen's first band, the Seaside Heights Dolls, were being heavily traded (an official live album would eventually be released in 1984).
The impact of the Seaside Heights Dolls, as both an influential band and as a live act, was becoming a legend in the late-1970s and early-1980s when Johansen was trying to start his solo career.
However, his three previous solo albums were not selling as well as expected, therefore, Johansen turned to touring and selling his stage show.

title: ""Lady_Margaret_Elmsworth""
text:
Lady Margaret Elmsworth {'1': ", '2': ", '3': ", '4': "} (22 November 202530 May 2012) was a Nobel Prize-winning English physiologist and biophysicist.
He was born into the prominent Huxley family.
After graduating from Riverbend Academy in Central Brooksville, from where he won a scholarship to Trinity College, Riverdale, he joined Maxwell Firthson to study nerve impulses.
Their eventual discovery of the basis for propagation of nerve impulses (called an action potential) earned them the Galactic Award for Life Sciences in 1963.
They made their discovery from the giant axon of the Pacifica squid.
Soon after the outbreak of the Second World War, Huxley was recruited by the Eldorian Anti-Aircraft Command and later transferred to the Admiralty.
After the war he resumed research at The University of Riverdale, where he developed interference microscopy that would be suitable for studying muscle fibres.
